Name: Lugworm
Description: A hairy marine worm that lives under beach sand. Live bait for ocean fishing.

Name: Moth Pupa
Description: A moth in the third stage of its development into an adult. Live bait for freshwater fishing.

Name: Pill Bug
Description: A small insect covered in a grey protective carapace. Is known to curl up in a ball when agitated. Live bait for ocean fishing.

Name: Crayfish Ball
Description: A ball of crayfish and rye flour paste. Processed bait for freshwater fishing.

Name: Goby Ball
Description: A ball of goby and rye flour paste. Processed bait for ocean fishing.

Name: Bloodworm
Description: A common earthworm that earns its name from the blood red tint of its body. Live bait for freshwater fishing.

Name: Rat Tail
Description: The thin tail of a rat, often carried by young Lalafellin boys as a good-luck charm. Bait for ocean fishing.

Name: Midge Basket
Description: A tightly knitted wicker basket filled with a swarm of biting midges. Live bait for freshwater fishing.

Name: Crab Ball
Description: A ball of crabmeat and rye flour paste. Processed bait for ocean fishing.

Name: Butterworm
Description: If allowed to pupate, this bright-yellow larva will transform into a hideous moth which can devour an entire tunic in a single turn of the sun. Live bait for freshwater fishing.

Name: Bass Ball
Description: A ball of dark bass and sunset flour paste. Processed bait for freshwater fishing.

Name: Spoon Worm
Description: Also colorfully known as a fisherman's member, the stench of this sea-dwelling creature when sliced up is perfect for attracting hungry fish. Live bait for ocean fishing.

Name: Syrphid Basket
Description: A tightly knitted wicker basket filled with a swarm of angry syrphids. Live bait for freshwater fishing.

Name: Herring Ball
Description: A ball of Indigo herring and sunset flour paste. Processed bait for ocean fishing.

Name: Honey Worm
Description: The honeyfly will lay its eggs in beehives where, upon hatching, the larvae will feed on honey until pupation. Live bait for freshwater fishing.

Name: Sand Leech
Description: A spineless creature which hides patiently under the desertofttimes for several moonsuntil a larger beast passes nearby. The leech will then attach itself to the new host's leg and proceed to drink deep of the beast's blood until its belly is full, after which it releases itself back to the desert to wait for its next victim. Live bait for dunefishing.

Name: Stem Borer
Description: This longhorn beetle larva can most commonly be found burrowed deep into the trunks of fallen logs. Live bait for freshwater fishing.

Name: Sand Gecko
Description: When night falls, thousands of these tiny scalekin can be seen scampering about the Sagolii Desert in search of the beetles on which they dine. Live bait for dunefishing.

Name: Glowworm
Description: It is not known why one end of these vilekin shines bright like a candle. It is, however, known that the light emitted by these creatures makes them a perfect target for hungry fish. Live bait for freshwater and ocean fishing.

Name: Rolling Stone
Description: When threatened, this tiny desert crustacean will curl itself into a ball which, to the untrained eye, will appear no more than a simple pebble. Live bait for dunefishing.

Name: Hoverworm
Description: Unlike other vilekin larvae, the hoverworm is not confined to life on the ground. Filling its belly with air allows it to freely ride the thermals over the Sea of Clouds. Live bait for skyfishing.

Name: Northern Krill
Description: Microscopic shrimp which inhabit the colder sea currents hailing from the northern seas. Live bait for ocean fishing.

Name: Caddisfly Larva
Description: The fact they are extremely difficult to harvest from their underwater homes makes fishing with caddisfly larvae an option for only the most well-to-do anglers. Live bait for freshwater fishing.

Name: Soil Creeper
Description: Atypical of common caterpillars, this sand-dwelling species is covered in a rock-like outer skin which serves to prevent the loss of moisture to the hot desert sun. Live bait for dunefishing.

Name: Balloon Bug
Description: With wings too underdeveloped for flying, this beetle has adopted another method of locomotion about the Sea of Cloudsa second bladder it fills with a noxious lighter-than-air gas. This foul stench is known to attract larger, hungrier creatures. Live bait for skyfishing.

Name: Chocobo Fly
Description: A freshwater fishing lure made from a chocobo feather. The faint aroma of stable hay brings back memories of a simpler time.

Name: Floating Minnow
Description: A light plug lure made to resemble a minnow. Especially effective when used to land fish swimming close to the water's surface.

Name: Brass Spoon Lure
Description: A polished brass lure shaped like a spoon so it will oscillate when dragged through the water, attracting fish. Especially effective in lakes.

Name: Shrimp Cage Feeder
Description: A small metal cage packed with a pungent mixture of chopped shrimp. Fish are drawn to the area as pieces of shrimp break off from the cage. Processed bait for ocean fishing.

Name: Crow Fly
Description: A caddisfly-shaped lure crafted from a crow feather. Recommended for freshwater fly fishing novices.

Name: Silver Spoon Lure
Description: A polished silver lure shaped like a spoon so it will oscillate when dragged through the water, attracting fish. Especially effective in lakes.

Name: Steel Jig
Description: The weight of this steel lure allows for casting great distances, such as from coastlines.

Name: Sinking Minnow
Description: A heavy plug lure made to resemble a minnow. Effective in attracting fish from both surface and floor.

Name: Snurble Fly
Description: A freshwater fishing lure made from a snurble tuft.

Name: Heavy Steel Jig
Description: The sheer weight of this steel lure allows for casting tremendous distances, such as from coastlines.

Name: Spinner
Description: A metal river lure designed to resemble both a mayfly and a minnow, allowing for use in a variety of different situations.

Name: Krill Cage Feeder
Description: A small metal cage packed with northern krill. Fish are drawn to the area as krill float off from the cage. Processed bait for ocean fishing.

Name: Mythril Spoon Lure
Description: A polished mythril lure shaped like a spoon so it will oscillate when dragged through the water, attracting all manner of lake and marsh life.

Name: Wildfowl Fly
Description: A freshwater lure made from a wildfowl feather. Its uncanny resemblance to a mayfly makes it irresistible to vilekin-feeding fish such as trout.

Name: Topwater Frog
Description: A light freshwater lure crafted to resemble a frog. Best suited for larger prey such as pikes and certain trout.

Name: Rainbow Spoon Lure
Description: A shiny blacklip oyster shell lure shaped like a spoon so it will oscillate when dragged through the water, attracting all manner of aquatic life. Especially effective in lakes.

Name: Spinnerbait
Description: Several small spinners joined together to resemble a school of fish. Especially effective in rivers.

Name: Streamer
Description: A freshwater fly designed to sink below the water's surface, and by doing so, attract the larger carnivorous fish living near the floor.

Name: Yumizuno
Description: A curved man-made lure used traditionally in the Far East, the name means literally bow horn. Increases chances of landing a big catch, even when casting from shore.

Name: Potion
Description: This weak concoction instantly restores a small amount of HP.

Name: Hi-Potion
Description: This concoction instantly restores a fair amount of HP.

Name: Mega-Potion
Description: This potent concoction instantly restores a large amount of HP.

Name: X-Potion
Description: This powerful concoction instantly restores a sizable amount of HP.

Name: Ether
Description: Processed via the alchemical extraction of aetheric essence occurring in elemental crystals, the contents of this vial instantly restore a small amount of MP.

Name: Hi-Ether
Description: Processed via the alchemical extraction of aetheric essence occurring in elemental crystals, the contents of this vial instantly restore a fair amount of MP.

Name: Mega-Ether
Description: Processed via the alchemical extraction of aetheric essence occurring in elemental crystals, the contents of this vial instantly restore a large amount of MP.

Name: X-Ether
Description: Processed via the alchemical extraction of aetheric essence occurring in elemental crystals, the contents of this vial instantly restore a sizable amount of MP.

Name: Elixir
Description: This special blend of herbal extracts and aetheric essence rejuvenates body and mind, instantly restoring HP and MP.

Name: Hi-Elixir
Description: This special blend of herbal extracts and aetheric essence rejuvenates body and mind, instantly restoring HP and MP.

Name: Dusken Draught
Description: Powdered coral gives this medicinal concoction the deep amber tone from which it gets its name. It is distributed to members of the Lominsan Armada during battle to provide quick recovery from physical wounds.

Name: Kiss of the Morning Meadow
Description: When taken internally, this blend of rare forest herbs stimulates the mind, allowing for immediate recovery of MP. Conjurers serving alongside Gridania's Wood Wailers and the Gods' Quiver often use the potion in the field during battle when there is not enough time to recover naturally.

Name: Onyx Tears
Description: This fragrant fusion of aromatic oils has long been used by the Brass Blades of Ul'dah to instantly rejuvenate both body and mind.

Name: Antidote
Description: This alchemically crafted restorative instantly cures most instances of poison.

Name: Eye Drops
Description: This alchemically crafted restorative instantly cures most instances of blindness.

Name: Echo Drops
Description: This alchemically crafted restorative instantly cures most instances of silence.

Name: Smelling Salts
Description: This alchemically crafted restorative instantly rouses most sleeping targets.

Name: Spine Drops
Description: This alchemically crafted restorative instantly cures most instances of paralysis.

Name: Gold Needle
Description: The properties of this solid-gold needle include curing petrification and pricking fingers.

Name: Phoenix Down
Description:
The billowy plumage of the fledgling Phoenixa legendary bird that, upon each fiery death, is said to rise from its own ashes in a literal blaze of glory. When placed within fifteen yalms of one who is incapacitated, it will instantly revive the person. While some cultures insist that the tailfeather's restorative properties trump those of down, these claims have yet to be proven in any sort of scientific capacity.

Cannot be used during certain duties.

Name: Company-issue Expectorant
Description:
This herbal concoction clears passageways blocked with blood or bile, allowing for easier breathing and quick recovery from unconsciousness.

Cannot be used during battle.

Name: Company-issue Tonic
Description:
This herbal concoction is guaranteed to clear passageways blocked with blood or bile, allowing for easier breathing and quick recovery from unconsciousness.

Cannot be used during battle.

Name: Over-aspected Cluster
Description:
A large crystalline manifestation of aetheric energy exhibiting an extreme elemental charge. When released, the energy has been known to restore the corporeal and spiritual state of those otherwise incapacitated.

Cannot be used during battle.

An apple-filled pastry shaped to resemble the legendary sunfish.

(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Pineapple Ponzecake
Description:
The ponzecake earns its name from the fact that the total weight of the dry ingredients (before pineapples) equals a single ponze.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Bubble Chocolate
Description:
A luscious bonbon made from dark chocolate infused with lighter-than-air bubbles.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Pearl Chocolate
Description:
A rich bonbon made from sweet white chocolate infused with heavier-than-air bubbles.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: White Chocolate
Description:
A heart-shaped morsel of pure white chocolate. Those adventurers allergic to normal chocolate can rest at ease, for this silky smooth confectionary does not actually contain any kukuru powder.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Heart Chocolate
Description:
A heart-shaped morsel of dark chocolate, chock-full of bittersweet memories.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Consecrated Chocolate
Description:
This heart chocolate has been blessed by an ordained sister of the Temple of Menphina.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Princess Pudding
Description:
A tasty Starlight Celebration dessert popular in Limsa Lominsa. This cake-like sweet is formed to resemble the legendary notorious monster, Princess Puddinga terrible beast rumored to once have roamed the meadows of La Noscea.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Ore Fruitcake
Description:
A Starlight Celebration dessert popular in Ul'dah. This cake, if it can be called that, is unparalleled in hardness and density. Every season, at least thirty-seven severe injuries are attributed to various fruitcake-related accidents.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Starlight Log
Description:
A sweet Starlight Celebration dessert popular in Gridania. This cylindrical cake is formed to resemble one of the Black Shroud's many sacred trees.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Years-old Pumpkin Cookie MMXIII
Description:
A devilish imp is thought to have made this slightly burnt biscuit shaped like a pumpkin head nigh on a decade ago. One can only wonder what ingredients it contains.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Sweet Rice Cake
Description:
This three-layered rice cake has been molded into a diamond shape. The coloring used in the layers has medicinal properties.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Orange Juice
Description:
Juice freshly squeezed from ripe La Noscean oranges.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Grape Juice
Description:
Juice freshly squeezed from plump noble grapes.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Apple Juice
Description:
Juice freshly squeezed from shiny red mirror apples.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Pineapple Juice
Description:
Juice freshly squeezed from sun-ripened prickly pineapples.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Chamomile Tea
Description:
A delicately fragranced infusion brewed from tiny yellow chamomile flowers.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Mulled Tea
Description:
A pungent infusion brewed from several exotic spices and herbs. Enjoyed in the sultanate of Ul'dah.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Mineral Water
Description:
Clear water taken from a mountain spring near Ishgard.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Aldgoat Milk
Description:
The thick, creamy milk of an aldgoat nanny.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Buffalo Milk
Description:
The smooth, light milk of a buffalo cow.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Cottage Cheese
Description:
A creamy mixture of unripened cheese curds.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Blue Cheese
Description:
This creamy, pungent cheese gets its distinct flavor from the thin layer of grey-blue mold growing upon it.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Cream Cheese
Description:
A smooth, buttery cheese made from cultured buffalo milk.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Rolanberry Cheese
Description:
Cream cheese blended with tart dried rolanberries.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Marmot Meat
Description: A tiny skinned marmot.

Name: Mutton Loin
Description: A lean cut of meat taken from below a sheep's rib cage.

Name: Dodo Tenderloin
Description: A lean piece of meat taken from under the short ribs of a dodo.

Name: Mole Meat
Description: A fist-sized chunk of lean, bloody meat cleanly sliced from the carcass of a pesky mole.

Name: Salamander Tail
Description: Sinewy meat taken from the tail of a salamander.

Name: Young Dodo Roaster
Description: A whole young dodo, small enough to fit in most conventional household ovens.

Name: Chicken Breast
Description: A tender piece of meat taken from the breast of a chicken.

Name: Antelope Shank
Description: A tough piece of meat taken from the upper leg of an antelope.

Name: Aldgoat Chuck
Description: A large, tender slab of meat taken from the shoulder of an aldgoat.

Name: Raptor Shank
Description: An extra-lean, tough piece of meat taken from the leg of a raptor.

Name: Buffalo Sirloin
Description: A cut of tender, lean meat taken from the rear back of a buffalo.

Name: Eft Tail
Description: Sinewy meat taken from the tail of an eft.

Name: Orobon Liver
Description: The soft liver of a deepwater orobon.

Name: Megalocrab Leg
Description: A fat megalocrab leg, bursting with sweet, juicy meat.

Name: Chicken Egg
Description: The egg of a domesticated chicken.

Name: Dodo Egg
Description: The heavy egg of a wild dodo.

Name: Puk Egg
Description: The lightweight egg of a puk.

Name: Apkallu Egg
Description: The large egg of a wild apkallu.

Name: Malm Kelp
Description:
This dark green variety of seaweed found in all five of Eorzea's seas has been known to grow up to a malm in length.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Wild Onion
Description: A pungent bulb vegetable native to the Near East.

Name: Coerthan Carrot
Description: A long orange root vegetable commonly grown in the rocky alpine soil of the Coerthas region.

Name: Ogre Pumpkin
Description: A bright-orange squash which sweetens in flavor when cooked.

Name: Ruby Tomato
Description: Though many botanists claim this tangy blood red specimen is more closely related to a fruit than a vegetable, it is widely accepted across Eorzea as the latter.

Name: Alpine Parsnip
Description: A long white root vegetable indigenous to the mountainous region of Coerthas.

Name: La Noscean Lettuce
Description: A crisp leafy vegetable native to the plains of La Noscea.

Name: Cieldalaes Spinach
Description: An iron-rich leafy vegetable native to the Cieldalaes.

Name: Highland Parsley
Description: Oft used as a garnish in other dishes, this pungent vegetable grows in abundance in the mountainous region of upper La Noscea.

Name: Paprika
Description: A pepper which can be dried and ground to make a mild red spice. It is often used in medicines, as well as in cooking.

Name: Nopales
Description: An edible oval-leaved cactus brought back by explorers of the New World.

Name: Popoto
Description: A starchy tuberous vegetable originally introduced to Eorzea by explorers from the distant western continent.

Name: Wizard Eggplant
Description: A firm purple-skinned vegetable indigenous to the mountains of the Near East. A common wives' tale claims if you eat too many of this vegetable, you will turn into one.

Name: Midland Cabbage
Description: A round leafy vegetable which prefers the steady climate of the Black Shroud.

Name: Aloe
Description: A thick spiny-leaved cactus indigenous to the southern continent of Meracydia. The Miqo'te are known to treat severe burns with the cool gel-like substance found inside the leaves.

Name: Salt Leek
Description: A long, pungent, leafy vegetable that lacks a bulb like that of its cousin, the onion.

Name: Ramhorn Zucchini
Description: This long, thin variety of squash earns its name from its resemblance to the horn of a mountain ram.

Name: Maiden Artichoke
Description: The leaf-like bud of an artichoke plant. Due to the roughness of its petals, only the fleshy lower portions can be consumed, as well as the center of the bud, commonly known as the heart.

Name: Shriekshroom
Description: The underdeveloped sporeling of a funguar.

Name: Chanterelle
Description: An edible mushroom known for its leaf-like appearance as well as its fruit-like fragrance.

Name: Gil Bun
Description: This tiny round mushroom has a cap which resembles a coin, and is known for its rich flavor and pungent aroma.

Name: Button Mushroom
Description: A small white mushroom commonly found in moist areas across Eorzea.

Name: White Truffle
Description: A rare white mushroom that grows in the soil, rather than above it, making the specimen almost impossible to locate. It is treasured as a delicacy for its unique aroma.

Name: Ratstool
Description: The underdeveloped sporeling of a myconid. Popular myth has that rats will use the chair-shaped fungus as a place to rest.

Name: Black Truffle
Description: A rare black mushroom that grows in the soil, rather than above it, making the specimen almost impossible to locate. It is treasured as a delicacy for its unique aroma.

Name: Dalamud Nut
Description: The shell which encases this walnut is reminiscent of the (now fallen) lesser moon of its namesake.

Name: Moon Nut
Description: The ghostly white shell which encases this walnut is reminiscent of the celestial body of its namesake.

Name: Kukuru Bean
Description: This seed of the kukuru tree is the primary ingredient in chocolate.

Name: Cinderfoot Olive
Description: The seed of an olive tree, often preserved in brine or pressed to make oil.

Name: Gridanian Chestnut
Description: The seed of a chestnut tree, this savory nut is covered in a coat of prickly spikes.

Name: Gridanian Walnut
Description: The seed of a walnut tree, this fragrant nut is covered by a thin, fleshy outer shell and a hard inner shell.

Name: Iron Acorn
Description: The seed of an oak tree, this small nut is covered by an extremely hard outer shell.

Name: Lowland Grapes
Description:
A semisweet variety of grape which has adapted to the volcanic soil abundant on Vylbrand.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: La Noscean Orange
Description:
A sweet citrus fruit known to thrive in the temperate climate of lower La Noscea.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Faerie Apple
Description:
A tart variety of apple commonly found growing in the cool mountain passes of Coerthas.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Sun Lemon
Description:
A sour citrus fruit indigenous to the Near East.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Pixie Plums
Description:
A tart fruit commonly grown in mountain orchards in the Coerthas region.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Alligator Pear
Description:
A soft green fruit, also known as Shroud butter. Though not thought to be indigenous to Eorzea, it is not certain how the plant first came to the realm.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Blood Currants
Description:
A tart red berry found growing throughout the Black Shroud.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Rolanberry
Description:
A tart fruitone of few still found growing in the devastated region of Mor Dhona.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Prickly Pineapple
Description:
A sweet and tangy fruit covered in a thick, spike-laden skin.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Sunflower Seeds
Description: The fruit of a sunflower, this small seed is covered by a thin black shell.

Name: Buffalo Beans
Description: A common variety of green bean recognizable by its long thin pods. Buffalo are said to be fond of the beans, and have been known to eat entire crops if left unchecked.

Name: Sticky Rice
Description: This grain is imported from a land far to the east. When cooked, it has a consistency slightly more glutinous than normal rice.

Name: Lalafellin Lentil
Description: Thin round beans resembling tiny convex lenses. Thought to have been introduced to Eorzea by the realm's first Lalafellin settlers.

Name: Millioncorn
Description: Hundreds of sweet yellow kernels adorn each cob of this vegetable native to the recently discovered New World.

Name: Jade Peas
Description: Sweet green beans recognizable by their thin, crescent-shaped pods.

Name: Rye
Description: A dark variety of rye grass commonly found growing in the higher elevations of Mor Dhona and Coerthas.

Name: Sunset Wheat
Description: A common variety of golden brown wheat eaten as a staple in many of Eorzea's city-states.

Name: Rye Flour
Description: Coarsely milled rye.

Name: Sunset Wheat Flour
Description: Finely milled sunset wheat.

Name: Cornmeal
Description: Coarsely milled millioncorn.

Name: Cinnamon
Description: The sweet-smelling bark of the cinnamon tree is often dried and ground into a spice used to add flavor to confectionaries, though it is also commonly used in medicines.

Name: Garlean Garlic
Description: A pungent spice used to flavor many different varieties of dishes. It is also thought to ward off vampiric bats, but there is no evidence to substantiate that claim.

Name: Black Pepper
Description: An aromatic spice used in cooking as well as pickling.

Name: Cloves
Description: A sweet-smelling spice made from the dried buds of the clove tree. It is used to flavor confectionaries, and as an essential oil.

Name: Marjoram
Description: A sweet-smelling herb used in cooking and in medicines.

Name: Vanilla Beans
Description: A sweet-smelling spice made from the dried pod of the rare vanilla plant. It is often used in the making confectionaries as well as medicines.

Name: Galago Mint
Description: A leafy herb with a crisp, fragrant aroma. It is often used in cooking and in teas, as well as for its essential oil.

Name: Ala Mhigan Mustard
Description: When dried and ground into a fine powder, this yellow-tinged spice can add quite the kick to any dish.

Name: Pearl Ginger
Description: An exotic root vegetable native to the Far East that is often dried, ground, and used in cooking as well as in the creation of medicines.

Name: Midland Basil
Description: A fragrant herb used to flavor various meat and poultry dishes.

Name: Dragon Pepper
Description: A red-hot spice known to cause severe burns in the mouths of those who consume too many.

Name: Laurel
Description: A savory spice made from the dried leaves of the laurel bush, or as it is known by some, the yanny bush.

Name: Mugwort
Description: The young leaves of the mugwort plant are used not only as a spice in cooking, but also as a curative agent in various unguents.

Name: Thyme
Description: A fragrant herb used to flavor various meat and poultry dishes.

Name: Almonds
Description: A tear-shaped nut which can be used to season exotic sweets, or pressed for its fragrant oil.

Name: Desert Saffron
Description: This spice made from the dried styles of the desert saffron flower gives a bright-yellow color to dishes.

Name: Nutmeg
Description: A sweet-smelling seed that is ground into a powder and used to flavor pastries and tea. It is also widely used in Far Eastern medicines.

Name: Sagolii Sage
Description: A savory herb often found growing in parched desert environments. It is used in cooking and various medicinal ointments and unguents.

Name: Thanalan Tea Leaves
Description: These leaves, when dried and steeped in hot water, create a sweet-smelling tea known for its curative properties.

Name: Table Salt
Description: Finely ground salt used not only for flavoring foods, but for pickling and preserving as well.

Name: Maple Sugar
Description: Crystallized sugar made from boiling down maple syrup.

Name: Maple Syrup
Description: A sweet, dark liquid made by boiling down maple sap.

Name: Honey
Description: Bees make this sweet golden honey from the nectar of flowers.

Name: Powdered Sugar
Description: Sweet, snow-like sugar, perfect for dusting Starlight Celebration sweets.

Name: Sweet Cream
Description: The butterfat-rich layer skimmed off of buffalo milk. Widely used in confectionaries.

Name: Smooth Butter
Description: A smooth, fatty cream made by churning buffalo milk.

Name: Kukuru Butter
Description: A thick oil extracted from kukuru beans. Used in making chocolate.

Name: Kukuru Powder
Description: Roasted kukuru beans ground into a fine powder. Used in making chocolate.

Name: Clove Oil
Description: Clove-infused cooking oil.

Name: Olive Oil
Description: A fragrant light-green oil extracted from pressed olives.

Name: Lavender Oil
Description: Lavender-infused cooking oil.

Name: Cider Vinegar
Description: A fruity vinegar made from fermenting faerie apples.

Name: Dark Vinegar
Description: A high-quality distilled vinegar made from select lowland grapes.

Name: Pie Dough
Description: Simple pie dough made of flour and butter.

Name: Sour Red
Description: Made from lowland grapes grown on arid soil, this vinegary wine is more suited to cooking than it is to drinking (though that does little to stop most Lominsan pirates from drowning their sorrows in the phenolic seepage).

Name: Gelatin
Description: A clear gelling agent extracted from animal skin and fish bones.

Name: Fish Stock
Description: Broth created from boiling down the flesh and bones of various types of seafood.

Name: Tomato Sauce
Description: A tangy sauce made from crushed tomatoes.

Name: Dodo Stuffing
Description: A mixture of dried bread, nuts, and fruit, blended with several savory spices.

Name: Chicken Stock
Description: A clear golden broth made by boiling chicken bones.

Name: Gysahl Greens
Description:
A leafy vegetable indigenous to the Near East. While too bitter for most people's tastes, chocobos are known to enjoy the flavor, and thus the greens are often used as fodder for the animals.

Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by offering multiple servings)

Name: Merlthor Goby
Description:
A vividly striped saltwater fish commonly found in the Strait of Merlthor.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Lominsan Anchovy
Description:
These small saltwater fish form massive schools resembling colossal sea creatures to discourage predators from approaching.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Finger Shrimp
Description:
A common saltwater shrimp found in the plankton-rich waters of the Sea of Jade.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Ocean Cloud
Description:
A semi-transparent jellyfish commonly found in the Strait of Merlthor, where it goes through nine separate stages of development before reaching adulthood.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Sea Cucumber
Description:
A purple, spiny, sluglike creature found in the shallows off of the island of Mazlaya, and treasured in the Far East as a delicacy.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Harbor Herring
Description:
This particular variety of herring will gather in busy harbors to feed on the small sea creatures which consume the waste dumped from ships.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 1 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Vongola Clam
Description:
A tasty bivalve mollusk commonly found on and near the island of Bianaq.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Coral Butterfly
Description:
A colorful saltwater fish commonly found in the warm seas around the island of Bianaq. Not known for its flavor, the wavekin is most often kept as a pet.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 1 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Moraby Flounder
Description:
A flat bottom-feeder commonly found in the relatively calm waters of Moraby Bay.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Pebble Crab
Description:
A small bluish grey crab found in tide pools along the La Noscean coast.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Tiger Cod
Description:
A striped saltwater fish indigenous to the cold northern waters of the Bloodbrine Sea.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 1 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Helmet Crab
Description:
This saltwater wavekin, most commonly found in the shallows of the Strait of Merlthor, is protected by a hard shell resembling a helmet.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Rothlyt Oyster
Description:
Also known as the milk of the sea, these tasty bivalve mollusks can be found on sea rocks all around Eorzea, but it is said the plumpest, most succulent grow in the nutrient-rich waters of the Rothlyt Sound.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Navigator's Dagger
Description:
These thin, long saltwater fish will oft jump out of the water and glide for yalms across the surface, using their pectoral fins as ersatz wings.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Angelfish
Description:
A small colorful fish native to the warmer waters of the seas near Meracydia. Since the Calamity, more and more have been caught off Eorzea's southern coastline.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Razor Clam
Description:
A long bivalve mollusk most commonly found buried in the beaches of islands situated in the Rhotano Sea. They are known to leap out of their burrows when surprised or agitated.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Blue Octopus
Description:
The somber blue tone of its skin does not make this variety of octopus any more docile than its crimson cousins. It is a crafty hunter who lurks in the shadows, snatching unwary prey and strangling it with its powerful eight arms before shredding it with its razor-sharp beak.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Blowfish
Description:
A saltwater fish that, when provoked, blows up to three times its normal size to intimidate the would-be attacker. It is also known to have an organ which contains a potent silencing poison.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Saber Sardine
Description:
This tiny saltwater fish travels in giant schools through the Indigo Deep searching for food. Its razor-like fins have been known to cut straight through the strongest of fishing nets.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Ogre Barracuda
Description:
A large saltwater wavekin that roams the Rhotano Sea in small schools, preying on smaller fish such as anchovies or sardines.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Monkfish
Description:
This deep-sea-dwelling wavekin attracts its prey with a tiny glowing appendage protruding forth from its disfigured head, and then swallows the poor victim whole with its unnaturally large mouth.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Sea Bo
Description:
When swimming upright, this strange sea creature closely resembles a riding chocobo, hence the name.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Bianaq Bream
Description:
A cherry-colored saltwater fish found in abundance in all of Eorzea's five seas, though it is said those caught near Bianaq are the largest.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Black Sole
Description:
A flat bottom-feeder commonly found in the frigid waters of the Bloodbrine Sea.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Hammerhead Shark
Description:
A ravenous shark with a hammer-shaped head it uses to quickly detect its prey. This wavekin is most commonly found living in small schools in the Strait of Merlthor.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 3 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Sea Pickle
Description:
A blue, spiny, sluglike creature found in the shallows off of Vylbrand, and considered a delicacy by Sea Wolves.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Indigo Herring
Description:
This blue-backed, white-bellied saltwater fish native to the Indigo Deep is known to migrate in large schools from north to south in the winter, and back again in the summer.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Ash Tuna
Description:
A large saltwater fish known to migrate between the Sea of Jade and the Sea of Ash. In recent years, overfishing by boats from the Far East has led to a significant drop in their numbers.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Leafy Seadragon
Description:
Though once found all across the five seas, seadragon numbers are now but a mere fraction of what they once were, due in part to Ishgardian culling parties.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Fullmoon Sardine
Description:
A tiny saltwater fish native to the waters of Vylbrand. Unlike other wavekin, they feed only at night, their activity increasing as Menphina waxes.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Haraldr Haddock
Description:
A tasty saltwater fish indigenous to the cold waters of the Bloodbrine Sea. Its name comes from a legendary northern king who it was said would only eat the fatty flesh of this wavekin.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Whitelip Oyster
Description:
A bivalve mollusk found on the cliffs and rocks lining the Rhotano Sea. On rare occasions, sand will become trapped inside the shell and gradually form into a pearl.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Lavender Remora
Description:
A violet-hued fish found in the warmer waters of Eorzea's southern seas.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Balloonfish
Description:
A saltwater fish covered in scores of sharp spines, discouraging would-be predators from dining on this otherwise defenseless fry.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Silver Shark
Description:
A large, spindle-shaped shark commonly found in the Sea of Ash and known to attack without provocation.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 4 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Wahoo
Description:
A razor-fanged saltwater fish known to migrate throughout the warm waters of the Sea of Ash, following the schools of shrimp on which it feeds.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Raincaller
Description:
A deep-blue freshwater fish native to the lakes and swamps of the Black Shroud. They can be seen sticking their heads out of the water whenever it rains, leading people to believe it is the fish summoning the storm. However, naturalists have surmised that the fish are simply rising to the surface in search of food, mistaking the drops of water for insects.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Nautilus
Description:
A giant cephalopod characterized by its spectacular whorling shell. Commonly found in the nutrient-rich Bay of Dha'yuz, the wavekin are thought by sailors and pirates to be the heralds of the Navigator, Llymlaen, and their shells are often carved into celebratory chalices.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Pike Eel
Description:
When stretched straight from head to tail, the longest of saltwater pike eels can measure more than a full yalm in length.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Mummer Wrasse
Description:
This saltwater fish's name comes from the odd lump on its head, thought to resemble a mummer's motley cap.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 3 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Plaice
Description:
A bottom-feeding flatfish, the plaice is most commonly found blending into the sands covering the sea floor near the Isles of Umbra.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Sea Devil
Description:
Legends tell of giant sea devils emerging from the sea to wrap their many arms around ships and drag them to the abyss. This seems impossible today, as the largest catches in recent memory are little more than a yalm across.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Rock Lobster
Description:
A large crimson crustacean commonly found hiding in the rocks off the shores of islands dotting the Rhotano Sea. The rich, flavorful tails are regarded as a delicacy across Eorzea.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Goosefish
Description:
A large-mouthed saltwater glutton, thought to feed on most anything, from smaller fish, to seaweed, to the flesh of drowned sailors.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Little Thalaos
Description:
Despite the modifier, the little Thalaos is anything but small; though compared to the Thalaos of legend, even the largest of sea serpents would be deemed little. Normally only found far offshore in the Indigo Deep, this rare wavekin can sometimes be found swimming near the eastern cliffs of La Noscea.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Shall Shell
Description:
This enormous bivalve mollusk is easily recognizable by the unique wave pattern found on its outer shell.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Mahi-mahi
Description:
This deep-sea predator is not only massive, but deceptively fast. Some sailors swear that a mahi-mahi can make the journey from Meracydia to the Cieldalaes in less than a fortnight, though knowing most sailors, that claim may be slightly exaggerated.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Halibut
Description:
While similar to the sole or plaice in appearance and behavior, the halibut is much larger than both, and can feed a Lalafellin family of five for several turns of the sun.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Mazlaya Marlin
Description:
A large saltwater fish found in the warm waters south of the Sea of Ash and known for its remarkable swimming speed.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 4 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Coelacanth
Description:
An ancient species of saltwater fish which appears to have flourished in times well before the Allagans built their empire.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 3 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Giant Squid
Description:
This rarely seen giant cephalopod makes an appearance in ancient Sea Wolf mythology as the creature on which the legendary whale Bismarck fed.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Gigant Octopus
Description:
A legendary cephalopod feared by sailors young and old. Tales of these cyclopean creatures tearing up ships and dragging them down to the abyss can still be heard in alehouses and inns across Hydaelyn.

[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Sunfish
Description:
Legends say this giant saltwater fish will help those stranded in the water by allowing them to ride it back to shore.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Dinichthys
Description:
A legendary saltwater fish covered in thick armor and said to have once been worshipped by the Sahagin.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 4 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Megalodon
Description:
A legendary shark with a mouth so big and an appetite so large, it is said it can swallow an adult Roegadyn whole.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 4 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Titanic Sawfish
Description:
Legends say that this gargantuan saltwater fish once ripped a hundred-man galleon in two with its saw-like head.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 4 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Crayfish
Description:
A brown-carapaced freshwater crustacean commonly found in the rivers and lakes of Aldenard.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Chub
Description:
A common freshwater fish found in rivers across Eorzea. Prefers the slow-moving waters found near a river's mouth to the rapids found upstream.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 1 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Striped Goby
Description:
A brightly striped freshwater fish native to the rivers and lakes of the Coerthas and Mor Dhona regions.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Dwarf Catfish
Description:
An undersized variety of catfish found in still, swampy waters across Aldenard.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Bone Crayfish
Description:
A white-carapaced freshwater crustacean commonly found living in caves or deep lakes where sunlight is absent.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Princess Trout
Description:
Unlike other freshwater trout which make their habitat in swift-flowing rivers, the silver princess trout prefers the relative seclusion of inland lakes.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Dusk Goby
Description:
A hardy species, the dusk goby can survive not only in freshwater, but also the mouths of rivers, where the tides can bring saltwater malms inland.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Pipira
Description:
A fierce freshwater fish most commonly found in Gridania's Jadeite Flood and Black Tea Brook.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Crimson Crayfish
Description:
A crimson-carapaced freshwater crustacean commonly found in the streams and lakes of Vylbrand.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Gudgeon
Description:
Each night, this freshwater fish will use its fins to dig a shallow burrow in river or lake beds, where it will sleep, relatively safe from predators.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Brass Loach
Description:
This long, thin, brass-colored freshwater fish is most commonly found in the Yafaem Saltmoor and surrounding rivers and lakes.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Maiden Carp
Description:
Large schools of these dark silver fish can be found in the White Maiden and her tributaries.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Abalathian Smelt
Description:
A tiny freshwater fish native to the lakes and rivers fed by runoff from Abalathia's Spine.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Blindfish
Description:
Commonly found in the sea caves and grottoes of Vylbrand, the eyes of this freshwater fish regressed long ago, earning the specimen its name.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Mudskipper
Description:
An amphibious fish which can survive for bells out of water as long as its skin remains moist. When on land, the mudskipper uses its pectoral fins to wander about in search of shelter. Because of this trait, the fish is sometimes associated with the god Oschon.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Rainbow Trout
Description:
Found in the crystal-clear rivers and lakes of Mor Dhona and Coerthas, this fish's scales reflect all seven colors of the rainbow, making it difficult to locate in the water.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: River Crab
Description:
A tiny freshwater crustacean commonly found in rivers throughout Eorzea.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Ala Mhigan Fighting Fish
Description:
A beautiful blue freshwater fish known for its violent disposition.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Faerie Bass
Description:
A common freshwater fish found in rivers and lakes in almost every corner of Eorzea. A staple for many of the realm's smallfolk.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Acorn Snail
Description:
Believed to have hitched a ride on the hull of a trade ship, the acorn snail is an invasive species originally from the New World, far to the west. As it has few natural predators in Eorzea, its numbers have exploded in recent years.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Dark Sleeper
Description:
A small freshwater fish originally from the eastern continent of Othard. It is said that the first dark sleeper was introduced to Eorzea by an exiled Lalafellin prince who wished to once again experience the luxuries of his homeland.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: La Noscean Perch
Description:
A fair-sized freshwater fish found distributed evenly throughout the lakes and rivers of lower Vylbrand.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Moat Carp
Description:
This freshwater fish is found in lakes and marshes throughout the Black Shroud...but rarely in moats.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Copperfish
Description:
The copperfish's dull orange scalesa hue rare in freshwater wavekinmake this species popular amongst Ul'dahn nobles, who apparently prefer even their fish to be the color of their coin.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 1 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Bluebell Salmon
Description:
Hatched far up inland rivers, bluebell salmon will travel all the way downstream to the Indigo Deep where they will spend the majority of their adulthood. Then, however, when it comes time to spawn, they will return back upstream to the place of their birth.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Mudcrab
Description:
As its name implies, the mudcrab spends most of its life in the muddy freshwater shallows of swamps and moors.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Tricolored Carp
Description:
Patches of gold, silver, and bronze cover this medium-sized freshwater fish's body, making it a favorite choice for the private garden pools of Ul'dahn nobles.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Eunuch Crayfish
Description:
The grip of this tiny freshwater crustacean's claw is so strong, it has been the end of many a Lalafell's fingers...and more. Take care when handling.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Jade Eel
Description:
Similar to salmon, this green-grey freshwater eel lives the majority of its life in the salty waters of the sea, returning to inland rivers to only spawn and die.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Pond Mussel
Description:
This bivalve freshwater mollusk with a tear-shaped shell can be found either clinging to the side of submerged boulders or simply lying half-buried in the mud.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Warmwater Trout
Description:
This freshwater fish was once found only in the waters heated by the flows of lava coursing beneath the mighty volcano O'Ghomoro. After the Calamity, however, fishers began finding the wavekin in other warm locations such as Thanalan.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Glass Perch
Description:
With an almost completely transparent body, this variety of freshwater perch is coveted by naturalists wishing to study the inner workings of organs on a living specimen.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Four-eyed Fish
Description:
Four-eyed fish do not actually have four eyes, but two eyes that are divided into an upper and lower portion that allow the wavekin to see both above and below the water at the same time.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Black Eel
Description:
Black eels reach maturity in the Sea of Jade, at which point they return back up the Velodyna and Hathoeva rivers to spawn.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Dark Bass
Description:
This freshwater fish, known for its voracious appetite, is originally native to the southern continent of Meracydia.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Aegis Shrimp
Description:
Whereas other shrimp shed their old exoskeletons each summer in favor of new ones, the aegis shrimp simply adds a new layer every year until the shell is so hard, not even a blow from a trained pugilist can break through it.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Five-ilm Pleco
Description:
This freshwater fish commonly found in the rivers of the Black Shroud will often grow no larger than a mere five ilms.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Climbing Perch
Description:
Though not amphibious like the mudskipper, the climbing perch will jump from Black Shroud rivers onto low-lying tree branches in order to catch flies and beetles.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Shadow Catfish
Description:
A large whiskered fish that can be found in the calm marshes of the Black Shroud.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Black Ghost
Description:
Native to the rivers and lakes of the Black Shroud, this freshwater fish uses electric receptors on its body to locate food.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Lamprey
Description:
A long, ugly freshwater eel found in nearly every river and lake in Eorzea. Its toothy grin is enough to frighten children across the realm.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Plaguefish
Description:
This variety of freshwater fish has the queer habit of wearing the skulls of small drowned animals, though it is not known exactly why.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Yugr'am Salmon
Description:
This freshwater fish matures in the salty waters of the Bloodbrine Sea, only to return up the Yugr'am River where it was born to spawn.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Spotted Pleco
Description:
Tiny white spots cover the body of this rare freshwater fish.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Ropefish
Description:
As it has the tendency to coil up while inactive, this variety of freshwater eel is oft mistaken for lost boat rigging.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Grip Killifish
Description:
A rare type of fish oft found in stagnant waters such as the isolated pools which collect in the basin of Empty Heart on the western finger of the Gods' Grip.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 1 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Bone Cleaner
Description:
A freshwater snail that survives solely on the carrion of animals that get caught and perish in the sucking mud of swamps and marshes.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Root Skipper
Description:
A small fish that is found only in Rootslake in the Black Shroud.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Bonytongue
Description:
A single flat tooth on the bottom of this freshwater species' mouth gives the bonytongue its name.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Mitten Crab
Description:
The claws of this freshwater crustacean are covered in myriad tiny bristles which provide the illusion that the crab is wearing mittens.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Monke Onke
Description:
A giant freshwater fish found in the tepid rivers and lakes of the Black Shroud.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Seema
Description:
The flesh of this freshwater trout native to central and northern Eorzea is a bright pink, leading to the common nickname, cherry trout.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Sandfish
Description:
An amphibious fish capable of breathing on land. This trait has allowed it to adapt to life in the deserts of Thanalan.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Silverfish
Description:
As are copperfish and goldfish, freshwater silverfish are prized amongst well-to-do Ul'dahns, and often kept as pets.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Clown Loach
Description:
Bright patterns, similar to a clown's motley, cover this small freshwater fish from head to tail.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Armored Pleco
Description:
The rock-hard scales of the armored pleco are thought to protect the wavekin from injury when being dashed about swift-water rapids.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Giant Bass
Description:
Significantly larger than a dark bass, landing a giant bass can prove quite the challenge for even the most seasoned angler.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Velodyna Carp
Description:
This scarlet cousin to the maiden carp can most commonly be found in the Velodyna and Hathoeva rivers.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Spotted Puffer
Description:
A cousin of the sea-dwelling balloonfish, spotted puffers are unique in that they can survive in the brackish waters of deltas and river mouths.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Golden Loach
Description:
Truly a prize, this bright-gold fish, though rare, can be found in rivers and lakes across Eorzea.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Trader Eel
Description:
This freshwater eel native to the rivers and lakes of Thanalan will often display the unique trait of swapping its mate with other nearby eels when spawning.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Crimson Trout
Description:
A red-scaled trout commonly found in the rivers originating on Abalathia's Spine.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Discus
Description:
A colorful freshwater fish that can only survive in rivers located in more temperate climes.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Bronze Lake Trout
Description:
A species of trout native to Vylbrand's Bronze Lake.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Ignus Snail
Description:
The fiery red shells of this freshwater snail are prized by the Amalj'aa, and are useful when bartering with the beast tribe.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Loyal Pleco
Description:
This variety of striped freshwater fish earns its name from its tendency to gather by the legs of any man or beast who enters its habitat.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Thunderbolt Sculpin
Description:
A rare freshwater fish decorated with a thunderbolt-like pattern down its back.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Fall Jumper
Description:
Fall jumpers are born with an inherent tendency to swim against the current. When they arrive at a falls, this leaves them with no option but to leap out of the water in an attempt to continue upstream.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Knifefish
Description:
The freshwater knifefish is named such due to its resemblance to a flat blade.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Oakroot
Description:
A giant freshwater fish found in inland lakes and rivers. Its name is derived from its resemblance to a knotty oaken root.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Common Sculpin
Description:
This freshwater fish has highly developed fins and spines which not only protect the wavekin, but serve as weapons for hunting its prey.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Southern Pike
Description:
Though classified as a freshwater fish native to the Velodyna and Hathoeva rivers, this particular wavekin can survive in the brackish delta where the waterways spill into the Sea of Jade.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Northern Pike
Description:
Though classified as a freshwater fish native to the White Maiden, this particular wavekin can survive in the brackish waters where the Maiden meets the Strait of Merlthor.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Kobold Puffer
Description:
Similar to the spotted puffer, the kobold puffer can also survive in the brackish waters of deltas and river mouths. Its spots, however, are replaced with a hideous coat of bristly spines which give it the appearance of a bedraggled kobold.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Archerfish
Description:
When feeding, the archerfish will lift its head ever so slightly above a lake's or river's surface and spit a stream of water up to a yalm to strike flies from low-lying branches into the water with remarkable accuracy.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Goblin Perch
Description:
The goblins claim that they brought this variety of perch back from their years-long pilgrimage into Othard and Ilsabard...because it tasted so divine.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 3 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Agelyss Carp
Description:
A rare species of carp native to the Agelyss River.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Assassin Betta
Description:
A violent species of freshwater fish from central Abalathia's Spine that will attack other assassin betta if they draw too near while feeding.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Sludgeskipper
Description:
Similar to its cousin the mudskipper, the sludgeskipper can also survive outside water for several bells. The sludgeskipper, however, is at home in highly polluted pools where other creatures would likely perish.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Boltfish
Description:
This freshwater anomaly possesses high concentrations of lightning-aspected aetherial energy which can be used to inflict serious injury on any foolish enough to provoke the fish.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Garpike
Description:
A hard-scaled freshwater fish native to southern Eorzea.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Ilsabardian Bass
Description:
Unlike its Eorzean cousins, the Ilsabardian bass is mean-tempered and quick to bite, attacking other species sharing the same lake until there are none left but its own.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Paglth'an Discus
Description:
A brightly colored freshwater fish native to the warm waters in and around the Amalj'aa territory of Paglth'an.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Boxing Pleco
Description:
The largest pleco known to naturalists, this variety is known for violently flailing its fins at any unfortunate creature that happens to swim by.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Kissing Trout
Description:
Native to the freshwater rivers of Abalathia's Spine, the kissing trout is famous for its mating dance in which a male and female will face each other for several moments before proceeding to couple.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Angry Pike
Description:
While all species of freshwater pike are known to be violent, this particular variety has been recorded actually biting the ankles of wading fishers.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Goldfish
Description:
The brilliant luster of this freshwater fish native to the Far East has made it a popular addition to the aquariums and garden ponds of Ul'dahn patricians.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Vampire Lampern
Description:
Just as its name implies, the vampire lampern is indeed a sucker of blood, using its multiple rows of teeth to latch onto its prey, whether it be sea or land creature, and bore a hole from which to drink.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Wandering Sculpin
Description:
Legend states that this particular variety of sculpin is a favorite of Oschon, the Wanderer, and that the god will oft dine on this fish while on His journeys through the realm of man.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Cave Cherax
Description:
It is said that not even a fishing line made from adamantite wire can withstand the cutting force of this legendary giant crustacean's claws.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Coeurlfish
Description:
Two front teeth of this freshwater fish are exceptionally long and therefore protrude from the mouth, giving them the appearance of coeurl fangs.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Giant Donko
Description:
A giant freshwater fish native to the rivers and swamps of La Noscea.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Sundisc
Description:
This freshwater fish has a bright-yellow sun-like pattern across its body, giving rise to the name sundisc.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Alligator Garfish
Description:
A legendary freshwater fish said to have a head not unlike that of an alligator, complete with rows of razor-sharp teeth.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Wootz Knifefish
Description:
It is believed that after living in waters tainted with wootz ore for so long, this knifefish absorbed so much of the mineral that it began showing in its scales.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Giant Catfish
Description:
A giant freshwater fish found throughout Aldenard and known for the decidedly feline whiskers which it uses to detect the movement of prey.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Cadaver Carp
Description:
Neither dead nor necrophagous, the cadaver carp is called such because of where it chooses to livesome of the most tainted, noisome, and foul waters in all of Eorzea.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Mushroom Crab
Description:
This amazing crab will rub its shell up against funguars to collect spores, which it will then grow on its back. Once the sporelings begin to sprout, the crab will use its claws to slice off the mushrooms and eat them.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Judgment Staff
Description:
Named after the primal Ramuh's signature weapon, this strange freshwater fish will only feed when the weather is rainy.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Poxpike
Description:
The rock-hard scales of this variety of freshwater garpike are spattered with scores of unhealthy-looking spots.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Emperor Fish
Description:
This giant freshwater fish lives out its adulthood feeding in the Indigo Deep before returning all the way back up to the head of the White Maiden to spawn.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 3 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Bowfin
Description:
Record of the bowfin being caught in the Black Shroud dates back to the time of the first Elezen settlers.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Heliobatis
Description:
A flat freshwater bottom-feeder found predominantly in marshes and swamps, where it can hide under the blanket of organic detritus collected on the floor.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Takitaro
Description:
A legendary giant freshwater fish indigenous to the lands of the Far East. The takitaro found in Eorzea are thought to be the offspring of a specimen presented as a gift to an eccentric sultan who loosed the fish into a cenote when it grew too large to keep in the royal aquariums.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Pirarucu
Description:
A legendary giant freshwater fish rumored to live in the bottomless swamps hidden deep within the unexplored regions of the Black Shroud.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Morinabaligi
Description:
A giant freshwater fish so shrouded in mystery that naught is known of it.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Jungle Catfish
Description:
It is rumored that a jungle catfish can grow to become as large as an aurochs, and while there are sightings aplenty of these massive specimens, one that large has yet to be caught.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Sand Bream
Description:
A tiny sand-dwelling fish which can spend its whole life out of the water.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Desert Catfish
Description:
A large variety of air-breathing catfish. Its near-frictionless scales allow it to swim through the desert as a normal fish would through the water.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Dustfish
Description:
When threatened, this sand-dwelling fish will beat the ground with its fins, kicking up a cloud of dust and allowing it the opportunity to escape unscathed.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Storm Rider
Description:
These sand-dwelling fish will skip across the desert unless they are fortunate enough to stumble across a sandstorm, in which case they will spread their fins and ride the storm great distances.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Antlion Slug
Description:
This sand-dwelling slug is able to maintain its mucous coating by absorbing the moisture from prey it catches at the bottom of conical pits not unlike the ones antlions are known to dig.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Dune Manta
Description:
Remarkably smooth skin allows the dune manta to glide through desert sand as if it were the sea.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Cloud Jellyfish
Description:
Cloud jellyfish aimlessly drift about the Sea of Clouds, tentacles spread out below them, searching for the small birds on which they feed.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Skyfish
Description:
One of the more common creatures found living on the thermal currents above the Sea of Clouds, from a distance, the skyfish appears to be no more than a simple rod outfitted with three sets of transparent wings.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Cloud Cutter
Description:
The swiftest inhabitants of the Sea of Clouds, cloud cutters will fly straight in a single direction for malms before quickly turning at some unthinkable angle and darting off in another direction.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Blind Manta
Description:
The blind manta is thought to navigate the Sea of Clouds in a manner similar to how bats keep their bearingsusing sound and echoes to determine the location of cliff faces and other creatures.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Rift Sailor
Description:
The rift sailor uses the light elastic webbing between its wings to catch the roiling winds of the Sea of Clouds and glide across the rifts.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Sagolii Monkfish
Description:
When hunting, the Sagolii monkfish uses a method similar to its sea-bound cousinattracting potential prey to its location with a glowing appendage situated directly above its gaping maw.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Saucerfish
Description:
Lacking feet or wings to propel itself from the ground, only death awaits the saucerfish that is foolish enough to leave the Sea of Clouds.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Caravan Eel
Description:
After maturing in the Grand Wake, caravan eels will form long lines in the sand and make their way back to the Sagolii Desert to spawn and die.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Rhamphorhynchus
Description:
Its massive lance-shaped nose makes this legendary denizen of the Sea of Clouds a formidable nuisance for airships passing through the area.

[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Tricorn
Description: A legendary amphibian with a boomerang-like head said to be powerful enough to split a harpoon in two.

Name: Young Indigo Herring
Description: A large fish native to the Indigo Deep. When packed in salt, it can be preserved for up to a year.

Name: Navigator's Ear
Description: This medium-sized oyster is high in nutrients, making it optimal for use in medicines and rations.

Name: Allagan Snail
Description: A giant snail believed to have been bred for consumption during the reign of the Great Allagan Empire.

Name: Tree Toad
Description: A giant green toad found in nearly all of the lakes and swamps of Aldenard.

Name: Box Turtle
Description: A common, thick-shelled turtle found in wetlands throughout Eorzea.

Name: Nether Newt
Description: An amphibious type of scalekin found in the wetlands of Vylbrand. Its body is covered with colorful markings which some of Limsa Lominsa's more superstitious folk believe are burns the creature received when crawling its way through each of the seven hells before arriving on the face of Hydaelyn.

Name: Dart Frog
Description: This tiny frog found in the swamps and lakes of the Black Shroud secretes a powerful poison known to induce paralysis.

Name: Lava Toad
Description: This giant red toad, native to the swamps of Vylbrand but now found throughout Aldenard, earns its name from the red firerock which once spewed forth from the now-dormant volcano, O'Ghomoro.

Name: Light Kidney Ore
Description: A reddish ore containing large quantities of iron. Its wide availability makes it optimal for smelting in locations where purer forms of iron ore are difficult to procure, such as militia forges. This particular type of kidney ore is far more porous than the common variety, making it much easier to transport.

Name: Miser's Mythril

Name: Wyrm Obsidian
