Name: Bone Chip
Description: A broken piece of bone from some man or beast.

Name: Soiled Femur
Description: The dirty bone of a large beast. It appears to have been gnawed on.

Name: Ram Horn
Description: The coiled horn of a male sheep.

Name: Antelope Horn
Description: The thin coiled horn of an antelope buck.

Name: Aldgoat Horn
Description: The large, curved horn of an aldgoat.

Name: Mossy Horn
Description: The massive moss-covered horn of a mosshorn billygoat.

Name: Buffalo Horn
Description: The colossal horn of a giant buffalo.

Name: Ogre Horn
Description: The curved horn of a cyclopean ogre.

Name: Hippogryph Talon
Description: The sharp, curved talon of a hippogryph.

Name: Raptor Talon
Description: The hard razor-sharp claw of a raptor.

Name: Bat Fang
Description: The tiny canine of a bat.

Name: Hellhound Fang
Description: The saw-like canine of a hellhound.

Name: Wolf Fang
Description: The sharp canine of a wolf.

Name: Jackal Fang
Description: The stone-like canine of a jackal.

Name: Goobbue Fang
Description: The knife-like canine of a goobbue.

Name: Sandworm Fang
Description: The sandpaper-like canine of a giant sandworm.

Name: Biast Scales
Description: The blue-brown scales of a biast.

Name: Drake Scales
Description: The red-brown scales of a drake.

Name: Gnat Wing
Description: The light translucent wing of a gnat.

Name: Weevil Elytron
Description: The chitinous wing case of a weevil, used to protect the vilekin's paper-thin wings from damage.

Name: Ladybug Elytron
Description: The chitinous wing case of a ladybug, used to protect the vilekin's paper-thin wings from damage.

Name: Firefly Elytron
Description: The glowing wing case of a firefly, used to protect the vilekin's paper-thin wings from damage.

Name: Yellow Yarzon Leg
Description: The pronged leg of a sand yarzon.

Name: Blue Yarzon Leg
Description: The pronged leg of a bog yarzon.

Name: Green Megalocrab Shell
Description: The hard green carapace of a megalocrab.

Name: Red Megalocrab Shell
Description: The hard red carapace of a megalocrab.

Name: Adamantoise Shell
Description: The shell of a giant tortoise originally native to the island of Thavnair, but now found living throughout Eorzea.

Name: Tortoiseshell
Description: A shiny, semi-translucent material made from boiling the shell of a hawksbill tortoise.

Name: White Coral
Description:
A piece of sharp white coral native to the shallow seas all along Eorzea's coastlines.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Blue Coral
Description:
A piece of sharp blue coral native to the shallow coastal regions of the Rhotano Sea.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Red Coral
Description:
A piece of sharp red coral, rarely found in any of Eorzea's five seas.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Scallop Shell
Description: A tasty bivalve mollusk found in the cold waters of the Bloodbrine Sea. Its foot is considered a delicacy, while its shell is used for jewelry.

Name: Miter Shell
Description: Native to the Rhotano Sea, the vortex-shaped shell of this wavekin is prized by goldsmiths who use it to craft beautiful jewelry.

Name: Sunrise Tellin
Description: A tiny bivalve mollusk commonly harvested on the Pearl. Its pink shells are prized by goldsmiths who craft them into beautiful jewelry.

Name: Blacklip Oyster
Description:
A bivalve mollusk found in the warm waters of the Sea of Ash. On rare occasions, sand will become trapped inside the shell and gradually form into a black pearl.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Hedgemole Spine
Description: The remarkably lightweight, yet sharp, spine of a hedgemole.

Name: Cactuar Needle
Description: The sharp spine of a cactuar.

Name: Bone Ash
Description: The fine grey ash left over after cremating a body.

Name: Growth Formula Alpha
Description: This alchemically formulated potation accelerates the growth of foliage.

Name: Growth Formula Beta
Description: This alchemically formulated potation accelerates the growth of foliage.

Name: Growth Formula Gamma
Description: This alchemically formulated potation accelerates the growth of foliage.

Name: Growth Formula Delta
Description: This alchemically formulated potation accelerates the growth of foliage.

Name: Growth Formula Delta Concentrate
Description: This alchemically formulated potation accelerates the growth of foliage. Now in concentrate!

Name: Enchanted Copper Ink
Description: Ink fortified with copper sand to improve aetherial conductivity.

Name: Enchanted Iron Ink
Description: Ink fortified with iron sand to improve aetherial conductivity.

Name: Enchanted Silver Ink
Description: Ink fortified with silver sand to improve aetherial conductivity.

Name: Enchanted Mythril Ink
Description: Ink fortified with mythril sand to improve aetherial conductivity.

Name: Enchanted Electrum Ink
Description: Ink fortified with electrum sand to improve aetherial conductivity.

Name: Enchanted Gold Ink
Description: Ink fortified with gold sand to improve aetherial conductivity.

Name: Enchanted Rose Gold Ink
Description: Ink fortified with rose gold sand to improve aetherial conductivity.

Name: Fish Oil
Description: A clear oil extracted from the fatty tissue of various fish.

Name: Jellyfish Humours
Description: A thick, viscid oil extracted from a variety of jellyfish known as the ocean cloud.

Name: Crab Oil
Description: A fragrant oil extracted from crabs.

Name: Linseed Oil
Description: An oil made by pressing flax seeds. Used for lubrication as well as in medicines.

Name: Shark Oil
Description: An odorless oil extracted from the fatty tissue of sharks.

Name: Distilled Water
Description: The distilling process has removed all impurities from this water.

Name: Muddy Water
Description: Cloudy water taken from a stagnant source.

Name: Quicksilver
Description: Liquid metal widely utilized by alchemists in the production of firesand and by smiths in the production of alloys.

Name: Vitriol
Description: A strong, viscous acid known to corrode almost any metal.

Name: Effervescent Water
Description: Naturally sparkling water bottled at the source.

Name: Beastkin Blood
Description: The warm blood of a beast. For some unknown reason, the humours will not coagulate.

Name: Scalekin Blood
Description: The cold blood of a scaled creature. For some unknown reason, the humours will not coagulate.

Name: Spoken Blood
Description: The warm blood of a bipedal sentient. For some unknown reason, the humours will not coagulate.

Name: Viscous Secretions
Description: The viscous secretions of a slug.

Name: Acidic Secretions
Description: The acidic secretions of a sea hare.

Name: Formic Acid
Description: The pungent and corrosive secretion of an antling.

Name: Maple Sap
Description: An odorless and colorless liquid extracted from maple trees. Can be boiled down to make sweet maple sugar.

Name: Treant Sap
Description: The lifeblood of a living tree.

Name: Coal Tar
Description: An oily black liquid made from coal. Used in the coloring and waterproofing of leather and cloth, as well as in the production of firesand.

Name: Potash
Description: A mixture of plant ashes soaked in distilled water.

Name: Lime Sulphur
Description: An alchemical compound made by boiling a mixture of powdered limestone and sulphur.

Name: Animal Glue
Description: An adhesive substance created by boiling down the hides of various animals.

Name: Fish Glue
Description: An adhesive substance created by boiling down various parts of fish and other wavekin.

Name: Horn Glue
Description: An adhesive substance created by boiling down horns.

Name: Void Glue
Description: A powerful adhesive created by boiling down the flesh of various voidsent.

Name: Wing Glue
Description: An adhesive substance created by boiling down the leathery wings of bats, wyverns, and imps.

Name: Scale Glue
Description: An adhesive substance created by boiling down the hard scales of peistes and dragons.

Name: Latex
Description: The milky sap of a mature tree.

Name: Rubber
Description: Pliable rubber made from latex.

Name: Rubber Band
Description: A pliant, durable band made from rubber.

Name: Clear Glass Lens
Description: A hard flat lens made of uncolored glass.

Name: Potter's Clay
Description: Thick, sticky clay used to make cups, pots, and jars.

Name: Humus
Description: Nutrient-rich soil consisting of decaying leaves.

Name: Beeswax
Description: Fragrant yellow wax created by melting down beehives.

Name: Beehive Chip
Description: The nest of a honeybee, comprised of several hundred hexagonal chambers made of a waxy substance secreted by the vilekin.

Name: Lanolin
Description: A waxy yellow substance extracted from sheep wool and used in ointments as well as to prevent rusting.

Name: Rock Salt
Description: A large chunk of naturally occurring salt crystals. It is often ground into fine grains before being used to flavor and preserve food.

Name: Cinnabar
Description: This red mineral is used to create quicksilver, as well as potent sedatives.

Name: Chalk
Description: A soft, white powder made by heating seashells in a furnace.

Name: Saltpeter
Description: A translucent crystalline substance often used in making glass, firesand, and dyes.

Name: Natron
Description: A white powder used in alchemy as a deodorizer and leavening agent.

Name: Silex
Description: A pure white sand made up of finely ground silica.

Name: Alumen
Description: A white mineral used by leatherworkers to tan animal hides. It also has deodorizing properties.

Name: Black Alumen
Description: A darker variety of the mineral used by leatherworkers to tan animal hides. It lacks the deodorizing properties of its lighter counterpart.

Name: Grenade Ash
Description: Dark grey ash produced by the internal combustions of a grenade.

Name: Brimstone
Description: A natural sulphur occurring in volcanic regions around Eorzea.

Name: Bomb Ash
Description: Grey ash produced by the internal combustions of a bomb.

Name: Resin
Description: The viscous sap of a coniferous tree. It can be used to not only treat and strengthen wood and leather, but also as a powerful adhesive.

Name: Coke
Description: A hot-burning fuel created by destructively distilling raw coal.

Name: Animal Fat
Description: The foul-smelling fatty tissue of a beastkin.

Name: Hardened Sap
Description: A partially congealed ball of sticky tree sap.

Name: Garlean Rubber
Description: A lightweight rubber far more elastic than the common variety found in Eorzea.

Name: Tinolqa Mistletoe
Description: A variety of parasitic plant that is commonly found growing on trees in the Black Shroud.

Name: Matron's Mistletoe
Description: This variety of parasitic plant is named after the goddess Nophica as it appears to embrace the trees on which it grows.

Name: Mistletoe
Description: A poisonous, parasitic plant which survives by attaching itself to other larger plants. It is often gathered and put on display during regional winter festivals.

Name: Thavnairian Mistletoe
Description: A variety of parasitic plant that is commonly found growing on the stout acacia trees of Thavnair. The inhabitants of Thavnair's capital city of Radz-at-Han have a strange custom that states if two people meet underneath a sprig of mistletoe, they must each give the other one of their shoes.

Name: Yellow Ginseng
Description: A Far Eastern root used in various medicines.

Name: Lavender
Description: A fragrant purple flower found growing in coastal areas throughout Aldenard.

Name: Carnation
Description: A beautiful red flower often planted in public gardens or picked and put on display in houses. Large plantations of carnations can be found in and around Gridania.

Name: Belladonna
Description: A beautiful flower common in Aldenard from which a potent sleeping poison can be extracted.

Name: Chamomile
Description: A fragrant yellow flower found growing throughout Vylbrand.

Name: Mandrake
Description: The man-shaped root of a wild plant commonly found growing on Vylbrand.

Name: Lamp Marimo
Description:
A rare type of luminescent moss found on the bottom of lakes and in caves. Slight currents cause the moss to form into a ball as it grows.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Trillium
Description: A beautiful, white, tripetaloid flower.

Name: Trillium Bulb
Description: If planted and tended with loving care, this bulb should grow into a lovely trillium plant.

Name: Vampire Plant
Description: This rare variety of parasitic plant is known to suck the lifeblood from all flora with which it comes in contact.

Name: Red Landtrap Leaf
Description: The thin, twitching leaf of a roseling.

Name: Blue Landtrap Leaf
Description: The thin, twitching leaf of a flytrap.

Name: Puk Wing
Description: The membranous wing of a puk. Often carried by young Lalafellin girls as a good-luck charm.

Name: Bat Wing
Description: The leathery wing of a bat.

Name: Imp Wing
Description: The membranous wing of an imp.

Name: Ahriman Wing
Description: The large, veined wing of an ahriman.

Name: Morbol Vine
Description: The squirming vine of a morbol.

Name: Ochu Vine
Description: The thick, leathery vine of an ochu.

Name: Jellyfish Cnida
Description: The poison-producing spines of a jellyfish.

Name: Jellyfish Umbrella
Description: The soft, gelatinous body of a jellyfish.

Name: Pudding Flesh
Description: A foul-smelling, gelatinous mass taken from a pudding.

Name: Moor Leech
Description: A bloodsucking leech. Used by barbers, chirurgeons, and chymists alike to drain the tainted humours from an ill patient.

Name: Grass Viper
Description: A deadly snake common in grasslands across Eorzea. Its venom is known to contain a potent bleeding poison.

Name: Bee Basket
Description: A tightly knitted wicker basket filled with a swarm of agitated honeybees.

Name: Tarantula
Description: A deadly forest spider from whose venom can be extracted a potent silencing poison.

Name: White Scorpion
Description: A rare albino scorpion, thought to be an ill omen by the early Dunesfolk tribes.

Name: Black Scorpion
Description: A deadly desert vilekin from whose venom can be extracted a potent paralyzing poison.

Name: Bloody Lance Head
Description: A blood-encrusted lance head found lodged in the thick hide of a great buffalo.

Name: Bloody Bardiche Head
Description: A blood-encrusted bardiche head found lodged in the thick hide of a great buffalo.

Name: Bloody Cesti Covers
Description: Blood-soaked cesti covers retrieved from the site of a gruesome battle.

Name: Bloody Bow Rim
Description: A bloodstained wooden bow rim retrieved from the site of a gruesome battle.

Name: Bloody Grimoire Binding
Description: A blood-soaked leather grimoire cover retrieved from the site of a gruesome battle.

Name: Mailbreaker Blade
Description: A sturdy darksteel blade used in the creation of mailbreakers.

Name: Avenger Grips
Description: A pair of tempered darksteel grips used in making avengers.

Name: Rampager Head
Description: A double-edged darksteel axe head used in the creation of rampagers.

Name: Obelisk Head
Description: A narrow darksteel head used in the creation of obelisks.

Name: Sarnga Limb
Description: A flexible bow limb carved from spruce used in the creation of Sarnga.

Name: Suspended Trillium Flower
Description: A trillium flower, preserved via alchemical agents. Used in the creation of trillium canes.

Name: Astrolabe Clinometer
Description: An astrally charged clinometer used in the creation of astrolabes.

Name: Vanya Silk Hat Lining
Description: A large piece of vanya silk cloth used to line a hat.

Name: Vanya Silk Robe Lining
Description: A large piece of vanya silk cloth used to line a robe.

Name: Vanya Silk Glove Lining
Description: A large piece of vanya silk cloth used to line gloves.

Name: Vanya Silk Crakow Lining
Description: A large piece of vanya silk cloth used to line crakows.

Name: Gryphonskin Shoulder Guards
Description: Pieces of hippogryph leather padding used on body armor to provide extra protection to the shoulders.

Name: Gryphonskin Shin Guards
Description: Pieces of hippogryph leather padding used on foot armor to provide extra protection to the shins.

Name: Gryphonskin Elbow Pads
Description: Pieces of hippogryph leather padding used on hand armor to provide extra protection to the elbows.

Name: Gryphonskin Knee Pads
Description: Pieces of hippogryph leather padding used on leg armor to provide extra protection to the knees.

Name: Darksteel Breastplate
Description: A darksteel breastplate, usually coupled with a matching backplate and worn over another piece of body armor, completing the set.

Name: Darksteel Gauntlet Plates
Description: A pair of darksteel plates used in the construction of gauntlets.

Name: Darksteel Couters
Description: Darksteel elbowguards used in the creation of heavy armor.

Name: Rose Gold Clasps
Description: Tiny rose gold clasps used to secure earrings to the wearer's ear.

Name: Rubber Sole
Description: Durable, shock-absorbent soles made from rubber.

Name: Tiny Crown
Description: A tiny golden crown used to decorate pastries.

Name: Black Odoshi Cord
Description: A thick, raven black cord used to securely fasten a kabuto to its wearer's head.

Name: Blue Odoshi Cord
Description: A thick, woad-blue cord used to securely fasten a kabuto to its wearer's head.

Name: Kabuto Mask
Description: Thin iron plating attached to a kabuto to not only protect the wearer's face, but to instill fear in all who behold the frightening visage it creates.

Name: Grade 1 Dark Matter
Description:
It has recently been discovered that this substance of unknown origin has the faculty to assimilate with other forms of matter, effectively restoring them to their original condition. This specific grade of dark matter has been shown to bond best with simple items crafted from common materials.

[Used to repair equipment for levels 1-10.]

Name: Grade 2 Dark Matter
Description:
It has recently been discovered that this substance of unknown origin has the faculty to assimilate with other forms of matter, effectively restoring them to their original condition. This specific grade of dark matter has been shown to bond best with relatively simple items crafted from common materials.

[Used to repair equipment for levels 1-20.]

Name: Grade 3 Dark Matter
Description:
It has recently been discovered that this substance of unknown origin has the faculty to assimilate with other forms of matter, effectively restoring them to their original condition. This specific grade of dark matter has been shown to bond best with items crafted from standard materials.

[Used to repair equipment for levels 1-30.]

Name: Grade 4 Dark Matter
Description:
It has recently been discovered that this substance of unknown origin has the faculty to assimilate with other forms of matter, effectively restoring them to their original condition. This specific grade of dark matter has been shown to bond best with expertly crafted items made from quality materials.

[Used to repair equipment for levels 1-40.]

Name: Grade 5 Dark Matter
Description:
It has recently been discovered that this substance of unknown origin has the faculty to assimilate with other forms of matter, effectively restoring them to their original condition. This specific grade of dark matter has been shown to bond best with precisely crafted items made from high-quality materials.

[Used to repair equipment for levels 1-50.]

Name: Grade 1 Carbonized Matter
Description: Naturally occurring coal infused with dark matter.

These fingers are then taken and blessed by anointed priests of Oschon, the Wanderer. It is thought that, when carried on a journey, these fingers will point out the safest routes, and are therefore cherished by caravan drivers and traveling merchants throughout Eorzea.

Description: Small, bite-sized victuals fortified with a blend of potent distillates. Increases the attack power and puts hair on the chests of all militia members who consume one.

Name: Musked Rations
Description: Small, bite-sized victuals fortified with a blend of pungent beastkin musk. Distracts enemies, effectively lowering the enmity of all militia laborers who consume one.

Name: Blessed Rations
Description: Small, bite-sized victuals fortified with a sprinkle of holy water blessed by an anointed priestess of the Matron. Grants the effect of Regen to all militia members who consume one.

Name: Pavis Parts (Reinforcement)
Description: A set of wooden planks and metal plates used to construct reinforced pavises.

Name: Pavis Parts (Spikes)
Description: A set of wooden planks and metal spikes used to construct spiked pavises.

Description: A set of wooden planks and pungent beastkin musk used to construct musked pavises.

Name: Pavis Parts (Blessing)

Description: A set of wooden limbs and metal plates used to construct reinforced decoys.

Description: A set of wooden limbs and metal spikes used to construct spiked decoys.

Description: A set of wooden limbs and pungent beastkin musk used to construct musked decoys.

Name: Decoy Parts (Blessing)
Description: A set of sanctified wooden limbs used to construct blessed decoys.

Name: Fortifying Philter
Description: A concentrated potion used to fortify the constitution.

Name: Spiking Philter
Description: A concentrated distillate used to stimulate the nerves.

Name: Musky Philter
Description: A pungent blend of musk from several different varieties of beastkin.

Name: Sanctifying Philter
Description: Holy water blessed by an anointed priestess of the Matron.

Description: A small, smoothed stone featuring in its center a single carved symbol representing Byregot, the Builder.

Description: A small, smoothed stone featuring in its center a single carved symbol representing Rhalgr, the Destroyer.

Description: A small, smoothed stone featuring in its center a single carved symbol representing Menphina, the Lover.

Name: Rope
Description: Rope made by spinning together several stalks of wheat straw.

Name: Brass Dish
Description: A serving dish made of solid brass.

Name: Silver Goblet
Description: A wine goblet made of solid silver.

Name: Tallow Candle
Description: A stout candle made from sheep fat.

Name: Beeswax Candle
Description: A stout candle made from hardened beeswax.

Name: Goblin Mask
Description: A leather mask that filters out bad odors, as well as most poisonous gases. Due to its odd shape, only goblins can wear it.

Name: Chocobo Whistle
Description: A small hand-carved whistle that emits a unique, high-pitched tone discernible only by a chocobo trained from birth to recognize and respond to the sound. Use to summon your personal chocobo.

Name: Goobbue Horn
Description: This polished horn emits a deep, bellowing tone that creates subtle vibrations in the land that carry for malms. While undetectable by most, goobbues can sense these mini tremblors which they often mistake for mating calls.

Name: Cherry Bomb
Description:
Summons a miniature recreation of a voidsent bomb, created via the thaumaturgical rendering of umbrally charged aetherial energy. Guaranteed never to self-destruct, or your gil back.

Use item to acquire the cherry bomb minion.

Name: Mammet #001
Description:
Summons a fully operational clockwork puppet built in a joint effort by the Alchemists' and Goldsmiths' Guilds.

Use item to acquire the mammet #001 minion.

Name: Wayward Hatchling
Description:
Summons a lost chocobo chick. Until he finds his real mother, you'll have to suffice.

Use item to acquire the wayward hatchling minion.

Name: Legacy Chocobo Whistle
Description: A small hand-carved whistle that emits a unique, high-pitched tone discernible only by a chocobo trained from birth to recognize and respond to the sound. Use to summon your legacy chocobo.

Name: Coeurl Bell
Description: A tiny brass bell used to summon your personal coeurl mount, trained on the Pearl by the last of the legendary coeurltamers.

Name: Armor Identification Key
Description: A thin, rectangular piece of what appears to be cermet. Placing it near your suit of magitek armor will magically bring the machine to life.

Name: Voidal Resonator
Description: A metal tuning fork that, when struck, emits a low tone which opens a temporary rift in the void, allowing your personal ahrimanand your personal ahriman onlyto pass through to this plane.

Name: Lapis Cross
Description: This medal featuring two crossed oars is awarded to those enlisted soldiers who have shown exceptional performance in service to the Maelstrom.

Name: Aquamarine Cross
Description: This medal featuring two crossed oars is awarded to those petty officers who have shown exceptional performance in service to the Maelstrom.

Name: Emerald Leaf
Description: This medal featuring a single green leaf is awarded to those enlisted soldiers who have shown exceptional performance in service to the Order of the Twin Adder.

Name: Emerald Bough
Description: This medal featuring a leafed branch is awarded to those petty officers who have shown exceptional performance in service to the Order of the Twin Adder.

Name: Gold Scales
Description: This medal featuring a solid-gold set of scales is awarded to those enlisted soldiers who have shown exceptional performance in service to the Immortal Flames.

Name: Platinum Scales
Description: This medal featuring a solid platinum set of scales is awarded to those petty officers who have shown exceptional performance in service to the Immortal Flames.

Name: On the Properties of Beastmen
Description: A text distributed by the Grand Companies of Eorzea explaining the various physical and physiological properties of the realm's beastmen.

Name: Storm Chocobo Issuance
Description: Present this deed to the Maelstrom company stables to receive your own chocobo.

Name: Serpent Chocobo Issuance
Description: Present this deed to the Order of the Twin Adder company stables to receive your own chocobo.

Name: Flame Chocobo Issuance

Name: Behemoth Barding

Name: Flyer Shaffron

Name: The Howling Spirit
Description: Cannot equip gear to head, hands, legs, or feet.

Name: The Wailing Spirit
Description: Cannot equip gear to head, hands, legs, or feet.

Name: Cordial
Description: A sweet, fermented concoction that instantly restores 300 GP (350 if the cordial is of high quality).

Name: Grilled Warmwater Trout
Description:
A fresh warmwater trout sprinkled with rock salt and grilled to perfection.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Grilled Raincaller
Description:
A fresh raincaller sprinkled with rock salt and grilled over an open flame.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Dagger Soup
Description:
After a light clear broth is taken from a freshly caught Navigator's dagger, the meat is removed from the bones and ground up into a paste. The paste is then rolled into tiny balls and returned to the broth, creating a hearty soup.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Noble Grapes
Description: Lowland grapes crossbred over generations to produce maximum sweetness. Their bitter skin makes them unsuitable for eating off the vine, and they are better consumed as juice or wine.

Name: Mirror Apple
Description:
A sweet yet sour variety of apples native to Coerthas. When polished, the skins become so shiny it is said one can see their own reflection in them.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Honey Lemon
Description:
This rare type of lemon native to the continent of Othard is so sweet, it can be eaten raw.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Dzemael Tomato
Description: A rare crossbreed of ruby tomato developed and perfected by House Dzemael botanists.

Name: Night Milk
Description:
Rich and creamy buffalo milk harvested immediately before the beast falls asleep.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Coeurl Meat
Description: A bloody strip of extra-lean coeurl meat.

Name: Cooking Sherry
Description: Fine Lominsan white wine fortified with grape spirit to increase alcohol content and improve its aroma, making it perfect for a variety of culinary dishes.

Name: Volcanic Rock Salt
Description: The red hue of this rock salt is said to come from the volcanic soil of O'Ghomoro.

Name: Filtered Water
Description: Water purified using a complex method of passing it through several layers of charcoal and rock.

Name: Voidsent Blood
Description: The bubbling blood of a voidsent. For some unknown reason, the humours will not coagulate.

Name: Behemoth Horn
Description: This giant sable horn is prized by furniture makers across the realm.

Name: Ifrit's Horn
Description: Torn from the head of the Lord of the Inferno himself, this night-black horn is still hot to the touch.

Name: Inferno Horn
Description: Torn from the head of the Lord of the Inferno himself, this night-black horn pulses with uncontrollably powerful fire-aspected energies.

Name: Garuda's Feather
Description: Ripped from the wings of the Lady of the Vortex herself, this feather generates a powerful gust each time it is waved.

Name: Vortex Feather
Description: Ripped from the wings of the Lady of the Vortex herself, this feather pulses with uncontrollably powerful wind-aspected energies.

Name: Titan's Heart
Description: Drawn forth from the chest of the Lord of Crags himself, this small stone weighs more than a grown Lalafell.

Name: Crag Heart
Description: Drawn forth from the chest of the Lord of Crags himself, this small stone pulses with uncontrollably powerful earth-aspected energies.

Name: Odin's Mantle
Description: Removed from the back of the elder primal Odin, this heavy mantle is fit for a god.

Name: Cait Sith Doll
Description:
The ever-extended tail helps the kitten keep his balance.

Use item to acquire the Cait Sith doll minion.

Name: Baby Behemoth
Description:
We can only hope his mother doesn't come looking for him.

Use item to acquire the baby behemoth minion.

Name: Mammet #003L
Description:
A fully operational clockwork puppet built for the Maelstrom.

Use item to acquire the mammet #003L minion.

Name: Mammet #003G
Description:
A fully operational clockwork puppet built for the Order of the Twin Adder.

Use item to acquire the mammet #003G minion.

Name: Mammet #003U
Description:
A fully operational clockwork puppet built for the Immortal Flames.

Use item to acquire the mammet #003U minion.

Name: Storm Hatchling
Description:
Not more than a fortnight out of the shell, but his blood already runs Maelstrom red. Till sea swallows all!

Use item to acquire the storm hatchling minion.

Name: Serpent Hatchling
Description:
Not more than a fortnight out of the shell, but his blood already runs Twin Adder yellow.

Use item to acquire the serpent hatchling minion.

Name: Flame Hatchling
Description:
Not more than a fortnight out of the shell, but his blood already runs Immortal Flames black.

Use item to acquire the flame hatchling minion.

Name: Morbol Seedling
Description:
For the nonce, his breath is the worst of your problems.

Use item to acquire the morbol seedling minion.

Name: Tiny Rat
Description:
He may infest your granaries, and he may carry the plague, but he's simply too adorable to condemn to the life-ending jaws of a metal trap.

Use item to acquire the tiny rat minion.

Name: Baby Bun
Description:
Tastes great on salads and in stews.

Use item to acquire the baby bun minion.

Name: Chigoe Larva
Description:
This tiny vilekin takes the blood pact with his master very seriously.

Use item to acquire the chigoe larva minion.

Name: Bluebird
Description:
Known to retroactively bring good fortune to those who have already experienced good fortune.

Use item to acquire the bluebird minion.

Name: Wide-eyed Fawn
Description:
His mother was either lost in a terrible hunting accident...or perhaps is just lost.

Use item to acquire the wide-eyed fawn minion.

Name: Infant Imp
Description:
Hopes that one day, he will rule the seven hells. But for now, your backside will do.

Use item to acquire the infant imp minion.

Name: Coeurl Kitten
Description:
It will still be several summers before his trademark whiskers grow out.

Use item to acquire the coeurl kitten minion.

Name: Black Coeurl
Description:
Beware, for if one should cross your path, you will experience seven years of...AWWWWWW.

Use item to acquire the black coeurl minion.

Name: Gravel Golem
Description:
Only you stand between it and a hard place.

Use item to acquire the gravel golem minion.

Name: Wind-up Tonberry
Description:
Now with 100% less rancor.

Use item to acquire the wind-up tonberry minion.

Name: Tiny Tortoise
Description:
Will not carry you to an underwater kingdom if you ride on its back.

Use item to acquire the tiny tortoise minion.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Baby Raptor
Description:
Luckily for you, his teeth haven't all grown in...yet.

Use item to acquire the baby raptor minion.

Name: Baby Bat
Description:
Has yet to acquire a taste for blood.

Use item to acquire the baby bat minion.

Name: Tiny Bulb
Description:
Some questions, such as why this bulb can walk, are best left unanswered.

Use item to acquire the tiny bulb minion.

Name: Dust Bunny
Description:
Despite the striking similarities, spriggans are not related to rabbits. But they have been known to eat them.

Use item to acquire the dust bunny minion.

Name: Wind-up Dullahan
Description:
Warning: may contain sharp parts.

Use item to acquire the wind-up dullahan minion.

Name: Gigantpole
Description:
Yes, it can survive for hours on end without any water, and yes, it can fly. Your argument is invalid.

Use item to acquire the gigantpole minion.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Pudgy Puk
Description:
Don't ask what he has eaten to grow so plump.

Use item to acquire the pudgy puk minion.

Name: Buffalo Calf
Description:
Milk-fed until tender and juicy. Not that anyone would ever think of eating him.

Use item to acquire the buffalo calf minion.

Name: Cactuar Cutting
Description:
Take care not to suffer 1,000 points of damage...to your heart.

Use item to acquire the cactuar cutting minion.

Name: Smallshell
Description:
The mere sight of this wee wavekin may cause severe psychological trauma to those who spent years of their lives on faraway shores culling his relatives.

Use item to acquire the smallshell minion.

Name: Wolf Pup
Description:
Idolizes one Gaius van Baelsar for obvious reasons.

Use item to acquire the wolf pup minion.

Name: Beady Eye
Description:
That feeling you get sometimes that you are being watched? More often than not it is him.

Use item to acquire the beady eye minion.

Name: Fledgling Dodo
Description:
Properly trained not to eructate, regurgitate, expectorate, or flatulate.

Use item to acquire the fledgling dodo minion.

Name: Coblyn Larva
Description:
Too dangerous to allow to grow any larger...too adorable to condemn to the furnace.

Use item to acquire the coblyn larva minion.

Name: Wind-up Aldgoat
Description:
No aldgoats were harmed in the making of this automaton.

Use item to acquire the wind-up aldgoat minion.

Name: Fledgling Apkallu
Description:
Will follow you until you give him a fish. Will continue to follow you after being given a fish.

Use item to acquire the fledgling apkallu minion.

Name: Goobbue Sproutling
Description:
Has been known to attack kittens for no apparent reason.

Use item to acquire the goobbue sproutling minion.

Name: Bite-sized Pudding
Description:
Though seemingly delicious, this spoonful of slime is not intended for consumption.

Use item to acquire the bite-sized pudding minion.

Name: Model Vanguard
Description:
An exact 1:9 scale replica of a ceruleum-powered magitek vanguard (imperial pilot action figure not included).

Use item to acquire the model vanguard minion.

Name: Demon Brick
Description:
We are all better off not knowing what arcane magicks animate this ordinary stone block.

Use item to acquire the demon brick minion.

Name: Mini Mole
Description:
When not dining on a protein-rich diet of earthworms and grubs, he dreams of making mountains.

Use item to acquire the mini mole minion.

Name: Tender Lamb
Description:
Mint jelly optional.

Use item to acquire the tender lamb minion.

Name: Slime Puddle
Description:
Fun for the whole family.

Use item to acquire the slime puddle minion.

Name: Kidragora
Description:
Even in space, everyone can hear this seedkin scream.

Use item to acquire the kidragora minion.

Name: Wind-up Goblin
Description:
Even this automaton's gobbiebag is bigger than yours.

Use item to acquire the wind-up goblin minion.

Name: Wind-up Sylph
Description:
If he could speak, it would be in the third person.

Use item to acquire the wind-up sylph minion.

Name: Wind-up Cursor
Description:
Modeled after the ivory glove of Oschon, the Wanderer, does this clockwork hand follow you...or guide you?

Use item to acquire the wind-up cursor minion.

Name: Wind-up Airship
Description:
A fully operational model of the legendary vessel, the Invincible.

Use item to acquire the wind-up airship minion.

Name: Wind-up Qiqirn
Description:
As adorable as the real thing, without the ratty odor.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Qiqirn minion.

Name: Black Chocobo Chick
Description:
Rumors about her being able to fly are completely unfounded...or are they?

Use item to acquire the black chocobo chick minion.

Name: Wind-up Dalamud
Description:
Do not attempt to pry open under any circumstances.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Dalamud minion.

Name: Wind-up Shantotto
Description:
If you fail to treat her right,
she will set your pants alight.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Shantotto minion.

Name: ADS Illuminant

Name: Fantasia
Description:
Legend states that any who drink this mysterious liquid before lying down for the evening will awaken a new man (or woman).

Grants you an opportunity to edit your appearance in the character creation screen upon your next login. Once logged in with a new appearance, you may continue to re-edit within a set period of time.

Name: Snowman Suit
Description: Cannot equip gear to legs and feet.

Name: Wind-up Amalj'aa
Description:
What is burnt may never burn, but rises again, harder and stronger.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Amalj'aa minion.

Name: Wind-up Brickman
Description:
The brickman gets up and looks over as if it wants to join the party!

Use item to acquire the wind-up brickman minion.

Name: Wind-up Edvya
Description:
Sometimes moonlights as a miller girl, much to her father the sultan's chagrin.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Edvya minion.

Name: Minion of Light
Description:
When Darkness veils the world, three Minions of Light shall come.
Unknown prophet

Use item to acquire a Minion of Light.

Name: Wind-up Leader
Description:
A leader who will follow you unquestioninglyfor coin and country; for serenity, purity, sanctitytill sea swallows all.

Use item to acquire the wind-up leader minion.

Name: Princely Hatchling
Description:
The chocobo who would be king.

Use item to acquire the princely hatchling minion.

Name: Behemoth Warhorn
Description: This imposing horn emits a thunderous tone that summons your mighty behemoth.

Name: Drake Horn
Description: This horn of bone emits a shrill tone that summons your cavalry drake, trained by the Brotherhood of Ash.

Name: Laurel Goobbue Horn
Description: This polished horn emits a deep, bellowing tone that creates subtle vibrations in the land that carry for malms. While undetectable by most, goobbues can sense these mini tremblors which they often mistake for mating calls. Use to summon your laurel goobbue.

Name: Gilded Armor Identification Key

Name: Sovereign Barding
Description: A suit of chocobo armor designed to resemble that of a chocobo king of legend.

Description: This peculiar contraption creates illusions by weaving together myriad shades of light. Produces the left side of a heart.

Name: Prismatic Heart (Right)
Description: This peculiar contraption creates illusions by weaving together myriad shades of light. Produces the right side of a heart.

Name: Bitter Heart Chocolate
Description: A heart-shaped morsel of bitter chocolate. Suitable for decorative purposes.

Name: Pure Heart Chocolate
Description: A heart-shaped morsel of sweet chocolate. Suitable for decorative purposes.

Name: Eternal Ice
Description: A crystalline agglomeration infused with the power of ice, said to grant snowmen temporary life.

Description:
A fiery choker worn by members of the dreaded Flamefang Amalj'aa.

Only for use in Amalj'aa society quests.

An identification key for a prototype suit of magitek armor. It is damaged beyond use.

Only for use in sylph society quests.

Name: Kafre's Tusk
Description:
A bloody tusk taken from the savage Kafre.

Only for use in sylph society quests.

Name: Carbuncle Garden Bench
Description: A fluffy and faithful garden bench designed in a Carbuncle motif.

Name: Riviera Striking Dummy
Description:
A striking dummy designed in the riviera fashion.

Up to three dummies may be placed in a single estate, regardless of type.

Name: Oasis Striking Dummy
Description:
A striking dummy designed in the oasis fashion.

Up to three dummies may be placed in a single estate, regardless of type.

Name: Glade Striking Dummy
Description:
A striking dummy designed in the glade fashion.

Up to three dummies may be placed in a single estate, regardless of type.

Name: Alps Striking Dummy
Description:
A striking dummy designed in the alps fashion.

Up to three dummies may be placed in a single estate, regardless of type.

Name: Sahagin Living Lamp
Description: Any Sahagin would feel at home by the gentle glow of this living lamp.

Name: Sahagin Hanging Larder
Description: The Sahagin typically hang their foodstuff on this treelike coral formation, the better to prevent its being swept away by the sea.

Name: Ixali Shelter
Description: A small and cozy shelter of Ixali design.

Name: Ixali Banner
Description: The mere sight of this banner instills any Ixal with courage.

Name: Automaton Digger
Description: An ingenious mining automaton created by the kobolds.

Name: Kobold Furnace
Description: A furnace made by the kobolds for alchemical purposes.

Name: Round Garden Patch
Description:
A garden patch with room for four beds.

Small, medium, and large estates can hold 1, 2, and 3 garden patches, respectively.

Name: Oblong Garden Patch
Description:
A garden patch with room for six beds.

Small, medium, and large estates can hold 1, 2, and 3 garden patches, respectively.

Name: Deluxe Garden Patch
Description:
A garden patch with room for eight beds. Comes complete with its own scarecrow.

Small, medium, and large estates can hold 1, 2, and 3 garden patches, respectively.

Name: Country Interior Wall
Description: An interior wall designed in the country fashion.

Name: Stone Interior Wall
Description: An interior wall of smooth-cut stone.

Name: Storm Interior Wall
Description: Display your patriotic zeal with this Maelstrom-themed interior wall.

Name: Serpent Interior Wall
Description: Display your patriotic zeal with this Twin Adder-themed interior wall.

Name: Flame Interior Wall
Description: Display your patriotic zeal with this Immortal Flames-themed interior wall.

Description: An interior wall made from tiles of various shades of blue.

Name: Metal Interior Wall

Name: Arbor Interior Wall
Description: An interior wall that puts you in an idyllic arbor setting.

Name: Chocobo Interior Wall
Description: An interior wall for all the chocobo-lovers out there.

Name: Moogle Interior Wall
Description: An interior wall for all the moogle-lovers out there.

Name: Tonberry Chandelier
Description: A rancorous chandelier designed in a tonberry king motif.

Name: Sultana Portrait
Description: A commissioned portrait of Nanamo Ul Namo entitled Heart of Ul'dah. Original artist unknown.

Name: Material Supplier Permit
Description:
This permit allows the hiring of material suppliers on the estate.

Private chambers (apartments), cottages, houses, and mansions can host 4, 6, 8, and 10 vendors, respectively.

Name: Junkmonger Permit
Description:
This permit allows the hiring of junkmongers on the estate.

Private chambers (apartments), cottages, houses, and mansions can host 4, 6, 8, and 10 vendors, respectively.

Name: Mender Permit
Description:
This permit allows the hiring of menders on the estate.

Private chambers (apartments), cottages, houses, and mansions can host 4, 6, 8, and 10 vendors, respectively.

Name: White Raven Armor Fragment
Description: A fragment of the armor worn by Legatus Nael van Darnus of the Garlean Empire.

Name: Stone Vigil Lumber
Description: Sturdy lumber scavenged from the Stone Vigil.

Name: Leviathan's Barb
Description: Wrenched from the maw of the Lord of the Whorl himself, this razor-sharp barb is constantly slick with brine.

Name: Barb of the Whorl
Description: Wrenched from the maw of the Lord of the Whorl himself, this razor-sharp barb churns with the unbridled power of the sea.

Name: Kingly Whisker
Description: This whisker, imbued with the majesty of all moogle monarchs past and present, once belonged to Good King Moggle Mog, Twelfth of His Name.

Name: Egg Harness
Description: An egg-themed chocobo harness created in celebration of Hatching-tide.

Name: Barding of Light
Description: A suit of chocobo armor designed to resemble a legendary Warrior of the Light.

Name: Tidal Barding
Description: A suit of chocobo armor designed to resemble Leviathan, the Lord of the Whorl.

Name: Fat Chocobo Whistle
Description: A small hand-carved whistle that emits a unique, high-pitched tone recognized by your fat chocobo as a feeding call.

Name: Elbst Horn
Description: This horn of bone emits a sonorous tone that summons your cavalry elbst, raised from an egg by Pahh of Novv's Clutch.

Name: Bomb Palanquin Horn
Description: This horn of bone emits a deep tone that summons a bevy of bombs who will bear you in comfort upon a hovering palanquin.

Name: Wind-up Kobold
Description:
With you, she will koboldly go where no kobold has gone before.

Use item to acquire the wind-up kobold minion.

Name: Wind-up Sahagin
Description:
He's got a trident and he's not afraid to use it.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Sahagin minion.

Name: Wind-up Moogle
Description:
With its button nose and fluffy pom, this clockwork moogle will make you the envy of all your friends.

Use item to acquire the wind-up moogle minion.

Name: Plush Cushion
Description:
Ever ready to shield your buttocks from the hardest of places.

Use item to acquire the plush cushion minion.

Name: Wind-up Sun
Description:
With this minion, the sun will never go down on you. /poke to adjust elevation.

Use item to acquire the wind-up sun minion.

Name: Wind-up Odin
Description:
Guaranteed not to wipe out your entire party in one fell stroke.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Odin minion.

Name: Wind-up Warrior of Light
Description:
Wheresoever thou goest, so too shall Light follow.
Ancient benediction

Use item to acquire the wind-up Warrior of Light minion.

Name: Wind-up Bahamut
Description:
This mysterious being emerged from within a broken wind-up Dalamud, and is nigh inseparable from its former prison.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Bahamut minion.

Name: Baby Opo-opo
Description:
The only thing he loves more than you is a juicy sprite apple.

Use item to acquire the baby opo-opo minion.

Name: Zu Hatchling
Description:
This newborn zu has yet to exhibit aggressive or territorial behavior, but when it gets bigger...

Use item to acquire the zu hatchling minion.

Name: Minute Mindflayer
Description:
This mindflayer young delights folk with its cuteness even as it fills them with an inexplicable sense of dread.

Use item to acquire the minute mindflayer minion.

Name: Tight-beaked Parrot
Description:
For best results, summon while wearing an eyepatch.

Use item to acquire the tight-beaked parrot minion.

Name: Magic Broom
Description:
For safety reasons, do not fall asleep while it is at work.

Use item to acquire the magic broom minion.

Name: Aetheryte Ticket
Description:
Good for a single journey through the aetheryte network.

[Collected in place of gil when using the Teleport command.]

Name: Steamed Catfish
Description:
A hearty dish made by steaming a whole giant catfish in wine and spices.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Popoto Pancakes
Description:
A pancake dish made of ground Dalamud popotoes, served with pured mirror apples.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Roast Canard
Description:
A canard breast roasted to perfection, drowned in a sweet and sour sauce made from two kinds of oranges.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Sachertorte
Description:
A divinely rich chocolate cake that features a fruity counterpoint by way of an apricot jam layer.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Chilled Popoto Soup
Description:
A refreshing soup made by blending popoto, leek, and sweet cream to a smooth consistency.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Spinach Quiche
Description:
A savory pastry made by baking a mixture of sauted spinach and cream cheese within pie dough.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Sands of Time
Description: Born of Allagan ingenuity, this peculiar sand is said to possess the power to turn back time. However, advances in crafting technology have rendered it obsolete.

Name: Oil of Time
Description: Born of Allagan ingenuity, this peculiar oil is said to possess the power to turn back time. However, advances in crafting technology have rendered it obsolete.

Name: Mossy Stone Sword
Description: A sword crafted from giantsgall, a type of stone found on Thavnair. It is so covered in moss as to be rendered unusable.

Name: Mossy Stone Axe
Description: An axe crafted from giantsgall, a type of stone found on Thavnair. It is so covered in moss as to be rendered unusable.

Name: Mossy Stone Claws
Description: A pair of claws crafted from giantsgall, a type of stone found on Thavnair. It is so covered in moss as to be rendered unusable.

Name: Mossy Stone Spear
Description: A spear crafted from giantsgall, a type of stone found on Thavnair. It is so covered in moss as to be rendered unusable.

Name: Mossy Stone Bow
Description: A bow crafted from giantsgall, a type of stone found on Thavnair. It is so covered in moss as to be rendered unusable.

Name: Mossy Stone Staff
Description: A staff crafted from giantsgall, a type of stone found on Thavnair. It is so covered in moss as to be rendered unusable.

Name: Mossy Stone Rod
Description: A rod crafted from giantsgall, a type of stone found on Thavnair. It is so covered in moss as to be rendered unusable.

Name: Weathered Tome
Description: This weathered tome appears to have been a magical grimoire in a previous life.

Name: Faded Tome
Description: This faded tome appears to have been a magical grimoire in a previous life.

Name: Ferberite
Description: A jet black mineral with alluring luster.

Name: Native Gold
Description: A high-purity, naturally occurring nugget of gold.

Name: Scarlet Sap
Description: Its color reminiscent of blood, this sap is used in the working of aged lumber.

Name: Shroud Tea Leaves
Description: Picked from plants that grow wild in the Black Shroud, these leaves are extremely bitter and are not ideal for brewing tea.

Name: Apricot
Description:
A variety of stone fruit borne over from the Near East. Its orange flesh is at once sweet and tart.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: La Noscean Leek
Description: A rare variety of leek, typically harvested young for a milder flavor.

Name: Young Cieldalaes Spinach
Description: This bunch of Cieldalaes spinach has been picked young to reduce bitterness.

Name: Blood Orange
Description:
A rare variety of orange grown in La Noscea, named for its unusual red flesh.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Petrified Log
Description: The passage of time has turned this log into stone.

Name: Scheelite
Description: A mysterious ore that glows intermittently.

Name: Raziqsand
Description: Discovered by a Far Eastern alchemist, this powder is used to harden gold.

Name: Saurian Skin
Description: The rare hide of a saurian.

Name: Cashmere Fleece
Description: Lustrous white wool sheared from a species of mountain goat prized for its fleece.

Name: Emery
Description: Powderized garnet used in the polishing of gemstones.

Name: Star Anise
Description: Originating from the Far East, this fragrant spice is shaped like eight-pointed stars.

Name: Dalamud Popoto
Description: Hailing also from the western continent, this cousin to the common popoto is lurid red in color.

Name: Royal Kukuru Bean
Description: A king among kukuru bean varieties, prized for its high nutritional value.

Name: Canard Breast
Description: A tender piece of meat taken from the breast of a farm-fattened duck.

Name: Ancient Lumber
Description: A length of lumber obtained by processing a petrified log.

Name: Wolfram Ingot
Description: An ingot of smelted wolfram.

Name: Saurian Leather
Description: A large piece of cured saurian skin.

Name: Cashmere Cloth
Description: Several yalms of cashmere cloth wrapped around a short wooden distaff.

Name: Umbral Rock
Description: A rock with an elemental aspect leaning heavily towards umbral.

Name: Fragrant Log
Description: A pleasant-smelling log obtained in the Black Shroud.

Name: Spruce Plywood
Description: A thin but sturdy construction material made by pressing together layers of wood, designed to achieve uniform strength.

Name: Darksteel Hook
Description: A hook masterfully wrought from darksteel.

Name: Darksteel Wire
Description: A roll of wire painstakingly drawn out from darksteel.

Name: Rose Gold Cog
Description: A cog masterfully wrought from rose gold.

Name: Gryphonskin Strap
Description: A continuous strap of leather painstakingly wrought from gryphonskin.

Name: Silver Brocade
Description: A luxurious fabric woven from silver thread, featuring raised patterns.

Name: Spirits of Salt
Description: A potent acid with myriad applications.

Name: Spicy Tomato Relish
Description: A zesty Near Eastern relish made by stewing tomatoes with select spices and seasoning.

Name: Diluted Vitriol
Description: A flask of vitriol diluted with pure water.

Name: Glamour Dispeller
Description: This black prism absorbs the magical lights woven upon a glamoured piece of equipment, thus dispelling the optical illusion. Be fairly warned that dyes and company crests are also removed in the process.

A crude piece of flattened mythril used as high-denomination currency by the kobolds of O'Ghomoro.

Only for use in kobold society quests.

Only for use in Sahagin society quests.

Name: Unidentified Allagan Tomestone
Description: Though they appear to be naught more than simple stones, Garlond Ironworks engineers insist they contain reams of invaluable information gathered by the lost Allagan Empire. However, this particular variety is not as highly sought as it once was, and may no longer be exchanged for other wares.

Name: Mysterious Map
Description:
This bottle is holding what appears to be a timeworn map of unknown origin, bearing peculiar markings.

Use the action Decipher to extract the map and examine its contents.
Level 50 recommended.

Name: Superior Enchanted Ink
Description: Ink originating from the Near East, boasting superior aetherial conductivity.

Name: Soul of the Ninja
Description: Upon the surface of this multi-aspected crystal are carved the myriad deeds of ninjas from eras past.

Name: Yoshimitsu
Description: One of the fabled relic weapons.

Name: Curiel Root
Description:
A parsnip-like tuber found growing on the windswept islands of the northern seas. While too bitter for most people's tastes, chocobos are known to enjoy the flavor, and thus the root is often used as fodder for the animals.

Increases EXP earned by your chocobo companion.

Name: Sylkis Bud
Description:
An artichoke-like flower found growing on a majority of the Cieldalaes. While too bitter for most people's tastes, chocobos are known to enjoy the flavor, and thus the meaty buds are often used as fodder for the animals.

Increases your chocobo companion's attack potency.

Name: Mimett Gourd
Description:
A large fleshy squash brought back from the New World by Lominsan explorers. While too sweet for most people's tastes, chocobos are known to enjoy the flavor, and thus the gourds are often used as fodder for the animals.

Increases your chocobo companion's healing magic potency.

Name: Tantalplant
Description:
A vibrant purple vegetable commonly found growing in the Near East. While too bitter for most people's tastes, chocobos are known to enjoy the flavor, and thus these aubergines are often used as fodder for the animals.

Increases your chocobo companion's maximum HP.

Name: Pahsana Fruit
Description:
A bright-red tomato-like fruit brought back from the New World by Lominsan explorers. While too tangy for most people's tastes, chocobos are known to enjoy the flavor, and thus the fruits are often used as fodder for the animals.

Increases your chocobo companion's enmity.

Name: Blood-spattered Mark Log
Description: A list of elite marks slain by the log's owner...before the owner herself was slain. Though such documents were once considered highly valuable, demand has dried up and they are now essentially worthless.

Name: Cupfish
Description:
A rare freshwater fish which spends the entirety of its life hiding in locations which rarely see the light of the sun.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Meteor Survivor
Description:
A king among helmet crabs, and lord of the waters off the Salt Strand.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Riviera Wall Shelf
Description: Wall-mounted shelves designed to complement riviera residences.

Name: Gourmet Lunch
Description:
A freshly prepared lunch, complete with a healthy green salad.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Critical Hit Bonus: +4% (Max 14)
  VIT Bonus: +4% (Max 9)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +2
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Gourmet Supper
Description:
A multiple-course meal certain to impress all manner of dinner guests, whether invited or not.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Skill Speed Bonus: +4% (Max 22)
  VIT Bonus: +4% (Max 15)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Afternoon Tea Set
Description:
Add a hint of sophistication to your residence with this elegant collection of ceramic ware.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Spell Speed Bonus: +4% (Max 22)
  VIT Bonus: +4% (Max 15)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Assorted Fruit
Description:
The world is better off oblivious of the fell magicks used to keep this basket of fruit eternally free of bruises and mold.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Direct Hit Bonus: +4% (Max 20)
  VIT Bonus: +4% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +2
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Chilled Red
Description:
Ice shards applied to the cooler's inner lining keep this bottle of Wineport's unfermented finest as cold as a Coerthan winter.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Piety Bonus: +4% (Max 5)
  VIT Bonus: +4% (Max 6)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +2
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: The Five Ages
Description: Impress your friends with these beautiful leather-bound replicas of Lewphon of Sharlayan's crowning achievement in the field of history, theology, and astrology. Just do not allow those friends to open any of the volumes, as they are all blank.

Name: Classified Documents
Description: Need to convince a special someone that you are deeply involved in a tangled web of international intrigue, so that they might keep you company in your chambers on what most certainly could be your last night amongst the living? A couple of official-looking documents can only help your ignoble cause.

Name: Stuffed Goblin
Description: All attempts to remove the mask of this goblin replica have failed, so do not even consider trying it yourself.

Name: Ultima Weapon Miniature
Description: An expertly crafted replica of the Ultima Weapon. (Miniature Gaius van Baelsar sold separately.)

Name: Onus of an Engineer
Description: A commissioned oil painting of Cid Garlond, former engineer for the Garlean Empire and founder of the Garlond Ironworks. Original artist unknown.

Name: Enquire Within
Description: A commissioned oil painting of realm-renowned agent of enquiry Hildibrand and his faithful assistant Nashu Mhakaracca. Original artist unknown.

Name: Wall Planter
Description: A simple wall-mounted planter, perfect for flowers or miniature shrubs.

Name: Encyclopedia Eorzea
Description: Impress your friends with these beautiful leather-bound replicas of naturalist Marcette Manne's comprehensive collection of knowledge. Just do not allow those friends to open any of the volumes, as they are all blank.

Name: Open Hearth
Description: A chimney-less hearth designed to resemble those popular in the Far East. Do not forget proper ventilation while using.

Name: Riviera Half Partition
Description: A partition designed in the riviera fashion, but reaching only less than halfway to the ceiling so as to provide privacy without making the room feel smaller.

Name: Potted Umbrella Fig
Description: A pruned and potted umbrella fig tree.

Name: Potted Dragon Tree
Description: A pruned and potted dragon tree. It is said that anyone in the presence of this breed of flora is unable to tell a lie, though it might also be that anyone in the presence of a dragon tree is unable to ask the hard questions.

Name: Model Star Globe
Description: A spherical map of the heavens based off of legendary Ishgardian astrologian Adaunel the Younger's lifetime of findings.

Name: Tatami Mat
Description: Woven from sweet-smelling rush grass, these rectangular floor mats are widely used in the Far Eastern land of Doma.

Name: Corner Counter
Description: A low counter-type table crafted in an L shape.

Name: Planter Partition
Description: A low partition outfitted with several planter pots.

Name: Plasma Lamp
Description:
A stylish floor lamp crafted from a rare Levin orb.

One per estate only.

Name: Lord of Levin Lamp
Description:
A stylish floor lamp crafted from a large Levin orbnow with more snap, crackle, and pop!

One per estate only.

Name: Emperor's Throne
Description:
Grant boons and make decrees in style while lounging in this near-perfect replica of Emperor Xande's throne.

One per estate only.

Name: Riviera Doormat
Description: A welcome mat designed to complement riviera residences. Don't tread on me.

Name: Double Feather Bed
Description: Made from the feathers of forty-leven geese, this large bed can hold approximately eight children, four hound dogs, and a piggy stolen from the shed.

Name: Chocobo Pillar
Description: A decorative pillar designed to resemble a chocobo.

Name: Riviera Cushion
Description: A plush cushion upholstered in the riviera fashion.

Name: Glade Cushion
Description: A plush cushion upholstered in the glade fashion.

Name: Oasis Cushion
Description: A plush cushion upholstered in the oasis fashion.

Name: Chocobo Stable
Description:
A simple stable large enough for keeping and raising as many chocobos as you can imagine (if 512 is the maximum number you can imagine).

One per estate only.

Name: Moonfire Lantern
Description: An outdoor lantern traditionally placed outside one's home for the duration of the Moonfire Faire.

Name: Ornamental Bamboo
Description: People hailing from the Far East claim that wishes written on small slips of parchment and tied to the bamboo will come true. (Magical wish parchment sold separately.)

Name: Rounded Shrub
Description: This leafy shrub has been expertly pruned and trimmed into a perfect sphere.

Name: Lattice Planter
Description: A wooden garden partition outfitted with planter pots.

Name: Water Lilies
Description: A ceramic pot filled with crystal-clear water and several water lilies.

Name: Garden Pond
Description: A decorative outdoor pond encircled by smooth stones.

Name: Cast-iron Cookpot
Description: A blackened pot perfect for hanging over a cookfire.

Name: Stepladder
Description: Because sometimes there are things even a Roegadyn cannot reach.

Name: Straight Stepping Stones
Description: Several flat smoothed stones arranged in a straight line.

Name: Curved Stepping Stones
Description: Several flat smoothed stones arranged in a curving pattern.

Name: Straight Stepping Stumps
Description: Several thinly cut cross sections of a massive tree trunk arranged to form a straight path.

Name: Curved Stepping Stumps
Description: Several thinly cut cross sections of a massive tree trunk arranged to form a curved path.

Name: Planter Box
Description: A rectangular wooden box filled with blooming wildflowers.

Name: Wooden Bucket
Description: A wooden bucket filled with crystal-clear water. Families in the Far East use these receptacles to chill fruit during the hot summer moons.

Name: Glade Hedgewall
Description: A living fence designed to complement glade residences. Mix and match at your own peril.

Name: Oasis Fence
Description: A decorated stone fence designed to complement oasis residences. Mix and match at your own peril.

Name: Riviera Fence
Description: A pointed iron fence designed to complement riviera residences. Mix and match at your own peril.

Name: Riviera Flora Interior Wall
Description: A flora-themed interior wall designed to complement riviera residences.

Name: Glade Flora Interior Wall
Description: A flora-themed interior wall designed to complement glade residences.

Name: Oasis Flora Interior Wall
Description: A flora-themed interior wall designed to complement oasis residences.

Name: Classic Interior Wall
Description: Experience luxury living with this interior wall which features an elegant pattern adored by the Ul'dahn elite.

Name: Striped Interior Wall
Description: These striped walls are guaranteed to make your room appear thin...or fat.

Name: Mosaic Interior Wall
Description: An intricate interior wall crafted from countless tiny pieces of ceramic fit together in breathtaking patterns.

Name: Bisque Flooring
Description: Simple, yet stylish, bisque flooring is perfect for the modern adventurer.

Name: Marble Flooring
Description: Carved from a single piece of beautiful marble, this floor is fit for a king (or queen).

Name: Ceramic Tile Flooring
Description: Specialty flooring that is cool to the touch and easy to clean.

Name: Bombard Lamp
Description: A massive lamp designed to resemble the villain of the Moonfire Fairethe Bombard.

Name: Throne Gem
Description: A brilliant bauble pried from the Emperor Xande's colossal seat of rule.

Name: Levin Orb
Description: A sphere of lightning-aspected energies encased in a transparent receptacle of hyperfused silica.

Name: Large Levin Orb
Description: A perfect sphere of overcharged lightning-aspected energies encased in a transparent receptacle of hyperfused silica.

Name: Rush Grass
Description: A durable sweet-smelling grass native to the Far East and used in the weaving of baskets and floor mats.

Name: Young Water Lily
Description: A unique type of flora which grows on inland ponds, its round, flat leaves creating a floating canopy on the water's surface.

Name: Pearl Roselle
Description: A milky white flower commonly found growing in the humid climes of the southern seas.

Name: Waterfowl Feather
Description: Unlike those of tree-dwelling cloudkin, waterfowl feathers are exceptional at trapping in heat while keeping out water.

Name: Floss Silk
Description: Silk that has been spun into lightweight balls that bear the appearance of cotton.

Name: Mist Silk
Description: Each strand of mist silk is twice as thin as regular silk, making it much more difficult to work with.

Name: Waterproof Cotton Cloth
Description: This soft cloth has been treated with a thin layer of resin to repel water.

Name: Polarized Glass
Description: Glass treated with a complex alchemical concoction to reduce glare.

Name: Wolfram Square
Description: A thin, tiny plate of hammered wolfram.

Name: Antumbral Rock
Description: A rock with an elemental aspect leaning unnaturally towards umbral.

Name: Redolent Log
Description: An unforgettably pleasant-smelling log obtained in the Black Shroud.

Name: Reinforced Spruce Plywood
Description: A thin but sturdy construction material made by pressing together layers of wood, designed to achieve uniform strength. Several additional layers have been applied to the board to improve durability.

Name: Balanced Darksteel Hook
Description: A hook masterfully wrought from darksteel and shaped to bear weight equally regardless of the direction in which it is pulled.

Name: Reinforced Darksteel Wire
Description: A roll of wire painstakingly drawn out from darksteel and combined with a second length of wire to enhance strength.

Name: Calibrated Rose Gold Cog
Description: A complex cog masterfully wrought from rose gold.

Name: Water-hardened Hippogryph Strap
Description: A continuous strap of leather painstakingly wrought from gryphonskin and then treated with water to increase hardness.

Name: Intricate Silver Brocade
Description: A luxurious fabric woven from silver thread, featuring raised patterns more beautiful than anything ever seen in the realm.

Name: Concentrated Spirits of Salt
Description: An ultra-concentrated potent acid with myriad applications.

Name: Rich Tomato Relish
Description: A zesty Near Eastern relish made by stewing tomatoes with select spices and seasoning. An extra turn of the sun over a cookfire has boiled off excess water, leaving a remarkably rich reduction sure to titillate the tongue.

Name: Talan's Seal of Mining
Description: A document bearing master crafter Talan's personal seal. Can be presented in exchange for select mining equipment.

Name: Talan's Seal of Botany
Description: A document bearing master crafter Talan's personal seal. Can be presented in exchange for select botanist's equipment.

Name: Talan's Seal of Fishing
Description: A document bearing master crafter Talan's personal seal. Can be presented in exchange for select fishing equipment.

Name: Gallant Armor Augmentation
Description: Materials required to augment a set of gallant armor.

Name: Temple Attire Augmentation
Description: Materials required to augment a set of temple attire.

Name: Fighter's Armor Augmentation
Description: Materials required to augment a set of fighter's armor.

Name: Drachen Armor Augmentation
Description: Materials required to augment a set of drachen armor.

Description: Materials required to augment a set of choral attire.

Description: Materials required to augment a set of wizard's attire.

Description: Materials required to augment a set of healer's attire.

Description: Materials required to augment a set of evoker's attire.

Description: Materials required to augment a set of scholar's attire.

A component to be used in creating the Dezul Qualan's figurehead.

Only for use in Ixal society quests.

Name: Unhidden Leather Map
Description:
A detailed map recovered from the treasure coffer in which it was hidden...officially rendering it no longer hidden.

Use the action Decipher to extract the map and examine its contents.
Level 50 recommended.
Item level 70 recommended.

Name: Xelphatol Apple
Description: A bitter fruit found growing in the Ixali homelands. While typically avoided by the Ixal themselves, it is a favorite amongst chocobos, and is known to deepen the red hues of their feathers.

Name: Doman Plum
Description: A hard, bitter fruit found in the forests of Far Eastern Doma. It is a favorite amongst chocobos, and is known to lighten the red hues of their feathers.

Name: Mamook Pear
Description: A bitter fruit found growing in the arid soils of Mamook. While typically avoided by the Mamool Ja themselves, it is a favorite amongst chocobos, and is known to deepen the green hues of their feathers.

Name: Valfruit
Description: A bitter berry found growing on the distant Isle of Val. It is a favorite amongst chocobos, and is known to lighten the green hues of their feathers.

Name: O'Ghomoro Berries
Description: A bitter fruit found growing on the volcanic soil of O'Ghomoro. While typically avoided by the kobolds, it is a favorite amongst chocobos, and is known to deepen the blue hues of their feathers.

Name: Cieldalaes Pineapple
Description: A bitter fruit found growing on the Cieldalaesa remote archipelago in the Rhotano Sea. It is a favorite amongst chocobos, and is known to lighten the blue hues of their feathers.

Name: Han Lemon
Description: A foul, bitter fruit found growing on the Near Eastern island of Thavnair. While typically avoided by the residents of Radz-at-Han, it is a favorite amongst chocobos, and is known to restore feathers to their original hue.

Name: Krakka Root
Description: A bitter carrot-like root vegetable native to the Near East and a favorite amongst chocobos.

Name: Thavnairian Onion
Description: A pungent, tear-inducing vegetable that thrives in the alkali sands of Near Eastern Thavnair. It is a favorite amongst chocobos.

Name: Pearl Roselle Seeds
Description: Pearl roselle seeds suitable for garden cultivation.

Name: Magicked Stable Broom
Description: Why entrust the sweeping of chocobo dung to a coinless pleb with a sick wife and two starving children when you can toss a bewitched broom into your personal stables and be done?
