Name: Wind-up Ixal
Description:
He believes he can fly. He believes he can touch the sky. Unfortunately he cannot.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Ixal minion.

Name: Wind-up Succubus
Description:
100% anatomically correct. Handle with care.

Use item to acquire the wind-up succubus minion.

Name: Wind-up Gilgamesh
Description:
Several arms appear to be missing, but that does not seem to otherwise hinder basic functionality.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Gilgamesh minion.

Name: Onion Prince
Description:
He would die 4 U. Or possibly cry 4 U. Or most likely make U cry. 4 U.

Use item to acquire the Onion Prince minion.

Name: Eggplant Knight
Description:
His childhood dream to become a wizard was frowned upon by his overbearing father.

Use item to acquire the Eggplant Knight minion.

Name: Garlic Jester
Description:
Every breath you take will act as a reminder that your pungent pal is right behind you.

Use item to acquire the Garlic Jester minion.

Name: Tomato King
Description:
Has issued a royal decree for the public defenestration of any and all who mistakenly claim the king is a vegetable.

Use item to acquire the Tomato King minion.

Name: Mandragora Queen
Description: Though wed to the Tomato King in a move to strengthen the bond of houses Tomato and Mandragora, the queen longs to steal away with her one true lovethe Eggplant Knight. What will become of this forbidden romance!? Use item to acquire the Mandragora Queen minion and find out!

Name: Wind-up Onion Knight
Description:
An accurate representation of the soldiers who once made up the greater portion of the Allagan Imperial Army.

Use item to acquire the wind-up onion knight minion.

Name: Treasure Box
Description:
It is unknown what manner of spirit possesses this tiny treasure chest, but the fact that it will not hesitate to nip at the fingers of any who try and pry it open is painfully evident.

Use item to acquire the treasure box minion.

Name: Tiny Tapir
Description:
Natives of the New World claim that tapirs grow by devouring the dreams of their unsuspecting owners. And now you know what to expect.

Use item to acquire the tiny tapir minion.

Name: Nana Bear
Description:
Pundits claim bears to be the deadliest beasts in the realm. They obviously have never stared into this cute cub's nebulous eyes.

Use item to acquire the Nana bear minion.

Name: Miniature Minecart
Description:
Best when ridden in abandoned mines and temples of doom.

Use item to acquire the miniature minecart minion.

Name: Nutkin
Description:
That nutkins are infamous for being shy and timid creatures shows that this brave beastkin comes complete with a pair of iron acorns on him.

Use item to acquire the nutkin minion.

Name: Wind-up Minfilia
Description:
Unlike the real Minfilia, this one actually accompanies you on your adventures.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Minfilia minion.

Name: Wind-up Thancred
Description:
Two hundred percent more dreamy than previous models.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Thancred minion.

Name: Naughty Nanka
Description:
Like its parent, the ninki nanka, this slippery wavekin will breed like a rabbit if left unsupervised.

Use item to acquire the naughty nanka minion.

Name: Panda Cub
Description:
Untrained in arts both martial and magical, but as scrumptiously adorable as chicken glazed in a tangy orange reduction.

Use item to acquire the panda cub minion.

Name: Draught Chocobo Whistle
Description: A small hand-carved whistle that emits a unique, high-pitched tone discernible only by a draught chocobo trained from birth to recognize and respond to the sound. Use to summon your personal draught chocobo.

Name: Direwolf Whistle
Description: A polished bone horn used to summon an Ixal-trained direwolf.

Name: Storm Warsteed Horn
Description: A hollowed beastkin horn adorned in Maelstrom red that emits a deep bellowing tone which summons your Storm warsteed.

Name: Serpent Warsteed Horn
Description: A hollowed beastkin horn adorned in Twin Adder yellow that emits a deep bellowing tone which summons your Serpent warsteed.

Name: Flame Warsteed Horn
Description: A hollowed beastkin horn adorned in Immortal Flames black that emits a deep bellowing tone which summons your Flame warsteed.

Name: Markab Whistle
Description: This tiny whistle emits a shrill tone which can only be heard by Markab, blessed steed of the Lord of Levin.

Name: Aetheryte Pendulum
Description: A shard of aetheryte which can be attuned to new adventurers, allowing for swift travel to their side in times of need.

Name: Realm Reborn Red
Description: A special vintage of sparkling red wine prepared by master vintner Byrglaent of Wineport for the Rising, an annual celebration of Eorzea's rebirth.

Name: Magicked Prism (Meteor Survivor)
Description: This peculiar contraption creates illusions by weaving together myriad shades of light. Produces a radiant light that projects images of the lesser moon Dalamud.

Name: Pinwheel
Description: A spinning firework popular in the Far East.

Name: Magitek Torch (Red Lotus)
Description: An original creation of the Garlond Ironworks, this handheld device harnesses the power of magitek to emit a sensuous red light.

Name: Skyrocket
Description: This particular variety of firework resembles a comet when ignited. Why it is not then called a skycomet, only the Far Eastern inventor who conceived the item knows.

Name: Ixali Oaknot Promissory Note
Description: A promissory note that can be exchanged for Ixali oaknotscarved pieces of oak used as currency by the Ixal.

Increases EXP earned from battle, crafting, and gathering when level 25 or below.
EXP Bonus: +20%

Description: [Must be equipped to craft certain Ixali recipes.]

Name: Levin Barding
Description: A suit of chocobo armor designed to resemble Ramuh, the Lord of Levin.

Name: Plumed Barding
Description: A suit of chocobo armor adorned with brilliant plumage. This particular design is quite popular amongst chocobo enthusiasts.

Name: Gysahl Greens Seeds
Description: Gysahl greens seeds suitable for garden cultivation.

Name: Soul of the Machinist
Description: Unlike other soul crystals, the surface of this multi-aspected stone has yet to be carved with the record of past deeds.

Name: Eternity Ring
Description: Material proof of a spiritual bond.

Name: Wind-up Violet
Description:
Touched by a primal and corrupted to the core...yet adorable nonetheless.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Violet minion.

Name: Wind-up Founder
Description:
Four score and many more years ago, the Amalj'aa founding fathers dreamed of a day when in their footsteps would walk adorable minions. That day has finally come.

Use item to acquire the wind-up founder minion.

Name: Wind-up Dezul Qualan
Description:
It is said Ixali engineer Dezul Qualan began crafting war dirigibles after having a vision of ninety-nine red balloons floating over the Black Shroud.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Dezul Qualan minion.

Name: Wind-up Kobolder
Description:
Bolder than a wind-up kobold, yet not any older.

Use item to acquire the wind-up kobolder minion.

Name: Wind-up Sea Devil
Description:
A clockwork automaton expertly crafted to resemble the infamous Scarlet Sea Devil, leader of the Coral Tridents.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Sea Devil minion.

Name: Promise of Innocence
Description: This wristlet signifies a standard agreement between two individuals to form an everlasting spiritual union.

Name: Promise of Passion
Description: This wristlet signifies a gold-clad agreement between two individuals to form an everlasting spiritual union.

Name: Promise of Devotion
Description: This wristlet signifies a platinum-clad agreement between two individuals to form an everlasting spiritual union.

Name: Flawless Band
Description: From this simple ring, a lifelong bond begins.

Name: Blank Invitation
Description: The Ceremony of Eternal Bonding invitation from which all future invitations are born.

Name: Ceremony Invitation
Description: Allows admittance to a Ceremony of Eternal Bonding. Speak with Etoinelle at the Sanctum of the Twelve before using.

Name: Demon Box
Description:
There is no better way to tell a special someone Thank you for attending my Ceremony of Eternal Bonding than by giving them a sentient box that may or may not devour their pets.

Use item to acquire the demon box minion.

Name: Ceremony Chocobo Whistle
Description: A small hand-carved whistle that emits a unique, high-pitched tone discernible only by a ceremony chocobo trained from birth to recognize and respond to the sound. Use to summon your ceremony chocobo mount.

Name: Demonic Cookie
Description: Though this small baked treat provided by the Continental Circus appears to be a cookie, it is difficult to tell what on Hydaelyn it might contain. Consumption should probably be avoided.

Name: Ironworks Fishing Rod
Description: Rumor has that fishing enthusiast Biggs used the Garlond Ironworks crafting facilities after-hours to create this magitek-enhanced rod.

Name: Eerie Barding
Description: A purely decorative chocobo costume created for All Saints' Wake.

Name: Model Enterprise
Description:
Designed to boldly go where you have gone before.

Use item to acquire the model Enterprise minion.

Name: Wind-up Delivery Moogle
Description:
For when you absolutely, positively require moogle accompaniment.

Use item to acquire the wind-up delivery moogle minion.

Name: Wind-up Nanamo
Description:
The automaton vehemently refuses to sit upon any shoulder but Raubahn's...and yours.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Nanamo minion.

Name: Wind-up Y'shtola
Description:
If we are to take her word for it, the Circle of Knowing Archon has seen but twenty-three summers.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Y'shtola minion.

Name: Wind-up Yda
Description:
Comes complete with irremovable mask.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Yda minion.

Name: Wind-up Papalymo
Description:
Comes complete with irremovable smirk.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Papalymo minion.

Name: Wind-up Urianger
Description:
When the senary moon did wane, there sounded a garrulous and convoluted monologue. A new minion had roused, one whose identity lieth within our ken.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Urianger minion.

Name: Sleipnir Horn
Description: This ebon horn emits a somber tone that summons Odin's loyal steed from the elder primal's side to yours.

Name: Odin Miniature
Description: An expertly crafted replica of the wandering elder primal Odin. (Miniature Sleipnir included.)

Name: Bahamut Miniature
Description: An expertly crafted replica of the elder primal Bahamut. (Miniature Nael van Darnus sold separately.)

Name: Stuffed Tonberry
Description: This plush doll is rumored to be stuffed with countless strips of cloth covered in terrible curses. Slicing open the tonberry to find out what they entail is not recommended.

Name: A Northerly Wind
Description: A commissioned portrait of Circle of Knowing Archon Louisoix Leveilleur entitled A Northerly Wind. Original artist unknown.

Name: The Antecedent
Description: A commissioned portrait of Scions of the Seventh Dawn leader Minfilia entitled The Antecedent. Original artist unknown.

Name: Imperial Goldfish
Description:
A king among goldfish.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: The Old Man in the Sea
Description:
A king among Mazlaya marlin.

[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Nepto Dragon
Description:
Believed by Eorzean fisherfolk to be the spawn of Thalaoslegendary creator of seas. It is, however, more likely to be no more than an overgrown little Thalaos.

[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Coelacanthus
Description:
A king among coelacanths.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Endoceras
Description:
An ancient sea-dweller with a body like a lance and a temper like the Fury's. Only few have ever seen this living legend, let alone landed one.

[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Seahag
Description:
A queen among dinichthys.

[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Ignus Horn
Description:
A king among ignus snails.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Void Bass
Description:
A king among Ilsabardian bass.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Cornelia
Description:
A champion among boxing plecos.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Ninja Betta
Description:
A king among assassin betta.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Canavan
Description:
A king among morinabaligi.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 4 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Kuno the Killer
Description:
A legendary white catfish rarely seen by even the eldest of fisherfolk.

[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Pirate's Bane
Description:
A king among titanic saws.

[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Ndendecki
Description:
A king among soft-shelled snapping turtles.

[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Bat-o'-Nine-Tails
Description:
A king among vampire lamperns.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Wootz Knifefish Zenith
Description:
A king among wootz knifefish.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Helicoprion
Description:
A legendary denizen of the sands, the helicoprion's maw is lined with long curved teeth that help it latch onto its airborne prey.

[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Darkstar
Description:
A king among angry pike.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Blue Corpse
Description:
A king among wandering sculpin.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Mahar
Description:
A king among rhamphorhynchus.

[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Shonisaurus
Description:
Within this legendary scalekin's body can be found a massive secondary bladder containing lighter-than-air gas.

[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Magicked Mushroom
Description:
A king among mushroom crabs.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Giant Takitaro
Description:
A king among takitaro.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 4 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Namitaro
Description:
This legendary freshwater fish cares not for those kings or queens who encroach upon his territory, and will turn to regicide to keep his waters his own.

[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Blood Red Bonytongue
Description:
A king among bonytongue.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 3 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: South Seas Armchair
Description: A plush chair designed in the south seas style.

Name: South Seas Couch
Description: An L-shaped couch designed in the south seas style.

Name: Riviera Canopy Bed
Description: A luxurious canopied bed designed in the riviera style.

Name: Glade Canopy Bed
Description: A luxurious canopied bed designed in the glade style.

Name: Oasis Canopy Bed
Description: A luxurious canopied bed designed in the oasis style.

Name: Potted Oliphant's Ear
Description: A broad-leafed perennial common on south seas islands such as the Cieldalaes. The shape of the leaf is said to resemble the ear of a legendary beast twice as tall as a Roegadyn and ten times as heavy.

Name: Shower Stand
Description: A simple indoor shower, perfect for cleansing the body and spirit after a long day of adventure.

Name: Head of the Dreadwyrm
Description:
An impressive objet d'art depicting the head of the dreadwyrm, Bahamut.

One per estate only.

Name: Syrcus Tower
Description:
An expertly crafted representation of the ancient crystalline tower.

One per estate only.

Name: Riviera Stool
Description: A quaint round stool designed in the riviera fashion.

Name: Glade Stool
Description: A quaint round stool designed in the glade fashion.

Name: Oasis Stool
Description: A quaint round stool designed in the oasis fashion.

Name: Armoire
Description:
A large wooden wardrobe in which sets of special gear may be stored.

One per estate only.

Name: Masonwork Stove
Description: A handcrafted stone stove similar to the ones found in the homes of the realm's smallfolk.

Name: Eternity Cake
Description: A family of four tended their gristmill for a full three turns of the sun to create enough flour to bake this massive tower cake.

Name: Empty Twinkleboxes
Description: A twinklebox without a present is like a child without a smile.

Name: Riviera Open-shelf Bookcase
Description: A backless bookshelf designed in the riviera fashion.

Name: Glade Open-shelf Bookcase
Description: A backless bookshelf designed in the glade fashion.

Name: Oasis Open-shelf Bookcase
Description: A backless bookshelf designed in the oasis fashion.

Name: Shipping Crate
Description: A sturdy wooden box once used to import exotics from across the boundless seas.

Name: Wine Barrel
Description: A wooden barrel once used to mature wine.

Name: Incensory
Description: A ceramic censer into which aromatic herbs and oils are inserted and then heated to produce a fragrant smoke.

Name: Sheep Dolls
Description: Two stuffed sheephusband and wifedressed in traditional Far Eastern garb.

Name: Hard Rice Cakes
Description: Known in the Far East as kagami mochi, these cakes are not traditionally eaten, but displayed before and during Heavensturn.

Name: Stuffed Qiqirn
Description: A handmade doll crafted to resemble a Qiqirn, and dressed in a festive Starlight Celebration outfit.

Name: Starlight Dodo
Description:
A whole dodo stuffed with savory vegetables and slow-roasted on a spit. Often prepared near the end of the year as an offering to the Twelve.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  VIT Bonus: +4% (Max 3)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +1
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Pumpkin Basket
Description: A pumpkin-shaped basket filled with All Saints' Wake goodies.

Name: Starlight Cake
Description:
Conceived by Bismarck chefs with far too much time on their hands, the Starlight cake is composed of layer after layer after layer...after layer of sweet, decadent heaven.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  VIT Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +1
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Wall Lantern
Description: A rectangular oil lamp for indoor use.

Name: Manor Sofa
Description: An extravagant sofa crafted from the rarest wood and finest cloth obtainable; no expense was spared for this Haukke Manor original.

Name: Stuffed Mazlaya Marlin
Description: As magnificent as the day it was caught, but without the unpleasant stench of decay.

Name: Megalodon Jaws
Description: The sheer size of these jawbones adds credit to rumors that megalodons enjoy feeding on unwary swimmers, and will swallow them whole so as not to saturate the surrounding waters with blood, thereby alerting other nearby predators.

Name: Stuffed Takitaro
Description: No more half-hearted tales about the one that got away. This legend of this rare, elusive fish will live on in style above your mantle or in your den.

Name: Starlight Wreath
Description: A simple circle of evergreen branches hung on doors during the Starlight Celebration. While the tradition is fairly new, there already exist several theories as to how the practice started. Some believe the circle represents the symbolic beginning and end of a year, and in turn, our lives, while others claim it is merely easier to hang a ring than it is a straight branch.

Name: Towel Hanger
Description: Without a hanger, where would towels hang?

Name: Adventurers' Guild Aduyses
Description: A semi-complete collection of notices and timetables, warnings and wanted posters, found in Eorzea's many Adventurers' Guilds.

Name: Glade Doormat
Description: A lawn-green welcome mat designed to complement glade residences.

Name: Oasis Doormat
Description: A welcome mat designed to complement oasis residences.

Name: Large Woven Rug
Description: Try not to wipe your well-traveled feet on this luxurious import.

Name: Large Planter Box
Description: A deep rectangular box for planting flowers or vegetables.

Name: Riviera Path Light
Description: A small crystal-powered lantern designed in the riviera style used outdoors to light walkways.

Name: Glade Path Light
Description: A small crystal-powered lantern designed in the glade style used outdoors to light walkways.

Name: Oasis Path Light
Description: A small crystal-powered lantern designed in the oasis style used outdoors to light walkways.

Name: Glade Lamppost
Description: A lamppost of steel such as one might see lining a Gridanian street.

Name: Oasis Lamppost
Description: A lamppost of steel such as one might see lining an Ul'dahn street.

Name: Pumpkin Candlestand
Description: A decorated lamppost displayed during All Saints' Wake.

Name: Star-topped Starlight Sentinel
Description:
A potted fir, decorated with a star-shaped ornament at its apex.

Only one Starlight sentinel may be placed in a single estate, regardless of type.

Name: Moon-topped Starlight Sentinel
Description:
A potted fir, decorated with a crescent moon-shaped ornament at its apex.

Only one Starlight sentinel may be placed in a single estate, regardless of type.

Name: Sun-topped Starlight Sentinel
Description:
A potted fir, decorated with a sun-shaped ornament at its apex.

Only one Starlight sentinel may be placed in a single estate, regardless of type.

Name: Snowman
Description: Garlean scholars have conducted extensive studies on the subject of why Eorzean snowmen are constructed of only two balls of snow rather than threethe number of choice throughout Ilsabard. The prevailing theory is that extensive studies should not have been conducted on said subject.

Name: Empty Gift Boxes
Description: A box without a gift is like a bird without a song.

Name: Kadomatsu
Description: A mini-tower of sliced bamboo and pine branchesthe kadomatsu is a Far Eastern oddity traditionally displayed at homes and in temples for the duration of Heavensturn.

Name: Eerie Wallpaper
Description: Ready your estate for All Saints' Wake with this frightening-yet-festive interior wall covering.

Name: Starlight Interior Wall
Description: This wall bears a festive design certain to bring joy and cheer to all...until you finally get around to taking it down six moons later.

Name: Masonwork Interior Wall
Description: A sturdy wall of locally quarried stones.

Name: Masonwork Flooring
Description: A smooth stone floor guaranteed to stay cool in the summer and toe-numbingly cold in the winter.

Name: Checkered Flooring
Description: Give your estate a modern feel with this quality flooring's contemporary pattern.

Name: Iron Plate Flooring
Description: Hammered steel flooring for those seeking an imperial feel to their residence.

Name: Ice Chandelier
Description: A breathtaking ceiling fixture crafted using tears taken from the Lady of Frost herself.

Name: Diamond Chandelier
Description: An awe-inspiring ceiling fixture crafted using tears taken from the Lady of Frost herself and imbued with magicks ancient and forbidden.

Name: Expansion of Duties Permit
Description:
An amendment to existing retainer employment contracts allowing for dispatchment on privately owned properties.

Cottage, house, and mansion gardens can accommodate 1, 2, and 3 retainers, respectively.

Name: Level 1 Aetherial Wheel Stand
Description:
A metal stand upon which aetherial wheels are placed and spun to charge. Holds one grade 1 wheel.
One stand per estate only.

Name: Soul of the Dark Knight
Description: Upon the surface of this multi-aspected crystal are carved the myriad deeds of dark knights from eras past.

Name: Soul of the Astrologian
Description: Upon the surface of this multi-aspected crystal are carved the myriad deeds of astrologians from eras past.

Name: Retainer Fantasia
Description:
Legend states that any who drink this mysterious liquid before lying down for the evening will awaken a new man (or woman).

Grants you a single opportunity to edit your retainer's appearance when speaking to a retainer vocate.

Name: Grade 1 Wheel of Confrontation
Description: A cylindrical wheel crafted from metal and aspected crystal which, when placed on a stand and spun repeatedly, accumulates an aetherial charge. When fully primed, the wheel can be used to initiate the company action The Heat of Battle (increased EXP earned through battle).

Name: Grade 1 Wheel of Productivity
Description: A cylindrical wheel crafted from metal and aspected crystal which, when placed on a stand and spun repeatedly, accumulates an aetherial charge. When fully primed, the wheel can be used to initiate the company action Earth and Water (increased EXP earned through gathering).

Name: Grade 1 Wheel of Industry

When fully primed, the wheel can be used to initiate the company action Brave New World (increased attributes for all Disciple of War or Magic members under level 25).

Description: A scroll bearing arcanima patterns of power for enhancing the relic Yoshimitsu daggers.

Description: Materials required to augment a set of ninja garb.

Name: Yellow Fallen Star
Description: A token of appreciation presented to you by a Starlight Celebration saint's little helper.

Name: Blue Fallen Star
Description: A token of appreciation presented to you by a Starlight Celebration saint's little helper.

Name: Red Fallen Star
Description: A token of appreciation presented to you by a Starlight Celebration saint's little helper.

Description: A token of appreciation presented to you by a Starlight Celebration saint's little helper.

Name: Premium Starlight Gift Bag
Description: No matter what wonders await inside this positively plump sack, always remember that during this season of giving, it is the thought that counts.

Name: Red Starlight Gift Bag
Description: No matter what wonders await inside this festive sack, always remember that during this season of giving, it is the thought that counts.

Name: Green Starlight Gift Bag
Description: No matter what wonders await inside this festive sack, always remember that during this season of giving, it is the thought that counts.

Name: The Emperor's New Necklace
Description: Can only be seen by the most astute observers.

Name: The Emperor's New Earrings
Description: Can only be seen by the most astute observers.

Name: The Emperor's New Bracelet
Description: Can only be seen by the most astute observers.

Name: The Emperor's New Ring
Description: Can only be seen by the most astute observers.

Name: Magitek Torch (Blue Lotus)
Description: An original creation of the Garlond Ironworks, this handheld device harnesses the power of magitek to emit a soft blue light.

Name: Magitek Torch (Yellow Lotus)
Description: An original creation of the Garlond Ironworks, this handheld device harnesses the power of magitek to emit a soft golden light.

Name: Carpentry for Beginners
Description: A volume covering only the most basic information. The majority of its content is considered common knowledge.

Name: Blacksmithing for Beginners
Description: A volume covering only the most basic information. The majority of its content is considered common knowledge.

Description: A volume covering only the most basic information. The majority of its content is considered common knowledge.

Name: Alchemy for Beginners
Description: A volume covering only the most basic information. The majority of its content is considered common knowledge.

Name: Cooking for Beginners
Description: A volume covering only the most basic information. The majority of its content is considered common knowledge.

Name: Triple Cream Coffee
Description:
Freshly roasted ground coffee beans percolated to perfection and mixed with an equal amount of thick dairy cream.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Bacon Bread
Description:
Soft dough mixed with thick-sliced bacon and twisted into a pattern resembling a sheaf of wheat.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Flint Caviar
Description:
Salted eggs of the rare emperor fish. Often referred to as black diamonds, the eggs are a delicacy that can only be afforded by the wealthiest of connoisseurs.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Shark Fin Soup
Description:
The massive fin of a megalodon, boiled in a rich Far Eastern broth until soft and gelatinous. While not included in the soup, the remainder of the sharkflesh is salted and dried until rock hard, then shaved into paper-thin slices which, when boiled in hot water, create a savory soup that is the base of countless other recipes.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Haddock Dip
Description:
A thick salty dip made from a pure of haddock, raw egg, and mashed popotoes. A favorite of Roegadyn tribes hailing from the north seas.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Bacon Broth
Description:
Though technically a soup, this Ixali dish consists mainly of large slabs of smoked bacon boiled with several other lesser ingredients.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Master Carpenter II
Description: This esoteric tomethe second in an equally esoteric seriescontains advanced woodworking recipes that can only be learned by highly skilled carpenters.

Name: Master Blacksmith II
Description: This esoteric tomethe second in an equally esoteric seriescontains advanced smithing recipes that can only be learned by highly skilled blacksmiths.

Name: Master Armorer II
Description: This esoteric tomethe second in an equally esoteric seriescontains advanced armorcraft recipes that can only be learned by highly skilled armorers.

Name: Master Goldsmith II
Description: This esoteric tomethe second in an equally esoteric seriescontains advanced goldsmithing recipes that can only be learned by highly skilled goldsmiths.

Name: Master Leatherworker II
Description: This esoteric tomethe second in an equally esoteric seriescontains advanced leatherworking recipes that can only be learned by highly skilled leatherworkers.

Name: Master Weaver II
Description: This esoteric tomethe second in an equally esoteric seriescontains advanced clothcraft recipes that can only be learned by highly skilled weavers.

Name: Master Alchemist II
Description: This esoteric tomethe second in an equally esoteric seriescontains advanced alchemy recipes that can only be learned by highly skilled alchemists.

Name: Master Culinarian II
Description: This esoteric tomethe second in an equally esoteric seriescontains advanced cooking recipes that can only be learned by highly skilled culinarians.

Name: Wind-up Ultros
Description:
A fraction of the size, yet every bit as annoying as the real thing. Be forewarned: once Ultros shows up, he's liable to stick around.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Ultros minion.

Name: Hoary the Snowman
Description:
Hoary the Snowman was a jolly happy soul, without a pipe, and without a nose, and two eyes made out of something other than coal. Probably slag.

Use item to acquire the Hoary the Snowman minion.

Name: Heavy Hatchling
Description:
Currently, baby fat is the prevailing excuse for this cherubic chick's gigant-like girth.

Use item to acquire the heavy hatchling minion.

Name: Fat Cat
Description:
Despite convincing research by top academics from around the realm and beyond, most Miqo'te scholars refuse to believe that there may be some ancestral connection between their race and cats (fat or not).

Use item to acquire the fat cat minion.

Name: Littlefoot
Description:
This particular yeti is content in knowing that bigger is not always necessarily better.

Use item to acquire the Littlefoot minion.

Name: Mummy's Little Mummy
Description:
While as cute as a button, remember, mummies are ultimately embalmed corpses damned to eternal thralldom in the land of the living. Have fun.

Use item to acquire the mummy's little mummy minion.

Name: Assassin Fry
Description:
There was an old betta who swallowed a fry. No one knows why it swallowed the fry, but for some reason, the fry can now fly.

Use item to acquire the assassin fry minion.

Name: Water Imp
Description:
Legend states these strange creatures can only survive on land as long as the plate atop their heads remains wet.

Use item to acquire the water imp minion.

Name: Wind-up Louisoix
Description:
The Seventh Astral Era is secure as long as the Archon is ever at our sides.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Louisoix minion.

Name: Parade Chocobo Whistle
Description: A small hand-carved whistle that emits a unique, high-pitched tone discernible only by a chocobo trained from birth to recognize and respond to the sound. Use to summon your parade chocobo.

Name: Boreas Whistle
Description: This whistle emits a shrill tone that is said to summon Boreas, the steed of legend.

Name: Ice Barding
Description: A suit of chocobo armor designed to resemble the Lady of Frost, Shiva.

Name: Quick-hardening Sealant
Description: A powerful adhesive developed and used by the Ehcatl Nine.

Name: Xelphatol Spring Water
Description: Slightly effervescent water bottled at a spring located deep in the heart of the Ixali homeland, Xelphatol. It has a light-blue tint and a distinctly metallic flavor.

Name: Wootz Ingot
Description: An ingot of smelted wootz alloy.

Name: Platinum Nugget
Description: A small nugget of impure platinum.

Name: Platinum Ingot
Description: An ingot of smelted platinum.

Name: Kirimu Leather
Description: A large piece of cured skin from the chimerical monstrosity Kirimu.

Name: Arachne Velveteen
Description: Thick cloth woven from the web of the chimerical monstrosity Arachne.

Name: Allagan Wootz Nugget
Description: A small chunk of the alloy used by the Allagan Empire to craft heavy armor.

Name: Allagan Leather
Description: A large piece of treated chimerical leather used by the Allagan Empire to craft light armor.

Name: Allagan Silk
Description: A spool of thick chimerical silk used by the Allagan Empire to craft mage robes.

Name: Borax
Description: This soft lusterless crystal is believed to stay the hands of corruption and is used in the preservation of organics.

Name: Arachne Web
Description: The wire-like web of the Allagan chimerical miscreation, Arachne.

Name: Wootz Ore
Description: A decent-sized piece of rock containing naturally occurring wootz alloy.

Name: Raziqsap
Description: Developed by a Far Eastern alchemist, this powder is used to harden platinum.

Name: Dubbin
Description: A greasy mixture of wax, oil, and tallow used for waterproofing and softening leather, while helping maintain its luster.

Name: Smoked Bacon
Description: A large side of boar, cured and then smoked. It is widely accepted across Eorzea that everything goes better with this flavorful meat.

Name: Roasted Coffee Beans
Description: Seeds harvested from the coffee plants which grow in volcanic mountainous soils, and then slow-roasted over an indirect flame for several bells to remove bitterness and bring out flavor.

Name: Enchanted Platinum Ink
Description: Ink fortified with platinum sand to improve aetherial conductivity.

Name: Bloody Knife Blades
Description: A pair of blood-soaked blades retrieved from the site of a gruesome battle.

Name: Mossy Stone Daggers
Description: A pair of daggers crafted from giantsgall, a type of stone found on Thavnair. They are so covered in moss as to be rendered unusable.

Name: Allagan Catalyst
Description: Dubbed a god in the machina by those who first discovered it, modern scholars have yet to discover not only what the catalytic agent contains, but exactly how it functions, understanding only that the substance is required to strengthen the properties of certain materials.

Name: Ice Tear
Description: A glass-like shard retrieved from the fallen Lady of Frost.

Name: Diamond Tear
Description: A glass-like shard retrieved from the fallen Lady of Frost. It pulses with uncontrollably powerful ice-aspected energies.

Name: Syrcus Shard
Description: A remarkably transparent piece of Syrcus Tower's outer wall.

Name: Burning Auricle
Description: A crystallized fragment of the dreadwyrm Bahamut's burning heart.

Name: Rowena's Token (Poetics)
Description: A note of promise received from Rowena for the delivery of Allagan tomestones of poetics. However, due to the House of Splendors changing its policies, it is now worth less than the paper on which it is scribed.

Name: Encrypted Tomestone
Description: While Garlond Ironworks engineers insist tomestones contain reams of invaluable information gathered by the lost Allagan Empire, even they are at a loss how to decipher the content of this particular one. This variety is not as highly sought as it once was, and may no longer be exchanged for other wares.

Name: Carboncoat
Description: Born of Allagan ingenuity, this aetherochemical concoction is said to increase a gem's hardness. However, advances in crafting technology have rendered it obsolete.

Name: Carbontwine
Description: Born of Allagan ingenuity, this aetherochemically engineered fiber can be used to improve the durability of almost anything. However, advances in crafting technology have rendered it obsolete.

Name: Antique Helm
Description: While this headpiece is far too old and dented to survive any further battles, collectors have been known to pay sizable sums for similar pieces.

Name: Antique Mail
Description: While this suit is far too old and battered to survive any further battles, collectors have been known to pay sizable sums for similar pieces.

Name: Antique Gauntlets
Description: While these gauntlets are far too old and rusted to survive any further battles, collectors have been known to pay sizable sums for similar pieces.

Name: Antique Breeches
Description: While this legwear is far too old and moth-eaten to survive any further battles, collectors have been known to pay sizable sums for similar pieces.

Name: Antique Sollerets
Description: While this footwear is far too old and worn to survive any further battles, collectors have been known to pay sizable sums for similar pieces.

Name: Antique Tassets
Description: Collectors were once known to pay sizable sums for similar pieces. Alas, advancements in trouser technology have rendered these worthless.

Name: Misericorde Blades
Description: Deadly darksteel blades used in the creation of misericordes.

Name: Level 2 Aetherial Wheel Stand
Description:
A metal stand upon which aetherial wheels are placed and spun to charge. Holds one grade 1 and one grade 2 wheel.
One stand per estate only.

Name: Level 3 Aetherial Wheel Stand
Description:
A metal stand upon which aetherial wheels are placed and spun to charge. Holds one grade 1, one grade 2, and one grade 3 wheel.
One stand per estate only.

Name: Level 4 Aetherial Wheel Stand
Description:
A metal stand upon which aetherial wheels are placed and spun to charge. Holds two grade 1, one grade 2, and one grade 3 wheel.
One stand per estate only.

Name: Level 5 Aetherial Wheel Stand
Description:
A metal stand upon which aetherial wheels are placed and spun to charge. Holds two grade 1, two grade 2, and one grade 3 wheel.
One stand per estate only.

Name: Level 6 Aetherial Wheel Stand
Description:
A metal stand upon which aetherial wheels are placed and spun to charge. Holds three grade 1, two grade 2, and one grade 3 wheel.
One stand per estate only.

Name: Ironworks Belt of Scouting
Description: Before becoming obsolete due to advancements in tailoring, belts such as this were used for holding up trousers and the like.

Name: Augmented Ironworks Leg Guards of Scouting
Augmented Ironworks Belt of Scouting
Description: Before becoming obsolete due to advancements in tailoring, belts such as this were used for holding up trousers and the like.

Name: Dreadwyrm Sash of Scouting
Description: Before becoming obsolete due to advancements in tailoring, belts such as this were used for holding up trousers and the like.

Name: Kirimu Belt of Scouting
Description: Before becoming obsolete due to advancements in tailoring, belts such as this were used for holding up trousers and the like.

Name: Excalibur
Description: One of the weapons wielded by the legendary Zodiac Braves.

Name: Kaiser Knuckles
Description: One of the weapons wielded by the legendary Zodiac Braves.

Name: Ragnarok
Description: One of the weapons wielded by the legendary Zodiac Braves.

Name: Longinus
Description: One of the weapons wielded by the legendary Zodiac Braves.

Name: Yoichi Bow
Description: One of the weapons wielded by the legendary Zodiac Braves.

Name: Nirvana
Description: One of the weapons wielded by the legendary Zodiac Braves.

Name: Lilith Rod
Description: One of the weapons wielded by the legendary Zodiac Braves.

Name: Apocalypse
Description: One of the weapons wielded by the legendary Zodiac Braves.

Name: Last Resort
Description: One of the weapons wielded by the legendary Zodiac Braves.

Name: Aegis Shield
Description: One of the shields borne by the legendary Zodiac Braves.

Name: Sasuke's Blades
Description: Two of the weapons wielded by the legendary Zodiac Braves.

Name: Magicked Prism (Petals)
Description: This peculiar contraption creates illusions by weaving together myriad shades of light. Produces a shower of ephemeral flower petals.

Name: Magicked Prism (Bubbles)
Description: This peculiar contraption creates illusions by weaving together myriad shades of light. Produces a shower of delicate bubbles certain to impress any Eorzean crab.

Name: Magicked Prism (Balloon)
Description: This peculiar contraption creates illusions by weaving together myriad shades of light. Releases a single lighter-than-air balloon.

Name: Magicked Prism (Heart)
Description: This peculiar contraption creates illusions by weaving together myriad shades of light. Releases a single romantic heart-shaped balloon.

Name: Book of Skylight
Description: A sacred tome depicting the valorous deeds of the Zodiac Braves, legendary heroes from a bygone era. This volume provides detailed descriptions of the mythical arms the men and women wielded.

Name: Zodium
Description: As with dark matter, zodium has the faculty to assimilate with other forms of matter, effectively restoring them to their original condition. However, unlike dark matter, which will bond only with certain materials depending on its purity, zodium appears to bond with almost everything, leading one to entertain the notion that this substance mayhap serves as one of the building blocks of all creation.

Name: Zodiac Scroll
Description: A sphere scroll designed to act as a receptacle for the soul energy stored within a relic weapon nexus.

Name: Flawless Alexandrite
Description: A variety of dark matter that possesses light-altering properties. A quick inspection reveals not a single impurity.

Name: Furnace Ring
Description: Fitted with a powerful eye of fire gemstone, this magicked band can instantly produce a white-hot flame at the command of its wearer.

Name: Perfect Firewood
Description: This expertly dried cypress exhibits a high pitch content which significantly improves its ability to burn long and hot.

Name: Perfect Mortar
Description: Despite the fact this mortar has been carefully crafted to withstand the creation of highly volatile zodium, chances are it will not survive the process.

Name: Perfect Pestle
Description: Despite the fact this pestle has been carefully crafted to withstand the creation of highly volatile zodium, chances are it will not survive the process.

Name: Perfect Vellum
Description: Meticulous pouncing has ensured that any ink applied to this dried calfskin will adhere without fail.

Name: Perfect Pounce
Description: An alchemical powder of a highly resinous texture used to not only prevent ink from spreading when applied to vellum, but to also maintain a high level of aetherial conductivity.

Name: Tailor-made Eel Pie
Description: The acetic odor emitted by this specially crafted pastry will turn away all but the most loyal of eel pie enthusiasts.

Name: Perfect Cloth
Description: A better balance of warp and weft has not been seen for centuries.

Name: Cypress Log
Description: A rough-cut log of cypress timber.

Name: Pumice
Description: Volcanic rock riddled with countless tiny holes which make the stone remarkably lighter than it appears. Parchment makers rub the pieces on vellum to prepare the pages for receiving ink.

Name: Belah'dian Silver
Description: Discovered buried deep within Belah'dian ruins, this surprisingly heat-resistant silver appears to have been tempered using a technique now lost to modern goldsmiths.

Name: Aged Eye of Fire
Description: A stone sphere elementally aspected to fire. A good polishing will be required to restore it to its former luster.

Name: Aged Spear Shaft
Description: Seasoned over countless years of use, this worn shaft may no longer be suitable for use in battle, but it will most definitely burn nicely in a fire.

Name: Aged Mortar Pieces
Description: A beautiful mortar that has, unfortunately, been split into several pieces. It is, however, not beyond repaira testament to the skill of the original crafter.

Name: Aged Pestle Pieces
Description: A beautiful pestle that has, unfortunately, been split into several pieces. It is, however, not beyond repaira testament to the skill of the original crafter.

Name: Aged Vellum
Description: A single sheet of what appears to be magicked uterine vellum torn from a quire bound within an ancient tome.

Name: Dried Ether
Description: Dry, flaky residue found at the bottom of a bottle of evaporated ether.

Name: Vintage Cooking Sherry
Description: Fine Lominsan white wine fortified with grape spirit and allowed to mature to the point of perfection, though the flavor may be too strong for weaker palates.

Name: Stained Cloth
Description: A beautiful piece of cloth that appears to have been dragged through the mud, dipped in sheep offal, and then forgotten in a latrine.

Name: Aged Ring
Description: An antiquated ring of unknown origin.

Name: Aged Spear
Description: An antiquated spear of unknown origin.

Name: Aged Mortar
Description: An antiquated mortar of unknown origin.

Name: Aged Pestle
Description: An antiquated pestle of unknown origin.

Name: Aged Grimoire
Description: An antiquated grimoire of unknown origin.

Name: Aged Phial
Description: An antiquated phial of unknown origin.

Name: Aged Decanter
Description: An antiquated decanter of unknown origin.

Name: Aged Robe
Description: An antiquated robe of unknown origin.

Name: Bronze Lake Crystal
Description: Discovered growing on the floor of Bronze Lake, this heretofore unseen aetherial formation appears to be impossibly aspected to two different elementswind and water.

Name: Bombard Core
Description: Gathered from the smoldering carcass of a Bombard during the most recent invasion and carefully stored in an underground cellar, this core remains red-hot despite being long removed from its owner.

Name: Sacred Spring Water
Description: Bottled from a spring found atop one of the Far East's holiest peaks, this water is believed to contain a vast amount of highly concentrated aetherial energy.

Name: Magicked Prism (Wings)
Description: This peculiar contraption creates illusions by weaving together myriad shades of light. Produces a pair of seraphic wings.

Name: Allagan Resin
Description: A multi-purpose aetherochemical concoction devised by the Allagans for use in many of their creations.

Name: Furite Sand
Description: Midnight black sand consisting of tiny grains of the rare ore furite.

Name: Brass Kettle
Description: A stunning teapotneither too short, nor too stoutforged by master craftsman Gerolt in his never-ending pursuit of the perfect kettle.

Name: Promise of Innocence (Standard)
Description: This wristlet signifies a standard agreement between two individuals to form an everlasting spiritual union. To use, both individuals must equip their promise wristlets, form a two-member party, and then speak with ceremony planner Claribel at the Sanctum of the Twelve.

Name: Promise of Passion (Gold)
Description: This wristlet signifies a gold-clad agreement between two individuals to form an everlasting spiritual union. To use, both individuals must equip their promise wristlets, form a two-member party, and then speak with ceremony planner Claribel at the Sanctum of the Twelve.

Name: Promise of Devotion (Platinum)
Description: This wristlet signifies a platinum-clad agreement between two individuals to form an everlasting spiritual union. To use, both individuals must equip their promise wristlets, form a two-member party, and then speak with ceremony planner Claribel at the Sanctum of the Twelve.

Name: Diamond Dust
Description: An icy crystal that harbors the power of the Lady of Frost.

Name: Proof of Covering
Description: An official deed documenting the covering of two select breeding chocobos, and granting ownership of the fledgling born of said coupling. The fledgling can be collected after the date specified above.

Name: Fledgling Chocobo Registration G1-M
Description: Official registration for a grade 1 male chocobo. Submit to a Chocobo Square representative to register the bird for chocobo racing.

Description: Official registration for a grade 2 male chocobo. Submit to a Chocobo Square representative to register the bird for chocobo racing.

Name: Grade 1 Feed - Speed Blend
Description: A simple blend of cereals and leafy greens believed to slightly improve a race chocobo's maximum speed.

Name: Grade 2 Feed - Speed Blend
Description: A complex blend of cereals and leafy greens believed to improve a race chocobo's maximum speed.

Name: Grade 3 Feed - Special Speed Blend
Description: A secret blend of cereals and leafy greens believed to significantly improve a race chocobo's maximum speed.

Name: Grade 1 Feed - Acceleration Blend
Description: A simple blend of cereals and leafy greens believed to slightly improve a race chocobo's acceleration.

Name: Grade 2 Feed - Acceleration Blend
Description: A complex blend of cereals and leafy greens believed to improve a race chocobo's acceleration.

Name: Grade 3 Feed - Special Acceleration Blend
Description: A secret blend of cereals and leafy greens believed to significantly improve a race chocobo's acceleration.

Name: Grade 2 Feed - Balance Blend
Description: A complex blend of cereals and leafy greens believed to improve a race chocobo's cunning.

Name: Grade 3 Feed - Special Balance Blend
Description: A secret blend of cereals and leafy greens believed to significantly improve a race chocobo's cunning.

Description: A complex blend of cereals and leafy greens believed to improve a race chocobo's endurance.

Name: Grade 2 Wheel of Confrontation
Description: A cylindrical wheel crafted from metal and aspected crystal which, when placed on a stand and spun repeatedly, accumulates an aetherial charge. When fully primed, the wheel can be used to initiate the company action The Heat of Battle II (increased EXP earned through battle).

Name: Grade 2 Wheel of Productivity
Description: A cylindrical wheel crafted from metal and aspected crystal which, when placed on a stand and spun repeatedly, accumulates an aetherial charge. When fully primed, the wheel can be used to initiate the company action Earth and Water II (increased EXP earned through gathering).

Name: Grade 2 Wheel of Industry
Description: A cylindrical wheel crafted from metal and aspected crystal which, when placed on a stand and spun repeatedly, accumulates an aetherial charge. When fully primed, the wheel can be used to initiate the company action Helping Hand II (increased EXP earned through crafting).

Name: Grade 2 Wheel of Longeing
Description: A cylindrical wheel crafted from metal and aspected crystal which, when placed on a stand and spun repeatedly, accumulates an aetherial charge. When fully primed, the wheel can be used to initiate the company action A Man's Best Friend II (increased EXP earned by companions).

Name: Grade 2 Wheel of Rivalry
Description: A cylindrical wheel crafted from metal and aspected crystal which, when placed on a stand and spun repeatedly, accumulates an aetherial charge. When fully primed, the wheel can be used to initiate the company action Mark Up II (increased Wolf Marks).

Name: Grade 2 Wheel of Company
Description: A cylindrical wheel crafted from metal and aspected crystal which, when placed on a stand and spun repeatedly, accumulates an aetherial charge. When fully primed, the wheel can be used to initiate the company action Seal Sweetener II (increased company seals).

Name: Grade 2 Wheel of Initiation
Description: A cylindrical wheel crafted from metal and aspected crystal which, when placed on a stand and spun repeatedly, accumulates an aetherial charge. When fully primed, the wheel can be used to initiate the company action Brave New World II (increased attributes for all Disciple of War or Magic members under level 49).

Name: Grade 2 Wheel of Capacity
Description: A cylindrical wheel crafted from metal and aspected crystal which, when placed on a stand and spun repeatedly, accumulates an aetherial charge. When fully primed, the wheel can be used to initiate the company action Live off the Land II (increased Gathering).

Name: Grade 2 Wheel of Observation
Description: A cylindrical wheel crafted from metal and aspected crystal which, when placed on a stand and spun repeatedly, accumulates an aetherial charge. When fully primed, the wheel can be used to initiate the company action What You See II (increased Perception).

Name: Grade 2 Wheel of Efficiency
Description: A cylindrical wheel crafted from metal and aspected crystal which, when placed on a stand and spun repeatedly, accumulates an aetherial charge. When fully primed, the wheel can be used to initiate the company action Eat from the Hand II (increased Craftsmanship).

Name: Grade 2 Wheel of Precision
Description: A cylindrical wheel crafted from metal and aspected crystal which, when placed on a stand and spun repeatedly, accumulates an aetherial charge. When fully primed, the wheel can be used to initiate the company action In Control II (increased Control).

Name: Grade 2 Wheel of Dedication

Name: Pine Bonsai
Description: While some view this traditional Doman gardening technique as naught more than a reflection of man's arrogance in believing nature can be bent to his will, most simply find it a beautiful and calming form of art.

Name: Longcase Chronometer
Description: A precision instrument for telling time. Its towering silhouette adds a touch of gravitas to the ambience of any room.

Name: Oriental Bathtub
Description: A large bathtub designed in the Doman fashion.

Name: Frolicking Beasts
Description: A folding partition commonly found in Far East nations. Upon one side is a reproduction of an ancient Doman wall painting depicting a variety of beastkin in their natural habitat.

Name: Kotatsu Table
Description: A table designed in the Doman fashion. The underside has been treated with strange Eastern magicks to emit heat during the winter months.

Name: Wax Vegetables
Description: While far less nutritious than real vegetables, these wax replicas will look nicer in your pantry.

Name: Guildleve Counter
Description: A counter designed to replicate those found in Adventurers' Guilds across Eorzea. This model comes complete with a built-in light that can be used to illuminate leve plates.

Name: Egg Floor Lamp
Description: A Hatching-tide-themed floor lamp.

Name: Glade Tea Set
Description:
For the denizens of the Twelveswood, the consumption of tea is a means of relaxing the mind, allowing for uninhibited communion with nature.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Spell Speed Bonus: +4% (Max 12)
  VIT Bonus: +4% (Max 7)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +2
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Riviera Supper
Description:
While for most La Nosceans supper consists of huddling around a fire pit while sopping up a splash of rancid fish stew with a hunk of moldy bread, those who have found their fortune on the seas prefer a multiple-course extravaganza certain to leave even the most wealthy Ul'dahn speechless.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Determination Bonus: +4% (Max 4)
  VIT Bonus: +4% (Max 5)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +2
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Oasis Breakfast
Description:
Considered the most important of the day's seven meals (preceding both pre-midday mead and eleventh bell tarts), the Ul'dahn elite rarely miss this opportunity to gorge themselves before moving on to the next opportunity to gorge themselves.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Critical Hit Bonus: +4% (Max 21)
  VIT Bonus: +4% (Max 13)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Scattered Documents
Description: This pile of parchment appears to be pages taken from The Last Paeana detailed account of the life and times of a legendary bard who traveled the realm bringing joy to all he met. Strewn across one's bureau, the documents give any library or study a heightened air of sophistication.

Name: Oriental Altar
Description: A miniature wooden altar hung in Doman houses, allowing people to worship the gods within the privacy of their own homes.

Name: Oriental Wall Scroll
Description: Upon this ornamental scroll is painted the Doman character jin, meaning mankind.

Name: Oriental Partition
Description: A partition designed in the Doman fashion, reaching to the ceiling and so sturdy that it may as well be a wall.

Name: Dead Man's Chest
Description: If the man who once owned the chest is now dead, he won't mind anyone else using it. Such was the logic employed when removing this sturdy treasure coffer from Sastasha.

Name: Oak Low Barrel Planter
Description: A barrel planter crafted from oak.

Name: Valentione's Cake
Description:
A decadent chocolate cake emblazoned with the House Valentione coat of arms.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  VIT Bonus: +4% (Max 18)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +2
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Royal Partition
Description: A luxurious partition designed to resemble those used in the sultana's palace.

Name: Order of Nald'thal Lectern
Description: A carved wooden podium not unlike the ones used by the Order of Nald'thal to deliver their sermons.

Name: Green Tea Set
Description:
Far more bitter than its black counterpart, green tea is by far the beverage of choice in Far Eastern Doma. To offset the sharpness of its flavor, it is oft accompanied by something sweet, such as sticky rice cakes.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  VIT Bonus: +4% (Max 13)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +2
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Dried Well
Description: Have you dreamed of owning your very own well, but are plagued by one or more of the following psychological ailments: acrophobia, claustrophobia, aquaphobia, bathophobia, or cleithrophobia? Well fear no longer. This quality stone well, manufactured in Eorzea with 100% Eorzean materials, requires no hole to be dug, no ground to be sanctified, and no chain letters to be passed along to your dearest enemies.

Name: Oriental Striking Dummy
Description:
A striking dummy designed in the Doman fashion.

Up to three dummies may be placed in a single estate, regardless of type.

Name: Eastern Cherry Tree
Description: A variety of cherry tree from the Far East modified through generations of grafting and crossbreeding to bloom perpetually.

Name: Crimson Felt Mat
Description: A square sheet of crimson-colored felt upon which dolls are displayed for Little Ladies' Day.

Name: Flame of Passion
Description: Outdoor lighting certain to heat up any relationship.

Name: Wild Banana Tree
Description: A green, leafy tree transplanted from an island in the Cieldalaes. The word banana is actually a bastardization of pamama, the term used in the fruit's native habitat.

Name: Personal Astroscope
Description: A miniature astroscope used by aspiring astrologians to peer into the farthest reaches of the firmament.

Name: Riviera Garden Table Set
Description: A round outdoor table and matching chairs designed in the riviera fashion.

Name: Dodo's Nest
Description: Though their beady eyes and awkward walk give them an air of unintelligence, dodos are actually quite clever creatures. A mother dodo will, when creating a nest, first dry grass in the sun for several days before adding it to the pile, so as to prevent the growth of molds harmful to her offspring.

Name: Retainer Cartonnier
Description:
A wooden receptacle for use by retainers to store goods entrusted for sale while protecting them from the elements.
Can only be placed outdoors.

Name: Retainer Counter
Description:
A wooden counter for use by retainers.
Can only be placed outdoors.

Name: Spotted Interior Wall
Description: An interior wall bespeckled with a hypnotically random pattern of colorful dots certain to drive any sane man to his wit's end.

Name: Wavy Interior Wall
Description: An interior wall covered from top to bottom in colorful wavy lines certain to induce seasickness in even the most hardened sailor.

Name: Tatami Flooring
Description: Woven from sweet-smelling rush grass, tatami flooring is the perfect complement to any home furnished in the Doman fashion.

Name: Monochrome Flooring
Description: Marble floor tiling alternately colored black and white.

Name: Oasis Cobble Flooring
Description: Cobbles commonly used in Ul'dahn roadways and plazas.

Name: Star Chandelier
Description: Ceiling-mounted lighting expertly crafted to resemble the moon and stars.

Name: Chocobo Training Manual - Choco Dash I
Description:
A comprehensive manual detailing chocobo training methods developed by experts across the realm. Use to teach your race chocobo the ability Choco Dash.

Ability Effect: Temporarily boosts speed without depleting stamina.
Duration:  1s

Name: Chocobo Training Manual - Choco Dash II
Description:
A comprehensive manual detailing chocobo training methods developed by experts across the realm. Use to teach your race chocobo the ability Choco Dash II.

Ability Effect: Temporarily boosts speed without depleting stamina.
Duration:  2s

Name: Chocobo Training Manual - Choco Dash III
Description:
A comprehensive manual detailing chocobo training methods developed by experts across the realm. Use to teach your race chocobo the ability Choco Dash III.

Ability Effect: Temporarily boosts speed without depleting stamina.
Duration:  3s

Name: Chocobo Training Manual - Choco Cure I
Description:
A comprehensive manual detailing chocobo training methods developed by experts across the realm. Use to teach your race chocobo the ability Choco Cure.

Ability Effect: Restores 6% of total stamina.

Name: Chocobo Training Manual - Choco Cure II
Description:
A comprehensive manual detailing chocobo training methods developed by experts across the realm. Use to teach your race chocobo the ability Choco Cure II.

Ability Effect: Restores 9% of total stamina.

Name: Chocobo Training Manual - Choco Cure III
Description:
A comprehensive manual detailing chocobo training methods developed by experts across the realm. Use to teach your race chocobo the ability Choco Cure III.

Ability Effect: Restores 12% of total stamina.

Name: Chocobo Training Manual - Choco Esuna I
Description:
A comprehensive manual detailing chocobo training methods developed by experts across the realm. Use to teach your race chocobo the ability Choco Esuna.

Ability Effect: Removes all current enfeeblements with a 75% success rate.

Name: Chocobo Training Manual - Choco Esuna II
Description:
A comprehensive manual detailing chocobo training methods developed by experts across the realm. Use to teach your race chocobo the ability Choco Esuna II.

Ability Effect: Removes all current enfeeblements with a 90% success rate.

Name: Chocobo Training Manual - Choco Esuna III
Description:
A comprehensive manual detailing chocobo training methods developed by experts across the realm. Use to teach your race chocobo the ability Choco Esuna III.

Ability Effect: Removes all current enfeeblements with a 100% success rate.

Name: Chocobo Training Manual - Choco Ease I

Name: Lethe Water
Description: A strong-smelling tonic made by distilling the leaves of a variety of ginger found only in the Far East. While used mainly as a cure for bad breath, one of its side effects is memory loss, prompting chocobo trainers to employ the potable when wishing to unteach an ability or trait.

Name: Thorne Dynasty Map
Description:
A faded map detailing the location of treasure buried during the rule of House Thorne.

Use the action Decipher to extract the map and examine its contents.
Level 40 recommended.
