Name: Model Magitek Bit
Description:
An exact 1:9 scale replica of a ceruleum-powered magitek bit (Ultima Weapon action figure not included).

Use item to acquire the model magitek bit minion.

Name: Puff of Darkness
Description:
When standing nearby, prithee refrain from coughing, sneezing, waving, flailing, or performing any other means of wild gesticulation, lest the puff be lost for eternity.

Use item to acquire the puff of Darkness minion.

Name: Wind-up Gentleman
Description:
If clockwork Hildibrand doesn't quite roll off the tongue, both minion of enquiry and mammet extraordinaire are acceptable alternatives.

Use item to acquire the wind-up gentleman minion.

Name: Wind-up Alphinaud
Description:
Perfect for international summits, family get-togethers, pre- or post-battle gatherings, or any other occasion where the recapitulation of past occurrences is absolutely, positively necessary.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Alphinaud minion.

Name: Wind-up Alisaie
Description:
For those who believe the better half deserves more time in the spotlight.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Alisaie minion.

Name: Enkidu
Description:
That green is not coming out, even with multiple washings.

Use item to acquire the Enkidu minion.

Name: Platinum Triad Card
Description: One of twelve unbelievably high rarity Triple Triad cards.

Name: Adamantoise Whistle
Description: A small polished whistle carved from thick turtle shell. Emits a low-pitched tone which summons an adamantoise mount to your side.

Name: Fenrir Horn
Description: A gilded horn that, when blown, summons a purebred Abalathian hoarhound mount named after its pack's legendary leader.

Name: Kirin Fife
Description: A magicked pipe that, when blown, summons the mythical Kirin to your side.

Name: Logistics System Identification Key
Description: A thin, rectangular piece of some unknown material. Placing it near your reprogrammed logistics system will magically bring the machine to life.

Name: Paramour Barding
Description: A gaudy suit of chocobo armor designed for use during Valentione's Day celebrations.

Name: Gambler Barding
Description: Chocobo armor designed to replicate the lavish accoutrements of a legendary gambler.

Name: Modern Aesthetics - Ponytails
Description:
The realm's premier publication on beauty and fashion, this specific copy of Modern Aesthetics covers, in detail, techniques on tying the perfect ponytail.

Use to unlock a new hairstyle at the aesthetician.

Name: Gold Saucer Ticket
Description: Redeem for one free play at any of the Manderville Gold Saucer mini attractions (Jumbo Cactpot, Mini Cactpot, chocobo racing, and Triple Triad not included).

Name: Tinker's Calm
Description:
A tonic commonly used by Disciples of the Hand to increase focus, allowing for enhanced results when deconstructing complex creations.

Duration: 10m

Name: Lucky Egg
Description: A plain white Archon egg believed to bring its bearer good luck as long as it remains uncracked.

Name: Nanapasi's Happy Smile Super Wish Bag
Description: Nanapasi originally wished to name his gift-filled sack the Happy Smile Super Challenge Family Wish Bag, but it would not fit neatly on one line, forcing him to compromise.

Name: Moth-eaten Doll Parts
Description: A collection of antique dolls dating back to the Thorne Dynasty. The miniature costumes are in a sorry state, most being moth-eaten and threadbare.

Name: Splintered Chest
Description: This chest, rumored to have once been stored aboard the Haarthe flagship of the dread pirate Mistbeardappears to have been not-so-gently pried open with a headsman's axe.

Name: Wild Banana Shoot
Description: Under the proper conditions, this seedling will grow into a tree almost ten fulms high, and produce upwards of four score bananas per season.

Name: Black Limestone
Description: When polished, this rare form of limestone closely resembles marble.

Name: Virgin Basilisk Egg
Description: While all eggs a basilisk lays contain traces of rare ore, the first egg laid in life is thought to contain the highest concentration, making it highly sought after by potion mixers and alchemists.

Name: Little Worm
Description: While commonly used as bait by fishers across the realm, little worms also make fine chocobo feed, providing a good source of protein for growing birds.

Name: Gregarious Worm
Description: A rare form of earthworm, these fat invertebrates also make fine chocobo feed, providing an excellent source of protein for growing birds.

Name: Rosemary
Description: A savory herb treasured for its ability to enhance focus and concentration.

Name: Yafaemi Wildgrass
Description: After gysahl greens, there's no other verdure a race chocobo would rather sink its beak into.

Name: Mazlaya Greens
Description: Once found growing all across the island of Mazlaya, this bright-green plant was almost completely wiped out when chocobos brought to the island by farmers devoured nearly every one they could find.

Name: Unaspected Crystal
Description: For reasons unknown to you, this crystal has completely lost its elemental charge.

Name: Petrified Orb
Description: A perfect sphere carved from a petrified tree and polished to enhance its natural luster.

Name: Mummer's Daggers
Description: A decorated pair of knives used by mummers in their traveling grotesqueries. The blades have been dulled to prevent injury.

Name: Lapdog Collar Bell
Description: A tiny copper bell commonly affixed to the collars of Ul'dahn lapdogs to inform owners the location of their precious pets.

Name: Fluorite Lens
Description: Carved from a shard of clear fluorite, this lens exhibits higher optical performance than a normal glass lens.

Name: Patent Leather
Description: Saurian leather that has been treated with linseed oil to give it a glossy black finish.

Name: Camlet
Description: An expensive fabric woven from camel hair. Imitations are common, though this piece appears to be legitimate.

Name: Enchanted Quicksilver
Description: This sample of hydrargyrum has been imbued with powerful magicks.

Name: Duck Broth
Description: While this broth can be made by simply boiling down the bones of a duck, true culinarians make it a point to brown the bones before adding them to a mixture of savory vegetables and fresh spring water.

Name: Talan's Seal of Mining Mastery
Description: A document bearing master crafter Talan's personal seal. Can be presented in exchange for unparalleled mining equipment.

Name: Talan's Seal of Botany Mastery
Description: A document bearing master crafter Talan's personal seal. Can be presented in exchange for unparalleled botanist's equipment.

Name: Talan's Seal of Fishing Mastery
Description: A document bearing master crafter Talan's personal seal. Can be presented in exchange for unparalleled fishing equipment.

Name: Urushi
Description: Made from the caustic sap of lacquer trees native to the Far East, urushi is used to protect wood by giving it a hard, glossy finish.

Name: Composite Whetstone
Description: A heavy whetstone that appears to be man-made, rather than carved from naturally occurring rock.

Name: Heat-resistant Plaster
Description: Due to its heat-resistant properties, this plaster is oft used to create molds for metalworking.

Name: Clear Fluorite
Description: A rare form of fluorite completely devoid of any interior flaws.

Name: Lampblack Linseed Oil
Description: Linseed oil mixed with soot collected from oil lamps to give it a deep-black color.

Name: Camel Hair
Description: Thick, brown hair of a Near Eastern monstrosity known as the camel. Dubious reports from sailors claim the beast stands thrice as high as a chocobo, can speak the tongues of man, and has massive humps upon its back which may contain water, wine, or even gold.

Name: Black Cinnabar
Description: A form of cinnabar known to contain traces of quicksilver.

Name: Duck Bones
Description: It is an oft-forgotten fact that Frandelont Raimdelle, famed naturalist, father of modern taxonomy, and author of the Raimdelle Codex, tried multiple times (without success) to classify the common duckmost obviously a cloudkinas a spoken, believing their incessant quackings to be a highly developed language beyond the comprehension of mankind.

Name: Magicked Oilcloth
Description: Linen cloth treated with magicked oil. When wrapped about ore or metal, it prevents the slow yet gradual diffusion of elemental charge from the material.

Name: Bamboo Paper
Description: Thinly sliced bamboo used to preserve the aroma of rare fragrant wood.

Name: Glacier Crystal
Description: A crystal aspected to both ice and water. House chefs for wealthy and noble families will oft use these rare specimens to chill ales and white wines during the summer moons.

Name: Gigant Clam
Description:
An especially large giant clam. Local fisher estimates put the age of this wavekin at over five score years.

[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Moonstone
Description: A type of mineral that, when polished, emits an eerie blue glow not unlike the moon while under the influence of Thaliak.

Name: Unstained Mark Log
Description: A list of elite marks slain by the log's owner...before the owner herself...fled the battlefield to hunt another day. Though such documents were once considered highly valuable, demand has dried up and they are now essentially worthless.

Name: Bronze Triad Card
Description: One of fifteen low rarity Triple Triad cards.

Name: Silver Triad Card
Description: One of fourteen medium rarity Triple Triad cards.

Name: Gold Triad Card
Description: One of fifteen high rarity Triple Triad cards.

Name: MGP Voucher
Description: Redeemable for 100 Manderville Gold Saucer points (MGP).

Name: Better Crowned Pie
Description:
A galette-style pie decorated with a golden crown and served at Ishgardian festivals. Baked using Talan's own special recipe.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Grade 2 Feed - Special Speed Blend
Description: A secret blend of cereals and leafy greens believed to improve a race chocobo's maximum speed.

Name: Grade 2 Feed - Special Acceleration Blend
Description: A secret blend of cereals and leafy greens believed to improve a race chocobo's acceleration.

Name: Grade 2 Feed - Special Balance Blend
Description: A secret blend of cereals and leafy greens believed to improve a race chocobo's cunning.

Name: Grade 2 Feed - Special Endurance Blend
Description: A secret blend of cereals and leafy greens believed to improve a race chocobo's endurance.

Name: Grade 2 Feed - Special Stamina Blend
Description: A secret blend of cereals and leafy greens believed to improve a race chocobo's stamina.

Name: Ceruleum Tank
Description: Airship-grade refined ceruleum. Required to fuel vessels traveling to the Sea of Clouds on exploratory voyages. Can also be used in submersibles on subaquatic voyages.

Name: Bronco-type Hull
Description: A reliable hull used in most Highwind Skyways airships.

Name: Invincible-type Hull
Description: A large hull adapted from those used in seafaring galleys.

Name: Enterprise-type Hull
Description: A hull designed by Cid for use in his personal airship the Enterprise.

Name: Invincible II-type Hull
Description: A modified version of the Invincible-type hull, redesigned to reduce wind resistance.

Name: Odyssey-type Hull
Description: The reinforced keel of this unique airship is specially tailored to long voyages.

Name: Tatanora-type Hull
Description: Named after the father of propeller-powered airships, the design used in this hull is certain to invoke a sense of inspiring nostalgia.

Name: Bronco-type Sail
Description: A simple yet highly durable sheet of thick canvas designed to serve both as a receptacle for lighter-than-air ceruleum gas, as well as a sail to assist propulsion.

Name: Invincible-type Propellers
Description: Airship lift is achieved by the rapid spinning of ceruleum-powered propellers mounted atop masts placed around the fore and aft decks.

Name: Enterprise-type Bladder
Description: The unique shape of this ceruleum gas bladder directs the flow of air around it, reducing wind resistance.

Name: Invincible II-type Propellers
Description: Speed and flight stability have been increased by adding auxiliary propulsive wings to the ship's masts.

Name: Odyssey-type Bladders
Description: Separate gas regulation control over each bladder allows for increased navigational efficiency.

Name: Tatanora-type Propellers
Description: Taking inspiration from the aether-manipulating flying fish found in the Sea of Clouds, these radical new propellers have been treated with wind-aspected crystals, allowing for increased lift.

Name: Bronco-type Forecastle
Description: The simply crafted front half of a Bronco-type airship, including the main deck and bowsprit.

Name: Invincible-type Forecastle
Description: The sturdily built front half of an Invincible-type airship, including the main deck, bowsprit, and a towering foremast.

Name: Enterprise-type Forecastle
Description: The front half of an Enterprise-type airship, including the main deck, bowsprit, and extra lighting to improve nighttime navigation.

Name: Invincible II-type Forecastle
Description: The front half of an Invincible II-type airship, including the main deck, bowsprit, and a towering foremast. Wooden parts have been replaced with lightweight metal to improve vessel durability.

Name: Odyssey-type Forecastle
Description: The front half of an Odyssey-type airship, including the main deck, bowsprit, an extended hold, and specially designed cooling pipes.

Name: Tatanora-type Forecastle
Description: The front half of a Tatanora-type airship, including the main deck, bowsprit, and banks for extra propellers.

Name: Bronco-type Aftcastle
Description: The simply crafted rear half of a Bronco-type airship, including the poop deck, ceruleum engine, tiller, and rudder.

Name: Invincible-type Aftcastle
Description: The sturdily built rear half of an Invincible-type airship, including the quarter and poop decks, tiller, rudder, ceruleum engine, and two propeller masts.

Name: Enterprise-type Aftcastle
Description: The rear half of an Enterprise-type airship, including the quarter and poop decks, tiller, rudder, ceruleum engine, and an all-purpose crane for extracting items, or on rare occasions, people in distress.

Name: Invincible II-type Aftcastle
Description: The rear half of an Invincible II-type airship, including the quarter and poop decks, tiller, rudder, ceruleum engine, and an all-purpose crane equipped with powerful claws.

Name: Odyssey-type Aftcastle
Description: The rear half of an Odyssey-type airship, including the poop deck, tiller, rudder, and an experimental aetherial propulsion engine.

Name: Tatanora-type Aftcastle
Description: The rear half of a Tatanora-type airship, including the quarter and poop decks, tiller, rudder, ceruleum engine, and tailplane for improved maneuverability.

Name: Centurio Seal
Description: Currency minted by Clan Centurio and distributed as requital for the successful completion of Clan Hunt bills.

Name: Blue Crafters' Scrip
Description: Currency paid to Disciples of the Hand by Rowena's House of Splendors in exchange for services rendered. Can be used to purchase items from the aforementioned establishment. Not valid anywhere else on Hydaelyn.

Name: Red Crafters' Scrip
Description: Currency paid to Disciples of the Hand by Rowena's House of Splendors in exchange for services rendered. Can be used to purchase items from the aforementioned establishment. Not valid anywhere else on Hydaelyn.

Name: Blue Gatherers' Scrip
Description: Currency paid to Disciples of the Land by Rowena's House of Splendors in exchange for services rendered. Can be used to purchase items from the aforementioned establishment. Not valid anywhere else on Hydaelyn.

Name: Red Gatherers' Scrip
Description: Currency paid to Disciples of the Land by Rowena's House of Splendors in exchange for services rendered. Can be used to purchase items from the aforementioned establishment. Not valid anywhere else on Hydaelyn.

Description: Fits: All

Description: Fits: All

Description: Fits: All

Description: Fits: All

Name: Striped Southern Seas Vest
Description: Fits: All

Name: Striped Southern Seas Swimsuit
Description: Fits: All

Name: Doman Whetstone
Description: A smooth black stone used in the Far East to sharpen blades. Recommended for the upkeep of Doman weapons. However, advances in crafting technology have rendered it obsolete.

Name: Doman Urushi
Description: A thick black resin used in the Far East to treat wood and metal. Recommended for the upkeep of Doman battle gear. However, advances in crafting technology have rendered it obsolete.

Name: Raw Doman Urushi
Description: A thick amber resin used in the Far East to treat wood and metal. Recommended for the upkeep of Doman accessories. However, advances in crafting technology have rendered it obsolete.

Name: Illuminati Gobdip
Description: An alchemical potion concocted in the dark laboratoriums of the Illuminati. Some of the realm's more daring blacksmiths have applied the unnaturally viscous substance to a variety of weapons and found that it heightens the attributes of certain ancient martial artifacts. However, advances in crafting technology have rendered it obsolete.

Name: Illuminati Gobtwine
Description: An alchemical thread woven in the dark laboratoriums of the Illuminati. Some of the realm's more daring weavers have applied the unnaturally pliable substance to a variety of vestments and found that it heightens the attributes of certain ancient martial artifacts. However, advances in crafting technology have rendered it obsolete.

Name: Illuminati Gobcoat
Description: An alchemical potion concocted in the dark laboratoriums of the Illuminati. Some of the realm's more daring goldsmiths have applied the unnaturally illuminated substance to a variety of gems and found that it heightens the attributes of certain ancient martial artifacts. However, advances in crafting technology have rendered it obsolete.

Name: Battered Fish
Description:
Deep-fried and accompanied by a generous portion of thick cut popotoes. Most delicious when sprinkled with a dash of malt vinegar.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Faire Voucher MMXV
Description: Currency minted and distributed by the Adventurers' Guild for use during the Moonfire Faire.

Name: Dark Matter Cluster

One per estate only.

Name: Deep Hive Ceiling Fan

A ceiling-mounted fan created with the wings of the Gnathic primal Ravana. It literally hums with the Lord of the Hive's untamed power.

Description: Before becoming obsolete due to advancements in tailoring, belts such as this were used for holding up trousers and the like.

Name: Wyvernskin Field Belt
Description: Before becoming obsolete due to advancements in tailoring, belts such as this were used for holding up trousers and the like.

Name: Dragonskin Belt of Gathering
Description: Before becoming obsolete due to advancements in tailoring, belts such as this were used for holding up trousers and the like.

Name: Griffin Leather Survival Belt
Description: Before becoming obsolete due to advancements in tailoring, belts such as this were used for holding up trousers and the like.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - The Bomb Dance
Description: An illustrated manual of the various steps that comprise the festive bomb dance. Use to learn the /bombdance emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Improper Greetings
Description: An illustrated manual of vulgar greeting customs from faraway lands. Use to learn the /fistbump emote.

Name: Heavenscracker
Description: An unexpected by-product of the Skysteel Manufactory's recent endeavors to develop a more volatile variety of firesand. Happy Moonfire Faire!

Name: The Primogs
Description:
The only mechanical musicians this side of Black Tea Brook...making them the greatest mechanical musicians this side of Black Tea Brook.

Use item to acquire the Primogs minion.

Name: Chocobo Chick Courier
Description:
It may not be in your best interest to entrust him with any important missives just yet.

Use item to acquire the chocobo chick courier minion.

Name: Wind-up Kain
Description:
A few moments may be needed to allow him to regain control of himself.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Kain minion.

Name: Wind-up Tataru
Description:
Prepare to have your heart melt.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Tataru minion.

Name: Wind-up Cid
Description:
When asked, if he had a granddaughter, what would he like to see her named, the Ironworks founder replied, Gertrude.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Cid minion.

Name: Unicolt
Description:
Because two horns are not always better than one.

Use item to acquire the unicolt minion.

Name: Wind-up Gundu Warrior
Description:
He weighs far less than he appears.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Gundu warrior minion.

Name: Atrophied Atomos
Description:
Putting money where this voidsent's mouth is merely results in devoured money.

Use item to acquire the atrophied Atomos minion.

Name: Owlet
Description:
Who needs eyes in the back of their head when you can spin your head full circle?

Use item to acquire the owlet minion.

Name: Ugly Duckling
Description:
Will he turn into a graceful swan? Inquiring minds want to know.

Use item to acquire the ugly duckling minion.

Name: Gaelikitten
Description:
Rumors that the gods kill one of these adorable creatures every time a young man thinks pleasurable thoughts are unfounded.

Use item to acquire the gaelikitten minion.

Name: Clockwork Barrow
Description:
Take a load off your shoulders. You deserve it.

Use item to acquire the clockwork barrow minion.

Name: Lesser Panda
Description:
Lesser only in size to normal pandas. And in life expectancy. And intelligence. And fluffiness. Well, perhaps not fluffiness.

Use item to acquire the lesser panda minion.

Name: Page 63
Description:
A detailed recapitulation of the preceding sixty-two pages is not necessary to fully enjoy the content of the sixty-third.

Use item to acquire the page 63 minion.

Name: Iron Dwarf
Description:
He prefers the term little iron person.

Use item to acquire the iron dwarf minion.

Name: Griffin Hatchling
Description:
Not to be confused with a gryphon hatchling, a griffon hatchling, a gryfon hatchling, or a gryphus hatchling.

Use item to acquire the griffin hatchling minion.

Name: Wind-up Iceheart
Description:
Too hot to handle, too cold to hold.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Iceheart minion.

Name: Gestahl
Description:
He's a cute puppy dog. Yes, he is. Yes, he is a cute puppy dog. A cute puppy dog, yes, he is. Awww, such a cute puppy dog... Yes...

Use item to acquire the Gestahl minion.

Name: Steam-powered Gobwalker G-VII
Description:
Gobwalker exhaust can be used to steam hams.

Use item to acquire the steam-powered gobwalker G-VII minion.

Name: Behemoth Heir
Description:
Currently forty-seventh in line to the behemoth throne.

Use item to acquire the behemoth heir minion.

Name: Accompaniment Node
Description:
Marvel at the advanced accompaniment technology of the Allagan Empire.

Use item to acquire the accompaniment node minion.

Name: Wind-up Yugiri
Description:
Her mask may significantly hold far less mystery than it once did.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Yugiri minion.

Name: Peridot Carbuncle
Description:
If ever unfaithful, return for a full refund.

Use item to acquire the Peridot Carbuncle minion.

Name: Heliodor Carbuncle
Description:
If ever unfaithful, return for a full refund.

Use item to acquire the Heliodor Carbuncle minion.

Name: Gold Rush Minecart
Description:
Unsurprisingly void of gold.

Use item to acquire the gold rush minecart minion.

Name: Sanuwa Horn
Description: A small bone whistle that, when blown, emits a piercing tone that resembles the cry of a sanuwa fledgling. Use to summon your sanuwa mount.

Name: Griffin Horn
Description: A large curved horn that emits a tone so deep, it is undetectable by the ears of man. Griffins however can hear the somber note from hundreds of malms away, and will be immediately drawn to the sound.

Name: Manacutter Key
Description: An iron key that completes the circuit connecting a manacutter's steering mechanism with its engine.

Name: Panther Bell
Description: When rung, this brass bell will summon a single black war panther, trained to serve his master, and his master only.

Name: Black Chocobo Whistle
Description: A small hand-carved whistle that emits a unique, high-pitched tone discernible only by a black chocobo trained from birth to recognize and respond to the sound. Use to summon your personal black chocobo.

Name: Gobwalker Gear
Description: An oddly shaped metal cog that has been removed from an Illuminati-constructed gobwalker. Using it should restore the machine's controls.

Name: Ishgardian Half Barding
Description: A lightweight suit of Ishgardian chocobo armor.

Name: Ishgardian Barding
Description: A full-plate suit of Ishgardian chocobo armor.

Name: Noble Barding
Description: A lavishly decorated suit of armor crafted for the riding chocobos of Ishgardian nobles.

Name: Highland Barding
Description: A suit of chocobo armor outfitted with multiple layers of leather and fur to protect its wearer from the elements.

Name: Expanse Barding
Description: A suit of chocobo armor designed to resemble Bismarck, the Lord of the Mists.

Name: Hive Barding
Description: A suit of chocobo armor designed to resemble Ravana, the Lord of the Hive.

Name: Alpine Chair
Description: A simple chair designed in the alpine style.

Name: Alpine Round Table
Description: A round table designed in the alpine fashion. Will seat twelve, but with some difficulty.

Name: Alpine Tea Set
Description:
Add an air of nobility to your residence with this set of antique pewter.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Piety Bonus: +4% (Max 19)
  VIT Bonus: +4% (Max 26)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Stuffed Carbuncle
Description: The right paw of this plush Carbuncle is raised to beckon fortune into a household or place of commerce. Effectiveness varies.

Name: Oriental Breakfast
Description:
The Domans break their fast with a simple, yet balanced meal consisting of rice and several small side dishes.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Skill Speed Bonus: +4% (Max 28)
  VIT Bonus: +4% (Max 26)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Nameday Cake
Description:
While not common amongst the poorer classes, many Eorzean highborn practice the custom of decorating a cake for family members celebrating their namedays.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Spell Speed Bonus: +4% (Max 28)
  VIT Bonus: +4% (Max 26)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Cake Tray
Description:
A multi-tiered tray stacked with several varieties of luscious sweetcakes and tarts.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Direct Hit Bonus: +4% (Max 28)
  VIT Bonus: +4% (Max 26)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Oriental Supper
Description:
Rather than large portions of one or two dishes, Doman suppers consist of one or two bites of several painstakingly prepared culinary creations served with a bowl of steamed rice.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Determination Bonus: +4% (Max 19)
  VIT Bonus: +4% (Max 26)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Riviera Lunch
Description:
A freshly prepared lunch, complete with portions large enough to satisfy the meanest of appetites.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Tenacity Bonus: +4% (Max 28)
  VIT Bonus: +4% (Max 26)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Oriental Wind Chime
Description: This small glass bell has a slip of parchment attached to its clapper which, when blown by the wind, causes the clapper to strike the rim.

Name: Toy Box
Description:
A toy box that is opened by sliding several interlocking pieces of wood.

One per estate only.

Name: Glade Half Partition
Description: A partition designed in the glade fashion, but reaching only less than halfway to the ceiling so as to provide privacy without making the room feel smaller.

Name: Oasis Half Partition
Description: A partition designed in the oasis fashion, but reaching only less than halfway to the ceiling so as to provide privacy without making the room feel smaller.

Name: Cask Rack
Description: A rack allowing for the horizontal storage of multiple ale kegs or wine barrels.

Name: Display Stand
Description: A cylindrical stand designed for displaying various objets d'art and spoils of war.

Name: Miniature Gold Saucer
Description: A scale model of the Manderville Gold Saucer.

Name: Royal Plotting Table
Description: A replica of the table used in the Ul'dahn royal war room to conceive and confirm battle strategies.

Name: Round Banquet Table
Description: A large round table suitable for banquets, reunions, bacchanals, and other manner of large-scale social gatherings. Easily sits twelve to thirteen knights.

Name: Gold Saucer Corner Counter
Description: A low L-shaped counter-type table used in the Manderville Gold Saucer.

Name: Bearskin Rug
Description: For maximum romantic effect, place rug directly in front of a fireplace, light a few candles, and crack open a bottle of aged Ishgardian brandy.

Name: Gordian Bureau
Description:
A writing desk crafted from gears found inside the right arm of the mechanical fortress Alexander.

One per estate only.

Name: Savage Gordian Bureau
Description:
A writing desk crafted from gears found inside the right arm of the mechanical fortress Alexander. Magicks imbued within the furnishing cause the bureau to emit a soft glow that, while no one can see, all believe is there.

One per estate only.

Name: Gordian Chair
Description:
A chair crafted from gears found within the right arm of the mechanical fortress Alexander.

One per estate only.

Name: Savage Gordian Chair
Description:
A chair crafted from gears found within the right arm of the mechanical fortress Alexander. Magicks imbued within the furnishing have been known to stimulate the backsides of those who sit on it for any extended period of time.

One per estate only.

Name: Star Sapphire Music Box
Description: This expertly crafted music box plays only one half of a melody. Pair with a star ruby music box to complete the song.

Name: Star Ruby Music Box
Description: This expertly crafted music box plays only one half of a melody. Pair with a star sapphire music box to complete the song.

Name: Triple Triad Board
Description: An official Triple Triad tournament board. Placing one in an estate will allow residents to play matches without having to make the journey to the Gold Saucer.

Name: Expanse Fountain
Description:
An outdoor fountain created from the baleen of Bismarck, Lord of the Mists.

One per estate only.

Name: Boundless Expanse Fountain
Description:
An outdoor fountain practically pulsing with magicks created from the baleen of Bismarck, Lord of the Mists.

One per estate only.

Name: Topiary Moogle
Description: A specially bred shrub pruned to the shape of a merry moogle.

Name: Standing Signboard
Description: A V-shaped sign used by shop owners to inform passersby of items on sale within.

Name: Laundry Pole
Description: A long pole upon which wet laundry is hung to dry in the sun. Take care when drying smallclothes, for the realm is rife with codpiece thieves.

Name: The Veil of Wiyu Zenith Replica
The Veil of Wiyu Atma Replica
The Veil of Wiyu Animus Replica
The Veil of Wiyu Novus Replica
The Veil of Wiyu Nexus Replica
Grade 1 Wheel of Recreation
Description: A cylindrical wheel crafted from metal and aspected crystal which, when placed on a stand and spun repeatedly, accumulates an aetherial charge. When fully primed, the wheel can be used to initiate the company action Jackpot (increased MGP payout at the Manderville Gold Saucer).

Name: Grade 2 Wheel of Recreation
Description: A cylindrical wheel crafted from metal and aspected crystal which, when placed on a stand and spun repeatedly, accumulates an aetherial charge. When fully primed, the wheel can be used to initiate the company action Jackpot II (increased MGP payout at the Manderville Gold Saucer).

Name: Grade 3 Wheel of Recreation
Description: A cylindrical wheel crafted from metal and aspected crystal which, when placed on a stand and spun repeatedly, accumulates an aetherial charge. When fully primed, the wheel can be used to initiate the company action Jackpot III (increased MGP payout at the Manderville Gold Saucer).

Name: Primed Grade 1 Wheel of Recreation
Description: A fully primed aetherial wheel that, when activated, will initiate the company action Jackpot (increased MGP payout at the Manderville Gold Saucer).

Name: Primed Grade 2 Wheel of Recreation
Description: A fully primed aetherial wheel that, when activated, will initiate the company action Jackpot II (increased MGP payout at the Manderville Gold Saucer).

Name: Primed Grade 3 Wheel of Recreation
Description: A fully primed aetherial wheel that, when activated, will initiate the company action Jackpot III (increased MGP payout at the Manderville Gold Saucer).

Name: Red Moko Grass
Description: A less-common variety of moko grass found growing predominantly in the northern mountainous regions of Aldenard.

Name: Cassia Log
Description: A rough-cut log of cassia timber. The sweet scent of its bark invokes memories of sweet buns and apple pie.

Name: Chemically Treated Chimera Hide
Description: The durability of this chimera hide has been enhanced using aetherochemical compounds formulated thousands of summers ago in an Allagan laboratorium.

Name: Raw Celestine
Description: An uncut, unpolished stone containing what appears to be celestinea light-blue crystal that is often added to alloys.

Name: Vivianite
Description: A smoke-blue iron-rich ore often found growing within the fossilized bones of long-dead wavekin.

Name: Deep-red Crystal
Description: A vividly colored crystal aspected to multiple elements.

Name: Deep-red Cluster
Description: A vividly colored cluster of crystals aspected to multiple elements.

Name: Deep-green Crystal
Description: A vividly colored crystal aspected to multiple elements.

Name: Deep-green Cluster
Description: A vividly colored cluster of crystals aspected to multiple elements.

Name: Deep-blue Crystal
Description: A vividly colored crystal aspected to multiple elements.

Name: Deep-blue Cluster
Description: A vividly colored cluster of crystals aspected to multiple elements.

Name: Farreach Canvas
Description: Originally conceived by inhabitants of the sparsely settled Farreach to withstand the gale-force winds ceaselessly blowing on the Bloodbrine Sea, this rugged sailcloth is one of few materials suited to air travel.

Name: Cassia Lumber
Description: Processed cassia lumber. Even with its bark removed, the wood still harbors a faint sweet scent.

Name: High Allagan Chimera Leather
Description: A large piece of specially treated chimerical leather used by the Allagan Empire to craft high armor.

Name: Lupin Plot
Description:
Each plant will produce a stalk of violet flowers more than a fulm tall.

Up to ten flower plots may be placed in a single garden, regardless of type.

Name: Explorer's Campfire
Description: All the essential culinary toolscamp stove, iron pot, and stump settlefor dining on the wild side.

Name: Amber-encased Vilekin
Description: A tiny vilekin unlike any currently found in Eorzea is trapped within this rock-solid piece of dried tree sap. Collectors will pay large sums for these rare treasures.

Name: Flight Credit
Description: Permission issued by the three Grand Companies, allowing flight of privately owned airships over public airspace. Depending on airship size, and number of airships in possession, multiple credits may be required to register a new vehicle.

Name: Tome of Geological Folklore - Coerthas
Description: Tales gathered from local Coerthan miners regarding the location of legendary ore veins and gem deposits.

Name: Tome of Geological Folklore - Dravania
Description: Tales gathered from local Dravanian miners regarding the location of legendary ore veins and gem deposits.

Name: Tome of Geological Folklore - Abalathia's Spine
Description: Tales gathered from miners newly arrived to the islets above the Sea of Clouds regarding the location of rich ore veins and gem deposits.

Name: Timeworn Archaeoskin Map
Description:
This bottle holds a timeworn map classified as risk-reward grade 6 among treasure hunters.

Use the action Decipher to extract the map and examine its contents.
Level 55 recommended.

Name: Timeworn Wyvernskin Map
Description:
This bottle holds a timeworn map classified as risk-reward grade 7 among treasure hunters.

Use the action Decipher to extract the map and examine its contents.
Level 60 recommended.

Name: Timeworn Dragonskin Map
Description:
This bottle holds a timeworn map classified as risk-reward grade 8 among treasure hunters.

Use the action Decipher to extract the map and examine its contents.
Level 60 full party (eight players) recommended.

Name: Master Carpenter III
Description: This esoteric tomethe third in an equally esoteric seriescontains advanced woodworking recipes that can only be learned by highly skilled carpenters.

Name: Master Blacksmith III
Description: This esoteric tomethe third in an equally esoteric seriescontains advanced smithing recipes that can only be learned by highly skilled blacksmiths.

Name: Master Armorer III
Description: This esoteric tomethe third in an equally esoteric seriescontains advanced armorcraft recipes that can only be learned by highly skilled armorers.

Name: Master Goldsmith III
Description: This esoteric tomethe third in an equally esoteric seriescontains advanced goldsmithing recipes that can only be learned by highly skilled goldsmiths.

Name: Master Leatherworker III
Description: This esoteric tomethe third in an equally esoteric seriescontains advanced leatherworking recipes that can only be learned by highly skilled leatherworkers.

Name: Master Weaver III
Description: This esoteric tomethe third in an equally esoteric seriescontains advanced clothcraft recipes that can only be learned by highly skilled weavers.

Name: Master Alchemist III
Description: This esoteric tomethe third in an equally esoteric seriescontains advanced alchemy recipes that can only be learned by highly skilled alchemists.

Name: Master Culinarian III
Description: This esoteric tomethe third in an equally esoteric seriescontains advanced cooking recipes that can only be learned by highly skilled culinarians.

Name: Coeurlregina Horn
Description: A massive elk-like horn taken from the queen of the coeurls, Coeurlregina.

Name: Proto Ultima Exoplating
Description: A heavy metal square removed from the outermost layer of Proto Ultima's protective plating.

Name: Gordian Gear
Description: A round cog removed from Alexander's Gordias sector.

Name: Large Gordian Gear
Description: A large round cog removed from Alexander's Gordias sector.

Name: Bismarck's Baleen
Description: Pulled from the Lord of the Mists's massive maw, this thick piece of keratinized tissue appears aspected to both wind and water.

Name: Expanse Baleen
Description: Pulled from the Lord of the Mists's massive maw, this thick piece of keratinized tissue bristles with the power of the endless skies.

Name: Ravana's Forewing
Description: Plucked from the Lord of the Hive's back, this remarkably light wing is impossible to tear despite its thinness.

Name: Hive Forewing
Description: Plucked from the Lord of the Hive's back, this remarkably light wing pulses with uncontrollably powerful aetherial energies.
