Name: Mythrite Rivets
Description: Short mythrite pins with large heads. Used in connecting metal plates.

Name: Titanium Rivets
Description: Short titanium pins with large heads. Used in connecting metal plates.

Name: Adamantite Rivets
Description: Short adamantite pins with large heads. Used in connecting metal plates.

Name: Mythrite Sand
Description: Glowing sand consisting of tiny grains of mythrite.

Name: Hardsilver Sand
Description: Oily sand containing tiny grains of hardsilver.

Name: Aurum Regis Sand
Description: Violet sand containing tiny grains of aurum regis.

Name: Mythrite Ore
Description: A decent-sized piece of rock containing the rare metal mythrite.

Name: Hardsilver Ore
Description: A decent-sized piece of rock containing the rare alchemic metal hardsilver.

Name: Aurum Regis Ore
Description: A decent-sized piece of rock containing the rare metal aurum regis.

Name: Titanium Ore
Description: A decent-sized piece of rock containing the rare metal titanium.

Name: Adamantite Ore
Description: A decent-sized piece of rock containing the rare metal adamantite.

Name: Cloud Mica
Description: A decent-sized chunk of rock made up of what appears to be thousands of thin sheets of silver crystal compacted together into a single mass.

Name: Sun Mica
Description: A decent-sized chunk of rock made up of what appears to be thousands of thin sheets of golden crystal compacted together into a single mass.

Name: Larimar
Description: A sky blue jewel.

Name: Tiger's Eye
Description: A golden brown jewel consisting of many colored layers. When polished, it resembles the eye of a tigera legendary beast believed to be the ancestor of the coeurl.

Name: Agate
Description: A cloudy pink jewel consisting of many colored layers.

Name: Star Ruby
Description: A red jewel that has been shaped and polished instead of faceted, creating the illusion of a six-pointed star within the stone.

Name: Star Sapphire
Description: A blue jewel that has been shaped and polished instead of faceted, creating the illusion of a six-pointed star within the stone.

Name: Opal
Description: A milky white jewel that, depending on the angle at which it is held, will exhibit a rainbow of color within the stone.

Name: Citrine
Description: A yellow jewel almost identical to topaz, but several times softer.

Name: Chrysolite
Description: A green jewel.

Name: Mormorion
Description: A smoky black jewel.

Name: Carnelian
Description: A translucent red jewel. Its relative softness makes it easy to carve, and it has been used by royalty throughout history for signet rings.

Name: Raw Larimar
Description: An uncut, unpolished stone containing what appears to be larimar.

Name: Raw Tiger's Eye
Description: An uncut, unpolished stone containing what appears to be tiger's eye.

Name: Raw Agate
Description: An uncut, unpolished stone containing what appears to be agate.

Name: Raw Star Ruby
Description: An uncut, unpolished stone containing what appears to be star ruby.

Name: Raw Star Sapphire
Description: An uncut, unpolished stone containing what appears to be star sapphire.

Name: Raw Opal
Description: An uncut, unpolished stone containing what appears to be opal.

Name: Raw Citrine
Description: An uncut, unpolished stone containing what appears to be citrine.

Name: Raw Chrysolite
Description: An uncut, unpolished stone containing what appears to be chrysolite.

Name: Raw Mormorion
Description: An uncut, unpolished stone containing what appears to be mormorion.

Name: Raw Carnelian
Description: An uncut, unpolished stone containing what appears to be carnelian.

Name: Cloud Mica Whetstone
Description: A whetstone carved from cloud mica. Used for sharpening metal or stone blades.

Name: Archaeornis Leather
Description: A large piece of cured archaeornis skin.

Name: Wyvern Leather
Description: A large piece of cured wyvern skin.

Name: Dhalmel Leather
Description: A large piece of cured dhalmel hide.

Name: Dragon Leather
Description: A large piece of cured dragon skin.

Name: Amphiptere Leather
Description: A large piece of cured amphiptere skin.

Name: Griffin Leather
Description: A large piece of cured griffin hide.

Name: Archaeornis Skin
Description: The tough hide of an archaeornis.

Name: Wyvern Skin
Description: The coarse hide of a wyvern.

Name: Dhalmel Hide
Description: The smooth hide of a dhalmel.

Name: Dragon Skin
Description: The thick scaly hide of a dragon.

Name: Amphiptere Skin
Description: The slick glossy hide of an amphiptere.

Name: Griffin Hide
Description: The leonine hide of a griffin.

Name: Bearskin
Description: The thick bushy hide of a bear.

Name: Yeti Fang
Description: The curved canine of a Coerthan yeti. You shudder to think how many throats were ripped open by this nail-like tooth.

Name: Dragon Fang
Description: The rapier-like fang of an ancient dragon. Some naturalists believe that the age of a dragon can be determined by horizontally slicing its tooth and counting the rings within.

Name: Griffin Talon
Description: The sharp curved talon of a griffin.

Name: Dark Chestnut Log
Description: A rough-cut log of dark chestnut timber.

Name: Birch Log
Description: A rough-cut log of birch lumber.

Name: Holy Cedar Lumber
Description: Processed cedar lumber purified with holy water.

Name: Dark Chestnut Lumber
Description: Processed dark chestnut lumber.

Name: Hallowed Chestnut Lumber
Description: Processed dark chestnut lumber purified with hallowed water.

Name: Birch Lumber
Description: Processed birch lumber.

Name: Astral Birch Lumber
Description: Processed birch lumber treated so that its elemental aspect tips towards astral.

Name: Dark Chestnut Branch
Description: The thick branch of a dark chestnut tree.

Name: Birch Branch
Description: The thin branch of a birch tree.

Name: Wattle Bark
Description: This bark, when boiled down, produces large amounts of tannina substance used by leatherworkers to tan hides.

Name: Rainbow Cloth
Description: Several yalms of undyed rainbow cloth wrapped around a short wooden distaff.

Name: Holy Rainbow Cloth
Description: Several yalms of rainbow cloth purified with holy water and wrapped around a short wooden distaff.

Name: Ramie Cloth
Description: Several yalms of undyed ramie cloth wrapped around a short wooden distaff.

Name: Hallowed Ramie Cloth
Description: Several yalms of ramie cloth purified with holy water and wrapped around a short wooden distaff.

Name: Chimerical Felt
Description: Several yalms of soft undyed felt created by matting down several layers of hair taken from chimera manes.

Name: Astral Silk
Description: Several yalms of silk treated so that its elemental aspect would tip slightly towards astral.

Name: Rainbow Thread
Description: Multicolored yarn spun from rainbow cotton.

Name: Ramie Thread
Description: Strong, absorbent yarn spun from ramie.

Name: Crawler Silk
Description: Silk gathered from crawler cocoons and spun into a thin lustrous thread.

Name: Rainbow Cotton Boll
Description: A rare variety of cotton which produces fibers that change color depending on the angle at which light strikes them.

Name: Stalk of Ramie
Description: A variety of swift-growing grass native to the Near East. The stalks can be dried and processed into thin threads which, when spun together, can be woven into a cloth not unlike hemp.

Name: Chimera Mane
Description: The bristly mane of a biologically engineered monstrosity.

Name: Crawler Cocoon
Description: The sticky cocoon of a giant crawler.

Name: Enchanted Mythrite Ink
Description: Ink fortified with mythrite sand to improve aetherial conductivity.

Name: Enchanted Hardsilver Ink
Description: Ink fortified with hardsilver sand to improve aetherial conductivity.

Name: Enchanted Aurum Regis Ink
Description: Ink fortified with aurum regis sand to improve aetherial conductivity.

Name: Holy Water
Description: Water blessed by an anointed Halonic Orthodox priest. Used to exorcise most evil spirits from worldly items.

Name: Hallowed Water
Description: Water blessed by an anointed Halonic Orthodox priest. Used to exorcise evil spirits from worldly items.

Name: Astral Oil
Description: Refined oil with an unbalanced elemental aspect tipping towards astral.

Name: Growth Formula Epsilon
Description: This alchemically formulated potation accelerates the growth of foliage.

Name: Growth Formula Zeta
Description: This alchemically formulated potation accelerates the growth of foliage.

Name: Bear Fat
Description: This musky all-purpose oil is commonly used in tinctures as well as lamps.

Name: Crystal Glass
Description: This exceptionally transparent glass does not actually contain any crystal, but earns its name for being as clear as crystallized aether.

Name: Black Firesand
Description: A higher concentration of saltpeter makes this flammable powder slightly more explosive than normal firesand.

Name: Grade 1 Strength Dissolvent
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to strength, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Grade 1 Dexterity Dissolvent
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to dexterity, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Grade 1 Vitality Dissolvent
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to vitality, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Grade 1 Intelligence Dissolvent
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to intelligence, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Grade 1 Mind Dissolvent
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to mind, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Grade 2 Strength Dissolvent
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to strength, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Grade 2 Dexterity Dissolvent
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to dexterity, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Grade 2 Vitality Dissolvent
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to vitality, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Grade 2 Intelligence Dissolvent
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to intelligence, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Grade 2 Mind Dissolvent
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to mind, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Draconian Potion of Strength
Description:
This intoxicating concoction brewed from an ancient dragon recipe temporarily increases strength.

Duration: 15s

Name: Draconian Potion of Dexterity
Description:
This intoxicating concoction brewed from an ancient dragon recipe temporarily increases dexterity.

Duration: 15s

Name: Draconian Potion of Vitality
Description:
This intoxicating concoction brewed from an ancient dragon recipe temporarily increases vitality.

Duration: 15s

Name: Draconian Potion of Intelligence
Description:
This intoxicating concoction brewed from an ancient dragon recipe temporarily increases intelligence.

Duration: 15s

Name: Draconian Potion of Mind
Description:
This intoxicating concoction brewed from an ancient dragon recipe temporarily increases mind.

Duration: 15s

Name: Dragon Scale
Description: This rock-hard scale can withstand the blow of a Roegadyn-wielded battleaxe.

Name: Deepeye Tears
Description: It would take at least twenty tears shed from a heartbroken Lalafellin maiden to equal the liquid volume of one deepeye tear.

Name: Dhalmel Saliva
Description: The odor of dhalmel saliva has been likened to that of the bloated corpse of a blue cheese artisan drowned in a Grand Company camp latrine and left to sit in the hot sun for a sennight.

Name: Dragon Blood
Description: Most likely the blood of a dragon. For some unknown reason, the humours will not coagulate.

Name: Dravanian Spring Water
Description: Clear water taken from a spring in the foothills of Abalathia's Spine.

Name: Abalathian Spring Water
Description: Clear water taken from a spring on one of the many islets floating above Abalathia's Spine.

Name: Skyspring Water
Description: Crystal-clear water taken from a secluded spring located on a remote islet floating above the Sea of Clouds.

Name: Seventh Heaven
Description: A rare flower that has an elemental aspect tipped severely in the direction of astral.

Name: Gelato Flesh
Description: A quivering gelatinous lump of voidsent flesh neither cold nor sweet. Consumption is not recommended, even during times of starvation.

Name: Wyvern Wing
Description: The thick leathery wing of a wyvern.

Name: Icetrap Leaf
Description: The thin, twitching leaf of an icetrap.

Name: Coneflower
Description: Brought back from the New World in the west, this plant bearing large, horn-shaped flowers has been recently discovered to be effective in curing several different ailments.

Name: Cow Bitter
Description: This sweet-smelling perennial can be found growing in all of the Three Great Continents.

Name: Dandelion
Description: This common flower produces a globe of lightweight seeds that are carried remarkable distances when blown in the wind. While the stalk is filled with a toxic milky substance, the leaves and roots can be dried and brewed into medicinal infusions.

Name: Gaelicatnip
Description: A relative to pepper- and spearmint, gaelicatnip is an aromatic herb often brewed into teas. The oil contained in the leaves is known to cause gaelicats and other normally aggressive feline beastkin to exhibit excessively playful behavior.

Name: Rue
Description: A low-growing shrub recognizable by its tiny yellow flowers and faint odor. The leaves contain a mild irritant that, when rubbed against the skin, may cause minor reddening and swelling.

Name: Coriander
Description: A highly fragrant herb. The leaves can be harvested and used in salads, or the plant can be allowed to bolt and the seeds gathered and used to spice ale.

Name: Aurum Regis Cylinder
Description: This small music box cylinder is studded with myriad pins arranged in a queer pattern. When placed in a music box and attached to the motor, the cylinder will rotate, causing the pins to strike the box's comb, creating music.

Name: Thavnairian Leather
Description: This leather has been tanned and treated using techniques from the Near Eastern island of Thavnair.

Name: Thavnairian Silk
Description: This silk has been spun from thread created by a worm found only on the Near Eastern island of Thavnair.

Name: Atomos Corpulence
Description: A small piece of throbbing flesh sliced from the devourer of worlds, Atomos.

Name: Steel Mainspring
Description: A coiled ribbon of steel commonly used in clockwork creations to perpetuate motion.

Name: Steel Wheel Bearing
Description: Several steel balls set into a polished metal ring. It is used to reduce friction, allowing a wheel to spin with little resistance.

Name: Lupin Seedling
Description: Its name meaning wolf, the lupin is a hardy plant resistant to the cold winds of the Eorzean north.

Name: Iron Giant Scrap
Description: A jagged sheet of plating fallen from the armor of an iron giant.

Name: Gobwalker Shielding
Description: Protective metal plating used in the fabrication of a magitek gobwalker G-VII.

Name: Far Eastern Coin
Description: An oblong coin of gold commonly used in the Far East for bribes.

Name: Toy Box Schema
Description: A detailed design document outlining the absurdly complex steps required to craft a toy box.

Name: Fine Alumen
Description: A yellowish mineral used by leatherworkers to tan animal hides. This particular variety exhibits some of the best deodorizing properties of all alumen.

Name: Shrub Seedling
Description: The seedling of a squat shrub favored by topiarists across the realm for its bright-green leaves and dense web of tiny branches.

Name: Magnanimous Mogcrown
Description: A gaudy moogle-sized crown crafted by moogles for use during moogle celebrations.

Name: Dusk Leather
Description: An especially dark variety of leather often used in formalwear and uniforms.

Name: Woodworking Delineation
Description:
A detailed outline of complex woodworking techniques.

[Can be exchanged with Calamity salvagers for all-purpose crafter's delineations.]

Name: Blacksmithing Delineation
Description:
A detailed outline of complex blacksmithing techniques.

[Can be exchanged with Calamity salvagers for all-purpose crafter's delineations.]

Name: Armoring Delineation
Description:
A detailed outline of complex armoring techniques.

[Can be exchanged with Calamity salvagers for all-purpose crafter's delineations.]

Name: Goldsmithing Delineation
Description:
A detailed outline of complex goldsmithing techniques.

[Can be exchanged with Calamity salvagers for all-purpose crafter's delineations.]

Name: Leatherworking Delineation
Description:
A detailed outline of complex leatherworking techniques.

[Can be exchanged with Calamity salvagers for all-purpose crafter's delineations.]

Name: Weaving Delineation
Description:
A detailed outline of complex weaving techniques.

[Can be exchanged with Calamity salvagers for all-purpose crafter's delineations.]

Name: Alchemy Delineation
Description:
A detailed outline of complex alchemy techniques.

[Can be exchanged with Calamity salvagers for all-purpose crafter's delineations.]

Name: Cooking Delineation
Description:
A detailed outline of complex cooking techniques.

[Can be exchanged with Calamity salvagers for all-purpose crafter's delineations.]

Name: Commercial Engineering Manual
Description:
This comprehensive manual, written by a disgruntled former employee of Rowena's House of Splendors, provides a detailed explanation of inhuman techniques forced upon consortium-hired Disciples of the Hand to increase their output. It is known to inspire (and frighten) all who read it, granting a temporary 150% boost to experience points earned from synthesis (up to a maximum of 1,750,000 points). Effect is halved at level 70 and above.

Duration: 18 hours

Name: Commercial Survival Manual
Description:
This comprehensive manual, written by a disgruntled former employee of Rowena's House of Splendors, provides a detailed explanation of inhuman techniques forced upon consortium-hired Disciples of the Land to increase their output. It is known to inspire (and frighten) all who read it, granting a temporary 150% boost to experience points earned from gathering activities (up to a maximum of 1,750,000 points). Effect is halved at level 70 and above.

Duration: 18 hours

Name: Hi-Cordial
Description: A sweet, fermented concoction that instantly restores 400 GP.

Name: Old World Striking Dummy
Description:
A striking dummy designed in the Sharlayan fashion.

Up to three dummies may be placed in a single estate, regardless of type.

Name: Sunflower Plot
Description:
The stalks of these bright-yellow flowers have been known to grow to heights of two or three yalms.

Up to ten flower plots may be placed in a single garden, regardless of type.

Name: Expanse Totem
Description: This wooden idol carved in the likeness of the primal Bismarck is used by Vanu Vanu priests during summoning ceremonies.

Name: Hive Totem
Description: This steel idol resembling the primal Ravana is used by the Gnath during summoning ceremonies.

Name: Tarnished Gordian Lens
Description:
A uniquely crafted lens discovered in Alexander's Gordias sector.

Two lenses can be traded for special headgear.

Name: Tarnished Gordian Shaft
Description:
A uniquely crafted shaft discovered in Alexander's Gordias sector.

Four shafts can be traded for special body gear.

Name: Tarnished Gordian Crank
Description:
A uniquely crafted crank discovered in Alexander's Gordias sector.

Two cranks can be traded for special arm gear.

Name: Tarnished Gordian Spring
Description:
A uniquely crafted spring discovered in Alexander's Gordias sector.

Four springs can be traded for special leg gear.

Name: Tarnished Gordian Pedal
Description:
A uniquely crafted pedal discovered in Alexander's Gordias sector.

Two pedals can be traded for special foot gear.

Name: Tarnished Gordian Chain
Description: A uniquely crafted chain discovered in Alexander's Gordias sector. Alas, advancements in trouser technology have rendered it worthless.

Name: Tarnished Gordian Bolt
Description:
A uniquely crafted bolt discovered in Alexander's Gordias sector.

One bolt can be traded for a special accessory.

Name: Gordian Manifesto - Page 1
Description:
The opening page of the Illuminati's catechismal masterwork.

Manifesto pages of the same type can be traded for special gear or materials.

Name: Gordian Manifesto - Page 2
Description:
The second page of the Illuminati's catechismal masterwork.

Manifesto pages of the same type can be traded for special gear.

Name: Gordian Manifesto - Page 3
Description:
The third page of the Illuminati's catechismal masterwork.

Manifesto pages of the same type can be traded for special gear.

Name: Gordian Manifesto - Page 4
Description:
The fourth page of the Illuminati's catechismal masterwork.

Manifesto pages of the same type can be traded for special gear.

Name: Tome of Botanical Folklore - Coerthas
Description: Tales gathered from local Coerthan botanists regarding the location of rare trees and herbs.

Name: Tome of Botanical Folklore - Dravania
Description: Tales gathered from local Dravanian botanists regarding the location of rare trees and herbs.

Name: Tome of Botanical Folklore - Abalathia's Spine
Description: Tales gathered from botanists newly arrived to the islets above the Sea of Clouds regarding the location of rare trees and herbs.

Name: Tome of Ichthyological Folklore - Coerthas
Description: Tales gathered from local Coerthan fishers regarding the location of legendary fish.

Name: Tome of Ichthyological Folklore - Dravania
Description: Tales gathered from local Dravanian fishers regarding the location of legendary fish.

Name: Tome of Ichthyological Folklore - Abalathia's Spine
Description: Tales gathered from fishers newly arrived to the islets above the Sea of Clouds regarding the location of heretofore unseen fish.

Name: Stonefly Nymph
Description: Stonefly nymphs are constantly moving, making them easily discernible targets for poor-sighted fish. Live bait for freshwater fishing.

Name: Purse Web Spider
Description: This lightweight spider can distribute its weight over a large surface area, allowing it to walk on water without sinking. Live bait for freshwater fishing.

Name: Goblin Jig
Description: A metal lure designed by goblin fishers to vibrate rapidly, thus making it more appealing to hungry fish.

Name: Bladed Steel Jig
Description: An all-purpose fishing lure crafted by combining three smaller lures.

Name: Red Balloon
Description: A bright-red breed of balloon bug found floating at higher elevations than its duller cousins. Live bait for both skyfishing and cloudfishing. Up to nine hundred and ninety-nine red balloons can be stacked together.

Name: Magma Worm
Description: A small worm with a stone-like shell encasing its entire body, protecting it from the extreme temperatures of the molten lava in which it resides. Live bait for hellfishing.

Name: Fiend Worm
Description: Discovered almost simultaneously by three naturalists, this strange creature was also named the demon worm and the goddess worm until a best-two-out-of-three round of stone-parchment-shears settled the naming problem once and for all. Fiend worms are one of the few baits suitable for aetherfishing, as the vilekin will remain alive in the sludge even when submerged.

Name: Brute Leech
Description: A fat bloodsucking worm often found attached to large fish or the legs of wading fauna. Live bait for freshwater fishing.

Name: Giant Crane Fly
Description: A mosquito-like vilekin with uncharacteristically long legs. Often utilized by anglers for both cloud and skyfishing.

Name: Icepick
Description:
A freshwater fish adapted to survive in the cold waters of Coerthas. It earns its name from its long, beak-like mouth.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Cloud Coral
Description:
A white, lightweight coral found growing on the floating islands above Eorzea.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Ice Faerie
Description:
A tiny winged slug commonly found in ice-ridden freshwater lakes.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Skyworm
Description:
A wingless worm that has somehow learned to fly.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Coerthan Crab
Description:
A freshwater crustacean only found in the coldest of lakes.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Fanged Clam
Description:
When closed, the shells of this freshwater bivalve mollusk form a demonic rictus that will haunt your nightmares until the end of time. Possibly beyond.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Lake Urchin
Description:
A freshwater urchin which survives by eating the sparse algal blooms in Twinpools.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Whilom Catfish
Description:
A small, red catfish native to the Whilom River.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 3 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Blueclaw Shrimp
Description:
A freshwater shrimp native to the Whilom River.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Starflower
Description:
A flower-like mollusk found floating about the Sea of Clouds.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Glacier Core
Description:
A spherical creature found flying in the icy northern reaches of the Sea of Clouds bordering the Coerthas western highlands.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Ogre Horn Snail
Description:
A freshwater mollusk with a twisted shell shaped like the horn of a voidsent ogre. Can only survive in warm temperatures, such as those found in hot springs.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Sorcerer Fish
Description:
A freshwater fish believed by some to have the ability to wield fire spells.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Hotrod
Description:
A freshwater fish native to the freshwater runoff of Abalathia's Spine. It is easily distinguishable by its long, ever-twitching whiskers.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Maiboi
Description:
A thin freshwater fish commonly found in the floating lakes above Abalathia.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Three-lip Carp
Description:
A large freshwater fish covered in gil-sized silver scales.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Bullfrog
Description:
A stout, deep-voiced wavekin found throughout Abalathia's Spine.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Cloudfish
Description:
A semi-transparent freshwater fish native to the lakes of legendary Voor Sian Siran.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Mahu Wai
Description:
A cloud white mollusk found living on the underbelly of Abalathia's floating islets.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Rock Mussel
Description:
A tiny freshwater bivalve mollusk native to the lukewarm waters of the Whilom River in the Dravanian forelands.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Buoyant Oviform
Description:
The expression when eggs fly was commonly used throughout Eorzea to express the impossibility of something...that is until the discovery of this strange creature floating about the Sea of Clouds.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Whiteloom
Description:
A mushroom/loom-like flying fish native to the Sea of Clouds.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Blue Cloud Coral
Description:
A blue, lightweight coral found growing on the floating islands above Eorzea.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Seema Patrician
Description:
A fatty freshwater fish native to Twinpools.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Ammonite
Description:
A giant cephalopod characterized by its spectacular dual-walled whorling shell.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Bubble Eye
Description:
A freshwater fish found only in the pools and lakes of Abalathia's floating islets.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 1 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Grass Carp
Description:
A freshwater fish native to the Hundred Throes, where it conceals itself in the churning waters of the myriad cataracts.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Pipira Pira
Description:
A deadly freshwater fish which will tear away flesh with its razor-sharp teeth. Crossing the Whilom River barefoot is not recommended.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Dravanian Squeaker
Description:
A peculiar breed of freshwater catfish that swims upside down. It was first discovered in Weston Waters.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 1 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Kissing Fish
Description:
An adorable freshwater fish native to the waters of Eil Tohm.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Mitre Slug
Description:
A flying slug native to the Sea of Clouds.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Lava Crab
Description:
This hard-shelled crustacean is one of few creatures on Eorzea which withstand the heat of molten lava.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Storm Core
Description:
A spherical creature found in the upper atmospheric region of the Sea of Clouds.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Scholar Sculpin
Description:
A freshwater fish named after Thaliak, the Scholar.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Gigant Grouper
Description:
A massive freshwater fish who lurks beneath the thick sheet of ice covering Ashpool.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Vanuhead
Description:
A freshwater fish inhabiting the Eddiesan isolated lake found atop one of Abalathia's floating islets.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 3 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Marble Oscar
Description:
A freshwater fish which prefers the heated pools of the Smoldering Wastes to the cooler waters of surrounding rivers.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Lungfish
Description:
A highly evolved air-breathing wavekin found in the muddy biome near the Pappus Tree.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Tigerfish
Description:
A striped freshwater fish native to the Quickspill Delta.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 4 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Sky Faerie
Description:
A tiny transparent mollusk often seen in the skies near the Blue Window.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Granite Crab
Description:
A thick-shelled crab capable of surviving the extreme temperatures of exposed lava pools.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Aithon's Colt
Description:
A graceful glass-like creature that glides with ease through the lava coursing through Anyx Old within the belly of Sohm Al.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Shipworm
Description:
A worm-like mollusk that lives in the fallen trees and ancient shipwrecks that litter the bottom of the Thaliak River.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Hedgemole Cricket
Description:
An amphibious vilekin found swarming about the Quickspill Delta.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Mogpom
Description:
An algal sphere found collecting in the lone pool on the floating islet of Greensward.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Magma Tree
Description:
A colony of tiny crystal-encased creatures found growing in the cavern of Mourn.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Cloud Rider
Description:
A flying fish native to the Churning Mists.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Dravanian Bass
Description:
A large freshwater fish native to the Whilom River.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Coerthan Puffer
Description:
A rare freshwater puffer found only in northern Eorzea.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Snowcaller
Description:
A freshwater fish native to the gelid waters of Banepool.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Dragonhead
Description:
A freshwater fish native to the Iron Feast. The skull on its head does not appear to be that of a dragon, but rather of a dragonfly.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Mercy Staff
Description:
A freshwater fish that only becomes active when the land is beset by snowstorms.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Rime Eater
Description:
A small floating jellyfish often seen in the Sea of Clouds.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Warmwater Bichir
Description:
A freshwater fish found in the heated pools of the Smoldering Wastes.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Noontide Oscar
Description:
An albino marble oscar only found with consistency in the corrupted waters of Eil Tohm.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Shadowhisker
Description:
A large freshwater fish found in the Hundred Throes.

[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Gobbie Mask
Description:
An airborne cephalopod native to the Churning Mists.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Blue Medusa
Description:
A stinging jellyfish native to the corrupted waters near the Landlord Colony.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Cindersmith
Description:
A heat-resistant mollusk found in the magma pools of Anyx Old.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Bullwhip
Description:
A mutated fish surviving only in the aetherochemical pools of Azys Lla.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Tiny Axolotl
Description:
An alien-like amphibian found living in the muddy flats near the Pappus Tree.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: High Allagan Helmet
Description:
An ancient breed of crab found in the aetherochemical pools of Azys Lla.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Platinum Fish
Description:
A mutant breed of goldfish native to the aetherochemical pools of Azys Lla.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Aether Eye
Description:
A freshwater fish found in the hydrothermal biome near the Pappus Tree.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Azysfish
Description:
A mutant breed of fish named after the floating island on which it is found.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Crystalfin
Description:
A colorfully finned freshwater fish found in the biome waters near the Pappus Tree.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Sweetfish
Description:
A delicious (though unsweet) freshwater fish native to the Thaliak River.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Orn Butterfly
Description:
A freshwater fish native to the Orn Wild, yet also found in the Quickspill Delta of the Thaliak River.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Hundred Fin
Description:
A strangely maned freshwater fish found only in Weston Waters.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Autumn Leaf
Description:
This freshwater fish native to the Thaliak River has an uncanny resemblance to fallen foliage.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Manasail
Description:
A flying fish found in the skies near Tharl Oom Khash in the Churning Mists.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Sky Sweeper
Description:
A flying fish often seen in small flocks circling the Azys Lla Habisphere.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Magma Louse
Description:
A beetle-like creature that can survive the extreme temperatures of the magma flows in Anyx Old.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Cometoise
Description:
A slow-moving tortoise found in the magma flows near Halo.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Aetherochemical Compound #123
Description:
This biologically engineered biomass can be found on Azys Lla.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Brown Bolo
Description:
A whip-like creature found in the skies surrounding Tharl Oom Khash in the Churning Mists.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Philosopher's Stone
Description:
A pink-shelled freshwater mollusk native to the Thaliak River.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Fountfish
Description:
A deadly breed of freshwater anglerfish found only on Azys Lla.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Weston Bowfin
Description:
A large freshwater fish found in the Churning Mists' Weston Waters.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Letter Puffer
Description:
A highly poisonous fish commonly found floating in the skies near the Landlord Colony.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Star Faerie
Description:
A tiny transparent mollusk found only at a certain altitude in the lower Churning Mists.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Gloaming Coral
Description:
A variety of cloud coral seen growing on the undersides of the floating islets that make up the Landlord Colony.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Albino Octopus
Description:
A rarely seen freshwater cephalopod that favors the frigid waters of the Coerthas western highlands.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Dragon's Soul
Description:
A small dragon-like creature that makes its home in the skies above and below the Landlord Colony in the Churning Mists.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Tornado Shark
Description:
A shark capable of riding tornados to extreme altitudes. A stage performance written by a Lominsan playwright on the subject of a tornado shark attack was voted the worst play of all time by the Eorzean Theatrical Society.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Warballoon
Description:
A gargantuan floating jellyfish found in skies high above Eorzea.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Fossiltongue
Description:
A magma-dwelling cousin of the bonytongue.

[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Proto-hropken
Description:
A manlike fish living in the aetherochemical pools of Azys Lla.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Caiman
Description:
An amphibious scalekin with extended rows of sharp teeth and a nigh-insatiable appetite for fresh meat. Can be found primarily in the Dravanian forelands.

[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Euphotic Pirarucu
Description:
A biologically engineered fish found in Azys Lla's Delta Quadrant.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 4 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Illuminati Perch
Description:
A foul-smelling fish introduced to the Thaliak River by the Illuminati.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Rudderfish
Description:
This eel-like flying fish with three pairs of thin wings is found throughout the Sea of Clouds.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Bomb Puffer
Description:
A balloon-like fish inhabiting the skies near the Azys Lla Habisphere.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Mucous Minnow
Description:
A strange breed of minnow able to survive the corrupted waters of Azys Lla's aetherochemical pools.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Unidentified Flying Biomass
Description:
Beyond the fact one can find it in the skies near the Habisphere, absolutely nothing is known about this lump of flying...something.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Hospitalier Fish
Description:
A tiny freshwater fish that inhabits the warm spring waters of Dragonspit.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Scorpionfly
Description:
A variety of flying shrimp believed only to live on and around the islets of the Sea of Clouds.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Rockclimber
Description:
A freshwater fish inhabiting the waters of the Azys Lla Delta Quadrant.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Blood Skipper
Description:
An ugly fish found in and around the aetherochemical pools of the Azys Lla Alpha Quadrant.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Cobrafish
Description:
A fanged fish native to the skies above Tharl Oom Khash.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Moogle Spirit
Description:
A flat ray-like creature which spends its life riding the thermals occurring throughout the Sea of Clouds.

[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Oil Eel
Description:
A slimy, finless creature that more closely resembles a worm than it does a fish.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Jeweled Jellyfish
Description:
A luminescent jellyfish capable of surviving within the pools of aetherochemical residue collecting on Azys Lla.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Battle Galley
Description:
A freshwater fish native to all of Coerthas, but now primarily found in Ashpool.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Yalm Lobster
Description:
A giant freshwater crustacean that primarily dwells beneath the boulders of the Quickspill Delta.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Hinterlands Perch
Description:
A freshwater fish native to the Thaliak River.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Oven Catfish
Description:
A magma-dwelling fish found in the mountain flows of Mourn.

[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Pteranodon
Description:
This flying scalekin can be seen scouting the lower reaches of the Churning Mists for insects and small birds.

[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Winged Gurnard
Description:
A flying fish found in the skies around the Blue Window.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Spring Urchin
Description:
A freshwater creature that prefers the warm waters released by the springs at Dragonspit.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Cherry Trout
Description:
Once found across Coerthas and Dravania, this reddish variety of trout now only survives in the heated waters of Dragonspit.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Stupendemys
Description:
If a flying crystal-shelled tortoise cannot be seen as stupendous, nothing can.

[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Black Magefish
Description:
The ability to wield powerful black magic is only this fish's second-most impressive characteristic, the ability to survive in scalding hot lava, the first.

[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Barreleye
Description:
An exotic fish found only in the aetherochemical reservoirs on central Azys Lla's research vessel.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Thunderbolt Eel
Description:
A narrow-bodied freshwater fish found in the pools flooding the Iron Feast, amongst other locations.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Catkiller
Description:
A large freshwater fish found lurking in the floating Abalathian lake known as the Eddies.

[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Loosetongue
Description:
A giant freshwater cousin of the bonytongue found only in the Thaliak River.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 4 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Thaliak Caiman
Description:
A giant breed of caiman native to the Thaliak River.

[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Lavalord
Description:
A legendary lava-dwelling fish covered in thick armor and rumored to be the guardian of the gate of the Hell of Fire.

[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Tupuxuara
Description:
An ancient wyvern still found living on the Habisphere, thousands of years after its creators perished in the calamity which destroyed their civilization.

[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Vampiric Tapestry
Description:
A flying cephalopod that rarely strays from the skies near Mok Oogl Island.

[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Storm Chaser
Description:
A flying fish native to the skies of Tharl Oom Khash.

[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Berserker Betta
Description:
A small, yet hostile freshwater fish found in small numbers in the Thaliak River.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Capelin
Description:
A tiny freshwater fish that dwells in Clearpool near Oakum Landing.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Red Crafters' Scrip Token
Description: A note of promise granted for the delivery of red crafters' scrips. However, due to a change in policy, it is now worth less than the paper on which it is scribed.

Name: Blue Crafters' Scrip Token
Description: A note of promise granted for the delivery of crafters' scrips.

Name: Red Gatherers' Scrip Token
Description: A note of promise granted for the delivery of red gatherers' scrips. However, due to a change in policy, it is now worth less than the paper on which it is scribed.

Name: Blue Gatherers' Scrip Token
Description: A note of promise granted for the delivery of gatherers' scrips.

Name: Ishgardian Tea
Description:
Rather than adding milk to boiling water that has been infused with tea leaves, as is the fashion in lower Eorzea, Ishgardian tea is brewed by boiling yak milk and letting dried Coerthan tea leaves steep right into the hot liquid.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Frozen Spirits
Description:
A cool concoction made by fermenting cloud bananas and Old World figs, freezing them with ice crystals, then mashing and mixing the fruit into a slush-like consistency.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Hot Chocolate
Description:
A sweet beverage commonly drunk in the Holy See, but rarely seen in Foundation due to inability of most of Ishgard's poorer residents to procure the relatively rare and expensive ingredients.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Fig Bavarois
Description:
A ripe Old World fig encased in a lightly sweetened jelly.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Sohm Al Tart
Description:
A traditional Ishgardian cake made up of several stacked layers tapered to resemble Sohm Al, a peak sacred to the Dravanians. Ishgardians believe that devouring the mountain will grant them fortune in their struggle with the dragons.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Marron Glace
Description:
Chestnuts peeled and soaked in honey for several moons until the entire fruit is permeated with sweetness.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Creme Brulee
Description:
A vanilla-flavored egg custard drenched in a sweet syrup that is then heated with a fire crystal until a crisp brown shell is created.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Kaiser Roll
Description:
A round Ishgardian bread first made by Halonic monastics who, when brewing ale, would add barm and leftover malt to their daily loaves.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Ishgardian Muffin
Description:
Leavened bread that is cooked on a griddle rather than in an oven. Cornmeal is dusted on the dough before cooking to prevent sticking to the pan.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Liver-cheese Sandwich
Description:
Several slices of a ground liver loaf sandwiched between two halves of a kaiser roll.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Almond Cream Croissant
Description:
A flaky crescent-shaped pastry sliced in two and buttered with a sweet creamy paste made from almonds.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Sauteed Porcini
Description:
Fragrant porcini mushrooms sliced and sauted in butter. Simple, yet elegant.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Morel Salad
Description:
A fresh green salad topped with sauted morels.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Grilled Sweetfish
Description:
A simple dish created by piercing a lightly salted fresh sweetfish with a sharpened stick and slowly roasting it over an open flame.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Baked Pipira Pira
Description:
A plump pipira pira wrapped with butter and porcini mushrooms and baked in an oven, the steam trapped in the leaf slowly cooking the fish to the perfect flakiness.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Urchin Loaf
Description:
Sea urchin corals mixed with mushrooms and herbs into a paste that is then placed back into the urchin shell and baked until hard.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Cockatrice Meatballs
Description:
Ground lean cockatrice meat hand rolled into bite-sized balls and fried in oil.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Royal Eggs
Description:
A breakfast dish consisting of an Ishgardian muffin sliced into halves and topped with salmon, a poached egg, and a creamy yellow sauce made from butter and egg yolks.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Deep-fried Okeanis
Description:
Thinly sliced okeanis fried in oil.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Baked Onion Soup
Description:
A hearty bouillon soup filled with sweet onions, covered with shredded cheese and baked in an oven until golden brown.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Beet Soup
Description:
Sliced magma beets and lean loaghtan meat slow-cooked with vegetables and served with a dollop of rich sour cream. A dish popular throughout Ishgard, though families in the Brume often use the meat of animals easier to find in the district's dark back alleys.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Emerald Soup
Description:
A bright-green soup made by cooking down emerald beans until they break down into a ghastly paste. Despised by children both high- and lowborn.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Clam Chowder
Description:
A milk-based soup made with various shellfish, but most often clams.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Seafood Stew
Description:
A simple stew made from available seafood boiled with tomatoes and spices.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Stuffed Cabbage Rolls
Description:
Ground meat rolled in cabbage and boiled in broth.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Dhalmel Gratin
Description:
Several layers of thinly sliced dhalmel meat and vegetables covered in a creamy white sauce and baked.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Stuffed Chysahl
Description:
Ground okeanis stuffed into a large chysahl head and sprinkled with fresh chives.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Dhalmel Fricassee
Description:
Chopped and braised dhalmel meat cooked in a white stew.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Snurbleberry Tart
Description:
A colorful tart made with blood red snurbleberries.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Gastornis Egg
Description: The hard-shelled egg of a gastornis.

Name: Okeanis Egg
Description: The soft-shelled, slime-covered, ever-so-slightly warm egg of an okeanis.

Name: Loaghtan Chump
Description: A marbled piece of meat taken from the rump of a loaghtan where the leg meets the loin.

Name: Dhalmel Meat
Description: A gristle-filled slice of meat that will require extensive simmering for it to be rendered palatable.

Name: Okeanis Tail
Description: When skinned, this slice of serpent-like meat almost appears edible.

Name: Cockatrice Thigh
Description: A lean slice of cockatrice meat good for flavorful broths.

Name: Pearl Sprouts
Description: Tiny cabbage-like vegetables native to the highlands of Coerthas.

Name: Cyclops Onion
Description: A giant yellow onion often found growing on Abalathia's Spine.

Name: Emerald Beans
Description: A deep-green legume recently discovered growing on the floating islets above the Sea of Clouds.

Name: Highland Wheat
Description: A variety of dark-colored wheat suited to the rocky soil, shorter days, and colder temperatures of the Coerthas highlands.

Name: Highland Flour
Description: Finely milled highland wheat. It has a rich, earthy aroma.

Name: Coerthan Tea Leaves
Description: Considerably smaller than Thanalan tea leaves, more than double the amount of Ishgardian tea leaves are required to brew a single cup of tea.

Name: Mist Dill
Description: A fragrant herb characterized by its thin leaves. It is used in both medicines and culinary dishes.

Name: Chives
Description: A thin green onion used in many Ishgardian dishes.

Name: Magma Beet
Description: A sweet, easy-to-grow tuber native to Abalathia's Spine, these deep-red beets are a staple in Ishgardian culinary culture.

Name: Heavenly Kukuru Powder
Description: A sweet, fragrant powder ground from high-quality kukuru beans imported from exotic lands at a great price. A delicacy only available to the Holy See's most privileged.

Name: Sesame Seeds
Description: A tiny seed rich in aromatic oil, sesame is native to Meracydia, and thought to have first been brought to Eorzea by migrating Miqo'te.

Name: Yak Milk
Description:
The unique flavor of yak milk can be somewhat off-putting to those raised on cow or aldgoat milk.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Heavens Lemon
Description:
Possibly due to the increased sunlight it receives growing above the clouds, heavens lemons lack the acidity of normal sun lemons.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Hollandaise Sauce
Description: A rich sauce created with butter, egg yolks, and a hint of lemon.

Name: Birch Sap
Description: A thin clear sap harvested from birch trees.

Name: Birch Syrup
Description: Birch sap boiled down to a thick, sweet syrup.

Name: Dark Chestnut
Description: The spine-encased fruit of the dark chestnut tree.

Name: Sour Cream
Description: A thick cream created by fermenting yak milk.

Name: Fermented Butter
Description: Slightly pungent butter allowed to ferment for several days after churning.

Name: Old World Fig
Description:
A symbol of long life and femininity, this autumn fruit was originally brought from their homeland to Eorzea by the Sharlayans.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Cloud Banana
Description:
Though it resembles a tree, cloud bananas actually grow from an oversized herb. That does not, however, make them any less sweet.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Morel
Description: This rare mushroom with an oblong webbed cap is highly sought after by culinarians the realm over.

Name: Porcini
Description: A large fragrant mushroom popular in Coerthan cuisine.

Name: Chysahl Greens
Description: Though nearly identical in shape and color to gysahl greens, chysahl greens have a deeper, earthier flavor that chocobos (and man) seem to prefer.

Name: Abalathian Rock Salt
Description: Mined from veins found in Abalathia's Spine, this pinkish salt has a high mineral content which adds depth to its flavor.

Name: Honeydew Almonds
Description: A sweet variety of rare white almonds.

Name: Dravanian Paprika
Description: A rare pepper that is more sweet than it is spicy.

Name: Snurbleberry
Description:
This sweet, yet tart red berry is covered in tiny soft hairs that can be removed by lightly rubbing the fruit between one's palms.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Bouillon Cube
Description: Animal broth that has been reduced down to a paste and hardened into cubes which will keep for an extended duration.

Name: Oriental Soy Sauce
Description: Similar to Mun-Tuy sauce, this Far Eastern seasoning is made by fermenting soybeans in salt and then pressing the beans to collect the remaining savory liquid.

Name: Oriental Miso Paste
Description: Similar to Mun-Tuy paste, this Far Eastern seasoning is made by fermenting soybeans in salt.

Name: Vermicelli
Description: Thin noodles made with highland flour, eggs, water, and salt. These have been dried and will keep indefinitely.

Name: Mossy Stone Greatsword
Description: A greatsword crafted from giantsgall, a type of stone found on Thavnair. It is so covered in moss as to be rendered unusable.

Name: Mossy Stone Cannon
Description: A hand cannon crafted from giantsgall, a type of stone found on Thavnair. It is so covered in moss as to be rendered unusable.

Name: Mossy Stone Globe
Description: A star globe crafted from giantsgall, a type of stone found on Thavnair. It is so covered in moss as to be rendered unusable.

Name: Celestine
Description: A light-blue crystalline mineral which, when ground and added to any flammable material, will cause it to burn red.

Name: Garlond Steel
Description: A lightweight form of steel developed by the eponymous chief engineer of the Garlond Ironworks.

Name: Deep-red Enchanted Ink
Description: Fortifying ink with powder created by grinding down multi-aspected crystals has been found to improve aetherial conductivity several times more than ink fortified with common metals.

Name: Superior Deep-red Enchanted Ink
Description: Fortifying ink with powder created by grinding down multi-aspected crystals has been found to improve aetherial conductivity several times more than ink fortified with common metals. The concentration of this bottle's contents appears to be remarkably high.

Name: Deep-green Enchanted Ink
Description: Fortifying ink with powder created by grinding down multi-aspected crystals has been found to improve aetherial conductivity several times more than ink fortified with common metals.

Name: Superior Deep-green Enchanted Ink
Description: Fortifying ink with powder created by grinding down multi-aspected crystals has been found to improve aetherial conductivity several times more than ink fortified with common metals. The concentration of this bottle's contents appears to be remarkably high.

Name: Deep-blue Enchanted Ink
Description: Fortifying ink with powder created by grinding down multi-aspected crystals has been found to improve aetherial conductivity several times more than ink fortified with common metals.

Name: Superior Deep-blue Enchanted Ink
Description: Fortifying ink with powder created by grinding down multi-aspected crystals has been found to improve aetherial conductivity several times more than ink fortified with common metals. The concentration of this bottle's contents appears to be remarkably high.

Name: Red Clay
Description: Natural clay commonly used by potters and sculptors for its high malleability.

Name: Black Clay
Description: A partially synthetic clay created by mixing ground stone with an alchemical reagent.

Name: Synthetic Resin
Description: A fully malleable synthetic resin created through the wonders of alchemy.

Name: Bamboo Weave
Description: Thinly cut strips of bamboo used for creating simple models.

Name: Balsa Wood Scrap
Description: Unevenly cut pieces of light balsa wood. Can be used to create models.

Name: Balsa Wood Lumber
Description: Processed balsa wood lumber. Optimal for creating large, detailed models.

Name: Synthetic Fiber
Description: Alchemically crafted fiber both thin and durable. Used for holding together pieces when creating models.

Name: Aetherochemical Fiber
Description: Super-strong fiber created using recently rediscovered Allagan aetherochemical techniques.

Name: Empty Crystal
Description: A transparent crystal almost completely devoid of elemental aspect.

Name: Empty Cluster
Description: A transparent crystal cluster almost completely devoid of elemental aspect.

Name: Purified Coke
Description: A hot-burning fuel created by destructively distilling raw coal. This particular piece contains very few impurities, allowing for longer, hotter combustion.

Name: Raziqcoat
Description: Developed by a Near Eastern alchemist, this powder is used to treat and harden aurum regis.

Name: Dryad Sap
Description: A partially congealed ball of sticky sap extracted from a dryad.

Name: Moonbeam Silk
Description: A brilliant white silk spun by a rare breed of Eorzean spider.

Name: Odorless Animal Fat
Description: This gobbet of beastkin tissue does not exhibit the rancid odor most commonly associated with animal fat.

Name: Duskborne Aethersand
Description: The elementally aspected remnants of aetherially reduced matter. This fine sand emits a weak glow indiscernible during the day.

Name: Dawnborne Aethersand
Description: The elementally aspected remnants of aetherially reduced matter. This fine sand emits a brilliant light discernible even at midday.

Name: Landborne Aethersand
Description: The elementally aspected remnants of aetherially reduced mineral matter.

Name: Leafborne Aethersand
Description: The elementally aspected remnants of aetherially reduced floral matter.

Name: Seaborne Aethersand
Description: The elementally aspected remnants of aetherially reduced sea life.

Name: Chalcocite
Description: A black metallic ore containing copper and traces of iron and saltpeter.

Name: Cuprite
Description: Though its appearance suggests it is a precious gem, this ore is actually a rare form of red translucent copper.

Name: Dravanian Mistletoe
Description: A variety of parasitic plant found growing on trees in the Churning Mists.

Name: Abalathian Mistletoe
Description: A variety of parasitic plant found growing on trees in the Sea of Clouds.

Name: Red Alumen
Description: A reddish variety of the mineral used by leatherworkers to tan animal hides. It lacks the deodorizing properties of its lighter counterpart.

Name: Red Ooid
Description: An egg-shaped stone composed of countless layers of reddish mineral deposits enveloping a tiny nucleus of rock or shell.

Name: Green Ooid
Description: An egg-shaped stone composed of countless layers of greenish mineral deposits enveloping a tiny nucleus of rock or shell.

Name: Blue Ooid
Description: An egg-shaped stone composed of countless layers of bluish mineral deposits enveloping a tiny nucleus of rock or shell.

Name: Yellow Ooid
Description: An egg-shaped stone composed of countless layers of yellowish mineral deposits enveloping a tiny nucleus of rock or shell.

Name: Violet Ooid
Description: An egg-shaped stone composed of countless layers of purplish mineral deposits enveloping a tiny nucleus of rock or shell.

Name: Red Roundstone
Description: A bright-red stone so perfectly spherical, it is difficult to believe it was not hand-carved.

Name: Green Roundstone
Description: A bright-green stone so perfectly spherical, it is difficult to believe it was not hand-carved.

Name: Blue Roundstone
Description: A bright-blue stone so perfectly spherical, it is difficult to believe it was not hand-carved.

Name: Yellow Roundstone
Description: A bright-yellow stone so perfectly spherical, it is difficult to believe it was not hand-carved.

Name: Violet Roundstone
Description: A bright-purple stone so perfectly spherical, it is difficult to believe it was not hand-carved.

Name: Foxglove
Description: A poisonous herb native to the Coerthas highlands. Up to twenty purple finger-length flowers can bloom on a single stalk.

Name: Bladeleaf
Description: This variety of wild grass native to the Dravanian forelands is characterized by long, serrated leaves which can leave lacerations on unprotected skin.

Name: Wyvern's Wart
Description: A mushroom so toxic that it is said a single bite can kill an adult wyvern.

Name: Void Nut
Description: Some of Eorzea's more superstitious smallfolk believe the pattern of grooves found upon the shell of this otherwise ordinary walnut to be proof that an evil voidsent has possessed the poor fruit.

Name: Black Swan Feather
Description: The long, glossy feather of a common black swan.

Name: Bitter Foxglove
Description: A rare herb native to the Coerthas highlands. Poison extracted from its leaves is several times more deadly than that found in common foxgloves.

Name: Swordleaf
Description: This rare variety of wild grass native to the Dravanian forelands is characterized by long, serrated leaves which have been known to slice through hardened leather like it were butter.

Name: Dragon's Wart
Description: A mushroom so toxic that it is said a single bite can kill an adult dragon.

Name: Heavensnut
Description: Some of Eorzea's more pious peasants believe the pattern of grooves found upon the shell of this otherwise ordinary walnut to be proof that a messenger of the heavens has blessed the fruit.

Name: Mute Swan Feather
Description: The long, glossy feather of a rare mute swan.

Name: Bright Fire Rock
Description: An uncut, unpolished stone imbued with aetheric fire energy.

Name: Bright Lightning Rock
Description: An uncut, unpolished stone imbued with aetheric lightning energy.

Name: Granular Clay
Description: Crumbly balls of reddish clay added to soil to improve both moisture retention and drainage.

Name: Peat Moss
Description: Soil created by thousands of years of decaying flora gathering on the bottom of marshes.

Name: Black Soil
Description: This rich, dark soil receives its color from a high concentration of organic matter.

Name: Highland Oregano
Description: Due to its higher oil content, highland oregano is preferred over other breeds of oregano by apothecaries and perfumeries across Eorzea.

Name: Furymint
Description: Named after the spear-like shape of its leaves, this variety of mint has a cooler, less biting flavor than its darker-leaved cousin peppermint.

Name: Clary Sage
Description: A fragrant herb used in medicines, perfumes, and cooking.

Name: Type-1 Woodworking Counterfoil
Description: Proof of submission of a collectable requested by Rowena's House of Splendors.

Description: Proof of submission of a collectable requested by Rowena's House of Splendors.

Description: Before becoming obsolete due to advancements in tailoring, belts such as this were used for holding up trousers and the like.

Description: Before becoming obsolete due to advancements in tailoring, belts such as this were used for holding up trousers and the like.

Description: Before becoming obsolete due to advancements in tailoring, belts such as this were used for holding up trousers and the like.

Name: Haddock
Description: A whitefish perfect for frying.

Name: Orthodox Barding
Description: A beautifully ornamented suit of plate armor worn by chocobos in the service of church officiants.

Name: Twintania Neurolink Key
Description: A square of hardened resin-like material that, when tapped, summons Twintania, an ancient wyvern enslaved by the Allagans several thousand summers past.

Name: Amber Draught Chocobo Whistle
Description: A small hand-carved whistle that emits a unique, high-pitched tone discernible only by a rare amber draught chocobo trained from capture to recognize and respond to the sound. Use to summon your personal amber draught chocobo.

Name: Gold Chocobo Feather
Description: A common symbol of friendship throughout the realm, these brilliant plumes can be exchanged at Calamity salvagers for special rewards.

Name: Silver Chocobo Feather
Description: A common symbol of friendship throughout the realm, these brilliant plumes can be exchanged at Calamity salvagers for special rewards.

Name: Iron Giant Core
Description: The control unit of an iron giant.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - The Last Huzzah
Description: An illustrated manual of celebratory gestures best to be avoided at balls, masquerades, and other social gatherings. Use to learn the /huzzah emote.

Name: Steward Permit
Description:
This permit allows the hiring of stewards on the estate.

Private chambers (apartments), cottages, houses, and mansions can host 4, 6, 8, and 10 vendors, respectively.

Name: Coffin Lid
Description: Pried from the lid of a coffin, this plank of ancient wood is cold to the touch.

Name: Sephirot Sap
Description: Left behind by the Fiend, this lump of sap appears to pulse with aetheric energy.

Name: Fiend Sap
Description: Left behind by the Fiend, this lump of sap appears to induce growth in living organisms.

Name: Crystal Bell
Description:
One ring summons the crafter of coiffures to save you from your pass existence.

One per estate only.

Name: Stuffed Succubus
Description: Take this All Saints' Wake-themed doll to bed at your own risk.

Name: Pumpkin Desk
Description: A pumpkin-themed desk designed with All Saints' Wake in mind.

Name: Starlight Ornament
Description: A wall decoration hung in homes during the Starlight Celebration.

Name: Twin Star Ornament
Description: A brilliant wall decoration hung in homes during the Starlight Celebration.

Name: Starlight Sentinel
Description: A potted conifer displayed in homes during the Starlight Celebration.

Name: Oriental Orange Basket
Description:
Oriental oranges, while small, are far softer and sweeter than the oranges found growing in Eorzea.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  VIT Bonus: +4% (Max 6)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +2
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Paissa Doll
Description: A stuffed toy recently adopted for use in Heavensturn festivities.

Name: The Unending Journey
Description:
A full record of your past adventures, in one massive volume.

One per estate only.

Name: Oriental Tea Set
Description:
Bring a touch of the exotic to teatime with this collection of authentic Doman woodware.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Piety Bonus: +4% (Max 28)
  VIT Bonus: +4% (Max 27)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Manor Oven
Description: A large cooking oven designed in a similar fashion to the unit found in Haukke Manor's kitchens.

Name: Manor Counter
Description: A large counter designed in a similar fashion to the unit found in Haukke Manor's kitchens.

Name: Stack of Tomes
Description: A neatly assembled collection of works ranging from poetry to history. A tidy bibliophile's dream.

Name: Pile of Tomes
Description: A slightly strewn collection of works ranging from mythology to philosophy. A tidy bibliophile's nightmare.

Name: Oriental Round Table
Description: A low, circular table used for sitting on the floor.

Name: Mhachi Coffin
Description:
A faithful replica of a coffin discovered in the Void Ark.

One per estate only.

Name: Funguar Chair
Description: A low stool designed to resemble a mushroom.

Name: Mahogany Partition Door
Description: A partition and door combination, reaching to the ceiling and so sturdy that it may as well be a wall.

Name: Pumpkin Chair
Description: The perfect partner for a pumpkin desk.

Name: Broken Heart Chair (Right)
Description: Half a heart. Also half a chair.

Name: Broken Heart Chair (Left)
Description: Half a heart. Also half a chair.

Name: Paramour Bed
Description: A plush heart-shaped bed far more sophisticated than those found on Limsa Lominsa's pleasure barges.

Name: Hatchling Lamp
Description: A table lamp crafted in the image of an adorable chocobo hatchling.

Name: Topiary Chocobo
Description: A specially bred shrub pruned to the shape of a chipper chocobo.

Name: Ultimate Kettle
Description:
Unlike other kettles of legend, it cannot turn water to ale, nor is it bottomless. But it can boil water for tea in a count of sixty. 
One per estate only.

Name: Ultimate Kettle Zenith
Description:
It can boil water for a quality blend of tea in a count of thirty. And it glows with a strange light. Everyone knows that strangely glowing objects are likely made of legends. 
One per estate only.

Name: Ultimate Kettle Nexus
Description:
A true kettle of legend that shines with such brilliance that it is said even gods would beg for a sip of its contents. It can boil water for a premium blend of tea in a count of five. 
One per estate only.

Name: Sephirot Root
Description:
A masterful objet d'art created using the sap of the Fiend. 

One per estate only.

Name: Sephirot Tree
Description:
An imposing objet d'art of a sacred tree. 

One per estate only.

Name: Oriental Grass Plot
Description:
A tall variety of wild grass with stalks that end in large silver tufts of wispy flowers.

Up to ten flower plots may be placed in a single garden, regardless of type.

Name: Dravanian Down Tree
Description:
A unique species of flora found only growing in the Sea of Clouds. As its seeds do not take in soil from the lower realm, the trees must be planted and raised on sky islets before being transplanted.

Up to ten flower plots may be placed in a single garden, regardless of type.

Name: Microscopically Small Mogwalls
Description:
A set of four walls designed for those who wish to transform their estate into a home fit for a moogle.

Can only be used with cottages on small plots of land.

Name: Middlingly Medium Mogwalls
Description:
A set of four walls designed for those who wish to transform their estate into a home fit for a moogle.

Can only be used with houses on medium plots of land.

Name: Monstrously Large Mogwalls
Description:
A set of four walls designed for those who wish to transform their estate into a home fit for a moogle.

Can only be used with mansions on large plots of land.

Name: Cob Inner Wall
Description: A rustic wall made of soil, straw, and lime.

Name: Manor Flooring
Description: Flooring similar in design to that used in Haukke Manor.

Name: Faerie Chandelier
Description: This delicate light fixture will remind you the wood is alive and always watching...

Name: Witch's Broom
Description: Flipp'er over, flip flip! This enchanted broom will reveal no hidden messages spelled backwards, but you can ride it through the skies.

Name: Doman Magpie
Description:
Approximately 3.14159 times more intelligent than the average swallow.

Use item to acquire the Doman magpie minion.

Name: Wild Rose Barding
Description: A suit of chocobo armor designed to resemble that worn by a long-forgotten hero of legend.

Name: Wind-up Firion
Description:
Free is a very good price.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Firion minion.

Name: Pumpkin Butler
Description:
Oft-forgotten member of the Mandragoras, if the Pumpkin Butler harbors any ill will for those who have so easily forsaken him, he does a fine job of hiding it.

Use item to acquire the Pumpkin Butler minion.

Name: General-purpose Pure White Dye
Description: A rare and expensive white dye, used for coloring anything from cloth to metal.

Name: General-purpose Jet Black Dye
Description: A rare and expensive black dye, used for coloring anything from cloth to metal.

Name: General-purpose Metallic Silver Dye
Description: A rare and expensive silver dye, used for coloring anything from cloth to metal.

Name: General-purpose Metallic Gold Dye
Description: A rare and expensive gold dye, used for coloring anything from cloth to metal.
