Name: Paissa Brat
Description:
The eyes of a newborn paissa are said to see only the truth. The truth and food.

Use item to acquire the paissa brat minion.

Name: Wind-up Illuminatus
Description:
Comes complete with two hands, both blue as an Illuminati baby's bum.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Illuminatus minion.

Name: Wind-up Echidna
Description:
A remarkably lifelike recreation of the shape-shifting seductress. Perhaps a tad too lifelike...

Use item to acquire the wind-up Echidna minion.

Name: Wind-up Relm
Description:
Come on now, you stubborn old bag of bones!

Use item to acquire the wind-up Relm minion.

Name: Hunting Hawk
Description:
She loves you more than life itself. She's had to.

Use item to acquire the hunting hawk minion.

Name: Shalloweye
Description:
Please refrain from staring.

Use item to acquire the shalloweye minion.

Name: Penguin Prince
Description:
An empire awaits.

Use item to acquire the penguin prince minion.

Name: Clockwork Twintania
Description:
Another advanced Allagan creation. Is there anything the Allagans couldn't create? The Allagans are believed to have created an instrument to answer this very question.

Use item to acquire the clockwork Twintania minion.

Name: Korpokkur Kid
Description:
For best results, keep moist at all times.

Use item to acquire the korpokkur kid minion.

Name: Wind-up Ifrit
Description:
It doesn't bleed. You cannot kill it. (But you may discard it at your leisure.)

Use item to acquire the wind-up Ifrit minion.

Name: Thorne Dynasty Mantelshelf
Description: A special multi-tiered shelf widely used during the Thorne Dynasty to display ornamental dolls.

Name: Round Table Barding
Description: A suit of chocobo armor crafted using a design employed during the age of Thordan and his knights twelve.

Name: Pegasus Whistle
Description: A small opaline ocarina that, when played, emits a rainbow of sound that summons forth a pegasus.

Name: Wyvern Horn
Description: This heavy horn emits a bellowing blare that summons your trained wyvern mount.

Name: A Knight to Remember
Description: A commissioned portrait of recently deceased companion Haurchefant Greystone entitled A Knight to Remember.

Name: Dreadwyrm Miniature

Name: Cold Knight's Cookfire
Description: A warm fire and a place to rest one's weary legstwo things every Ishgardian knight looks forward to after a long cold day of duty.

Name: Oriental Snowcave
Description: A tightly packed pile of snow hollowed out and formed into a tiny dwelling. A thin coating of eternal ice ensures the snowcave will never melt.

Name: Mission Ceruleum
Description: Airship-grade refined ceruleum. Having long since begun the process of decay, it is not recommended for useunless one is keen to die in a fiery explosion.

Name: Mission Ceruleum Voucher
Description: Proof of purchase for a single tank of airship-grade refined ceruleum. Alas, it has long since passed its date of validity.

Name: Luminous Ice Crystal
Description: Formed during a battle waged in the Coerthas western highlands, this crystal's unusual luminosity is the result of a concentrated elemental charge.

Name: Luminous Wind Crystal
Description: Formed during a battle waged in the Sea of Clouds, this crystal's unusual luminosity is the result of a concentrated elemental charge.

Name: Luminous Fire Crystal
Description: Formed during a battle waged on Azys Lla, this crystal's unusual luminosity is the result of a concentrated elemental charge.

Name: Umbral Nodule
Description: A crystalline amalgamation of umbrally charged crystals.

Name: Enchanted Rubber
Description: A variety of pliable rubber imbued with arcane magicks to improve aetherial conductivity.

Name: Fast-drying Carboncoat
Description: Born of Allagan ingenuity, this aetherochemical concoction is said to rapidly increase a gem's hardness.

Name: Divine Water
Description: Water believed to be blessed by the Twelve. Used to exorcise powerful demons from worldly items.

Name: Fast-acting Allagan Catalyst
Description: Dubbed a god in the machina by those who first discovered it, modern scholars have yet to discover not only what the catalytic agent contains, but exactly how it functions, understanding only that the substance is required to quickly strengthen the properties of certain materials.

Name: Precision Gordian Bolt
Description: An expertly crafted bolt discovered in Alexander's Gordias sector.

Name: Unidentifiable Bone
Description: This highly collectable bone appears to be from a creature not recorded in the Raimdelle Codex.

Name: Precision Gordian Lens
Description: An expertly crafted lens discovered in Alexander's Gordias sector.

Name: Unidentifiable Shell
Description: This highly collectable shell appears to be from a creature not recorded in the Raimdelle Codex.

Name: Precision Gordian Spring
Description: An expertly crafted spring discovered in Alexander's Gordias sector.

Description: This highly collectable variety of ore is undocumented in the extensive Amajina & Sons mining logs.

Name: Precision Gordian Shaft
Description: An expertly crafted shaft discovered in Alexander's Gordias sector.

Name: Unidentifiable Seeds
Description: These highly collectable seeds appear to be from flora not recorded in the Raimdelle Codex.

Name: Adamantite Francesca
Description: A small throwing axe forged from adamantite.

Name: Pterodactyl Strap
Description: A thin leather strap cut from the cured hide of a pterodactyl.

Name: Titanium Alloy Mirror
Description: The reflective surface on this mirror has been achieved through countless days of buffing and polishing.

Name: Titanium Alloy Square
Description: A thin, tiny plate of hammered titanium alloy.

Name: Dispelling Arrow
Description: Not actually an arrow, but rather a warding charm carved into the shape of one.

Name: Blessed Fletchings
Description: Arrow fletchings crafted from the large, rigid feathers of an eagle and then blessed by an anointed Halonic priest.

Name: Kingcake
Description: A festive ring-shaped cake baked from brioche dough.

Name: Moogle Miniature
Description: A small ceramic figurine bearing the likeness of a plump moogle.

Name: Clan Mark Log
Description: A list of elite marks slain by the log's owner...before the owner himself vanished without a trace following an embarrassing defeat at the hands of a ladybug.

Name: Mhachi Farthing
Description: A small coin of low denomination once used in the long-fallen nation of Mhach. Once actively sought by numismatists across Eorzea, the market soon became oversaturated, causing this ancient currency to lose its value entirely.

Name: Heavens' Ward Helm Fragment
Description: A small piece of steel salvaged from a helm worn by one of the Heavens' Ward.

Name: Brass Sky Pirate Spoil
Description: When sky pirates raiding in the Sea of Clouds board another vessel, it is tradition to claim a piece of the airship to serve as proof of the deadly deed. These objects of honor and bravery have also been known to be used as currency between the brigands.

Name: Steel Sky Pirate Spoil
Description: When sky pirates raiding in the Sea of Clouds board another vessel, it is tradition to claim a piece of the airship to serve as proof of the deadly deed. These objects of honor and bravery have also been known to be used as currency between the brigands.

Name: Vanu Whitebone Promissory Note
Description: A promissory note that can be exchanged for Vanu whitebonestiny, bleached bones used as common currency amongst the many Vanu Vanu tribes.

Name: Sylphic Goldleaf Promissory Note
Description: A promissory note that can be exchanged for sylphic goldleavesgolden, decaying leaves used as currency by the sylphs.

Name: Steel Amalj'ok Promissory Note
Description: A promissory note that can be exchanged for steel Amalj'oksmall, curved steel blades used as currency by the Amalj'aa.

Name: Rainbowtide Psashp Promissory Note
Description: A promissory note that can be exchanged for rainbowtide psashpcolorful shells used as currency by the Sahagin.

Name: Titan Cobaltpiece Promissory Note
Description: A promissory note that can be exchanged for Titan cobaltpiecescrude pieces of flattened cobalt used as high-denomination currency by the kobolds of O'Ghomoro.

Name: Max-Potion
Description: This spiritous concoction instantly restores a considerable amount of HP.

Name: Max-Ether
Description: Processed via the alchemical extraction of aetheric essence occurring in elemental crystals, the contents of this vial instantly restore a considerable amount of MP.

Name: Lady's Suikan
Description: Fits: All

Name: White Devil Identification Key
Description: A thin, rectangular piece of what appears to be cermet. Placing it near the White Devil suit of magitek armor will magically bring the machine to life.

Name: Red Baron Identification Key
Description: A thin, rectangular piece of what appears to be cermet. Placing it near the Red Baron suit of magitek armor will magically bring the machine to life.

Name: Modern Aesthetics - Scion Special Issue
Description:
The realm's premier publication on beauty and fashion, this limited edition of Modern Aesthetics covers, in detail, techniques on transforming yourself into Scions of the Seventh Dawn Antecedent Minfilia.

Use to unlock a new hairstyle at the aesthetician.
Fits:  (excepting Viera and Hrothgar)

Name: Modern Aesthetics - Curls
Description:
The realm's premier publication on beauty and fashion, this specific copy of Modern Aesthetics covers, in detail, techniques on crafting a perfect dome of tight curls.

Use to unlock a new hairstyle at the aesthetician.
Unavailable to female Hrothgar.

Name: Modern Aesthetics - Adventure
Description:
The realm's premier publication on beauty and fashion, this limited edition of Modern Aesthetics covers, in detail, a hair styling technique submitted by one of the realm's readers.

Use to unlock a new hairstyle at the aesthetician.
Unavailable to female Hrothgar.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - The Thavnairian Dance
Description: An illustrated manual of the various steps that comprise the exotic Thavnairian dance. Use to learn the /thavnairiandance emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - The Gold Dance
Description: An illustrated manual of the various steps that comprise the Gold dance. Use to learn the /golddance emote.

Name: Iron Clapper
Description: A short piece of iron loosely affixed to the inside of a bell, causing it to ring when the clapper strikes the bell's wall.

Name: Functional Proto-hropken
Description:
A remarkably developed manlike fish living in the aetherochemical pools of Azys Lla.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Coerthan Clione
Description:
Though believed by scholars to be a distant cousin of the snail, this tiny transparent mollusk does not have a shell.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Dravanian Smelt
Description:
A tiny freshwater fish native to the lakes fed by runoff from the Slate Mountains.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Heavens Coral
Description:
A lightweight, sky blue coral found growing on the floating islands above Eorzea.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Sunsail
Description:
A flying fish found in the skies near the Landlord Colony.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Goblin Bass
Description:
Introduced to the Thaliak River by goblins, this variety of voracious bass has driven native species to the brink of extinction.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Pterodactyl
Description: A winged scalekin native to the Diadem.

Name: Eurhinosaur
Description: A rare scalekin that utilizes its highly developed air bladder to float above the Sea of Clouds.

Name: Gem Marimo
Description: A bright-green variety of aquatic moss found on the bottom of lakes. Slight currents cause the moss to gather and form into a ball as it grows.

Name: Crown Trout
Description: A freshwater fish native to the Diadem.

Name: Retribution Staff
Description: A large freshwater fish native to the Diadem.

Name: Thief Betta
Description: An aggressive freshwater fish native to the Diadem.

Name: Goldsmith Crab
Description: A tiny freshwater crustacean native to the Diadem.

Name: Certificate of Collaboration MMXVI
Description: A small, square slip of parchment stamped with the Ul'dahn royal seneschal's seal proving your aid in the very first promotion of the Songbirds.

Name: Steamed Staff
Description:
Not actually a staff, but a dish made from steaming a freshwater fish known as a retribution staffa long, thin wavekin believed to be the cause of storms.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Sesame Cookie
Description:
Tales of a blue monster who greedily devours these baked delights have frightened children across the realm for generations.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Wind Silk
Description: This silk is exposed to aetherial turbulence in order to strengthen its aspect to wind.

Name: Dinosaur Leather
Description: A large piece of cured dinosaur skin.

Name: Falconer's Hemp
Description: A double-weave variety of hemp used by falconers to protect themselves from the sharp talons of their raptors.

Name: Titanium Alloy Ingot
Description: A durable alloy created by smelting titanium with zinc.

Name: Cloud Cloth
Description: Soft, light cotton woven from rare cloud cotton bolls.

Name: Pterodactyl Leather
Description: A large piece of cured pterodactyl skin.

Name: Sphalerite
Description: A semi-translucent mineral containing large amounts of zinc and iron.

Name: Potters Stone
Description: A hard clay found exclusively on the islets of the Diadem. When fired in a kiln, the result is a brilliant white pottery.

Name: Royal Mistletoe
Description: A parasitic plant that is only found growing on the trees of the Diadem.

Name: Cloud Cotton Boll
Description: The cloud-like flower of a cotton plant native to the Diadem.

Name: Blood Pepper
Description: A deep red variety of dragon pepper so hot it is widely believed by Far Eastern cultures to drive away malignant spirits.

Name: Blood Pepper Seeds
Description: Blood pepper seeds suitable for garden cultivation.

Name: Dravanian Mote
Description: This lighter-than-air flora is unique to the Churning Mists.

Name: Oriental Grass Tuft
Description: A tall variety of grass common in the Far East.

Name: Cassia Block
Description: An expertly cut cube of fragrant cassia lumber.

Name: Tektite
Description: A type of naturally occurring glass first discovered after the Calamity which ushered in the Seventh Umbral Era.

Name: Eventide Jade
Description: A rare form of jade as red as a sunset.

Name: Fossilized Dragon Bone
Description: There is much debate amongst Eorzean scholars as to how much time must pass before a bone becomes fossilized. Some say a mere generation will suffice, citing evidence such as the proliferation of petrification magicks. Others believe it may take upwards of a thousand thousand years, casting doubts on the theories which state Hydaelyn was created a mere twenty thousand summers past.

Name: Periwinkle
Description: A mildly poisonous flower found across the Three Great Continents.

Name: Cloud Mushroom
Description: An aptly named fungus commonly found in the Sea of Clouds, wind providing a means of spore distribution from one islet to the next.

Name: Wind Widow
Description: A tiny poisonous spider that weaves sail-like webs used by the vilekin to traverse the Sea of Clouds.

Name: Old World Fig Seeds
Description: Old World fig seeds suitable for garden cultivation.

Name: Chive Seeds
Description: Chive seeds suitable for garden cultivation.

Name: Pearl Sprout Seeds
Description: Pearl sprout seeds suitable for garden cultivation.

Name: Coerthan Tea Seeds
Description: Coerthan tea seeds suitable for garden cultivation.

Name: Wind-up Zundu Warrior
Description:
Like a spring wind, the Zundu warrior is strong...until he winds down.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Zundu warrior minion.

Name: Wind-up Haurchefant
Description:
What isn't dead (or is recreated in a goldsmith's workshop) can never die.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Haurchefant minion.

Name: The Emperor's New Fists
Description: The most beautiful pair of pugilist's arms you will never see.

Tales of Adventure: A Realm Reborn
Description:
A detailed record of recent Eorzean historyso detailed, in fact, that all who read it come to swear they experienced the events firsthand.

Use to instantly complete all main scenario quests up through Before the Dawn. Cannot be used outside large settlements. Automatic logout will commence upon usage.

Name: Viltgance-type Hull
Description: A hull which utilizes a rigid, lightweight frame for a more stable flight.

Name: Viltgance-type Aetherwings
Description: The wings of a Viltgance-type airship, which adopt the same technology as Garlond Ironworks' manacutters in treating the wings with wind-aspected aether for buoyancy.

Name: Viltgance-type Forecastle
Description: The front half of a Viltgance-type airship, including the main deck and a sharp, narrow bow to balance air resistance.

Name: Viltgance-type Aftcastle
Description: The rear half of a Viltgance-type airship, with smaller aetherwings for supported buoyancy.

Name: Oldrose Seeds
Description:
Some say love, it is a river. Some say love, it is a flower. Plant these seeds and learn the truth.

For use in planters.

Name: Riviera Vase
Description:
A vase decorated in the riviera fashion.

Select flowers can be displayed within.

Name: Glade Vase
Description:
A vase decorated in the glade fashion.

Select flowers can be displayed within.

Name: Oasis Vase
Description:
A vase decorated in the oasis fashion.

Select flowers can be displayed within.

Name: Red Pomace
Description: An all-natural fertilizer used to increase red pigment in flowers.

Name: Blue Pomace
Description: An all-natural fertilizer used to increase blue pigment in flowers.

Name: Mountain Pomace
Description: An all-natural fertilizer used to increase yellow pigment in flowers.

Name: Type-1 Crafting Receipt
Description: Proof of submission of a collectable requested by Rowena's House of Splendors.

Name: Type-1 Gathering Receipt
Description: Proof of submission of a collectable requested by Rowena's House of Splendors.

Name: Fists of the Sephirot
Description: Weapon appearance may take precedence over the display of hand gear.

Name: Brand-new Ring
Description: Increases EXP earned by 30% when level 30 and below.

Name: Modern Vocation
Description: A publication on lost combat arts and the weapons and armor associated with those ancient schools of teaching. It has a section of blank pages to record one's own observations.

Name: Orchestrion
Description:
A furnishing that is sure to delight guests and residents alike, as they while away the hours listening to some of their favorite tunes.

One orchestrion of any type per estate only.

Name: Stuffed Onion Prince
Description: Attempting to peel away the layers of what makes this plush prince so glum will leave you with less than you started out with. As well as a mess of fabric.

Name: Pudding Floor Lamp
Description: A slimy floor lamp designed in the likeness of a pudding.

Name: Pudding Throw Rug
Description: A slimy throw rug designed in the likeness of a pudding.

Name: Pudding Settee
Description: A slimy settee designed in the likeness of a pudding.

Name: Pudding Desk
Description: A slimy desk designed in the likeness of a pudding.

Name: Alpine Supper Set
Description:
This warm array of comfort food has become a treat for special occasions amongst the commoner families of Ishgard, who have been known to save their coin for moons to procure the ingredients.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Skill Speed Bonus: +4% (Max 29)
  VIT Bonus: +4% (Max 28)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: High House Supper Set
Description:
An extravagant multiple-course meal enjoyed by the nobility of Ishgard on saint feast days and other ceremonious occasions. 

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Determination Bonus: +4% (Max 28)
  VIT Bonus: +4% (Max 27)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Senor Sabotender Trophy
Description: Everybody loves a winner. And with this trophy you, too, can feel like a winner.

Name: Riviera Flowerpot
Description:
A garden planter designed in the riviera style.

Small, medium, and large estates can hold 2, 3, and 4 planters, respectively. Private chambers and apartments can hold 2.

Name: Glade Flowerpot
Description:
A garden planter designed in the glade style.

Small, medium, and large estates can hold 2, 3, and 4 planters, respectively. Private chambers and apartments can hold 2.

Name: Oasis Flowerpot
Description:
A garden planter designed in the oasis style.

Small, medium, and large estates can hold 2, 3, and 4 planters, respectively. Private chambers and apartments can hold 2.

Name: Dinosaur Skull
Description: The crown of an ancient beast. While one may find it comical to stick his or her head in its mouth, collectors warn that its teeth are still razor-sharp and there have been unfortunate accidents.

Name: Dinosaur Skeleton
Description: The torso and legs of an ancient beast. Scholars are unsure why its modern cousins still have short arms, but they argue they must be of some merit in their hunting habits.

Name: Dinosaur Tailbone
Description: The tail of an ancient beast. Some believe that when struck with a mallet, the hollowed tailbones emit pleasant-sounding notes.

Name: Topiary Sabotender
Description: A specially bred shrub pruned to the shape of a scampering sabotender.

Name: Archon Egg Tower
Description: A Hatching-tide decoration with tiers of Archon eggs tirelessly hand-painted by the youngest of the Dreamers.

Name: Dandelion Plot
Description:
A tiny field of cheery dandelions that begs to be frolicked in.

Up to ten flower plots may be placed in a single garden, regardless of type.

Name: Living Arch
Description: An aging stone bridge covered in ivy and moss. Perfect for the romantic rendezvous.

Name: Shishi-odoshi
Description:
A fountain from the Far East originally used to scare away creatures and neighbors come to nibble on garden patches. 

Up to five may be placed in a single estate, regardless of type.

Name: Faust Striking Dummy
Description:
A striking dummy created by the Illuminati to train their ranks for combat.

Up to three dummies may be placed in a single estate, regardless of type.

Name: Gnathic Lamp Tree
Description: Any Gnath would click contently beneath the gentle glow of this lamp tree.

Name: Alpine Chandelier
Description: A sumptuous chandelier designed to complement alpine residences.

Name: Alpine Flooring
Description: Floorboards designed to complement alpine residences.

Name: Alpine Inner Wall
Description: An interior wall designed in the alpine fashion.

Name: Red Oldroses
Description:
A bunch of red oldroses, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Blue Oldroses
Description:
A bunch of blue oldroses, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Yellow Oldroses
Description:
A bunch of yellow oldroses, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Green Oldroses
Description:
A bunch of green oldroses, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Orange Oldroses
Description:
A bunch of orange oldroses, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Purple Oldroses
Description:
A bunch of purple oldroses, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: White Oldroses
Description:
A bunch of white oldroses, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Black Oldroses
Description:
A bunch of black oldroses, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Rainbow Oldroses
Description:
A bunch of multicolored oldroses, selectively fertilized to achieve a variety of vibrant colors.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Sephirotic Barding
Description: A suit of chocobo armor designed to resemble Sephirot, the Fiend.

Name: Egg Hunter Barding
Description: A suit of chocobo armor equipped with a basket for hunting eggs during Hatching-tide.

Name: Kongamato Whistle
Description: A small, conch-like whistle used to summon a Gnath-trained kongamato.

Name: Zu Horn
Description: This horn of bone emits a howling blare that summons your trained zu mount.

Name: Bennu Horn
Description: This horn of bone emits a golden tone that summons a mythical bennu.

Name: White Lanner Whistle
Description: This whistle emits a shrill tone that is said to summon a legendary falcon of the mists.

Name: Rose Lanner Whistle
Description: This whistle emits a shrill tone that is said to summon a legendary falcon of fury.

Name: Round Lanner Whistle
Description: This whistle emits a shrill tone that is said to summon a legendary falcon of the heavens.

Name: Warring Lanner Whistle
Description: This whistle emits a shrill tone that is said to summon a legendary falcon of catastrophe.

Name: Gloria Ignition Key
Description: This ignition key winds the gears of the Gloria-class airship. Remember to keep your balance.

Name: OFC Whistle
Description: A small hand-carved whistle that emits a high-pitched tone recognized as a feeding call by the original fat chocobo.

Name: Wind-up Gnath
Description:
<click> <click> He will obey.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Gnath minion.

Name: Wind-up Vath
Description:
<click> <click> He seeks purpose. So he will follow you. Everywhere.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Vath minion.

Name: Wind-up Garuda
Description:
Hopefully she will not HEEHEE haha HEEE!!! too loudly in your ear.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Garuda minion.

Name: Wind-up Titan
Description:
Placing this wind-up Titan on an elevated surface may compel it to knock everything else to the ground. 

Use item to acquire the wind-up Titan minion.

Name: Wind-up Leviathan
Description:
Your flesh cannot feed this minion of the deep. 

Use item to acquire the wind-up Leviathan minion.

Name: Wind-up Nero tol Scaeva
Description:
Better engineered than the wind-up Cid. In every way. 

Use item to acquire the Nero tol Scaeva minion.

Name: Faustlet
Description:
He will shelter you from the sturms. 

Use item to acquire the faustlet minion.

Name: Calca
Description:
Whether she is cute or creepy has been oft debated, but all agree it is best not to leave her to her own devices.  

Use item to acquire the Calca minion.

Name: Brina
Description:
Collectors warn that one who wishes to complete the set should be well versed in the art of combat. 

Use item to acquire the Brina minion.

Name: Morpho
Description:
With blue wings practically glowing, this butterfly feels almost like a spirit. Almost. 

Use item to acquire the morpho minion.

Name: Poro Roggo
Description:
Enchanted familiar though it may be, kissing it will do nothing to alter its corporeal form. 

Use item to acquire the Poro Roggo minion.

Name: Spoony Bard
Description:
Although there are many different accounts of what was actually said during the famous altercation, all agree on the single utterance that became his legacy.  

Use item to acquire the spoony bard minion.

Name: Fenrir Pup
Description:
This stray hoarhound pup is as feisty as the leader of his pack, and just as aloof. 

Use item to acquire the Fenrir pup minion.

Name: Goblin Cup
Description: Goblins fill these iron cups with rot-tea. It should probably be scoured before use.

Name: Goblin Dice
Description: A pair of precisely carved and balanced dice used for goblin gambling games.

Name: Handmaster's Tool Belt
Description: Before becoming obsolete due to advancements in tailoring, belts such as this were used for holding up trousers and the like.

Name: Landmaster's Survival Belt
Description: Before becoming obsolete due to advancements in tailoring, belts such as this were used for holding up trousers and the like.

Name: Master Carpenter IV
Description: This esoteric tomethe fourth in an equally esoteric seriescontains advanced woodworking recipes that can only be learned by highly skilled carpenters.

Name: Master Blacksmith IV
Description: This esoteric tomethe fourth in an equally esoteric seriescontains advanced smithing recipes that can only be learned by highly skilled blacksmiths.

Name: Master Armorer IV
Description: This esoteric tomethe fourth in an equally esoteric seriescontains advanced armorcraft recipes that can only be learned by highly skilled armorers.

Name: Master Goldsmith IV
Description: This esoteric tomethe fourth in an equally esoteric seriescontains advanced goldsmithing recipes that can only be learned by highly skilled goldsmiths.

Name: Master Leatherworker IV
Description: This esoteric tomethe fourth in an equally esoteric seriescontains advanced leatherworking recipes that can only be learned by highly skilled leatherworkers.

Name: Master Weaver IV
Description: This esoteric tomethe fourth in an equally esoteric seriescontains advanced clothcraft recipes that can only be learned by highly skilled weavers.

Name: Master Alchemist IV
Description: This esoteric tomethe fourth in an equally esoteric seriescontains advanced alchemy recipes that can only be learned by highly skilled alchemists.

Name: Master Culinarian IV
Description: This esoteric tomethe fourth in an equally esoteric seriescontains advanced cooking recipes that can only be learned by highly skilled culinarians.

Name: Spiced Cider
Description:
A warmed jug filled with piquant apple juice mulled with zested ginger and cloves, complete with a stick of cinnamon.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Apple Strudel
Description:
A handful of chopped apples glazed with birch syrup are thinly wrapped in a warm flaky crust, topped with just a sprinkling of cinnamon.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Peperoncino
Description:
Noodles tossed in mature olive oil that has been infused with solstice garlic and dragon peppers.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Boscaiola
Description:
A hearty dish of chewy noodles, heaped with a generous portion of seasonal mushrooms and drowned in tomato sauce.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Loaghtan Steak
Description:
A tough cut of loaghtan meat soaked in a marinade of paprika, sherry, and thyme and grilled over an open flame.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Oyster Confit
Description:
A serving of succulent Coerthan oysters on the half shell, simmered in rich olive oil and seasoned with fresh spices.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Angler Stew
Description:
A thick, creamy stew brimming with tender chunks of fish, onions, and chives.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Sweet Gnomefish
Description:
A gnomefish boiled in sweet birch syrup. The glaze preserves the fish for days after cooking.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Golden Apple
Description:
A mildly sweet apple with a tart aftertaste, this rare fruit is highly sought after amongst bakers.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Solstice Garlic
Description: Favored by chefs for leaving one's breath scant of odor after a meal, this zesty garlic is often used in gourmet dishes.

Name: Mature Olive Oil
Description: A rich-tasting oil produced with pressed olives at the peak of ripeness.

Name: Loaghtan Fillet
Description: Taken from the upper loin of a domesticated loaghtan, this meat is tender enough that it does not require any preparation before cooking.

Name: High Mythrite Ingot
Description: An ingot of smelted lumythrite.

Name: Eikon Mythrite
Description: Mythrite blessed by a primal.

Name: Lumythrite Ore
Description: An uncut, unpolished stone containing what appears to be lumythrite.

Name: Eikon Iron Ingot
Description: An ingot of smelted iron blessed by a primal.

Name: Eikon Metal
Description: A heavy piece of unidentifiable metal blessed by a primal.

Name: Smithsonite Ore
Description: This slightly lustrous ore is characterized by its extremely high zinc content.

Name: Eikon Cloth
Description: Finely woven cloth blessed by a primal.

Name: Eikon Fiber
Description: Tightly spun thread blessed by a primal.

Name: Frost Cotton Boll
Description: A soft and fluffy variety of cotton named for its resemblance to morning hoarfrost.

Name: Eikon Leather
Description: A large piece of cured beastkin skin blessed by a primal.

Name: Eikon Hide
Description: The skin of a large, yet unidentifiable creature, blessed by a primal.

Name: Treated Camphorwood Lumber
Description: A processed length of camphor lumber, treated with an alchemical agent to harden the wood.

Name: Camphorwood Lumber
Description: Processed camphor lumber. Its piquant aroma remains years after harvesting, making it a favorite for use in armoires and furnishings.

Name: Camphorwood Log
Description: A rough-cut log of camphorwood timber.

Name: Camphorwood Branch
Description: The thick branch of a camphorwood tree.

Name: Camphor
Description: The waxy, crystallized remnants of a liquid drawn from steamed bits of camphorwood.

Name: Gobcraft Resin
Description: A synthetic resin created by the goblins to protect leatherwork and carpentry from the elements.

Name: Grade 3 Strength Dissolvent
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to strength, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Grade 3 Dexterity Dissolvent
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to dexterity, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Grade 3 Vitality Dissolvent
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to vitality, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Grade 3 Intelligence Dissolvent
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to intelligence, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Grade 3 Mind Dissolvent
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to mind, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Max-Potion of Strength
Description:
This extremely powerful concoction temporarily increases strength.

Duration: 15s

Name: Amber Salamander
Description:
This freshwater amphibian is characterized by whorling patterns of deep amber across its moist skin.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Gnomefish
Description:
A decidedly ugly freshwater fish commonly found in and around the Thaliak River.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Fleece Stingray
Description:
The white belly of this flying fish native to the skies above Coerthas is ofttimes mistaken for a cloud.

[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Nyctosaur
Description:
A tiny winged dragon only recently discovered in the Churning Mists.

[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Lava Snail
Description:
The lumpy shell of the lava snail is extremely heat resistant, protecting its tiny resident from otherwise unbearable temperatures.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Priestfish
Description:
A distant cousin of the monkfish, this ravenous resident of the lakes and swamps of Coerthas also possesses a luminescent proboscis which it uses to attract prey.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Coerthan Oyster
Description:
A bivalve mollusk native to the lakes of Coerthas, and prized as a delicacy by Ishgardian nobles.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Oliphant's Trunk
Description:
Extended exposure to the unclassifiable aetherochemicals tainting the pools in which this fishlike creature lives has contributed to the abnormal development of its mouth and jaw.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Mountain Kraken
Description:
A massive freshwater squid found in the lakes of Coerthas.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Armored Catfish
Description:
This large freshwater fish is covered in thick armor-like scales which protect it from the jaws of hungry bears and yetis.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Rowena's Token (Lore)
Description: A note of promise received from Rowena for the delivery of Allagan tomestones of lore or poetics. However, due to the House of Splendors changing its policies, it is now worth less than the paper on which it is scribed.

Name: High-capacity Tomestone
Description: Ironworks experts insist these tomestones not only contain reams of invaluable information from the Allagan Empire, but compress a far greater wealth of knowledge within than the average tomestone. However, this particular variety is not as highly sought as it once was, and may no longer be exchanged for other wares.

Name: Fiend Totem
Description: This ligneous idol resembling the primal Sephirot is said to have been used by a tribe of treelike beings during summoning ceremonies.

Name: Tarnished Midan Lens
Description:
A uniquely crafted lens discovered in Alexander's Midas sector.

Two lenses can be traded for special headgear.

Name: Tarnished Midan Shaft
Description:
A uniquely crafted shaft discovered in Alexander's Midas sector.

Four shafts can be traded for special body gear.

Name: Tarnished Midan Crank
Description:

Name: Tarnished Midan Chain

Name: Tarnished Midan Bolt
Description:

One bolt can be traded for a special accessory.

Name: Kettle Knuckles
Description: Weapons crafted using the same metallurgical techniques employed in creating the weapons wielded by the legendary Zodiac Braves.

Name: Kettle Knuckles Zenith
Description: Weapons crafted and enhanced using the same metallurgical techniques employed in creating the weapons wielded by the legendary Zodiac Braves.

Name: Kettle Knuckles Nexus
Description: Weapons crafted and enhanced using the same metallurgical techniques employed in creating the weapons wielded by the legendary Zodiac Braves.

Name: Midan Gear
Description: A round cog removed from Alexander's Midas sector. Though such articles were once considered highly valuable, demand has dried up and they are now essentially worthless.

Name: Illuminati Deep Gobdip
Description: An alchemical potion concocted in the dark laboratoriums of the Illuminati. Some of the realm's more daring blacksmiths have applied the unnaturally viscous substance to a variety of weapons and found that it heightens the attributes of eikon-inspired equipment. However, advances in crafting technology have rendered it obsolete.

Name: Illuminati Taut Gobtwine
Description: An alchemical thread woven in the dark laboratoriums of the Illuminati. Some of the realm's more daring weavers have applied the unnaturally pliable substance to a variety of vestments and found that it heightens the attributes of eikon-inspired equipment. However, advances in crafting technology have rendered it obsolete.

Name: Illuminati Dark Gobcoat
Description: An alchemical potion concocted in the dark laboratoriums of the Illuminati. Some of the realm's more daring goldsmiths have applied the unnaturally illuminated substance to a variety of gems and found that it heightens the attributes of eikon-inspired equipment. However, advances in crafting technology have rendered it obsolete.

Name: Aether Oil
Description: Born of Allagan ingenuity, this aetherochemical oil can be applied to metal to lower its aetherial conductivity.

Name: Stuffed Eggplant Knight
Description: Designed with the most complicated pattern of the plush Mandragoras, this knight will protect your castle by day, and woo the queen by night. (Mandragora Queen sold separately.)

Name: Stuffed Garlic Jester
Description: This stuffed jester may fill your heart with childish glee, but too much cuddling and you will reek to high heavens.

Name: Stuffed Tomato King
Description: Having no kingdom to call his own, this stuffed plush will be more than willing to rule your realm with his adorable little green fist.

Name: Stuffed Mandragora Queen
Description: This adorable plush doll comes complete with a fabric flower and tiny hooks on the hands that can be attached to her secret lover. (Eggplant Knight sold separately.)

Name: Chocobo Training Manual - Choco Drain I
Description:
A comprehensive manual detailing chocobo training methods developed by experts across the realm. Use to teach your race chocobo the ability Choco Drain.

Ability Effect: Generates a field which drains the stamina of nearby chocobos at a rate of 15 per second.

Name: Chocobo Training Manual - Choco Drain II
Description:
A comprehensive manual detailing chocobo training methods developed by experts across the realm. Use to teach your race chocobo the ability Choco Drain II.

Ability Effect: Generates a field which drains the stamina of nearby chocobos at a rate of 25 per second.

Name: Chocobo Training Manual - Choco Drain III
Description:
A comprehensive manual detailing chocobo training methods developed by experts across the realm. Use to teach your race chocobo the ability Choco Drain III.

Ability Effect: Generates a field which drains the stamina of nearby chocobos at a rate of 35 per second.

Name: Chocobo Training Manual - Paradigm Shift
Description:
A comprehensive manual detailing chocobo training methods developed by experts across the realm. Use to teach your race chocobo the ability Paradigm Shift.

Ability Effect: Swaps current item with a different one.

Name: Chocobo Training Manual - Mimic I
Description:
A comprehensive manual detailing chocobo training methods developed by experts across the realm. Use to teach your race chocobo the ability Mimic.

Ability Effect: Repeats any ability or item used by a forerunning chocobo.
Duration:  7s

Name: Chocobo Training Manual - Mimic II
Description:
A comprehensive manual detailing chocobo training methods developed by experts across the realm. Use to teach your race chocobo the ability Mimic II.

Ability Effect: Repeats any ability or item used by a forerunning chocobo.
Duration:  11s

Name: Chocobo Training Manual - Mimic III
Description:
A comprehensive manual detailing chocobo training methods developed by experts across the realm. Use to teach your race chocobo the ability Mimic III.

Ability Effect: Repeats any ability or item used by a forerunning chocobo.
Duration:  15s

Name: Chocobo Training Manual - Feather Field I
Description:
A comprehensive manual detailing chocobo training methods developed by experts across the realm. Use to teach your race chocobo the ability Feather Field.

Ability Effect: Nullifies the detrimental field effects of any nearby chocobos.
Duration:  10s

Name: Chocobo Training Manual - Feather Field II
Description:
A comprehensive manual detailing chocobo training methods developed by experts across the realm. Use to teach your race chocobo the ability Feather Field II.

Ability Effect: Nullifies the detrimental field effects of any nearby chocobos.
Duration:  20s

Name: Chocobo Training Manual - Feather Field III
Description:
A comprehensive manual detailing chocobo training methods developed by experts across the realm. Use to teach your race chocobo the ability Feather Field III.

Ability Effect: Nullifies the detrimental field effects of any nearby chocobos.
Duration:  30s

Name: Chocobo Training Manual - Super Sprint
Description:
A comprehensive manual detailing chocobo training methods developed by experts across the realm. Use to teach your race chocobo the ability Super Sprint.

Ability Effect: Sprint without weather or terrain penalties until all stamina is spent.

Name: Chocobo Training Manual - Choco Reraise I
Description:
A comprehensive manual detailing chocobo training methods developed by experts across the realm. Use to teach your race chocobo the trait Choco Reraise.

Trait Effect: Instantly restores 60 stamina when stamina meter reaches zero.

Name: Chocobo Training Manual - Choco Reraise II
Description:
A comprehensive manual detailing chocobo training methods developed by experts across the realm. Use to teach your race chocobo the trait Choco Reraise II.

Trait Effect: Instantly restores 130 stamina when stamina meter reaches zero.

Name: Chocobo Training Manual - Choco Reraise III
Description:
A comprehensive manual detailing chocobo training methods developed by experts across the realm. Use to teach your race chocobo the trait Choco Reraise III.

Trait Effect: Instantly restores 200 stamina when stamina meter reaches zero.

Name: Chocobo Training Manual - Enfeeblement Clause I
Description:
A comprehensive manual detailing chocobo training methods developed by experts across the realm. Use to teach your race chocobo the trait Enfeeblement Clause.

Trait Effect: Reduces enfeeblement duration by 20%.

Name: Chocobo Training Manual - Enfeeblement Clause II
Description:
A comprehensive manual detailing chocobo training methods developed by experts across the realm. Use to teach your race chocobo the trait Enfeeblement Clause II.

Trait Effect: Reduces enfeeblement duration by 35%.

Name: Chocobo Training Manual - Enfeeblement Clause III
Description:
A comprehensive manual detailing chocobo training methods developed by experts across the realm. Use to teach your race chocobo the trait Enfeeblement Clause III.

Trait Effect: Reduces enfeeblement duration by 50%.

Name: Chocobo Training Manual - Breather I
Description:
A comprehensive manual detailing chocobo training methods developed by experts across the realm. Use to teach your race chocobo the trait Breather.

Trait Effect: Restores stamina at a rate of 0.8% per second while decelerating.

Name: Chocobo Training Manual - Breather II
Description:
A comprehensive manual detailing chocobo training methods developed by experts across the realm. Use to teach your race chocobo the trait Breather II.

Trait Effect: Restores stamina at a rate of 1% per second while decelerating.

Name: Chocobo Training Manual - Breather III
Description:
A comprehensive manual detailing chocobo training methods developed by experts across the realm. Use to teach your race chocobo the trait Breather III.

Trait Effect: Restores stamina at a rate of 1.2% per second while decelerating.

Name: Antique Rug
Description: Someone, many decades past, paid a considerable sum for this expertly woven floorpiece.

Name: Antique Leather
Description: An attestation to its quality, this leather remains supple and uncracked despite its age.

Name: Tincalconite
Description: A pure white mineral closely related to borax.

Name: Dinosaur Fossil
Description: The lithified remains of a dinosaur long deceased.

Name: Galvanized Garlond Steel
Description: A lightweight form of steel developed by the eponymous chief engineer of the Garlond Ironworks. This particular sample has been treated to increase hardness.

Name: Faust Armor Plating
Description: A heavy square of body armor removed from the Illuminati-constructed battlemachina Faust.

Name: Powdered Merman Horn
Description: This mysterious powder is claimed to have been ground from the horn of a merman, prompting the question, do mermen have horns? Regardless of its origins, the powder has been proven to be decidedly potent.

Name: Black Copper Gil Promissory Note
Description: A promissory note that can be exchanged for black copper gil which, at first glance, appears to be standard Eorzean currency. Until, that is, one notices the crooked stamping and texture of smelted scrap metal.

Name: Chipped Fortune Egg
Description: A plain white Archon egg believed to bring its bearer good luck as long as it remains uncracked. While scholars still hotly debate whether chipped is synonymous to cracked, it may be safer to simply obtain a new egg.

Name: Squadron Enlistment Manual
Description:
Grand Company-issue literature outlining basic techniques used in soldier recruitment.

Increases the chance a new recruit will request enlistment in your squadron. Effect ends upon recruit arrival.

Name: Priority Seal Allowance
Description:
A Grand Company-issue pass authorizing a temporary increase in payment for services rendered.

Increases number of company seals earned by completing Grand Company duties.
Seal Bonus: +15%  Duration: 120m
Overwrites company actions with similar effects.

Name: Gold Saucer VIP Card
Description:
A Grand Company-issue pass for officers granting a temporary increase in MGP payouts at the Manderville Gold Saucer.

Increases quantity of MGP earned by participating in Gold Saucer attractions.
MGP Bonus: +15%  Duration: 120m
Overwrites company actions with similar effects.

Name: Squadron Battle Manual
Description:
Grand Company-issue literature outlining basic combat techniques.

Increases EXP earned by defeating enemies in the field.
EXP Bonus: +15%  Duration: 120m
Overwrites company actions with similar effects.

Name: Squadron Survival Manual
Description:
Grand Company-issue literature outlining basic foraging techniques.

Increases EXP earned from gathering activities.
EXP Bonus: +20%  Duration: 120m
Overwrites company actions with similar effects.

Name: Squadron Engineering Manual
Description:
Grand Company-issue literature outlining basic sapping and engineering techniques.

Increases EXP earned from crafting activities.
EXP Bonus: +20%  Duration: 120m
Overwrites company actions with similar effects.

Name: Squadron Spiritbonding Manual
Description:
Grand Company-issue literature outlining advanced weapon techniques.

Increases spiritbonding speed.
Spiritbond Bonus: +3  Duration: 120m
Overwrites company actions with similar effects.

Name: Squadron Rationing Manual
Description:
Grand Company-issue literature outlining basic cooking and rationing techniques.

Increases meal effect duration.
Duration Increase: +15m  Duration: 120m
Overwrites company actions with similar effects.

Name: Squadron Gear Maintenance Manual
Description:
Grand Company-issue literature outlining basic gear maintenance techniques.

Decreases gear wear.
Wear Decrease: +30%  Duration: 120m
Overwrites company actions with similar effects.

Name: Priority Aetheryte Pass
Description:
A Grand Company-issue pass authorizing priority use of realm-wide aetherytes at a discounted rate.

Decreases aetheryte teleportation fees.
Fee Reduction: 40%  Duration: 120m
Overwrites company actions with similar effects.

Name: Lumythrite Sand
Description: Glowing sand consisting of tiny grains of lumythrite.

Name: Whitefrost Cotton Boll
Description: Despite their delicate appearance, the fibers of the whitefrost cotton flower are deceptively durable.

Name: Old-growth Camphorwood Log
Description: A glance at a cross section of this log reveals that a mere glance isn't enough to count the hundreds, perhaps thousands, of rings present.

Name: Golden Sparkler
Description: Unsatisfied with the spark output of regular sparklers, Manderville & Manderville hired their own team of pyrotechnicians to create the perfect work of fire.

Name: Deluxe Heavenscracker
Description: An unexpected by-product of the Skysteel Manufactory's recent endeavors to develop a more volatile variety of firesand. Packs twice the amount of explosive punch as a regular heavenscracker.

Name: Modern Aesthetics - Pulse
Description:
The realm's premier publication on beauty and fashion, this specific copy of Modern Aesthetics covers, in detail, techniques on becoming the ultimate enigmatic protagonist.

Use to unlock a new hairstyle at the aesthetician.

Name: MGP Gold Card
Description: Use to immediately add 30,000 MGP to your Manderville Gold Saucer account.

Name: Flying Cumulus Seed
Description: The incantation on this enchanted scroll is believed to birth a wondrous cloud, lighter than air, yet solid enough to bear a rider.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Exotic Greetings
Description: An illustrated manual of curious greeting customs from the Far East. Use to learn the /easterngreeting emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Improper Celebration
Description: An illustrated manual of vulgar celebratory rituals from faraway lands. Use to learn the /backflip emote.

A distinct variety of dark matter only found in areas with ties to the ancient civilization of Mhach.

[Can be exchanged for select combat-based varieties of materia V.]

Name: Copper Voyage Spoil
Description: One of various items collected on an expeditionary voyage.

Name: Iron Voyage Spoil
Description: One of various items collected on an expeditionary voyage.

Name: Race Barding
Description: Lightweight armor designed for race chocobos.

Name: Storm Trophy (Left)
Description: A sensibly sized monument to Limsa Lominsa's Grand Company, the Maelstrom. One of three independent pieces.

Name: Storm Trophy (Center)
Description: A sensibly sized monument to Limsa Lominsa's Grand Company, the Maelstrom. One of three independent pieces.

Name: Staggered Shelf
Description: A bookshelf with crannies of various sizes, designed in the Doman fashion.

Name: Washbasin
Description: An elegant, stand-alone sink for washing up before dinner. And you will wash up before dinner.

Name: Stuffed Bear
Description: If you can catch him unawares, you may see him picnic on his holiday.

Name: Alpine Breakfast
Description:
A simple but hearty breakfast oft supped upon by Temple Knights before taking their morning tilts.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Tenacity Bonus: +4% (Max 28)
  VIT Bonus: +4% (Max 27)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Hat Stand
Description: A hat stand designed in the alpine fashion.

Name: Ashtray
Description: A clay bowl for the neat disposal of fogweed ash. For the adventurer who likes to unwind between battles without getting soot on the furniture.

Name: Indirect Lighting
Description:
A footlight focused in a single direction for dramatic theatrical effect.

Up to two may be placed in a single estate, regardless of type.

Name: Indirect Stand Lighting
Description:
A standing light focused in a single direction for a dramatic theatrical effect.

Up to two may be placed in a single estate, regardless of type.

Name: Chirurgeon's Curtain
Description: A large hanging cloth used to provide a patient and his caregiver privacy.

Name: Nidhogg Miniature
Description:
A statuette depicting the great wyrm, Nidhogg (Azure Dragoon not included).

One per estate only.

Name: Markworthy Mogsofa
Description: A sofa so soft, you will forget you are the only one sitting on it...

Name: Dragon Floor Lamp
Description: A somber floor lamp designed in the likeness of a dragon.

Name: Season One Lone Wolf Trophy
Description: A trophy awarded to those who left their mark in Season One of the Feast.

Name: Rising Banner
Description: A handsome banner designed to decorate residences for the annual Rising celebration.

Name: Beach Chair
Description: A brightly striped lounging space for beachgoers, elevated to keep sand from finding its way into trunks.

Name: Morning Glory Plot
Description:
Brilliant purple flowers that will follow the sun as it makes its journey across the morning sky.

Up to ten flower plots may be placed in a single garden, regardless of type.

Name: Large Garden Pond
Description: A large decorative outdoor pond encircled by mossy stones.

Name: Oriental Wood Bridge
Description: An arched bridge colored brilliant vermilion using traditional Far Eastern lacquering techniques.

Name: Oriental Deck
Description: A roofed, wooden deck with a Far Eastern aesthetic. Perfect for stoically fanning yourself on humid summer days.

Name: Pumpkin Carriage
Description: Someday your prince (or princess) will come. Probably not in this, though.

Name: Firefly Lamp
Description:
A wooden cage weaved in a Far Eastern style. The fireflies within provide very little light, but are pleasing to gaze upon.

Up to five may be placed in a single estate, regardless of type.

Name: Sharlayan Flooring
Description: Elegant marbled flooring capable of transforming any estate into a bastion of enlightenment.

Name: Bluesky Interior Wall
Description: A cheery interior wall for those who wish their skies to be forever blue.

Name: Gold Saucer Chandelier
Description: A chandelier used in the Manderville Gold Saucer.

Name: Yo-kai Medal
Description: A simple silver coin that sends chills down your spine.

Name: Legendary Jibanyan Medal
Description: A small multicolored metal disk bearing the image of Jibanyan.

Description: A small multicolored metal disk bearing the image of Komasan.

Name: Jibanyan
Description:
He tends to take out his anger on passing vehicles.

Use item to acquire Jibanyan.

He got bored with guarding his shrine. Now he wants to guard you.

Use item to acquire Komasan.

Name: Whisper

Use item to acquire Whisper.

Name: Blizzaria

Name: Kyubi
Description:
A quite charming and extremely strong Yo-kai.

Use item to acquire Kyubi.

Name: Komajiro
Description:
He might as well tag along on your adventures as he searches for his older brother.

Use item to acquire Komajiro.

Name: Manjimutt

Use item to acquire Manjimutt.

Name: Noko
Description:
This Yo-kai is one lucky snake!

Use item to acquire Noko.

Name: Venoct
Description:
All of his abilities are truly first class.

Use item to acquire Venoct.

Name: Shogunyan
Description:
This legendary warrior's armor smells faintly of tuna.

Use item to acquire Shogunyan.

Name: Hovernyan
Description:
He may be a wanderer, but he's actually quite dependable.

Use item to acquire Hovernyan.

Name: Robonyan F-type
Description:
An upgraded robot that thinks it's a cat.

Use item to acquire Robonyan F-type.

Name: USApyon
Description:
A Yo-kai that aims for the moon.

Use item to acquire USApyon.

Description:

Use item to acquire the Piggy minion.

Use item to acquire the magic bucket minion.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases, for some reason.]

Description:
Use item to acquire the calamari minion.

(Or is it a trap!?)

The greatest adventure ever born.

Use item to acquire the baby brachiosaur minion.

Oh, I think that you've found yourself a cheerleader.

Use item to acquire the wind-up cheerleader minion.

Description:
She is terribly, terribly sorry to have kept you waiting.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Krile minion.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Aymeric minion.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Calofisteri minion.

It thankfully cannot pelt you with its steaming stool.

Use item to acquire the wind-up sasquatch minion.

Name: Tier 1 Aquarium
Description:
A circular glass tank that, when filled with water, can serve as a home for select wavekin caught in the wild. The higher an aquarium's tier, the larger the specimens that can be kept within.
Private chambers (apartments), cottages, houses, and mansions can hold 4, 6, 8, and 10 aquariums, respectively.

Description: An illustrated manual of the queer stretching exercises employed by Far Eastern hermits to ensure their bodies remain limber. Use to learn the /easternstretch emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Eastern Dance
Description: An illustrated manual of the various steps that comprise a dance originating in the fantastical Far East. Use to learn the /easterndance emote.

Name: Disembodied Head Resonator
Description: A metal tuning fork that, when struck, emits a high-pitched tone which can animate inanimate objects possessing voidal propertiesincluding your personal disembodied stone head.

Name: Managarm Horn
Description: A twisted horn whose eerie bellow renders the deadly moon hound, Managarm, meek as a newborn whelp.

Name: Pellitory
Description: A fine powder ground from dried mountain daisies. The pungent smoke emitted when burned as an incense is believed to repel all manner of vilekin.

Name: Whisper A-go-go Key
Description: It may just be their imagination, but some say they can hear the sound of a thousand groans and a single meow as the key winds the gears.

Name: Mhachi Penny
Description: A small coin of low denomination once used in the long-fallen nation of Mhach. There are four Mhachi farthings in a penny. Once actively sought by numismatists across Eorzea, the market soon became oversaturated, causing this ancient currency to lose its value entirely.

Name: Lover's Laurel
Description: A highly fragrant variety of laurel named for the goddess of the moon, Menphina.

Name: Radiant Astral Moraine
Description: Luminous gravel with an unbalanced elemental aspect tipping towards astral.

Name: Chocobo Cottage Walls
Description:
A set of four walls designed for those whose love for chocobos transcends mundane aesthetic sensibilities.

Can only be used with cottages on small plots of land.

Name: Chocobo House Walls
Description:
A set of four walls designed for those whose love for chocobos transcends mundane aesthetic sensibilities.

Can only be used with houses on medium plots of land.

Name: Chocobo Mansion Walls
Description:
A set of four walls designed for those whose love for chocobos transcends mundane aesthetic sensibilities.

Can only be used with mansions on large plots of land.

Name: Riviera Chocobo Stable
Description:
A simple stable designed in the La Noscean riviera style.

Cannot be retrieved once placed.
One per estate only.

Name: Glade Chocobo Stable
Description:
A simple stable designed in the Gridanian glade style.

Cannot be retrieved once placed.
One per estate only.

Name: Oasis Chocobo Stable
Description:
A simple stable designed in the Ul'dahn oasis style.

Cannot be retrieved once placed.
One per estate only.

Name: Compact Level 6 Aetherial Wheel Stand
Description:
A small metal stand upon which aetherial wheels are placed and spun to charge. Holds three grade 1, two grade 2, and one grade 3 wheel.
One stand per estate only.

Name: Tiny Bronco Miniature
Description: A made-to-scale model of a Bronco-type airship, expertly crafted by Garlond Ironworks engineers.

Name: Invincible Miniature
Description: A made-to-scale model of an Invincible-type airship, expertly crafted by Garlond Ironworks engineers.

Name: Enterprise Miniature
Description: A made-to-scale model of an Enterprise-type airship, expertly crafted by Garlond Ironworks engineers.

Name: Invincible II Miniature
Description: A made-to-scale model of an Invincible II-type airship, expertly crafted by Garlond Ironworks engineers.

Name: Odyssey Miniature
Description: A made-to-scale model of an Odyssey-type airship, expertly crafted by Garlond Ironworks engineers.

Name: Tatanora Miniature
Description: A made-to-scale model of a Tatanora-type airship, expertly crafted by Garlond Ironworks engineers.

Name: Viltgance Miniature
Description: A made-to-scale model of a Viltgance-type airship, expertly crafted by Garlond Ironworks engineers.

Name: Sophia Miniature
Description:
A statuette depicting the Meracydian goddess, Sophia. (Barbelo statuette suspiciously missing.)

One per estate only.

Name: Alexander Miniature
Description:
An expertly crafted replica of the primal Alexander. (Arms, cuffs, and burdens included.)

One per estate only.

Name: Happy New Chocobo
Description: A feathered objet d'art placed in homes to celebrate Heavensturn.

Name: Stuffed Calca
Description: What every impressionable toddler needs in her toy box. Psychosomatic trauma increased tenfold when paired with a stuffed Brina.

Name: Stuffed Brina
Description: What every impressionable toddler needs in her toy box. Psychosomatic trauma increased tenfold when paired with a stuffed Calca.

Name: Mammet Lantern
Description: A stout table lantern designed to resemble an automaton mammet.

Name: Mounted Box Shelf
Description: Several interconnected boxes hung on walls to store knickknacks, gewgaws, and other assorted miscellany.

Name: Knightly Round Table
Description: A handcrafted replica of the table at which the Heavens' Ward hold conclave.

Name: Pumpkin Stew
Description:
An All Saints' Wake culinary tradition, this rich, buttery soup is oft served in a hollowed-out pumpkin.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  CP Bonus: +9% (Max 23)
  GP Bonus: +5% (Max 22)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +2
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Mounted Bookshelf
Description: A large bookshelf commonly found in private libraries.

Name: Great Gubal Floor Lamp
Description: A tall, standing lamp of the same design as the light fixtures found in the Great Gubal Library.

Name: Combed Wool Rug
Description: A plush throw rug so soft, it will have your guests swearing they tread upon the very Sea of Clouds.

Name: Spirits Collection
Description: Several half-filled bottles of rare potables certain to impress any crapulent callers.

Name: Starlight Pillar
Description: A festive pillar used to decorate residences for the Starlight Celebration.

Name: Season Two Lone Wolf Trophy
Description: A trophy awarded to those who left their mark in Season Two of the Feast.

Name: Season Two Pack Wolf Trophy
Description: A trophy awarded to those who left their mark in Season Two of the Feast.

Name: Autumnal Maple Tree
Description: A young maple tree transplanted at the moment its leaves began turning red, and magicked so that it might remain in this state for all eternity (or until the spell weakens).

Name: Autumnal Ginkgo Tree
Description: A young ginkgo tree transplanted at the moment its leaves began turning yellow, and magicked so that it might remain in this state for all eternity (or until the spell weakens).

Name: Maple Leaf Pile
Description: This near-perfect pile of meticulously gathered maple leaves simply begs passersby to throw all self-restraint to the wind and take the plunge.

Name: Ginkgo Leaf Pile
Description: This near-perfect pile of meticulously gathered ginkgo leaves simply begs passersby to throw all self-restraint to the wind and take the plunge.

Name: Snow Drift
Description: A giant pile of pristine white snow. Yellow coloring optional.

Name: Firecrest Trophy
Description:
A stunning trophy crafted from an item believed to contain the soul of a legendary dragon.

One per estate only.

Name: Glass Pumpkin Trophy
Description:
A stunning trophy crafted using a flawless crystal pumpkin believed to be imbued with arcane magicks.

One per estate only.

Name: Deluxe Pumpkin Basket
Description: A pumpkin-shaped basket filled with All Saints' Wake goodies. Decidedly better than last year's basket in ways far too numerous to list here.

Name: Deluxe Stuffed Succubus
Description: Take this All Saints' Wake-themed doll to bed at your own risk. Decidedly better than last year's succubus in ways far too numerous to list here.

Name: Deluxe Pumpkin Desk
Description: A pumpkin-themed desk designed with All Saints' Wake in mind. Decidedly better than last year's desk in ways far too numerous to list here.

Name: Deluxe Pumpkin Chair
Description: The perfect partner for a pumpkin desk. Decidedly better than last year's chair in ways far too numerous to list here.

Name: Empty Sparkleboxes
Description: A sparklebox without a present is like a twinklebox without a present is like a child without a smile.

Name: Jumbo Stuffed Qiqirn
Description: A handmade doll crafted to resemble a Qiqirn, and dressed in a festive Starlight Celebration outfit. The difference in size with a normal stuffed Qiqirn is indiscernible to all but the most observant.

Name: Jumbo Starlight Wreath
Description: A simple circle of evergreen branches hung on doors during the Starlight Celebration. While the tradition is fairly new, there already exist several theories as to how the practice started. Some believe the circle represents the symbolic beginning and end of a year, and in turn, our lives, while others claim it is merely easier to hang a ring than it is a straight branch. The difference in size with a normal Starlight wreath is indiscernible to all but the most observant.

Name: Jumbo Starlight Ornament
Description: A wall decoration hung in homes during the Starlight Celebration. The difference in size with a normal Starlight ornament is indiscernible to all but the most observant.

Name: Jumbo Twin Star Ornament
Description: A brilliant wall decoration hung in homes during the Starlight Celebration. The difference in size with a normal twin star ornament is indiscernible to all but the most observant.

Name: Jumbo Starlight Sentinel
Description: A potted conifer displayed in homes during the Starlight Celebration. The difference in size with a normal Starlight sentinel is indiscernible to all but the most observant.

Name: Jumbo Sheep Dolls
Description: Two stuffed sheephusband and wifedressed in traditional Far Eastern garb. The difference in size with normal sheep dolls is indiscernible to all but the most observant.

Name: Jumbo Hard Rice Cakes
Description: Known in the Far East as kagami mochi, these cakes are not traditionally eaten, but displayed before and during Heavensturn. The difference in size with normal hard rice cakes is indiscernible to all but the most observant.

Name: Jumbo Oriental Orange Basket
Description:
Oriental oranges, while small, are far softer and sweeter than the oranges found growing in Eorzea. The difference in size with a normal oriental orange basket is indiscernible to all but the most observant.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  VIT Bonus: +4% (Max 6)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +2
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Jumbo Paissa Doll
Description: A stuffed toy recently adopted for use in Heavensturn festivities. The difference in size with a normal paissa doll is indiscernible to all but the most observant.

Name: Deluxe Pumpkin Candlestand
Description: A decorated lamppost displayed during All Saints' Wake. Decidedly better than last year's candlestand in ways far too numerous to list here.

Name: Jumbo Star-topped Starlight Sentinel
Description:
A potted fir, decorated with a star-shaped ornament at its apex. The difference in size with a normal star-topped Starlight sentinel is indiscernible to all but the most observant.

Only one Starlight sentinel may be placed in a single estate, regardless of type.

Name: Jumbo Moon-topped Starlight Sentinel
Description:
A potted fir, decorated with a crescent moon-shaped ornament at its apex. The difference in size with a normal moon-topped Starlight sentinel is indiscernible to all but the most observant.

Only one Starlight sentinel may be placed in a single estate, regardless of type.

Name: Jumbo Sun-topped Starlight Sentinel
Description:
A potted fir, decorated with a sun-shaped ornament at its apex. The difference in size with a normal sun-topped Starlight sentinel is indiscernible to all but the most observant.

Only one Starlight sentinel may be placed in a single estate, regardless of type.

Name: Jumbo Snowman
Description: Garlean scholars have conducted extensive studies on the subject of why Eorzean snowmen are constructed of only two balls of snow rather than threethe number of choice throughout Ilsabard. The prevailing theory is that extensive studies should not have been conducted on said subject. The difference in size with a normal snowman is indiscernible to all but the most observant.

Name: Empty Present Boxes
Description: A box without a present is like a box without a gift is like a bird without a song.

Name: Jumbo Kadomatsu
Description: A mini-tower of sliced bamboo and pine branchesthe kadomatsu is a Far Eastern oddity traditionally displayed at homes and in temples for the duration of Heavensturn. The difference in size with a normal kadomatsu is indiscernible to all but the most observant.

Name: Deluxe Eerie Wallpaper
Description: Ready your estate for All Saints' Wake with this frightening-yet-festive interior wall covering. Decidedly better than last year's wallpaper in ways far too numerous to list here.

Name: Deluxe Starlight Interior Wall
Description: This wall bears a festive design certain to bring joy and cheer to all...until you finally get around to taking it down six moons later. Decidedly more stellar than last year's walls in ways far too profound to explain here.

Name: Crystal Chandelier
Description: The aether contained within the crystals used to construct this magnificent lighting fixture emits an ethereal glow which enhances the mood of any hall or parlor.

Name: Palace of the Dead Flooring
Description: Flooring designed using reports penned by those fortunate enough to return from their expeditionary missions into the Palace of the Dead...with their sanity intact.

Name: Palace of the Dead Interior Wall
Description: An interior wall designed using reports penned by those fortunate enough to return from their expeditionary missions into the Palace of the Dead...with their sanity intact.

Name: Viola Seeds

And there is pansies, that's for thoughts. And there is pansy seeds, that's for growing pansies.

For use in planters.

My will is strong! So is this automaton's resistance to rust.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Yuna minion.

Name: Wind-up Rikku

Victory is ours! This automaton is yours.

Name: Wind-up Bartz

I like small Bartz and I cannot lie.

Name: Wind-up Red Mage
Description:
He'd rather be red than dead.

Use item to acquire the wind-up red mage minion.

Name: Syldra Horn

Description: This small glass bell has a slip of parchment attached to its clapper which, when blown by the wind, causes the clapper to strike the rim. Completely different than last year's chime, we promise.

Name: Deluxe Bombard Lamp
Description: A massive lamp designed to resemble the villain of the Moonfire Fairethe Bombard. Completely different than last year's lamp, we promise.

Name: Deluxe Moonfire Lantern
Description: An outdoor lantern traditionally placed outside one's home for the duration of the Moonfire Faire. Completely different than last year's lantern, we promise.

Name: Deluxe Ornamental Bamboo
Description: People hailing from the Far East claim that wishes written on small slips of parchment and tied to the bamboo will come true. (Magical wish parchment sold separately.) Completely different than last year's bamboo, we promise.

Name: Deluxe Wooden Bucket
Description: A wooden bucket filled with crystal-clear water. Families in the Far East use these receptacles to chill fruit during the hot summer moons. Completely different than last year's bucket, we promise.
