Name: Micro Tomestone
Description: Similar to the more common tomestones believed to store the lost knowledge of the Allagan Empire, yet at the fraction of the size, micro tomestones are highly sought by collectors and scholars alike. However, that was before the market became flooded with this particular variety, and as a result, it is no longer accepted as a viable bartering material.

Name: Illuminati Darkest Gobcoat
Description: An alchemical potion concocted in the dark laboratoriums of the Illuminati. Some of Idyllshire's goblin goldsmiths have applied the unnaturally viscous substance to a variety of precious stones and found that it heightens the attributes of the gear and accessories crafted in their workshops. However, advances in crafting technology have rendered it obsolete.

Name: Illuminati Tautest Gobtwine
Description: An alchemical thread woven in the dark laboratoriums of the Illuminati. Some of Idyllshire's goblin weavers have applied the unnaturally pliable substance to a variety of vestments and found that it heightens the attributes of gear woven in their looms. However, advances in crafting technology have rendered it obsolete.

Name: Illuminati Deepest Gobdip
Description: An alchemical potion concocted in the dark laboratoriums of the Illuminati. Some of Idyllshire's goblin smithies have applied the unnaturally illuminated substance to a variety of metals and found that it heightens the attributes of weapons crafted in their forges. However, advances in crafting technology have rendered it obsolete.

Name: Alexandrian Gear
Description: A round cog removed from Alexander's main sector.

Name: Tarnished Alexandrian Lens
Description:
A uniquely crafted lens discovered in Alexander's main sector.

Two lenses can be traded for special headgear.

Name: Tarnished Alexandrian Shaft
Description:
A uniquely crafted shaft discovered in Alexander's main sector.

Four shafts can be traded for special body gear.

Name: Tarnished Alexandrian Crank
Description:
A uniquely crafted crank discovered in Alexander's main sector.

Two cranks can be traded for special arm gear.

Name: Tarnished Alexandrian Spring
Description:
A uniquely crafted spring discovered in Alexander's main sector.

Four springs can be traded for special leg gear.

Name: Tarnished Alexandrian Pedal
Description:
A uniquely crafted pedal discovered in Alexander's main sector.

Two pedals can be traded for special foot gear.

Name: Tarnished Alexandrian Chain
Description: A uniquely crafted chain discovered in Alexander's main sector. Alas, advancements in trouser technology have rendered it worthless.

Name: Tarnished Alexandrian Bolt
Description:
A uniquely crafted bolt discovered in Alexander's main sector.

One bolt can be traded for a special accessory.

Name: Alexandrian Manifesto - Page 1
Description:
The opening page of the Illuminati's least-known catechismal masterwork.

Manifesto pages of the same type can be traded for special gear.

Name: Alexandrian Manifesto - Page 2
Description:
The second page of the Illuminati's least-known catechismal masterwork.

Manifesto pages of the same type can be traded for special gear.

Name: Alexandrian Manifesto - Page 3
Description:
The third page of the Illuminati's least-known catechismal masterwork.

Manifesto pages of the same type can be traded for special gear.

Name: Alexandrian Manifesto - Page 4
Description:
The fourth page of the Illuminati's least-known catechismal masterwork.

Manifesto pages of the same type can be traded for special gear.

Name: Sophic Barding
Description: A suit of chocobo armor designed to resemble Sophia, the Goddess.

Name: Abigail Barding
Description: A suit of chocobo armor designed to fulfill your lifelong desire to see a chocobo dressed like a scullery maid.

Name: Angelic Barding
Description: A suit of armor designed to give your chocobo another pair of flightless wings.

Name: Demonic Barding
Description: A suit of armor designed to have you questioning your chocobo's motives.

Name: Mystic Panda Pipe
Description: A hand-carved flute whose song will summon a mystic panda down from the mist-covered mountains of Othard's Fanged Crescent.

Name: Sophic Lanner Whistle
Description: This whistle emits a shrill tone that is said to summon a legendary falcon bred to serve the ancient Meracydian goddess, Sophia.

Name: Arrhidaeus Master Key
Description: A heavy gold key that, when inserted into the proper slot on the Arrhidaeus transport module, will power the superannuated device.

Name: Night Pegasus Whistle
Description: A small ebon ocarina that, when played, emits a rainbow of sound that summons forth a night pegasus.

Name: Goten Pipe
Description: An otherworldly flute that, when played, summons the armored Mado steed, Goten.

Name: Ginga Pipe
Description: An otherworldly flute that, when played, summons the armored Mado steed, Ginga.

Name: Raigo Pipe
Description: An otherworldly flute that, when played, summons the armored Mado steed, Raigo.

Name: Dress-up Thancred
Description:
Take a walk on Thancred's wild side...but with fewer nutkins.

Use item to acquire the dress-up Thancred minion.

Name: Dress-up Alisaie
Description:
Now 120% more discernable from the wind-up Alphinaud minion.

Use item to acquire the dress-up Alisaie minion.

Name: Shaggy Shoat
Description:
This adorable piglet will gore your heart and leave you yearning for more.

Use item to acquire the shaggy shoat minion.

Name: Wind-up Edda
Description:
Because true love never dies.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Edda minion.

Name: Toy Alexander
Description:
A special something for all good Illuminati gobs and girls.

Use item to acquire the toy Alexander minion.

Name: Continental Eye
Description:
I see you. You see me.

Use item to acquire the Continental eye minion.

Name: Modern Aesthetics - Samsonian Locks
Description:
The realm's premier publication on beauty and fashion, this specific copy of Modern Aesthetics covers, in detail, methods for styling longer hair.

Use to unlock a new hairstyle at the aesthetician.
Unavailable to female Hrothgar.

Name: Materia Melder Permit
Description:
This permit allows the hiring of materia melders on the estate.

Private chambers (apartments), cottages, houses, and mansions can host 4, 6, 8, and 10 vendors, respectively.

Name: Heavy Metal Ingot
Description: An ingot of smelted wolfram alloy.

Name: Scintillant Ingot
Description: An ingot of smelted luminium ore.

Name: Star Velvet
Description: Tufted fabric with extremely short pile rendering it smooth to the touch. This rare velvet's thin fibers grant it a unique glossiness from which it earns its name.

Name: Hemicyon Leather
Description: A large piece of cured hemicyon hide.

Name: Heavenly Eggnog
Description:
A decadently creamy concoction crafted from raw eggs, thick cream, honey, andif you are feeling adventurousa healthy splash of a dark spiced rum. A favorite in Ishgard's Vault.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Flaugnarde
Description:
A baked pudding filled to bursting with ripened apples and dusted with fragrant spices.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Spaghetti Carbonara
Description:
Tender wheat noodles slathered in a rich sauce made from egg yolks and pungent cheese.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Wildwood Scrambled Eggs
Description:
Fragrant mushrooms sauted in a generous pat of creamery butter and served upon a bed of fluffy eggs, scrambled to perfection.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Spaghetti Pescatore
Description:
Common fare of fisherfolk across Eorzea's southwestern coasts, the sauce used in this pasta dish consists of a wide variety of fresh local seafoodfrom fish to mollusk.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Loaghtan Cordon Bleu
Description:
Lean loaghtan chops sliced horizontally, stuffed with a thick slice of cheese, breaded, and fried to a golden brown.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Priestly Omelette
Description:
While similar to a regular omelette, this recipe perfected in the Vault's kitchens calls for a fistful of shredded cheese and mushrooms to further enhance the dish's richness.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Supramax-Potion of Strength
Description:
This unthinkably powerful concoction temporarily increases strength.

Duration: 15s

Name: Supramax-Potion of Dexterity
Description:
This unthinkably powerful concoction temporarily increases dexterity.

Duration: 15s

Name: Supramax-Potion of Vitality
Description:
This unthinkably powerful concoction temporarily increases vitality.

Duration: 15s

Description:

Duration: 15s

Name: Star Cotton Boll
Description: A rare variety of cotton which produces nitid fibers that, when struck by light, coruscate like the very stars in the heavens.

Name: Brown Mushroom
Description: An earthen fungus that can commonly be found sprouting beneath trees growing in the Churning Mists.

Name: Noble Sage
Description: A fragrant herb used in medicines, perfumes, and cooking. Its deep blue flowers set it apart from its cousin, clary sage.

Name: Tungstite
Description: A bright-yellow mineral formed by the weathering of scheelite.

Name: Luminium Ore
Description: A decent-sized piece of rock containing the precious metal luminium.

Name: Zeolite Ore
Description: A porous silicate that adsorbs poisons, making it invaluable in myriad alchemical and medical concoctions.

Name: Titanium Carbide
Description: Titanium that has been ground to a powder and carbonized via extreme heat.

Name: Scintillant Nugget
Description: A small nugget of impure luminium.

Name: Invisible Silk
Description: Silk so thin, it is barely discernable with the naked eye, despite proving as tensile as normal silken thread. Only silkworms bred under strict conditions will produce such fiber.

Name: Hemicyon Hide
Description: The thick bristly hide of an ancient breed of canine believed unchanged for seven Astral Eras.

Name: Goblacquer
Description: A protective sealant created by goblins and used to protect wood from rot and water damage, as well as provide it a lustrous sheen.

Name: Goblinol
Description: A potent solvent created by goblins and known for its biting odor said to resemble unrefined ceruleum.

Name: Demicrystal
Description: Aetherial residue seeped forth from spiritbound weapons.

Name: Sweet Cream Milk
Description: Fat-rich milk taken from buffaloes raised in a controlled, stress-free environment.

Name: Stone Cheese
Description: Gas which forms during the fermentation process creates hollow bubbles throughout this otherwise hard, flavorful cheese.

Name: Season Two Lone Wolf Voucher A
Description: Documentation of noteworthy accomplishments for Season Two of the Feast.

Name: Dimorphodon
Description:
This rarely seen winged scalekin is thought to be lord of the skies adjacent the Sohm Al summit.

[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Basking Shark
Description:
The basking shark's characteristic colossal maw makes it the de facto lord of the skies near Mok Oogl Island.

[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Allagan Bladeshark
Description:
Only found near the Flagship in Azys Lla, the bladeshark is an alpha predator with few enemiesa true lord of the skies.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Hailfinder
Description:
A king among rime eaters, and lord of the skies near Greytail Falls.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Flarefish
Description:
A king among sorcerer fish, and lord of the waters of the unfrozen pond.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Twin-tongued Carp
Description:
A king among three-lip carp, and lord of the waters of the Whilom River.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Madam Butterfly
Description:
A queen among Orn butterflies, and lady of the waters of the Quickspill Delta.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Moggle Mogpom
Description:
A king among mogpoms, and lord of the skies near Greensward.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Cirrostratus
Description:
A king among fleece stingrays, and lord of the skies off Cloudtop.

[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Hraesvelgr's Tear
Description:
A king among Aithon's colts, and lord of the lava pools of west Mourn.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Aetherochemical Compound #666
Description:
A king among aetherochemical compounds, and lord of the aetherochemical spill.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Hundred-eyed Axolotl
Description:
A king among tiny axolotls, and lord of the waters near the Pappus Tree.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Bobgoblin Bass
Description:
A king among goblin bass, and lord of the waters of the middle Thaliak River.

[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Merciless
Description:
A queen among mercy staves, and lady of the waters of Banepool.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Starlight Gift Box
Description: No matter what wonders await inside this festive package, always remember that during this season of giving, it is the thought that counts.

Name: Stale Pumpkin Cookie MMXVI
Description: A devilish imp is thought to have made this slightly burnt biscuit shaped like a pumpkin head. Not recommended for consumption...especially after having been sitting in your inventory for more than a twelvemoon.

Name: Indirect Wall Lighting
Description:
A mounted wall light focused in a single direction for a dramatic theatrical effect.

Up to two may be placed in a single estate, regardless of type.

Name: Palace Pedestal
Description: A boxlike pedestal designed according to an adventurer's harrowing recollection of a similar accursed object discovered deep within the Palace of the Dead.

Name: Troupe Stage
Description: A large portable stage suitable for the performance of concertos or large-scale productions of literary masterpieces such as the Ballad of Longhaft.

Name: Round Stage
Description: All the world is a stage. Now your room can be even more so.

Name: Mhachi Demimatter
Description:
A distinct variety of dark matter only found in areas with ties to the ancient civilization of Mhach.

[Can be exchanged for select non-combat-based varieties of materia V.]

Description: Use to immediately add 50,000 MGP to your Manderville Gold Saucer account.

Name: Wind-up Moenbryda
Description:
Destined to die a hero...and live on as a mechanized servitor.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Moenbryda minion.

Name: Rowena's Token (Scripture)
Description: A note of promise received from Rowena for the delivery of Allagan tomestones of scripture or poetics. However, due to the House of Splendors changing its policies, it is now worth less than the paper on which it is scribed.

Name: Magicked Prism (Pumpkin)
Description: This peculiar contraption creates illusions by weaving together myriad shades of light. Releases a heart-stopping disembodied pumpkin head.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - A Fitting End
Description: An illustrated manual detailing the ten essential steps to die a graceful death. Use to learn the /playdead emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Better Dead than Underbred
Description: An illustrated manual detailing actions unbecoming for a maid of noble upbringing. Use to learn the /prettyplease emote.

Name: Newborn Soulstone
Description: An artificially crafted soulstone used primarily in the conjuring of arcane entities.

Name: Pneumite
Description: A peculiar crystalline rock formed from dark matter fused with elementally aspected crystals.

Name: Archaic Enchanted Ink
Description: Ink enchanted using ancient techniques now lost. This bottle could contain the very last sample of its kind. Or not.

Name: Grade 1 Picture Frame
Description: A frame suitable for holding small paintings or illustrations.

Name: Grade 2 Picture Frame
Description: A frame suitable for holding medium-sized paintings or illustrations.

Name: Grade 3 Picture Frame
Description: A frame suitable for holding large paintings or illustrations.

Name: Material Supplier Permit A-2
Description:
This permit allows the hiring of material suppliers on the estate.

Private chambers (apartments), cottages, houses, and mansions can host 4, 6, 8, and 10 vendors, respectively.

This permit allows the hiring of junkmongers on the estate.

Private chambers (apartments), cottages, houses, and mansions can host 4, 6, 8, and 10 vendors, respectively.

Private chambers (apartments), cottages, houses, and mansions can host 4, 6, 8, and 10 vendors, respectively.

Certificate of Collaboration MMXVII
Description: A small, square slip of parchment stamped with the Ul'dahn royal seneschal's seal proving your aid in the promotion of the Songbirds.

Name: Tales of Adventure: One Retainer's Journey I
Description:
A detailed record of one retainer's path to becoming a highly sought-after servitorso detailed, in fact, that all who read it come to swear they experienced the events firsthand.

Hand over to instantly raise the level of a retainer up to a maximum of 60. (Retainer level cannot exceed current character level in the relevant class/job.)

Name: Stuffed Baby Behemoth
Description: We can only hope his stuffed mother comes looking for him.

Name: Paissa Cottage Walls
Description:
A set of four walls designed for those who wish to transform their estate into paissa paradise.

Can only be used with cottages on small plots of land.

Name: Paissa House Walls
Description:
A set of four walls designed for those who wish to transform their estate into a paissa paradise.

Can only be used with houses on medium plots of land.

Name: Paissa Mansion Walls
Description:
A set of four walls designed for those who wish to transform their estate into a paissa paradise.

Can only be used with mansions on large plots of land.

Name: Demonic Lanner Whistle
Description: This whistle emits a shrill tone that is said to summon a legendary falcon bred to serve the ancient Meracydian god, Zurvan.

Name: Firebird Whistle
Description: A mysterious whistle that, when sounded, calls forth a fiery bird of Far Eastern legend.

Name: Eggshilaration System Identification Key
Description: A thin, rectangular piece of some unknown material. Placing it near your reprogrammed eggshilaration system will magically bring the machine to life.

Name: Lone Hellhound Whistle
Description: A metallic tube-like whistle that emits a unique, high-pitched tone only discernable by a hellhound raised and trained in captivity. Use to summon your lone hellhound mount.

Name: Pack Hellhound Whistle
Description: A metallic tube-like whistle that emits a unique, high-pitched tone only discernable by a hellhound raised and trained in captivity. Use to summon your pack hellhound mount.

Name: Archon Throne
Description: A mysterious floating chair rumored to have been used by the famed Archon Louisoix himself...despite the fact no one actually ever saw him ride it.

Name: Zurvan Miniature
Description:
A statuette depicting the Meracydian god, Zurvan. (Fetters conveniently missing.)

One per estate only.

Name: Diabolos Miniature
Description:
A statuette depicting the high voidsent, Diabolos. (Feels too heavy to be hollow.)

One per estate only.

Name: Scathach Miniature
Description:
A statuette depicting the high voidsent, Scathach. (Guaranteed to cast a shadow, even in complete darkness.)

One per estate only.

Name: Paramour Vase
Description:
The perfect way to say I love you without having your hands torn to shreds by thousands of prickly rose thorns.

Select flowers can be displayed within.

Name: Forever Friends
Description: A commissioned oil painting of Papalymo and YdaArchons, Scions, heroes...and friends. Original artist unknown.

Name: Plundered Treasure
Description: Because nothing says high class like a hundred gold coin replicas sprawled about your floor.

Name: Yarn Basket
Description: The stuff of feline dreams.

Name: Riviera Breakfast
Description:
An eggcellent way to start your day.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Critical Hit Bonus: +4% (Max 28)
  VIT Bonus: +4% (Max 27)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Little Ladies' Day MMXVI Advertisement
Description: One of hundreds of hand-drawn images posted about Ul'dah in preparation for Little Ladies' Day.

Name: Paissa Floor Lamp
Description: The complete hide of a skinned paissa, cured and then molded into a quaint lampshade...or at least that is what one might think when first viewing this intricately crafted lamp. (No paissas were harmed in the creation of this furnishing.)

Name: Merchant's Shelf
Description: When a merchant needs somewhere to stack his wares.

Name: Ivy Pillar
Description: The vibrant vines curling about this marble-like pillar have been treated with elemental magicks so that they require no water, never brown, and never grow.

Name: Season Three Lone Wolf Trophy
Description: A trophy awarded to those who left their mark in Season Three of the Feast.

Name: Season Three Pack Wolf Trophy
Description: A trophy awarded to those who left their mark in Season Three of the Feast.

Name: White Partition
Description: A simple white wall to provide the purest form of privacy.

Name: Eastern Cherry Petal Pile
Description: There is nothing quite as ephemeral as a single pink cherry petal dancing in the wind as it makes its long descent from tree to earth, just as there is nothing quite as exhilarating as jumping in a drift of tens of thousands of said petals.

Name: Topiary Paissa
Description: An evergreen shrub, tightly cropped to resemble an adorable paissa.

Name: Moongrass Plot
Description:
A sweet-smelling plant with delicate flowers that blossom only when kissed by the light of the moon.

Up to ten flower plots may be placed in a single garden, regardless of type.

Name: Fortemps Manor Interior Wall
Description: An interior wall for those in the mood for a dash of northern sophistication.

Name: Eggstravagant Interior Wall
Description: An interior wall designed to complement private Hatching-tide celebrations.

Name: White Interior Wall
Description: A plain white interior wall for those estate owners with minimalistic tastes.

Name: Tribunal Flooring
Description: A close replica of the flooring found in the Supreme Sacred Tribunal of Halonic Inquisitory Doctrine.

Name: Pendant Lamp Planter
Description: All the beauty of a pendant lamp coupled with all the functionality of a garden planter. Why did no one think of this before!?

Name: Authentic Broken Heart Chair (Right)
Description: Half a heart. Also half a chair. One hundred percent authentic.

Name: Authentic Broken Heart Chair (Left)
Description: Half a heart. Also half a chair. One hundred percent authentic.

Name: Authentic Paramour Bed
Description: An authentic heart-shaped bed far more sophisticated than those found on Limsa Lominsa's pleasure barges.

Name: Authentic Thorne Dynasty Mantelshelf
Description: An authentic multi-tiered shelf widely used during the Thorne Dynasty to display ornamental dolls.

Name: Authentic Egg Floor Lamp
Description: An authentic Hatching-tide-themed floor lamp.

Name: Authentic Senor Sabotender Trophy
Description: Everybody loves a winner. And with this authentic trophy you, too, can feel like a winner.

Name: Authentic Flame of Passion
Description: Authentic outdoor lighting certain to heat up any relationship.

Name: Authentic Eastern Cherry Tree
Description: An authentic cherry tree from the Far East modified through generations of grafting and crossbreeding to bloom perpetually.

Name: Authentic Felt Mat
Description: A square sheet of authentic crimson-colored felt upon which dolls are displayed for Little Ladies' Day.

Name: Authentic Archon Egg Tower
Description: An authentic Hatching-tide decoration with tiers of Archon eggs tirelessly hand-painted by the youngest of the Dreamers.

Name: Crystalscape Tank Trimmings
Description:
An assortment of items used to outfit an aquarium that it might resemble a crystalline wonderland.

[For use in any tier aquarium.]

Description:

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Description: Oft employed by sky pirates and other unsavory individuals to protect their hard-earned plunder, these small containers are nigh impossible to open by all but the most skilled lockpicks.

Name: Damaged Lockbox
Description: This lockbox is so badly damaged that the chances whatever lies within remains undamaged are slim. Name: Demon Totem
Description: This queer idol resembling the primal Zurvan is said to have been used during summoning ceremonies by tribes of centaur-like Meracydians.

Name: Modern Aesthetics - Rainmaker
Description:
The realm's premier publication on beauty and fashion, this specific copy of Modern Aesthetics is a compilation of festive stylings for any occasion.

Use to unlock a new hairstyle at the aesthetician.

Name: Modern Aesthetics - Master & Commander
Description:
The realm's premier publication on beauty and fashion, this specific copy of Modern Aesthetics covers, in detail, techniques on imitating Ishgard's Lord Commander Aymericrecently voted by Modern Aesthetics readers the realm's dreamiest temple knight.

Use to unlock a new hairstyle at the aesthetician.
Unavailable to Hrothgar.

Name: Lord Commander's Coat
Description: Fits: All

Name: Lord Commander's Gloves
Description: Fits: All

Name: Proto Ultima Heat Shielding
Description: A surprisingly light piece of metal that made up Proto Ultima's outer armor, protecting the machinery within from extreme temperatures.

Name: Zurvanite Barding
Description: A suit of chocobo armor designed to resemble Zurvan, the Demon.

Name: Legendary Clan Mark Log
Description: A list of elite marks slain by the log's ownera hunter so great, that her legendary exploits are almost too remarkable to believe. Though such documents were once considered highly valuable, demand has dried up and they are now essentially worthless.

Name: Pegasus Colt
Description:
Unfortunately does not emit rainbows from any of its orifices.

Use item to acquire the pegasus colt minion.

Name: Bullpup
Description:
Runt of the canis pugnaces litter.

Use item to acquire the bullpup minion.

Name: Angel of Mercy
Description:
Come and save me tonight.

Use item to acquire the angel of mercy minion.

Name: Wind-up Estinien
Description:
Absolutely, positively not possessed by an evil dragon bent on ridding the world of mankind.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Estinien minion.

Name: Wind-up Hraesvelgr
Description:
Comes complete with overhead nameplate to help with spelling.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Hraesvelgr minion.

Name: Gigi
Description:
Also known as Vivi...but his secret is safe with you.

Use item to acquire the Gigi minion.

Name: Anima
Description:
From your heart and from your hand. Finally people will understand your intentions.

Use item to acquire the anima minion.

Name: Wind-up Scathach
Description:
Surprisingly visible despite being a queen of the shadows.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Scathach minion.

Name: Wind-up Nidhogg
Description:
Now with more eyes.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Nidhogg minion.

Name: Hellpup
Description:
Not all children are products of their environment. This one, however, is.

Use item to acquire the hellpup minion.

Name: Faepup
Description:
Every dog has its fae.

Use item to acquire the faepup minion.

Name: Wind-up Ohl Deeh
Description:
100% less subject to violent mood swings than its living counterpart.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Ohl Deeh minion.

Name: Wind-up Moon
Description:
/poke to adjust elevation. /point to inform others of its location. /blowkiss to get strange looks from passersby.

Use item to acquire the wind-up moon minion.

Name: Shroud Cherry Sapling
Description:
Looks so good, bring a tear to your eye.

For use in planters.

Name: Cloud Acorn Sapling
Description: The humble beginnings of a mighty cloud oak.

Name: Cloud Acorn
Description: The Vanu Vanu will oft use these large seeds in the creation of sacred ornaments, or even armor.

Name: Near Eastern Antique
Description: A piece of Radz-at-Han's illustrious history.

Name: Coerthan Souvenir
Description: A novel item to remember the northern region by.

Name: Maelstrom Materiel
Description: A practical item handy in times of war or peace.

Name: Heartfelt Gift
Description: The best gifts are those that come from the heart.

Name: Orphanage Donation
Description: An everyday item necessary in the operation and upkeep of a public home for forsaken wastrels.

Name: Near Eastern Antique Component
Description: A component used to complete a Near Eastern antique.

Name: Coerthan Souvenir Component
Description: A component used to complete a Coerthan souvenir.

Name: Maelstrom Materiel Component
Description: A component used to complete a piece of Maelstrom materiel.

Name: Dated Radz-at-Han Coin
Description: Currency once used on the Near Eastern island of Thavnair, now only sought by numismatists and historians.

Name: Ice Stalagmite
Description: Ice stalactites hold on tight to the ceiling of a cave. This is not an ice stalactite.

Name: Duskfall Moss
Description: Infusions made with this hardy brown-black foliage are believed to restore vigor.

Name: Glass Eye
Description: A small bead of naturally formed glass that could pass off as an eye, if viewed from thirty paces...in the fog.

Name: Rainbow Pigment
Description: Extracted from natural sources, this colorful powder can be prepared to create an equally colorful dye.

Name: Thavnairian Leaf
Description:
A freshwater fish originally native to the Near Eastern island of Thavnair. How they ultimately ended up in the upper Thaliak River remains an enigma.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Ghost Faerie
Description:
An almost entirely transparent shell-less mollusk found solely in the waters of Clearpool.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Red Sky Coral
Description:
A blood red species of coral found growing on the undersides of islands in the Sea of Clouds.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Lovers' Clam
Description:
A tiny pinkish bivalve mollusk found primarily in Weston Waters.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: River Shrimp
Description:
A rare freshwater shrimp that typically makes its home beneath the rocks that produce the rapids near the Hundred Throes.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Cloud Mythril Ingot
Description: An ingot of smelted cloud mythril.

Name: Stormcloud Cotton Cloth
Description: Several yalms of undyed stormcloud cotton cloth wrapped around a short wooden distaff.

Name: Peteinosaur Leather
Description: A large piece of cured peteinosaur skin.

Name: Cloud Mythril Ore
Description: Extended exposure to the extreme aetherial currents found on and near the Diadem have somehow altered the mythril contained in this piece of rock.

Name: Stormcloud Cotton Boll
Description: Extended exposure to the extreme aetherial currents found on and near the Diadem have somehow altered the fibers of this otherwise ordinary cloud cotton.

Name: Zurvanite Carapace Fragment
Description: A blazing fragment retrieved from the protective armor of Zurvan, the Demon.

Name: Void Matter
Description: Little is known about this deceptively heavy substance save that its origins lie not in this world.

Name: Flannel
Description: Sturdy cloth woven with two varieties of threadwool and cotton.

Name: Stuffed Sabotender
Description: Because who hasn't dreamed of hugging a cactus?

Name: Honey Bun
Description:
Most often found in markets located across the eastern and southern regions of Eorzea, this lightly glazed buttery brioche pastry will keep for several days (making it a fine companion for long journeys), but is best when freshly baked. Guaranteed to make life sweeter.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Bishopfish
Description:
An archbishop among priestfish, and lord of the waters of Clearpool.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Captain Nemo
Description:
A king among ammonites, and lord of the waters of Banepool.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Paikiller
Description:
A king among catkillers, and lord of the waters of the Eddies.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 4 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Ceti
Description:
A king among oliphant's trunks, and lord of the skies near the Hyperstellar Downconverter.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Crystal Pigeon
Description:
A king among stupendemys, and lord of the skies near the Habisphere.

[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Thunderscale
Description:
A king among amber salamanders, and lord of the waters of the Iron Feast.

[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Riddle
Description:
A king among magma lice, and lord of the magma flows in Anyx Old.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: The Lord of Lords
Description:
A king among lavalords, and unquestioned ruler of the magma flows near Halo.

[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: The Speaker
Description:
A king among armored catfish, and lord of the waters of the upper Thaliak River.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Thousand Fin
Description:
A king among hundred fins, and lord of the pools of Weston Waters.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Bloodchaser
Description:
A king among storm chasers, and lord of the skies near Tharl Oom Khash.

[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Problematicus
Description:
A colossal magma-dwelling fish and legend of the lava pools near Halo.

[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Opabinia
Description:
A rarely seen Allagan abomination rumored to dwell in the aetherochemical pools collecting on the Flagship in Azys Lla.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Armor Fish
Description:
A massive glowing freshwater fish found living in the Thaliak River.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 1 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Sea Butterfly
Description:
Though oft referred to as king of the skies near Mok Oogl Island, to claim this floating mollusk is elusive would be a gross understatement.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Charibenet
Description:
Lord of the waters of Clearpool, Charibenet is (was) one of the largest, most voracious ice faeries to ever be captured.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Raimdellopterus
Description:
The moogles of Moghome say that one can live his entire life without ever witnessing a raimdellopterus descend from the upper reaches of Tharl Oom Khash. They also say that some moogles spend a lot of their lives sleeping.

[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Peteinosaur
Description: A winged scalekin recently discovered in the skies near the Diadem.

Name: Mhachi Shilling
Description: A small coin of low denomination once used in the long-fallen nation of Mhach. There are twelve Mhachi pennies in a shilling. Once actively sought by numismatists across Eorzea, the market soon became oversaturated, causing this ancient currency to lose its value entirely.

Name: Fists of the Fiend
Description: Weapon appearance may take precedence over the display of hand gear.

Description: Currency paid to Disciples of the Hand by Rowena's House of Splendors in exchange for services rendered. Can be used to purchase items from the aforementioned establishment. Not valid anywhere else on Hydaelyn.

Description: Currency paid to Disciples of the Land by Rowena's House of Splendors in exchange for services rendered. Can be used to purchase items from the aforementioned establishment. Not valid anywhere else on Hydaelyn.

Name: Timeworn Gaganaskin Map
Description:
This bottle holds a timeworn map classified as risk-reward grade 9 among treasure hunters.

Use the action Decipher to extract the map and examine its contents.
Level 70 recommended.

Name: Timeworn Gazelleskin Map
Description:
This bottle holds a timeworn map classified as risk-reward grade 10 among treasure hunters.

Use the action Decipher to extract the map and examine its contents.
Level 70 full party (eight players) recommended.

Name: Grade 7 Dark Matter
Description:
It has recently been discovered that this substance of unknown origin has the faculty to assimilate with other forms of matter, effectively restoring them to their original condition. This specific grade of dark matter has been shown to bond best with precisely crafted items made from high-quality materials.

[Used to repair equipment for levels 1-80.]

Description: This esoteric tomethe fifth in an equally esoteric seriescontains advanced leatherworking recipes that can only be learned by esoterically skilled leatherworkers.

Name: Master Weaver V
Description: This esoteric tomethe fifth in an equally esoteric seriescontains advanced clothcraft recipes that can only be learned by esoterically skilled weavers.

Name: Master Alchemist V
Description: This esoteric tomethe fifth in an equally esoteric seriescontains advanced alchemy recipes that can only be learned by esoterically skilled alchemists.

Name: Master Culinarian V
Description: This esoteric tomethe fifth in an equally esoteric seriescontains advanced cooking recipes that can only be learned by esoterically skilled culinarians.

Name: Dressing Case Materials
Description: All the materials necessary to construct an oriental dressing case. (Crystals not included.)

Name: Lavish Dressing Case
Description: A dressing case of oriental design, featuring a large mirror of polished metal and countless compartments for jewelry and sundry maquillage.

Name: Pipe Box Materials
Description: All the materials necessary to construct an oriental pipe box. (Crystals not included.)

Name: Stylish Pipe Box
Description: A pipe box of oriental design, complete with an ashtray and compartments for several varieties of tobacco.

Name: Partition Materials
Description: All the materials necessary to construct an authentic Doman partition. (Crystals not included.)

Name: Ornate Partition
Description: An exquisitely crafted partition of traditional Doman design.

Name: Teahouse Bench Materials
Description: All the materials necessary to construct a folding bench traditionally used in the Far East. (Crystals not included.)

Name: Teahouse Bench
Description: A folding bench commonly found in Far Eastern teahouses, complete with a paper parasol to shield tea-drinkers from the elements.

Name: Shortsword Materials
Description: All the materials necessary to forge a shortsword. (Crystals not included.)

Name: Featherlight Shortsword
Description: A sword so lightweight, even the elder steward Fremondain can wield it with relative ease.

Name: Rusted Iron Scrap
Description: Pieces of iron so rusted it is difficult to discern their former use. (Crystals not included.)

Name: Heavy Uchigatana
Description: A katana forged to be, above all else, durable.

Name: Guild-forged Ingot
Description: An ingot forged in the hell-hot furnaces of Limsa Lominsa's Blacksmiths' Guild. (Crystals not included.)

Name: Custom-made Hammer
Description: A remarkably small hammer intended for use on projects requiring extreme delicacy.

Name: Uchigatana Materials
Description: All the materials necessary to forge a proper uchigatana. (Crystals not included.)

Name: Examination Uchigatana
Description: A katana forged as your final test, and to be delivered to a prominent noble house.

Name: Paladin Mail Materials
Description: All the materials necessary to forge a suit of paladin mail. (Crystals not included.)

Name: Paladin Mail
Description: A titanium-alloy breastplate fit for a paladin.

Name: Kote Materials
Description: All the materials necessary to forge a pair of Far Eastern gauntlets known as kote. (Crystals not included.)

Name: Titanium Kote
Description: Lightweight gauntlets of Far Eastern design, forged with titanium for added durability.

Name: Somen Materials
Description: All the materials necessary to forge a Far Eastern helm known as a somen. (Crystals not included.)

Name: Tournament Somen
Description: Lightweight headgear of Far Eastern design. For use in Hingan tournaments known as gozen-jiai.

Name: Hara-ate Materials
Description: All the materials necessary to forge a Far Eastern breastplate known as a hara-ate. (Crystals not included.)

Name: Lominsan Hara-ate
Description: A breastplate that combines Hingan design with Lominsan craftsmanship, bringing east and west together at last.

Name: Ring Materials
Description: All the materials necessary to forge a silver ring. (Crystals not included.)

Name: Sample Silver Ring
Description: A silver ring set with a single brilliant lapis lazuli recovered from the crown of Nanamo Ul Namo's mother.

Name: Eyewear Materials
Description: All the materials necessary to craft a pair of spectacles. (Crystals not included.)

Name: Precision Spectacles
Description: A pair of corrective glasses crafted to accommodate for J'khebica's failing eyesight.

Name: Chronometer Materials
Description: All the materials necessary to craft a desktop chronometer. (Crystals not included.)

Name: Sample Chronometer
Description: A small desktop chronometer to be employed in the training of apprentices.

Name: Orchestrion Materials
Description: All the materials necessary to craft a fully operational orchestrion. (Crystals not included.)

Name: Tribute Orchestrion
Description: An elegant and compact orchestrion custom-made by the Crown Gemworks as a tribute for the sultana.

Name: Hengr Dhalmel Hide
Description: The smooth hide of a towering dhalmel found only in Hengr's Crucible. (Crystals not included.)

Name: Large Dhalmel Cape
Description: A dhalmel hide expertly trimmed and prepared for stuffing.

Name: Velodyna Grizzly Bear Hide
Description: The bristly hide of a ferocious Velodyna grizzly bear. The countless holes attest to difficulty in bringing down the beast. (Crystals not included.)

Name: Grizzly Bear Gloves
Description: A thick pair of protective gloves crafted from the tanned hide of a grizzly bear.

Name: Jacket Materials
Description: All the materials necessary to craft a stylish dhalmelskin jacket. (Crystals not included.)

Name: Dashing Dhalmelskin Jacket
Description: Sophisticated outerwear for the discerning gentleman or woman.

Name: Large Gagana Skin
Description: The luxurious skin of an exotic gagana. (Crystals not included.)

Name: Large Gagana Cape
Description: A gagana hide expertly trimmed and prepared for stuffing.

Name: Bustle Materials
Description: All the materials necessary to sew an Ishgardian bustle dress. (Crystals not included.)

Name: Elegant Bustle
Description: A bustle dress of Ishgardian design, featuring extra hoops and springs to prevent unsightly sagging.

Name: Spring Dress Materials
Description: All the materials necessary to sew a spring dress. (Crystals not included.)

Name: Winsome Spring Dress
Description: A beautiful dress crafted with only the finest materials.

Name: Bustier Materials
Description: All the materials necessary to sew a figure-enhancing bustier. (Crystals not included.)

Name: Seductive Bustier
Description: A bustier of Thavnairian design, cut low to distract potential business clients, thus providing the upper hand in negotiations.

Name: Hagoromo Materials
Description: All the materials necessary to sew a Far Eastern robe known as a hagoromo. (Crystals not included.)

Name: Tennyo Hagoromo
Description: A billowy kimono of Far Eastern design named for angelic beings from Hingan folklore.

Name: Electuary Ingredients
Description: All the ingredients necessary to brew a potent performance-enhancing tonic. (Crystals not included.)

Name: Intellectuary
Description: A sweetened tonic believed to improve cognition.

Name: Juice Ingredients
Description: All the ingredients necessary to brew a mean beverage. (Crystals not included.)

Name: Twice-fermented Mun-Tuy Juice
Description: Fermenting Mun-Tuy extract twice greatly lessens the beans' natural bitterness, resulting in a smoother aftertaste. Side effects of the beverage include a decided loosening of the tongue.

Name: Luminol Ingredients
Description: All the ingredients necessary to concoct a batch of blood-detecting luminol. (Crystals not included.)

Name: Luminol
Description: When applied to an object that has recently been in contact with blood, this alchemical admixture will change color.

Name: Dissolvent Ingredients
Description: All the ingredients necessary to concoct a batch of highly acidic dissolvent. (Crystals not included.)

Name: Potent Dissolvent
Description: Dissolvent so potent it will eat through almost anything.

Name: Rice Ball Ingredients
Description: All the ingredients necessary to cook a rice ballthe Far Eastern treat. (Crystals not included.)

Name: Doman Rice Balls
Description: Simple triangular balls of steamed sticky rice sprinkled with naught but a pinch of sea salt so that one might appreciate the subtle flavors of the original ingredients.

Name: Broth Ingredients
Description: All the ingredients necessary to brew a simple fish stockone of the pillars of Far Eastern cuisine. (Crystals not included.)

Name: Doman Udon Broth
Description: Golden savory stock taken by boiling flakes of a dried bonito. Used in many varieties of Far Eastern cuisine, including the noodle dish, udon.

Name: Sushi Ingredients
Description: All the ingredients necessary to create the traditional Far Eastern specialtysushi. (Crystals not included.)

Name: Nigiri-zushi
Description: One of many types of sushi, nigiri-zushi is called such because chefs use their hands to grip (nigiri) and form small balls of vinegared rice onto which are placed various items such as vegetables or fish.

Name: Sukiyaki Ingredients
Description: All the ingredients necessary to create the (supposedly) traditional Far Eastern specialtysukiyaki. (Crystals not included.)

Name: Doman Sukiyaki
Description: Originally introduced to Doma by Ala Mhigan merchants, sukiyaki is a popular dish that consists of thinly sliced meat and vegetables cooked in sweet and savory soy-based sauce.

Name: Beggar's Mythril Ore
Description:
Lower aetherial conductivity than regular mythril makes this a poor substitute for the precious green metal...unless low aetherial conductivity is what you require.

Not included in the gathering log.

Name: Feather Iron Ore
Description:
Not technically as light as an actual feather, this rare variety of iron weighs slightly less than normal iron, making it a preferable alternative...if enough can be procured.

Not included in the gathering log.

Name: Serpentine
Description:
This rare mineral, also known as lizardite, is still believed in some regions to be the lithified remains of a great scalekin.

Not included in the gathering log.

Name: Pummelite
Description:
This oddly named ore was dubbed such by early Gyr Abanian settlers who believed the chunks of colorful mineral to be pieces of a larger rock shattered by a single blow of the Destroyer's fist.

Not included in the gathering log.

Name: Wild Popoto
Description:
Allowed to grow unchecked in the wild, it only took a matter of generations for this transplant from the New World to become decidedly different than its farm-grown cousins.

Not included in the gathering log.

Name: Walker's Popoto
Description:
A variety of popoto bred by a botanist named Walker to withstand the harsh winds and rocky soil of southern La Noscea.

Not included in the gathering log.

Name: Nanoriso
Description:
This light brown seaweed with spiked leaves is quite common in the seas off Hingashi, and collected and dried for use in cuisine.

Not included in the gathering log.

Name: Rhalgr's Streak
Description:
Also known as Rhalgr's staff, this long-leafed medicinal herb is native to the highlands of Gyr Abania.

Not included in the gathering log.

Name: Deep Velodyna Carp
Description:
This variety of Velodyna carp is not named for the deep river pools in which it hides from predators, but the dark coloring of its skin.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Harutsuge Sprag
Description:
A newly hatched fry of the brilliantly red harutsuge.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Dafangshi
Description:
Rumored to be immortal by local villagers, this freshwater fish native to Yanxia is easily discernable by its countless facial whiskers.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Giant Plesiosaur
Description:
Few scholars will disagree that this enormous scalekin sits atop the oceanic food chain.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Carbuncle Bed
Description: This quaint pallet will never betray you a good night's sleep.

Name: Table Orchestrion
Description:
All the music from your world, all in the palm of your...table.

One orchestrion of any type per estate only.

Name: Mounted Flower Vase
Description:
Is your table cluttered with ashtrays, deathmouse pelts, or forbidden tomes, leaving little to no room to display those beautiful begonias? This wall-adorning vase would like a word with you.

Select flowers can be displayed within.

Name: Stuffed Dhalmel
Description: One of the tallest beastkin known on Eorzea, the dhalmel is almost as majestic in your living room as it is in the wild. Almost.

Name: Stuffed Gagana
Description: A majestic gagana, gutted, tanned, and stuffed, so as not to wrinkle the noses of your houseguests.

Name: Oriental Pipe Box
Description: A pipe box of Far Eastern design, complete with an ashtray and compartments for several varieties of tobacco.

Name: Oriental Dressing Case
Description: A dressing case of Far Eastern design, featuring a large mirror of polished metal and countless compartments for jewelry and sundry maquillage.

Name: Doman Partition
Description: A partition of traditional Doman design for use in both homes and places of business.

Name: Lakshmi Miniature
Description:
A statuette depicting the Lady of Bliss, Lakshmi. (Qalyana chieftainess unsurprisingly missing.)

One per estate only.

Name: Susano Miniature
Description:
A statuette depicting the Lord of the Revel, Susano. (Legendary blade Ame-no-Murakumo included. Second O missing, and nowhere to be found.)

One per estate only.

Name: Season Five Lone Wolf Trophy
Description: A trophy awarded to those who left their mark in Season Five of the Feast.

Name: Stuffed Edda
Description: Go ahead. Try and convince yourself that the reason this stuffed doll weighs considerably more than similar toys is because her heart is full to bursting with love.

Name: Rising Balloon
Description: The bladder of some poor beast, colored with dye and filled with lighter-than-air gas to dazzle the young and the young at heart come the Rising.

Name: Oriental Sushi Lunch
Description:
An exotic Far Eastern dish of sweet, vinegared rice, raw fish, and marine flora prepared to stimulate not only the tongue, but the eyes.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Critical Hit Bonus: +4% (Max 35)
  VIT Bonus: +4% (Max 36)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Oriental Soba Lunch
Description:
An exotic Far Eastern dish of earthy buckwheat noodles eaten by dipping them into a chilled broth of soy sauce and fish stock.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Skill Speed Bonus: +4% (Max 35)
  VIT Bonus: +4% (Max 36)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Oriental Udon Lunch
Description:
An exotic Far Eastern dish of thick flour noodles swimming in a hot broth of soy sauce and fish stock.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Spell Speed Bonus: +4% (Max 34)
  VIT Bonus: +4% (Max 36)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Oriental Rice Ball Lunch
Description:
A simple Far Eastern dish consisting of hand-shaped balls of lightly salted rice wrapped in dried seaweed.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Determination Bonus: +4% (Max 35)
  VIT Bonus: +4% (Max 36)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Easel
Description: A three-legged wooden frame upon which a painting may be placed to cozen your kith and kin into believing you were responsible for the masterpiece.

Name: Elixir Bottle
Description: An empty glass receptacle that dreams of being full once more.

Name: Zabuton Cushion
Description: A thin square pillow common in Hingashi where denizens of the Far Eastern nation prefer to sit upon the floor than employ chairs.

Name: White Half Partition
Description: An unadorned partition, reaching only less than halfway to the ceiling so as to provide privacy without making the room feel smaller.

Name: Moonfire Faire MMXIV Advertisement
Description: A faithful depiction of summer's hottest festival so that you may feel the heat year-round.

Name: Evercold Shaved Ice
Description:
Thinly shaved ice, generously heaped into an oversmall bowl and drizzled with sweet-yet-tangy rolanberry syrup. Why it never melts is a question best served cold.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  VIT Bonus: +4% (Max 11)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +1
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Unmoving Maneki Moogle
Description: This charming knickknack is designed after the maneki neko, a Far Eastern cat fetish whose uplifted paw is believed to beckon fortune to its owner's establishment.

Name: Matanga Lamp
Description: Much like the maneki neko (or moogle, for that matter), the Matanga lamp is also believed to bring fortune to any and all who might place them inside their homes.

Name: Stuffed Khloe
Description: A tiny rendition of the already tiny Khloe Aliapoh, seeker of a thousand tales.

Name: Stuffed Fox
Description: In the Far East, foxes are believed to be the most cunning of thieves. And once you find your heart missing, you will be a believer, too.

Name: Ixion Trophy
Description:
A slightly suggestive objet d'art that will ever remind you of your dominance over the mythic steed.

One per estate only.

Name: Eastern Pine
Description: A surprisingly old pine tree, meticulously trimmed for years by trained botanists to remain relatively small, yet maintain the air of a lofty sentinel.

Name: Eastern Teahouse Bench
Description: A wooden folding bench and accompanying papercraft umbrella similar to those found at Hingan teahouses.

Name: Topiary Carbuncle
Description: A specially bred shrub pruned to the shape of a curious Carbuncle.

Name: Moai Statue
Description: A giant stone head carved to resemble drawings found in an unknown sailor's diary that one day washed up on the eastern shores of Othard.

Name: Dataqi Standard
Description: A brightly dyed banner bearing the ancestral mark of the Dataq tribe.

Name: Gyr Abanian Striking Dummy
Description:
A striking dummy designed in the Gyr Abanian fashion.

Up to three dummies may be placed in a single estate, regardless of type.

Name: Topmast Interior Wall
Description: An interior wall designed to complement Topmast apartments.

Name: Lily Hills Interior Wall
Description: An interior wall designed to complement Lily Hills apartments.

Name: Sultana's Breath Interior Wall
Description: An interior wall designed to complement Sultana's Breath apartments.

Name: Topmast Flooring
Description: Floorboards designed to complement Topmast apartments.

Name: Lily Hills Flooring
Description: Floorboards designed to complement Lily Hills apartments.

Name: Sultana's Breath Flooring
Description: Floorboards designed to complement Sultana's Breath apartments.

Name: House Fortemps Chandelier
Description: A faithful replica of the grand chandelier found in Fortemps Manor.

Name: Ruby Sea Tank Trimmings
Description:
An assortment of items used to outfit an aquarium that it might resemble the deadly waters of the Ruby Tide.

[For use in any tier aquarium.]

Name: Daisy Seeds
Description:
Daisy, Daisy. Give me your answer, do. Go half crazy waiting for these godsdamned seeds to bloom.

For use in planters (built for two).

Name: Red Daisies
Description:
A bunch of red daisies, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Blue Daisies
Description:
A bunch of blue daisies, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Yellow Daisies
Description:
A bunch of yellow daisies, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Green Daisies
Description:
A bunch of green daisies, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Orange Daisies
Description:
A bunch of orange daisies, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Purple Daisies
Description:
A bunch of purple daisies, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: White Daisies
Description:
A bunch of white daisies, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Black Daisies
Description:
A bunch of black daisies, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Rainbow Daisies
Description:
A bunch of multicolored daisies, selectively fertilized to achieve a variety of vibrant colors.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Description:
A large, yet severely damaged crystalline manifestation of aetheric energy.

[Can be exchanged for select combat-based varieties of materia VI.]

Name: Cracked Crystal
Description:
A crystalline manifestation of aetheric energy cracked through in several places.

[Can be exchanged for select non-combat-based varieties of materia VI.]

Name: Stygian Ash
Description:
The charred remnants of a malevolent spirit known to possess the bodies of the dead. Detested by the legendary beast Ixion.

Duration: 30s

Name: Lost Allagan Roborant
Description: An alchemical potion concocted by mad scientists a thousand years dead. Some of the realm's more daring blacksmiths have applied the unnaturally viscous substance to a variety of weapons and found that it heightens the attributes of certain martial artifacts of ancient Allagan design. However, advances in crafting technology have rendered it obsolete.

Name: Lost Allagan Twine
Description: An alchemical thread woven by mad scientists a thousand years dead. Some of the realm's more daring weavers have applied the unnaturally pliable substance to a variety of vestments and found that it heightens the attributes of certain martial artifacts of ancient Allagan design. However, advances in crafting technology have rendered it obsolete.

Name: Lost Allagan Glaze
Description: An alchemical potion concocted by mad scientists a thousand years dead. Some of the realm's more daring goldsmiths have applied the unnaturally illuminated substance to a variety of gems and found that it heightens the attributes of certain martial artifacts of ancient Allagan design. However, advances in crafting technology have rendered it obsolete.

Name: Rowena's Token (Creation)
Description: A note of promise received from Rowena for the delivery of Allagan tomestones of creation or poetics. However, due to the House of Splendors changing its policies, it is now worth less than the paper on which it is scribed.

Name: Early Model Tomestone
Description: Though considerably different in construction, Garlond Ironworks engineers insist this bulky contraption serves the same purpose as a traditional tomestone, and is merely of an earlier, less efficient design. This particular variety is not as highly sought as it once was, and may no longer be exchanged for other wares.

Name: Revel Totem
Description: The Kojin carve, from shell, idols such as this one to present as offerings to their exalted Lord of the Revel, Susano.

Name: Bliss Totem
Description: This pulsating metal idol forged in the likeness of the primal Lakshmi is thought to be employed by the Ananta in forbidden summoning ceremonies.

Name: Deltascape Lens
Description:
A uniquely crafted lens discovered in the Deltascape.

Two lenses can be traded for special headgear.

Name: Deltascape Shaft
Description:
A uniquely crafted shaft discovered in the Deltascape.

Four shafts can be traded for special body gear.

Name: Deltascape Crank
Description:
A uniquely crafted crank discovered in the Deltascape.

Two cranks can be traded for special arm gear.

Name: Deltascape Spring
Description:
A uniquely crafted spring discovered in the Deltascape.

Four springs can be traded for special leg gear.

Name: Deltascape Pedal
Description:
A uniquely crafted pedal discovered in the Deltascape.

Two pedals can be traded for special foot gear.

Name: Deltascape Chain
Description: A uniquely crafted chain discovered in the Deltascape. Alas, advancements in trouser technology have rendered it worthless.

Name: Deltascape Bolt
Description:
A uniquely crafted bolt discovered in the Deltascape.

One bolt can be traded for a special accessory.

Name: Deltascape Datalog v1.0
Description:
Detailed records of past battles waged in the Deltascape.

Logs of the same type can be traded for special gear.

Name: Deltascape Crystalloid
Description: A remarkable crystalline fragment within which can be seen images from another world.

Name: Blade of Revelry
Description: The blade from a sword used by the Lord of the Revel himself. Despite being long removed from its hilt, the steel still shudders with unseen magicks.

Name: Blissful Shroud
Description: A long sheet of translucent cloth taken from the robes worn by the Lady of the Bliss. In addition with being unnaturally lightweight, the shroud tingles the skin when touched.
