Carbuncle Cottage Walls
Description:
A set of four walls designed for those whose love of their loyal Carbuncle companions transcends a simple pat on the head or scratch under the chin.

Can only be used with cottages on small plots of land.

Name: Carbuncle House Walls
Description:
A set of four walls designed for those whose love of their loyal Carbuncle companions transcends a simple pat on the head or scratch under the chin.

Can only be used with houses on medium plots of land.

Name: Carbuncle Mansion Walls
Description:
A set of four walls designed for those whose love of their loyal Carbuncle companions transcends a simple pat on the head or scratch under the chin.

Can only be used with mansions on large plots of land.

Name: Timeworn Thief's Map
Description:
A timeworn map revealing the location of a teleportation portal leading to a hidden sluice filled with untold riches.

Level 70 full party (8 players) recommended.
Average item level 370 recommended.

Name: Doman Tea
Description:
An after-supper beverage naturally sweetened with dried persimmons. Widely popular in the Far East.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Loquat Juice
Description:
A thick, orange juice freshly squeezed from ripe loquats.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Buckwheat Tea
Description:
A dark, nutty infusion made from steeping buckwheat kernels in boiling water.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Steppe Tea
Description:
A thick, creamy beverage popular on the Azim Steppe made from steeped fermented tea leaves and a generous helping of dzo milk.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Baklava
Description:
A traditional Near Eastern pastry made of a sweetened paste of chopped nuts and honey sandwiched between layers of thin unleavened dough.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Jellied Compote
Description:
Stewed fruit rendered firm with gelatin, then chilled and cut into bite-sized squares.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Persimmon Pudding
Description:
A rich steamed dessert made with pured persimmons and eggs.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Chirashi-zushi
Description:
One of many varieties of the Hingan dish sushi, this iteration consists of a full bowl of sweet vinegared rice topped with various items such as thinly sliced omelet, salted fish eggs, dried gourd, stewed mushrooms, and other local fare. Commonly eaten at celebratory events.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Persimmon Leaf Sushi
Description:
One of many varieties of the Hingan dish sushi, this iteration consists of sweet vinegared rice topped with fish, pressed into a narrow rectangle, and finally wrapped in green persimmon leaves.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Popoto Soba
Description:
Buckwheat noodles steeped in savory broth and topped with a starchy paste created by grinding a raw mountain popoto.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Shorlog
Description:
Heavily spiced dzo meat charred to perfection over an open flame. Common fare amongst the nomadic steppe tribes.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Pork Kakuni
Description:
Thick slices of succulent Koshu pork slow cooked in a sweet, savory sauce. If prepared properly, the meat literally melts in your mouth.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Jerked Jhammel
Description:
Thin slices of tough jhammel meat salted and dried to preserve for long journeys.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Egg Foo Young
Description:
Succulent crab legs folded into a fluffy omelette and topped with a thick, savory sauce.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Onigara-yaki
Description:
A lobster split in half lengthwise, slathered with a heavily seasoned sauce, and grilled in its shell over an open flame.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Grilled Turban
Description:
A live horned turban cooked in its shell with a splash of soy sauce and rice wine.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Boiled Amberjack Head
Description:
The head of an amberjack boiled in a soy-based sauce with thick-sliced daikon radish.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Steamed Grouper
Description:
A large Zekki grouper steamed whole, then doused in fragrant boiling oil.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Sweet and Sour Frogs' Legs
Description:
Chunks of meaty steppe bullfrog legs, breaded and deep-fried, then tossed in a sweet and tangy vinegar-based glaze with fresh colorful vegetables.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Tempura Platter
Description:
A selection of seafood and vegetables dipped in batter and lightly fried in oil. A Hingan delicacy.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Stewed River Bream
Description:
River bream topped in a sauce made by thickening the broth in which the fish was stewed.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Charred Charr
Description:
Heather charr sprinkled with salt and blackened over an open flame.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Miso Dengaku
Description:
Stiff tofu squares and vegetables impaled on a stick and slathered in a sweet miso sauce then roasted over hot coals.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Jhammel Moussaka
Description:
A Near Eastern casserole made from a spiced jhammel and eggplant mincemeat topped with creamy mashed popotoes.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Gameni
Description:
A hodgepodge of boldly sliced tubers, mushrooms, and hornbill tenders, stewed slowly in a soy-based broth.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Steppe Salad
Description:
A salad of various seasonal tubers tossed lightly in a rice vinegar dressing.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Crab Croquette
Description:
Rich, buttery crab legs blended with fluffy mashed vegetables, rolled into a ball, covered in bread crumbs, and fried to a crispy, golden brown. Best served slathered in a sweet sauce.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Miso Soup with Tofu
Description:
A Far Eastern staple, often eaten multiple times a day, this soup is made by mixing miso paste with light fish stock. Bite-sized cubes of tofu are added near the end of preparation to ensure the pieces retain their shape.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Fish Stew
Description:
A salty broth containing balls of finely ground fish paste. A common dish in Far Eastern coastal settlements.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Pork Stew
Description:
This Far Eastern take on a campsite mainstay features thinly sliced pork belly and various root vegetables in a piping hot miso-based soup.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Warrior's Stew
Description:
A simple stew commonly made of diced dzo chuck and whatever vegetables are readily available. A popular dish amongst the nomadic tribes of the Azim Steppe.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Kasha
Description:
Buckwheat kernels boiled in bouillon to form a soft, hearty porridge.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Nomad Meat Pie
Description:
Ground dzo chuck and various steppe vegetables wrapped in buttery dough and deep-fried in oil.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Tea Brick
Description: The fermenting of tea leaves is common practice in the Far East where tea is consumed multiple times a day. Fermentation is thought to enhance flavor while dulling the leaves' natural bitterness. Fermented leaves are pressed into bricks to save space when shipping.

Name: Gyr Abanian Flour
Description: Finely milled Gyr Abanian wheat.

Name: Firm Tofu
Description: A traditional source of protein in the Far East, tofu is made from curdled soy bean extract.

Name: Rice Vinegar
Description: One of Far Eastern cuisine's five main seasonings, rice vinegar is slightly more sweet and mild than Aldenard's vinegars of popoto or apple.

Name: Beet Sugar
Description: A sweetener made by juicing sugar beets and then boiling the extract down until all the water has evaporated, leaving only a fine, grey powder.

Name: Cooking Sake
Description: Far Eastern rice wine prepared with other ingredients for use in cooking. Often added to seafood dishes to remove unpleasant aromas.

Name: Cottonseed Oil
Description: Cooking oil pressed from ruby cotton seeds. Its high flash point and lack of odor make it ideal for deep-frying.

Name: Nigari
Description: A coagulant naturally found in seawater, commonly used in the Far East to make tofu.

Name: Algae Salt
Description: A briny salt harvested by sun-drying then burning sea algae.

Name: Koshu Sticky Rice
Description: Unlike the drier varieties common in Aldenard and Ilsabard, this particular strand of Far Eastern rice becomes extremely sticky when cooked.

Name: Buckwheat Kernels
Description: A nutty grain that can be substituted for flour in breads and noodles. Found across the Three Great Continents, but grown in abundance in the heart of Gyr Abania.

Name: Loquat
Description:
A sweet yet slightly tangy fruit with a thin skin and a fleshy orange interior. Can be found in the warmer valleys of Gyr Abania.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Othardian Plum
Description:
A greenish pink plum common across the eastern continent of Othard.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Kudzu Root
Description: The root of the quick-growing kudzu vine is dug up and processed into kudzu powder which serves as a substitute for animal-based gelatins in Far Eastern desserts. It also is believed to exhibit healing properties, and can be found in most Hingan and Doman apothecaries.

Name: Doman Eggplant
Description: While just as brilliantly purple, this Far Eastern cousin of the wizard eggplant is noticeably thinner, and thus requires less time to cook.

Name: Daikon Radish
Description: The spicy daikon radishes of Othard are known to grow as long and thick as a grown Hyur's forearm.

Name: Sugar Beet
Description: These tubers can be several times sweeter than most fruit, and as such are commonly processed into sugar for sweetening cakes and other confections.

Name: Jhammel Ginger
Description: Jhammel ginger's bulbous, aromatic roots can be sliced fresh and added to stews and seafood dishes to remove gaminess, ground and steeped in hot water to cure head colds, or dried and ground into a powder to use as a spice for breads and cookies.

Name: Gyr Abanian Carrot
Description: Gyr Abanian carrots are not only longer, but a far deeper orangenay, crimsonthan those grown in central and western Eorzea.

Name: Green Leek
Description: Similar to green onions in flavor, the leeks of Gyr Abania are several times thicker, and far more piquant.

Name: Bamboo Shoot
Description: If removed from the ground when less than a fulm in length, bamboo shoots can be peeled and the fleshy interior eaten. A popular ingredient in Far Eastern stews and stir-fries.

Name: Mountain Popoto
Description: Crisp mountain popotoes contain high quantities of starch that create a viscous paste when the tubers are ground. This paste can be eaten raw, fried into cakes, or added to stews for thickening.

Name: Soybeans
Description: These emerald legumes grow two to three beans per pod on stout bushes that are ready for harvest in the early fall. The beans are most often pressed into the milk which is used to make tofu, or fermented into various savory pastes and sauces.

Name: Shiitake Mushroom
Description: These fungi native to the Far East are rarely eaten raw, the majority of those harvested dried, then used to make soup stock.

Name: Cumin Seeds
Description: A pungent spice that can be used in seed form, or ground into a powder, enhancing the aroma tenfold.

Name: Lotus Root
Description: Though they appear solid from the outside, the cylindrical root nodules of the lotus flower are riddled with holes, possibly to accommodate for the waterlogged environments in which the plant grows.

Name: Sun Cabbage
Description: The sweet, tightly packed leaves of Othardian sun cabbages are deceptively sweet, making them perfect in salads or stews.

Name: Fennel
Description: With an aroma similar to licorice, both the stalks and the seeds of this Othardian herb can be used to enhance the flavor of exotic Far Eastern dishes.

Name: Gyr Abanian Wheat
Description: A close cousin to highland wheat, Gyr Abanian wheat has been improved by Ala Mhigan farmers over generations to increase both flavor and yield.

Name: Persimmon
Description:
A hard, orange fruit common in eastern Othard. It is well known that seven summers must pass before a newly planted persimmon tree will bear fruit.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Persimmon Leaf
Description: While not edible, the leaves of the persimmon tree are oft used in the preservation of other food.

Name: Gyr Abanian Mineral Water
Description: Clear water taken from a mountain spring on the eastern end of Abalathia's Spine.

Name: Crescent Spring Water
Description: Clear, odorless water taken from one of the many springs found on Othard's Fanged Crescent.

Name: Dzo Chuck
Description: The unbearably tough shoulder meat of a steppe dzo.

Name: Hornbill Tenderloin
Description: A lean piece of meat taken from under the short ribs of an Othardian hornbill.

Name: Jhammel Haunch
Description: Heavy salting and spicing are methods commonly employed to remove the oft overpowering gaminess of this beastkin flesh.

Name: Koshu Pork
Description: A dark-haired variety of swine bred on Hingashi's Koshu island. Its carefully selected diet is believed to render its meat tender and its fat flavorful.

Name: Gagana Egg
Description: The massive egg of a gagana.

Name: Steppe Milk
Description:
Compared to that of an aldgoat, marid, or deathmouse, the milk of a steppe dzo is high in fat and flavor.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Ama Nori
Description: This edible seaweed can be consumed raw, or dried into paper-like squares and wrapped around sticky rice.

Name: Ruby Tide Kelp
Description: A distant cousin of malm kelp, Ruby Tide kelp is harvested and dried in the sun to enhance flavor. Squares of the seaweed are cut and steeped in boiling water to create one of the savory broths used in Hingan cuisine.

Name: Gem Algae
Description: A variety of algae found in the Ruby Sea, commonly harvested for its salt.

Name: Competent Craftsman's Tea
Description:
This infusion brewed from the powdered horn of a powerful beastkin is believed to improve crafting efficiency.

Duration: 15m

Name: Commanding Craftsman's Tea
Description:
This infusion brewed from the powdered horn of a powerful beastkin is believed to improve crafting efficiency.

Duration: 15m

Name: Cunning Craftsman's Tea
Description:
This infusion brewed from the powdered horn of a powerful beastkin is believed to improve crafting efficiency.

Duration: 15m

Name: Potent Spiritbond Potion
Description:
This sweet-smelling concoction enhances the rate at which your equipment gains spiritbond.

Duration: 180m

Name: Infusion of Strength
Description:
This diluted brew temporarily increases strength, but for twice the duration of similar potions.

Duration: 30s

Name: Infusion of Dexterity
Description:
This diluted brew temporarily increases dexterity, but for twice the duration of similar potions.

Duration: 30s

Name: Infusion of Vitality
Description:
This diluted brew temporarily increases vitality, but for twice the duration of similar potions.

Duration: 30s

Name: Infusion of Intelligence
Description:
This diluted brew temporarily increases intelligence, but for twice the duration of similar potions.

Duration: 30s

Name: Infusion of Mind
Description:
This diluted brew temporarily increases mind, but for twice the duration of similar potions.

Duration: 30s

Name: Grade 1 Reisui of Strength
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this Far Eastern potation will, similarly to Eorzean dissolvents, dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to strength, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Grade 1 Reisui of Dexterity
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this Far Eastern potation will, similarly to Eorzean dissolvents, dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to dexterity, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Grade 1 Reisui of Vitality
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this Far Eastern potation will, similarly to Eorzean dissolvents, dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to vitality, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Grade 1 Reisui of Intelligence
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this Far Eastern potation will, similarly to Eorzean dissolvents, dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to intelligence, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Grade 1 Reisui of Mind
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this Far Eastern potation will, similarly to Eorzean dissolvents, dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to mind, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Grade 2 Reisui of Strength
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this Far Eastern potation will, similarly to Eorzean dissolvents, dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to strength, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Grade 2 Reisui of Dexterity
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this Far Eastern potation will, similarly to Eorzean dissolvents, dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to dexterity, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Grade 2 Reisui of Vitality
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this Far Eastern potation will, similarly to Eorzean dissolvents, dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to vitality, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Grade 2 Reisui of Intelligence
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this Far Eastern potation will, similarly to Eorzean dissolvents, dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to intelligence, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Grade 2 Reisui of Mind
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this Far Eastern potation will, similarly to Eorzean dissolvents, dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to mind, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Enchanted Koppranickel Ink
Description: Ink fortified with koppranickel sand to improve aetherial conductivity.

Name: Enchanted Durium Ink
Description: Ink fortified with durium sand to improve aetherial conductivity.

Name: Enchanted Palladium Ink
Description: Ink fortified with palladium sand to improve aetherial conductivity.

Name: Growth Formula Eta
Description: This alchemically formulated potation accelerates the growth of foliage.

Name: Growth Formula Theta
Description: This alchemically formulated potation accelerates the growth of foliage.

Name: Beetle Glue
Description: An adhesive substance created by grinding down the chitinous carapaces of beetles and mixing it with heated pine resin.

Name: Ala Mhigan Salt Crystal
Description: These pinkish crystals grow naturally on the shores of Loch Seld.

Name: Pine Resin
Description: A sticky substance secreted by pine trees when their limbs are cut.

Name: Persimmon Tannin
Description: A translucent liquid extracted from persimmon wood by steeping it in hot water. Used in the tanning of raw animal hides.

Name: Gyr Abanian Alumen
Description: A brownish variety of the mineral used by leatherworkers to tan animal hides. It is only found in the mountains of Eastern Aldenard.

Name: Yanxian Parsley
Description: This Far Eastern perennial has a biting aroma that even many Othardians find off-putting.

Name: Alyssum
Description: This annual is coveted by perfumers for its honey-sweet aroma.

Name: Nagxian Cudweed
Description: Though recognized as a weed, this winter annual is edible and will oft be harvested in the late months for use in various Doman and Hingan dishes.

Name: Chickweed
Description: Though recognized as a weed, this winter annual is edible and will oft be harvested in the late months for use in various Doman and Hingan dishes.

Name: Nipplewort
Description: Named for the protruding buds from which its bright-yellow flowers bloom, nipplewort is a common winter annual whose leaves are gathered for use in Othardian cuisine.

Name: Windtea Leaves
Description: When steeped in boiling water, the leaves of this rare perennial change color, turning a bright bluish green.

Name: Holy Basil
Description: A herb with an aroma so heavenly, it will cleanse both your soul and your palate of ill flavors (or so say merchants who would see you buy their stock).

Name: Hallowed Basil
Description: A herb with an aroma so heavenly, the gods themselves must have blessed it (or so say merchants who would see you buy their stock).

Name: Muud Suud Horn
Description: The curved horn of a muud suud.

Name: Gazelle Horn
Description: The twisted horn of a gazelle.

Name: Dzo Horn
Description: The massive ebon horn of a steppe dzo.

Name: Moth Scales
Description: The powdery scales of a giant moth's wing.

Name: Bombfish Spine
Description: A single adult bombfish can have as many as a thousand of these lightweight-yet-sturdy spines jutting from its body.

Name: Rhino Beetle Carapace
Description: The thick chitinous head of a rhino beetle, complete with eyes, antennae, and mandibles.

Name: Beech Lumber
Description: Processed beech lumber.

Name: Larch Lumber
Description: Processed larch lumber.

Name: Persimmon Lumber
Description: Processed persimmon lumber.

Name: Zelkova Lumber
Description: Processed zelkova lumber.

Name: Torreya Lumber
Description: Processed torreya lumber.

Name: Beech Log
Description: A rough-cut log of beech timber.

Name: Larch Log
Description: A rough-cut log of larch timber.

Name: Persimmon Log
Description: A rough-cut log of persimmon timber.

Name: Zelkova Log
Description: A rough-cut log of zelkova timber.

Name: Torreya Log
Description: A rough-cut log of torreya timber.

Name: Scarlet Urushi
Description: This glossy red coating, made from the sap of the lacquer tree, is used to both color and preserve wooden crafts.

Name: Beech Branch
Description: The thick branch of a beech tree.

Name: Torreya Branch
Description: The thick branch of a torreya tree.

Name: Koppranickel Nugget
Description: A small nugget of impure koppranickel.

Name: High Steel Nugget
Description: A small nugget of impure high steel.

Name: Koppranickel Ingot
Description: An ingot of smelted koppranickel.

Name: High Steel Ingot
Description: An ingot of smelted high steel.

Name: Durium Nugget
Description: A small nugget of impure durium.

Name: Oroshigane Ingot
Description: An ingot of Doman iron, smelted using Far Eastern techniques.

Name: Durium Ingot
Description: An ingot of smelted durium.

Name: Tama-hagane Ingot
Description: An ingot of Doman steel, smelted using Far Eastern techniques.

Name: Palladium Nugget
Description: A small nugget of impure palladium.

Name: Molybdenum Ingot
Description: An ingot of smelted molybdenum.

Name: Palladium Ingot
Description: An ingot of smelted palladium.

Name: Chromite Ingot
Description: An ingot of smelted chromite.

Name: Koppranickel Sand
Description: Amber-colored sand consisting of tiny grains of koppranickel.

Name: Koppranickel Ore
Description: A decent-sized piece of rock containing the metal koppranickel.

Name: Durium Sand
Description: Jade-colored sand consisting of tiny grains of durium.

Name: Doman Iron Ore
Description: A decent-sized piece of rock containing the metal Doman iron (also known as mochi iron for its resemblance to the Far Eastern rice cakes).

Name: Durium Ore
Description: A decent-sized piece of rock containing the metal durium.

Name: Doman Iron Sand
Description: Metallic sand consisting of tiny grains of Doman iron.

Name: Palladium Sand
Description: Silver-colored sand consisting of tiny grains of palladium.

Name: Molybdenum Ore
Description: A decent-sized piece of rock containing the metal molybdenum.

Name: Palladium Ore
Description: A decent-sized piece of rock containing the metal palladium.

Name: Chromite Ore
Description: A decent-sized piece of rock containing the metal chromium.

Name: Domacoat
Description: Not to be outdone by their Near Eastern counterparts who perfected the aurum regis-hardening agent, Raziqcoat, several Far Eastern alchemists have joined together to create Domacoata substance capable of hardening palladium.

Name: Bone Charcoal
Description: Not actually created from bones, this hot-burning fuel is the result of baking coal in an airless furnace at an extremely high temperature.

Name: Triphane
Description: A yellow jewel.

Name: Kyanite
Description: A light-blue jewel.

Name: Star Spinel
Description: A violet jewel.

Name: Azurite
Description: A deep blue jewel.

Name: Imperial Jade
Description: Also known as true jade, this milky green stone is coveted by the Far Eastern elite.

Name: Rhodonite
Description: A blood red jewel.

Name: Raw Triphane
Description: An uncut, unpolished stone containing what appears to be triphane.

Name: Raw Kyanite
Description: An uncut, unpolished stone containing what appears to be kyanite.

Name: Raw Star Spinel
Description: An uncut, unpolished stone containing what appears to be star spinel.

Name: Raw Azurite
Description: An uncut, unpolished stone containing what appears to be azurite.

Name: Raw Imperial Jade
Description: An uncut, unpolished stone containing what appears to be imperial jade.

Name: Raw Rhodonite
Description: An uncut, unpolished stone containing what appears to be rhodonite.

Name: Bloodhempen Cloth
Description: Several yalms of undyed, bright-red bloodhempen cloth wrapped around a short wooden distaff.

Name: Bloodhempen Yarn
Description: Coarse yarn spun from bloodhemp fiber.

Name: Bloodhemp
Description: A common grass found growing throughout Othard. From its stalks, bloodhempen yarn is created.

Name: Ruby Cotton Cloth
Description: Several yalms of undyed ruby cotton cloth wrapped around a short wooden distaff.

Name: Ruby Cotton Yarn
Description: Light yarn spun from ruby cotton.

Name: Ruby Cotton Boll
Description: The fibrous flower of a rare cotton plant that only grows under the Ruby Sea. As such, Eorzean scholars insist that the flora is in no way related to normal cotton, and is instead a unique variety of sea kelp.

Name: Kudzu Cloth
Description: Several yalms of undyed kudzu cloth wrapped around a short wooden distaff.

Name: Kudzu Thread
Description: Thick, fibrous yarn spun from kudzu vines.

Name: Kudzu Vine
Description: If allowed to grow unchecked, a single kudzu plant can cover an acre of forest in less than a single summer, blocking the sun from the plants it envelops. A large swath of the outer Black Shroud currently finds itself being slowly suffocated by the invasive weed.

Name: Steppe Serge
Description: Several yalms of undyed steppe serge wrapped around a short wooden distaff.

Name: Worsted Yarn
Description: Soft, water-absorbent yarn spun from multiple varieties of hair sheared from beastkin of the Azim Steppe.

Name: Halgai Mane
Description: The regal mane of a halgai.

Name: Manzasiri Hair
Description: The long brown hair of a steppe manzasiri.

Name: Twinsilk
Description: Though exhibiting a similar luster as normal silk, twinsilk is far more durable and resistant to discoloring.

Name: Twinthread
Description: A thin lustrous thread woven from countless silken strands pulled from a rare highland twincoon.

Name: Twincoon
Description: A massive cocoon spun by not one, but multiple highland erucas.

Name: Rhea Cloth
Description: Cloth woven from the plant rhea. Due to the complexity of the spinning process, there are very few clothcrafters in the world who can produce this weave, making it extremely rare. Most known samples are in the possession of Far Eastern royalty.

Name: Rhea
Description: A variety of ramie better suited to the climes of Far Eastern Othard.

Name: Doman Weave
Description: Hempen cloth woven using age-old methods passed down for countless generations by Doman clothiers.

Name: Gagana Leather
Description: A large piece of cured gagana skin.

Name: Gyuki Leather
Description: A large piece of cured gyuki hide.

Name: Tiger Leather
Description: A large piece of cured tiger skin.

Name: Marid Leather
Description: A large piece of cured marid hide.

Name: Gazelle Leather
Description: A large piece of cured gazelle hide.

Name: True Griffin Leather
Description: A large piece of cured true griffin hide.

Name: Gagana Skin
Description: The rough skin of a majestic gagana.

Name: Gyuki Hide
Description: The smooth hide of a devilish gyuki.

Name: Tiger Skin
Description: The striped skin of a ferocious tiger.

Name: Marid Hide
Description: The thick hide of a mammoth marid.

Name: Gazelle Hide
Description: The bristly hide of a steppe gazelle.

Name: True Griffin Hide
Description: The downy hide of a true griffin.

Name: Forbidden Wax
Description: Forbidden in many markets for the nefarious means with which it is extracted, this wax is cherished by leatherworkers for the luster it brings to tanned hides when applied.

Name: Diatomite
Description: Geological scholars claim that this sedimentary stone is actually comprised of the shells of thousands upon thousands of tiny sea creatures.

Name: Slate
Description: Unlike other sedimentary stone, slate has been compressed under the weight of mountains for so long that it is surprisingly hard, making it ideal for whetstones and grinding stones.

Name: Slate Whetstone
Description: A whetstone carved from slate. Used for sharpening metal or stone blades.

Name: Schorl
Description: A blackish mineral possibly containing trace amounts of the precious stone tourmaline.

Name: Perlite
Description: A strange, pearlescent volcanic rock that expands tenfold upon heating in a kiln or forge.

Name: Almandine
Description: A garnet-like mineral that, due to its extreme hardness, is used in grinding wheels.

Name: Doman Yellow
Description: A soft, clay-like soil believed to be formed of compacted yellow dust carried on the wind from faraway lands.

Name: Dusklight Aethersand
Description: The elementally aspected remnants of aetherially reduced matter. This fine sand emits a weak glow indiscernible at gloaming.

Name: Dawnlight Aethersand
Description: The elementally aspected remnants of aetherially reduced matter. This fine sand emits a weak glow indiscernible at dawn.

Name: Everbright Aethersand
Description: The elementally aspected remnants of highly concentrated aetherially reduced mineral matter.

Name: Everborn Aethersand
Description: The elementally aspected remnants of highly concentrated aetherially reduced mineral matter.

Name: Everdeep Aethersand
Description: The elementally aspected remnants of highly concentrated aetherially reduced mineral matter.

Name: Liopleurodon
Description:
Though king of the five seas and beyond, scholars classify the liopleurodon with scalekin rather than wavekin.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 4 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Ala Mhigan Ribbon
Description:
A freshwater fish named for its long, ribbon-like fins that it uses to both attract prey and distract predators.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Yanxian Barramundi
Description:
This large carnivorous specimen is native to the southeastern reaches of the One River where the waters run slow and deep.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Seraphim
Description:
The beauty of this small freshwater fish native to Yanxia is oft compared to the angels of ancient eastern scripture.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 1 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Blackfin Snake Eel
Description:
Like most saltwater eels, the blackfin snake eel of the Ruby Sea is a nocturnal hunter.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Tail Mountains Minnow
Description:
These tiny fish commonly found in the many shallow tributaries feeding into the upper One River rarely grow beyond a few ilms in length.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Sweatfish
Description:
Despite their small size, sweatfish prefer the swift rapids of the One River's northern tributaries for the cover it provides them from predators.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Rock Saltfish
Description:
By no means the most winsome of wavekin, the rock saltfish has adapted to survival in the saline waters of Loch Seld.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Comet Minnow
Description:
Near the bottom of the food chain, swift-swimming comet minnows serve as food for many of the larger fish that swim the waters of the Hathoeva and Velodyna rivers.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Doman Grass Carp
Description:
This common variety of freshwater carp is found up and down the One River.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Samurai Fish
Description:
Named after the Hingan warriors whose grace and elegance in battle resemble the means by which this wavekin swims the turbid depths of the One River.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Golden Cichlid
Description:
This bright-yellow fish is native to Gyr Abania and found in both the Hathoeva and Velodyna rivers, sometimes as far west as East End.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Hak Bitterling
Description:
A small-yet-plump fish most commonly found in Hak Khaal, one of the One River's many narrow steppe tributaries.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Yat Goby
Description:
The Yat goby is an eel-like bottom dweller named after the Azim Steppe tributary in which it is most commonly found.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Ruby Meagre
Description:
Similar to a bass in appearance and flavor, the similarities end there, with this variety of meagre preferring the coastal waters of the Ruby Sea and the Glass Ocean to fresher rivers and lakes.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Greenstream Loach
Description:
This distant relative to the carp can be found hunting the waters of the Hathoeva and Velodyna rivers.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Tawny Wench Shark
Description:
Some say this Ruby Sea shark earned its name from sailors long out of port who, upon seeing the shark's pale skin cresting above the waves, would reminisce of their favorite pleasure boat courtesan.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Whitehorse
Description:
This queer horse-like wavekin swims upright, using two tiny fins near its head to slowly swim through the waters of extreme salinity it calls home.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Killifish
Description:
This freshwater specimen of minuscule proportions can be found in almost any river and lake from central to eastern Othard.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Coeurl Snake Eel
Description:
Scholars are divided as to whether this wavekin native to the Ruby Sea and Glass Ocean is in fact a snake or an eel.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Zekki Grouper
Description:
Groupers gather in swift currents of the Ruby Sea and the Rasen Kaikyo to feed on the abundant life drawn to the area.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Saltshield Snapper
Description:
This violent scalekin has the jaws of a carpenter's vise. Many a careless fisher has lost a fingertip or three when navigating the snapper-rich waters of Loch Seld.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Sculptor
Description:
Remarkably similar in appearance to a shark, it is believed this salt lake fish periodically exposes its dorsal fin above the water's surface to frighten land predators such as bears.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Pearl-eye
Description:
Prehistoric drawings of this salt lake fish have been discovered on cave walls throughout Gyr Abania, suggesting that this particular species has endured at least six umbral eras.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Abalathian Bitterling
Description:
The Abalathian bitterling's ivory white skin easily distinguishes it from its silver cousins also found in the freshwater rivers and lakes of Gyr Abania.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Steelshark
Description:
One of only a few freshwater sharks discovered in Eorzea, the steelshark can primarily be found in the rivers and lakes of Gyr Abania.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Tao Bitterling
Description:
Though a cousin to the Hak bitterling, the waters of Tao Khaal have taken the Tao bitterling on a slightly different evolutionary path.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Idle Goby
Description:
This large goby uses its natural black and brown mottling to conceal itself in the sandy bed of the Slow Wash.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: River Barramundi
Description:
Called akame or red eye in the Far East for the unique color of this freshwater fish's optical organs.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Mirage Chub
Description:
This freshwater fish is known to change the color of its skin come spawning season.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Harutsuge
Description:
This saltwater fish has a distinct crimson coloring that makes it popular amongst aquarium owners.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 1 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Steelhead Trout
Description:
A delicious, fatty freshwater fish native to the Velodyna and Hathoeva rivers.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Heather Charr
Description:
A unique variety of freshwater charr found only in the waters near Heather Falls.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Silken Koi
Description:
A plump freshwater wavekin with pearlescent scales and a name that sounds better than the fish tastes.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Yellow Prismfish
Description:
The pale yellow glow emitted by this freshwater fish is believed to be caused by unbalanced levels of aspected aether in the wavekin's humours.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Blue Prismfish
Description:
The pale blue glow emitted by this freshwater fish is believed to be caused by unbalanced levels of aspected aether in the wavekin's humours.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Hanatatsu
Description:
Similar to the sea horse, the hanatatsu swims standing, though instead of resembling a beast of burden, this saltwater fish has taken on the appearance of a sprig of coral.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 3 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Broken Crab
Description:
A wildly misnamed freshwater crab with a highly durable carapace.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Gyr Abanian Trout
Description:
This succulent pink-fleshed fish commonly found in the Hathoeva and Velodyna rivers will oft command a high price in local markets.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Bloodsipper
Description:
This freshwater crustacean is widely found in lakes and marshes across the Three Great Continents.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Miounnefish
Description:
This feisty freshwater fish is found throughout the Black Shroud.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Monk Betta
Description:
This freshwater betta is native to the lakes and marshes of eastern Gyr Abania.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Electric Catfish
Description:
This massive whiskered wavekin can be found lurking in the calm, turbid lakes and marshes of eastern Gyr Abania.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Pagan Pirarucu
Description:
Though only ever seen by fishers who spend more time telling tales in taverns than actually fishing, the pagan pirarucu can supposedly be found in the highland lakes and swamps of eastern Gyr Abania.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Temple Carp
Description:
A freshwater fish commonly found in the lakes and marshes dotting the eastern end of Abalathia's Spine.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Gilfish
Description:
The Far Eastern gilfish was first introduced to Eorzea by Othardian merchants hoping their platinum sheen would make them attractive to wealthy nobles. Now the freshwater fish can be found in rivers and lakes across the realm.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Balloon Frog
Description:
A hardy amphibian found in the relatively warm-watered lakes of eastern Abalathia's Spine. The plump legs make for a fine meal.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Lantern Marimo
Description:
A rare type of luminescent moss found in the lightless depths of lakes, as well as in caves. Slight currents cause the moss to form into a ball as it grows.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Death Loach
Description:
This particular variety of loach can be found in the lakes, rivers, and swamps of northern Gyr Abania.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Grymm Crab
Description:
A succulent freshwater crab remarkably found only in the Peaks lake of Grymm.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Enid Shrimp
Description:
A succulent freshwater shrimp remarkably found only in the Peaks lake of Enid.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Invisible Crayfish
Description:
The pristine white shell of this freshwater crustacean makes it nigh invisible when the wavekin is hiding amongst rocks or sand of a similar hue.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Rapids Jumper
Description:
A lifetime of swimming against strong-yet-slow river currents has left this freshwater fish bereft of most fatty flesh.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Abalathian Salamander
Description:
An amphibian commonly found living in the myriad lakes and swamps of Gyr Abania.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Adamantite Bichir
Description:
A freshwater fish native to the wetlands of Gyr Abania.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Meditator
Description:
Possessed of the unique ability to survive for extended periods out of water, the meditator will periodically bathe on the banks of the rivers and lakes in which it resides.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Deemster
Description:
A freshwater fish so enormous, even the legends sung of the elusive wavekin do not do it justice.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Stonytongue
Description:
This distant cousin to the Coerthan bonytongue can be found dwelling in the freshwater lakes and rivers of Gyr Abania.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Bull's Bite
Description:
A small carnivorous fish found solely in the isolated Gyr Abanian pond known as the Bull's Bath.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Peeping Pisces
Description:
This freshwater fish is possessed of an eye on both the top and bottom of its head, allowing it to simultaneously spy threats above and below the water, should the need arise.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Scimitarfish
Description:
Not a swordfish, but a sword-like fish found in the rivers of Gyr Abania.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Gigant Bass
Description:
An aptly named freshwater fish native to the rivers of Gyr Abania.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Nhaama's Boon
Description:
One of the rare fish found in the Nhaama Desert's even rarer freshwater oases.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Cave Killifish
Description:
These small fries found primarily in the caves of Gyr Abania rarely grow to more than one or two ilms.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Bone Melter
Description:
This lake snail feeds by attaching itself to the bones of drowned animals.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Fallen Leaf
Description:
The still waters of Dimwold are teeming with these fish who, to the untrained eye, appear naught more than fallen leaves.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Falling Star
Description:
This glowing orb is actually a colony of rare luminescent algae found in the caves of eastern Gyr Abania.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Capsized Squeaker
Description:
This odd, whiskered fish is found only in the sheltered waters of the Comet's Tail.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Nirvana Crab
Description:
The backs of these freshwater crabs are adorned with colorful colonies of water-resistant fungus.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Velodyna Grass Carp
Description:
This variety of grass carp is most often found in the northeastern Eorzean river from which it earns its name.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Black Velodyna Carp
Description:
One of several varieties of carp found in the Velodyna River, this particular species is immediately recognizable from its pitch-black skin.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Rhalgr's Bolt
Description:
This eel-like freshwater fish has been blessed with the capacity to emit an electric charge that can prove deadly to smaller wavekin.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Highland Perch
Description:
Once common throughout the Gyr Abanian highlands, overfishing has relegated the remainder of the species to Mirage Creek.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Gravel Gudgeon
Description:
This freshwater fish will bury itself deep in the gravel-littered beds of rivers, making it a difficult catch.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Grinning Anchovy
Description:
These small saltwater fish swim in massive schools, using their sheer numbers to ensure that even if a few stragglers are swallowed, the species will endure.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Glass Herring
Description:
This common silver fish will travel back and forth between the Ruby Sea and the Glass Ocean searching for food.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Hellyfish
Description:
The abundance of these translucent amorphs to the volcanic island of Hells' Lid was an invitation to an ill-conceived moniker, most likely given by a rum-soaked pirate.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Ruby Coral
Description:
A piece of sharp crimson coral, widely found throughout the Ruby Sea.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Sapphire Coral
Description:
A piece of sharp azure coral, widely found throughout the Ruby Sea.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Bone Coral
Description:
A piece of sharp milky white coral, widely found throughout the Ruby Sea.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Butterfly Fish
Description:
One of few brightly colored fish native to the Ruby Tide.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Dafu
Description:
Its sheer dominance over other life in the Ruby Sea has earned this sizable wavekin the title dafu, or literally, the top dog...er, fish.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Swordfish
Description:
Fishers seeking to land ocean-dwelling swordfish must take care not to accidentally impale themselves on the wavekin's serrated bladelike maw.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Leaf Tatsunoko
Description:
At a glance, one might mistake this queerly shaped denizen of the Ruby Sea for an errant piece of seaweed.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Glass Flounder
Description:
This flat bottom dweller spends most of its life skittering about the floors of the Glass Ocean, but can also be found in the Ruby Sea.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Zekki Gator
Description:
This giant shark regularly hunts the waters of the coast of the Isle of Zekki, and has been known to attack the pirates and fishers who frequent its strands.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Daio Squid
Description:
A rarely seen giant squid, thought to be the inspiration for 35% of all pirate chanties sung on the Ruby Sea.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Koromo Octopus
Description:
A highly elusive giant octopus, so rarely seen that not a single pirate chanty sung on the Red Sea mentions the poor cephalopod.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Gliding Fish
Description:
A unique saltwater fish that will jump from the water to evade predators, using its pectoral fins to glide across the ocean surface.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Globefish
Description:
A saltwater fish that will puff its spike-laden body to bursting to protect itself when provoked.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Fan Clam
Description:
The shell of this bivalve mollusk is ribbed like the uchiwa hand fans used by Hingan festival-goers in summer.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Blockhead
Description:
A saltwater fish as stubborn as its name suggests. It is pure coincidence that it also has a hard bony plate protecting its tiny brain.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Glass Tuna
Description:
One of the most popular ingredients in Hingan sushi, the giant Glass tuna are thought to follow the strong ocean currents for thousands of malms in their lifetime.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Doman Crayfish
Description:
These tiny freshwater crustaceans can be found in relative abundance in the flooded rice paddies of Yanxia.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Ruby Shrimp
Description:
One of the most common shrimp found in the Ruby Sea.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Striped Fugu
Description:
Similar to the globefish, the fugu will puff up its body to frighten away potential predators. Those who do not heed the wavekin's warning and devour it anyway will most certainly succumb to the lethal poison found in the fugu's flesh.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Raitonfish
Description:
A large freshwater fish named for the levin-manipulating technique mastered by the ninja of Doma.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Blank Oscar
Description:
The body of this rare freshwater fish is entirely void of pigment.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Dragonfish
Description:
Despite the insistence of Yanxian villagers, the freshwater dragonfish is ten parts fish, zero parts dragon.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Lordly Salmon
Description:
Just as do the salmon of Eorzea, the steely blue salmon of the Far East spend their lives in the sea before returning to the freshwater rivers where they were born to spawn and die.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Yanxian Koi
Description:
A mottled freshwater carp of middling size native to the southern reaches of the One River.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Kotsu Zetsu
Description:
A large, slow-swimming freshwater fish found primarily in Yanxia's Plum Spring.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Longhair Catfish
Description:
Though named for its lengthy whiskers, this catfish's most ready feature is not its mustache, but the wavy scale-like patterns on its back.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Plum Gazer
Description:
Those seeking to land a plum gazer must travel to the secluded Plum Spring, hidden deep in Yanxia's Gensui Chain.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Pandamoth
Description:
This regal freshwater fish has a distinct white and black mottling which, while giving the wavekin an air of majesty, also makes it easy to spot by predators.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Doman Trout
Description:
An extremely common fish found throughout Yanxia, and a popular dish amongst the realm's residents.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Doman Eel
Description:
A thin freshwater eel that can be found living amongst the reeds growing in the Valley of the Fallen Rainbow.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Brassfish
Description:
This brightly colored freshwater fish of Far Eastern origin is a favorite amongst aquarium owners.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Othardian Trout
Description:
A freshwater fish found in rivers across the entire Othardian continent.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Zagas Khaal
Description:
A freshwater fish extremely common to many of the One River's northern tributaries. Its name literally translates to river fish.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Steppe Skipper
Description:
A swift freshwater fish that, when swimming near the surface of the One River tributaries in which it is commonly found, appears to skip through the rivers' reeds.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Dry Steppe Skipper
Description:
A small freshwater fish found in the arid southern grasslands bordering the Nhaama Desert.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Sun Bass
Description:
This violent fish native to the Azim Steppe prefers the calm waters of a lake or wetland to the swift-moving currents of a river.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Skytear
Description:
The skytear can be found in the quick-flowing shallow rapids near a river's source rather than in the deeper, slow-moving waters downstream.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Dawn Crayfish
Description:
A red-shelled freshwater crustacean found in abundance in the lakes and rivers of the Azim Steppe.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Dusk Crayfish
Description:
A white-shelled freshwater crustacean found in abundance in the lakes and rivers of the Azim Steppe.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Bowfish
Description:
This swift-moving freshwater fish can be found up and down the One River.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Jade Sculpin
Description:
Highly developed scales and spines set this sculpin apart from its western counterparts.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Padjali Loach
Description:
A horn-shaped fish native to the dark bogs of Dimwold.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Nogoi
Description:
A common variety of koi found in almost every region on Othard.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Curtain Pleco
Description:
This freshwater fish has a billowy, curtain-like dorsal fin that it uses to confuse predators.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Hardscale
Description:
A freshwater cousin of the lightscale with scales as hard as its name suggests.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Eastern Pike
Description:
The massive eastern pike is technically classified as a freshwater fish. The breed, however, can survive the brackish waters of the Hathoeva and Velodyna river deltas.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Wraithfish
Description:
This freshwater fish native to the bogs of Dimwold will oft conceal itself beneath the planks of the Wraithwalk for protection.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Little Perykos
Description:
As is the case with the little Thalaos, the little Perykos is anything but small. Though normally only found in the Indigo Deep, this lord of the North Isle of Endless Summer can sometimes be found swimming in the five seas and beyond...yet for what reason, no one knows.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Wentletrap
Description:
A tiny Ruby Sea mollusk with a beautiful spiral shell that is sought by jewelry makers across the Far East.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Black Boxfish
Description:
This saltwater cousin to the puffers changes color several times during its development, and it is only in the final years of adulthood that it bears the hue from which it earns its moniker.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Glass Manta
Description:
This denizen of the Glass Ocean is one of the largest fish of its type ever recorded.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Regal Silverside
Description:
According to Hingan fishers, it was not until the past twenty summers that the regal silverside began appearing in their nets. It is popular opinion that the fish may have been introduced via bilge water dumped by foreign trade bulks.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Snowflake Moray
Description:
A saltwater fish that exhibits a peculiar symbiotic relationship with spiny lobsters.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Hoppfish
Description:
While hopping out of the water will aid this saltwater species in escaping larger fish, the action attracts flocks of hungry seagulls that will harry the schools for entire turns of the sun.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Lightscale
Description:
A freshwater cousin of the hardscale with scales as light as its name suggests.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Grass Fugu
Description:
This highly poisonous saltwater fish can survive for long periods of time in freshwater rivers, and can, on occasion, be found as far as ten malms upstream.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Giant Eel
Description:
An eel's size is proportional to the amount it eats. The giant freshwater eels of the One River eat...a lot.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Kamina Crab
Description:
While abundant in the sea, hermit crabs are quite rare in fresh water, possibly due to the lack of available homes. The kamina crab is one example.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Spider Crab
Description:
The spider crab's spindly legs carry the deep-sea crustacean hundreds of malms across their migratory routes.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Little Dragonfish
Description:
The elongated forehead of this saltwater species is compared to the nose of a tengua legendary birdlike creature of Far Eastern legend.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Black Fanfish
Description:
This saltwater wavekin uses both the size and color of its fins to its advantage, allowing it to, for all intents and purposes, disappear in the darker depths of the sea.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Zebra Shark
Description:
Unlike those of the mystical zebra, the pronounced stripes upon this wavekin's back are more accurately compared to a tiger's spots.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 3 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Nophica's Comb
Description:
The sharp, bone-like protrusions on this carnivorous mollusk's massive shell give it the comb-like appearance from which it earns its name.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Warty Wartfish
Description:
This sluggardly wartfish native to the One River somehow has more warts than a common wartfish, if that can be believed.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Common Whelk
Description:
It would not be called a common whelk if this whelk was not found as abundantly as it is across the whole of Othard.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Hairless Barb
Description:
This impossibly monstrous freshwater fish grew impossibly monstrous despite a diet of mostly river grasses.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Hatchetfish
Description:
The Ruby Sea hatchetfish earns its name from its overgrown head which, if you squint hard enough, might appear similar to the head of a timberlord's hatchet.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 1 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Threadfish
Description:
This spindly saltwater fish spurns the colder currents of the north in favor of the warm waters along Othard and Ilsabard's southern coasts.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Garden Eel
Description:
Garden eels spend most of their lives buried in sandy sea bottoms, emerging only to hunt and to mate.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Eastern Sea Pickle
Description:
Named for its shape and not its flavor, this repugnant sluglike mass is found throughout the Glass Ocean and Ruby Sea.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Brindlebass
Description:
This enormous saltwater bass can be highly territorial, devouring anything and everything that passes through its chosen demesne.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Demon Stonefish
Description:
A saltwater wavekin commonly avoided by fishers due to the extreme amount of toxins found in its flesh.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Armored Crayfish
Description:
A deep-red relative of the Doman crayfish.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Bighead Carp
Description:
A dark-scaled carp found in the One River, easily identified by its queer downward-pointing eyes.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Zeni Clam
Description:
Named after an ancient Far Eastern currency, this bivalve mollusk is most commonly found in the lakes and rivers of Yanxia.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Corpse-eater
Description:
A large carnivorous wavekin that dwells in the warm currents of the southern seas.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 3 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Ronin Trevally
Description:
This large variety of trevally is given the name ronin for its tendency to journey the warm southern seas in solitude.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Toothsome Grouper
Description:
The most delicious of saltwater groupers...if the merchants selling it for thrice the price of a regular grouper are to be believed.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Horned Turban
Description:
The shell of this warm-water sea mollusk is twisted like the turbans worn by the dhalmel drivers of Thavnair.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Ruby Sea Star
Description:
These spiny five-limbed invertebrates survive by feeding on the flesh of dead fish fallen to the sea floor.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Gauntlet Crab
Description:
These giant crabs hide themselves amongst the plants that grow on a river's bed, the moss growing on their claws used as camouflage.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Hermit Goby
Description:
A decent-sized fish found in the One River.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Skythorn
Description:
An ancient breed of freshwater fish found with little frequency in the One River.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Swordtip
Description:
One of the most widespread squid species on Hydaelyn.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: False Scad
Description:
A common saltwater fish doing its best scad impression.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Snow Crab
Description:
Snow crabs live in deep waters, scurrying hither and thither across the ocean floor in search of carrion.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Red-eyed Lates
Description:
A saltwater fish found in both the Glass Ocean and the Ruby Sea.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Common Bitterling
Description:
This freshwater fish is found on both the Othardian east coast and in Shishuthe Hingan island upon which sits Kugane.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Fifty-summer Cod
Description:
This long-living freshwater cod is commonly found in the One River.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 3 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Nagxian Mullet
Description:
A thin, eel-like fish native to Nagxia, but found throughout the One River.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Redcoat
Description:
A large, reddish orange fish with distinctively enormous eyes to help it see in the murky depths of the Ruby Sea.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Yanxian Tiger Prawn
Description:
This Far Eastern crustacean has not only the stripes, but also the ferocity of a Yanxian tiger.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Tengu Fan
Description:
The tengu fan, named for its round, flat shape, will emit electric shocks from its body when threatened. Though the shocks cannot kill, they do stun, affording the fish ample opportunity to flee.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Star Turban
Description:
When viewed from the side, this sea mollusk's shell looks like a turban; however, when viewed from above, its radiating spines give it the appearance of a twinkling star.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Blue-fish
Description:
A delicious freshwater fish with the most jejune moniker of all the One River's aquatic denizens.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Steppe Bullfrog
Description:
Steppe bullfrogs can be found across both Yanxia and Nagxia and are easily identifiable by their deep, bellowing mating croaks.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Cavalry Catfish
Description:
This large, aggressive freshwater fish will charge most anything moving, regardless of its size.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 3 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Redfin
Description:
Second only to the blue-fish in mediocrity of monikers, the freshwater redfin of the One Riverunsurprisinglyhas bright-red fins.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Moondisc
Description:
A cousin of the sundisc, the moondisc also features celestial patterns upon its body, though its are decidedly brighter to serve as camouflage in the white-bedded waters of Loch Seld.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Bleached Bonytongue
Description:
Similar to most wavekin that have taken up residence in Loch Seld, the bleached bonytongue is almost entirely white.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Salt Shark
Description:
The salt shark has an elongated body that it can bend like an eel, allowing it to navigate Loch Seld's obstacle-strewn lakebed in search for prey.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: King's Mantle
Description:
Very few species of octopus have been discovered in Loch Seld, but those that havesuch as the king's mantleare magnificently monstrous.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Sea Lamp
Description:
This variety of sea anemone emits a soft green glow when its tentacles are disturbed.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Amberjack
Description:
This large saltwater predator can be found in the waters off both the eastern and western coasts of Hingashi.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Cherry Salmon
Description:
Though dubbed a salmon, this particular variety does not journey downstream to the sea, spending its entire life in the river where it was born.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Yu-no-hana Crab
Description:
Hingan folklore has that all hot springs were once dug from the ground by these hardy crustaceans.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Dotharli Gudgeon
Description:
This freshwater fish commonly found in the upper One River is also known as the Mol gudgeon, the Kahkol gudgeon, the Dataqi gudgeon, the Horo gudgeon, and after whichever other Xaela tribe that insists their ancestors first caught the species.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: River Clam
Description:
A small bivalve mollusk found living in the sands of the One River.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Grass Shark
Description:
Grass sharks are massive, their size rivaling that of even the Glass Ocean's greatest predatorsan amazing feat considering grass sharks live their entire lives in the confines of the One River.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 3 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Typhoon Shrimp
Description:
The typhoon shrimp is one of only a few shrimp species that can survive the toxically salty waters of Loch Seld.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Rock Oyster
Description:
This bivalve mollusk grows in abundance on boulders and statues submerged in Loch Seld.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Salt Urchin
Description:
The white coloring of the salt urchin's spines make them difficult to see on Loch Seld's colorless lakebed. Those who choose to wade through the shallows should always take care to protect their feet.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Carpenter Crab
Description:
A carpenter crab's claws are powerful enough to cut through solid wood. Whether or not a carpenter crab has ever constructed something from that wood remains unconfirmed.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Spiny Lobster
Description:
This massive crustacean found in both the Ruby Sea and the Glass Ocean is considered a delicacy in the Far East, and is a luxury oft too extravagant for any but the richest of nobles to partake in.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Mitsukuri Shark
Description:
There is no doubt that the mitsukuri shark's most defining feature is its katana-like mouth and the tales it has spawned of poor fishers being impaled.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Doman Bubble Eye
Description:
A variety of bubble eye goldfish selectively bred by Doman royalty for innumerable generations.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 1 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Dragon Squeaker
Description:
There are many theories as to why this remarkable breed of One River squeaker swims tail first, yet most have been dismissed as feeble attempts to explain what simply cannot be explained, such as why the sky is blue or why tides come in and the tides go out.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Dawn Herald
Description:
Though smaller than the dusk herald, the dawn herald is as commonly found in the waters of the One River as its close cousin.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Salt Cellar
Description:
An ashen-shelled snail found throughout Loch Seld. Cooking the gastropods in their shells with garlic and herbs is the preferred method of consumption.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: White Sturgeon
Description:
The white sturgeon is believed by some scholars to simply be normal sturgeons exhibiting albinisma rare trait that became common once all the darker sturgeons were poached from Loch Seld on account of them being easy to see.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Tithe Collector
Description:
One of Loch Seld's largest native species.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Bashful Batfish
Description:
The unique shape and coloration of the batfish makes this denizen of the Ruby Sea a highly sought-after specimen amongst collectors.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: River Bream
Description:
Unlike sea breams, this quirky cousin will travel back and forth 'twixt the brackish waters of a river's delta and the fresher waters upstream.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Snipe Eel
Description:
The snipe eels of the One River will never grow plumper than an ilm or two in diameter, but can stretch to several yalms in length.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Cherubfish
Description:
A rare freshwater fish native to Yanxia and the Azim Steppe.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Dusk Herald
Description:
The dusk herald is a fair-sized fish commonly found in the One River.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Glaring Perch
Description:
This freshwater perch is found up and down the One River.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Abalathian Pipira
Description:
While given the modifier Abalathian, this particular pipira will not be found in the Spine's western or even central regions, preferring the biting salty waters of the Lochs.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Steel Loach
Description:
The steel loach's scintillant silver body reflects sunlight in a manner that makes the fish difficult to spot in its native Loch Seld.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Ivory Sole
Description:
The whitish grey skin of this large flatfish allows it to hide itself on the bottom of Loch Seld with such efficiency that for years Ala Mhigans thought the species extinct.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Motley Beakfish
Description:
A striped carnivore that hunts the Ruby Sea.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 3 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Thousandfang
Description:
A rare, sea-dwelling scalekin infamous for its gaping maw lined with multiple rows of bladelike teeth, though official observations by scholars put the fang count at no more than a few score.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Ichthyosaur
Description:
Let not its dolphin-like appearance fool you. The ichthyosaur is a ravenous scalekin that feeds on squid, fish, and the occasional man overboard.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 3 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Sailfin
Description:
A unique freshwater fish featuring astonishingly overgrown dorsal and anal fins.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Fangshi
Description:
An extremely rare freshwater fish whose face is covered in countless whisker-like protrusions.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Flamefish
Description:
This large freshwater fish's skin features brilliant streaks of fiery yellow and orange.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Fickle Krait
Description:
Special glands within the fickle krait's body create a deadly poison feared by fishers and coveted by assassins.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Eternal Eye
Description:
This tiny species' skin exhibits a violet hue rarely seen in freshwater fish.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 1 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Soul of the Stallion
Description:
A rare white freshwater fish believed to harbor the soul of a once-proud steppe stallion.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Flood Tuna
Description:
The descendants of sea tuna believed by scholars to have arrived in Loch Seld during the great flood that ended the Fifth Astral Era.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Mercenary Crab
Description:
This heavily armored crab is one of few species adapted to the hypersalinated waters of Loch Seld.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Ashfish
Description:
A pigmentless fish found solely in Loch Seld.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Silken Sunfish
Description:
A rare breed of sunfish that can survive only in waters exhibiting extreme salinity.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Mosasaur
Description:
An aggressive scalekin native to the saline waters of Loch Seld.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Regional Folklore Trader's Token A
Description: A note of promise granted for the delivery of tomes of regional folklore.

Name: Nagxian Silk
Description: A light, billowy silk woven using traditional methods of the Nagxian people.

Name: Ratanhia Leaves
Description: Leaves of a low-growing shrub native to the plains of Nagxia. The leaves contain high concentrations of tannin, an ingredient necessary in tanning leather.

Name: Taoist's Wool
Description: Despite supposedly being woven countless generations past, this cloth appears as it was crafted yesterday.

Name: Nagxian Leather
Description: A beastkin hide tanned using traditional Nagxian methods.
