Name: Tales of Adventure: Heavensward
Description:
A detailed record of recent Eorzean historyso detailed, in fact, that all who read it come to swear they experienced the events firsthand.

Use to instantly complete all main scenario quests up through The Far Edge of Fate. Cannot be used outside large settlements. Automatic logout will commence upon usage.

Name: Tales of Adventure: One Paladin's Journey I
Description:
A detailed record of one adventurer's path to becoming a realm-renowned paladinso detailed, in fact, that all who read it come to swear they experienced the events firsthand.

Use to instantly level paladin to 60 and complete all job quests up through This Little Sword of Mine. Cannot be used outside large settlements. Automatic logout will commence upon usage.

Name: Faire Voucher MMXVII
Description: Currency minted and distributed by the Adventurers' Guild for use during the Moonfire Faire.

Name: Stuffed Dog
Description: Said to bring a full twelvemoon of good fortune...or as much can be expected from a disturbingly realistic dog skin filled with sawdust and bittersweet memories.

Name: Yugiri and Gosetsu Sketch
Description: A surprisingly accurate depiction of Yugiri and Gosetsu, once again suggesting that Alphinaud may have mistaken his life's calling.

Name: Morin Khuur
Description: A traditional instrument of the Azim Steppe's nomadic Xaela tribes, the morin khuur has two strings (the male and the female) woven together from the tail hair of a stallion and a mare, respectively.

Name: Veteran's Clan Mark Log
Description: A list of elite marks slain by the log's ownera hunter so dedicated, that it is said she tracked prey until the ripe age of one hundred and seventy-two summers, dying of natural causes after slaying her thirtieth king behemoth.

Name: Sustaining Potion
Description:
Grants the effect of Rehabilitation (HP regeneration) to yourself.

Duration: 30s
Only available for use in the Palace of the Dead.

Name: Imitation Square Window
Description: The next best thing to a real window, without all the fuss.

Description: A painting of the Dusk Throne based off notes compiled from your sightseeing log.

Name: Reunion Painting
Description: A painting of Reunion based off notes compiled from your sightseeing log.

Name: Chakha Zoh Painting
Description: A painting of Chakha Zoh based off notes compiled from your sightseeing log.

Name: Dawn Throne Painting
Description: A painting of the Dawn Throne based off notes compiled from your sightseeing log.

Name: Sassho-seki Fragment
Description: Literally the killing stone, this curiosity is said to bring death to all who touch it. Handle with care.

Name: Castaway Chocobo Chick
Description:
Currently without a name. Wilson recommended.

Use item to acquire the castaway chocobo chick minion.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Odder Otter
Description:
Is there anything odder than an otter who lives out of water?

Use item to acquire the odder otter minion.

Name: Fox Kit
Description:
His devotion toward you will prove fair and balanced.

Use item to acquire the fox kit minion.

Name: Tora-jiro
Description:
His name suggests that this tiny tiger cub has an older brother. His parents deny everything.

Use item to acquire the Tora-jiro minion.

Name: Tiny Tatsunoko
Description:
If the Hingan word for sea horse is tatsunoko, would that make this a sea pony? Your little sea pony?

Use item to acquire the tiny tatsunoko minion.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Bombfish
Description:
He will give you an offer that can't be defused.

Use item to acquire the bombfish minion.

Name: Bom Boko
Description:
An adorable raccoon dog pup with a big heart and even bigger testicles.

Use item to acquire the Bom Boko minion.

Name: Road Sparrow
Description:
This house sparrow's home is on the road. Sparrow.

Use item to acquire the road sparrow minion.

Name: Wind-up Lyse
Description:
Most certainly not a repurposed wind-up Yda.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Lyse minion.

Name: Dress-up Yugiri
Description:
One Yugiri is never enough.

Use item to acquire the dress-up Yugiri minion.

Name: Wind-up Gosetsu
Description:
Wanted by the Empire...and good little boys and girls across Othard.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Gosetsu minion.

Name: Wind-up Yotsuyu
Description:
Now she can be the bane of your existence! A font of your misery!

Use item to acquire the wind-up Yotsuyu minion.

Name: Mock-up Grynewaht
Description:
Bwahahahaha!

Use item to acquire the mock-up Grynewaht minion.

Name: Wind-up Namazu
Description:
Half cat. Half fish. All fish.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Namazu minion.

Name: Ivon Coeurlfist Doll
Description:
Technically Coeurlpaw. 

Use item to acquire the Ivon Coeurlfist minion.

Name: Wind-up Chimera
Description:
Crafted by piecing together the remnants of unsold automata.

Use item to acquire the wind-up chimera minion.

Name: Wind-up Meateater
Description:
Watch out boys, he'll (literally) chew you up.

Use item to acquire the wind-up meateater minion.

Name: Magitek Avenger F1
Description:
Avenger, assembled!

Use item to acquire the magitek avenger F1 minion.

Name: Ghido
Description:
There is most likely a logical explanation as to why this aged turtle can navigate the skies. Most likely.

Use item to acquire the Ghido minion.

Name: Wind-up Exdeath
Description:
Most maniacal tree beings bent on world domination are usually not intimidated by turtles. This one is.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Exdeath minion.

Name: Wind-up Khloe
Description:
Because there is nothing wrong with a fully automated mechanical reconstruction of a young girl of three and ten summers.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Khloe minion.

Name: Wind-up Susano
Description:
If the Kojin believe that within every item resides a deity, then who exactly resides inside this automaton?

Use item to acquire the wind-up Susano minion.

Name: Wind-up Lakshmi
Description:
Your, your, your serpentine.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Lakshmi minion.

Name: Wind-up Bismarck
Description:
The hairiest whale you will see this fortnight.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Bismarck minion.

Name: Falcon Ignition Key
Description: This ignition key winds the gears of the Falcon-class airship.

Name: Blissful Kamuy Fife
Description: The sweet song of this stout flute is said to summon a kamuy blessed by Lakshmi herself.

Name: Reveling Kamuy Fife
Description: The powerful tones emitted by this stout flute are said to summon a kamuy blessed by Susano himself.

Name: Magitek Predator Identification Key
Description: A thin, rectangular piece of what appears to be cermet. Placing it near your magitek predator will magically bring the machine to life.

Name: Battle Lion Horn
Description: An iron-banded horn used to summon your battle lion mount...to battle!

Name: Battle Bear Horn
Description: A simple horn used to summon your battle beara towering mount certain to strike fear into the hearts of your foes.

Name: Battle Panther Bell
Description: A brass bell used to summon your battle panther mount. How only your panther answers the summons, and not the panthers of hundreds of other adventurers with similar summoning bells is a mystery for the ages.

Name: Yol Whistle
Description: A rough-hewn whistle whose clear tone summons your loyal yol mount.

Name: Alte Roite Prism
Description: A multifaceted prism that, when held aloft, refracts light in a way that can be seen only by your Alte Roite mounta being who possesses the uncanny ability to hide in plain sight until summoned.

Name: Centurio Tiger Horn
Description: The horn of a beast felled on a legendary Hunt used to summon a legendary tiger gifted to you by the Clan Centurio.

Name: Reveler's Barding
Description: A suit of chocobo armor designed to resemble Susano, the Lord of the Revel.

Name: Ala Mhigan Barding
Description: A suit of traditional Ala Mhigan chocobo armor.

Name: Blissful Barding
Description: A suit of chocobo armor designed to resemble Lakshmi, Lady of Bliss.

Name: Hingan Barding
Description: Lightweight chocobo armor designed to resemble traditional Hingan garb.

Name: Oriental Barding
Description: Lightweight chocobo armor designed to resemble traditional Hingan garb.

Name: Nezha Barding
Description: Chocobo armor designed to resemble the protective garb worn by the great Nezhahero of Doman legend.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Display of Power
Description: An illustrated manual of various Far Eastern vulgarities. Use to learn the /powerup emote.

Name: Salmon Roe
Description: The ruby red eggs of salmon returning upriver to spawn. Bait for freshwater fishing.

Name: Nightcrawler
Description: These fat earthworms that feed above ground in the small hours of the night have been known to grow up to two full fulms in length. Live bait for freshwater fishing.

Name: Midge Larva
Description: The bright-red coloring of this undeveloped midge makes it an easy target for sharp-eyed fish. Live bait for freshwater fishing.

Name: Silkworm
Description: The plump, cream-colored larva of a silkworm moth. Live bait for salt lake fishing.

Name: Live Shrimp
Description: A tiny, twitching sea shrimp. Live bait for ocean fishing.

Name: Bream Lure
Description: A lure for bream made by attaching rubber fins to a heavy lead ball.

Name: Suspending Minnow
Description: A plug lure made to resemble a minnow. Effective in attracting freshwater fish from both surface and floor.

Name: Limited Edition Rising Banner
Description: A handsome banner designed to decorate residences for the annual Rising celebration. Available for a short time only!

Name: Limited Edition Firefly Lamp
Description:
A wooden cage weaved in a Far Eastern style. The fireflies within provide very little light, but are pleasing to gaze upon. Available for a short time only!

Up to five may be placed in a single estate, regardless of type.

Name: Limited Edition Rising Pillar
Description: A festive pillar designed to decorate residences for the Rising. Available for a short time only!

Name: Pumpkin Pie Set
Description:
Pured pumpkin mixed with cream, eggs, and spices, and baked into a flaky, buttery crust. An All Saints' Wake staple (for reasons unknown).

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

  VIT Bonus: +4% (Max 8)

Name: Peaks Pigment
Description: Extracted from natural sources in the Gyr Abanian highlands, this clay-based substance can be dried and ground, then prepared with water and oil to create a colorful dye.

Name: Yellow Kudzu Root
Description: This variety of kudzu not only exhibits the curative properties of its more common cousin, it has been observed growing almost twice as fast. It has also been observed withering and dying twice as fast.

Name: Gyr Abanian Chub
Description:
A freshwater fish most commonly found in the Velodyna and Hathoeva rivers.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Coral Horse
Description:
This rare specimen of sea horse has a body that so closely resembles coral that it can be almost impossible to locate amongst the reefs it calls home.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Maiden's Heart
Description:
It is believed that only one in every thousand marimo is born blood red instead of the more common green. An exact count has yet to be conducted.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Velodyna Salmon
Description:
Similar to Aldenard's other salmon species, this salmon also spends its entire life in the sea, until returning to the Velodyna to spawn...and die.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Purple Buckler
Description:
There was a time that these snapping turtles were caught for their nigh-impenetrable shells which were used as shields by the ancient Gyr Abanian highland clans.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: High-grade Company-issue Tonic
Description: This herbal concoction is guaranteed to clear passageways blocked with blood or bile, allowing for easier breathing and full, immediate recovery from unconsciousness.

Name: Cloudsbreath

Name: Wind-up Hien
Description:
Be proud, my new owner. Be proud.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Hien minion.

Name: Wind-up Kojin
Description:
Is it green? Is it blue? Or...is it neither?

Use item to acquire the wind-up Kojin minion.

Name: Wind-up Ravana
Description:
Low on low he stands, gazing up to see.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Ravana minion.

Name: Mameshiba
Description:
Who let the newborn miniature Far Eastern canine specimen out? Who, who, who, who, who!?

Use item to acquire the mameshiba minion.

Name: Tengu Doll
Description:
And you know what they say about the size of a doll's nose.

Use item to acquire the tengu doll minion.

Name: Wind-up Matanga
Description:
This is not Matanga. Matanga is graceful.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Matanga minion.

Name: Wind-up Ramza
Description:
Stands ready to fight for truth, justice, and the Ivalician way.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Ramza minion.

Name: Wind-up Ixion
Description:
A horse is a horse, of course. Except when it is Ixion.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Ixion minion.

Name: Axolotl Eft
Description:
Because there truly is nothing more adorable than an oddly Lalafellin face on the body of a moist, frilled salamander.

Use item to acquire the axolotl eft minion.

Name: Koala Joey
Description:
Shows no signs of stress or crotch rot, so hug away.

Use item to acquire the koala joey minion.

Name: Wind-up Shinryu
Description:
Exhibits an almost preternatural urge to hide in treasure chests and guard powerful weapons.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Shinryu minion.

Name: Dress-up Raubahn
Description:
Detachable arm optional.

Use item to acquire the dress-up Raubahn minion.

Name: Cardinalfish
Description:
A freshwater fish easily recognizable for its vivid black-and-white stripes.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Rockfish
Description:
Despite the insistence of fishers raised on colorful local folklore, the massive knob atop this freshwater fish's head does not contain hidden treasure.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 1 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Ukiki
Description:
Its Hingan name roughly translating to floating tree, this variety of Eastern sunfish neither floats nor is a tree.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 3 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Violet Prismfish
Description:
The pale violet glow emitted by this freshwater fish is believed to be caused by unbalanced levels of aspected aether in the wavekin's humours.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Guppy
Description:
This tiny fish once found throughout the Three Great Continents has been harvested to near extinction, and is now prized by pisciculturists.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 1 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Ichimonji
Description:
Named after a blade appearing in Hingan legend, the ichimonji has a long, protruding mouth lined with countless razor-like teeth.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Snailfish
Description:
This unique saltwater fish has not a scale on its entire body.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Red Mage Barding
Description: Chocobo barding designed to pair well with traditional red mage garb.

Name: Citrine Carbuncle Whistle
Description: A jeweled whistle that emits a heart-melting tone said to summon a Citrine Carbuncle.

Name: Salt & Pepper Seal
Description:
What a seal, what a mighty good seal.

Use item to acquire the salt & pepper seal minion.

Name: Shinryu Totem
Description: It is unknown by whom or for what purpose this pulsating metal idol forged in the likeness of Shinryu was created.

Name: Dreadwyrm Totem
Description: A golden idol created by the worshipers of Bahamutpossibly the Lambs of Dalamud.

Name: Rabanastran Coin
Description: A small gold coin stamped with the royal Rabanastran seal. Once considered to be of great historical significance, a sudden influx caused their value to plummet, rendering them almost worthless.

Name: Material Supplier Permit A-3
Description:
This permit allows the hiring of material suppliers on the estate.

Private chambers (apartments), cottages, houses, and mansions can host 4, 6, 8, and 10 vendors, respectively.

Name: Junkmonger Permit A-3
Description:
This permit allows the hiring of junkmongers on the estate.

Private chambers (apartments), cottages, houses, and mansions can host 4, 6, 8, and 10 vendors, respectively.

Name: Mender Permit A-3
Description:
This permit allows the hiring of menders on the estate.

Private chambers (apartments), cottages, houses, and mansions can host 4, 6, 8, and 10 vendors, respectively.

Name: Hannish Wool
Description: An improved variety of Thavnairian wool conceived by the Radz-at-Han Weavers' Guild.

Name: Thavnairian Wool
Description: A coarse woolen cloth made from large gauge yarn. A historically important cloth in Thavnair's textile trade.

Name: Hingan Partition
Description: A partition designed in the Hingan fashion, reaching to the ceiling and so sturdy it may as well be a wall.

Description: Timeworn pages of sheet music for The Worm's Head and The Worm's Tail. The composer is unknown.

Name: Moldy Pumpkin Cookie MMXVII
Description: A devilish imp is thought to have made this slightly burnt biscuit shaped like a pumpkin head. One can only wonder what ingredients it containsbut at this point, tasting it to find out is not recommended.

Name: Starlight Box
Description: One can only hope its sender remembered to fill it with a gift.

Name: Crimson Pepper
Description: A pungent spice with just a hint of bitterness behind its bite.

Name: Scion Liberator's Jacket
Description: Fits: All

Description: Fits: All

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Improper Amorism
Description: An illustrated manual of how not to express one's feelings of love. Use to learn the /dote emote.

Name: Authentic Pumpkin Pie Set
Description:
This recreation of an All Saints' Wake staple is so authentic that you can almost believe it's really pured pumpkin mixed with cream, eggs, and spices, and baked into a flaky, buttery crust. Almost.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Tenacity Bonus: +4% (Max 12)
  VIT Bonus: +4% (Max 8)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Authentic Pumpkin Pudding Set
Description:
For those who like their All Saints' Wake treats sans crust, this rich, creamyand most importantly, authenticalternative will have you in heaven...er, hell.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Spell Speed Bonus: +4% (Max 12)
  VIT Bonus: +4% (Max 8)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Authentic Ghost Candlestand
Description: A spooky stand designed to be displayed during All Saints' Wake festivities. Decidedly equal to last year's candlestand in ways far too numerous to list here.

Name: Authentic MMXIII All Saints' Wake Advertisement
Description: A hand-painted notice advertising the All Saints' Wake festivities of a year gone by.

Name: Authentic Pumpkin Tower
Description: What authentic fell magicks keep these authentic pumpkins from authentically toppling to the ground, no one knows.

Name: Authentic Starlight Stew Set
Description:
A hearty meat and vegetable soup brewed by families across the realm every Starlight Celebration. Authentically edible!

Cannot be retrieved once used.
 Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Determination Bonus: +4% (Max 7)
  VIT Bonus: +4% (Max 8)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Authentic Starlight Log Set
Description:
Fortunately, this faithful reproduction of a festive log-shaped cake tastes nothing like its appearance would suggest.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Piety Bonus: +4% (Max 7)
  VIT Bonus: +4% (Max 8)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Authentic Starlight Celebration MMXIII Advertisement
Description: A hand-painted notice advertising the Starlight Celebration of a year gone by.

Name: Authentic Starlight Sapling
Description: A tiny evergreen used to decorate homes during the Starlight Celebration. Painstakingly pruned to size for maximum authenticity.

Name: The Measure of Our Reach Orchestrion Roll
Description: Music roll for The Garlean Territorial Anthem for Gyr Abania and Surrounding States - The Measure of Our Reach. Use to add to your orchestrion list.

Name: Starlit Gateway Orchestrion Roll
Description: Music roll for Starlit Gateway. Use to add to your orchestrion list.

Description: An illustrated manual of one of the most basic stances in any military organization. Use to learn the /attention emote.

Name: Battlefield Etiquette - At Ease

Name: Byakko Totem
Description: It is unknown by whom or for what purpose this wooden idol carved in the likeness of the auspice Byakko was created.

Name: Sigmascape Lens
Description:
A uniquely crafted lens discovered in the Sigmascape.

Two lenses can be traded for special headgear.

Name: Sigmascape Shaft
Description:
A uniquely crafted shaft discovered in the Sigmascape.

Four shafts can be traded for special body gear.

Name: Sigmascape Crank
Description:
A uniquely crafted crank discovered in the Sigmascape.

Two cranks can be traded for special arm gear.

Name: Sigmascape Spring
Description:
A uniquely crafted spring discovered in the Sigmascape.

Four springs can be traded for special leg gear.

Name: Sigmascape Pedal
Description:
A uniquely crafted pedal discovered in the Sigmascape.

Two pedals can be traded for special foot gear.

Name: Sigmascape Chain
Description: A uniquely crafted chain discovered in the Sigmascape. Alas, advancements in trouser technology have rendered it worthless.

Name: Sigmascape Bolt
Description:
A uniquely crafted bolt discovered in the Sigmascape.

One bolt can be traded for a special accessory.

Name: Sigmascape Datalog v1.0
Description:
Detailed records of past battles waged in the Sigmascape.

Logs of the same type can be traded for special gear.

Name: Sigmascape Datalog v2.0
Description:
Detailed records of past battles waged in the Sigmascape.

Logs of the same type can be traded for special gear.

Name: Sigmascape Datalog v3.0
Description:
Detailed records of past battles waged in the Sigmascape.

Logs of the same type can be traded for special gear.

Name: Sigmascape Datalog v4.0
Description:
Detailed records of past battles waged in the Sigmascape.

Logs of the same type can be traded for special gear.

Name: Sigmascape Crystalloid
Description: A remarkable crystalline fragment within which can be seen images from another world. Though such articles were once considered highly valuable, demand has dried up, leaving them with little value as bartering materials.

Name: Ryumyaku Solvent
Description: A dissolving agent concocted by Doman artisans that, when applied to certain weapons, heightens their attributes by removing impurities on their surface. However, advances in crafting technology have rendered it obsolete.

Name: Ryumyaku Twine
Description: A durable thread used by Doman artisans. When woven into certain armor, it is believed to heighten its attributes. However, advances in crafting technology have rendered it obsolete.

Name: Ryumyaku Polish
Description: A slightly corrosive paste concocted by Doman goldsmiths that, when applied to certain accessories, heightens their attributes by restoring their luster. However, advances in crafting technology have rendered it obsolete.

Name: Rowena's Token (Mendacity)
Description: A note of promise received from Rowena for the delivery of Allagan tomestones of mendacity or poetics. However, due to the House of Splendors changing its policies, it is now worth less than the paper on which it is scribed.

Name: Prototype Tomestone
Description: Garlond Ironworks engineers believe this device to be an attempt by Allagan scientists to increase tomestone capacity, while keeping overall size relatively small. This may have become the next standard in tomestone data storage...had not their civilization been inconveniently wiped from the realm. This particular variety is not as highly sought as it once was, and may no longer be exchanged for other wares.

Name: Diamond Weapon Coffer (IL 375)
Description:
A heavy chest containing a diamond weapon.

Required level: 70. IL: 375. Weapon type determined by current job or class at time of opening. Cannot be opened in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.

Name: Shark-class Bow
Description: Comprising the front end of a shark-class submersible, this bow has been reinforced to double as a battering ram for subduing unruly sea creatures.

Name: Shark-class Bridge
Description: Comprising the top of a shark-class submersible, the bridge houses all of the equipment necessary for the vessel's crew to navigate the unplumbed depths of the Ruby Sea and beyond.

Name: Shark-class Pressure Hull
Description: Comprising the center of a shark-class submersible, this ovoid hull is multi-walled to stabilize and maintain pressure within so that the vessel's crew does not succumb to the crushing weight of the waters it navigates. Several sturdy rudder fins serve to increase maneuverability.

Name: Shark-class Stern
Description: Comprising the rear end of a shark-class submersible, this stern contains the unique independent engine which propels the craft.

Name: Unkiu-class Bow
Description: Unlike the bows of most submersibles, the unkiu-class model is outfitted with rudder fins usually relegated to the stern.

Name: Unkiu-class Bridge
Description: Designed by the Onishishua collective of skilled Far Eastern craftsmenthis submersible bridge differs dramatically in build from those built in the West.

Name: Unkiu-class Pressure Hull
Description: Comprising the center of an unkiu-class submersible, this ovoid hull is multi-walled to stabilize and maintain pressure within so that the vessel's crew does not succumb to the crushing weight of the waters it navigates. Supplemental propulsion engines have been affixed to the sides to increase underwater speed.

Name: Unkiu-class Stern
Description: Comprising the rear end of an unkiu-class submersible, this stern contains a double propeller engine.

Name: Glamour Prism
Description:
This crystalline prism captures the likeness of a piece of equipment and projects it onto another object of comparable form and function.

[Necessary to project glamours.]

Name: Protean Crystal
Description: The elemental energies of this unstable crystal are in a perpetual state of flux.

Name: Pazuzu's Feather
Description: A foul feather plucked from the Eurekan nightmare, Pazuzu.

Name: Anemos Crystal
Description: A crystal discovered in Eureka Anemosa region where the elemental aspect leans heavily to wind.

Name: Ornate True Linen Coat of Striking
Ornate True Linen Jacket of Aiming
Ornate True Linen Jacket of Scouting
Ornate True Linen Robe of Healing
Ornate True Linen Robe of Casting
Futon Mattress
Description: Common in the Far East, futons are thin down-filled mattresses laid directly on the floor instead of upon a frame. After use, they are generally rolled up and stored in a closet until needed again.

Name: Hatching-tide Banner
Description: An expertly woven tapestry displayed during Hatching-tide festivities.

Name: Odder Otter Lantern
Description: An indoor lantern designed to resemble the oddest of otters.

Name: Boar's Head Kadomatsu
Description: A Heavensturn decoration displayed at homes and places of business. The spinning umbrella is thought to bring fortune as long as an object remains atop.

Name: Moogle Wall Chronometer
Description: When faced with the dilemma of adorning his wall with a normal chronometer or a chronometer carved in the adorable likeness of a moogle, it is said the dread (though most likely nonexistent) pirate Mustbeard replied with a hearty arrr and found room for both.

Name: Byakko Sideboard
Description:
A round desk carved to resemble Byakko, one of the mystic Four Lords of the Far East.

One per estate only.

Name: Byakko Throne
Description:
A regal throne, fit for a king...or emperor that also happens to be a giant white tiger.

One per estate only.

Name: Stuffed Spriggan
Description: So realistic is this stuffed spriggan that many a mage has lost face after sending one up in a gout of sorcerous flame.

Name: Season Six Lone Wolf Trophy
Description: A trophy awarded to those who left their mark in Season Six of the Feast.

Name: Valentione's Day MMXIV Advertisement
Description: Without proper advertisement, some may mistake Valentione's Day for any other day, albeit one with far more pink balloons.

Name: Valentione's Day Balloons
Description: To create these festive balloons, the bladders of various flying fish caught in the Sea of Clouds were dried, colored, then stamped with the House Valentione coat of arms before being filled with heated air to keep them afloat.

Name: Bread Basket
Description:
Aromatic loaves of freshly baked bread fill this wicker basket to the brim.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Tenacity Bonus: +4% (Max 12)
  VIT Bonus: +4% (Max 8)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +2
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Stuffed Alpha
Description: A charming recreation of the chocobo Alpha, filled with the feathers of a fowl less fortunate.

Name: House Borel Tea Set
Description:
A faithful replication of the selfsame set used every morning by Aymeric de Borel himself.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Skill Speed Bonus: +4% (Max 12)
  VIT Bonus: +4% (Max 8)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +2
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Royal Dowager Tea Set
Description:
The design used on this quaint porcelain tea set is based off a passage in an ancient literary work on Halicarnassus, Queen of Dimension Castle.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Critical Hit Bonus: +4% (Max 12)
  VIT Bonus: +4% (Max 8)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +2
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Brick Interior Wall
Description: An interior wall built with genuine kiln-fired bricks.

Name: Mounted Cupboard
Description: A space-saving cupboard that can be mounted anywhere there is a wall.

Name: Vegetable Basket
Description: The vegetables contained within this basket have not been approved for consumption. Dine at your own risk.

Name: Open Partition
Description: A low partition cut with a hole to provide estates with the illusion of more space than actually exists.

Name: Counter Cart
Description: An island for kitchens designed to resemble those carts used by hawkers in city markets.

Name: Sharlayan Cabinet
Description: A decorative cabinet designed in the Old World Sharlayan style.

Name: Sharlayan Wardrobe
Description: A decorative wardrobe designed in the Old World Sharlayan style.

Name: Carbuncle Bathtub
Description: A small tub crafted to resemble a summoner's best friend. Just large enough for two.

Name: Chirurgeon's Essentials
Description: From scalpels to saws, panaceas to placebos, this basic set of medical devices has everything the unlicensed surgeon needs.

Name: Kitchen Hanger
Description: Save space in your cupboards for liquor and fruitcake by hanging all your kitchen appliances from hooks.

Name: Hanya Mask
Description: A frightening mask of Far Eastern design. Perfect for children's bedrooms and nurseries.

Name: Sake Set
Description: A set of Hingan bottles and cups perfect for taking one's evening refreshment with gueststhough using it to take one's afternoon refreshment alone is not unheard of.

Name: Stage Panel
Description: A large white panel used by acting troupes as a simple backdrop for plays.

Name: Stuffed Ananta
Description: Those without a deathly fear of snakes claim this plush doll to be one of the most beautiful ever crafted. Most ophidiophobes, however, would beg to differ.

Name: Tier 1 Metal Aquarium
Description:
A small, reinforced glass tank that, when filled with water, can serve as a home for select wavekin caught in the wild. The higher an aquarium's tier, the larger the specimens that can be kept within.
Private chambers (apartments), cottages, houses, and mansions can host 4, 6, 8, and 10 aquariums, respectively.

Name: Tier 2 Metal Aquarium
Description:
A reinforced glass tank that, when filled with water, can serve as a home for select wavekin caught in the wild. The higher an aquarium's tier, the larger the specimens that can be kept within.
Private chambers (apartments), cottages, houses, and mansions can host 4, 6, 8, and 10 aquariums, respectively.

Name: Eorzean Lantern
Description: Not one to be humbled by craftsmen of the East, a prominent Eorzean lamp maker conceived this fixture he hopes will become the new standard in home and garden lighting.

Name: Bomb Stove
Description: A cast-iron wood stove designed after a fateful encounter with a voidsent bomb.

Name: Hingan Pillar
Description: A decorative pillar designed in the Hingan fashion.

Name: Stack of Documents
Description: What better way to tell unwanted visitors, can't you see I'm busy? than by strewing stacks of important-looking documents all about your humble abode?

Name: Mummer's Maquillage
Description: Countless varieties of rouges, putties, and talcums commonly used by mummers to prepare themselves for their acts.

Name: Dress Hanger
Description: Because one wouldn't dare hang a dress on a coat hanger.

Name: Mummer's Wardrobe
Description: An oversized locker used by mummers to house not only their costumes, but their various tools of the trade.

Name: Far Eastern Doll Display
Description: A tiered dais used in the Far East to display dolls. Adapted in Eorzea for use on Little Ladies' Day.

Name: Coat Hanger
Description: Because one wouldn't dare hang a coat on a dress hanger.

Name: Altar to Pazuzu
Description: Make profane offerings from the comfort of your home with this sinister altar to the high voidsent Pazuzu.

Name: Hokonin Permit
Description:
This permit allows the hiring of Hingan servants known as hokonin on the estate.

Private chambers (apartments), cottages, houses, and mansions can host 4, 6, 8, and 10 vendors, respectively.

Name: Allagan Resupply Node Permit
Description:
This permit allows the renting of Allagan resupply nodes on the estate.

Private chambers (apartments), cottages, houses, and mansions can host 4, 6, 8, and 10 vendors, respectively.

Name: Allagan Commerce Node Permit
Description:
This permit allows the renting of Allagan commerce nodes on the estate.

Private chambers (apartments), cottages, houses, and mansions can host 4, 6, 8, and 10 vendors, respectively.

Name: Allagan Repair Node Permit
Description:
This permit allows the renting of Allagan repair nodes on the estate.

Private chambers (apartments), cottages, houses, and mansions can host 4, 6, 8, and 10 vendors, respectively.

Name: Allagan Housekeeping Node Permit
Description:
This permit allows the renting of Allagan housekeeping nodes on the estate.

Private chambers (apartments), cottages, houses, and mansions can host 4, 6, 8, and 10 vendors, respectively.

Name: Ananta Material Supplier Permit
Description:
This permit allows the hiring of Ananta material suppliers on the estate.

Private chambers (apartments), cottages, houses, and mansions can host 4, 6, 8, and 10 vendors, respectively.

Name: Ananta Junkmonger Permit
Description:
This permit allows the hiring of Ananta junkmongers on the estate.

Private chambers (apartments), cottages, houses, and mansions can host 4, 6, 8, and 10 vendors, respectively.

Name: Ananta Mender Permit
Description:
This permit allows the hiring of Ananta menders on the estate.

Private chambers (apartments), cottages, houses, and mansions can host 4, 6, 8, and 10 vendors, respectively.

Name: Ananta Maidservant Permit
Description:
This permit allows the hiring of Ananta maidservants on the estate.

Private chambers (apartments), cottages, houses, and mansions can host 4, 6, 8, and 10 vendors, respectively.

Name: Rose Wagon
Description: A pushcart filled with thousands upon thousands of fragrant roses (give or take a few thousand).

Name: Corner Hedge Partition
Description: A low-growing hedge, expertly pruned and trimmed into the shape of an L.

Name: Bamboo Copse
Description: A controlled cluster of bamboo cut from a Yanxian forest for display in private gardens.

Name: Hingan Hot Spring
Description: Scalding water tapped from the very bowels of the land, and collected in a quaint rock pool certain to draw the envy of neighbors.

Name: House Borel Interior Wall
Description: A wall that matches the design of those used in Aymeric de Borel's very manor.

Name: White Marble Flooring
Description: Smooth, elegant floor tiling made of polished marble.

Name: Classic Chandelier
Description: A lavish light fixture that hearkens to days long past.

Name: Melodious Mogchestrion
Description:
A fully functional moogle-themed orchestrion for the moogle-lover who has everything...but a fully functional moogle-themed orchestrion.

One orchestrion of any type per estate only.

Name: Authentic Paramour Vase
Description:
An authentic reproduction of the perfect way to say I love you without having your hands torn to shreds by thousands of prickly rose thorns.

Select flowers can be displayed within.

Name: Authentic Little Ladies' Day MMXVI Advertisement
Description: An authentic reproduction of one of hundreds of hand-drawn images posted about Ul'dah in preparation for Little Ladies' Day.

Name: Authentic Eastern Cherry Petal Pile
Description: There is nothing quite as ephemeral as a single pink cherry petal dancing in the wind as it makes its long descent from tree to earth, just as there is nothing quite as exhilarating as jumping in an authentic reproduction of a drift of tens of thousands of said petals.

Name: Authentic Eggstravagant Interior Wall
Description: An authentic reproduction of an interior wall designed to complement private Hatching-tide celebrations.

Name: Tulip Bulbs
Description:
Several hard, brown bulbs the size of a gigantoad's eye.

For use in planters.

Name: Red Tulips
Description:
A bunch of red tulips, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Blue Tulips
Description:
A bunch of blue tulips, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Yellow Tulips
Description:
A bunch of yellow tulips, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Green Tulips

Name: Black Tulips

Name: Rainbow Tulips
Description:
A bunch of multicolored tulips, selectively fertilized to achieve a variety of vibrant colors.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: The Destroyer Oil Painting
Description: An oil painting of the Destroyer based off notes compiled from your sightseeing log.

Name: Bloodstorm Oil Painting
Description: An oil painting of Bloodstorm based off notes compiled from your sightseeing log.

Description: An oil painting of the Yawn based off notes compiled from your sightseeing log.

Name: Imperial Hypersonic Assault Craft L-XXIII Oil Painting

Name: Mol Iloh Oil Painting
Description: An oil painting of Mol Iloh based off notes compiled from your sightseeing log.

Name: Moai Statue Oil Painting
Description: An oil painting of a moai statue based off notes compiled from your sightseeing log.

Name: Red Hare Horn
Description: This horn of bone emits a plangent tone that summons the Red Hare, warsteed of the great Ganen himself.

Name: Auspicious Kamuy Fife
Description: The prophetic song of this stout flute is said to summon a kamuy blessed by Lord Byakko himself.

Name: Marid Horn
Description: A horn of ivory used to summon a towering marid.

Name: Air Force Identification Key
Description: A thin, rectangular piece of what appears to be cermet. Placing it near your Air Force mobile assault unit will magically bring the machine to life.

Name: Magitek Death Claw Identification Key
Description: A thin, rectangular piece of what appears to be cermet. Placing it near your magitek death claw will magically bring the machine to life.

Name: Tyrannosaur Horn
Description: A rough-hewn horn of petrified bone that, when blown, emits a somber tone that summons a supposedly tamed tyrannosaur.

Name: Broken Heart Pendant (Right)
Description: When held aloft, this pendant magically summons half of a flying heart. The right half.

Name: Broken Heart Pendant (Left)
Description: When held aloft, this pendant magically summons half of a flying heart. The left half.

Name: Typhon Horn
Description: The sneeze-like blare of this horn summons Typhon, for reasons that no one knows and everyone refuses to find out.

Name: White Whittret
Description:
Once you pop...

Use item to acquire the white whittret minion.

Name: Wind-up Kefka
Description:
Just can't believe it? Believe it!

Use item to acquire the wind-up Kefka minion.

Name: Wind-up Ananta
Description:
Why did it have to be a snake?

Use item to acquire the wind-up Ananta minion.

Name: Motley Egg
Description:
The tiny Archon inside is certain to kickstart your heart.

Use item to acquire the motley egg minion.

Name: Wind-up Magnai
Description:
Ever in search of true love.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Magnai minion.

Name: Private Moai
Description:
It's watching you. Watching you. Watching you.

Use item to acquire the private moai minion.

Name: Wind-up Mithra
Description:
Opinions on how Miqo'te rate compared to their supposed ancestors are best kept to oneself.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Mithra minion.

Name: Wind-up Fafnir
Description:
Protective eyewear highly recommended.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Fafnir minion.

Name: The Prince of Anemos
Description:
Cute and cudgely.

Use item to acquire the Prince of Anemos minion.

Name: Byakko Cub
Description:
Got to be the fuzziest.

Use item to acquire the Byakko cub minion.

Name: Aurelia Polyp
Description:
Lighter than airer...water.

Use item to acquire the aurelia polyp minion.

Name: The Gold Whisker
Description:
Beckons you to enter his barrel of sin, but don't go in.

Use item to acquire the Gold Whisker minion.

Name: Komainu
Description:
Part lion, part dog, all lion-dog.

Use item to acquire the komainu minion.

Name: Byakko Barding
Description: A suit of chocobo armor designed to resemble the Far Eastern auspice Byakko.

Name: Chocobo Raincoat
Description: A light tarp designed to protect a chocobo from the rain...and not much else.

Name: Ananta Dreamstaff
Description: These magicked metal rods are used as currency by the Ananta.

Description:
This potent concoction gradually restores own HP.

Duration: 40s
Only available for use in the Forbidden Land, Eureka.

Name: Byakko's Mane
Description: The brilliant white mane of the Far Eastern white tiger of legend. He probably won't miss it.

Name: Alpha's Feather
Description: A single yellow feather fallen from the chocobo Alpha.

Name: Master Carpenter VI
Description: This esoteric tomethe sixth in an equally esoteric seriescontains advanced woodworking recipes that can only be learned by esoterically skilled carpenters.

Name: Master Blacksmith VI
Description: This esoteric tomethe sixth in an equally esoteric seriescontains advanced smithing recipes that can only be learned by esoterically skilled blacksmiths.

Name: Master Alchemist VI
Description: This esoteric tomethe sixth in an equally esoteric seriescontains advanced alchemy recipes that can only be learned by esoterically skilled alchemists.

Name: Master Culinarian VI
Description: This esoteric tomethe sixth in an equally esoteric seriescontains advanced cooking recipes that can only be learned by esoterically skilled culinarians.

Name: Dive Credit
Description: Permission issued by Kugane, allowing operation of privately owned submersibles within public waters. Depending on submersible size, and number of submersibles in possession, multiple credits may be required to register a new vehicle.

Name: Wrapped Present
Description:
A special gift from a special someone.

Cannot be opened in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.

Name: Strider Boots
Description: Increases sprint duration in city-states.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Salacious Sentiments
Description: An illustrated manual of vulgar reactions to lustful advances. Use to learn the /charmed emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Improper Praise (Cheer On: Blue)
Description: The first installment of a three-volume manual on how to express admiration in a manner unbefitting one of high birth. Use to learn the /cheeronblue emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Improper Praise (Cheer Wave: Yellow)
Description: The second installment of a three-volume manual on how to express admiration in a manner unbefitting one of high birth. Use to learn the /cheerwaveyellow emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Improper Praise (Cheer Jump: Red)
Description: The final installment of a three-volume manual on how to express admiration in a manner unbefitting one of high birth. Use to learn the /cheerjumpred emote.

Name: Mirage Mahi
Description:
A sizable catch found primarily in the freshwater highland rivers of Gyr Abania.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 3 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Triplespine
Description:
A deadly saltwater breed that protects itself with a pair of needle-like fins and a nigh-impenetrable coat of translucent scales.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Alligator Snapping Turtle
Description:
This land turtle can easily be identified by both its pointed shell and its powerful bite.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Redtail
Description:
A large freshwater fish that hassurprisea distinct red tail fin.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Usuginu Octopus
Description:
This crafty cephalopod can be found all along the Ruby Sea coastlineusually in the belly of some Hingan fisher who has eaten the creature raw and with a splash of soy sauce and citrus.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Saltmill
Description:
The saltmill is believed to be an ancient sea specimen which adapted to life in hypersalinated waters after being transplanted into Loch Seld after the Sixth Umbral Calamity.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Bonsai Fish
Description:
From afar, this freshwater fish can appear to be a piece of floating woodland debris. Up close, it looks like a fish.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Ribbon Eel
Description:
A unique petal-shaped maw and ribbon-like body distinguish this saltwater eel from more common varieties.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Red Prismfish
Description:
The pale red glow emitted by this freshwater fish is believed to be caused by unbalanced levels of aspected aether in the wavekin's humours.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Elder Gourami
Description:
Despite the beard-like ventral fins which give this freshwater wavekin an aged look, gourami only have an average lifespan of three to five summers.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Season Six Pack Wolf Voucher A
Description: Documentation of noteworthy accomplishments for Season Six of the Feast.

Name: Season Six Pack Wolf Voucher B
Description: Documentation of noteworthy accomplishments for Season Six of the Feast.

Name: Season Six Pack Wolf Voucher C
Description: Documentation of noteworthy accomplishments for Season Six of the Feast.

Name: Grey Hound Armor Coffer
Description:
A banded chest containing a complete set of grey hound armor.

Required level: 1. IL: 1. Cannot be opened in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.

Name: Old Valentione's Day Chocolate
Description: A less-than-fresh piece of rich milk chocolate resembling a rather more mottled House Valentione coat of arms.

Name: Certificate of Collaboration MMXVIII
Description: A small, square slip of parchment stamped with the Ul'dahn royal seneschal's seal proving your aid in the promotion of the Songbirds.

Name: Authentic Hatching-tide Banner
Description: An authentic reproduction of an expertly woven tapestry displayed during Hatching-tide festivities.

Name: Authentic Boar's Head Kadomatsu
Description: An authentic reproduction of the Heavensturn decoration displayed at homes and places of business.

Name: Authentic Valentione's Day MMXIV Advertisement
Description: An authentic reproduction of an official Valentione's Day announcement. Without proper advertisement, some may mistake Valentione's Day for any other day, albeit one with far more pink balloons.

Name: Authentic Valentione's Day Balloons
Description: An authentic reproduction of festive Valentione's Day balloons created by drying, coloring, then stamping the bladders of various flying fish caught in the Sea of Clouds with the House Valentione coat of arms. The bladders are then filled with heated air to keep them afloat.

Name: Authentic Far Eastern Doll Display
Description: An authentic reproduction of a tiered dais used in the Far East to display dolls. Adapted in Eorzea for use on Little Ladies' Day.

Name: Authentic Rose Wagon
Description: An authentic reproduction of a pushcart filled with thousands upon thousands of fragrant roses (give or take a few thousand).

Name: Magicked Prism (Hatching-tide)
Description: This peculiar contraption creates illusions by weaving together myriad shades of light. Used during Hatching-tide for celebratory purposes.

Name: Thavnairian Resin
Description: A long-lasting synthetic resin concocted by Radz-at-Han's finest alchemists. Used as both an adhesive as well as a varnish.

Name: Thavnairian Abrasive
Description: A coarse-grained abrasive concocted by Radz-at-Han's finest alchemists. Used to restore the luster of even the most corroded metals.

Name: Thavnairian Cotton
Description: A traditional Near Eastern weave that keeps its wearer cool while protecting her from the harsh rays of the sun.

Name: Thavnairian Alumen
Description: Quarried from Thavnair's towering sea cliffs, this mineral is prized by leatherworkers for its use in tanning hides.

Name: Thavnairian Adhesive
Description: Countless Hannish alchemists have chosen death over revealing the secret recipe of this odorless paste used in the creation of some of the island nation's most valuable armor.

Name: Nightsteel Ore
Description: Iron ore that has been exposed to the waters of a mineral spring, and undergone significant changes to both color and chemical makeup.

Name: Silvergrace Ore
Description: A sizable piece of rock containing traces of a precious metal known as silvergrace.

Name: Black Willow Log
Description: A rough-cut log of black willow timber.

Name: Hingan Flax
Description: A distant cousin to the flax found in the highlands of Coerthas, the stalk of this fibrous plant is used to create a yarn known in Hingashi as true linen.

Name: Ground Sloth Pelt
Description: The coarse, bristly hide of a giant ground sloth.

Name: Grade 3 Reisui of Strength
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this Far Eastern potation will, similarly to Eorzean dissolvents, dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to strength, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Grade 3 Reisui of Dexterity
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this Far Eastern potation will, similarly to Eorzean dissolvents, dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to dexterity, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Grade 3 Reisui of Vitality
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this Far Eastern potation will, similarly to Eorzean dissolvents, dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to vitality, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Grade 3 Reisui of Intelligence
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this Far Eastern potation will, similarly to Eorzean dissolvents, dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to intelligence, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Grade 3 Reisui of Mind
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this Far Eastern potation will, similarly to Eorzean dissolvents, dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to mind, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Nightsteel Ingot
Description: An ingot of smelted nightsteel.

Name: Silvergrace Ingot
Description: An ingot of smelted silvergrace.

Name: Black Willow Lumber
Description: Processed black willow lumber.

Name: Ground Sloth Leather
Description: A large piece of cured ground sloth hide.

Name: Spriggan Chocolate
Description:
A small piece of bitter dark chocolate molded into the shape of a spriggan.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Tako-yaki
Description:
Bite-sized balls of fried pastry each containing a solitary chunk of tender octopus in their gooey, molten centers.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Futo-maki Roll
Description:
Crisp dried seaweed and sweet vinegared rice rolled around a smorgasbord of sweet and savory fillings. Thought to bring fortune...or at least end hunger.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Oden
Description:
A veritable hodgepodge of vegetables, meats, and seafood simmered in a light fish broth for literally days upon end.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Dzo Steak
Description:
A thick cut of dzo sirloin sprinkled with salt and seared to perfection.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Crimson Cider
Description:
Official beverage of both the Ala Mhigan Resistance and the Doman Liberation Front, or so cider brewers would have you believe.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Sauteed Green Leeks
Description:
A simple dish of thick, meaty leeks sauted with garlic.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Dzo Sirloin
Description: A remarkably lean slice of red meat from the back of a steppe-grazing dzo.

Name: Doman Rice
Description: A hardy hybrid of sweet, sticky rice perfected by Far Eastern farmers after countless generations of cross-pollination. Known in Yanxia as Doman Sunrise.

Name: Hedge Partition
Description: A low-growing hedge, oft used to create natural barriers around homes.

Name: Crimson Coral
Description: A deep red piece of rare coral native to the Ruby Sea.

Name: Colossus Slab
Description: This piece of carved stone appears to have once been part of a large statue.

Name: Khloe's Gold Certificate of Commendation
Description: An extra-special award presented to you by Khloe Aliapoh. Try not to mind the numerous misspellings and juice stains.

Name: Khloe's Silver Certificate of Commendation
Description: A relatively special award presented to you by Khloe Aliapoh. Try not to mind the numerous misspellings and juice stains.

Name: Tofu Pancakes
Description:
The adding of tofu results in a light, fluffy pancake that is cherished by families across Doma.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Honeydew Honey
Description: Instead of from collecting pollen, this deep, flavorful variety of honey is made from bees collecting honeydew excreted by the aphids that gather on the flowers.

Name: Grade 2 Infusion of Strength
Description:
This diluted brew temporarily increases strength, but for twice the duration of similar potions.

Duration: 30s

Name: Grade 2 Infusion of Dexterity
Description:
This diluted brew temporarily increases dexterity, but for twice the duration of similar potions.

Duration: 30s

Name: Grade 2 Infusion of Vitality
Description:
This diluted brew temporarily increases vitality, but for twice the duration of similar potions.

Duration: 30s

Name: Grade 2 Infusion of Intelligence
Description:
This diluted brew temporarily increases intelligence, but for twice the duration of similar potions.

Duration: 30s

Name: Grade 2 Infusion of Mind
Description:
This diluted brew temporarily increases mind, but for twice the duration of similar potions.

Duration: 30s

Description: Fits: All

Description: Fits: All

Description: Fits: All

Description: Fits: All

Description: Fits: All

Name: True Griffin Horn
Description: A beautifully carved horn that summons a true griffin trained since birth to carry riders on her back.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Secrets of the Fist
Description: An illustrated manual of how to perform the ancient Fist of Rhalgr battle dance made popular by Lyse. Use to learn the /crimsonlotus emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Calamitous Endings
Description: An illustrated manual of how to mimic the summoning motions of the dreadwyrm Bahamut. Use to learn the /megaflare emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Unseemly Exertions
Description: An illustrated manual of how not to compose yourself after extended bouts of strenuous activities. Use to learn the /winded emote.

Name: Holy Linen
Description: This length of true linen has been blessed by one or more religious figures of varying holiness.

Name: Ala Mhigan Weave
Description: Cloth woven using traditional techniques that date back to the Fifth Astral Era.

Name: Babbling Brook Orchestrion Roll
Description: Music roll of the soothing babbling of a countryside brook. Use to add to your orchestrion list.

Name: Bustling Boulevard Orchestrion Roll
Description: Music roll of the soothing bustle of a busy boulevard. Use to add to your orchestrion list.

Name: Temple Bell Orchestrion Roll
Description: Music roll of the soothing toll of a temple bell. Use to add to your orchestrion list.

Name: Chapel Bell Orchestrion Roll
Description: Music roll of the soothing toll of a chapel bell. Use to add to your orchestrion list.

Name: Cyan's Theme Orchestrion Roll
Description: Music roll for Cyan's Theme. Use to add to your orchestrion list.

Name: Iroha Orchestrion Roll
Description: Music roll for Iroha. Use to add to your orchestrion list.

Name: Daring Dalliances Orchestrion Roll
Description: Music roll for Daring Dalliances. Use to add to your orchestrion list.

Name: Prelude - Long March Home Orchestrion Roll

Description:
A message book stand designed in the likeness of a dodo. Not likely to regurgitate on whatever you place upon it.

One per estate only.

Description: Use to immediately add 5,000 MGP to your Manderville Gold Saucer account.

Name: Whale-class Bow
Description: Comprising the front end of a whale-class submersible, this bow offers special protection against undersea volcanic eruptions. Theoretically.

Description: Comprising the top of a whale-class submersible, this bridge improves on the depth rating of other models, allowing submersibles equipped with it to delve even further.

Name: Whale-class Stern

Name: Solid-brick Interior Wall

Name: Unfinished Wood Flooring

Name: Odder Otter Hanging Andon Lamp

Description:
A set of four walls for those who wish to make their homes a bit odder.

Can only be used with cottages on small plots of land.

Name: Odder Otter House Walls
Description:
A set of four walls for those who wish to make their homes somewhat odder.

Can only be used with houses on medium plots of land.

Name: Odder Otter Mansion Walls
Description:
A set of four walls for those who wish to make their homes much odder.

Can only be used with mansions on large plots of land.

Name: Merry Mog Bed

Name: Odder Otter Dining Table

Description: A screen with an odder otter motif.

Description: A chair with an odder otter motif.

Name: Season Seven Lone Wolf Trophy
Description: A trophy awarded to those who left their mark in Season Seven of the Feast.

Name: Stuffed Tsukuyomi
Description:
Like the real Tsukuyomi, she looks as if she needs a hug. Unlike the real Tsukuyomi, she will not slice you in half if you try.

One per estate only.

Name: Falcons Banner
Description: Show your undying support for the Falcons with this authentic banner.

Name: Ravens Banner
Description: Show your undying support for the Ravens with this authentic banner.

Name: Disordered Wardrobe

Name: Assorted Candles

Name: Glade Bachelor's Chest
Description: A compact chest of drawers designed to complement glade residences.

Name: Portable Stepladder

Name: Glade Partition Door

Name: Oasis Partition Door
Description: A partition with a built-in door designed to complement oasis residences.

Name: Wine Glass
Description: Merely placing this glass in any home adds a veneer of sophistication.

Name: Bar Counter

Name: Bar Stool
Description: A stool to sit on, and tumble off of.

Name: Trouser Hanger

Name: Sumptuous Dimension Castle Vase

Name: Imposing Dimension Castle Vase

Name: Stuffed Namazu

Name: Season Eight Lone Wolf Trophy
Description: A trophy awarded to those who left their mark in Season Eight of the Feast.

Name: Empyrean Shrine
Description: Small shrines such as this are said to mark the boundaries between our world and the heavens.

Name: Basket of Steamed Buns
Description:
Meat buns so fresh that they have yet to be removed from the steaming basket.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Determination Bonus: +4% (Max 7)
  VIT Bonus: +4% (Max 8)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +2
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Indoor BBQ Spit

Description:
Very punny.

Use item to hire a Palico minion.

Beloved by hunters, though the feeling is not always mutual.

Description: This unsettling metal totem of unknown origin depicts the Ultima Weapon as if it were a god.

Name: Doyen's Clan Mark Log
Description: A list of highly elite marks documented by the log's owner. It is unclear whether the marks within were ever slain by said owner, but the overuse of modifiers such as ghastly, terrifying, and beyond all horrors that haunt the sleeping mind in their descriptions suggests perhaps not. Though such documents were once considered highly valuable, demand has dried up and they are now essentially worthless.

Name: Empyrean Reliquary
Description: A holy vessel discovered in Heaven-on-High. The contents are doubtless of great value to the spiritually inclined...unless you have pulverized them by unceremoniously stowing the vessel in your bag, that is.

Name: Stormsap
Description: The chemical composition of this milky violet liquid is unknown, but its colorreminiscent of a thundercloud illuminated by lightninghas given rise to rumors surrounding its origins that have led to the unfortunate electrocution of many a scholar and profiteer alike.

Name: Hawk's Eye
Description: A blue-grey jewel consisting of many colored layers. When polished, it resembles the piercing eye of a raptor.

Name: Hardened Veteran Tree Sap
Description: A partially congealed ball of sticky sap extracted from an aged tree.

Name: Kingcraft Demimateria
Description: A crystallized mass of residual spiritbond energies transferred to an article of weaponry or armor by its exceptionally skilled maker during the crafting process.

Name: Duskglow Aethersand
Description: The elementally aspected remnants of aetherially reduced matter. This fine sand emits a crepuscular glow independent of ambient light.

Name: Hawk's Eye Sand
Description: Conversion of the mineral hawk's eye via an alchemical process is the only way to create this incomparably fine sand.

Name: Veteran Tree Sap
Description: This sap has been reverted from hardened lumps to its original liquid state via an alchemical process.

Name: Konpeito
Description:
Colorful clusters of crystalline sugara childhood treat for Hingans and Domans alike.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Banh Xeo
Description:
A traditional Nagxian dish consisting of meat and vegetables swaddled in a thin shell of crispy fried batter.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Matcha
Description:
A sophisticatedly bitter infusion prepared by whisking fine-ground tea leaves into piping hot water. Drinking it properly requires such finesse that Hingashi is home to many a school focused solely on perfecting the art.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Ema Datshi
Description:
Rich, oozing cheese complements the seething bite of inferno-hot peppers in this Azim Steppe staple.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Handking's Tool Belt
Description: Before becoming obsolete due to advancements in tailoring, belts such as this were used for holding up trousers and the like.

Name: Landking's Survival Belt
Description: Before becoming obsolete due to advancements in tailoring, belts such as this were used for holding up trousers and the like.

Name: Celestial Kimono Remnant
Description: This length of fabric was cut from the Lady of the Moon's own kimono.

Name: Resistance Token
Description: Used by the Ala Mhigan Resistance to verify the submission of battle gear.

Name: Wooden Hakutaku Eye
Description: A ligneous eyeball of the legendary Hakutaku. Rumor has it that its sight will be restored when immersed in blood.

Name: Burning Hakutaku Eye
Description: A fiery eyeball of the legendary Hakutaku. Rumor has it that its sight will be restored when immersed in blood.

Name: Earthen Hakutaku Eye
Description: A soiled eyeball of the legendary Hakutaku. Rumor has it that its sight will be restored when immersed in blood.

Name: Golden Hakutaku Eye
Description: A lustrous eyeball of the legendary Hakutaku. Rumor has it that its sight will be restored when immersed in blood.

Name: Damp Hakutaku Eye
Description: A dripping eyeball of the legendary Hakutaku. Rumor has it that its sight will be restored when immersed in blood.

Name: Hakutaku Eye Cluster
Description: A cluster of eyes from a legendary beast, the Hakutaku. The eyes are slowly yet steadily growing in number as they divide via mitosis.

Name: Speed Belt
Description:
Before becoming obsolete due to advancements in tailoring, belts such as this were used for holding up trousers and the like. This particular design, however, has retained some modicum of value, or so the Calamity salvagers appear to believe.

[Can be exchanged with Calamity salvagers for a blitzring.]

Name: Yanxian Soil
Description: Fine, rich earth from Yanxia.

Name: Yanxian Verbena
Description: A hearty plant that can proliferate on nearly any surface, including tree trunks. Its leaves release a pleasant scent when touched.

Name: Marine Wax Ester
Description: A saturated wax ester harvested from the fathomless abyss.

Name: Silver-haloed Sack
Description: This radiant bag containing a portion of Heaven-on-High's Accursed Hoard has been sealed with powerful magicks. Only an appraiser almost suspiciously well versed in the dispelling of hexes might be able to undo such a seal.

Name: Gold-haloed Sack
Description: This radiant bag containing a portion of Heaven-on-High's Accursed Hoard has been sealed with powerful magicks. Only an appraiser almost suspiciously well versed in the dispelling of hexes might be able to undo such a seal.

Name: Platinum-haloed Sack
Description: This radiant bag containing a portion of Heaven-on-High's Accursed Hoard has been sealed with powerful magicks. Only an appraiser almost suspiciously well versed in the dispelling of hexes might be able to undo such a seal.

Name: Empyrean Pine Log
Description: Though this was perhaps once a run-of-the-mill cutting of timber, it has since been warped in the oddest of ways by exposure to the powerful magicks of Heaven-on-High.

Name: Empyrean Clay
Description: Though this was perhaps once unremarkable mud, it has since been warped in the oddest of ways by exposure to the powerful magicks of Heaven-on-High.

Name: Stuffed Happy Bunny
Description: This plush rabbit is so realistic that it is rumored to bring fortune, just like a real happy bunny would, to all who come across it. All except those who are prone to allergies, anyway.

Name: Journeyman Salvager Permit
Description:
This permit allows the hiring of journeyman salvagers on the estate.

Private chambers (apartments), cottages, houses, and mansions can host 4, 6, 8, and 10 vendors, respectively.

Frosted Protean Crystal
Description: Hastily forged from the aspected aether of slain beasts, this crystal quickly accumulated a fragile veneer of ice when exposed to the frigid air of Pagos. Its energies have yet to settleif indeed they ever will.

Name: Whalaqee Off-guard Totem
Description:
An intricately carved wooden totem imbued with the secrets of a defense-shattering technique.

Only for use by blue mages.

Name: Whalaqee Transfusion Totem
Description:
An intricately carved wooden totem imbued with the secrets of a self-sacrificial support technique.

Only for use by blue mages.

Name: Whalaqee Mighty Guard Totem
Description:
An intricately carved wooden totem imbued with the secrets of a protective technique.

Only for use by blue mages.

Name: Whalaqee Moon Flute Totem
Description:
An intricately carved wooden totem imbued with the secrets of an offense-boosting technique.

Only for use by blue mages.

Name: Whalaqee Doom Totem
Description:
An intricately carved wooden totem imbued with the secrets of a life-ending technique.

Only for use by blue mages.

Name: Ambient Wind Chime Orchestrion Roll
Description: Music roll of the soothing tintinnabulation of an oriental wind chime. Use to add to your orchestrion list.

Name: Ambient Abyss Orchestrion Roll
Description: Music roll of the soothing sound of the cobalt deep. Use to add to your orchestrion list.

Name: Wayward Daughter Orchestrion Roll
Description: Music roll for Wayward Daughter. Use to add to your orchestrion list.

Name: Rise of the White Raven (Orchestral Version) Orchestrion Roll
Description: Music roll for Rise of the White Raven (Orchestral Version). Use to add to your orchestrion list.

Name: Revenge Twofold (Orchestral Version) Orchestrion Roll
Description: Music roll for Revenge Twofold (Orchestral Version). Use to add to your orchestrion list.

Name: Oblivion (Orchestral Version) Orchestrion Roll
Description: Music roll for Oblivion (Orchestral Version). Use to add to your orchestrion list.

Name: Faded Copy of Under the Moonlight
Description: Timeworn pages of sheet music containing full scores for Nightbloom and Wayward Daughter.

Name: Faded Copy of Ambient Abyss
Description: Timeworn pages of sheet music containing a full panoply of the ambient melodies one might expect to hear under the sea.

Name: Authentic Moonfire Faire MMXIV Advertisement
Description: An authentic reprint of a faithful depiction of summer's hottest festival so that you may feel the heat year-round.

Name: Authentic Evercold Shaved Ice
Description:
Authentic thinly shaved ice, generously heaped into an authentic oversmall bowl and drizzled with sweet-yet-tangy rolanberry syrup...authentically. Why it never melts is a question best served cold.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  VIT Bonus: +4% (Max 11)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +1
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Authentic Rising Balloon
Description: The bladder of some poor beast, colored with dye and filled with lighter-than-air gas to dazzle the young and the young at heart come the Rising. So authentic to the previous year's balloons that you can almost smell it.

Name: Behemoth Pelt
Description: The no longer glossy, yet still massive, coat of a behemoth.

Name: Lizard Tail
Description: In defiance of all logic and natural laws, this tail is still partly alive, and twitches occasionally. Delightful.

Name: Reishi Mushroom
Description: This rare mushroom is known for its high nutritive content...and not much else.

Name: Pagos Spring Water
Description: Clear, cool water taken from a spring in the Pagos region of Eureka.

Name: Pagos Sage
Description: A fragrant herb that can be used medicinally or to add a pleasant flavor to cuisine. The variety found in Pagos is notably crisp and hearty.

Name: Potion of Harmony
Description:
This innovative alchemical concoction assists the body in acclimating to Eureka's discordant aetheric environment.

Elemental EXP Bonus: +10%  Duration: 60m (if HQ, 90m)
Only available for use in the Forbidden Land, Eureka.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - The Box Step
Description: An illustrated manual of the various steps that comprise the box step. Use to learn the /boxstep emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - The Side Step
Description: An illustrated manual of the various steps that comprise the side step. Use to learn the /sidestep emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Ultima
Description: An illustrated manual of how to obliterate your enemies in style when pushed to the brink of annihilation. Use to learn the /ultima emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - The Yol Dance
Description: An illustrated manual of the various steps that comprise a traditional dance of the Oronir tribe. Use to learn the /yoldance emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Excessive Petticoats
Description: An illustrated manual of how to cool oneself with at least some semblance of dignity after a rousing circuit of the dance floor. Use to learn the /sweat emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Insufficient Petticoats
Description: An illustrated manual of how not to conduct oneself while trapped on the balcony with an indefatigable admirer in the evening hours. Use to learn the /shiver emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Stimulating Soliloquies
Description: An illustrated manual of how to confidently explain a matter in excruciating detail, regardless of whether anyone asked. Use to learn the /elucidate emote.

Name: Modern Aesthetics - Gyr Abanian Plait
Description:
The realm's premier publication on beauty and fashion, this specific copy of Modern Aesthetics covers, in detail, techniques on braiding hair in the traditional Ala Mhigan fashiona style that was popular until the imperial invasion.

Use to unlock a new hairstyle at the aesthetician.
Unavailable to female Hrothgar.

Name: Modern Aesthetics - Fashionably Feathered
Description:
The realm's premier publication on beauty and fashion, this specific copy of Modern Aesthetics covers, in detail, techniques for styling short hair using only a razor (and copious amounts of wax).

Use to unlock a new hairstyle at the aesthetician.

Name: Oroniri Cloth
Description: The dyeing techniques used to color this bolt of cloth are unique to the Oronir.

Name: Dotharli Cloth
Description: The dyeing techniques used to color this bolt of cloth are unique to the Dotharl.

Name: Cloth Cointe Quaint
Description: No real lady of fashion would be caught dead wearing a skirt orheavens forfenda dress made from anything else.

Name: Leather Cointe Quaint
Description: No real lady of fashion would be caught dead wearing a hat orheavens forfendshoes made from anything else.

Name: Boutique Batiste
Description: No real gentleman of fashion would be caught dead wearing a shirt orheavens forfendpants made from anything else.

Name: Boutique Boarded Leather
Description: No real gentleman of fashion would be caught dead wearing a hat orheavens forfendshoes made from anything else.

Name: Cold-warped Lockbox
Description: A firmly sealed box discovered deep in the Pagos wilds, its shape made irregular by prolonged exposure to the elements. Only a skilled picker of locks might grant you access to the treasure within.

Name: Endless Summer Coffer
Description:
A banded chest containing a complete set of Endless Summer attire.

Required level: 1. IL: 1. Cannot be opened in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.

Name: Rising Token MMXVIII
Description: An official voucher issued to participants in the Calamity Retold. Celebrate Eorzea's rebirth by trading for fabulous prizes!

Name: Thavnairian Rain
Description: A highly concentrated elixir blended in the Near Eastern island nation of Radz-at-Han.

Name: Rathalos Scale+
Description: Rare Rathalos material. Mostly obtained by carving. Broadly used for many purposes. - Words from an impressively terse tracker of beasts, as recorded in Wisdom of the Hunters.
