Name: Mannequin
Description:
Once the nightmare of shopkeeps alone, highly detailed models such as this one have gained popularity amongst adventurers as means of selling unneeded accoutrements, displaying hard-won ensembles, and unnerving unsuspecting visitors.

Private chambers (apartments), cottages, houses, and mansions can hold 4, 6, 8, and 10 facilities, respectively.

Name: Magicked Prism (Hearts)
Description: This peculiar contraption creates illusions by weaving together myriad shades of light. Produces a shower of translucent hearts.

Name: Magicked Prism (Glassy Wings)
Description: This peculiar contraption creates illusions by weaving together myriad shades of light. Produces a pair of ethereal wings reminiscent of cathedral glass.

Name: Chocobo Round Table
Description: A round table for all the chocobo- and food-lovers out there.

Name: Chocobo Chair
Description: A chair for all of (well, one of) the chocobo-lovers out there.

Name: Odder Otter Round Andon Lamp
Description: A tall indoor lamp with an odder otter motif.

Name: Chocobo Dining Table
Description: A large dining table for all the chocobo-, food-, and chocobo-as-food-lovers out there.

Name: Season Nine Lone Wolf Trophy
Description: A trophy awarded to those who left their mark in Season Nine of the Feast.

Name: Season Ten Lone Wolf Trophy
Description: A trophy awarded to those who left their mark in Season Ten of the Feast.

Name: Pot of Cream Stew
Description:
A warming dish of familiar vegetables simmered for bells in a rich sauce of thickened milk.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Spell Speed Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  VIT Bonus: +4% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +2
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Suzaku Wall Hanging
Description:
An elegant relief depicting one of the Four Lords, alive with dancing flame.

One per estate only.

Name: Doman Dogwood
Description: A sizable potted tree, perpetually in bloom with redolent magenta flowers.

Name: Enclave Map
Description: An artistic ink rendering of the spectacularly reconstructed Doman Enclave.

Name: Heavensturn Bounty
Description: A traditional Heavensturn decoration meant to beckon fortune through its depiction of a traditional bumper crop of rice, traditionally infested by mice.

Name: Pumpkin Party Pennants
Description: A festive wall decoration dominated by All Saints' Wake motifs. If one did not know better than to suspect the troupe of trickery, one might think this reward merely a hastily assembled hodgepodge of spare party decorations.

Name: Pumpkin Pastry Platter
Description:
In the spirit of All Saints' Wake, each of these pastries is pumpkin-flavored...except for the pumpkin-shaped one, which was deemed thematically sufficient regardless. Also in the spirit of All Saints' Wake, there are more of them than is advisable to consume in one sitting.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Critical Hit Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  VIT Bonus: +4% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +2
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Familiar Pawprints
Description: An adhesive wall decoration to make any witches in your company this All Saints' Wake feel at home.

Name: Silver Starlight Sentinel
Description: A potted conifer displayed in homes during the Starlight Celebration. Its snowy color will make your dcor sumptuousand your gatherings lively as you argue with friends and neighbors over whether it is superior to the more traditional green.

Name: Starlight Donuts
Description:
Festive treats for those who prefer to express their Starlight spirit through eating until they lose consciousness.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Piety Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  VIT Bonus: +4% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +2
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Evercold Starlight Snowman
Description: This indoor frosty snowman will never melt away. He'll be there forever. Watching. Waiting.

Name: Opened Twinkleboxes
Description: The detritus of many happy Starlight Celebration surprises.

Name: Redoubtable Rolanberry Tart
Description:
A flaky-crusted tart with a slight acidity that complements its pleasant sweetness, so enormous that it should only be served at parties. Of course, sometimes a party can be just one hungry homeowner and a clean fork. Or a dirty one. It doesn't really matter.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Tenacity Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  VIT Bonus: +4% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +2
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Crystal Boule
Description: A mounted sample of the luminous euhedral crystals that grow uninhibited on the sea floor.

Name: Gridanian Bouquet
Description: An elegant bouquet for romantic occasions, each bloom painstakingly selected by the florist Tanie.

Name: Imitation Shuttered Window
Description: Unlike those attached to non-imitation windows, these louvered shutters will ever remain pristine as they add a touch of the rustic to your interior dcor.

Name: Little Chef's Playset
Description: This set for aspiring culinary artists includes soft, child-safe replicas of everything one might need in the kitchen, including a helpful Miqo'te poissonnier.

Name: Wooden Showcase
Description: Spare a thought for the poor carpenter who toiled to make this furnishing both simple and elegant as you inevitably pile as many objects as physically possible atop its shelves.

Name: Unfinished Shawl
Description: A knitter's work is never done. In this case, literally.

Name: Adventuring Pack
Description: An adventurer never leaves home without his compass! And his waterskin. And his lantern. And his potions. And his telescope. And his books. Really, an adventurer needs to learn to pack a bit lighter.

Name: Spice Rack
Description: This storage unit is packed with enough spices, herbs, oils, and other ingredients to satisfy even the most dedicated culinarian.

Name: Bread Rack
Description: One could raise an entire army of ducks with this much bread. Hypothetically.

Name: Mahogany Bunk Bed
Description: For weary adults who have spent overmuch on alligator pears and cannot afford to live alone.

Name: Handbasket
Description: A large and lovely woven vessel. Be advised that if a Lalafell fits in it, she will sits in it.

Name: Strewn Smallclothes
Description: Home is where the heap of unfolded undergarments is.

Name: Strewn Bottoms
Description: There's no better way to vaunt your wealth than buying three nearly identical pairs of trousers and refusing to wear any of them.

Name: Glass Jars
Description: Opaque vessels of assorted size, perhaps containing flour and sugar. Or cookies. Or bugs.

Name: Wooden Plates
Description: Dishes for those with simple tastes and many friends.

Name: Wooden Cups
Description: A half-dozen goblets for fancy parties. Cupbearer not included.

Name: Mounted Plate Rack
Description: A sturdy wooden display. For the good plates, not the food plates.

Name: Verdant Partition
Description: A lush partition covered floor-to-ceiling in ivy and assorted ferns.

Name: Bathroom Floor Tiles
Description: A large square of cerulean tiling with a built-in drain.

Name: Bathroom Wall Tiles
Description: A square of tiling used to prevent walls from becoming so waterlogged that the house slowly but surely collapses in on itself.

Name: Towels
Description: Such neatly folded and extraordinarily fluffy towels can only have been purloined from an expensive inn.

Name: Sofa Cushions
Description: Does one truly require a sofa if he has this many pillows?

Name: Birdbath
Description: An elegant two-tiered water feature. Perhaps doubting that potential purchasers would be patient enough to wait for real ones to appear, the sculptor helpfully attached model birds as well.

Name: Garden Gravel
Description: Myriad tiny rocks that await your landscaping pleasure.

Name: Brick Garden Circle
Description: All these squares make a circle.

Name: Carpeting
Description: Durable yet fuzzy loop carpet with a checkerboard pattern.

Name: Divine Chandelier
Description: A contemporary light fixture designed with the Twelve as its primary theme.

Name: Unfinished Interior Wall
Description: An interior wall of pale unvarnished wood.

Name: Coelacanth-class Bow
Description: Comprising the front end of a coelacanth-class submersible, this streamlined bow is designed to allow a vessel to reach greater speeds underwater.

Name: Coelacanth-class Bridge
Description: Comprising the top of a coelacanth-class submersible, this bridge is expansive and equipped with amenities to enable longer voyages.

Name: Coelacanth-class Pressure Hull
Description: Comprising the center of a coelacanth-class submersible, this ovoid hull is designed to be resilient against external water pressure and thereby raises maximum operating depth.

Name: Coelacanth-class Stern
Description: Comprising the rear end of a coelacanth-class submersible, this stern includes a hydrodynamic rudder for optimal lateral maneuverability.

Name: Suzaku Totem
Description: It is unknown by whom or for what purpose this wooden idol carved in the likeness of the auspice Suzaku was created.

Name: Alphascape Lens
Description:
A uniquely crafted lens discovered somewhere within the Interdimensional Rift.

Two lenses can be traded for special headgear.

Name: Alphascape Shaft
Description:
A uniquely crafted shaft discovered somewhere within the Interdimensional Rift.

Four shafts can be traded for special body gear.

Name: Alphascape Crank
Description:
A uniquely crafted crank discovered somewhere within the Interdimensional Rift.

Two cranks can be traded for special arm gear.

Name: Alphascape Spring
Description:
A uniquely crafted spring discovered somewhere within the Interdimensional Rift.

Four springs can be traded for special leg gear.

Name: Alphascape Pedal
Description:
A uniquely crafted pedal discovered somewhere within the Interdimensional Rift.

Two pedals can be traded for special foot gear.

Name: Alphascape Chain
Description: A uniquely crafted chain discovered somewhere within the Interdimensional Rift. Alas, advancements in trouser technology have rendered it worthless.

Name: Alphascape Bolt
Description:
A uniquely crafted bolt discovered somewhere within the Interdimensional Rift.

One bolt can be traded for a special accessory.

Name: Alphascape Datalog v1.0
Description:
Detailed records of past battles waged somewhere within the Interdimensional Rift.

Logs of the same type can be traded for special gear.

Name: Alphascape Datalog v2.0
Description:
Detailed records of past battles waged somewhere within the Interdimensional Rift.

Logs of the same type can be traded for special gear.

Name: Alphascape Datalog v3.0
Description:
Detailed records of past battles waged somewhere within the Interdimensional Rift.

Logs of the same type can be traded for special gear.

Name: Alphascape Datalog v4.0
Description:
Detailed records of past battles waged somewhere within the Interdimensional Rift.

Logs of the same type can be traded for special gear.

Name: Alphascape Crystalloid
Description: A remarkable crystalline fragment within which can be seen images from another world. Though such articles were once considered highly valuable, demand has dried up, leaving them with little value as bartering materials.

Name: Scaevan Ester
Description: A lubricant concocted by a certain Garlond Ironworks consultant that, when applied to weapons of similar origin, heightens their attributes by smoothing interactions between their many interlocking parts. However, advances in crafting technology have rendered it obsolete.

Name: Scaevan Twine
Description: A sturdy fiber devised by a certain Garlond Ironworks consultant for the purpose of heightening the attributes of armor of his own design. However, advances in crafting technology have rendered it obsolete.

Name: Scaevan Shellac
Description: A fixing agent concocted by a certain Garlond Ironworks consultant that, when applied to accessories of similar origin, heightens their attributes by rebuffing vapor penetration and insulating delicate internal mechanisms. However, advances in crafting technology have rendered it obsolete.

Name: Rowena's Token (Genesis)
Description: A note of promise received from Rowena for the delivery of Allagan tomestones of genesis or poetics. However, due to the House of Splendors changing its policies, it is now worth less than the paper on which it is scribed.

Name: Military-grade Tomestone
Description: The exacting specifications to which this tomestone was made, along with its half-deciphered contents, have led Ironworks engineers to believe that it was manufactured for exclusive use by the Allagan armed forces. This particular variety is not as highly sought as it once was, and may no longer be exchanged for other wares.

Name: Omega Weapon Coffer (IL 405)
Description:
A heavy chest containing an Omega weapon.

Required level: 70. IL: 405. Weapon type determined by current job or class at time of opening. Cannot be opened in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.

Name: SDS Fenrir Key
Description: A thin key that brings the beastly vehicle Fenrir roaring to life.

Name: Grani Horn
Description: A stygian horn that, when blown, summons the otherworldly steed Grani.

Name: Fatter Cat Bugle
Description: This horn emits a playful honk that calls a rotund-yet-sprightly feline to your side.

Name: Euphonious Kamuy Fife
Description: The melodious song of this stout flute is said to summon a kamuy blessed by Lady Suzaku herself.

Name: Model O Identification Key
Description: A thin, rectangular piece of some unknown alloy. Placing it near your Model O will magically bring the machine to life.

Name: Magitek Sky Armor Identification Key
Description: A thin, rectangular piece of what appears to be cermet. Placing it near your magitek sky armor will magically bring the machine to life.

Name: Magna Roader Identification Key
Description: A thin, rectangular piece of what appears to be cermet. Placing it near your magna roader will bring it roaring terrifyingly to life.

Name: Fat Black Chocobo Whistle
Description: A small hand-carved whistle that emits a high-pitched tone recognized as a feeding call by the fat black chocobo.

Name: Scarlet Peacock
Description:
Prettier than your average peacock, and several times as flammable.

Use item to acquire the scarlet peacock minion.

Name: Wind-up Alpha
Description:
Kweh-ing along under some distant sky.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Alpha minion.

Name: OMG
Description:
Weird. Technological. Fascinating.

Use item to acquire the OMG minion.

Name: Wind-up G'raha Tia
Description:
The future is where his destiny awaits.

Use item to acquire the wind-up G'raha Tia minion.

Name: Little Yin
Description:
Turn around.

Use item to acquire the Little Yin minion.

Name: Little Yang
Description:
Every now and then he gets a little bit closer.

Use item to acquire the Little Yang minion.

Name: Wind-up Cloud
Description:
Sharp hair, don't care.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Cloud minion.

Name: Wind-up Aerith
Description:
The future ith not only yourth.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Aerith minion.

Name: Wind-up Tifa
Description:
Not the wrong person.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Tifa minion.

Name: Mudpie
Description:
At last, portable filth.

Use item to acquire the mudpie minion.

Name: Bridesmoogle
Description:
What is a blushing bride without a dutiful bridesmoogle to scatter petals in her general vicinity?

Use item to acquire the bridesmoogle minion.

Name: Wind-up Elvaan
Description:
Remarks relating to a certain people's perpetually dour facial expressions are best kept to oneself.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Elvaan minion.

Name: Dhalmel Calf
Description:
Oddly short yet alarmingly tall.

Use item to acquire the dhalmel calf minion.

Name: Capybara Pup
Description:
Loves bath time, and you.

Use item to acquire the capybara pup minion.

Name: Scarlet Tailfeather
Description: A fiery red plume that previously adorned the auspice Suzaku.

Name: Smoldering Protean Crystal
Description: Barely visible wisps of smoke curl from the surface of this aether-forged crystal. Its peculiar warmth may be the result of its elemental energies' perpetual entropy.

Name: Penthesilea's Flame
Description: An ever-burning ember collected from the site of the warrioress Penthesilea's vanquishment.

Name: Pyros Crystal
Description: A crystal discovered in Eureka Pyrosa region where the elemental aspect leans heavily to fire.

Name: Replica Elemental Knuckles
Description: Weapon appearance may take precedence over the display of hand gear.

Name: Pyros Lockbox
Description: A firmly sealed box discovered deep in the Pyros wilds. Only a skilled picker of locks might grant you access to the treasure within.

Name: Heat-warped Lockbox
Description: A firmly sealed box discovered deep in the Pyros wilds, its shape made irregular by prolonged exposure to the elements. Only a skilled picker of locks might grant you access to the treasure within.

Name: Suzaku Barding
Description: A suit of chocobo armor designed to resemble the Far Eastern auspice Suzaku.

Name: Samurai Barding
Description: Chocobo barding designed to pair well with traditional samurai garb.

Name: Arum Bulbs
Description:
Bulbs such as these are the most efficient means of cultivating arums, and thus a must-have for busy hostesses needing to prepare decorative centerpieces or significant volumes of poison in a hurry.

For use in planters.

Description:
A bunch of red arums, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Golden Kasamatsu Interior Wall

Name: Ripe Pumpkin Cookie MMXVIII
Description: A devilish imp is thought to have made this slightly burnt biscuit shaped like a pumpkin head. One can only wonder what ingredients it containsbut whatever they are, they've somehow managed to go off despite having been baked.

Name: Indigo Prismfish
Description:
An elementally aspected, elegantly colored, and vanishingly rare cousin to the common carp.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 1 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Green Prismfish
Description:
Due to its shockingly bright coloration, this wind-aspected fish is oft sought after for display in garden ponds, but almost never for consumption.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 1 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Watcher Catfish
Description:
A king among electric catfish, and lord of the waters of Rhalgr's Reach.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Bloodtail Zombie
Description:
A king among redtails, and lord of the waters of the Outer Fist.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Hardhead Trout
Description:
A king among steelhead trout, and lord of the waters of Timmon Beck.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Downstream Loach
Description:
A king among greenstream loach, and lord of the waters of the Velodyna River.

A king among meditators, and lord of the waters of the Ephor.

A princessobviouslyamong rainbow killifish, and lady of the waters of the Silver Canal.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Description:
A khan among hardscales, and lord of the waters of Azim Khaat.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Blade Skipper
Description:
A khan among dry steppe skippers, and lord of the waters of the upper Yat Khaal.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Eldthurs Horn
Description: This scorched horn emits a rumbling tone that summons your Eldthurs on burning feet of fire.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Get Fantasy
Description: An illustrated manual of the various steps that comprise the popular dance dubbed get fantasy. Use to learn the /getfantasy emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - The Popoto Step
Description: An illustrated manual of the various steps that comprise the popoto step. Use to learn the /popotostep emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Scholarly Certitude
Description: An illustrated manual of how to consult reference materials with an air of gravitas sufficient to impress upon high society the significance of anything you say. Use to learn the /confirm emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Ideal Gossip
Description: An illustrated manual of how to put an evening spent amongst the wealthy and powerful to best use. Use to learn the /scheme emote.

Name: Fringes Riding Map
Description: This highly detailed map of the Fringes, including everything from land elevation to the location of exposed rocks and roots, was originally drafted by chocobo couriers seeking to reduce delivery times.

Name: Peaks Riding Map
Description: This highly detailed map of the Peaks, including everything from land elevation to the location of exposed rocks and roots, was originally drafted by chocobo couriers seeking to reduce delivery times.

Name: Lochs Riding Map
Description: This highly detailed map of the Lochs, including everything from land elevation to the location of exposed rocks and roots, was originally drafted by chocobo couriers seeking to reduce delivery times.

Name: Ruby Sea Riding Map
Description: This highly detailed map of the Ruby Sea, including everything from land elevation to the location of exposed rocks and roots, was originally drafted by Far Eastern merchants seeking to reduce delivery times.

Name: Yanxia Riding Map
Description: This highly detailed map of Yanxia, including everything from land elevation to the location of exposed rocks and roots, was originally drafted by Far Eastern merchants seeking to reduce delivery times.

Name: Azim Steppe Riding Map
Description: This highly detailed map of the Azim Steppe, including everything from land elevation to the location of exposed rocks and roots, was originally drafted by Far Eastern merchants seeking to reduce delivery times.

Name: Modern Aesthetics - Strife
Description:
The realm's premier publication on beauty and fashion, this specific copy of Modern Aesthetics covers, in detail, techniques on becoming the most memorable of all protagonists.

Use to unlock a new hairstyle at the aesthetician.
Unavailable to Viera and Hrothgar.

Name: Modern Aesthetics - Form and Function
Description:
The realm's premier publication on beauty and fashion, this specific copy of Modern Aesthetics covers, in detail, techniques for weaving a simple-yet-elegant braided headband.

Use to unlock a new hairstyle at the aesthetician.
Unavailable to female Hrothgar.

Name: Modern Aesthetics - Styled for Hire
Description:
The realm's premier publication on beauty and fashion, this specific copy of Modern Aesthetics covers, in detail, techniques for trimming and coiffing one's way to the dashing look that's in vogue amongst sellswords across the Three Great Continents.

Use to unlock a new hairstyle at the aesthetician.
Unavailable to female Hrothgar.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Positively Prickly
Description: An illustrated manual of how to imitate Senor Sabotender's whimsical motions. Please note that the publisher is not responsible for any deaths resulting from the improper use of techniques described in this volume. Use to learn the /sabotender emote.

Name: Magicked Prism (Advent Cakes)
Description: This peculiar contraption creates illusions by weaving together myriad shades of light. Produces a festive stack of Heavensturn advent cakes.

Name: Cut Mochi
Description: A perfectly proportioned rice cake deftly cleaved from a mass of sentient mochi. Perhaps, thus separated from its host, it has become just another tasty dessert. Or perhaps it still retains some awareness, wishing desperately for a mouth with which to scream.

Name: Gyr Abanian Ore
Description: A naturally occurring chunk of lodestone.

Name: Evergleam Ore
Description: A decent-sized piece of rock containing a rare natural alloy of iron and chromium.

Name: Urunday Log
Description: A rough-cut log of urunday timber.

Name: Yanxian Cotton Boll
Description: These whimsical cotton flowers, found only in Yanxia, glimmer faintly like stars in the night.

Name: Procoptodon Skin
Description: The tough hide of a long-extinct marsupial. Unnervingly, it has somehow survived the test of time.

Name: Gyr Abanian Carbon Rods
Description: Pure carbon used in the manufacture of specialty steel.

Name: Tatara Iron Sand
Description: Fine metallic sand consisting of tiny grains of Doman iron, for use specifically in tatara smelting.

Name: Stardust Cotton Yarn
Description: Glimmering yarn reminiscent of a comet's tail.

Name: Gyr Abanian Wax
Description: A uniquely Gyr Abanian wax that renders even the most decrepit of hides supple and lustrous when applied as part of the tanning process.

Name: High-gloss Urushi
Description: This black coating, made from the sap of the lacquer tree, is used to both color and preserve wooden crafts, and can be polished to an extraordinarily glossy sheen.

Name: Chigusa Ingot
Description: An ingot of tatara-smelted Doman steel.

Name: Evergleam Ingot
Description: An ingot of smelted evergleam steel.

Name: Urunday Lumber
Description: Processed urunday lumber.

Name: Procoptodon Leather
Description: A large piece of cured procoptodon skin.

Name: Stardust Cotton Cloth
Description: Several yalms of undyed stardust cotton wrapped around a short distaff.

Name: Azim Spring Water
Description: Water of uncommon clarity sourced from underground springs on the Azim Steppe.

Name: Grade 4 Reisui of Strength
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this Far Eastern potation will, similarly to Eorzean dissolvents, dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to strength, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Grade 4 Reisui of Dexterity

Name: Grade 3 Infusion of Strength
Description:
This diluted brew temporarily increases strength, but for twice the duration of similar potions.

Duration: 30s

Name: Grade 3 Infusion of Dexterity
Description:
This diluted brew temporarily increases dexterity, but for twice the duration of similar potions.

Duration: 30s

Name: Master Blacksmith VII
Description: This esoteric tomethe seventh in an equally esoteric seriescontains advanced smithing recipes that can only be learned by esoterically skilled blacksmiths.

Name: Rooibos Tea
Description:
A healthful herbal tea known for its natural mellow sweetness.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Ginger Salad
Description:
A zesty salad that beckons with the aroma of fresh-cut ginger.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Laghman
Description:
A popular comfort food in Othard consisting of thick, chewy noodles and tender minced dzo in a wholesome broth.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Imam Bayildi
Description:
Miniature Doman eggplants stuffed to bursting with juicy marinated vegetablesand enough peppers to knock a trained Fist of Rhalgr monk out cold.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Papanasi
Description:
Thick dough kneaded with soft cheese and fried into a hearty donut, slathered with yet more creamy cheese and a sweet-and-tart berry sauce.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Salmon Muffin
Description:
A buttery Ishgardian muffin topped with the winning combination of succulent fresh salmon, silky sliced alligator pear, and a drizzling of rich cheese.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Shakshouka
Description:
Eggs perfectly poached in a robust, spicy tomato sauce.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Rooibos Leaves
Description: Red bush leaves whose prickly texture belies the marvelously velvety brew they can be steeped to create.

Name: Reunion Cheese
Description: A washed-rind cheese made possible by the fortuitous meeting of a Steppe cheesemaker and an itinerant winemaker. It possesses a creamy texture and nutty flavorthough one would be forgiven for being skeptical, given the smell.

Name: Exclusive Stuffed Dog
Description: Said to bring a full twelvemoon of good fortune...or as much can be expected from a disturbingly realistic dog skin filled with sawdust and bittersweet memories. Perhaps this is related to why there are a limited number in circulation.

Name: Certificate of Good Cheer MMXVIII
Description: A slip of parchment issued in recognition of efforts toward spreading Starlight spirit. Only valid for one year from date of issuethe better to encourage cheer-related efforts annually.

Name: Lamebrix's Dice
Description: A pair of precisely carved dice, subtly weighted for the purpose of cheating in goblin gambling games.

Name: Ying-Yang's Tissue
Description: An unsightly portion of veined membrane ripped from Ying-Yang's (hopefully vestigial) wings.

Name: Skoll's Claw
Description: A gleaming, knifelike appendage torn from Skoll's frigid paw.

Name: Syldra-class Bow
Description: Comprising the front end of a Syldra-class submersible, this unique bow resembles the head and neck of a legendary sea dragon.

Name: Syldra-class Bridge
Description: Comprising the top of a Syldra-class submersible, this bridge is equipped with escape pods to be used in the event of an emergency.

Name: Syldra-class Pressure Hull
Description: Comprising the center of a Syldra-class submersible, this hydrodynamic finned hull is insusceptible to the pull of even the strongest currents.

Name: Syldra-class Stern
Description: Comprising the rear end of a Syldra-class submersible, this stern is shaped so as to allow the craft to operate nigh silently, even at top speed.

Name: Modified Shark-class Bow
Description: Comprising the front end of a shark-class submersible, this redesigned bow doubles as an exceptionally sturdy battering ram for subduing unruly sea creatures.

Name: Modified Shark-class Bridge
Description: Comprising the top of a shark-class submersible, this bridge has been fully outfitted with any and all equipment that could possibly be necessary for exploring faraway seas.

Name: Modified Shark-class Pressure Hull
Description: Comprising the center of a shark-class submersible, this multi-walled ovoid hull and its sturdy rudder fins have been redesigned to provide additional stability while maneuvering through the depths.

Name: Modified Shark-class Stern
Description: Comprising the rear end of a shark-class submersible, this stern contains a high-powered independent engine which propels the craft.

Name: Modified Unkiu-class Bow
Description: Unkiu-class bows are outfitted with rudder fins, relegated to the stern on most submersiblesand this particular model's have been upgraded for additional durability.

Name: Modified Unkiu-class Bridge
Description: But recently redesigned by the Onishishua collective of skilled Far Eastern craftsmenthis submersible bridge differs dramatically from those built in the West.

Name: Modified Unkiu-class Pressure Hull
Description: Comprising the center of an unkiu-class submersible, this ovoid hull is multi-walled to stabilize and maintain pressure within. Its supplemental propulsion engines have been upgraded to further increase underwater speed.

Name: Modified Unkiu-class Stern
Description: Comprising the rear end of an unkiu-class submersible, this stern contains a new model of double propeller engine.

Name: Modified Whale-class Bow
Description: Comprising the front end of a whale-class submersible, this specially reinforced bow will protect the vessel's interior even should it be caught directly in an undersea volcanic eruption.

Name: Modified Whale-class Bridge
Description: Comprising the top of a whale-class submersible, this redesigned bridge improves even further on the depth rating of other models, allowing submersibles equipped with it to delve deeper than previously imagined possible.

Name: Modified Whale-class Pressure Hull
Description: Comprising the center of a whale-class submersible, this ovoid hull is equipped with two reinforced auxiliary propellers for superior maneuverability.

Name: Modified Whale-class Stern
Description: Comprising the rear end of a whale-class submersible, this stern features a modern, energy-efficient propeller.

Name: Modified Coelacanth-class Bow
Description: Comprising the front end of a coelacanth-class submersible, this bow has been further streamlined to allow the vessel to reach speeds greater than ever before.

Name: Modified Coelacanth-class Bridge
Description: Comprising the top of a coelacanth-class submersible, this bridge has been altered to provide even more storage space and equipped with myriad amenities for longer voyages.

Name: Modified Coelacanth-class Pressure Hull
Description: Comprising the center of a coelacanth-class submersible, this ovoid hull has been redesigned to be even more resilient against external water pressure, thereby further raising maximum operating depth.

Name: Modified Coelacanth-class Stern
Description: Comprising the rear end of a coelacanth-class submersible, this stern includes a streamlined hydrodynamic rudder that further enhances lateral maneuverability.

Name: Modified Syldra-class Bow
Description: Comprising the front end of a Syldra-class submersible, this unique bow still resembles the head and neck of a legendary sea dragon, but has been adjusted for greater stability.

Name: Modified Syldra-class Bridge
Description: Comprising the top of a Syldra-class submersible, this bridge has been redesigned to provide further defense against the dangers of the seathough it remains equipped with escape pods to be used in the event of an emergency.

Name: Modified Syldra-class Pressure Hull
Description: Comprising the center of a Syldra-class submersible, this hydrodynamic finned hull has been altered for even greater resistance to the pull of underwater currents.

Name: Modified Syldra-class Stern
Description: Comprising the rear end of a Syldra-class submersible, this stern has been streamlined so as to allow the craft to operate silently, even at top speed.

Name: Paissa Chronometer
Description: As if the beastkin's physique simply does not beg to be reimagined as a convenient timepiece.

Name: Paint Can
Description: The size of this can is indicative of an ambitious home improvement project. The amount of paint remaining suggests that said project has proven more difficult than expected.

Name: Emerald Crystal Boule
Description: A mounted sample of the luminous green crystals that grow uninhibited on the sea floor.

Name: Mirific Mogshelf
Description: A charming bookshelf topped with decorative moogles beckoning readers to the myriad worlds that come alive through the written word.

Name: Tier 3 Metal Aquarium
Description:
A large reinforced glass tank that, when filled with water, can serve as a home for select wavekin caught in the wild. The higher an aquarium's tier, the larger the specimens that can be kept within.
Private chambers (apartments), cottages, houses, and mansions can host 4, 6, 8, and 10 aquariums, respectively.

Name: Tier 4 Metal Aquarium
Description:
A massive reinforced glass tank that, when filled with water, can serve as a home for select wavekin caught in the wild. The higher an aquarium's tier, the larger the specimens that can be kept within.
Private chambers (apartments), cottages, houses, and mansions can host 4, 6, 8, and 10 aquariums, respectively.

Name: Travel Paint Set
Description: A robust, portable set of art supplies for adventurous artists and artistic adventurers.

Name: Seiryu Statuette
Description:
An elegant carving of the venerable Seiryu. The geomantic orb in its claws reputedly fills one's home with auspicious energies.

One per estate only.

Name: Valentione Lobster Platter
Description:
A sumptuous plate of boiled and buttered lobster. Comes complete with a heart-shaped pizza. For reasons.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Determination Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  VIT Bonus: +5% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Valentione Cake Pairing
Description:
Rich cake powdered with dark chocolate and paired with a fine wine.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

  Skill Speed Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  VIT Bonus: +5% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Description:

  Gear Durability Bonus: +3

Name: Archon Egg Pile
Description: In your abode, eggs hide you.

Name: Small Imitation Window
Description: Despite its sizeand the minor detail of it not being a real windowthis plain would-be portal provides a surprising amount of light.

Name: Bag of Booty
Description: The shine of the historic coins contained within has been professionally restored with great care. Nevertheless, whether you tuck this bag safely away or wave it about while putting on a terrible faux-pirate accent is entirely up to you.

Name: Undersea Spoils
Description: Not all that glitters is gold. This is, though.

Name: Level Checker Replica
Description: A model of an advanced piece of technology described in the pages of arather eccentricancient tome.

Name: Cerulean Crystal Boule
Description: A mounted sample of the luminous blue crystals that grow uninhibited on the sea floor.

Name: Fat Cat Bank
Description: Presumably due to the resemblance in terms of rotundity, the fat cat has overtaken the pig as a popular motif for coin banks. Comes with a matching purse to better facilitate the spending of one's hard-earned savings.

Name: Tree Slice Tower
Description: Pets love it! Miqo'te, too!

Name: Botanist's Dried Herbs
Description: An assortment of pleasant-smelling medicinal and culinary herbs verified to be nontoxic. Mostly.

Name: Steppe Kitchen
Description: This cooking facility was fashioned after those used by the Xaela tribes of the Azim Steppe.

Name: Four Lords
Description: An evocative ink depiction of the Four Lords.

Name: Wooden Loft
Description: Create the perfect space for sleeping, reading, displays, or enjoying an insurmountable advantage in pillow fights with this wall-mounted platform.

Name: Wooden Steps
Description: Useful in climbing up to lofts or removing rival heirs.

Name: Wooden Beam
Description: For use with the wooden loft, though beam enthusiasts are sure to enjoy it regardless.

Name: White Rectangular Partition
Description: Thus named despite the fact that none would fain expect a blue triangle.

Name: Bowl of Oden
Description:
A heaping bowl of juicy fishcakes, tender daikon, hearty boiled eggs, and other savory ingredients steeped for hours in a warming broth.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Spell Speed Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  VIT Bonus: +5% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Fruit Stall
Description: A two-tiered unit displaying assorted colorful fruit.

Name: Vegetable Stall
Description: A large shelf packed with artfully displayed vegetables.

Name: Pastry Cupboard
Description: Shelves lined with an assortment of pre-plated sweets to sell, share, or...not.

Name: Mineral Display
Description: Glittering gemstones meticulously arranged atop several tiers of shelving.

Name: Fabric Rack
Description: A neatly arranged collection of assorted fabrics and spindles of thread for sale.

Name: Potion Rack
Description: These shelves are packed with enough concoctions and extracts to run a full apothecary and still have some left over for what will doubtless be totally safe and ethical experimentation.

Name: Prism Pouch
Description: A pouch for many standard-sized prisms, or one extremely large one.

Name: Marimo Lamp
Description: The product of a skilled yet not particularly creative metalworker who took inspiration from the lamp marimo to create...a lamp containing lamp marimo.

Name: Honey Pot
Description: Keeping this much honey in the house is just asking for bear-related trouble.

Name: Red Carpet
Description: A slim length of carpeting to welcome honored guests.

Name: Hanging Planter Shelf
Description: Various potted plants dangle from this wall-mounted shelf, leaving the space atop it free for other items. Or more plants.

Name: Plush Pile
Description: Stuffed moogles and tonberries and bears, oh my.

Name: Fat Cat Sofa
Description: So large. So fluffy.

Name: Enormous Stuffed Alpha
Description: A fair flock of fowl's feathers were required to stuff this larger-than-life tribute to Garlond Ironworks' cutestand yellowestmember.

Name: Stuffed Mammet
Description: All the cuddliness of a mammet with all the functionality of a plush doll.

Name: Festive Chirashi-zushi
Description:
Almost identical to normal chirashi-zushi, but with markedly more festivity.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Direct Hit Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  VIT Bonus: +5% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Festive Sushi Balls
Description:
Off put by the oblongitudinal proportions of regular sushi? Well, your prayers have been answered. All the fresh fish and vinegared rice you love, ham-fisted into semi-sophisticated spheroids perfect for popping.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Piety Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  VIT Bonus: +5% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Season Eleven Lone Wolf Trophy
Description: A trophy awarded to those who left their mark in Season Eleven of the Feast.

Name: Season Twelve Lone Wolf Trophy
Description: A trophy awarded to those who left their mark in Season Twelve of the Feast.

Name: Simple Treehouse
Description: No girls allowed. And while we're at itno boys, either.

Name: Botanist's Garden
Description: A vegetable patch so lovingly tended that it could only have been cultivated by an expert.

Name: Big One Festival Float
Description: Though this towering vehicle is meant for use in parades celebrating the Big One, a modern Namazu, rather than said venerable ancestor, is depicted atop it. Is this a means of increasing its appeal among the common Namazu, or simply the result of Gyoshin's brethren refusing to allow him to melt down any more koban to make large golden fish statues? Those who do not purchase A Meditation on the Metaphysics of Merrymaking may never know.

Name: Teal Blue Carpeting
Description: Durable yet fuzzy loop carpet in a soothing blue-green.

Name: Black-and-white Interior Wall
Description: A wooden interior wall painted with a monochrome pattern of wide horizontal stripes.

Name: Moonlit Tank Trimmings
Description:
An assortment of items used to outfit an aquarium that it might resemble the moonlit eve upon which a nightbloom once flowered...

[For use in any tier aquarium.]

Name: Lily of the Valley Pips
Description:
Mature rootstalks that will grow and flower with sweet-smelling (though highly poisonous) bell-shaped blooms.

For use in planters.

Name: Red Lilies of the Valley
Description:
A bunch of red lilies of the valley, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Blue Lilies of the Valley
Description:
A bunch of blue lilies of the valley, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Yellow Lilies of the Valley
Description:
A bunch of yellow lilies of the valley, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Green Lilies of the Valley
Description:
A bunch of green lilies of the valley, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Orange Lilies of the Valley
Description:
A bunch of orange lilies of the valley, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Purple Lilies of the Valley
Description:
A bunch of purple lilies of the valley, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: White Lilies of the Valley
Description:
A bunch of white lilies of the valley, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Black Lilies of the Valley
Description:
A bunch of black lilies of the valley, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Rainbow Lilies of the Valley
Description:
A bunch of multicolored lilies of the valley, selectively fertilized to achieve a variety of vibrant colors.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Northern Oyster
Description:
The shell of this bivalve mollusk mimics the jagged rocks found throughout the cold northern seas, making it almost impossible to find by anyone but the most keen-eyed of fishers.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Ruby Laver
Description:
Though a brilliant red when in water, the thin leaves of this seaweed turn pitch black when removed from the sea and dried.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Chakrafish
Description:
This freshwater fish can be found throughout Gyr Abania, and is a staple amongst those monks who have chosen not to abstain from consuming the flesh of living creatures.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Wicked Wartfish
Description:
This grotesque deep-sea dweller has adapted to the warm waters off the volcanic isle of Hells' Lid, and thus cannot be found anywhere else in the world.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Othardian Salmon
Description:
As is the case with all salmon, this freshwater fish will migrate to the sea after hatching, only to return to the river in which it was spawned to die.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Ishgardian Culinary Essentials
Description: Cooking tools and ingredients without which the making of authentic Ishgardian cuisine is simply impossibleor so Ishgardian culinarians claim.

Name: Fermented Juice
Description: A now-alcoholic liquid ready to be distilled into a strong but tasty liquor.

Name: Signature Buuz Cookware
Description: This assemblage of tools and ingredients strongly resembles that used by tribes of the Azim Steppe, but has been modified slightly for use in preparing a variety of buuz exclusive to the Hard Place.

Name: Hard Place Decorative Furnishings
Description: Dcor perfect for convincing customers that they don't have to go homeand they can stay here.

Name: Arkhi Brewing Set
Description: An assortment of items for brewing the milk-based alcohol that is traditional on the Azim Steppe.

Name: Sparkstone
Description: The burning aether contained within this volcanic stone allows for its use not only in striking fires, but also maintaining them at a consistent heat.

Name: Malleable Still Material
Description: This flexible material is ideal for use in creating a home-brewing facility of one's very own.

Name: Strong Steppe Spice
Description: This spice is so potent as to often go unused on the Azim Steppe itself, but after overhearing a patron state that buuz tastes like wet sheep, Adkiragh was inspired to add it to create a flavor more palatable to non-Xaela.

Name: Hard Place Furnishing Materials
Description: A collection of items that look suitable for use in creating furnishings, and aren't that dirty.

Name: Sturdy Vat Material
Description: When fully assembled, an arkhi vat made with this material should be impermeable enough to prevent liquid escaping during the evaporation process and overly intoxicating hapless brewers.

Name: Ishgardian Culinary Materials
Description: Processed materials that still look like any other sort of materials, but are nevertheless ready to be combined into authentic Ishgardian cooking essentials.

Name: Juice Fermenting Supplies
Description: Pulped fruit, yeast, and other prepared supplies necessary for fermenting juice into alcohol.

Name: Signature Buuz Cookware Materials
Description: Processed materials that can be combined into the necessary components for cooking authentic buuz.

Name: Decorative Tavern Furnishing Materials
Description: Processed materials that genuinely look as if they could be used to create stylish furnishings.

Name: Arkhi Brewing Vat Materials
Description: Processed materials that can be combined into the necessary components for brewing arkhi.

Name: Raw Ishgardian Materials
Description: Unsorted and unrefined materials that look like any other sort of materials, but which you are assured are genuinely Ishgardian.

Name: Raw Fermenting Supplies
Description: Unsorted and unprocessed fruit, yeast, and other materials necessary for fermenting alcohol.

Name: Raw Steppe Cookware Materials
Description: Unsorted and unrefined materials from the Azim Steppe that you are assured can be used to create the necessary components for cooking authentic buuz.

Name: Raw Tavern Furnishing Materials
Description: Unsorted and unrefined materials that look as if they could be used to create stylish furnishingsif you squint.

Name: Raw Brewing Vat Materials
Description: Unsorted and unrefined materials that you are assured can be used to assemble the necessary components for brewing arkhi.

Name: True Blue Attire Coffer (IL 1)
Description:
A banded chest containing a complete set of true blue attire.

Required level: 1. IL: 1. Cannot be opened in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.

Name: Magus's Attire Coffer (IL 130)
Description:
A banded chest containing a complete set of magus's attire.

Required level: 50. IL: 130. Cannot be opened in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.

Name: Aetheryte Earring
Description: Increases EXP earned by 30% when level 70 and below. Attributes and item level vary according to class/job and current level when equipped.

Name: Far Eastern Schoolboy's Hat
Description: Fits: All

Name: Far Eastern Schoolboy's Hakama
Description: Fits: All

Name: Far Eastern Schoolboy's Zori
Description: Fits: All

Name: Far Eastern Schoolgirl's Hair Ribbon
Description: Fits: All

Name: Far Eastern Schoolgirl's Hakama
Description: Fits: All

Name: Far Eastern Schoolgirl's Boots
Description: Fits: All

Name: Ananta Metalworks
Description: A number of beautifully detailed, opulent golden vessels created in honor of Sri Lakshmi.

Name: Kojin Material Supplier Permit
Description:
This permit allows the hiring of Kojin material suppliers on the estate.

Private chambers (apartments), cottages, houses, and mansions can host 4, 6, 8, and 10 vendors, respectively.

Name: Kojin Junkmonger Permit
Description:
This permit allows the hiring of Kojin junkmongers on the estate.

Private chambers (apartments), cottages, houses, and mansions can host 4, 6, 8, and 10 vendors, respectively.

Name: Kojin Mender Permit
Description:
This permit allows the hiring of Kojin menders on the estate.

Private chambers (apartments), cottages, houses, and mansions can host 4, 6, 8, and 10 vendors, respectively.

Name: Kojin Manservant Permit
Description:
This permit allows the hiring of Kojin manservants on the estate.

Private chambers (apartments), cottages, houses, and mansions can host 4, 6, 8, and 10 vendors, respectively.

Name: Maxima Roader Identification Key
Description: A thin, rectangular piece of what appears to be cermet. Placing it near your maxima roader will bring it roaring terrifyingly to life.

Name: Hallowed Kamuy Fife
Description: The solemn song of this stout flute is said to summon a kamuy blessed by Lord Seiryu himself.

Name: Regalia Type-G Title
Description: A deed certifying your ownership of a brand-new vehicle, embossed with the Regalia crest as a symbol of authenticity.

Name: Fabled Kamuy Fife
Description: The lonely song of this stout flute is said to summon a long-lived auspiceKamuy of the Nine Tailsrarely glimpsed by mortal eyes.

Name: Demi-Ozma
Description: This conveniently sized result of experimentation on the part of the Students of Baldesion may not be entirely stable enough to safely ridebut there's only one way to find out.

Name: Magicked Carpet
Description: With but a few magic words, this carpet will bear you upward to a whole new worldor at least a more elevated one.

Name: Sabotender Emperador Horn
Description: This eccentric horn emits a thunderous toot that summons the Sabotender Emperador.

Name: War Tiger Horn
Description: This curved horn emits a roaring tone that summons your war tiger.

Name: Eurekan Petrel Horn
Description: A delicate shell horn that summons the beautiful and dangerous gastropod known as the Eurekan petrel.

Name: Magitek Avenger A1 Identification Key
Description: A thin, rectangular piece of what appears to be cermet. Placing it near your magitek avenger A1 will magically bring the machine to life.

Name: Wind-up Fran
Description:
Stilettos guaranteed not to impede progress through markedly rough terrain such as jungles, bogs, and abandoned monasteries serving as prisons for extra-dimensional forces of evil.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Fran minion.

Name: Wind-up Nu Mou
Description:
So cuddlesome it hurts.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Nu Mou minion.

Name: Seitei
Description:
Dragon-ness is in the eye of the beholder.

Use item to acquire the Seitei minion.

Name: Conditional Virtue
Description:
Cuddle not to dullness; coddle not to elevation.

Use item to acquire the Conditional Virtue minion.

Name: Minitek Conveyor
Description:
The latest in miniature transport technology.

Use item to acquire the minitek conveyor minion.

Name: Wind-up Qalyana
Description:
She may or may not break through the borderline.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Qalyana minion.

Name: Wind-up Redback
Description:
Don't tell mom the Kojin minion's red.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Redback minion.

Name: Wind-up Weapon
Description:
Somewhat buggy.

Use item to acquire the wind-up weapon minion.

Name: Yukinko Snowflake
Description:
Falling, falling, falling, falling, falling...falling on his head.

Use item to acquire the yukinko snowflake minion.

Name: Dress-up Tataru
Description:
Say what you willshe wears it well.

Use item to acquire the dress-up Tataru minion.

Name: Baby Gremlin
Description:
Feeding after midnight may result in injury. Yours.

Use item to acquire the baby gremlin minion.

Name: Seemingly Special Timeworn Map
Description:
This bottle is holding what appears to be a particularly valuable leather map.

Use the action Decipher to extract the map and examine its contents.
Level 70 full party (eight players) recommended.
Guaranteed to summon a teleportation portal.

Name: Seiryu Totem
Description: This wooden idol carved in the likeness of the auspice Seiryu was likely created by a devout islander in days long gone by.

Name: Mullondeis Coin
Description: A small gold coin stamped with what you assume to be Mullonde's mint mark. Once considered to be of great historical significance, a sudden influx caused their value to plummet, rendering them almost worthless.

Name: Seiryu Barding
Description: A suit of chocobo armor designed to resemble the Far Eastern auspice Seiryu.

Name: Yojimbo Barding
Description: A suit of chocobo armor designed to resemble the...colorful...bodyguard known to some as Jim.

Name: Modern Aesthetics - Lexen-tails
Description:
The realm's premier publication on beauty and fashion, this specific copy of Modern Aesthetics covers, in detail, techniques for imitating the Lexentale siblings' signature stage-ready styles.

Use to unlock a new hairstyle at the aesthetician.
Unavailable to female Hrothgar.

Name: Modern Aesthetics - Lucian Locks
Description:
The realm's premier publication on beauty and fashion, this specific copy of Modern Aesthetics covers, in detail, techniques on becoming a suitably windswept protagonist.

Use to unlock a new hairstyle at the aesthetician.
Unavailable to Viera and Hrothgar.

Name: Seiryu's Scale
Description: A shimmering scale that once protected the body of the most venerable serpentine auspice.

Name: Waterproof Cloth
Description: This durable fabric is backed with a layer of rubber, making it far less permeable to water than typical garment materials.

Name: Peerless Clan Mark Log
Description: A list of highly elite marks documented by the log's owner. Said owner may never have slain the marks, but he did achieve a remarkable level of detail in his entriesby unabashedly hiding in the bushes to observe the grisly deaths met by his fellow hunters. Though such documents were once considered highly valuable, demand has dried up and they are now essentially worthless.

Name: Crystalline Scale
Description: A beautifully faceted scale that fell from the back of the Provenance Watcher.

Name: Hydatos Crystal
Description: A crystal discovered in Eureka Hydatosa region where the elemental aspect leans heavily to water.

Name: Eureka Fragment
Description: Surprisingly heavy for its size, this cube contains a small portion of the aether that comprises the primal Eureka itself.

Name: Obscure Logogram
Description: Crystallized memory that likely contains knowledge of arts so specialized or ill-advised as to have been kept hidden from all but a select few.

Name: Wisdom of the Breathtaker
Description:
Crystallized memory that once belonged to a fleet-footed assassin of uncommon ingenuity.

Only available for use in the Forbidden Land, Eureka.

Description: A small statuette engraved with inscrutable ancient pictographs.

Name: Damascene Cloth
Description: This cloth was woven using a long and complicated process. It is a traditional fabric from the south of Othard.

Name: Molech's Horn
Description: A hulking horn that once adorned the head of the cruel Molech.

Name: Goldemar's Horn
Description: As part of his efforts to project a sense of economic might, King Goldemar had even his own horns opulently engravednot that it will do him much good now that you have torn this one from his head.

Name: Ceto's Claw
Description: This was once the pointiest point on one of Ceto's lethally sharp appendages. Handle with care.

Name: Aethertight Flask
Description: An utterly impermeable vessel of Sharlayan design, created for the purpose of securely storing experimental alchemical concoctions.

Name: Replica Pyros Knuckles
Description: Weapon appearance may take precedence over the display of hand gear.

Name: Hydatos Lockbox

Name: Moisture-warped Lockbox
Description: A firmly sealed box discovered deep in the Hydatos wilds, its shape made irregular by prolonged exposure to the elements. Only a skilled picker of locks might grant you access to the treasure within.

Name: Lily of the Veil
Description:
A queen among Ala Mhigan ribbons, and lady of the waters of the Arms of Meed.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: The Vegetarian
Description:
Fisher legend has there was once a mighty liopleurodon who, unsatisfied with a diet of Namazu, is said to have set its sights on plumper preynamely a portly Lalafellin regent with a penchant for skinny dipping in the warm waters near Hells' Lid. However, the fish quickly learned the limits of its maw's gape, and crestfallen, abandoned the king, a crown-shaped scar on its upper lip its only prize. But rather than sulk, this beast from the deep spent the rest of its life devouring creatures far larger than it, and now, five thousand summers later, the descendant of that legendary pioneer polishes off Plainsfolk like they were popotoes, proving once and for all...life truly does find a way.

[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Seven Stars
Description:
A king among tawny wench sharks, and lord of the waters off the Isle of Bekko.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Pinhead
Description:
A king among globefish, and lord of the waters off Isari.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Pomegranate Trout
Description:
A queen among Doman trout, and lady of the waters of the Heron's Nest.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Glarramundi
Description:
A king among river barramundi, and lord of the waters of the Heron's Way.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Hermit's End
Description:
A king among nogoi, and lord of the waters of Namai.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Suiten Ippeki
Description:
A king among lordly salmon, and lord of the waters near the mercantile docks.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Axelrod
Description:
A king among Yanxian barramundi, and lord of the waters of the One River (east).

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: The Unraveled Bow
Description:
A king among Doman eels, and lord of the waters of Prism Canyon.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Nhaama's Treasure
Description:
A queen among Nhaama's boons, and lady of the waters of Dotharl Khaa.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Garden Skipper
Description:
A king among steppe skippers, and lord of the waters of Nem Khaal.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Banderole
Description:
A king among curtain plecos, and lord of the waters of Hak Khaal.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Zephyrous Zabuton
Description:
More pushing for another cushion.

Use item to acquire the zephyrous zabuton minion.

Name: Abroader Otter
Description:
Hobbies include playing and having fun on an island in the sun.

Use item to acquire the abroader otter minion.

Name: Hedgehoglet
Description:
Only your selfless love and affection can keep him blissfully dilemma-free.

Use item to acquire the hedgehoglet minion.

Name: Aetherially Conductive Plate
Description: A thin piece of metal that assists in dampening fluctuations in the aetherial current. Used in the creation of aetherytes.

Name: Hydatos Cluster
Description: A large chunk of crystals discovered steeping in the water-aspected aether of Hydatos.

Name: Sharlayan Aether Oil
Description: A Sharlayan imitation of an Allagan concoction, this aetherochemical oil can be applied to metal to lower its aetherial conductivity.

Name: Aetheric Stabilizer
Description: A clever little device that harmonizes discordant aetherial currents, allowing for the safe use of previously unstable nodes.

Name: Salvaged Coinage
Description: Antique coins tarnished by centuries spent in the briny deep.

Name: Irregular Tomestone of Philosophy
Description:
One of only a few in existence, this Allagan tomestone contains arguments from a school of thought that was likely considered eccentric even in its time.

Can be exchanged with itinerant moogles for certain items.

Name: Doman Reiyaku
Description: A concentrated elixir created through the use of closely guarded geomantic techniques.

Name: Xenacanthus
Description:
This massive predator has haunted the nightmares of Gyr Abanians for generations as the legendary impaler of Timmon Beck, thanks to its centuries-old legacy of terrorizing smallfolk attempting to do their washing.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 4 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Drepanaspis
Description:
Perhaps the greatest catch to be found at Grymm & Enid, the drepanaspis is so rare that, until now, no one was sure that one could be found at Grymm & Enid.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Stethacanthus
Description:
The size of the growths on this stethacanthus indicate that it may be the oldest still in existenceand also why it has come to be known as the Loch Seld monster.

[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: The Ruby Dragon
Description:
This legendary king of the deep is known to all who have ever come near the Ruby Priceand yes, it is a dragon. Or at least it quite closely resembles one.

[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Warden of the Seven Hues
Description:
Though beautiful, this polychromatic carp ruled Prism Lake with an iron fin...until now.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 4 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: The Unconditional
Description:
Not so much a lord as a god of Dotharl Khaa, this particular specimen is thought to be a blessing sent by the Dusk Mother and Dawn Father themselves. As such, this catch might be best left unboasted of.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 1 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Description: Fits: All

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Overzealous Affirmations
Description: An illustrated manual of how not to express your enthusiasm for mashed popotoes in the middle of the dinner course. Use to learn the /fistpump emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Refined Reproaches
Description: An illustrated manual of dignified means by which to put your social inferiors in their place. Use to learn the /reprimand emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - The Heel Toe
Description: An illustrated manual of the various steps that comprise the aptly named heel toe. Use to learn the /heeltoe emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - The Goobbue Do
Description: An illustrated manual of the various steps that comprise the so-called goobbue do. Use to learn the /goobbuedo emote.

Name: Magicked Prism (Job Mastery)
Description: This peculiar contraption creates illusions by weaving together myriad shades of light. Produces a halo of stars to indicate that you are the very model of a modern major job master.

Name: Magicked Prism (Daisies)
Description: This peculiar contraption creates illusions by weaving together myriad shades of light. Produces a shimmering chain of flowers overhead.

Name: Unidentified Magitek
Description: A hunk of heavy metal that is clearly part of some greater whole, but resembles no component found in the designs of Garlond Ironworks or even the Garlean Empire.

Name: Kamacite Ore
Description: A chunk of long-fallen meteor containing the rare alloy kamacite.

Name: Kamacite
Description: A thin piece of smelted kamacite.

Name: Whalaqee White Wind Totem
Description:
An intricately carved wooden totem imbued with the secrets of a restorative technique.

Only for use by blue mages.

Name: Miracle Elixir
Description: This carbonated beveragenow with royal jelly and lemon extractis guaranteed to change your fate in a tick. Just like an elixir ought to do!

Name: Exclusive Far Eastern Journey Battle Staff
Far Eastern Journey Attire Coffer
Description:
A banded chest containing a complete set of exclusive Eastern journey attire and matching battle staff.

Required level: 1. IL: 1. Cannot be opened in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.

Description: The incantation on this enchanted scroll is believed to call forth a cloud gold as the sun and fleet as the wind.

Name: Irregular Tomestone of Mythology
Description:
One of only a few in existence, this Allagan tomestone contains ancient legends too bizarre and disturbing to have been passed down by any other means.

Can be exchanged with itinerant moogles for certain items.

Name: Tales of Adventure: Stormblood
Description:
A detailed record of recent historyso detailed, in fact, that all who read it come to swear they experienced the events firsthand.

Use to instantly complete all main scenario quests up through A Requiem for Heroes. Cannot be used outside large settlements. Automatic logout will commence upon usage.

Description:

Name: Revised Survival Manual
Description:
This comprehensive manual on survival techniquesnow entirely rendered in modern languages and free of lacunaecontains knowledge amassed over centuries by trackers, hunters, and woodsmen. It is known to inspire all who read it, granting a temporary 150% boost to experience points earned from gathering activities (up to a maximum of 2,000,000 points). Effect is halved at level 80 and above.

Duration: 18 hours

Name: Revised Engineering Manual
Description:
This comprehensive manual on craftingnow entirely rendered in modern languages and free of lacunaecontains knowledge amassed over centuries by well-traveled Disciples of the Hand. It is known to inspire all who read it, granting a temporary 150% boost to experience points earned from synthesis (up to a maximum of 2,000,000 points). Effect is halved at level 80 and above.

Duration: 18 hours

Name: Timeworn Gliderskin Map
Description:
This bottle holds a timeworn map classified as risk-reward grade 11 among treasure hunters.

Use the action Decipher to extract the map and examine its contents.
Level 80 recommended.

Name: Timeworn Zonureskin Map
Description:
This bottle holds a timeworn map classified as risk-reward grade 12 among treasure hunters.

Use the action Decipher to extract the map and examine its contents.
Level 80 full party (eight players) recommended.

Name: Eighteyes Eel
Description:
Named for the markings that run down each side of its head, although its circular maw lined with serrated teeth is perhaps more worthy of attention.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Creamy Oyster
Description:
While the texture of many species of oyster could be described as creamy, there is only one specifically named for this quality.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Brightmirror Clam
Description:
These rare bivalve mollusks are harvested more for their shells than for their meat, as the inner nacre can be used as a form of naturally occurring mirror.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Amber Monkfish
Description:
Fish can adapt to the most unlikely of environments, as this repulsive sand-dweller amply proves. It spends most of its adult life burrowing through the sands of Amh Araeng searching for moisture and snaring unsuspecting prey in its fearsome jaws.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Calico Trout
Description:
The beautiful markings and coloration of this elusive species are known to cause pangs of guilt in those who catch one, shortly before they bash it over the head and gut it.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Prospero Eel
Description:
This species native to the Tempest is believed by locals to possess the ability to control the elements using some form of innate magic. This may, however, be no more than a ruse invented by the Ondo to keep intruders out of their waters.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Animal Trace
Description: Will this specimen yield a breakthrough in the search for the samiel? Only time and effort will tell...

Name: Animal Droppings
Description:
A steaming, fly-ridden pile of excrement is a veritable repository of knowledge.
Qeshi-Rae

Name: Megafauna Leftovers
Description: Whatever bit into this plant part can only be described as massive.

Name: Megafauna Trace
Description: The possibility cannot be denied: something massive this way came.

Name: Ancient Animal Skin
Description:
Shed by what is believed to be an ancient creature, this shred of skin may well shed light on the samiel.

Not included in the gathering log.

Name: Black Aethersand
Description:
This aetherially charged sand is a key ingredient in the preparation of glamour dispellers.

Not included in the gathering log.

Name: Fae Gwiber Trumpet
Description: This horn-carved instrument emits an ethereal tone that beckons an elusive fae gwiber from its hiding place.

Name: Skyslipper Key
Description: A thin, rectangular piece of what appears to be cermet. Placing it near your skyslipper will activate the curious vehicle's propulsion unit.

Name: Triceratops Horn
Description: A rough-hewn horn of petrified bone that, when blown, emits a somber tone that summons a lumbering triceratops.

Name: Ironfrog Mover Ignition Key
Description: Inserting this small piece of painted iron will ignite the internal propulsion furnace of your dwarven ironfrog mover.

Name: Magicked Bed
Description: This flying furnishing eliminates the need to get up in the morningor ever. Modern magic put to good use at last!

Name: Innocent Gwiber Trumpet
Description: This horn-carved instrument emits an ethereal tone that beckons a light-touched innocent gwiber from its refuge.

Name: Circus Resonator
Description: A metal tuning fork that, when struck, emits an almost comically eerie tone which opens a temporary rift in the void, allowing your Circus ahriman to pass through to this plane.

Name: Brave New Y'shtola
Description:
Not wont to run from her troublesand couldn't get very far, anyway.

Use item to acquire the brave new Y'shtola minion.

Name: Wind-up Ryne
Description:
Not merely a palette swap.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Ryne minion.

Name: Black Hayate
Description:
Gaze upon the visage of a ruthless killer.

Use item to acquire the black hayate minion.

Name: Chameleon
Description:
Marvel as it melts into your surrounds...and then panic as you realize you cannot find it again.

Use item to acquire the chameleon minion.

Name: Wind-up Fuath
Description:
Markedly less murderous than the real thing.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Fuath minion.

Name: Armadillo Bowler
Description:
Possessed of a superior sense of balance.

Use item to acquire the armadillo bowler minion.

Name: The Great Serpent of Ronka
Description:
Tremble, child of man, for a creature of purest divinity wiggleth before thee.

Use item to acquire the Great Serpent of Ronka minion.

Name: Micro Gigantender
Description:
Is it small or is it big? You be the judge.

Use item to acquire the micro gigantender minion.

Name: Clionid Larva
Description:
Small on size but massive on appetite.

Use item to acquire the clionid larva minion.

Name: Bitty Duckbill
Description:
Do not attempt to put on your feet.

Use item to acquire the bitty duckbill minion.

Name: Eden Minor
Description:
Free of sin, though not for lack of trying.

Use item to acquire the Eden Minor minion.

Name: Giant Beaver
Description:
A mystery better left unsolved.

Use item to acquire the giant beaver minion.

Name: Wind-up Suzaku
Description:
Complete with her flute and her senses.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Suzaku minion.

Name: Wind-up Omega-M
Description:
Irrational behavior detected. Further observation required.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Omega-M minion.

Name: Wind-up Omega-F
Description:
Combat role allocation test initiated. Analyzing...

Use item to acquire the wind-up Omega-F minion.

Name: Tinker's Bell
Description:
Said to be named for a pixie...unless you ask the pixies, who adamantly deny that any of their kind would ever have borne such a ludicrous name.

Use item to acquire the tinker's bell minion.

Name: Tiny Echevore
Description:
Its tail tastes like nectar...but you wouldn't know such things.

Use item to acquire the tiny echevore minion.

Name: Sharksucker-class Insubmersible
Description:
Warning: do not immerse.

Use item to acquire the sharksucker-class insubmersible minion.

Name: Shoebill
Description:
An unflappable bird possessed of a regal air...or perhaps simply a condescending one.

Use item to acquire the shoebill minion.

Name: Butterfly Effect
Description:
Illusory and therefore incapable of invoking any history-shattering consequences...right?

Use item to acquire the butterfly effect minion.

Name: Ironfrog Ambler
Description:
A darling, diminutive, dwarven-made...automaton.

Use item to acquire the ironfrog ambler minion.

Name: Forgiven Hate
Description:
Having repented its sins, it poses no danger.

Use item to acquire the forgiven hate minion.

Name: Bicolor Gemstone
Description: A precious stone that shimmers with multiple hues.

Name: Tome of Geological Folklore - Norvrandt
Description: Tales gathered from local Vrandtic miners regarding the location of legendary ore veins and gem deposits.

Name: Tome of Botanical Folklore - Norvrandt
Description: Tales gathered from local Vrandtic botanists regarding the location of rare trees and herbs.

Name: Tome of Ichthyological Folklore - Norvrandt
Description: Tales gathered from local Vrandtic fishers regarding the location of legendary fish.

Name: Rising Token
Description: An official voucher issued to participants in the Calamity Retold. Celebrate Eorzea's rebirth by trading for fabulous prizes!

Name: Cracked Planicluster
Description:
A multifaceted crystalline manifestation of aetheric energy cracked through in several places.

[Can be exchanged for select combat-based varieties of materia VII.]

Name: Cracked Planicrystal
Description:
A multifaceted crystalline manifestation of aetheric energy cracked through in several places.

[Can be exchanged for select non-combat-based varieties of materia VII.]

Name: Cracked Stellacluster
Description:
A many-pointed crystalline manifestation of aetheric energy cracked through in several places.

[Can be exchanged for select combat-based varieties of materia VIII.]

Name: Cracked Stellacrystal
Description:
A many-pointed crystalline manifestation of aetheric energy cracked through in several places.

[Can be exchanged for select non-combat-based varieties of materia VIII.]

Name: Khloe's Bronze Certificate of Commendation
Description: An ever-so-slightly special award presented to you by Khloe Aliapoh. Try not to mind the numerous misspellings and juice stains.

Name: White Oak Weapon Coffer (IL 385)
Description:
A polished oak chest with lavish filigree that suggests a valuable weapon lies within.

Required level: 70. IL: 385. Weapon type determined by current job or class at time of opening. Cannot be opened in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.

Name: White Oak Waist Gear Coffer (IL 385)
Description: A polished oak chest with lavish filigree that suggests a valuable piece of attireor rather, a formerly valuable piece of attirelies within. Due to advancements in trouser technology, the belt within this chest is no longer worth the trouble of opening it.
