Name: Old Pumpkin Cookie MMXIX
Description: A devilishthough, admittedly, industriousimp is thought to have made this slightly burnt biscuit shaped like a pumpkin head. One can only wonder what ingredients it contains, but as the people of Eorzea have been consuming these for years now with no ill effects beyond mild disappointment, they're probably not too horrific.

Name: Metal Gauntlets
Description: A pair of sturdy-yet-flexible gauntlets, designed to protect the hands from amaro bites.

Name: Metal Worm Jar
Description: A metal jar designed to keep worms fresh.

Name: Metal Trident
Description: A fearsome metal weapon ending in three deadly looking spikes.

Name: Nullifying Neckpiece
Description: An amulet imbued with magic-resisting properties.

Name: Intricate Censer Materials
Description: A set of materials needed to forge an intricate censer.

Name: Intricate Censer
Description: A solid metal censer of exquisite design.

Name: Enchanting Ring Materials
Description: A set of materials needed to forge an enchanting ring.

Name: Enchanting Ring
Description: This finely wrought ring gleams with an almost sorcerous sheen.

Name: Canvas Repair Materials
Description: Materials for repairing the canvas of the painting of Dampsole, Lakeland.

Name: Upholstery Repair Materials
Description: Materials for repairing the upholstery of the Voeburtite jewelry box.

Name: Amaro Barding Repair Materials
Description: Materials for repairing the inner lining of the antique amaro barding.

Name: Lute Repair Materials
Description: Materials for repairing Harig's broken lute.

Name: Workshop Sign Materials
Description: Materials for crafting the sign for Cherished Memories.

Name: Workshop Sign
Description: The sign for Cherished Memories, masterfully crafted by your good self.

Name: Lute Modification Component Materials
Description: Materials for crafting the modification component for Harig's lute.

Name: Lute Modification Component
Description: The modification component that you hope will make Harig's lute sing as it once did.

Name: Edible Antidote
Description: A potent medicinal concoction mixed into a vegetable pure catering to amaro sensibilities.

Name: Nutrient-rich Porridge
Description: Wholesome and easily digestible food for delicate amaro stomachs.

Name: Fortifying Soup
Description: A comforting and invigorating vegetable and herb medley sure to have a restorative effect on both body and soul.

Name: Berube Feed
Description: This dish of assorted greens will be instantly recognizable to any Berube skipper as the feed it was raised on.

Name: Sweets Ingredients
Description: Assorted ingredients for the preparation of desserts that will please the faesuch as sugar, sugar, and more sugar.

Name: Offering of Sweets
Description: A variety of colorful confections to excite and delight the fae.

Name: Zun Culinary Components
Description: Assorted ingredients for the traditional amaro feed used by the Zun.

Name: Zun-style Amaro Feed
Description: The traditional nutritious feed used by the Zun in raising healthy and happy amaro.

Name: Brick Flooring

Name: Crystarium Chandelier

Name: Lily Floor Lamp
Description: This elegant lamp, its natural motifs rendered in polished and painted metal and glass, will make a master of white magic feel right at home.

Name: Lily Wall Lamp
Description: The reason that the sight of one of these warmly glowing light fixtures puts those with a penchant for healing so very much at ease will ever remain a mystery to people not versed in the secrets of white magic.

Name: Marble Arch Partition
Description: A large white partition with a marble-carved arch creating a portal through the center.

Name: Simple Curtain
Description: A yellow curtain gathered with a polished wooden fastener.

Name: Messy Dishes
Description: At least they're clean. Ish.

Name: Butterfly Specimen
Description: One of Il Mheg's many brilliant butterflies, mounted for display.

Name: Grocery Bag
Description: All manner of foodstuffs could be inside this plain brown shopping bag. ...Hopefully they did not require refrigeration.

Name: Hunting Supplies
Description: The requisite weapons and traps for a foray into the wilds.

Name: War Chest
Description: The requisite defensive and offensive accoutrements for combat.

Name: Imitation Stained Crystal Pane
Description: Though this is neither real crystal nor a real windowpane, the rear lighting makes it appear sumptuous all the same.

Name: Marble Partition
Description: A cream-colored partition with a white marble baseboard.

Name: Crystarium Bench
Description: A wrought-iron seat identical to those found throughout the Crystarium.

Name: Potted Orange Tree
Description: A small citrus tree in an elegant wrought-iron vessel.

Name: Crystarium Stove
Description: A warmly glowing iron kitchen stove.

Name: Crystarium Kitchen Hanger
Description: This wall-mounted hanger provides easy access to pots and pans for use in cooking or punctuating one's statements with loud clanging noises.

Name: Crystarium Teapot
Description: This metal teapot comes with a serving tray, cup, and jar of tea leaves for your convenience.

Name: Ruby Crystal Boule
Description: A mounted sample of the luminous red crystals that grow uninhibited on the sea floor.

Name: Crystarium Wall Chronometer
Description: Rather unfortunately for those attempting to get anywhere on time, this chronometer features a mesmerizing pattern and pendulum.

Name: Moonfire Faire MMXVIII Advertisement
Description: A hand-painted notice advertising the Eorzean Nimble Warrior course.

Name: All Saints' Wake MMXV Advertisement
Description: A hand-painted notice advertising the fantastical sorcery and spooks of All Saints' Wake.

Name: Crystarium Mechanical Till
Description: A convenient clockwork contraption for the counting and keeping of currency.

Name: Stuffed Fuath
Description: The manufacturer of this plush toy assures you that the gleam in its button eye is mischievous rather than murderous.

Name: Antique Vessels
Description: These remarkably well-preserved vessels, retrieved from their lengthy slumber on the sea floor, probably belong in a museum. Oh well.

Name: Decadent Fruit Platter
Description:
A branching golden vessel harboring enough fruit to feed two Crystarium families or one Eulmoran hedonist for several days.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Piety Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  VIT Bonus: +5% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Sandwich Basket
Description:
A picnic's worth of scrumptious sandwiches, aesthetically arranged.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Skill Speed Bonus: +4% (Max 2)
  VIT Bonus: +5% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Wooden Handrail
Description: This railing can be used to ensure that none will fall into the stairwell unless you push them.

Name: Misplaced Eyeglasses
Description: As the person to whom these eyeglasses belonged is now without eyeglasses, he will likely never be able to find them again and is probably wandering around bumping into things at this very moment.

Name: Carpet of Flowers
Description: A circular patch of rug upon which colorful flowers have been enchanted to grow. Not recommended for those with seasonal allergies.

Name: Blades of Innocence
Description:
A wall-mounted trophy that quite conclusively indicates your victory over Innocence, greatest of the Lightwardens.

One per estate only.

Name: Titania Shadow Box
Description:
A glimmering wall-mounted decoration featuring a pair of wings acquired in the Dancing Plague.

One per estate only.

Name: Season Thirteen Lone Wolf Trophy
Description: A trophy awarded to those who left their mark in Season Thirteen of the Feast.

Name: Team Season Pack Wolf Trophy
Description: A trophy awarded to those who left their mark in the Team Season of the Feast.

Name: Metal Work Lantern
Description: Though simple its design may be, there is no better lantern for those whose work requires reliable illumination.

Name: Wooden Work Lantern
Description: This unobtrusive lantern provides necessary illumination without sacrificing ambience.

Name: Alchemical Lantern
Description: An alchemical flame burns perpetually within the metal-and-glass casing of this lantern.

Name: Liberation
Description: A masterfully rendered oil depiction of key players in the conflict between the Garlean Empire and its erstwhile territories Ala Mhigo and Doma.

Name: The Legend Returns
Description: A masterfully rendered oil depiction of figures from Ivalician legend old and new.

Name: Rise of a New Sun
Description: A masterfully rendered oil depiction of certain employees of Garlond Ironworks and an enigmatic piece of technology.

Name: Under the Moonlight
Description: A masterfully rendered oil depiction of the erstwhile acting imperial viceroy of Doma, Yotsuyu, and those instrumental in her destruction.

Name: Prelude in Violet
Description: A masterfully rendered oil depiction of the ruthless Garlean elite and a few noble souls who sought to stop their nefarious machinations.

Name: Requiem for Heroes
Description: A masterfully rendered oil depiction of a noble warrior who journeyed across many a realm to fight for the sake of the common man.

Name: Crystarium Umbrella Stand
Description: A dark-blue vessel containing one umbrella of a style popular in the Crystarium.

Name: Stuffed Clionid
Description: Whether this plush toy can actually restore its owner to good health as is rumored is unclear, but it certainly does look as if it would like to.

Name: Fallen Tree
Description: The perfect yard ornament for those who wish to issue a reminder to passersby that they too shall someday fall and be reclaimed by the earth.

Name: Crystarium Striking Dummy
Description:
A striking dummy designed in the Crystarium fashion.

Up to three dummies may be placed in a single estate, regardless of type.

Name: Firebloom
Description: A delicate plant that casts a gentle glow upon its surrounds.

Name: Seastone Brazier
Description: A naturally luminous stone from the deep, mounted on a brazier in the Ondo fashion.

Name: Portable Pool
Description: A peculiar rubber enclosure that can be filled with water for purposes of mild entertainment.

Name: Wind Chime Stand
Description: Nothing says summer like the dissonant tinkling of half a dozen wind chimes at once.

Name: Hydrangea Seeds
Description:
Plants from these seeds will burst into bloom in brightly colored clusterslike fireworks in your very own home, without the danger of burning down your very own home.

For use in planters.

Name: Red Hydrangeas
Description:
A bunch of red hydrangeas, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Blue Hydrangeas
Description:
A bunch of blue hydrangeas, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Yellow Hydrangeas
Description:
A bunch of yellow hydrangeas, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Green Hydrangeas
Description:
A bunch of green hydrangeas, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Orange Hydrangeas
Description:
A bunch of orange hydrangeas, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Purple Hydrangeas
Description:
A bunch of purple hydrangeas, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: White Hydrangeas
Description:
A bunch of white hydrangeas, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Black Hydrangeas
Description:
A bunch of black hydrangeas, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Rainbow Hydrangeas
Description:
A bunch of multicolored hydrangeas, selectively fertilized to achieve a variety of vibrant colors.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Season Thirteen Pack Wolf Voucher A
Description: Documentation of noteworthy accomplishments for Season Thirteen of the Feast.

Name: Season Thirteen Pack Wolf Voucher B
Description: Documentation of noteworthy accomplishments for Season Thirteen of the Feast.

Name: Season Thirteen Pack Wolf Voucher C
Description: Documentation of noteworthy accomplishments for Season Thirteen of the Feast.

Name: Koro Armor Coffer
Description:
A banded chest containing a complete set of koro armor.

Required level: 1. IL: 1. Cannot be used in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.

Name: Gunro Armor Coffer
Description:
A banded chest containing a complete set of gunro armor.

Required level: 1. IL: 1. Cannot be used in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.

Name: Windfire Wheels of the Crimson Lotus
King Totem
Description: This ligneous idol was, once upon a time, carved by the pixies to celebrate their noble king Titania.

Name: Immaculate Totem
Description: A platinum idol created by the sin eaters...at Vauthry's command.

Name: Helm of Early Antiquity
Description:
A winged helmet forged by some ancient civilization, recovered from Eden's Gate.

Two helms can be traded for special headgear.

Name: Armor of Early Antiquity
Description:
Emblazoned armor forged by some ancient civilization, recovered from Eden's Gate.

Four suits can be traded for special body gear.

Name: Gauntlets of Early Antiquity
Description:
Wrought-iron gauntlets forged by some ancient civilization, recovered from Eden's Gate.

Two pairs can be traded for special arm gear.

Name: Chausses of Early Antiquity
Description:
Heavy chausses forged by some ancient civilization, recovered from Eden's Gate.

Four pairs can be traded for special leg gear.

Name: Greaves of Early Antiquity
Description:
Tarnished greaves forged by some ancient civilization, recovered from Eden's Gate.

Two pairs can be traded for special foot gear.

Name: Belt of Early Antiquity
Description: An ornamented belt created by some ancient civilization, recovered from Eden's Gate. Alas, advancements in trouser technology have rendered it worthless.

Name: Bangle of Early Antiquity
Description:
An extravagant bangle forged by some ancient civilization, recovered from Eden's Gate.

One bangle can be traded for a special accessory.

Name: Book of Resurrection
Description:
A short apocryphal tome presumably created by Eden for recordkeeping purposes.

Copies of the same Eden's Gate apocrypha can be traded for special gear.

Name: Book of Descent
Description:
A short apocryphal tome presumably created by Eden for recordkeeping purposes.

Copies of the same Eden's Gate apocrypha can be traded for special gear.

Name: Book of Inundation
Description:
A short apocryphal tome presumably created by Eden for recordkeeping purposes.

Copies of the same Eden's Gate apocrypha can be traded for special gear.

Name: Book of Sepulture
Description:
A short apocryphal tome presumably created by Eden for recordkeeping purposes.

Copies of the same Eden's Gate apocrypha can be traded for special gear.

Name: Blade of Early Antiquity
Description: A golden blade forged by some ancient civilization, recovered from Eden's Gate. Though such weapons were once considered highly valuable, demand has dried up and they are now essentially worthless.

Name: Deepshadow Solvent
Description: A clever alchemical potion concocted through the combined efforts of craftspeople from the Crystalline Mean's various facets. When applied in carefully measured amounts, it removes imperfections invisible to the naked eye from deepshadow weapons, thereby enhancing their more desirable attributes. However, advances in crafting technology have rendered it obsolete.

Name: Deepshadow Twine
Description: An alchemical thread woven through the combined efforts of craftspeople from the Crystalline Mean's various facets for the purpose of enhancing the attributes of deepshadow vestments. However, advances in crafting technology have rendered it obsolete.

Name: Deepshadow Coating
Description: This viscous concoction, devised through the combined efforts of craftspeople from the Crystalline Mean's various facets, can be used to seal deepshadow accessories with a lustrous stygian coating that enhances their attributes. However, advances in crafting technology have rendered it obsolete.

Name: Mowen's Token (Phantasmagoria)
Description: A note of promise received from Mowen for the delivery of Allagan tomestones of phantasmagoria. However, due to the Boutique of Splendors changing its policies, it is now worth less than the paper on which it is scribed.

Name: Lightweight Tomestone
Description: As the popular saying attests, Knowledge is power, though librarians will also claim, Knowledge is heavy, which is perhaps the reason why the Allagans developed this exceedingly thin means of storing data. Unfortunately, these tomestones are rather prone to being bent or snapped, and it is believed that many have fallen victim to the posteriors of careless scholars. This particular variety is not as highly sought as it once was, and may no longer be exchanged for other wares.

Name: Crystarium Tetra
Description:
This small freshwater fish raised in the Crystarium is, appropriately, a shade of blue resembling that of the Crystal Tower.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Laxan Carp
Description:
Despite what the name may imply, this variety of freshwater fish can be found in multiple locations in the Crystarium.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Asteroidea
Description:
This variety of starfish is a deep blue and shimmers like a comet's tail.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Jacketed Snail
Description:
This peculiar, though curiously endearing, gastropod is draped in layers of membrane.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Lover's Flower
Description:
Despite the petal-like appearance of their appendages, presenting a fistful of these mollusks to one's sweetheart is not recommended.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Sinspitter
Description:
This Crystarium freshwater fish is in fact much prettier than its crude name implies.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Wandering Catfish
Description:
This variety of catfish was named not for any particular propensity for travel, but rather after its homethe Wandering Stairs.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Crystal Knife
Description:
A slim, metal-colored freshwater fish from the Crystarium.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Skeletonfish
Description:
The flesh of this diminutive freshwater fish is so pale as to be translucent.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Milky Coral
Description:
White coral commonly found near the city of Eulmore.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Gravel Mussel
Description:
These shellfish are often scooped up by residents of the Derelicts to supplement their meager diets.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Crimson Sea Spider
Description:
Hopefully picking this up wasn't how you learned of the existence of sea spiders. If it wassurprise! Sea spiders are real.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Bonefish
Description:
These unappetizing specimens proliferate in the Derelicts, where residents have little choice but to scrape what flesh they can from them.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Eulmore Butterfly
Description:
A brightly colored and riotously patterned fish that looks right at home in the gaudy environs of Eulmore.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 1 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Red Hammerhead
Description:
Despite its whimsical appearance, this shark is nevertheless perfectly capable of biting one's face off if provoked.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 4 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Hard Candy
Description:
A glossy ball of moss found in Lakeland. Does not, in fact, taste like candy.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Water Ball
Description:
A rotund, white freshwater fish found in Lakeland.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Abyssal Snail
Description:
This gastropod sports an unusual purple shell.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Clean Saucer
Description:
In its natural habitat, this fish spends most of its time deep below the surface, skipping itself across the lakebed.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Rabbit Skipper
Description:
It is said that this fish's frolicsome nature gave rise to its namethough it is entirely possible that scholars retroactively came up with this explanation to conceal the fact that they simply named it after the first white thing that came to mind.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Xanthic Bass
Description:
This unusually vivid freshwater bass has scales of yellow and burnt orange.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Albino Caiman
Description:
A naturally pure white caiman.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Platinum Guppy
Description:
This beautiful freshwater fish was given its name by the Crystal Exarch, if rumors are to be believed.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Misty Killifish
Description:
The body of this freshwater fish is semi-transparent, like a thin fog over the sea.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Albino Rock Crab
Description:
A bright white crab snared in Lakeland.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Snakeskin Discus
Description:
This variety of vividly patterned freshwater fish is oft spotted near Sullen.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Albino Garfish
Description:
Its ghostly color and threatening size makes encountering this sort of garfish a uniquely alarming experience for folk fishing in the Source.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 3 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Vicejaw
Description:
An armor-plated fish found near the Isle of Ken, as vicious as it is ancient.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 4 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Skulleater
Description:
A bone white freshwater lobster from Kholusia.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Toffee Snail
Description:
A snail native to Kholusia. Though its shell is much more appetizing, its flesh is the only edible bit.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Watts Trout
Description:
A frankly unremarkable species of trout found in Watts River.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Hucho Taimen
Description:
This placid freshwater fish displays a distinct preference for calm currents.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Winged Hatchetfish
Description:
A freshwater fish with an oversized belly, commonly found in the upper reaches of Watts River.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Noble's Fan
Description:
Some say that this Kholusian fish looks just like a fan. Others say, more specifically, that it looks like a fan with the capacity to feel murderous rage.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Zebra Catfish
Description:
This catfish was named for its beautiful black-and-white pattern, reminiscent of the zebras occasionally pictured in storybooks.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Sepia Sole
Description:
A remarkably flat freshwater fish found in Kholusia.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Shellfracture Kelp
Description:
This variety of leafy kelp grows to incredible size off the southern coast of Kholusia.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Blood Cloud
Description:
Seen distantly from a boat, this jellyfish could be mistaken for the reflection of a red airship aboveor the gory aftermath of a violent underwater encounter.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Kholusian Flounder
Description:
A flatfish living off the coast of Kholusia.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: South Kholusian Cod
Description:
This common saltwater fish is a staple food for Kholusian locals.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Razorfish
Description:
This tiny saltwater fish swims with its head facing down toward the depths.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Rose Shrimp
Description:
This pink crustacean is both delicious and plentiful, resulting in its frequent use in a variety of Vrandtic dishes.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Shapeshifter
Description:
This octopus sports a mesmerizing black-and-white pattern, and is unnervingly skilled at both disguising itself and manipulating objects with its dextrous arms.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Minstrelfish
Description:
The urge to play this shark like a lute is best resisted.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Kholusian Wrasse
Description:
A knobbly-headed fish native to the oceans surrounding Kholusia.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Weedy Seadragon
Description:
This ocean-dweller could easily be mistaken for a clump of fallen autumn leaves.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Henodus
Description:
This ancient species, in modern times sighted only in the vicinity of Cracked Shell Beach, bears significant similarities to the tortoise.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Spearhead Squid
Description:
A reddish cephalopod with a pointed head.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Shadow Crab
Description:
This dark grey crab dwells in eastern Amh Araengor did until someone poached it.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Desert Dustfish
Description:
This variety of fish can be found frolicking amidst the sands of Amh Araeng.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Hornhelm
Description:
This sand-dwelling fish in fact boasts not merely one, but three hornlike protrusions.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Web-footed Sand Gecko
Description:
The minute pieces of webbing between this gecko's toes help to propel it across dry sands.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Sand Egg
Description:
This peculiar creature was found rolling its way across the sands despite having no visible means of propulsion.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Amber Lamprey
Description:
A blood red eel native to the Fields of Amber.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Desert Saw
Description:
Those already alarmed by the sight of this fish's vicious-looking fins protruding from the sands will be discomfited to know that its teeth are equally pointy.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Garik Crab
Description:
One of a species of crabs native to western Amh Araeng.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Nabaath Manta
Description:
This manta is able to glide effortlessly through sandy hill and valley in its desert home.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Thorned Lizard
Description:
One of several varieties of lizards that inhabit the desert sands of Amh Araeng.

[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Spotted Blue-eye
Description:
A large-finned killifish found in Il Mheg.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 1 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Official Ball
Description:
This rotund freshwater fish is native to Il Mhegmuch to its misfortune.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Grey Skipper
Description:
This variety of skipper is found all across Il Mheg, where it, paradoxically, stands out like a sore thumb due to its dull color.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Pixie Fish
Description:
The coloration of this fish reminds you of one pixie in particular. (They assure you there is no relation.)

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Blood-eyed Frog
Description:
This small amphibian boasts bright-red eyes, but overall is still much less weird than a Fuath.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Cherry Herring
Description:
This freshwater fish was named for its colorpresumably by someone poorly versed in specific shades of red.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Wimple Carp
Description:
A striped freshwater fish found in Handmirror Lake.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Lemonfish
Description:
A speckled, bright-yellow freshwater fish.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 1 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Rebel
Description:
In spite ofor perhaps to spiteits diminutive size, this freshwater wavekin can often be seen swimming upstream.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Wild Red Betta
Description:
A distinctly colored betta native to Longmirror Lake.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Spotted Ctenopoma
Description:
This fish's scales feature an eye-catching pattern in shades of brown.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Cerulean Loach
Description:
This bright blue fish can be found in aquatic environs throughout Il Mheg.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Golden Lobster
Description:
This massive lobster is so shiny that one could be forgiven for mistaking it for a gaudy decoration at first sight.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Toadhead
Description:
A dazed-looking fish found in Il Mheg.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 1 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Clawbow
Description:
This type of crab is native to the Rak'tika Greatwood, and was doubtless named by the Viis.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Black Tri-star
Description:
A spotted freshwater fish found at Lozatl's Conquest.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 1 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Robber Crab
Description:
A member of an omnivorous and aggressive species of hermit crab.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Darkroot
Description:
A black eel native to Woven Oath.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Yellow Pipira
Description:
A tiny-yet-fierce fish from the Rak'tika Greatwood.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Oathfish
Description:
One of a species of fish farmed by the Children of the Everlasting Dark...who will not be best pleased to find it has been poached.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Night's Bass
Description:
It is thought that this variety of bass was originally bred in Voeburt, and only later introduced to Rak'tika.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Rak'tika Trout
Description:
A member of a species of trout that thrives in the bough-sheltered waters of the Greatwood.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Clown Tetra
Description:
A freshwater fish patterned with broad black stripes.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Eryops
Description:
A massive and ancient amphibian found solely in Lake Tusi Mek'ta.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Diamond Pipira
Description:
A freshwater fish with gleaming silver-white scales.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Silver Kitten
Description:
A catfish caught at Mjrl's Regretmuch to its own regret, probably.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Darkdweller
Description:
A sinister-looking cave dweller native to Woven Oath.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 1 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Deep Purple Coral
Description:
A sharp piece of stinging coral. Handle with care, or not at all.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Sycorax
Description:
A silvery bivalve mollusk found in the Tempest.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Stormfish
Description:
A grey wavekin native to the Tempest.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Azure Sea Spider
Description:
A spindly-legged creature that, among other things, breathes through its porous exoskeleton.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Caliban
Description:
A hulking, prehistoric wavekin that dwelt in the Tempest.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Hoodwinker
Description:
A large, ovular saltwater fish with charming blue-and-white coloration.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Bubble Angler
Description:
The see-through flesh of this bizarre anglerfish makes it all the more disturbing to look at.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 1 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Ondo Harpoon
Description:
A sharp-nosed shark native to the Tempest.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Ondobane
Description:
This shark, native to the Tempest, is voracious, territorial, and massivewhich savvy fishers may recognize as the worst combination of traits for a shark to have.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 4 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Stippled Eel
Description:
A carnivorous eel covered with a complex and colorful pattern.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Seatrap
Description:
A deceptively delicate-looking anemone native to the Tempest.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Ancient Shrimp
Description:
An old, old shrimp with long, reaching pincers, arisen from the dark depths of the sea after untold centuries.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Yeti Crab
Description:
This pale deep-sea crustacean is entirely covered in fine white cilia.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Aapoak
Description:
Ancient relatives of the nautilus, aapoak are colloquially known as crawling gems for their rainbow-colored shells.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Cyan Sea Devil
Description:
A fiendishly clever horned octopus easily identifiable by its bright blue coloration.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Pancake Octopus
Description:
Though they make a valiant effort, members of this species of octopus never manage to look quite as sinister as any of their fellow deep-sea dwellers.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Maneater Clam
Description:
A bivalve mollusk with a shell that resembles nothing so much as rows of vicious teeth.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Stargazer
Description:
A deep-sea fish with a penchant for concealing itself among the sediment on the sea floor.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Sweetflesh Oyster
Description:
The only defense that this particularly delicious variety of oyster has against being devoured is its thick shell.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Rainbow Shrimp
Description:
As the coloration of these cousins to the mantis shrimp is entirely in the shell, consuming vast quantities of them will not, unfortunately, make its predators rainbow-colored in turn.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Predator
Description:
Quite literally everyone who has seen one of these Tempest-dwelling ancients open its maw has regretted the experience within moments.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Grey Carp
Description:
A common carp native to Lakeland.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Lilac Goby
Description:
A small, brightly colored freshwater fish native to Lakeland.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Purple Ghost
Description:
This particular species of freshwater fish has unusual organs that can produce powerful jolts of electricity. Rubber gloves recommended.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Lakelouse
Description:
If it looks like a vilekin, and crawls like a vilekin, it's...actually an arthropod with a robust exoskeleton.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Gazing Glass
Description:
This semi-transparent sphere harvested from the depths of the Source is actually a living creatureor was, before being unceremoniously torn from the water it requires to survive.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Source Octopus
Description:
A bright-purple cephalopod native to the Source.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Elven Spear
Description:
An aggressively territorial freshwater fish.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Shade Gudgeon
Description:
This timid wavekin's skin has been turned ghostly pale by overexposure to unbalanced aether.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Lakethistle
Description:
A rare and fascinating wavekin that acquires oxygen via pulmonary respiration rather than gills.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Platinum Bream
Description:
A shimmering, silvery fish.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Wardenfish
Description:
This massive undersea guardian was found stalking the depths around the Isle of Ken.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Finned Eggplant
Description:
Though its name is apt in terms of shape and coloration, this wavekin is considerably larger than all but the most freakishly oversized of eggplants.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Skykisser
Description:
A cloud-colored, highly social fish native to Lakeland.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Viola Clam
Description:
The delicate color and shape of this bivalve mollusk's shell make it reminiscent of a wind-kissed flower when seen through rippling water.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Geayi
Description:
This wavekin is instantly recognizable by the two bold black stripes that stand out starkly against its otherwise pale scales.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Noblefish
Description:
An elegantly shaped freshwater wavekin.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Misteye
Description:
Whether this ancient wavekin was always blind or if its eyes have simply been clouded by time is a riddle that no still-living person can answer.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 3 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Lakeland Cod
Description:
A member of a particularly large species of cod.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Little Bismarck
Description:
Fishers who wish to keep all of their remaining limbs intact would do well to remember that the name of this wavekin is not indicative of diminutive sizealmost all creatures are little compared to Bismarck.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 3 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Bothriolepis
Description:
A primeval wavekin found in the Source.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Big-eye
Description:
A colorful freshwater fish native to Il Mheg.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Jenanna's Tear
Description:
This bivalve mollusk was named in honor of a long-suffering queen of Voeburt.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Daisy Turban
Description:
These gastropods' sunny yellow shells have tricked spearfishers with poor eyesight into forgetting they were underwater on more than one occasion.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Shade Axolotl
Description:
Like most creatures native to Il Mheg, this amphibian is just odd enough to cause one to look twice.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Little Flirt
Description:
A gastropod named for the heart-shaped pink marking on its head.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Peallaidh
Description:
This peculiar wavekin wears a perpetually inscrutable expression.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Voeburt Bichir
Description:
An ancient wavekin native to what is now Il Mheg.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Poecilia
Description:
A freshwater wavekin with bright coloration resembling that of many pixies.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 1 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Gilded Batfish
Description:
A diminutive and delicate-looking freshwater fish found in Il Mheg.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Petalfish
Description:
A pale pink-and-blue wavekin that calls to mind a single flower petal adrift upon the water.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Mirrorfish
Description:
A freshwater wavekin native to Il Mheg known for its reflective scales.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Glass Eel
Description:
The long, thin body of this freshwater wavekin is a deep, glossy blue.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Voeburt Salamander
Description:
A large amphibian of a species long native to the area that is now Il Mheg.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Bedskipper
Description:
This variety of freshwater fish can be found reveling in the ponds and streams of the fae's gardenlike home.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Dandyfish
Description:
The eccentric reddish purple of this wavekin's fins gave rise to its teasing appellation.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Sauldia Ruby
Description:
A spherical, gemlike creature found in Il Mheg.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Mock Pixie
Description:
In a kinder world, this creature might have become a member of the fae. In this one, it seems to have made it less than halfway there.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Hunter's Arrow
Description:
This prehistoric creature was found lurking in Il Mheg.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Fuathgobbler
Description:
Does this large wavekin native to Il Mheg actually feed on Fuath? One can only hope.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Paradise Crab
Description:
The shell of this unusual crab is covered with mushrooms of such bright and appealing colors that they almost seem to be screaming, Eat me!

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Saint Fathric's Ire
Description:
A stinging anemone native to Il Mheg.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Queensgown
Description:
A freshwater fish named for its fabulously frilly fins.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Flowering Kelpie
Description:
This wavekin, which bizarrely resembles a sinister supernatural horse rendered in petal-pink, could only have originated in Il Mheg.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Ghoulfish
Description:
The flesh of this Il Mheg native's head is transparent, rendering its bright-purple innards visible to all who gaze upon itwhether they like it or not. 

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 3 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Measan Deala
Description:
A lemon yellow freshwater fish native to Il Mheg.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 3 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Dohn Horn
Description:
This creature's striped shell features several shades of vibrant green reminiscent of the foliage of Dohn Mheg.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Aquabloom
Description:
This creature's delicate, flower-like appearance succeeds admirably in disguising the fact that it is, essentially, a slug.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Jester Fish
Description:
A freshwater wavekin with colorful fins and bulging eyes.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Blue Lightning
Description:
This unusual wavekin is remarkably hydrodynamic.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Maidenhair
Description:
The sweeping, golden fins of this freshwater wavekin might, in autumn, be mistaken for fallen leaves from the tree that is its namesake.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Blue Mountain Bubble
Description:
The fins of this rotund fish, native to Longmirror Lake, are suggestive of butterfly wings.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Elder Pixie
Description:
A gastropod with bright green markings and appendages resembling wings.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Ankle Snipper
Description:
Freshwater crabs of this species native to the Rak'tika Greatwood are not known for their discrimination in what they clamp with their claws when they are surprised, threatened, or merely in a bad mood.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Treescale
Description:
These bivalve mollusks are often found nestled between underwater roots in the Rak'tika Greatwood.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Ronkan Pleco
Description:
This variety of pleco bears ivory stripes in a pattern suggestive of the veins on a leaf.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Gourmand Crab
Description:
Though this crab is omnivorous in the sense that it will eat both flesh and plant matter, this should not be taken to mean that it does not have a discerning palate.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Gatorl's Bead
Description:
This species of blood red freshwater wavekin inhabits the ponds and marshes of the Rak'tika Greatwood.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Diamondtongue
Description:
This ancient breed of wavekin is prized for the way in which its scales glimmer in the light.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Hermit's Hood
Description:
A tiny mollusk native to Lake Tusi Mek'ta.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Hermit Crab
Description:
This species of crab is known for its cowardice and incredibly specific shell preferences.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Megapiranha
Description:
A specimen belonging to a vicious species that seems to have survived largely unchanged since time immemorial.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Everdark Bass
Description:
This species was allegedly bred by the Voeburtites in their homeland before making its way to the Rak'tika Greatwood.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Lozatl Pirarucu
Description:
A large freshwater wavekin native to the Rak'tika Greatwood.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Anpa's Handmaid
Description:
A large, silvery wavekin that features in Ronkan myth.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 3 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Viis Ear
Description:
These sea slugs are generally content to let the current carry them where it will.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Rak'tika Goby
Description:
Their odd shape and placement make this striped fish's fins its most unique feature.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Fruit Worm
Description: A nascent wriggler torn from the fragrant fruit's flesh in which it hatched. Live bait for freshwater fishing.

Name: Moyebi Shrimp
Description: Conveniently enough, the sickly tinge this shrimp has taken on from the algae it eats makes it no less appetizing to other creatures in the aquatic food chain. Live bait for ocean fishing.

Name: Desert Dessert Frog
Description: A charming dunefishing lure carved from plain wood to pose as a sweet treat for sandfish.

Name: Marble Nymph
Description: The unnervingly pale larva of a stonefly. Live bait for freshwater fishing.

Name: Jerked Ovim
Description: A sun-dried strip of ovim flesh. Fishers love itfish do too. Live bait for dunefishing.

Name: Robber Ball
Description: A soft ball of robber crab flesh and sunset flour paste. Processed bait for freshwater fishing.

Name: Short Bill Minnow
Description: An ocean fishing lure that looks and moves like a tiny, bright fish.

Name: Baitbugs
Description: A box full of wriggling water insects. Appetizing. Live bait for freshwater fishing.

Name: Squid Strip
Description: A thin piece of cephalopod flesh. Live(ish) bait for ocean fishing.

Name: Freshwater Boilie
Description:
A hard, round ball incorporating multiple highly effective baitsdesigned by fishers, for fishers. All-purpose bait for freshwater fishing, dunefishing, and cloudfishing.

Has no effect on certain fish.

Name: Saltwater Boilie
Description:
A hard, round ball incorporating multiple highly effective baitsdesigned by fishers, for fishers. All-purpose bait for ocean fishing, dunefishing, and cloudfishing.

Has no effect on certain fish.

Name: Altered Heavy Steel Armor
Description: Cannot equip gear to head.

Name: Altered High Mythril Armor
Description: Cannot equip gear to head.

Name: Altered Linen Cowl
Description: Cannot equip gear to head.

Name: Altered Woolen Cowl
Description: Cannot equip gear to head.

Name: White Oak Log
Description: A rough-cut log of white oak timber.

Name: Miracle Apple Log
Description: A rough-cut log of miracle apple timber.

Name: White Ash Log
Description: A rough-cut log of white ash timber.

Name: Sandteak Log
Description: A rough-cut log of sandteak timber.

Name: Lignum Vitae Log
Description: A rough-cut log of lignum vitae timber.

Name: Sandalwood Log
Description: A rough-cut log of sandalwood timber.

Name: White Oak Lumber
Description: Processed white oak lumber.

Name: Miracle Apple Lumber
Description: Processed miracle apple lumber.

Name: White Ash Lumber
Description: Processed white ash lumber.

Name: Sandteak Lumber
Description: Processed sandteak lumber.

Name: Lignum Vitae Lumber
Description: Processed lignum vitae lumber.

Name: Sandalwood Lumber
Description: Processed sandalwood lumber.

Name: Multifaceted Varnish
Description: A single coat of this all-in-one sealant, created in a collaborative effort by the Mean's various facets, can strengthen, protect, and polish any wooden surface to which it is applied.

Name: Truegold Sand
Description: Bright sand that shines like the sun, consisting of tiny grains of truegold.

Name: Truegold Ore
Description: A decent-sized piece of rock containing the metal truegold, both harder and more colorful than standard gold.

Name: Bluespirit Ore
Description: A sizable hunk of the remarkably aether-rich mineral known as bluespirit.

Name: Manasilver Sand
Description: Sand that moves almost as a liquid, consisting of tiny grains of manasilver.

Name: Titancopper Sand
Description: Varicolored sand consisting of tiny grains of titanium and copper.

Name: Titancopper Ore
Description: A decent-sized piece of rock containing a naturally occurring mixture of titanium and copper.

Name: Dimythrite Sand
Description: Darkly glowing sand consisting of tiny grains of dimythrite.

Name: Dimythrite Ore
Description: A decent-sized piece of rock containing what appears to be dimythrite.

Name: Tungsten Ore
Description: A decent-sized piece of rock containing the metal tungsten.

Name: Prismstone
Description: This peculiar type of stone shines with all the colors of the rainbow.

Name: Deepgold Nugget
Description: A small nugget of impure deepgold.

Name: Stonegold Nugget
Description: A small nugget of impure stonegold.

Name: Deepgold Ingot
Description: An ingot of smelted deepgold.

Name: Stonegold Ingot
Description: An ingot of smelted stonegold.

Name: Manasilver Nugget
Description: A small nugget of impure manasilver.

Name: Bluespirit Tile
Description: A thin slab of cut and polished bluespirit.

Name: Titanbronze Nugget
Description: A small nugget of impure titanbronze alloy.

Name: Titanbronze Ingot
Description: An ingot of smelted titanbronze.

Name: Dwarven Mythril Ingot
Description: An ingot of smelted dwarven mythril.

Name: Dwarven Mythril Nugget
Description: A small nugget of impure dwarven mythril.

Name: Tungsten Steel Ingot
Description: An ingot of smelted tungsten steel.

Name: Prismatic Ingot
Description: A thin slab of cut and polished prismstone.

Name: Multifaceted Abrasive
Description: This all-in-one abrasive, created in a collaborative effort by the Mean's various facets, can be used to both sand metals and polish them to a lustrous sheen.

Name: Multifaceted Resin
Description: This all-in-one resin, created in a collaborative effort by the Mean's various facets, can be used as either an adhesive or protective varnish as necessary.

Name: Hematite
Description: A silver-black jewel.

Name: Diaspore
Description: A light-green jewel.

Name: Lazurite
Description: A clear blue jewel.

Name: Triplite
Description: An amber jewel.

Name: Petalite
Description: A whitish jewel.

Name: Onyx
Description: A starkly black jewel.

Name: Raw Hematite
Description: An uncut, unpolished stone containing what appears to be hematite.

Name: Raw Diaspore
Description: An uncut, unpolished stone containing what appears to be diaspore.

Name: Raw Lazurite
Description: An uncut, unpolished stone containing what appears to be lazurite.

Name: Raw Triplite
Description: An uncut, unpolished stone containing what appears to be triplite.

Name: Raw Petalite
Description: An uncut, unpolished stone containing what appears to be petalite.

Name: Raw Onyx
Description: An uncut, unpolished stone containing what appears to be onyx.

Name: Smilodon Skin
Description: The sleek hide of a smilodon.

Name: Green Glider Skin
Description: The glistening veridian hide of a glider.

Name: Atrociraptor Skin
Description: The coarse hide of an atrociraptor.

Name: Zonure Skin
Description: The resilient hide of a zonure.

Name: Sea Swallow Skin
Description: The slippery hide of a sea swallow.

Name: Chalicotherium Skin
Description: The short-haired hide of a giant odd-toed ungulate.

Name: Smilodon Leather
Description: A large piece of cured smilodon skin.

Name: Green Glider Leather
Description: A large piece of cured green glider skin.

Name: Atrociraptor Leather
Description: A large piece of cured atrociraptor skin.

Name: Zonure Leather
Description: A large piece of cured zonure skin.

Name: Sea Swallow Leather
Description: A large piece of cured sea swallow skin.

Name: Chalicotherium Leather
Description: A large piece of cured chalicotherium skin.

Name: Multifaceted Alumen
Description: This all-in-one alumen, refined and modified in a collaborative effort by the Mean's various facets, is used to tan and deodorize hides.

Name: Bright Linen Cloth
Description: Several yalms of undyed white fabric.

Name: Bright Linen Yarn
Description: Sturdy yarn spun from bright linen.

Name: Bright Flax
Description: This flowering plant, hardy enough to grow in harsh climes, has a stalk that can be used in the spinning of a naturally white yarn.

Name: Iridescent Silk
Description: Not only does this fabric have a lustrous sheen, it also shimmers with hints of myriad colors.

Name: Iridescent Silk Thread
Description: Shimmering thread spun from iridescent cocoons.

Name: Iridescent Cocoon
Description: This worm-spun cocoon reflects a rainbow's worth of colors in the light.

Name: Pixie Cotton
Description: A soft fabric woven from pixie floss.

Name: Pixie Floss
Description: Unbelievably delicate cotton thread.

Name: Pixie Floss Boll
Description: The brilliantly white flower of an unusual variety of cotton plant.

Name: Ovim Wool
Description: Resilient fabric woven with the hair of the mountain-dwelling ovim.

Name: Ovim Wool Yarn
Description: Coarse yarn spun from ovim fleece.

Name: Ovim Fleece
Description: Long, lustrous hair shorn from an ovim.

Name: Dwarven Cotton
Description: This thick-yet-supple variety of cotton is the traditional cloth of the dwarven peoplewhich makes it the best cloth, as far as said people are concerned.

Name: Dwarven Cotton Thread
Description: Versatile thread spun from dwarven cotton bolls.

Name: Dwarven Cotton Boll
Description: Flowers of the coincidentally short-stalked dwarven cotton plant are used by the people bearing the same name to create everything from undergarments to beards.

Name: Ethereal Silk
Description: This sheen of this oft-sought, rarely found silk is at once both foreign and familiar.

Name: Ethereal Cocoon
Description: As difficult to lay hands upon as bubbles on the water, from these cocoons can be spun a rare type of silk.

Name: Multifaceted Cotton Cloth
Description: This multi-purpose cloth, created through collaborative efforts by the Mean's various facets, is soft, supple, and durable.

Name: Hoptrap Leaf
Description: The thin, twitching leaf of a hoptrap.

Name: Silkmoth Scales
Description: The powdery scales of a silkmoth's wing.

Name: Growth Formula Iota
Description: This alchemically formulated potation accelerates the growth of foliage.

Name: Enchanted Truegold Ink
Description: Ink fortified with truegold sand to improve aetherial conductivity.

Name: Grade 1 Strength Alkahest
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this experimental alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to strength, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Grade 1 Dexterity Alkahest
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this experimental alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to dexterity, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Grade 1 Vitality Alkahest
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this experimental alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to vitality, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Grade 1 Intelligence Alkahest
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this experimental alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to intelligence, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Grade 1 Mind Alkahest
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this experimental alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to mind, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Enchanted Manasilver Ink
Description: Ink fortified with manasilver sand to improve aetherial conductivity.

Name: Vampire Cup Vine
Description: The thick, leathery vine of a vampire cup.

Name: Vampire Vine Sap
Description: Sap harvested from the vampire vinethankfully not the color of blood.

Name: Starch Glue
Description: An adhesive substance created by boiling down assorted plant matter.

Name: Extra Effervescent Water
Description: Naturally sparkling water bottled at the source. Do not shake before opening.

Name: Refined Natron
Description: A pure white powder with no trace of impurity. Used in alchemy as a deodorizer and leavening agent.

Name: Growth Formula Kappa
Description: This alchemically formulated potation accelerates the growth of foliage.

Name: Sweet Alyssum
Description: This plant that blooms with myriad tiny flowers smelling of honey.

Name: Fernleaf Lavender
Description: A fragrant herb with notched leaves.

Name: Enchanted Dimythrite Ink
Description: Ink fortified with dimythrite sand to improve aetherial conductivity.

Name: Underground Spring Water
Description: Clear, sweet water bottled at its subterranean source.

Name: Lime Basil
Description: A herb that smells strongly of citrus.

Name: Tiger Lily
Description: A variety of tall-growing lily, the bulbs of which can be used in various medicines.

Name: Light Gerbera
Description: A type of gerbera named for its bright white flowers.

Name: Tincture of Strength
Description:
This diluted brew temporarily increases strength for twice the duration of similar potions.

Duration: 30s

Name: Tincture of Dexterity
Description:
This diluted brew temporarily increases dexterity for twice the duration of similar potions.

Duration: 30s

Name: Tincture of Vitality
Description:
This diluted brew temporarily increases vitality for twice the duration of similar potions.

Duration: 30s

Name: Tincture of Intelligence
Description:
This diluted brew temporarily increases intelligence for twice the duration of similar potions.

Duration: 30s

Name: Tincture of Mind
Description:
This diluted brew temporarily increases mind for twice the duration of similar potions.

Duration: 30s

Name: Grade 2 Strength Alkahest
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this experimental alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to strength, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Grade 2 Dexterity Alkahest
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this experimental alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to dexterity, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Grade 2 Vitality Alkahest
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this experimental alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to vitality, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Grade 2 Intelligence Alkahest
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this experimental alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to intelligence, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Grade 2 Mind Alkahest
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this experimental alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to mind, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Multifaceted Alchemic
Description: This alchemical concoction, created through collaborative efforts by the Mean's various facets, can be put to myriad usesnot all of them safe or recommended.

Name: Lorikeet Down

Description: The coarse-grained, elementally aspected remnants of aetherially reduced matter.

Description: The coarse-grained, elementally aspected remnants of highly concentrated aetherially reduced mineral matter.
