Name: Season Fifteen Pack Wolf Voucher B
Description: Documentation of noteworthy accomplishments for Season Fifteen of the Feast.

Name: Season Fifteen Pack Wolf Voucher C
Description: Documentation of noteworthy accomplishments for Season Fifteen of the Feast.

Name: Season Fourteen Lone Wolf Trophy
Description: A trophy awarded to those who left their mark in Season Fourteen of the Feast.

Name: Season Fifteen Lone Wolf Trophy
Description: A trophy awarded to those who left their mark in Season Fifteen of the Feast.

Name: Morbol Horn
Description: This horn of bone emits a deep tone (and a retch-inducing odor) that will bring your morbol undulating to your side.

Name: Portly Porxie Horn
Description: Wrought of clay, this horn emits a mellow sound and the aroma of cured meats to lure your portly porxie to your side.

Name: Epimetheus Identification Key
Description: A thin, rectangular piece of what appears to be cermet. Placing it near your Epimetheus will bring the machine roaring alarmingly to life.

Name: Menoetius Identification Key
Description: A thin, rectangular piece of what appears to be cermet. Placing it near your Menoetius will bring the machine roaring alarmingly to life. (Manufacturer not responsible for any acts of hubris committed by this vehicle or its operator.)

Name: Construct VII Core
Description: Rumors that this core and the mechanical golem it activates are heavily based on an Ivalician design are entirely unfounded. Well, almost.

Name: Shadow Gwiber Trumpet
Description: This horn-carved instrument emits an ethereal tone that beckons a dark-touched shadow gwiber from its refuge.

Name: Spriggan Stonecarrier Horn
Description: The plangent honking of this horn summons your spriggan stonecarrier, eager to hoist you aloft and scamper away.

Name: Forgiven Reticence Horn
Description: Thrumming with the power of Light, this horn emits a muted sound that summons forth your forgiven reticence.

Name: Dhalmel Whistle
Description: This appropriately lengthy wind pipe calls a dhalmel loping to your side.

Name: Albino Karakul Horn
Description: This horn of carved...horn emits a tone to which your albino karakul is well attuned.

Name: Eulmoran Inner Wall
Description: A deep scarlet interior wall with a slightly rough texture for those estate owners who wish to recreate the opulence of Eulmore.

Name: Eulmoran Marble Flooring
Description: Smooth, elegant floor tiling made of deep green marble.

Name: Eulmoran Chandelier
Description: A bright and elegant ceiling light identical to those found throughout Eulmore.

Name: Starlight Goobbue Wreath
Description: A stuffed goobbue sits within a festive wreath, its mouth agape, ready to devour your soul.

Name: Indoor Oriental Garden
Description: A miniaturized version of a traditional Far Eastern garden, complete with stone bridge, bamboo, and deer scarer.

Name: Oriental Chawan-mushi Lunch
Description:
A piping hot bowl of the classic Far Eastern dish, with a wealth of vegetables and other delicious ingredients hiding within the egg custard.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Spell Speed Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  VIT Bonus: +5% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Oasis Wall-mounted Fountain
Description: A wall-mounted fountain that sends water tumbling into the decorative dish below, reminiscent of the desert abodes found throughout Thanalan.

Name: Flooring Mat
Description: A large, square mat made from long wooden planks, perfect for decorating interior floors. It can be dyed in a variety of colors to match any sort of dcor.

Name: Golden Ewer
Description: A decorative metallic ewer that will bring a touch of decadence to any interior.

Name: Dishware
Description: A full set of dishes, washed and all.

Name: Imitation Long Window
Description: Its size and ability to illuminate your abode despite merely being mounted on your wall are sure to impress your guests.

Name: Imposing Ishgardian Shelf
Description: An exceedingly large frame that is so heavy it must be placed on the floor, rather than mounted on a wall. It features a striking image of Ishgard, so true to life that you can almost feel an icy chill exuding from the painting.

Name: Stuffed Hraesvelgr
Description: As few homeowners have the space to accommodate a member of the first brood, this stuffed version of Hraesvelgr has been created especially for those who enjoy the sensation of an ancient dragon observing their every move.

Name: Misplaced Mog Slippers
Description: These delightful slippers can be placedor misplacedalmost anywhere inside your home, allowing you to enjoy gazing at a prize pair of pom-poms whenever you please.

Name: Basket of Flowers
Description: A simple basket of blooms that will work wonders in brightening up your home, despite not requiring a great deal of space.

Name: Hades Trophy
Description:
An ominous reminder of an unforgettable encounter with Hades, featuring a hefty base and ever-ominous purple aura.

One per estate only.

Name: Ale Tap
Description: Despite being able to be placed on top of almost any interior surface, it is capable of producing a stream of delicious ale whenever you please.

Name: Allagan Tomestone of Frivolity
Description: While this particular tomestone does not appear to have any function whatsoever, it does add a dash of Allagan style to your interior. Be careful where you place it, however, as it will be even more useless if you accidentally step on it.

Name: Tabletop Hat Stand
Description: Comes complete with its own orange, wide-brimmed hat, which unfortunately appears to be stuck to the stand with rather strong adhesive.

Name: Vanity Mirror
Description: This gold-framed mirror reflects your true self. Your true self apparently glows in a rather unsettling fashion.

Name: Necklace Display Stand
Description: This stand can be placed on almost any surface, though it is only capable of displaying one type of necklace, which cannot be removed.

Name: Empty Boxes
Description: Though they take up rather a lot of floor space, this pile of boxes gives the impression that you have a host of admirers willing to shower you with giftswhich is surely more than worth the increased difficulty of walking through your home.

Name: Set of Liquor Bottles
Description: Having a comprehensive selection of unopened drinks is a sign of good taste and restraint. These seven bottles of varying colors and sizes will add a touch of class wherever you place them, except for beside your bed, perhaps.

Name: Starlight Celebration MMXVIII Advertisement
Description: A commissioned painting which depicts the Starlight Celebration choir and their delighted audience.

Name: Starlight Roll Cake
Description:
Two cream-filled sponge cakes complete with strawberries on top. While it may not be the most obvious choice for a festive treat, the color scheme certainly conjures up images of the Starlight Celebration.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Piety Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  VIT Bonus: +5% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Log Partition
Description: A partition designed in the style of a rustic cottage, reaching to the ceiling and so sturdy it may as well be a wall.

Name: Stuffed Giant Beaver
Description: While not quite as gigantic as an actual giant beaver, its blank expression is equally disconcerting.

Name: Stuffed Porxie
Description: Although porxies are generally created from animated clay, and are akin to porcelain, this stuffed version is somehow far more rigid.

Name: Handmade Akabeko
Description: The year of the ox simply would be incomplete without a pair of nodding cattle in every home. May their nodding never cease, even after their appointed year comes to an end.

Name: Chocolate Fountain
Description:
Complete with a range of fruit and other sweet treats. Just try not to get any chocolate on the upholstery.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Determination Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  VIT Bonus: +5% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Vegetable Garden
Description: An enormous patch of soil for growing vegetables, complete with a selection of verdant crops.

Name: Cedar Tree
Description: A towering cedar tree that retains its vibrant green throughout the year.

Name: Armorer's Stall
Description: Place this stall in your garden to play at armorer whenever the mood takes you.

Name: Weaponsmith's Stall
Description: Place this stall in your garden to play at weaponsmith whenever the mood takes you.

Name: Jeweler's Stall
Description: Place this stall in your garden to play at jeweler whenever the mood takes you.

Name: Florist's Stall
Description: Place this stall in your garden to play at florist whenever the mood takes you.

Name: Baker's Stall
Description: Place this stall in your garden to play at baker whenever the mood takes you.

Name: Fruiterer's Stall
Description: Place this stall in your garden to play at fruiterer whenever the mood takes you.

Name: Greengrocer's Stall
Description: Place this stall in your garden to play at greengrocer whenever the mood takes you.

Name: Bookseller's Stall
Description: Place this stall in your garden to play at bookseller whenever the mood takes you.

Name: Enchanter's Stall
Description: Place this stall in your garden to play at enchanter whenever the mood takes you.

Name: Butcher's Stall
Description: Place this stall in your garden to play at butcher whenever the mood takes you.

Name: Trader's Cottage Walls
Description:
A set of four walls designed for those who wish to transform their estate into a trader's shop.

Can only be used with cottages on small plots of land.

Name: Trader's House Walls
Description:
A set of four walls designed for those who wish to transform their estate into a trader's shop.

Can only be used with houses on medium plots of land.

Name: Trader's Mansion Walls
Description:
A set of four walls designed for those who wish to transform their estate into a trader's shop.

Can only be used with mansions on large plots of land.

Name: Campanula Seeds
Description:
These seeds grow into what are commonly known as bellflowers, which are said to be edible. Good to know if one were to find oneself with a lack of victuals but an abundance of these dainty blooms.

For use in planters.

Name: Red Campanulas
Description:
A bunch of red campanulas, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Blue Campanulas
Description:
A bunch of blue campanulas, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Yellow Campanulas
Description:
A bunch of yellow campanulas, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Green Campanulas
Description:
A bunch of green campanulas, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Orange Campanulas
Description:
A bunch of orange campanulas, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Purple Campanulas
Description:
A bunch of purple campanulas, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: White Campanulas
Description:
A bunch of white campanulas, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Black Campanulas
Description:
A bunch of black campanulas, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Rainbow Campanulas
Description:
A bunch of multicolored campanulas, selectively fertilized to achieve a variety of vibrant colors.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Laxan Inkhorn
Description:
A spiral-shaped mollusk that secretes a bizarre purple liquid.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: White Oil Perch
Description:
A docile freshwater wavekin that inhabits the plunge pool of White Oil Falls.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Faeshine Clam
Description:
This bivalve mollusk is believed to have been granted its pearlescent sheen by the pixies themselves.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Areng Dire
Description:
Those with the bravery to face its snapping jaws and the strength to prise open its thick shell are rewarded with a highly nutritious meal.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Kholusian King Crab
Description:
Though few can deny its exquisite taste when cooked, some may feel that this species is rather lacking in king-like qualities.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Flyer Printing Set
Description: Contains almost everything needed to make several bundles of flyers. Elbow grease not included.

Name: Kholusian Cuisine Set
Description: Contains all the seasonings, condiments, and utensils needed to produce a range of hearty, yet affordable, dishes. Meat of questionable origin, popotoes, and general greenery sold separately.

Name: Honeybee Trappings
Description: There are enough sequins, spangly things, and assorted frippery here to turn even the plainest of scullery maids into a dazzling songbird. Provided that she can actually sing, that is.

Name: Airship Fittings
Description: To decorate an airship to the exacting standards of Eulmoran high society, only the finest of handcrafted ornamentation using the most opulent of materials will suffice. Provided that no one looks too closely, the contents of this crate should pass muster.

Name: Beehive Souvenir
Description: These delightful trinkets serve as perfect conversation pieces, though the designs vary significantly depending on what random odds and ends happened to be available at the time of creation.

Name: Raven Coal
Description: Once the dense coal has been ground into powder and mixed with water, it can be used as a substitute for ink. Be sure to keep it away from white clothing, as the stains are a bugger to get out.

Name: Amh Araeng Seasonings
Description: This selection of rare varieties of salt and spices native to Amh Araeng can be used to add a dash of elegance and a pinch of class to even the most unappetizing of dishes.

Name: Clinquant Stones
Description: Every region of Norvrandt is, for some reason, blessed with an astonishing variety of glittering, shimmering, sparkling, and otherwise shiny stones. Il Mheg is no exception, as is amply demonstrated by these fine specimens.

Name: Airship Fitting Components
Description: In the hands of an artisan, these bits and pieces gathered from around Amh Araeng will eventually become the decorations used to adorn Eulmore's fleet of airships. In fact, it took another sort of artisan to even find them in the first place, having been forced to separate the proverbial wheat from the chaff in some of the desert's most perilous locations.

Name: Kholusian Miscellany
Description: While not everything included in this assortment of locally sourced materials could be considered valuable, the various items combine to convey the very essence of Kholusia. This could, however, be attributed to the pungent oceanic odor they all seem to share.

Name: Flyer Printing Materials
Description: Perhaps one day, these humble materials will fulfill their dream of being turned into flyers to advertise Eulmore's finest drinking and ogling establishment. With your help, this dream may very well come true.

Name: Kholusian Cuisine Paraphernalia
Description: An artisan's touch is required to turn this hodgepodge into something the Beehive's kitchen staff can use to produce its reasonably priced and reasonably tasty fare.

Name: Honeybee Trappings Materials
Description: As sparkly and fabulous as these assorted materials may be, they have a long way to go before they can be added to the costume worn by the Beehive's songstress.

Name: Airship Fitting Materials
Description: Few could envision that these rather uninspiring objects will eventually be soaring gracefully through the skies. Strictly speaking, it will be the airship to which they are attached that will be doing the flying, but it still counts.

Name: Beehive Souvenir Materials
Description: As anyone who has had the dubious pleasure of visiting a seaside tourist trap can attest, the majority of the souvenirs sold are made from cheap and readily available materials, often found washed up on the shore along with the driftwood and dead jellyfish. The contents of this bag areas is traditionof similar ilk, clearly indicated by the dried seaweed with which most of the items are covered.

Name: Warg Belt of Fending
Description: Before becoming obsolete due to advancements in tailoring, belts such as this were used for holding up trousers and the like.

Name: Warg Belt of Maiming
Description: Before becoming obsolete due to advancements in tailoring, belts such as this were used for holding up trousers and the like.

Description: Before becoming obsolete due to advancements in tailoring, belts such as this were used for holding up trousers and the like.

Name: Warg Belt of Casting
Description: Before becoming obsolete due to advancements in tailoring, belts such as this were used for holding up trousers and the like.

Augmented Facet Plate Belt of Fending
Description: Before becoming obsolete due to advancements in tailoring, belts such as this were used for holding up trousers and the like.

Description: Before becoming obsolete due to advancements in tailoring, belts such as this were used for holding up trousers and the like.

Description: Before becoming obsolete due to advancements in tailoring, belts such as this were used for holding up trousers and the like.

Description: Before becoming obsolete due to advancements in tailoring, belts such as this were used for holding up trousers and the like.

Name: Dragonsong Reproduction
Description: A large-scale reproduction of a piece entitled Dragonsong.

Name: Liberation Reproduction
Description: A large-scale reproduction of a piece entitled Liberation.

Name: Nightfall Reproduction
Description: A large-scale reproduction of a piece entitled Nightfall.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Celebratory Cups
Description: An illustrated manual of how to raise one's glass without causing offense or undue dampness. Use to learn the /toast emote.

Name: Kingly Peacock Horn
Description: A horn that, when blown, summons a peacock to bear you in majesty.

Name: Majestic Dress
Description: Fits: All

Name: Majestic Wristdresses
Description: Fits: All

Name: Majestic Boots
Description: Fits: All

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Omega Simulations
Description: An illustrated manual detailing how to imitate an inexplicable opponent. Use to learn the /simulationm and /simulationf emotes.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - The Winsome Wallflower
Description: An illustrated not-quite-instruction manual that is nevertheless instructive in warding off potential dance partnersand looking good doing so. Use to learn the /lean emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Feigning Fatigue
Description: An illustrated manual of how to avoid the unwanted attention of would-be suitors, overbearing great-aunts, and other such dullards by pretending to have been overcome by a sudden bout of giddiness. Use to learn the /headache emote.

Name: Modern Cosmetics - A Wicked Wake
Description:
The realm's premier publication on cosmeticsas well as dating advice and, for some reason, politicsthis copy of Modern Cosmetics covers, in detail, techniques for painting an appropriately spooky All Saints' Wake pattern on one's cheek.

Use to unlock new face paint at the aesthetician.

Name: Modern Aesthetics - Modern Legend
Description:
The realm's premier publication on beauty and fashion, this specific copy of Modern Aesthetics covers, in detail, techniques on styling oneself to resemble the hero of the world's oldest fable.

Use to unlock a new hairstyle at the aesthetician.
Unavailable to female Hrothgar.

Name: Hades Barding
Description: A suit of chocobo armor designed to commemorate Hades.

Name: Saintly Barding
Description: A suit of chocobo armor designed to spread festive cheer.

Name: Bacon Bits
Description:
Tastes like bacon...if bacon and clay taste the same to you.

Use item to acquire the bacon bits minion.

Name: Wind-up Pixie
Description:
Won't make mischief at your expensepixie's honor.

Use item to acquire the wind-up pixie minion.

Name: Mystic Weapon
Description:
Only slightly cursed.

Use item to acquire the mystic weapon minion.

Name: Meerkat
Description:
Keeps an eye out for danger while basking in the sun.

Use item to acquire the meerkat minion.

Name: Miniature White Knight
Description:
Aids in the purging of sickness. Or not.

Use item to acquire the miniature white knight minion.

Name: Cute Justice
Description:
Rocket Punch parts may present a choking hazard. Not for children under the age of two.

Use item to acquire the Cute Justice minion.

Name: Domakin
Description:
Close, but not a warrior with the body of a mortal and soul of a dragon.

Use item to acquire the domakin minion.

Name: Dress-up Estinien
Description:
Sun-dried squid not included.

Use item to acquire the dress-up Estinien minion.

Name: Little Leannan
Description:
Doesn't see you as food. Yet.

Use item to acquire the little leannan minion.

Name: Wind-up Hobgoblin
Description:
Crafted in the likeness of your mother...or so certain dwarves would say.

Use item to acquire the wind-up hobgoblin minion.

Name: Cerberpup
Description:
With three wet little noses and three sets of adorable staring eyes, what's not to love? Aside from all of the teeth, obviously.

Use item to acquire the Cerberpup minion.

Name: Pod 054
Description:
The perfect assistant for adventuring...or it would be, if it worked properly.

Use item to acquire the pod 054 minion.

Name: Pod 316
Description:
The perfect assistant for adventuring...or it would be, if it worked properly.

Use item to acquire the pod 316 minion.

Name: Hades's Auracite
Description: A small chip of the auracite in which Hades was sealed. May you keep it close, and ever remember.

Name: Manufactured Coin
Description: A dented artifact collected from the Copied Factory. At one time, avid and eccentric collectors would have paid a king's ransom for it, but such numismatic baubles have fallen out of style. Glory to mankind.

Name: Colossus Totem
Description: This gleaming idol of unknown provenance is carved in the shape of a very, very, very small Alexander.

Name: Metal Spinner
Description: This particularly clever invention relies on a fish's natural tendency to snag its face on spinning, jagged objects.

Name: Greatwood Planter
Description: Botanists would no doubt be fascinated and confused in equal measure by this inexplicably effervescent potted plant.

Name: Shirt Display Rack
Description: The shirts placed upon this shelf are perfectly folded, and woe betide he who disturbs them in the name of trying one on.

Name: Lakeland Chair
Description: A chair in the classical elven style.

Name: Lakeland Table
Description: A table in the classical elven style.

Name: Leather Sofa
Description: This sofa is so luxurious that you will never want to get upand nor will you be able to on those particularly warm days when your skin practically fuses to it.

Name: Il Mheg Flower Lamp
Description: A softly glowing light fixture crafted to resemble one of the many lovely flowers in the pixies' home.

Name: Macaron Cushion
Description: A cute cushion designed to resemble a popular pastry.

Name: Wooden Deck
Description: A large, rectangular section of wooden decking, complete with low fences, flower baskets, and a table laid with tea for two.

Name: Whalaqee Revenge Blast Totem
Description:
An intricately carved wooden totem imbued with the secrets of a vengeful technique.

Only for use by blue mages.

Name: Whalaqee Angel Whisper Totem
Description:
An intricately carved wooden totem imbued with the secrets of a resurrective technique.

Only for use by blue mages.

Name: Nail of the Heavens Orchestrion Roll
Description: Music roll for Nail of the Heavens. Use to add to your orchestrion list.

Name: Imperium Orchestrion Roll
Description: Music roll for Imperium. Use to add to your orchestrion list.

Name: Irregular Tomestone of Soldiery
Description:
One of only a few in existence, this Allagan tomestone contains myriad explanations of military tactics and stratagems certain to confound one's enemies with their complexity.

Can be exchanged with itinerant moogles for certain items.

Name: Certificate of Good Cheer
Description: A slip of parchment issued in recognition of efforts toward spreading Starlight spirit.

Name: Valentione's Day Chocolate MMXX
Description: A bite-sized piece of rich milk chocolate resembling the coat of arms for House Valentione.

Name: Heavensturn of the Ox MMXXI Ticket
Description: An ornamented piece of parchment recognizing services rendered to the bugyo overseeing the festivities.

Name: Dream Triad Card
Description: One of eleven otherworldly Triple Triad cards.

Name: Hades Totem
Description: Perhaps this hard-won idol carved in the likeness of Hades is proof enough that he once lived.

Name: Alumina Whetstone
Description: A whestone carved from alumina. Used for sharpening metal or stone blades.

Name: Pliable Glass Fiber
Description: This thinly spun glass is remarkably resistant to breakage, even when handled by a particularly clumsy craftsman.

Name: Sandalwood Sap
Description: A partially congealed ball of sticky sap extracted from a sandalwood tree.

Name: Beryllium Ore
Description: A decent-sized piece of rock containing the precious metal beryllium.

Name: Sublime Solution
Description: Whatever it does, it does it sublimely.

Name: Sweetmeat Mussel
Description:
A variety of mussel with coloring so stygian that it appears almost to have been steeped in shadow. A mussel of darkness, if you will.
...Become what you mussel.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Mejillones al Ajillo
Description:
A sumptuous serving of delectable mussels smothered in an oily garlic sauce, each one a perfectly bite-sized burst of flavor.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Arros Negre
Description:
Though the squid ink makes for an unusual appearance, its contribution to this dish's flavor profile is undeniable it blends with several herbs and spices to complement the buttery mussels and hearty rice for an immensely satisfying culinary experience.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Kholusian Rain
Description: A highly concentrated elixir blended on the island of Kholusia.

Name: Eulmoran Certificate of Import
Description: A note of promise received for the delivery of facet equipment.

Name: Crafter's Delineation
Description: A detailed outline of complex crafting techniques. One delineation is consumed when using a specialist action.

Name: Skybuilders' Plywood
Description: Sturdy enough to support the weight of several large Roegadyn. Until it isn't.

Name: Skybuilders' Alloy
Description: At this stage, it is anyone's guess what this alloy will become. If it is extremely lucky, it may even end up as a door knocker.

Name: Skybuilders' Steel Plate
Description: Unless a skilled blacksmith or armorer can intervene, this steel is doomed to spend eternity as a useless metal square.

Name: Skybuilders' Ingot
Description: Even the skybuilders themselves are not quite sure what goes into these ingots, although the general consensus is that it is nothing valuable.

Name: Skybuilders' Leather
Description: Leather made for skybuilders, not from them. Apparently.

Name: Skybuilders' Rope
Description: How long is a length of rope? In this particular rope's case, this long.

Name: Skybuilders' Ink
Description: Used for writing in ledgers to keep track of who is owed what. Considering the scale of the Ishgardian restoration, it is expected that a fair few bottles will be exhausted before the work is completed.

Name: Skybuilders' Hemp Milk
Description: By all accounts, this plant-based milk has a pleasant enough taste, though Ishgardian culinarians have yet to succeed in efforts to turn it into cheese.

Name: Skybuilders' Wain
Description: Surprisingly maneuverable, even when loaded with bricks and such.

Name: Skybuilders' Nails
Description: Thankfully, this is a handful of metal nails, not ones grown from the fingers of the skybuilders themselves. That would be far less pleasant.

Name: Skybuilders' Rivets
Description: Those with a penchant for having little bits of metal sticking out from every surface in sight will be delighted to receive these carefully crafted metal studs.

Name: Skybuilders' Rings
Description: An object without a clear purpose but will probably come in handy one day, as hoarders of useless junk are wont to say.

Name: Skybuilders' Leather Straps
Description: Can be attached to the handles of tools to allow them to be hung from belts and so forth, though care should be taken while walking to avoid having them flailing around wildly.

Name: Skybuilders' Cloth
Description: It seems this cloth is destined to become part of a comfortable couch, or perhaps a nice set of drapes.

Name: Skybuilders' Plant Oil
Description: Used in the preparation of several varieties of Ishgardian cooking and, on some occasions, as a condiment.

Name: Skybuilders' Uncooked Pasta
Description: Uncooked pasta that is perfect for eating during construction. If you like uncooked pasta.

Name: Skybuilders' Barrel
Description: The expression a barrel of laughs was never meant to be taken literally, though if it were, one could fit a fair few in this voluminous wooden container.

Name: Skybuilders' Hammer
Description: In days to come, this most versatile of tools will become the bane of every nail that dared to stick out. And the occasional thumb.

Name: Skybuilders' Cooking Pot
Description: In times of war, this metallic item of cookware can double as a makeshift helmet, provided the wearer has an unnaturally large head.

Name: Skybuilders' Candelabra
Description: It almost seems a shame to cover this in layers of melted wax, though sadder still would be a candelabra without a candle.

Name: Skybuilders' Rug
Description: The eventual owner of this majestic piece of thick cloth will be as snug as a bug in a rug. Or on a rug, to be precise.

Name: Skybuilders' Broom
Description: As the saying goes, A new broom sweeps clean, though the person wielding said broom is also due at least some of the credit for any increase in cleanliness that may result.

Name: Skybuilders' Charcoal
Description: The recipients of the other items in your inventory would probably prefer that you refrained from carrying loose pieces of charcoal about your person.

Name: Skybuilders' Tea
Description: As is tradition with tea brewed for builders, it contains enough sugar to make the spoon stand on end.

Name: Skybuilders' Pedestal
Description: Though one should avoid putting other people on a pedestal, the placement of inanimate objects should not pose any problems.

Name: Skybuilders' Crosscut Saw
Description: It is not only double-edged blades that cut both ways.

Name: Skybuilders' Counter
Description: Considering that it lacks the ability to count anything whatsoever, counter seems to be something of a misnomer.

Name: Skybuilders' Stone
Description: If the time you have spent in Ishgard has taught you anything, it is that the locals really like stone.

Name: Skybuilders' Longboots
Description: Ideal for leaping from scaffold to scaffold as one merrily frolics about the construction site, while others go about their backbreaking labor.

Name: Skybuilders' Gloves
Description: Any Ishgardian with any sense will already own a pair of gloves, but for those who do not, these will be a welcome gift.

Name: Skybuilders' Soap
Description: Be careful to whom you give this. They may think you are trying to tell them something.

Name: Skybuilders' All-purpose Infusion
Description: Though the recipe states that this mysterious concoction can cure any ailment, one must remember that it will under no circumstances reattach dismembered fingers, which is a remarkably common complaint among the skybuilders.

Name: Skybuilders' Bed
Description: Children who fail to heed the word of their parents will be sent here without any supper.

Name: Skybuilders' Oven
Description: In many Ishgardian residences, the oven doubles as a means of heating the house, with the occupants finding themselves subconsciously drawn to the kitchen during the colder months. Which is all of them.

Name: Skybuilders' Lamppost
Description: Of all the items you have managed to stow about your person, this surely ranks as one of the largest and most cumbersome. Even the most proficient of aetherochemists would be baffled by the unsolved mystery of your impossibly deep pockets.

Name: Skybuilders' Brazier
Description: Not only can this be used for the cooking of various dishes, it also works wonders in the prevention of frostbite, as many residents of the Brume will attest.

Name: Skybuilders' Overalls
Description: Designed to be worn on top of other layers of clothing to protect them from dust and dirt and provide additional protection against the cold. Since Ishgardians tend to wear several layers of clothing to begin with, these overalls are cut much larger than those worn in warmer climes.

Name: Skybuilders' Waterproof Sheet
Description: Serves to keep out not only water, but wind as well, though the cold inevitably finds a way through eventually.

Name: Skybuilders' Alchemic
Description: One of many concoctions that serves little purpose on its own, but can be mixed with others for a variety of effects upon consumption, the large majority being some sort of agonizing death.

Name: Skybuilders' Stew
Description: One unfortunate rail was left to stew in its own juices after finding its way into the pot. Literally.

Name: Skybuilders' Yew Log
Description: The distinct lack of trees is one of many problems the first people to settle in Ishgard chose to ignore, making this otherwise commonplace materialsourced from the East Shroudextremely valuable.

Name: Skybuilders' Iron Ore
Description: While this may look much like any other iron ore found in middle La Noscea, there are subtle differences that only an expert in the field will recognize. The name, for one, is considerably longer.

Name: Skybuilders' Fine Sand
Description: This sand gathered in central Thanalan is not only fine, but extremely well behaved, choosing to stay in one closely knit lump while jostling alongside the rest of your possessions.

Name: Skybuilders' Hemp
Description: Though this hardy plant can grow almost anywhere, the snow-blasted precipices of Ishgard have so far proven too steep a challenge for it to overcome. This particular specimen was harvested in lower La Noscea, an environment far more conducive to plant lifeor any sort of life, for that matter.

Name: Skybuilders' Ash Log
Description: Ash! A-Ah! Savior of the Firmament!

Name: Skybuilders' Rock Salt
Description: Although upper La Noscea seems rather a distant location from which to source something as simple as salt, the Ishgardians are nothing if not particular in their tastes.

Name: Skybuilders' Electrum Ore
Description: The electrum ore found in upper La Noscea is believed to be far better suited to the skybuilders' needs than any other variety. Were anyone to ask them why, they would, in most cases be met with a response along the line of, Because it just is.

Name: Skybuilders' Iron Sand
Description: The tradition of measuring powdered substances in units of pinches has been the cause of many arguments, largely due to differences in finger size between the various races. Folk in eastern Thanalan, where this sample was gathered, have been known to ask Lalafells to measure when selling, and Roegadyn when buying, for obvious reasons.

Name: Skybuilders' Flax
Description: It is a well known fact among botanists that the flax in the South Shroud is superior to every other kind, for reasons far too complicated and boring for anyone else to care about.

Name: Skybuilders' Spring Water
Description: Having only traveled the relatively short distance from the Coerthas central highlands to Ishgard, this spring water is still remarkably fresh, though the icy chill threatens to freeze it inside the bottle.

Name: Skybuilders' Camphorwood Log
Description: Few members of the mortal races are equipped to make the perilous journey to the Churning Mists, and those who do normally hope to have more than a log or two to show for their troubles.

Name: Skybuilders' Straw
Description: Why the skybuilders would specify that their straw be brought from the Dravanian forelands is anyone's guess. Perhaps the smell helps their chocobos sleep more peacefully?

Name: Skybuilders' Hardsilver Ore
Description: The time spent mining this ore in the Dravanian hinterlands would perhaps have seemed less arduous if you had the faintest idea how the skybuilders plan to use it.

Name: Skybuilders' Mythrite Sand
Description: You have a sneaking suspicion that you may have lost some of the sand during the return journey from the Sea of Clouds, though the amount you have in your possession should still suffice.

Name: Skybuilders' Tea Leaves
Description: The thought of happy skybuilders drinking delicious tea was the only motivation you needed as you risked life and limb gathering these leaves in the Sea of Clouds.

Name: Skybuilders' Dravanian Spring Water
Description: There are easier places to collect spring water than the Dravanian forelands, though it seems your personal safety is not especially high on the skybuilders' list of concerns.

Name: Skybuilders' Urunday Log
Description: Compared to most places in Gyr Abania, the Peaks has more than its fair share of trees, so who would object to you taking a few logs? Bloodthirsty Qiqirn and rampaging ruud suuds, that's who. Or perhaps they just see you as an easy meal?

Name: Skybuilders' Nightsteel Ore
Description: The Ruby Sea is not especially well known as a prime location for mining, though those who are nautically minded can uncover all sorts of rare and unique treasures. Whether the skybuilders choose to turn this into fine jewelry or something more mundane, like a tea strainer, remains to be seen.

Name: Skybuilders' Adder
Description: Venomous snakes are something of a rarity in Ishgard, so the skybuilders have ordered that some be delivered from the Azim Steppe to help improve morale. Workers displaying a lack of enthusiasm will be given some time in the pit to rediscover their commitment to the cause.

Name: Skybuilders' Molybdenum Ore
Description: While the Lochs are better known as a source of salt, the rich veins of ore are drawing in miners from far and wide.

Name: Skybuilders' Horsetail
Description: Yanxia is rich in both flora and fauna, and horsetail forms a major part of the diet of many grazing creatures.

Name: Skybuilders' Ala Mhigan Rock Salt
Description: When an Ishgardian culinarian stated that her latest dish needed a pinch of salt, the skybuilders sought out the very best, though perhaps more than a single pinch would be required to make the lengthy journey to the Lochs worthwhile.

Name: Skybuilders' Ruby Sea Water
Description: While water from the Ruby Sea may not sound particularly appealing, this was actually brought from a small freshwater spring on one of the surrounding islands. Drinking this is unlikely to result in life-threatening dehydration.

Name: Skybuilders' Durium Sand
Description: A pinch of anything tends not to be an awful lot, though this particular sand from the Azim Steppe is apparently worth more than its weight in gold.

Name: Skybuilders' Vine
Description: Quite why a particular type of vine that can only be found in the Azim Steppe is necessary to the skybuilders' plans has yet to be explained. Perhaps they are planning to surprise you with a work of surpassing genius? Or perhaps not.

Name: Skybuilders' White Ash Log
Description: Obviously, none of the skybuilders has even heard of the Rak'tika Greatwood, though the specific qualities they seek in their timber can most easily be found in the white ash trees that grow there.

Name: Skybuilders' Reef Rock
Description: If a porous rock from the bottom of the ocean is required in the rebuilding of Ishgard, then so be it. Your job is to mine, not question the reasoning behind such dubious demands.

Name: Skybuilders' Truegold Ore
Description: Why submit a boring chunk of gold ore when you can bring one all the way from Il Mheg instead?

Name: Skybuilders' Cotton Boll
Description: This cotton must be very special indeed for you to bring it all the way from Lakeland in the First. You can only hope that the skybuilders appreciate you going the extra malm. And traveling to another world.

Name: Skybuilders' Dawn Lizard
Description: One day, this poor lizard is chasing other, smaller scurrying creatures across the desert plains of Amh Araeng, and the next, it is being transported to another world and dragged lashing and kicking to Ishgard. The chances of the cold-blooded scalekin being content in its frozen new surroundings are slim at best, and you can only hope that the skybuilders are grateful to you for supplying a miserable and motionless lizard.

Name: Skybuilders' Wheat
Description: Were the other contributors to hear that you traveled to Amh Araeng in the First simply to procure wheat, they would think you are just trying to show off.

Name: Skybuilders' Truegold Sand
Description: The isle of Kholusia is known by the inhabitants of Norvrandt to have the very finest of gold sand. Whether this is up to the impossibly high standards of the skybuilders will only become apparent when it is submitted for inspection.

Name: Skybuilders' Highland Spring Water
Description: Any water gathered from Il Mheg is likely to have been enchanted by either the pixies or the Fuath, though that is a problem for the skybuilders, not you, to worry about.

Name: Skybuilders' Resin
Description: Thankfully, the resin appears to have suffered no ill effects during your return from the Rak'tika Greatwood, meaning that it is still a gelatinous blob with seemingly no practical application whatsoever.

Description: Music roll for The Worm's Tail (Orchestral Version). Use to add to your orchestrion list.

Name: Faded Copy of Invincible
Description: Timeworn pages of sheet music containing the full score for Hades's theme, Invincible.

Name: Shell Leather
Description: A particularly glossy and durable variety of leather, the production of which is no mean feat.

Name: Skysteel Ingot
Description: The most advanced technology of the Skysteel Manufactory went into the creation of this block of metal. According to Biggs, equipment made from this material will allow its user to see around corners.

Name: Skysteel Leather
Description: The most advanced technology of the Skysteel Manufactory went into the creation of this piece of leather. According to Biggs, equipment made from this material will allow its user to hear sounds before they are made.

Name: Skysteel Cloth
Description: The most advanced technology of the Skysteel Manufactory went into the creation of this bolt of cloth. According to Biggs, equipment made from this material will allow its user to smell a person's thoughts from a malm away.

Name: Skybuilders' Cocoon
Description: While there seems to be an endless supply of these in Yanxia, why anyone would actually want them is unclear. They have a taste to match their appearance, in other words, revolting.

Name: Skybuilders' Sea Salt
Description: The ocean depths are dark and full of horrors... But also, rather a good location to harvest salt. Just watch out for the horrors.

Name: Authentic Silver Starlight Sentinel
Description: A potted conifer displayed in homes during the Starlight Celebration. Its snowy color will make your dcor sumptuousand your gatherings lively as you argue with friends and neighbors over whether it is superior to the more traditional green. It is not known how long ago it was placed in its ceramic prison, and some attribute its unnatural longevity to it having formed a blood pact with a voidsent, which may be unlikely considering its distinct lack of blood.

Name: Authentic Starlight Donuts
Description:
Festive treats for those who prefer to express their Starlight spirit through eating until they lose consciousness. While one may be forgiven for mistaking these for leftovers from a previous year, that could not be further from the truth, according to their baker.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Piety Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  VIT Bonus: +4% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +2
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Authentic Evercold Starlight Snowman
Description: This indoor frosty snowman will never melt away. He'll be there forever. Watching. Waiting. Authentically.

Name: Authentic Opened Twinkleboxes
Description: The detritus of many happy Starlight Celebration surprises. They may be empty, but at least they are authentically empty.

Name: Scions of the Seventh Dawn Reproduction
Description: A large-scale reproduction of the piece entitled Scions of the Seventh Dawn.

Name: Skybuilders' Toad
Description: What is worse than being born a toad? Being born a toad and then carried against your wishes from your home in western Thanalan to icy Ishgard, where if you don't freeze to death, are likely to be chopped up and boiled in a pot. That is what is worse. Much worse, in fact.

Name: Ufiti Horn
Description: A horn that emits a primal sound that summons forth your hulking ufiti.

Name: Dashing Valentione Rose Chest
Description:
A banded chest containing a complete set of red Valentione's attire.

Required level: 1. IL: 1. Cannot be opened in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.

Name: Dashing Valentione Acacia Chest
Description:
A banded chest containing a complete set of yellow Valentione's attire.

Required level: 1. IL: 1. Cannot be opened in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.

Name: Dashing Valentione Forget-me-not Chest
Description:
A banded chest containing a complete set of blue Valentione's attire.

Required level: 1. IL: 1. Cannot be opened in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.

Name: Prim Valentione Rose Chest
Description:
A banded chest containing a complete set of red Valentione's attire.

Required level: 1. IL: 1. Cannot be opened in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.

Name: Prim Valentione Acacia Chest
Description:
A banded chest containing a complete set of yellow Valentione's attire.

Required level: 1. IL: 1. Cannot be opened in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.

Name: Prim Valentione Forget-me-not Chest
Description:
A banded chest containing a complete set of blue Valentione's attire.

Required level: 1. IL: 1. Cannot be opened in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.

Name: No.2 Type B Materiel Storage Crate
Description:
A manufactured crate containing a full set of No.2 Type B attire.

Required level: 1. IL: 1.

Name: The Jaws of Undeath
Description:
A king among vicejaws, and lord of the waters of the Isle of Ken (one notable exception aside).

[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: White Ronso
Description:
A king among zebra catfish, and lord of the waters of lower Watts River.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Ambling Caltrop
Description:
A king among thorned lizards, and lord of the Hills of Amber.

[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Fae Rainbow
Description:
A capricious queen among spotted blue-eyes, and lady of the waters of the Jealous One.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Black Jet
Description:
A king among black tri-stars, and lord of the waters of the Lozatl.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Ondo Sigh
Description:
A king among bubble anglers, and lord of the waters of the Flounders' Floor.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Small Angler's Canvas
Description: A tiny blank canvas on which an ink print of some aquatic creature or another might be rendered, complete with frame.

Name: Medium Angler's Canvas
Description: A modest blank canvas on which an ink print of some aquatic creature or another might be rendered, complete with frame.

Name: Large Angler's Canvas
Description: A robust blank canvas on which an ink print of some aquatic creature or another might be rendered, complete with frame.

Name: Extra Large Angler's Canvas
Description: An imposing blank canvas on which an ink print of a truly enormous aquatic creature might be rendered, complete with frame.

Name: Galadion Goby
Description:
Amateur anglers are advised to familiarize themselves with the difference between the Merlthor and Galadion gobies as early as possible, as devotees of both varieties tend to become rather heated when one is (understandably) mistaken for the other.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Galadion Chovy
Description:
What makes a Galadion chovy distinct from other Lominsan anchovies? Depends on who's asking.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Rosy Bream
Description:
The sunset coloring of these inhabitants of Galadion Bay makes them just as appealing to other predators as to anglers, leaving them somewhat beleaguered as a rule.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Tripod Fish
Description:
Many a seafarer has lain awake contemplating the cursed knowledge that, as its name implies, this fish can indeed stand on its fins. 

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Sunfly
Description:
A brightly colored fish that swims merrily through the Strait of Merlthor...or did.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Tarnished Shark
Description:
Like a long-neglected antique, perhaps this shark just needs some love to become the perfect addition to afternoon tea parties. Alas, no one has yet volunteered to be the first to find out.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Hyacinth Bulbs
Description:
Each bulb is the nascent and substantially more hideous form of the many-flowered hyacinth.

For use in planters.

Name: Red Hyacinths
Description:
A bunch of red hyacinths, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Blue Hyacinths
Description:
A bunch of blue hyacinths, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Yellow Hyacinths
Description:
A bunch of yellow hyacinths, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Green Hyacinths
Description:
A bunch of green hyacinths, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Orange Hyacinths
Description:
A bunch of orange hyacinths, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Purple Hyacinths
Description:
A bunch of purple hyacinths, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: White Hyacinths
Description:
A bunch of white hyacinths, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Black Hyacinths
Description:
A bunch of black hyacinths, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Rainbow Hyacinths
Description:
A bunch of multicolored hyacinths, selectively fertilized to achieve a variety of vibrant colors.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Half-timbered Cottage Walls
Description:
A set of four walls designed for those who wish to transform their estate into a quaint mercantile establishment.

Can only be used with cottages on small plots of land.

Name: Half-timbered House Walls
Description:
A set of four walls designed for those who wish to transform their estate into a quaint mercantile establishment.

Can only be used with houses on medium plots of land.

Name: Half-timbered Mansion Walls
Description:
A set of four walls designed for those who wish to transform their estate into a quaint mercantile establishment.

Can only be used with mansions on large plots of land.

Name: Rough Stone Interior Wall
Description: An imposing interior wall of haphazardly arranged hunks of stone.

Name: Rough Stone Flooring
Description: Unpolished flagstonefor everyone's favorite seedy tavern ambience.

Name: Wooden Chandelier
Description: Ideal for swinging on with roguish gracethough do try not to burn the place down.

Name: Moogle Round Table
Description: A charmingly rustic wooden table, attended by a trio of musical (though unmoving) moogles.

Name: Modern Mogseat
Description: Those who sit in this chair may be unable to get up again, but considerwill they really need to?

Name: Cosmetics Box
Description: This enormous case is replete with enough paints and powders to satisfy an entire Eorzean theater troupeor one Eulmoran dame.

Name: Hatching-tide MMXVIII Advertisement
Description: A cheerful hand-painted notice proclaiming the eggcellence of Hatching-tide.

Name: Wine Rack
Description: Nice vintage you've got there. Be a shame if someone were to...quaff it.

Name: Rope Stanchion
Description: A set of velvety ropes for your queue management needs.

Name: Cardpaper Box
Description: Not recommended for subterfuge.

Name: Dish Rack
Description: A spacious box in which to dry dishware, with accompanying mat for glasses.

Name: Garment Rack
Description: Featuring the latest in Ishgardian fashion...which is generally traditional Ishgardian fashion.

Name: Amaurot Wall Lamp
Description: A metallic fixture of the sort popular in the Amaurot of Emet-Selch's recollection.

Name: Manor Dressing Table
Description: A haunting dressing table custom-made for Haukke Manor. ...In retrospect, Lady Amandine wasn't very subtle about the whole voidsent issue.

Name: Cheese Collection
Description: Why in the gods' name would a person amass such an amount of cheese? A peculiar obsession? A craving that transcends all reason? Some manner of cheese-related divination known only to a forbidden sect? Whatever the reason, one can only hope that the results are still saleable.

Name: Oldrose Wall Planter
Description: A riot of vibrant red and pale pink blooms within this quaint wall-mounted box.

Name: Folded Futon
Description: Put it awayquick, before the guests see!

Name: The Bismarck
Description:
Impressive enough to bear the name of Limsa's premier culinary establishment as its own, this is the sort of sandwich one eats off of a nice plate.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Tenacity Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  VIT Bonus: +5% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Devil's Salad Bowl
Description:
A pleasant mix of crisp greens topped by satisfying and zesty deviled eggs.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Critical Hit Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  VIT Bonus: +5% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Lord Commander Portrait
Description: A commissioned portrait of Ser Aymeric entitled The Scion of House Borel. Original artist unknown.

Name: Golden Crystal Boule
Description: A mounted sample of the luminous yellow crystals that grow uninhibited on the sea floor.

Name: Cosmos Partition
Description: A partition design to evoke the grandeur and magnificence of the Grand Cosmos.

Name: Wooden Table
Description: Now there is one less tree in the woods, and one more table in your room.

Name: Picnic Basket
Description: Includes everything required for a sunlit meal in the outdoors.

Name: First Chair's Trumpet
Description: Designed in homage to a legendary trumpeter, its majesty may someday inspire someone to finally pick up that instrument they have been meaning to learn.

Name: Sunflower Bouquet
Description: A bouquet sure to brighten any room it is in.

Name: Cutting Board
Description: Perfect for cutting all manner of vegetables on. Also suitable for placing already cut vegetables on.

Name: Open Book
Description: Opened to the page revealing the most impressively wordy words entirely by accident.

Name: Milk Carton
Description: A paper milk carton, fortunately lacking an illustration of someone's face on the side.

Name: Azure Dragoon Portrait
Description: A commissioned portrait of Ser Estinien entitled simply Azure. Original artist unknown.

Name: Cosmos Decoration
Description: Be transported to the majestic Grand Cosmos without stepping foot from your room.

Name: Used Banquet Table
Description: There's no telling how many banquets have been eaten off of this table.

Name: Steppe Bed
Description: Sleep as soundly as the nomadic peoples of the Azim Steppe do.

Name: Stuffed Rabbit
Description: This rabbit looks as if he walked straight out of a storybook, and is prepared to keep on walking. (Please contact authorities immediately in the event that the toy actually demonstrates ambulatory capabilities.)

Name: Ruby Weapon Bust
Description:
The heart of this Garlond Ironworks scale replica of a select portion of the Ruby Weapon pulsates menacingly. Accept no substitutes.

One per estate only.

Name: Apron Rack
Description: Every literally or figuratively butterfingered chef needs a good apron or two.

Name: Eastern Stage
Description: The festivities never need come to an end with this stage adorned with peach blossoms.

Name: Little Ladies' Day Banner
Description: A princess needs no crown when this banner exists to always remind them how special they are.

Name: Dohn Trellis
Description: Make even the fae jealous with this trellis, designed to evoke the verdant splendor of Dohn Mheg.

Name: Lakeland Elf Tree
Description: Elf trees are in such high demand that some are grown for the express purpose of being cut down and sold.

Name: Lakeland Flower Garden
Description: Lakeland's most arresting flowers right in your own home.

Name: Ruby Totem
Description: A metallic idol forged in the likeness of the Ruby Weapon.

Name: Helm of Golden Antiquity
Description:
A winged helmet forged by some ancient civilization, recovered from Eden's Verse.

Two helms can be traded for special headgear.

Name: Armor of Golden Antiquity
Description:
Emblazoned armor forged by some ancient civilization, recovered from Eden's Verse.

Four suits can be traded for special body gear.

Name: Gauntlets of Golden Antiquity
Description:
Wrought-iron gauntlets forged by some ancient civilization, recovered from Eden's Verse.

Two pairs can be traded for special arm gear.

Name: Chausses of Golden Antiquity
Description:
Heavy chausses forged by some ancient civilization, recovered from Eden's Verse.

Four pairs can be traded for special leg gear.

Name: Greaves of Golden Antiquity
Description:
Tarnished greaves forged by some ancient civilization, recovered from Eden's Verse.

Two pairs can be traded for special foot gear.

Name: Belt of Golden Antiquity
Description: An ornamented belt created by some ancient civilization, recovered from Eden's Verse. Alas, advancements in trouser technology have rendered it worthless.

Name: Bangle of Golden Antiquity
Description:
An extravagant bangle forged by some ancient civilization, recovered from Eden's Verse.

One bangle can be traded for a special accessory.

Name: Book of Fulmination
Description:
A short apocryphal tome presumably created by Eden for recordkeeping purposes.

Copies of the same Eden's Verse apocrypha can be traded for special gear.

Name: Book of Furor
Description:
A short apocryphal tome presumably created by Eden for recordkeeping purposes.

Copies of the same Eden's Verse apocrypha can be traded for special gear.

Name: Book of Iconoclasm
Description:
A short apocryphal tome presumably created by Eden for recordkeeping purposes.

Copies of the same Eden's Verse apocrypha can be traded for special gear.

Name: Book of Refulgence
Description:
A short apocryphal tome presumably created by Eden for recordkeeping purposes.

Copies of the same Eden's Verse apocrypha can be traded for special gear.

Name: Blade of Golden Antiquity
Description: A golden blade forged by some ancient civilization, recovered from Eden's Verse. Though such weapons were once considered highly valuable, demand has dried up and they are now essentially worthless.

Name: Crystalline Ester
Description: A sparkling substance produced by the artisans of the Crystalline Mean, usedwhen resources permitto enhance the properties of Crystarium weapons such as those used by the guard. However, advances in crafting technology have rendered it obsolete.

Name: Crystalline Twine
Description: A sparkling thread produced by the artisans of the Crystalline Mean, usedwhen resources permitto augment Crystarium vestments such as those used by the guard. However, advances in crafting technology have rendered it obsolete.

Name: Crystalline Glaze
Description: A sparkling coating produced by the artisans of the Crystalline Mean, usedwhen resources permitto strengthen Crystarium accessories such as those used by the guard. However, advances in crafting technology have rendered it obsolete.

Name: Mowen's Token (Allegory)
Description: A note of promise received from Mowen for the delivery of Allagan tomestones of allegory. However, due to the House of Splendors changing its policies, it is now worth less than the paper on which it is scribed.

Name: Perdurable Tomestone
Description: A rare and beautiful tomestone made of nigh-indestructible fused quartz. This particular variety is not as highly sought as it once was, and may no longer be exchanged for other wares.

Name: Edenchoir Tassets of Fending
Description: Before becoming obsolete due to advancements in tailoring, belts such as this were used for holding up trousers and the like.

Description: Before becoming obsolete due to advancements in tailoring, belts such as this were used for holding up trousers and the like.

Description: A hunk of crimson metal torn from the Ruby Weapon.

Name: Ruby Barding
Description: A suit of chocobo armor designed to resemble the Ruby Weapon.

Name: Machinist Barding
Description: Chocobo barding designed to pair well with machinist's garb.

Name: Neo-Ishgardian Plate Belt of Fending
Description: Before becoming obsolete due to advancements in tailoring, belts such as this were used for holding up trousers and the like.

Name: Neo-Ishgardian Plate Belt of Maiming
