Description: Before becoming obsolete due to advancements in tailoring, belts such as this were used for holding up trousers and the like.

Name: Master Carpenter VIII
Description: This esoteric tomethe eighth in an equally esoteric seriescontains advanced woodworking recipes that can only be learned by esoterically skilled carpenters.

Name: Master Blacksmith VIII
Description: This esoteric tomethe eighth in an equally esoteric seriescontains advanced smithing recipes that can only be learned by esoterically skilled blacksmiths.

Name: Master Armorer VIII
Description: This esoteric tomethe eighth in an equally esoteric seriescontains advanced armorcraft recipes that can only be learned by esoterically skilled armorers.

Name: Master Goldsmith VIII
Description: This esoteric tomethe eighth in an equally esoteric seriescontains advanced goldsmithing recipes that can only be learned by esoterically skilled goldsmiths.

Name: Master Leatherworker VIII
Description: This esoteric tomethe eighth in an equally esoteric seriescontains advanced leatherworking recipes that can only be learned by esoterically skilled leatherworkers.

Name: Master Weaver VIII
Description: This esoteric tomethe eighth in an equally esoteric seriescontains advanced clothcraft recipes that can only be learned by esoterically skilled weavers.

Name: Master Alchemist VIII
Description: This esoteric tomethe eighth in an equally esoteric seriescontains advanced alchemy recipes that can only be learned by esoterically skilled alchemists.

Name: Master Culinarian VIII
Description: This esoteric tomethe eighth in an equally esoteric seriescontains advanced cooking recipes that can only be learned by esoterically skilled culinarians.

Name: Grade 3 Tincture of Strength
Description:
This diluted brew temporarily increases strength for twice the duration of similar potions.

Duration: 30s

Name: Grade 3 Tincture of Dexterity
Description:
This diluted brew temporarily increases dexterity for twice the duration of similar potions.

Duration: 30s

Name: Grade 3 Tincture of Vitality
Description:
This diluted brew temporarily increases vitality for twice the duration of similar potions.

Duration: 30s

Name: Grade 3 Tincture of Intelligence
Description:
This diluted brew temporarily increases intelligence for twice the duration of similar potions.

Duration: 30s

Name: Grade 3 Tincture of Mind
Description:
This diluted brew temporarily increases mind for twice the duration of similar potions.

Duration: 30s

Name: Ovim Meatballs
Description:
Savory, round chunks of minced ovim meat accented with a lingonberry sauce that's sweet yet tart.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Mors
Description:
A traditional beverage brewed from the extract of fermented lingonberries.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Lemon Waffle
Description:
Crispy on the outside and moist on the inside, this baked delight with a distinctive texture has a slight hint of citrus.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Honey Croissant
Description:
A flaky, decadent pastry sweetened with rich, golden honey.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Sausage and Sauerkraut
Description:
Aromatic, herb-seasoned meat and pickled cabbage come together in a mouthwatering combination.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Stuffed Highland Cabbage
Description:
This traditional dish of minced meat seasoned and packed inside leafy highland cabbage, then stewed in a light broth, is sure to warm you up on the coldest of nights.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Pickled Herring
Description:
Succulent chunks of platinum herring marinated in vinegar and topped with finely sliced lemonette to give it a hint of tang.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Herring Pie
Description:
Chunks of seasoned herring baked into a flaky crust that's been shaped like a fish so as to inform the eater to expect savory instead of sweet.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Farmer's Breakfast
Description:
This simple-yet-delightful dish of popotoes and lightly scrambled eggs will fill you up before a day of tilling the fields.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Silkie Pudding
Description:
The distinctively smooth texture and rich taste of this lightly sweet, boiled dessert will have your mouth watering.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Lingonberry
Description: Plump, ripe, and bursting with flavor. Perfect for jams and sweet treats.

Name: Strong Flour
Description: While there may be nothing particularly strong about it in its present state, the difference soon becomes clear when using it to bake bread.

Name: Highland Cabbage
Description: Some particularly hardy Highlanders have been seen to grasp a cabbage in one hand and take great bites from it, though this is not recommended.

Name: Platinum Herring
Description: Other than the rather fancy name, this species is extraordinarily ordinary.

Name: Silkie Egg
Description: The breed of chicken that lays these eggs is known for its incredibly voluminous plumage. The eggs, on the other hand, are entirely indistinguishable from that of any other chicken.

Name: Shimmering Quartz
Description:
A curious stone that glistens faintly in your hand.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the gathering log.

Name: Serpent's-eye
Description:
A rare gemstone named for its resemblance to the watchful eye of a snake. Said to ward off evil.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the gathering log.

Name: Blessed Spring Water
Description:
Water collected from a natural fount said to be blessed by Ox'Dalan, guardian of the underworld.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the gathering log.

Name: Kindling Crystal
Description:
Translucent stones of this sort are lightly warm to the touch and often employed by the Night's Blessed to aid in starting bonfires.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the gathering log.

Name: Slough Serpentinite
Description:
A hunk of mottled rock covered thick with verdant moss.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the gathering log.

Name: Splendid Iron Ore
Description:
High-purity iron ore splendid for making durable mining tools.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the gathering log.

Name: Splendid Flint Stone
Description:
Just an ordinary flint stone used to strike sparks, but Qhoterl Pasol will surely find it splendid.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the gathering log.

Name: Splendid Slate
Description:
This slab of slate is splendid for adding a touch of home to the Stopple.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the gathering log.

Name: Splendid Ant Egg
Description:
Savory-sweet and nourishing, this ant egg will have any Qitari exclaiming Splendid!

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the gathering log.

Name: Splendid Scorpion
Description:
Dwelling in rocky areas, this scorpion is splendidly hardy and promises to impart this quality to those who devour it.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the gathering log.

Name: Splendid Amber
Description:
An ingredient used by the Qitari to make their splendid perfumes.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the gathering log.

Name: Splendid Chalcanthite
Description:
Though splendid to behold, this mineral is quite toxicbut for Qhoterl Pasol's purposes, that too may be considered splendid.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the gathering log.

Name: Splendid Mineral Oil
Description:
Anyone hoping to use this oil in its raw state to close wounds and heal grazes will be left sorely disappointed, and perhaps just sore.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the gathering log.

Name: Splendid Purple Pigment
Description:
Certain Qitari scholars maintain that this pigment is in fact a shade of mauve, while others argue it is more of a dark lilac hue. The debate rages on.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the gathering log.

Name: Splendid Natron
Description:
While the Qitari use this rare substance as an ingredient in cleansing solutions, some suspect that it merely masks odors rather than eliminating them. Several members of the community rub this on the more pungent areas of the body as a substitute to proper washing, a practice that is largely frowned upon.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the gathering log.

Name: Splendid Clay
Description:
While clay is a common enough material, only the truly splendid is used in the repair of broken pots and such, as the Qitari tend to be rather fussy about such matters.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the gathering log.

Name: Splendid Graphite
Description:
When this rare mineral is ground down and made into ink, it can be used in a variety of artistic pursuits, such as calligraphy and so forth. Unfortunately, this particular sample is destined for a far more mundane purpose: the logging of excavated trinkets. To make matters worse, most Qitari have exceptionally poor handwriting.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the gathering log.

Name: Splendid Rock Salt
Description:
This splendid rock salt is sprinkled on meat during the smoking process to draw out its natural flavor. The same could, in fact, be said for practically any salt, but the Qitari tend to notice when someone tries to fob them off with anything less than the genuine article, hence the need to seek out this particular variety.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the gathering log.

Name: Splendid Saltpeter
Description:
Not to be confused with salt. Or Peter, whoever that is.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the gathering log.

Name: Splendid Holey Stone
Description:
Countless years of weathering have produced a stone full of holes that produce a most splendid sound when air passes through them.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the gathering log.

Name: Splendid Gravel
Description:
To maintain the splendid sheen of the stone tablets, one must use stones to polish stone.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the gathering log.

Name: Splendid Stone
Description:
Suffused with magical energy, this stone can be used to make a trap as deadly as it is splendid.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the gathering log.

Name: Splendid Worm
Description:
Packed with splendid nutrients, any who consume this worm will become as hardy as the rocks it dwells within.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the gathering log.

Name: Splendid Dense Iron Ore
Description:
Only the most splendid picks will suffice for the Stewards, and to make those only the most splendid and densest ore will do.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the gathering log.

Name: Splendid Bone Fragment
Description:
Bones tend to make splendid lures, especially when one seeks to catch splendid fish.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the gathering log.

Name: Splendid Black Rock
Description:
Qhoterl Pasol's magnum opus, a history of Ronka, must be splendid in every respect, as must the tools she will use to write it.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the gathering log.

Name: Ancient Amber
Description:
This resin harvested from a primeval tree glows faintly with an otherworldly light.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the gathering log.

Name: Spectral Cocoon
Description:
Spun by a rare breed of silkworm, this ghostly white casing is said to ward off baleful spirits.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the gathering log.

Name: Spiritweed Root
Description:
The underground portion of a ghastly-looking shrub, used in offerings to the god of death.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the gathering log.

Name: Serpent Pepper
Description:
A pungent spice often used by the Night's Blessed in preparing meals and medicines to warm the body.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the gathering log.

Name: Boggy Bark
Description:
This slab of bark harvested from an ancient swampland tree is covered thick in verdant moss.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the gathering log.

Name: Splendid Flax
Description:
This fibrous plant makes splendidly sturdy rope.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the gathering log.

Name: Splendid Seeds
Description:
The oil extracted from these seeds burns splendidly in lamps.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the gathering log.

Name: Splendid Water Ivy
Description:
This length of ivy is splendid for adding a touch of home to the Stopple.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the gathering log.

Name: Splendid Silkworm
Description:
Succulent and nourishing, this silkworm will have any Qitari exclaiming Splendid!

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the gathering log.

Name: Splendid Wild Berries
Description:
Fairly bursting with juice, these berries make a truly splendid treat.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the gathering log.

Name: Splendid Lavender
Description:
Bold yet soothing, the splendid scent of this herb helps the Qitari to navigate in the darkwhile presumably keeping them relaxed.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the gathering log.

Name: Splendid Tarantula
Description:
The venom of this spider is splendid for concocting a potent poison.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the gathering log.

Name: Splendid Greenwattle
Description:
Named for its likeness to the skin dangling from a chicken's neck, only much greener.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the gathering log.

Name: Splendid Turmeric
Description:
Through the work of masters in the ways of spice, this root of decidedly unremarkable appearance is transformed into a bright-orange powder. This would make for a rather impressive magic trick, were it not for the fact the process takes several days to complete, which is somewhat longer than the attention span of the average audience.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the gathering log.

Name: Splendid Marimo
Description:
While even the most scholarly of scholars struggle to identify exactly what this mysterious aquatic substance actually is, the Qitari have discovered it to be incredibly useful in the removal of unwanted odors. A few scrubs with a marimo produces a distinctive pond-like fragrance, which is many magnitudes more pleasant than what Qitari usually smell of, which does not bear description.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the gathering log.

Name: Splendid Trillium
Description:
Some Qitari will claim that this flower is an essential ingredient in their traditional adhesive formula, while others have the sneaking suspicion that it actually makes no difference whether it is included in the mixture or not. Nevertheless, it continues to be used to this day, as Qitari are content to comply with the teachings of the ancients, no matter how absurd they may be.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the gathering log.

Name: Splendid Tarichuk Feather
Description:
Fortunately, the former owner was kind enough to molt this fine feather for you to collect without the need to resort to bloodshed, which may explain how it retains its natural splendidness.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the gathering log.

Name: Splendid Tree Bark
Description:
The bark of a tree once barked at by a dog barking up the wrong tree.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the gathering log.

Name: Splendid Mugwort
Description:
Few would suspect that such an innocuous plant could be used in the production of explosives. Culinarians are investigating the connection between its combustive properties and claims that the consumption of mugwort causes indigestion.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the gathering log.

Name: Splendid Stalk
Description:
This hollow stalk makes the perfect flute, and produces sounds so splendid as to transport one to another world.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the gathering log.

Name: Splendid Broombush
Description:
To keep a place looking splendid, you must have tools equally as splendid. This broombush can be used to sweep away even the most stubborn dust.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the gathering log.

Name: Splendid Nut
Description:
Nuts typically are not thought of as traps, but when  they're this splendidand packed with arcane energytheir uses expand exponentially.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the gathering log.

Name: Splendid Beehive Chip
Description:
The royal honey that can be scraped off this beehive chip can fortify the body and make splendid even the most downcast of spirits.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the gathering log.

Name: Splendid Roots
Description:
These splendid roots can endure the harshest of stresses, making them well suited to the extreme conditions the Stewards oft find themselves in.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the gathering log.

Name: Splendid Earthworm
Description:
At first glance, this appears to be a common earthworm, but a closer look will reveal just how splendid it actually is.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the gathering log.

Name: Splendid Hemp
Description:
This hemp can be woven into splendid paper that can stand the test of time Qhoterl Pasol's masterpiece will have to endure.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the gathering log.

Name: Glowfish
Description:
The scales of this ancient denizen of the deep exude an unearthly glow.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Shimmershell
Description:
The faint light given off by this rare mollusk is said to ward off danger.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Dalan's Claw
Description:
A modestly sized yet fearsome-looking crustacean often used as an offering to Ox'Dalan. 

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Magma Eel
Description:
A finless fish whose body is oddly warm to the touch. Often used by the Night's Blessed in preparing meals and medicines to warm the body.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Mossy Tortoise
Description:
The shell of this ancient swamp-dwelling creature grows thick with verdant moss.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Splendid Clawbow
Description:
The sturdy pincers of this crab are splendid for making tools.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Splendid Trout
Description:
The oil extracted from this fish burns splendidly in lamps.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Splendid Eryops
Description:
The skin of this amphibian is splendid for adding a touch of home to the Stopple.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Splendid Robber Crab
Description:
Toothsome and nourishing, the flesh of this robber crab will have any Qitari exclaiming Splendid!

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Splendid Piranha
Description:
Though somewhat bony, the flesh of this freshwater fish is splendid for one's vigor.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Splendid Pirarucu
Description:
The liver of this enormous fish is used by the Qitari to make their splendid perfumes.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Splendid Poison Catfish
Description:
The venom found in the fins of this catfish can be used to concoct a poison, and a splendid one at that.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Splendid Pondfrond
Description:
A firm favorite of fruit worms, despite their apparent inability to plumb the depths of the lake where it grows. However, a hook through the belly awakes within them their innate swimming instincts, and they will stop at nothing to locate this elusive pond weed.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Splendid Spiralshell
Description:
When these shells are ground into powder, they form the basis for a wide range of dyes. How this method was discovered is a secret lost to the sands of time, although one may assume it involved a fair amount of trial and error, not to mention time and effort that may perhaps have been better spent on more worthwhile pursuits.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Splendid Sponge
Description:
The question of whether this enigmatic...thing is flora or fauna has yet to be answered, although from the way the Qitari use it to vigorously scrub the stench from their furry bodies, one can only hope it does not possess any form of sentience.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Splendid Cockle
Description:
Perhaps not the first thing that would spring to mind when discussing potential ingredients for an adhesive, the Qitari nevertheless swear by it.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Splendid Silver Kitten
Description:
Being a smaller relation to the catfish, this fine specimen possesses whisker-like barbs which may have served some purpose in the days before they devolved into utter uselessness.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Splendid Night's Bass
Description:
Even a regular Night's bass acts as though it owns whatever body of water it chooses to inhabit, and the overt splendidness of this particular specimen makes it particularly unpopular within fish circles, whose social hierarchy is remarkably complex. Apparently.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Splendid Magmatongue
Description:
Descended from a long line of similarly monikered fish famous for their distinctive tongues, this breed's coloration resembles that of flowing magma. Its tongue, however, is rumored to melt whatever it licks, which is an oft-used excuse used by fishers who have allowed it to escape after being hooked.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Splendid Treescale
Description:
The shells of these bivalve mollusks have long been favored as percussion instruments by the Qitari for the splendid sound they make when struck.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Splendid Pipira
Description:
The rough teeth of these fish can scour centuries of dirt from the stone tablets, thus making splendid the histories of the Ronkan people.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Splendid Shellfish
Description:
Unbeknownst to many, the pearls slumbering within these splendid shellfish contain potent magical energy, which Qhoterl Pasol intends to use to fend off intruders.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Splendid Egg-bearing Trout
Description:
This fish is most splendid when it bears eggs, which are said to strengthen the body against all manner of ailments.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Splendid Diamondtongue
Description:
The rough scales of this fish make it ill-suited for a meal, but they will serve splendidly to make boots which will be used to traverse treacherous terrain.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Splendid Larva
Description:
A larva so plump and splendid that even fishers have been known to eat one or two on occasion.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Splendid Mammoth Shellfish
Description:
Since ancient times, this shellfish has been prized for its ink sacs, which produce a most splendid shade of black.

Only for use in Qitari society quests.
Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Pelagic Clay
Description: Heavy on eolean dust and the bones of marine creaturesit is generally better to not ask whichthis clay is found only in the deepest parts of the sea.

Description: Skysteel tool.

Name: Oddly Specific Petrified Orb
Description: A sphere of fossilized wood sanded to exacting specifications.

Name: Oddly Specific Rivets
Description: Far too many painstakingly forged metal bolts.

Name: Oddly Specific Wire
Description: Metal wire of unusual diameter.

Name: Oddly Specific Whetstone
Description: Whether this whetstone is materially much different from others or simply much more aesthetically appealing is difficult to discern.

Name: Oddly Specific Leather
Description: It is fortunate that the Skysteel engineers provided instructions as to how this leather ought to be tanned, as it is still impossible to tell what manner of creature it came from.

Name: Oddly Specific Moonbeam Silk
Description: Soft. Shiny. Specific.

Name: Oddly Specific Synthetic Resin
Description: This compound is the result of hours of painstaking experimentationwhich likely could have been avoided if the Skysteel engineers who ordered it had thought to provide the ratio of ingredients alongside their excruciatingly detailed description of what the end result ought to look, smell, and taste like.

Name: Oddly Specific Seed Extract
Description: An exact quantity of extract produced through an exacting extraction process.

Name: Oddly Specific Shaft
Description: Neillemard doubtless regrets allowing Denys to write out the order sheet for this particular material.

Name: Oddly Specific Fitting
Description: On one hand, it is a relatively simple matter to understand why precision in the measurement and shaping of this joining piece is required. On the other, the instructions also requested that it smell lightly of La Noscean orange, so perhaps some skepticism is warranted.

Name: Oddly Specific Chainmail Sheet
Description: Far too many painstakingly forged metal links, fastened together equally painstakingly.

Name: Oddly Specific Gemstone
Description: A jewel cut and polished to perfectionor arbitrary preference. One of the two.

Name: Oddly Specific Vellum
Description: This page has been trimmed and prepared for its likely use in drafting plans.

Name: Oddly Specific Velvet
Description: The depth and density of this cloth's plush pile has been measured to 1/1000th of an ilm.

Name: Oddly Specific Glass
Description: This pane is see-through, but not too see-through, precisely as ordered.

Name: Oddly Specific Seed Flour
Description: A fine powder, ground and sifted with extraordinarysome might even say excessiveprecision.

Name: Oddly Specific Petrified Log
Description: Whence this fossilized wood is sourced is for Skysteel engineers to specify, and you to never find out.

Name: Oddly Specific Iron Sand
Description: It is unclear what precise qualities make this particular sort of granulated metal so desirable, but presumably the old blacksmiths' adage, Don't get iron sand in your eye. Seriously. Don't, still applies, so probably best not look too closely.

Name: Oddly Specific Iron Ore
Description: Not your granddad's iron ore. Or perhaps specifically your granddad's iron ore. Who's to say?

Name: Oddly Specific Uncut Gemstone
Description: A mineral chunk of the precise luster, color, cleavage, and lumpiness requested.

Name: Oddly Specific Skin
Description: Someone knows what sort of skin this is, and really, isn't that what matters?

Name: Oddly Specific Cotton
Description: If cotton's fluffiness were rated on a scale of one to one thousand, which it absolutely is notby anyone other than Nimie, at any ratethis would rate exactly nine hundred and eighty-seven.

Name: Oddly Specific Quartz
Description: If you look really, really, really close, you can see the difference between this and the sort of quartz that can be bought from a street urchin for a single shiny gil. Maybe.

Name: Oddly Specific Seeds
Description: These seeds have been closely inspected for quality. And other things.

Name: Oddly Specific Latex
Description: It is a relatively simple matter for a skilled botanist to collect latex from a specified plant in a specified vessel by specified means. Excruciating, yes, but simple.

Name: Oddly Specific Fossil Dust
Description: Whether naturalists would wholly approve of the Skysteel Manufactory's appropriation of microfossil-rich powder for industrial purposes is a matter probably best not raised in company of said naturalists, as to do so would likely bring about swift confiscation.

Name: Oddly Specific Obsidian
Description: It's all about the sheen. Apparently.

Name: Oddly Specific Mineral Sand
Description: If Nimie is to be believed, the precise mineral composition by grain is key in sand-related projects.

Name: Thinker's Coral
Description:
Freshwater coral far too pretentious to thrive anywhere but the Thaliak.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Oddly Specific Amber
Description: A hunk of fossilized resin of very particular hue, clarity, and age.

Name: Oddly Specific Bauble
Description: Given the detailed nature of their request, one would think that the Skysteel engineers ought to have been able to come up with a more precise means of referring to this so-called bauble.

Name: Oddly Specific Dark Matter
Description: Darker (and more specific) than your average matter.

Name: Oddly Specific Striking Stone
Description: This curious sphere tends to set nearby tinder alight at but a touch, whether such an effect is desired or not.

Name: Dragonspine
Description:
This spiked shell belies the soft and harmless form of the mollusk withinwhich itself belies the deranged lethality of said mollusk.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Skysteel Prototype Coffer
Description:
A tool chest containing a Skysteel prototype.

Required level: 80. IL: 440. Primary tool type determined by current class at time of opening. Cannot be opened in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.

Name: Mahogany Aqueduct
Description: Reliable and stylish irrigation well suited to residential properties.

Name: Crystallized Coral
Description: This crystallized mass of coral matches almost any color scheme one could imagine.

Name: White Screen
Description: That this screen always maintains its sterling whiteness speaks to the quality of its construction.

Name: Siphon Coffee Brewer
Description: Many a connoisseur have sworn off all other methods of making coffee after trying a single sip of a cup made with this one.

Name: Fat Cat Wall Chronometer
Description: This convenient timekeeping device will always remind you when it is time to eatunless, of course, it is time for your pets to eat, in which case you will be repeatedly reminded long before you have the chance to consult your timepiece.

Name: Bomb Cauldron
Description: Crafted with painstaking attention to detail, put this cauldron in any room to terrify guests and pets alike.

Name: Ronkan Rocking Chair
Description: A rocking chair representing Ronkan resourcefulness and resilience.

Name: Brick Garden Wall
Description: A portion of brick wall that would complement nearly any garden, be it full of flowers or full of more subdued plant life.

Name: Authentic Festive Chirashi-zushi
Description:
Almost identical to normal chirashi-zushi, but with markedly more festivity. This serving is guaranteed authentic...and hopefully fresh.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Direct Hit Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  VIT Bonus: +5% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Authentic Festive Sushi Balls
Description:
Put off by the oblongitudinal proportions of regular sushi? Well, your prayers have been answered. All the fresh fish and vinegared rice you love, authentically ham-fisted into semi-sophisticated spheroids perfect for popping.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Piety Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  VIT Bonus: +5% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Authentic Archon Egg Pile
Description: In your (authentically adorned) abode, eggs hide you.

Name: Authentic Eggcentric Crown Roast
Description:
An authentically artful arrangement of several succulent, spice-rubbed racks of lamb, accompanied by a side of steaming soup.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Tenacity Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  VIT Bonus: +5% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Authentic Eggcentric Chocolate Cake
Description:
A staggeringly sweet chocolate cake served with chocolate bunnies and what one can only hope are chocolate eggs, rather than authentic ones that might have been farm-fresh as of last year.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Critical Hit Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  VIT Bonus: +5% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Description:
A banded chest containing an Edenchoir weapon.

Required level: 80. IL: 505. Weapon type determined by current job or class at time of opening. Cannot be opened in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.

Description:
A banded chest containing a piece of Edenchoir attire.

Required level: 80. IL: 500. Head gear type determined by current job or class at time of opening. Cannot be opened in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.

Name: Edenchoir Waist Gear Coffer (IL 500)
Description: A banded chest containing a piece of Edenchoir attire. Due to advancements in trouser technology, the belt within this chest is no longer worth the trouble of opening it.

Name: Edenchoir Earring Coffer (IL 500)
Description:
A banded chest containing an Edenchoir accessory.

Required level: 80. IL: 500. Earring type determined by current job or class at time of opening. Cannot be opened in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.

A banded chest containing an Edenchoir accessory.

Required level: 80. IL: 500. Necklace type determined by current job or class at time of opening. Cannot be opened in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.

Name: Edenchoir Bracelet Coffer (IL 500)
Description:
A banded chest containing an Edenchoir accessory.

Required level: 80. IL: 500. Bracelet type determined by current job or class at time of opening. Cannot be opened in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.

A banded chest containing an Edenchoir accessory.

Required level: 80. IL: 500. Ring type determined by current job or class at time of opening. Cannot be opened in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.

Name: Flower Basket Card
Description:
A common () card used in the game Triple Triad.
Card No. 269

Name: Qitari Card
Description:
A common () card used in the game Triple Triad.
Card No. 270

Name: Gnoll Card
Description:
An uncommon () card used in the game Triple Triad.
Card No. 271

Name: Lizbeth Card
Description:
An uncommon () card used in the game Triple Triad.
Card No. 278

Name: Batsquatch Card
