A rare () card used in the game Triple Triad.
Card No. 272

Name: Forgiven Obscenity Card
Description:
A rare () card used in the game Triple Triad.
Card No. 273

Name: Huaca Card
Description:
A rare () card used in the game Triple Triad.
Card No. 274

Name: Unknown Card
Description:
A rare () card used in the game Triple Triad.
Card No. 275

Name: Ruby Weapon Card
Description:
An epic () card used in the game Triple Triad.
Card No. 276

Name: Therion Card
Description:
A legendary () card used in the game Triple Triad.
Card No. 277

Name: Ragworm
Description:
A marine worm that slithers about in the rocks dotting the ocean floor. Effective for luring small fish.

Only for use in Ocean Fishing.

Name: Krill
Description:
A species of krill commonly found in the Rhotano Sea. Effective for luring medium-sized fish.

Only for use in Ocean Fishing.

Name: Plump Worm
Description:
A species of worm that grows fat on the nutrients swirling about in the currents of the Rhotano Sea. Effective for luring large fish.

Only for use in Ocean Fishing.

Name: Versatile Lure
Description: A lure developed by the Fishermen's Guild specifically for novice anglers. Can be used on land or at sea.

Name: Tossed Dagger
Description:
Often seen skimming the waves, shimmering like a blade in flight.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Jasperhead
Description:
Sought for the gemlike objects that form in their stomachs, not in their heads, as the name might suggest.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Merlthor Lobster
Description:
As ubiquitous as they are delicious. A staple of seafood cuisine across Eorzea.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Heavenswimmer
Description:
Easily spotted from afar due to their bright coloration, although sightings in the oceans surrounding Eorzea are scarce due to their unusual migratory patterns.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Ghoul Barracuda
Description:
Despite its considerable size, this ocean-dweller chooses to feast on the flesh of the dead rather than expend effort pursuing live prey.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Leopard Eel
Description:
As per its namesake, it occupies a position fairly close to the top of the food chain, but is still forced to flee from larger and more dangerous predators.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Marine Bomb
Description:
Known more for its tendency to explode with rage in a figurative sense rather than a literal one, as its name might suggest.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Momora Mora
Description:
Unlike the Lalafell from whom its name derives, this ocean-drifter is far from diminutive.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Merlthor Butterfly
Description:
Highly sought by aquarium owners for its vivid coloration, this increasingly rare species is arguably worth its weight in gold.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Gladius
Description:
A fish named after a swordor was the sword named after the fish?

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Rhotano Wahoo
Description:
Though it seems harmless enough at first glance, this fish has been rendered all but inedible by its highly poisonous diet. The taste is said to be exquisite by those brave enough to try it, however.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Rhotano Sardine
Description:
Usually seen traveling in large schools, these rather plain fish possess the group mentality of a flock of sheepthat is, to follow whoever is in front and, lacking that, just keep moving forward until something with big teeth appears. Then all hells break loose.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Deep Plaice
Description:
The name provides a useful hint as to the areas of the ocean this creature usually inhabits.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Crimson Monkfish
Description:
An angler never forgets the first time they reel in one of these deep-sea demons, no matter how hard they try.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Lampfish
Description:
Sought more for its roe than its meat. Thankfully its lack of muscular mass in comparison to the size of its body makes for an easy catch.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Ogre Eel
Description:
Even when it finds itself dangling from an angler's line, its only thought is to consume as much flesh as possible, which causes many a fisher to cast it back into the sea in sheer panic.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Cyan Octopus
Description:
Hunted for the copious amounts of ink it produces, the vast majority of which is spilled upon its capture. As a result, anglers with bright blue hands are a common sight around Galadion Bay.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Chrome Hammerhead
Description:
Differentiated from similar species by its unique coloration, which gives it a certain metallic sheen.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Floefish
Description:
This small, almost entirely defenseless fish forms an important link in the food chainone quite near to the bottom.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Megasquid
Description:
One does not earn a name like megasquid by being small and unassuming, which this aquatic abomination certainly is not.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Oschon's Stone
Description:
Seemingly living up to its namesake, this heavy and largely immobile wavekin spends most of its life on the ocean floor. It feeds by opening its mouth and waiting for curious prey to swim inside. 

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: La Noscean Jelly
Description:
It was named as part of a movement to expunge the word fish from jellyfish, for reasons pertaining to consistency and accuracy, although this has met with little success thus far.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Shaggy Seadragon
Description:
Almost indistinguishable in appearance from the seaweed on which it feeds. It must take care not to overeat and thereby destroy its own hiding place from predators.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Net Crawler
Description:
Unlike most crabs, the main source of edible meat is found in the legs. The torso is often discarded as it mostly consists of hard gristle and unappetizing...matter.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Dark Nautilus
Description:
Known for its ability to survive on aether alone, researchers are willing to part with huge sums of gil for live samples.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Elder Dinichthys
Description:
Swims about the Strait of Merlthor as though it owns the placea claim which few of the other inhabitants are in any position to dispute.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Drunkfish
Description:
If you had a face like this, you'd look sad, too.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Little Leviathan
Description:
Even a greatly scaled-down (pun very much intended) version of the Lord of the Whorl is more than a match for all but the most experienced fishers.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Sabaton
Description:
Strangely for a mollusk, its body is covered in hard scales in addition to the more common shell. Many predators will steer clear of them simply because they are a bother to eat.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Shooting Star
Description:
One's chances of seeing an actual shooting star are greater than that of being able to observe one of these rare wavekin in its natural habitat.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Hammerclaw
Description:
While most wavekin object quite strongly to being caught on a hook, these crustaceans make life especially difficult for anglers in retaliation. If they are not pinching fingers, they are flailing wildly with their heavy claws, both of which most fishers should and do go to great lengths to avoid.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Heavenskey
Description:
Due to being highly poisonous, it is believed to send those who eat of its flesh to the heavens. Compared to the seven hells, this may prove a more desirable destination.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Ghost Shark
Description:
According to certain sources, it is able to appear spontaneously from any body of water. Such stories, however, are probably best ignored.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Quicksilver Blade
Description:
While there may be larger and deadlier wavekin roaming the oceans, few can claim to be as hideous as this aberration of nature.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Navigator's Print
Description:
This denizen of the deep can proudly claim to take its name from a goddess, even if the tale behind it does involve being stepped on by said goddess.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Casket Oyster
Description:
While there are several theories surrounding the origin of its name, the general consensus is that it is as hard to open as a casket that has been nailed shut. However, it is nothing a brief spell in a pot of boiling water cannot solve.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Fishmonger
Description:
Known for its habit of seeking out a variety of fish, though unlike its namesake, these are purely for its own consumption.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Mythril Sovereign
Description:
Known for its beautifully shimmering scales, which are in contrast to its rather lackluster meat.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Nimble Dancer
Description:
Coveted by keepers of exotic fish for the mesmerizing manner in which its trailing fins catch the light.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Sea Nettle
Description:
Not the most welcome of catches, as it tends to deliver a nasty sting to those whose hands wander too close.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Great Grandmarlin
Description:
More often than not, this hulking yet deceptively quick wavekin escapes the angler's hook, usually by severing the line with its bladelike bill.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Shipwreck's Sail
Description:
This wavekin is so broad and flat that it has been compared to the sail of a ship left to float on the tide. In actuality, it is waiting for seabirds to pick the parasites from its flanks.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Azeyma's Sleeve
Description:
Many artist's impressions of Azeyma depict Her with flowing, bell-adorned sleeves, not unlike the elegant silhouette of this wavekin.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Hi-aetherlouse
Description:
An aetherially charged wavekin that has a habit of appearing when one least expects or wants it.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Floating Saucer
Description:
Far less welcome at a mess hall table than an actual saucer, as these odd creatures taste rather like a sailor's subligar. Apparently.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Aetheric Seadragon
Description:
Framed in fabulous frond-like fins, this ferocious fish frequently frightens off foes who would fight for its feed.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Coral Seadragon
Description:
Dedicates its life to lookingand behavingas much like coral as possible.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Roguesaurus
Description:
Named after the river rather than the traditional Lominsan profession. Those unfortunate enough to encounter one will testify that to describe it as roguish would be an understatement, and that murderous, man-eating, and malevolent would all be more applicable adjectives.

[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Merman's Mane
Description:
Though the existence of mermen is much debated, if any were to exist, they would no doubt object to the comparisons drawn between their long locks and the tentacles of this grotesque cephalopod.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Sweeper
Description:
Its habit of moving its head from side to side while searching the seabed for food has earned it this unusual moniker.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Silencer
Description:
While technically edible, it is not without side effects. Temporary loss of speech being the most noticeable, though there may be others that are harder to detect.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Deep-sea Eel
Description:
As may be inferred from the less-than-spectacular name, this eel resides in the sea. The deep part.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Executioner
Description:
Goes out of its way to make life as difficult as possible for those who enter its territory, including sawing holes in hulls and tearing through nets.

[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Wild Urchin
Description:
A creamy center encased in horrendously sharp spines. Only those who acquire the knack of eating one without impaling themselves can acquire the decidedly acquired taste.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: True Barramundi
Description:
This slow-moving, ponderous wavekin manages to avoid the attention of predators by being so unremarkable as to hardly warrant attention in the first place.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Mopbeard
Description:
Lifting it above the waterline causes it to transform from an elegant oceanic beauty to something resembling...well, a mop.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Slipsnail
Description:
While it may seem harmless enough, it has a nasty surprise in store for unwitting predators.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Aronnax
Description:
Its remarkable speed is matched only by its unfathomable clumsiness, the combination of which often leads it straight into the waiting nets of fishers.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Coccosteus
Description:
Revered by the Sahagin and reviled by practically everyone else. Its proclivity for biting fingers means that most who catch one end up wishing they hadn't.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Bartholomew the Chopper
Description:
Suspected by some to be the reincarnation of an unhinged murderer, although it is also known to have a more amiable side. Well, about as amiable as one can expect from a wavekin that revels in killing.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Prowler
Description:
While the word prowl may suggest the slow, deliberate movement of one tracking its prey, this particular wavekin is simply slow by nature, mainly as a result of sheer indolence.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Charlatan Survivor
Description:
At first glance, the charlatan survivor may appear to be a well-armored crustacean, but the outer shell is merely a purloined disguise concealing a much smaller creature beneath. Luckily, predatory wavekin are quite easily deceived and often choose to leave it alone in order to pursue less chitinous prey.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Prodigal Son
Description:
Rather than follow the standard migratory patterns of his brethren, this wandering wavekin swims to the beat of his own drum, and comes and goes as he pleases.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Gugrusaurus
Description:
Spends most of its life attempting to slaughter anything and everything that it catches sight of. Considering the ample opportunities to practice such skills, it has become rather good at it.

[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Funnel Shark
Description:
Its gaping maw draws in all manner of ocean life, along with a range of less-than-edible objects.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 4 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: The Fallen One
Description:
Believed by some to have descended from the heavens, and judging by the way it nervously flits about the ocean, it wishes it could return to whence it came. Few wavekin look less comfortable in their habitat than this unfortunate creature.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Spectral Megalodon
Description:
Due to the fact that most of its prey are petrified upon catching sight of this ominously glowing predator, it has rather an easy time finding a steady supply of food.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 4 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Spectral Discus
Description:
This aetherially infused wavekin gathers rather a lot of unwanted attention, and it has no natural defenses to fend off curious predators.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Spectral Sea Bo
Description:
Its strange blue glow seems to have done wonders for its self-confidence, and it can be seen doing the underwater variation of strutting like a peacock...or whatever the chocobo equivalent of a peacock is.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Spectral Bass
Description:
This most ordinary of fish has become rather extraordinary thanks to being bathed in otherworldly aether, giving it a fetching blue tinge.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 3 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Sothis
Description:
It is unclear how this species of turtle came to have a shell covered in glittering crystal, though it does give oceanic hunters pause for thought before they attempt to bite down on it. This could be considered a form of unnatural protection.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 4 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Coral Manta
Description:
Few creatures can claim to have an entire ecosystem on their back, although this appears to afford the host no practical benefits whatsoever.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 4 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Stonescale
Description:
The thick covering of rock-like substance does little to improve this shark's mobility. Being an apex predator means it has little need of excessive armor plating.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 4 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Elasmosaurus
Description:
In the harsh, unforgiving open sea, few creatures have proven a more valuable ally to mankind than the elasmosaurus. Though they are most often known to tow ships and carry out courageous acts of self-sacrifice, these gentle giants can also be lethally dangerous when angered.

[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Grade 2 Skybuilders' Plywood
Description: While this could be combined with a few bricks to create a makeshift bench, that may fall somewhat short of the skybuilders' rather more lofty aspirations.

Name: Grade 2 Skybuilders' Alloy
Description: Even in its current state, it would make a functional, if not especially elegant, murder weapon.

Name: Grade 2 Skybuilders' Steel Plate
Description: To some, it may seem a shame to ruin such a beautifully square piece of metal by battering it with a hammer.

Name: Grade 2 Skybuilders' Ingot
Description: These would make a suitable substitute for house bricks were it not for their natural propensity to conduct cold, which is less than ideal in the freezing climes of Ishgard.

Name: Grade 2 Skybuilders' Leather
Description: Considered to be particularly valuable, especially by the creature to which it originally belonged.

Name: Grade 2 Skybuilders' Rope
Description: Perfectly suited to pulling heavy objects. Less well suited to pushing them.

Name: Grade 2 Skybuilders' Ink
Description: While some may question the skybuilders' need for a specific type of ink, it is believed that this particular variety is more resistant to the cold. After all, frozen ink does not lend itself well to fine penmanship, or any sort of penmanship, for that matter.

Name: Grade 2 Skybuilders' Hemp Milk
Description: While the layman may question exactly how one goes about milking a plant, the process is much the same as milking anything else: you give it a damned good squeeze and hope for the best.

Name: Grade 2 Skybuilders' Crate
Description: Despite much of the work in the Firmament involving taking supplies out of boxes, the need occasionally arises to put them into boxes instead. Suggestions that the skybuilders simply reuse the boxes they already have were immediately shot down, presumably by someone who stands to profit from the production of new containers.

Name: Grade 2 Skybuilders' Nails
Description: Never was the description tough as nails more apt, because they are, in fact, nails.

Name: Grade 2 Skybuilders' Rivets
Description: Despite their name, discussions on these commonplace metal studs tend to be anything but riveting.

Name: Grade 2 Skybuilders' Rings
Description: Attempting to impress a potential spouse by presenting one of these mass-produced metallic circles will generally end in failure, and perhaps even a slap in the face for good measure.

Name: Grade 2 Skybuilders' Leather Straps
Description: Some may wonder whether this leather was in fact more useful before it was cut into long strips. It could have been used to make a nice coat, for example.

Name: Grade 2 Skybuilders' Cloth
Description: As the popular Coerthan adage attests, One can never have too much cloth.

Name: Grade 2 Skybuilders' Plant Oil
Description: Not only is it used by chefs, but also masseuses. Unfortunately, there is not much call for such work in Ishgard, as the general consensus is that clothes are best kept on at all times unless absolutely necessary.

Name: Grade 2 Skybuilders' Bread
Description: While it is true that man cannot live on bread alone, a little bit here and there certainly does not go amiss.

Name: Grade 2 Skybuilders' Grindstone
Description: Clearly, the expression nose to the grindstone was not meant to be taken literally, though some have chosen to find this out the hard way.

Name: Grade 2 Skybuilders' Hammer
Description: Tenderizing pork with this craftsman's tool does not, as one might be forgiven for thinking given the name, turn it into ham.

Name: Grade 2 Skybuilders' Still
Description: This bizarre contraption is coveted by alchemists and culinarians alike. When asked for what purpose, the response is generally along the lines of, Mumble, mumble, steam, mumble, mumble.

Name: Grade 2 Skybuilders' Embroidery Frame
Description: A firm favorite among ladies of leisure, oft held mid-stitch as they gaze wistfully from the window of their opulent bedchamber, high in their metaphoricaland in some cases, actualivory tower.

Name: Grade 2 Skybuilders' Rug
Description: Some things are best swept under one of these.

Name: Grade 2 Skybuilders' Broom
Description: Those expecting this perfectly ordinary broom to start speaking backwards or sweeping floors of its own accord will be disappointed to find it does neither, unless a passing witch is in the mood for a couple of incantations.

Name: Grade 2 Skybuilders' Dye
Description: Those thinking about using this colorful dye for their own purposes should put such thoughts aside, as it is strictly for skybuilder use only. After all, one can hardly expect them to go about their work deprived of the ability to turn something purple at a moment's notice.

Name: Grade 2 Skybuilders' Tea
Description: Skybuilders have garnered a reputation for punctuating their work with frequent tea breaks. The number of cups drunk by a laborer over the course of a single day can easily reach double digits.

Name: Grade 2 Skybuilders' Stepladder
Description: Unlike most other items requested by the skybuilders, this one actually seems to serve some practical purpose. It can even be carried on one shoulder, allowing the bearer to pivot quickly, which leads to all sorts of hilarity as their colleagues attempt, often in vain, to avoid having their skull cracked.

Name: Grade 2 Skybuilders' Crosscut Saw
Description: The sound it makes as it cleaves through timber is akin to that of a person snoring. One particular linguist even went so far as to investigate a possible connection between the words sawing and snoring, and to no one's surprise but her own, discovered that nothing of the sort exists.

Name: Grade 2 Skybuilders' Mesail
Description: Perfect for protecting one's face from the accusing glares of innocent bystanders during daylight robberies and so forth, although the skybuilders have a far more pedestrian use in mind.

Name: Grade 2 Skybuilders' Stone
Description: A strong contender for the heaviest item requested by the skybuilders. How the volunteers are expected to transport these without an exceedingly sturdy cart is anyone's guess.

Name: Grade 2 Skybuilders' Longboots
Description: As the name implies, these boots are what some might consider long, although longer still are the grade 2 skybuilders' longlongboots.

Name: Grade 2 Skybuilders' Gloves
Description: Keepers of hounds with the tendency to bite the hand that feeds will be delighted to receive a pair of these fine gloves. The smooth lining allows the wearer to slip out easily, leaving said dog with a mouthful of tough leather, which it will soon learn makes a poor substitute for proper food.

Name: Grade 2 Skybuilders' Soap
Description: When combined with an empty stocking, can be used as a makeshift weapon. In Ishgard, this appears to be the most common use, since many residents have discovered that the need to wash is largely mitigated by the wearing of multiple layers of thick clothing, which does little to prevent bodily odor, but does cause it to take longer to seep through and reach the nostrils of those in the immediate vicinity.

Name: Grade 2 Skybuilders' All-purpose Infusion
Description: There may be uncertainty surrounding its exact effects, although one thing is clear: it definitely tastes as if it does one good. That is to say, revolting.

Name: Grade 2 Skybuilders' Bed
Description: As it stands only a few ilms off of the floor, any things that go bump in the night will have trouble squeezing under this particular bed.

Name: Grade 2 Skybuilders' Oven
Description: Complete with raging fire and billowing smoke, which, while impressive, does make it rather troublesome to transport.

Name: Grade 2 Skybuilders' Lamppost
Description: Those with high ceilings in their chambers may wish to employ this as a rather extravagant bedside reading light.

Name: Grade 2 Skybuilders' Brazier
Description: Any meat fried on this outdoor brazier produces smoke with the uncanny ability to find its way into the eyes of those foolish enough to wander too near.

Name: Grade 2 Skybuilders' Overalls
Description: Designed to be worn on top of other, nicer clothes. Ideal for those who like to muck out their chocobo stables immediately before going for afternoon tea with an overbearing but wealthy aunt.

Name: Grade 2 Skybuilders' Gazebo
Description: Purpose-built for picnics in the great outdoors, protecting those beneath from any untimely precipitation. Unfortunately, the snow in most parts of Coerthas tends to fall in a rather sideways fashion, thus rendering this gazebo entirely pointless.

Name: Grade 2 Skybuilders' Alchemic
Description: The joy gained from sampling its fragrancereminiscent of summer meadowsnormally only lasts until the caustic vapors burn the skin from the inside of one's nostrils.

Name: Grade 2 Skybuilders' Stew
Description: The term potluck applies perfectly to this particular dish, as it is traditionally assembled from whatever the chef can dig up from an often poorly lit pantry. The fact that rats tend to squeak and wriggle a fair bit when picked up is probably all that prevents them from being added to the mix. The dead ones, on the other hand...

Name: Grade 2 Artisanal Skybuilders' Wardrobe
Description: If, for any reason, one has the need to hide inside, such as the unexpected return of one of the residents and so on, the air holes provided should prevent untimely suffocation. Not that there is such a thing as timely suffocation.

Name: Grade 2 Artisanal Skybuilders' Chandelier
Description: Most of the diamonds are actually imitations, but thankfully, chandeliers are usually positioned high enough that no one will notice.

Name: Grade 2 Artisanal Skybuilders' Fireplace
Description: The ideal place to put a fire, hence the clever name. Well, the last part, that is.

Name: Grade 2 Artisanal Skybuilders' Bathtub
Description: In mankind's ongoing quest to keep water and not water ever separate, few inventions have done more to further the cause than the humble bathtub.

Name: Grade 2 Artisanal Skybuilders' Overcoat
Description: If dapperness could be captured, refined, and made into a wearable material, that is what this fine garment would be made from. Until then, cloth and leather will have to suffice.

Name: Grade 2 Artisanal Skybuilders' Wallpaper
Description: Generally less messy than covering walls with paint, although its natural tendency to tear and wrinkle with the slightest provocation is enough to make a saint swear.

Name: Grade 2 Artisanal Skybuilders' Remedies
Description: It is assumed that each of these glass phials contains something useful, as none of them are labeled. Identification by taste is probably best left to a professional or someone who is not opposed to being lightly poisoned.

Name: Grade 2 Artisanal Skybuilders' Quiche
Description: In cases such as these, artisanal actually means so complex that even the chef doesn't remember what went into it, hence the impossibility of replicating the recipe.

Name: Approved Grade 2 Skybuilders' Switch
Description:
A sharp rap across the back of the thigh in the cold, crisp Ishgardian morning air with one of these light and flexible branches is a surefire way to blow away the proverbial cobwebs of any workers caught yawning.

Used in level 20 crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 2 Skybuilders' Hemp
Description:
One can only hope that whatever purpose the skybuilders have in mind for this hardy plant was worth depriving some herbivorous creature of its leafy goodness.

Used in level 20 crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 2 Skybuilders' Ore
Description:
Something of a mixed bag of metallic elements, but as everyone knows, smithies love a good surprise. Just not when they're swinging a hammer dangerously close to their fingers.

Used in level 20 crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 2 Skybuilders' Copper Sand
Description:
A special place in one of the seven hells exists for those who attempt to fob off the skybuilders by mixing in regular sand with the copper, or so the skybuilders would have one believe.

Used in level 20 crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 2 Skybuilders' Maple Log
Description:
The sap slowly leaking from the logs tends to attract ants, which even the skybuilders have yet to find a use for. This may come as a surprise considering the plethora of bizarre items they request, and it may only be a matter of time until some bright spark invents ant sandwiches.

Used in level 40 crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 2 Skybuilders' Maple Sap
Description:
Any insect foolhardy enough to attempt sampling its delight will invariably find itself trapped within this glutinous substance, preserved for future generations to study and possibly experiment on. Still, there are worse ways to go than being enveloped in one's favorite sweet treat.

Used in level 40 crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 2 Skybuilders' Flax
Description:
Included in a surprising number of recipes and concoctions despite its only notable property being it smells nice.

Used in level 40 crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 2 Skybuilders' Zinc Ore
Description:
Zinc is said to prevent a number of common ailments. However, it must be noted that attempting to ingest it in its current state may actually cause problems such as broken teeth and stomachache, usually in that order.

Used in level 40 crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 2 Skybuilders' Rock Salt
Description:
There are few dishes that cannot be improved with a sprinkling of salt. Strangely, this even includes a number of desserts, which flies in the face of all common logic.

Used in level 40 crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 2 Skybuilders' Iron Sand
Description:
In the event that one somehow accidentally mixes this with normal sand, the two can be separated by waving a magnet nearby. This knowledge mayor more likely, may notsave your life one day.

Used in level 40 crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 2 Skybuilders' Teak Log
Description:
Although such logs are the perfect material for fashioning rafts and canoes, the distinctly frozen bodies of water that surround Ishgard scupper the locals' chances of enjoying the pleasures of boating.

Used in level 60 crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 2 Skybuilders' Mistletoe
Description:
Any ancient myths describing darts made from a sprig of mistletoe neglect to mention the fact that when thrown, it displays the airborne grace of a drunken, one-winged chicken.

Used in level 60 crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 2 Skybuilders' Beehive
Description:
A bee colony will often respond to the presence of intruders by swarming their intended target and using their own body heat to cook it alive. The skybuilders have discovered that this can be utilized to keep their hands warm, although the fact that said bees are still very much capable of stinging does present a minor flaw in this otherwise brilliant idea.

Used in level 60 crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 2 Skybuilders' Straw
Description:
In some parts of Eorzea, straw is used to weave hats with wide peaks to keep the sun from the wearer's eyes. Fortunatelyor perhaps unfortunatelyfor Ishgardians, there is seldom enough sunlight to warrant such headwear, and the vicious winds would prevent the owner from remaining behatted for more than a few scant moments.

Used in level 60 crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 2 Skybuilders' Tea Leaves
Description:
For Ishgardians, discussing the virtues of various blends of tea is almost as much of a pastime as actually drinking the stuff. This fine selection of choice leaves could be placed in the center of a table to serve to facilitate stimulating conversation, while the skybuilders continue to labor away in the bitter cold outside.

Used in level 60 crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 2 Skybuilders' Cobalt Ore
Description:
A lot less blue than one might expect, although it tastes about right.

Used in level 60 crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 2 Skybuilders' Pigment
Description:
While some of the skybuilders were in favor of naming this substance purple stuff, the need to follow a more sensible naming convention eventually prevailed.

Used in level 60 crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 2 Skybuilders' Asphaltum
Description:
Plans to use this sticky, black substance to cover the streets of Ishgard were vehemently opposed, as it would ruin the uniformly grey aestheticwhich on most days includes the sky itself.

Used in level 60 crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 2 Skybuilders' Mythril Sand
Description:
The bright hue of this valuable substance does make it stand out from the surrounding rocks and so forth, but only under the condition that one is able to find the damnable stuff in the first place.

Used in level 60 crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 2 Skybuilders' Mica
Description:
Mica would make rather a nice name for a person, if it were not already taken by this rather unremarkable rock.

Used in level 60 crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 2 Skybuilders' Oak Log
Description:
The tiny acorn that grew into this mighty oak had its life cut tragically short by the cruel axe of a woodsman (or possibly woodslady). If there is any justice in the world, it will be born anew as a nice dresser or an attractive hat stand.

Used in level 70 crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 2 Skybuilders' Feather
Description:
While even Ishgard's finest ornithologist would be hard-pressed to identify the bird from which this came, one thing is certain: there are more where this came from, unless said bird only ever possessed a single feather.

Used in level 70 crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 2 Skybuilders' Vine
Description:
Careless owners of high-walled castles in faerie tales often allow these to grow over said walls, thereby allowing dashing heroes to infiltrate the premises to steal jewels, damsels in distress, scones from the pantry, and so forth.

Used in level 70 crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 2 Skybuilders' Toad
Description:
One skybuilder was heard to claim that to assign grades to living creatures is degrading. The response was, No, taking the grade away from it would be called degrading.

Used in level 70 crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 2 Skybuilders' Barbgrass
Description:
According to local legend, a night raid on a Temple Knights encampment was foiled when the assailants wandered into a patch of barbgrass. Nothing gives the game away quite like pained squeals of, Oh, my poor bottom!

Used in level 70 crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 2 Skybuilders' Mythrite Ore
Description:
Due to the fact it is almost identical in appearance to mythril ore, it is sometimes known as fool's mythril. Conversely, actual mythril is often referred to as fool's mythrite.

Used in level 70 crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 2 Skybuilders' Spring Water
Description:
Despite the potentially misleading name, it can also be collected in summer and autumn. Winter, however, is generally out of the question, for obvious reasons.

Used in level 70 crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 2 Skybuilders' Alumen
Description:
Were the skybuilders less exacting in their demands, the standard alumen found in market stalls across Eorzea would be more than sufficient. Many volunteers suspect that such tasks are set merely to test their patience.

Used in level 70 crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 2 Skybuilders' Rock
Description:
If you think this rock is uninteresting, you should see the grade 1 skybuilders' rock, which is so plain that it can blend into any background by virtue of its sheer dullness.

Used in level 70 crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 2 Skybuilders' Silex
Description:
The name makes it sound far more sinister than it actually is.

Used in level 70 crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 2 Skybuilders' Walnut Log
Description:
Think of all the walnuts that could have grown on this tree had it not been cut down! Walnuts for breakfast, walnuts for elevenses, walnuts for luncheon... The possibilities were endless.

Used in level 80 crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 2 Skybuilders' Resin
Description:
Resin this pure, this beautiful is far too good for the skybuilders. Perhaps you should keep it all to yourself. They need never know.

Used in level 80 crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 2 Skybuilders' Wheat
Description:
There is a possibility that some grade 1 wheat slipped in by mistake.

Used in level 80 crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 2 Skybuilders' Cotton Boll
Description:
One of the skybuilder's children asked, Is this what sheep are made from? The answer was a resounding, I'm not sure. Possibly.

Used in level 80 crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 2 Skybuilders' Adder
Description:
Venomous, but not fatally so. Perfect for practical jokes and party tricks.

Used in level 80 crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 2 Skybuilders' Darksteel Ore
Description:
Has the potential to be made into something very scary indeed, like spiked pauldrons or an enormous battleaxe. In all likelihood, however, it will probably become a slightly extravagant kettle or decorative letter opener.

Used in level 80 crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 2 Skybuilders' Crystal-clear Rock Salt
Description:
With a name that long, one might be forgiven for expecting it to be some sort of miraculous super-salt, capable of turning even the blandest dish into a festival of flavor. Sadly, this is not the case, although it is nonetheless rather good as far as salt goes.

Used in level 80 crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 2 Skybuilders' Cloud Drop Water
Description:
Most people realize cloud drop is just a fancy way to say rain. Not many customers would be willing to pay for mere rainwater, but cloud drop water, on the other hand...

Used in level 80 crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 2 Skybuilders' Lutinite
Description:
Said to be blessed by cloud spirits, which may or may not be a good thing. Still, blessed is infinitely preferable to cursed.

Used in level 80 crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 2 Skybuilders' Basalt
Description:
Basalt actually has very little in common with salt, despite its name being approximately two-thirds the same.

Used in level 80 crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 2 Artisanal Skybuilders' Log
Description:
As the skybuilders prefer to use wooden planks of standardized dimensions, this log is already cut to be exactly the length they require, to minimize the carpenters' workload. One can only hope they appreciate the extra effort by throwing a few more scrips your way.

Used in expert crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 2 Artisanal Skybuilders' Hardened Sap
Description:
Although the practical applications of a piece of hardened sap are somewhat unclear, it is at least considerably less sticky than unhardened sap, which helps to keep it free of impurities such as loose hairs, bits of pocket fluff, and so on.

Used in expert crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 2 Artisanal Skybuilders' Wheat
Description:
What about this wheat makes it artisanal? Those in the know claim it is massaged daily and fed beer, which is the reason for the delicious marbled texture. Or perhaps they were talking about some sort of cow?

Used in expert crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 2 Artisanal Skybuilders' Cotton Boll
Description:
To the untrained eye, this may appear to be no different from any other cotton boll. Those with trained eyes, however, will notice that it is pink, not the usual white.

Used in expert crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 2 Artisanal Skybuilders' Dawn Lizard
Description:
Those wondering what separates this from a non-artisanal dawn lizard need only observe the way it devours its prey. For a carnivorous, slavering scalekin, it has the most impeccable table manners, or more precisely, blood-spattered patch of ground manners.

Used in expert crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 2 Artisanal Skybuilders' Cloudstone
Description:
Believed to be a piece of fossilized cloud.

Used in expert crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 2 Artisanal Skybuilders' Rock Salt
Description:
It seems there are almost as many varieties of rock salt as there are varieties of rock, if the skybuilders' somewhat arbitrary system of assigning names is to be believed.

Used in expert crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 2 Artisanal Skybuilders' Spring Water
Description:
Rather than simply being free of impurities, this water actually possesses the ability to preemptively destroy any impurities that dare to come near it. As such, only those pure of heart can drink of it without being killed instantly, or so it is rumored.

Used in expert crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 2 Artisanal Skybuilders' Aurum Regis Sand
Description:
One of the few substances known to be both edible and highly explosive. While some spicy ingredients are said to be capable of blowing one's head off, in this case, it is no exaggeration.

Used in expert crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 2 Artisanal Skybuilders' Jade
Description:
In the Brume, to be jaded means to have a large piece of jade thrown at the back of one's head. Thankfully, the prohibitive pricing of this precious substance means that such incidents are rare.

Used in expert crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 2 Skybuilders' Umbral Galewood Log
Description:
Carried on raging winds, charged with potent aether. Probably the most powerful log in existence.

Can only be gathered during an umbral tempest.

Used in expert crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 2 Skybuilders' Umbral Earthcap
Description:
Charged with aether drawn from the earth. In actual fact, most mushrooms possess some earth-aspected aether, but this particular species is especially greedy.

Can only be gathered during an umbral duststorm.

Used in expert crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 2 Skybuilders' Umbral Flarestone
Description:
Red-hot to the touch, which makes it a bastard to carry.

Can only be gathered during an umbral flare.

Used in expert crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 2 Skybuilders' Umbral Levinshard
Description:
If you thought catching lightning in a bottle was difficult, catching it in a crystal fragment is even trickier. At least a bottle comes with a handy cap to keep in said lightning when caught, whereas crystal relies on nothing more than the bolt's willing cooperation.

Can only be gathered during umbral levin.

Used in expert crafting recipes.

Name: Grade 2 Skybuilders' Switch
Description:
A sharp rap across the back of the thigh in the cold, crisp Ishgardian morning air with one of these light and flexible branches is a surefire way to blow away the proverbial cobwebs of any workers caught yawning.

Used in level 20 crafting recipes.

Name: Grade 2 Skybuilders' Hemp
Description:
One can only hope that whatever purpose the skybuilders have in mind for this hardy plant was worth depriving some herbivorous creature of its leafy goodness.

Used in level 20 crafting recipes.

Name: Grade 2 Skybuilders' Ore
Description:
Something of a mixed bag of metallic elements, but as everyone knows, smithies love a good surprise. Just not when they're swinging a hammer dangerously close to their fingers.

Used in level 20 crafting recipes.

Name: Grade 2 Skybuilders' Copper Sand
Description:
A special place in one of the seven hells exists for those who attempt to fob off the skybuilders by mixing in regular sand with the copper, or so the skybuilders would have one believe.

Used in level 20 crafting recipes.

Name: Grade 2 Skybuilders' Maple Log
Description:
The sap slowly leaking from the logs tends to attract ants, which even the skybuilders have yet to find a use for. This may come as a surprise considering the plethora of bizarre items they request, and it may only be a matter of time until some bright spark invents ant sandwiches.

Used in level 40 crafting recipes.

Name: Grade 2 Skybuilders' Maple Sap
Description:
Any insect foolhardy enough to attempt sampling its delight will invariably find itself trapped within this glutinous substance, preserved for future generations to study and possibly experiment on. Still, there are worse ways to go than being enveloped in one's favorite sweet treat.

Used in level 40 crafting recipes.

Name: Grade 2 Skybuilders' Flax
Description:
Included in a surprising number of recipes and concoctions despite its only notable property being it smells nice.

Used in level 40 crafting recipes.

Name: Grade 2 Skybuilders' Zinc Ore
Description:
Zinc is said to prevent a number of common ailments. However, it must be noted that attempting to ingest it in its current state may actually cause problems such as broken teeth and stomachache, usually in that order.

Used in level 40 crafting recipes.

Name: Grade 2 Skybuilders' Rock Salt
Description:
There are few dishes that cannot be improved with a sprinkling of salt. Strangely, this even includes a number of desserts, which flies in the face of all common logic.

Used in level 40 crafting recipes.

Name: Cobalt Alloy Ingot
Description: An ingot of smelted cobalt alloy.

Name: Purpure Bead
Description: A mysterious deep-green orb.

Name: Merbau Lumber
Description: Processed merbau lumber.

Name: Duskcourt Cloth
Description: Finely woven cloth with that distinctive duskbloom hue that says, wealthier than you.

Name: Megalania Leather
Description: A large piece of cured megalania skin.

Name: Grade 3 Strength Alkahest
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this experimental alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to strength, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Grade 3 Dexterity Alkahest
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this experimental alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to dexterity, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Grade 3 Vitality Alkahest
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this experimental alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to vitality, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Grade 3 Intelligence Alkahest
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this experimental alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to intelligence, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Grade 3 Mind Alkahest
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this experimental alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to mind, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Fireheart Cobalt
Description: Seasoned miners will recognize this as a type of sulfide, its composition lending its surface a permanent sheen that makes it look like a glowing ember in the light.

Name: Dwarven Chromite
Description: This ore has a high concentration of naturally occurring chromewhich is presumably why dwarves will under no circumstances divulge where veins of it might be found.

Name: Purpure Shell Chip
Description: A shiny piece of Purpure carapace.

Name: Workbench Resin
Description: Grenoldt's signature resinwhether the result of one of his more inspired moments or creative dry spells, no one can say.

Name: Merbau Log
Description: A rough-cut log of merbau timber, bearing the wood's distinctive scent.

Name: Tempest Adhesive
Description: Another of Grenoldt's creations. Probably best not to ask what's in it.

Name: Duskblooms
Description: A flowering plant with tiny purple blooms.

Name: Caprice Fleece
Description: Hair shorn from the pixies' lovinglyin some sense, at leastraised flock.

Name: Ashen Alumen
Description: Unusually dark-hued alumen.

Name: Megalania Skin
Description: The hide of the megalaniaa scalekin that has changed little since prehistoric eras.

Name: Imperial Fern
Description: Presumably named by one of history's many oppressed lower classes, this fern's appellation cannot but refer to the pretentious way in which it curls.

Name: Dried Hi-Ether
Description: Dry, flaky residue found at the bottom of a bottle of evaporated hi-ether.

Name: Authentic Valentione Lobster Platter
Description:
An authentically sumptuous plate of boiled and buttered lobster. Comes complete with a heart-shaped pizza. For reasons...of authenticity.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Determination Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  VIT Bonus: +5% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Authentic Valentione Cake Pairing
Description:
Rich cake powdered with dark chocolate and paired with a fine wine (now authentically aged for your enjoyment).

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Skill Speed Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  VIT Bonus: +5% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Authentic Stuffed Mammet
Description: All the authentic cuddliness of a mammet with all the authentic functionality of a plush doll.

Name: Bejeweled Egg
Description: This fragile ovoid is even more sumptuously decorated than the Archon eggs of yesteryear.

Name: Apprentice's Practice Materials
Description: Eager to reduce pointless, pointless waste, Eorzea's guildmasters organized an assemblage of sacks of low-quality materials such as this one that artisans-in-training may practice their skills (or lack thereof, in many cases). However, advances in crafting tuition have rendered this collection of largely useless components entirely obsolete.

Name: Rank VIII Artisan's Durable Practice Materials
Description: Assorted low-cost materials suited for trying one's hand at master recipes of the 8th level. Durability: 70.

Name: Rank VIII Artisan's Fragile Practice Materials
Description: Assorted low-cost materials suited for trying one's hand at master recipes of the 8th level. Durability: 35.

Name: Grade 2 Expert Skybuilders' Practice Materials
Description: Assorted low-cost materials suited for trying one's hand at expert recipes of the sort used in the Ishgardian restoration.

Name: Varis yae Galvus Card
Description:
A legendary () card used in the game Triple Triad.
Card No. 279

Name: Grade 2 Skybuilders' Cloudskipper
Description:
True to its name, this rare species spends its entire life in the firmament (the actual firmament, not the place in Ishgard) where it skips from cloud to cloud. Sadly, its ability to remain airborne relies on the presence of said clouds, without which it falls inelegantly to the ground below.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Grade 2 Skybuilders' Meditator
Description:
Like all meditators, this particular variety is capable of surviving out of water. The reason for its superior grading appears to be its ability to get back into water afterwards, which many of its brethren sadly lack.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Grade 2 Skybuilders' Coeurlfish
Description:
Coeurlfish fall into the category of species that anglers would rather not have thrashing at the end of their line, and many would rather lose their lure than face its vicious fangs. Only those with nerves of steel would attempt to reel in one of these aquatic abominations, though they are often made to regret it.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Grade 2 Skybuilders' Garpike
Description:
The skybuilders' primary reason for requesting this especially savage variety of garpike is to limit the havoc it wreaks in whatever body of water it inhabits. There is nothing less welcoming to a school of docile freshwater dwellers looking for a new home than a snapping maw of razor-sharp teeth heading in their general direction.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Grade 2 Skybuilders' Pirarucu
Description:
The pirarucu's habit of swallowing the lure whole means that most anglers wait until the beast is well and truly dead before they attempt to retrieve it. There is always the option of leaving it in the fish's bellybut that would be a nasty surprise for the poor soul who has to gut it.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Grade 2 Skybuilders' Brown Bolo
Description:
While this bizarre creature is known to entangle its prey in a manner similar to its namesake, the grade 2 variety can be used as an actual bolo when thrown. Just make sure the thing is dead first or you may find yourself being the one entangled.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Grade 2 Skybuilders' Bitterling
Description:
Most creatures tend not to enjoy being pulled to their death via a hook to the mouth, but this poor specimen looks especially miserable when caught.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Grade 2 Skybuilders' Caiman
Description:
Though the skybuilders are often willing to take in scalekin captured alive, they have specifically requested that any caiman presented be certifiably dead before being brought to the Firmament. Given its resemblance to a wingless dragon, the less sensible members of the populace may fear a second Dragonsong War is upon them.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Grade 2 Skybuilders' Cloud Cutter
Description:
Often caught accidentally by anglers in mid-cast, due to its habit of flying several fulms above the waterline.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Grade 2 Skybuilders' Vampiric Tapestry
Description:
Another species that largely fails to live up to its namesake, especially the vampiric part. As for tapestry, the only similarity appears to be the shared ability to stay stuck to a wall through the use of a series of well-placed pins.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Grade 2 Skybuilders' Tupuxuara
Description:
The word fishing usually implies that some sort of aquatic, or at the very least, amphibious creature is the intended prey, though the paraphernalia used by anglers is equally effective for snagging flying scalekin. Whether one would actually want to or not is a separate matter entirely.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Grade 2 Skybuilders' Blind Manta
Description:
As this species of manta uses echolocation to find its way around, it can be heard making a series of high-pitched squeals when hoisted out of the water. Many fishers end up feeling sorrow for the poor beast and returning it whence it came, although the more cynically minded suspect it of intentionally wielding a pity-based form of self-defense.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Grade 2 Artisanal Skybuilders' Rhomaleosaurus
Description:
An aquatic scalekin so enormous that one cannot help but wonder how a mere fishing rod could bear its weight.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Grade 2 Artisanal Skybuilders' Gobbie Mask
Description:
According to some sources, several attempts have been made by goblins to convert the carcasses of these cephalopods into masks. Unfortunately, the retch-inducing stench is too much for most to bear, especially when in such close proximity to the face.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Grade 2 Artisanal Skybuilders' Pterodactyl
Description:
One must take great care when attempting to catch one of these winged scalekin, as they may find themselves lifted from the ground. In such cases, it is normally best to let go of the rod, although the more absent-minded may find themselves clinging on for dear life for reasons that even they cannot comprehend.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Grade 2 Artisanal Skybuilders' Skyfish
Description:
Sought by collectors as a rare curio rather than for its use in Ishgardian cuisine. Often used to decorate trees during the Starlight Celebration, although the smell does get to be quite noticeable after a few days.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Grade 2 Artisanal Skybuilders' Cometfish
Description:
Named not for the speed with which it cuts through the water, but for the fact that, much like its namesake, having one fall on your head can be rather painful.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Grade 2 Artisanal Skybuilders' Anomalocaris
Description:
This airborne cephalopod often dives from above to savage unsuspecting anglers, as it is presumably a follower of the get your retaliation in first style of self-defense. However, a well-timed sidestep and a well-placed fishing net can soon turn the tables.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Grade 2 Artisanal Skybuilders' Rhamphorhynchus
Description:
It is strongly advised not to attempt to spear this particular species, as more often than not, it ends up doing most of the spearing.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Grade 2 Artisanal Skybuilders' Dragon's Soul
Description:
While most people are aware by now that this is not the soul of a dragon trapped in the rather pathetic and quite small body of a wavekin, it is nevertheless allowed to keep its incredibly impressive name.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Approved Grade 2 Skybuilders' Cloudskipper
Description:
True to its name, this rare species spends its entire life in the firmament (the actual firmament, not the place in Ishgard) where it skips from cloud to cloud. Sadly, its ability to remain airborne relies on the presence of said clouds, without which it falls inelegantly to the ground below.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Sintered Whetstone
Description: A whetstone created through compression and intense heat. Used for sharpening tools.

Name: Rabbit Suit
Description: Cannot equip gear to hands, legs, or feet.

Name: Dapper Rabbit Suit
Description: Cannot equip gear to hands, legs, or feet.

Name: Scion Sorceress's Headdress
Description: Fits: All

Name: Scion Sorceress's Robe
Description: Fits: All

Name: Scion Sorceress's Shadowtalons
Description: Fits: All

Name: Scion Sorceress's High Boots
Description: Fits: All

Name: Sungold Talos
Description:
Guaranteed to make you the envy of collectors and younglings alike.

Use item to acquire the sungold Talos minion.

Name: Malone
Description:
If it weren't following you around, it would be tearing hapless adventurers apart on the Diadem.

Use item to acquire the Malone minion.

Name: Little Leafman
Description:
Definitely a leafman. The pixie said so.

Use item to acquire the little leafman minion.

Name: The Behelmeted Serpent of Ronka
Description:
Tremble, child of man, for a creature of purest divinity wiggleth before thee in all of its behelmeted glory.

Use item to acquire the Behelmeted Serpent of Ronka minion.

Name: The Behatted Serpent of Ronka
Description:
Tremble, child of man, for a creature of purest divinity wiggleth before thee in all of its behatted glory.

Use item to acquire the Behatted Serpent of Ronka minion.

Name: Silver Dasher
Description:
Never was there a bird so adorable.

Use item to acquire the silver dasher minion.

Name: Paissa Patissier
Description:
Currently in training as a culinarian, and looks the part.

Use item to acquire the paissa patissier minion.

Name: Paissa Threadpuller
Description:
Currently in training as a weaver, and looks the part.

Use item to acquire the paissa threadpuller minion.

Name: Ancient One
Description:
Small and appearing to be fractured, but whole.

Use item to acquire the ancient one minion.

Name: The Major-General
Description:
It's a shark. With legs.

Use item to acquire the Major-General minion.

Name: Wind-up Dulia-Chai
Description:
Complete with asphyxiated Chai-Nuzz.

Use item to acquire the Dulia-Chai minion.

Name: Amaro Hatchling
Description:
It may make a fine steed if you live long enough to see it reach maturity.

Use item to acquire the amaro hatchling minion.

Name: Laladile
Description:
Because small is beautiful.

Use item to acquire the Laladile minion.

Name: Unlucky Rabbit
Description:
Has known the bitterest lows and the sweetest highs.

Use item to acquire the unlucky rabbit minion.

Name: Construct 14 Identification Key
Description: A thin, rectangular piece of what appears to be cermet. Placing it near your Construct 14 will magically bring the machine to life.

Name: Ronkan Flute
Description: This whistle emits a sublime tone that summons forth the Great Vessel of Ronka, pre-filled with divinity for your worshipping convenience.

Name: Pteranodon Horn
Description: This horn emits a primitive tone that brings a prehistoric pteranodon soaring to your side.

Name: Ruby Gwiber Trumpet
Description: This horn-carved instrument emits an ethereal tone that beckons an imposing ruby gwiber from its refuge.

Name: Hybodus Horn
Description: This horn emits a deep and menacing tone that summons forth your fearsome hybodus.

Name: Ramuh Crystal
Description: Thrumming with lightning energy, this crystal gives rise to an entity which assumes the form of the Lord of Levin in all of his horse-legged, hulking glory.

Name: Rubellite Carbuncle Whistle
Description: A jeweled whistle that emits a heart-melting tone said to summon a Rubellite Carbuncle.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Defter Digits
Description: An illustrated manual detailing the myriad ways one may use one's fingers to effectively communicate. Described by critics as a finger-snapping good read. Use to learn the /snap emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Well Bread
Description: An illustrated manual providing instruction in the eating of bread, a deceptively nuanced act that philosophers have likened to a good marriage. Use to learn the /bread emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Intelligent Impressions
Description: An illustrated manual of how and when to employ books in a social setting so as to appear well-read to those around you. Use to learn the /read emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Emphatic Elucidation
Description: An illustrated manual of how to speak powerfully and persuasively, drawing upon techniques employed by the finest orators in history. Use to learn the /insist emote.

Name: Modern Aesthetics - Controlled Chaos
Description:
The realm's premier publication on beauty and fashion, this limited edition of Modern Aesthetics covers, in detail, trimming and coiffing techniques for an attractively asymmetrical look that's a cut above the ordinary.

Use to unlock a new hairstyle at the aesthetician.

Name: Season One Writ of Beatification
Description:
Documentation of noteworthy accomplishments on behalf of the Ishgardian Restoration.

Use to gain the Minor Miracle achievement for Season One.

Name: Season One Writ of Canonization
Description:
Documentation of noteworthy accomplishments on behalf of the Ishgardian Restoration.

Use to gain the Divine Ascension achievement for Season One.

Name: Ruby Red Dye
Description: A labor-saving red dye, used for coloring anything from cloth to metal.

Name: Cherry Pink Dye
Description: A labor-saving pink dye, used for coloring anything from cloth to metal.

Name: Canary Yellow Dye
Description: A labor-saving yellow dye, used for coloring anything from cloth to metal.

Name: Vanilla Yellow Dye
Description: A labor-saving yellow dye, used for coloring anything from cloth to metal.

Name: Dragoon Blue Dye
Description: A labor-saving blue dye, used for coloring anything from cloth to metal.

Name: Turquoise Blue Dye
Description: A labor-saving blue dye, used for coloring anything from cloth to metal.

Name: Gunmetal Black Dye
Description: A labor-saving black dye, used for coloring anything from cloth to metal.

Name: Pearl White Dye
Description: A labor-saving white dye, used for coloring anything from cloth to metal.

Name: Metallic Brass Dye
Description: A labor-saving yellow dye, used for coloring anything from cloth to metal.

Name: Magicked Prism (Ishgard)
Description: This peculiar contraption creates illusions by weaving together myriad shades of light. Used in Ishgard for celebratory purposes.

Name: Magicked Prism (House Dzemael)
Description: This peculiar contraption creates illusions by weaving together myriad shades of light. Used by House Dzemael for celebratory purposes.

Name: Magicked Prism (House Haillenarte)
Description: This peculiar contraption creates illusions by weaving together myriad shades of light. Used by House Haillenarte for celebratory purposes.

Name: Magicked Prism (House Durendaire)
Description: This peculiar contraption creates illusions by weaving together myriad shades of light. Used by House Durendaire for celebratory purposes.

Name: Magicked Prism (House Fortemps)
Description: This peculiar contraption creates illusions by weaving together myriad shades of light. Used by House Fortemps for celebratory purposes.

Name: Magicked Prism (Temple Knights)
Description: This peculiar contraption creates illusions by weaving together myriad shades of light. Used by the Temple Knights for celebratory purposes.

Name: Cloth-softening Powder
Description: Gives even brand-new clothes that worn-in feeling.

Name: Signature Skyball
Description: The ingredients of this pungent, pasty ball are a closely guarded Skysteel Manufactory secret. Processed bait specially designed for snaring certain species.

Name: Idealized Head Gear Coffer (IL 480)
Description:
A banded chest containing a piece of idealized attire.

Required level: 80. IL: 480. Head gear type determined by current job or class at time of opening. Cannot be opened in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.

Name: Idealized Chest Gear Coffer (IL 480)
Description:
A banded chest containing a piece of idealized attire.

Required level: 80. IL: 480. Chest gear type determined by current job or class at time of opening. Cannot be opened in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.

Name: Idealized Hand Gear Coffer (IL 480)
Description:
A banded chest containing a piece of idealized attire.

Required level: 80. IL: 480. Hand gear type determined by current job or class at time of opening. Cannot be opened in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.

Name: Idealized Leg Gear Coffer (IL 480)
Description:

Required level: 80. IL: 480. Leg gear type determined by current job or class at time of opening. Cannot be opened in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.

Name: High Legatus Idol
Description: An almost worshipful graven rendering of Varis yae Galvus.

Name: Aged Oak Log
Description: A rough-cut log from an old oak tree. Yellow ribbon sold separately.

Description: Music roll for Blue Fields. Use to add to your orchestrion list.

Name: Faded Copy of Ultima (The Primals)
Description: Timeworn pages of sheet music containing the full score for Ultima (The Primals).

Name: Parasol
Description: The perfect accessory to protect you from the summer sun, spring showers, and birds seeking to relieve themselves. Use to acquire a parasol.

Name: Sky Blue Parasol
Description: The perfect accessory to protect you from the summer sun, spring showers, and birds seeking to relieve themselves. Use to acquire a sky blue parasol.

Name: Coffer o' Kupos
Description:
This nonsensically named coffer contains a full set of moogle-approved kupo attire.

Required level: 1. IL: 1.

Name: Irregular Tomestone of Law
Description:
One of only a few in existence, this Allagan tomestone contains arguments of dubious legal grounds and tales of their at times horrific, at times hilarious results when used during judicial proceedings.

Can be exchanged with itinerant moogles for certain items.

Name: Thavnairian Scalepowder
Description: A fine powder blended in the Near Eastern island nation of Radz-at-Han designed to promote aetherial conductivity.

Name: Diadem Balloon Bug
Description:
Try not to think of all of the sky-spiders that these sky-bugs will attract. Live bait for skyfishing.

Only for use in the Diadem.

Name: Diadem Red Balloon
Description:
You'd best not set ninety-nine of these free in the skies over Ishgard, lest the knights be very cross indeed. Live bait for skyfishing.

Only for use in the Diadem.

Name: Diadem Crane Fly
Description:
The veined wings and spindly legs of the crane fly will attract a plethora of skyborne predators in no time. Presumably some part of this situation is desirable to you. Live bait for skyfishing.

Only for use in the Diadem.

Name: Diadem Hoverworm
Description:
What is there to say about the Diadem hoverworm? Nothing, so long as they might be listening. Live bait for skyfishing.

Only for use in the Diadem.

Name: Carpenter's Gobbiegoo
Description: A Skysteel tool coating crafted by means that are intriguingbut not quite so intriguing that you would risk finding out what they are. Tastes of sawdust...not that you would know.

Name: Highly Viscous Carpenter's Gobbiegoo
Description: Though you naturally understand how paper and the like is made, you cannot fathom how the materials you provided might have become this Skysteel tool coating.

Name: Blacksmith's Gobbiegoo
Description: A Skysteel tool coating crafted by means that are intriguingbut not quite so intriguing that you would risk finding out what they are. Cold to the touch.

Name: Highly Viscous Blacksmith's Gobbiegoo
Description: This Skysteel tool coating is of a peculiar shiny black, and you cannot shake the feeling that it is somehow gooier than ever before.

Name: Armorer's Gobbiegoo
Description: A Skysteel tool coating crafted by means that are intriguingbut not quite so intriguing that you would risk finding out what they are. Brittle when spread overthin.

Name: Highly Viscous Armorer's Gobbiegoo
Description: A Skysteel tool coating. Now with extra...goo.

Name: Goldsmith's Gobbiegoo
Description: A Skysteel tool coating crafted by means that are intriguingbut not quite so intriguing that you would risk finding out what they are. Enticingly shiny.

Name: Highly Viscous Goldsmith's Gobbiegoo
Description: This thick Skysteel tool coating emits fumes that you recall fondly from the gilding process. You also recall said fumes are highly toxic.

Name: Leatherworker's Gobbiegoo
Description: A Skysteel tool coating crafted by means that are intriguingbut not quite so intriguing that you would risk finding out what they are. Known for its delightful aromathough perhaps leatherworkers are not best positioned to judge.

Name: Highly Viscous Leatherworker's Gobbiegoo
Description: Even practiced leatherworkers are disgusted by the texture of this Skysteel tool coatingwhich is really saying something.

Name: Weaver's Gobbiegoo
Description: A Skysteel tool coating crafted by means that are intriguingbut not quite so intriguing that you would risk finding out what they are. Not a suitable substitute for medicinal salves, no matter how much your fingers ache.

Name: Highly Viscous Weaver's Gobbiegoo
Description: Generally viscous is not high on the list of attributes one associates with delicate needlework, but perhaps the frankly alarming amount of goo that Skysteel engineers will soon apply to your needle will change that.

Name: Alchemist's Gobbiegoo
Description: A Skysteel tool coating crafted by deeply intriguing means.

Name: Highly Viscous Alchemist's Gobbiegoo
Description: Does the adjective placement here imply that the alchemist in question is particularly viscous? is a thought that could only come from the addled mind of one steeped in the alchemical artswhich is precisely the reason that no one trusts those people.

Name: Culinarian's Gobbiegoo
Description: A Skysteel tool coating crafted by means that are intriguingbut not quite so intriguing that you would risk finding out what they are. Incredibly inedible.

Name: Highly Viscous Culinarian's Gobbiegoo
Description: But I cook food in that! you may plead as the Skysteel engineers make to apply this coating to your frypan, but they will not heed your cries.

Name: Botanist's Gobbiegoo
Description: A Skysteel tool coating crafted by means that are intriguingbut not quite so intriguing that you would risk finding out what they are. Minty fresh.

Name: Highly Viscous Botanist's Gobbiegoo
Description: This Skysteel tool coating is deeply weird, but frankly, nature has produced weirder.

Name: Miner's Gobbiegoo
Description: A Skysteel tool coating crafted by means that are intriguingbut not quite so intriguing that you would risk finding out what they are. Tastes of soil, which is a perfectly reasonable thing to know.

Name: Highly Viscous Miner's Gobbiegoo
Description: This Skysteel tool coating is darker than the depths of a mineshaft, and more viscous than...regular goo.

Name: Fisher's Gobbiegoo
Description: A Skysteel tool coating crafted by means that are intriguingbut not quite so intriguing that you would risk finding out what they are. Smells of fish.

Name: Highly Viscous Fisher's Gobbiegoo
Description: Try not to think about the process involved in rendering the materials you provided into this gloopy, pinkish Skysteel tool coating.

Name: Vesper Bay Aetheryte Ticket
Description: A voucher redeemable by Scions of the Seventh Dawn for instant teleportation to Vesper Bay.

Name: Allagan Melon Seeds
Description: Allagan melon seeds suitable for garden cultivation.

Name: Cosmos Seeds
Description:
These seeds will grow into bright and cheery cosmos bloomsunless one is a terrible gardener, in which case they will grow into a sense of self-loathing.

For use in planters.

Name: Red Cosmos
Description:
A bunch of red cosmos, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Blue Cosmos
Description:
A bunch of blue cosmos, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.
