Name: Small Smithy Walls
Description:
A set of four walls designed for those who wish to give their estate hall a smithy-inspired look.

Can only be used with cottages on small plots of land.

Name: Medium Smithy Walls
Description:
A set of four walls designed for those who wish to give their estate hall a smithy-inspired look.

Can only be used with houses on medium plots of land.

Name: Large Smithy Walls
Description:
A set of four walls designed for those who wish to give their estate hall a smithy-inspired look.

Can only be used with mansions on large plots of land.

Name: Factory Interior Wall
Description: An industrial wall resembling those seen in the Copied Factory.

Name: Factory Flooring
Description: Rusted metal factory flooring.

Name: Factory Chandelier
Description: A rusted metal lighting fixture unlike any to which you are accustomed.

Name: Trophy of Light
Description:
A wall-mounted sword and shield to mark your victory in a battle of like wills.

One per estate only.

Name: Sapphire Weapon Bust
Description:
The chest of this Garlond Ironworks scale replica of a select portion of the Sapphire Weapon glows ominously. Accept no substitutes.

One per estate only.

Name: Verdant Shelf Partition
Description: A charming open partition with ample shelf space in the middle and overflowing planters above.

Name: Ironfrog Keeper
Description: This diminutive automaton has ample space for storing the energy-rich crystals of dismembered knockers and other useful objects.

Name: Wooden Staircase Bookshelf
Description: Versatile book storage that doubles as tiered shelving for other knickknacks.

Name: Gemseeker's Pack
Description: This bag is bursting with unpolished gems and crystalsand as such, may attract spriggans. Homeowners are advised to lock their doors.

Name: Bluebird Mobile
Description: If one bluebird brings happiness, surely those who adorn their homes with this revolving display have naught to fearaside from taking a faux bluebird to the eye should they move carelessly.

Name: Nomad's Tent
Description: A little piece of the Azim Steppe, created by trade-minded Xaela using traditional methods and materials.

Name: Stage Curtain
Description: This sumptuous curtain impresses upon audiences that what they are about to witness is no two-gil production.

Name: Floor Sofa
Description: A spacious seating option for those who prefer to remain at floor level.

Name: Tako-yaki Boat
Description:
A steaming and sauce-slathered serving of enough doughy fried octopus to share.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Determination Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  VIT Bonus: +5% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Barrel Table
Description: This reused cask screams adventure! Or perhaps alcohol, depending on what sort of tavern patron you are.

Name: Indoor Pond
Description: Bring the outdoors indoors with this perfect imitation of nature. Toads not included...or are they?

Name: Giant Beaver Burger Set
Description:
No actual beavers were harmed in the making of this massive burger.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Critical Hit Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  VIT Bonus: +5% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Red Brick Kitchen
Description: This rustic outdoor cooking facility is more than capable of keeping any amount of garden party guests well fed.

Name: Cracked Arch Window
Description: Too competent to smash your own windows? This is the product for you!

Name: Industrial Wall Pipes
Description: These decorative pipes were designed by the employees of Garlond Ironworks to make their abodes feel more like home.

Name: Season Sixteen Lone Wolf Trophy
Description: A trophy awarded to those who left their mark in Season Sixteen of the Feast.

Name: Factory Grate
Description: A rusted piece of grating. Watch your toes.

Name: Factory Staircase
Description: These metallic stairs make a satisfying clunking noise when stepped on. You know the one.

Name: Factory Railing
Description: An industrial safety rail. Given the visible wear and tear, one of those adjectives may have become less applicable over time.

Name: Factory Beam
Description: A giant steel beam. Elegant.

Name: Factory Automatic Door
Description: The internal mechanisms that allow this door to open and close on its own remain something of a mystery. Luckily, this one was ripped from its surroundings wholesale, and operates regardless.

Name: Factory Partition
Description: A rusted chain-link barrier.

Name: Factory Wall Lamp
Description: A grimy lamp extracted from the machine graveyard.

Name: Factory Bench
Description: An iron bench that remains sturdy despite having seen better days.

Name: Wooden Footbridge
Description: For those who find walking on the ground simply too pedestrian.

Name: Gulg Planter
Description: An alpine shrub from the heights of Kholusia.

Name: Marble Alcove Bed
Description: This indulgent bed frame constitutes an entire wall, and will banish any illusions guests might have held regarding your humility.

Name: Watts's Sketches
Description: Drawn many, many moons ago by the famed Watts, these illustrations depict a concept for a form of wheeled transportation. Unfortunately, details on the inner workings have been largely omitted, but even in this undeveloped state, the design showed promise.

Name: Dwarven Floor Lamp
Description: A low-lying lamp designed for use in narrow, enclosed spacesbut usable anywhere mineshaft ambience is desired.

Name: Mandragora Table Chronometer
Description: A massive mandragora-themed timepiece, for those who are into that.

Name: Paissa Rug
Description: What have they seen? What do they know?

Name: Huggable Gaelicat
Description: This stuffed imitation of the weatherproof gaelicat looks as if it isrightlyready to be adored.

Name: Ishgardian Display Stand
Description: A decorative pedestal in the Coerthan style.

Name: Fortemps Sofa
Description: An ostentatious, though elegant, round seat of the sort favored by House Fortemps.

Name: Stuffed Estinien
Description: Though cuddlier than the real thing, still decidedly prickly. Please enjoy responsibly.

Name: Helldiver SD
Description: An amazingly lifelike model constructed using specially engineered cloth and cotton bolls by Ironworks employees with a particular...enthusiasm for the helldiver variety of machina. Designation: snuggly.

Name: Dainsleif SD
Description: An amazingly lifelike model constructed using specially engineered cloth and cotton bolls by Ironworks employees with a particular...enthusiasm for the Dinsleif machina. Designation: snuggly.

Name: Oriental Wooden Deck
Description: A slatted deck in the Far Eastern fashion, perfect for quiet contemplation or loud consumption of dango.

Name: Slanted Wall
Description: This freestanding wall adds fashionable and potentially confounding angles to any interior.

Name: Slanted Skylight
Description: A freestanding sloped wall with an inbuilt window to let the sunand only the sun, somehowin.

Name: The Moogle's Paw Machine
Description: Experience the extreme sensory overload of the Gold Saucer in your own home with this authentic the Moogle's Paw machine.

Name: Out on a Limb Machine
Description: Experience the heart-exploding excitement of the Gold Saucer in your own home with this authentic Out on a Limb machine.

Name: The Finer Miner Machine
Description: Experience the heart-exploding excitement of the Gold Saucer in your own home with this authentic the Finer Miner machine.

Name: Sliced Watermelon
Description:
This juicy, fresh-cut watermelon makes the perfect summer treat.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Tenacity Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  VIT Bonus: +5% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Water Bomb Stand
Description: Bring home this hallmark of the Moonfire Faire and pelt passersby with aquatic surprises from the comfort of your very own front garden!

Name: Authentic Moonfire Faire MMXVIII Advertisement
Description: A hand-painted notice advertising the Eorzean Nimble Warrior course. So authentic, you can practically smell the fireworks, sunburned flesh, and slightly suspect festival snacks.

Name: Authentic Portable Pool
Description: A peculiar rubber enclosure that can be filled with water for purposes of mild entertainment. Maintains an authentic new rubber smell many moons after the initial purchase.

Name: Authentic Wind Chime Stand
Description: Nothing says summer like the dissonant tinkling of half a dozen wind chimes at once. Those in doubt of its authenticity will be pleased to discover that the chimes do in fact ring in response to wafts of air, and are not mechanically controlled, unlike more complex but far less charming devices such as orchestrions.

Name: The Sinsteeped
Description:
A king among sinspitters, and lord of the waters of the Quadrivium.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Sweetheart
Description:
A queen among albino caimans, and lady of the waters of the Rift of Sighs.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Giant Taimen
Description:
A king among hucho taimen, and lord of the waters of upper Watts River.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 3 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Leannisg
Description:
A king among wimple carp, and lord of the waters of Handmirror Lake.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Gold Hammer
Description:
A king among golden lobsters, and lord of the waters of Saint Fathric's Temple.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Recordkiller
Description:
A queen among silver kittens, and lady of the waters of south Mjrl's Regret.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: The Mother of All Pancakes
Description:
A queen among pancake octopodes, and lady of the waters of east Caliban Gap.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Opal Shrimp
Description:
A king among rainbow shrimp, and lord of the waters of the Norvrandt Slope.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Aesthete's Tool Belt
Description: Before becoming obsolete due to advancements in tailoring, belts such as this were used for holding up trousers and the like.

Name: Aesthete's Belt of Gathering
Description: Before becoming obsolete due to advancements in tailoring, belts such as this were used for holding up trousers and the like.

Name: Crab Cakes
Description:
To preserve the toothsome texture of blue crab, chunks of flesh are gently folded into flour and molded into cakes, which are panfried to golden perfection.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Chili Crab
Description:
A whole blue crab braised in its shell in a piquant sauce, which takes on a rich shellfish flavor in the course of cooking.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Brashgold Plate
Description: A sheet of highly durable brashgold plate.

Name: Defthand's Dissolvent
Description: When applied to crafting or gathering gear, this alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to dexterity, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Tender Dill
Description: A small variety of dill characterized by its sweet fragrance. Finds use in both medicinal and culinary applications.

Name: Brashgold Ore
Description: A decent-sized piece of rock rich in a highly durable, naturally occurring alloy.

Name: Blue Crab
Description:
A small crab that would be otherwise unremarkable if not for its vibrant blue shell.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Hoplite
Description:
While the shape of this wavekin's shell may resemble Halone's fabled shield, it is not recommended for use in battle.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Hook Fish
Description:
Woe betide any who accidentally swallow one of this fish's sharp bones.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Cloudweed
Description:
A flavorful weed that has come to have more utility in the kitchen than in the ocean.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Fatty Herring
Description:
In a blind taste test, three out of four people cannot tell the difference between fatty herring steak and antelope steak.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Inkshell
Description:
Perfect for producing ink and hoodwinking those who are hard of hearing.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Printing Essentials

Name: Gathering Tool Paraphernalia
Description: An assortment of materials that, when assembled properly, can make a gathering tool that even dragons can use.

Name: Weaving Paraphernalia

Name: Crafting Tool Paraphernalia

Name: Handpicked Ingredients

Name: Printing Paraphernalia

Name: Dragon's Gathering Tool Component Materials

Name: Printing Component Materials

Name: Levinstrike Aethersand
Description: This coarse-grained, highly concentrated aetherially reduced mineral matter carries the distinctive scent of ozone.

Name: Thunder Rock
Description: An uncut stone imbued with so much aetheric lightning energy as to echo with tiny claps of thunder.

Name: Levin Mint
Description: The pink leaves of this peculiar mint thrum gently with lightning energy.

Name: Fuchsia Bloom
Description:
Vibrantly hued and daintily shaped, this freshwater fish is right at home in the waters of Il Mheg.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Stuffed Paissa Patissier
Description: There's a lot to unpack here.

Name: Stuffed Behelmeted Serpent
Description: A being beyond mortal ken would never deign to snuggle, of course, but this facsimile doesn't mind.

Description: A shimmering carving honoring a hero that once was.

Description: A small hand-carved whistle that emits a unique, high-pitched tone discernible only by a chocobo trained from birth to recognize and respond to the sound, carriage and all.

Name: Rolling Tankard Ignition Key
Description: Inserting this small piece of painted iron will ignite the advanced nine-cylinder radial ethanol engine of your Rolling Tankard. Please refrain from imbibing while driving.

Name: Gabriel  Identification Key
Description: A thin, rectangular piece of what appears to be cermet. Placing it near your Gabriel  will magically bring the machine to life.

Name: Megalotragus Horn
Description: This imposing horn emits a primordial tone that summons forth your megalotragus, a herbivore so intimidating it puts carnivores to shame.

Name: Gwiber of Light Trumpet
Description: This horn-carved instrument emits an ethereal tone that beckons a refulgent gwiber of light from its hiding place.

Name: Jibanyan Couch Medal
Description: This medal can be used to summon forth the Jibanyan couch, a mysterious piece of furniture designed in the likeness of a Yo-kai named Jibanyan.

Name: Incitatus Whistle
Description: This whistle emits a shrill tone that is said to summon Incitatus, the steed of legend.

Name: Ehll Tou Whistle
Description: When blown, this ornate whistle emits a distinct tone that summons to your side Ehll Tou, the young dragon with a passion for crafting.

Name: Lalinator 5.H0
Description:
It doesn't feel pity, or remorse, or fear. And it absolutely will not stop, ever, until you have been lali-ho'd.

Use item to acquire the Lalinator 5.H0 minion.

Name: Wind-up Mystel
Description:
Modeled upon no one in particular. No, really.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Mystel minion.

Name: Wind-up Ardbert
Description:
What he lacks in size, he makes up for in heart...and his disproportionately large axe.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Ardbert minion.

Name: Magitek Helldiver F1
Description:
Minimal firepower, maximum attitude.

Use item to acquire the magitek helldiver F1 minion.

Name: Weatherproof Gaelicat
Description:
Makes you feel toasty warm simply to behold it.

Use item to acquire the weatherproof gaelicat minion.

Name: Ephemeral Necromancer
Description:
If it could, it would summon forth an army of equally adorable undead.

Use item to acquire the ephemeral necromancer minion.

Name: Allagan Melon
Description:
Capable of movement and tremendously juicy.

Use item to acquire the Allagan melon minion.

Name: Sand Fox
Description:
Will perform tricks for a lick of birch syrup.

Use item to acquire the sand fox minion.

Name: Petit Pteranodon
Description:
It might be cute now, but wait till it grows and becomes a scourge of the skies.

Use item to acquire the petit pteranodon minion.

Name: Dainsleif F1
Description:
Does not form the head. Or any other part of the body, for that matter.

Use item to acquire the Dinsleif F1 minion.

Name: Lord Enma
Description:
The last in a line of kings who guided the fate of the Yo-kai World.

Use item to acquire the Lord Enma minion.

Name: Lord Ananta
Description:
The new ruler of the Yo-kai World.

Use item to acquire the Lord Ananta minion.

Name: Zazel
Description:
Counselor to generations of Enmas, the Yo-kai kings.

Use item to acquire the Zazel minion.

Name: Damona
Description:
The daughter of an Oni pirate king.

Use item to acquire the Damona minion.

Name: 2B Automaton
Description:
For when you need the company of a compact version of an advanced combat android dressed in a distinctive subculture style. 

Use item to acquire the 2B automaton minion.

Name: 2P Automaton
Description:
For when you need the company of a compact version of an advanced combat android dressed in a distinctive subculture style. 

Use item to acquire the 2P automaton minion.

Name: The Sultana's Seven
Description: A faithful recreation of the stained glass artwork that adorned the main stage at Ul'dah's Rising festival. The historic moment when Nanamo Ul Namo and her seven most trusted followers confronted a baying crowd and restored peace to the city is captured in all its glory. For aesthetic reasons, however, the artist has wisely chosen not to include the angry mob.
