Name: Rarefied Cedar Longbow
Description:
A fine hunter's bow to display alongside that buffalo head above the fireplace. Which was also purchased.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Cedar Fishing Rod
Description:
A shame this beautiful rod will likely never feel a drop of water, fresh or otherwise.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Holy Cedar Spinning Wheel
Description:
This cedar spinning wheel will look stunning collecting dust in the sewing room.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Dark Chestnut Rod
Description:
A dark, chestnut rod that whispers dark, chestnut lies about its owner's nonexistent magical talents.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Hallowed Chestnut Ring
Description:
A lovingly carved ring to sit in a lovingly curated collection.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Birch Signum
Description:
No, dear, it's not a cane, it's a signum.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Beech Composite Bow
Description:
For when those fancy bows simply aren't fancy enough.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Larch Necklace
Description:
A necklace of wood never looked this good.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Pine Cane
Description:
Tool of conjury, or eye-catching centerpiece? You decide.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Persimmon Bracelets
Description:
The percussive pleasure of pronouncing persimmon when replying to the predictable question.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Zelkova Spinning Wheel
Description:
If you don't have one in zelkova, do you really have a spinning wheel collection?

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied White Oak Partisan
Description:
A stately weapon, regal in appearance and lethal in practice. To be locked in a showcase.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Applewood Staff
Description:
She had that applewood staff and the robes with the fur (with the fur!). The whole collector's club will be looking at her.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied White Ash Earrings
Description:
The pinnacle of wooden ear accessories for the discerning collector.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Sandteak Fauchard
Description:
Forget an eyeyou could take someone's whole face off with that thing. Put it back on the wall.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Mythrite Katzbalger
Description:
A wonderful martial showpiece...if you can lift the bloody thing onto the table.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Mythrite Pugiones
Description:
Just don't let the servants catch you slinking around in the dark, pretending to be a shadow warrior.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Mythrite Halfheart Saw
Description:
The more expensive the mythrite, the more exquisite the cut. That's how it works...right?

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Titanium Creasing Knife
Description:
What do you mean, 'what do I need it for?' Why, for creasing things, of course!

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Titanium Mortar
Description:
The hardest part about owning this collector's dream is resisting the urge to see what things can be ground into a fine, smooth paste.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Adamantite Bill
Description:
Large letter-opening problems require large letter-opener solutions.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied High Steel Guillotine
Description:
No smudgy fingerprints on the blade, or heads will roll.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied High Steel Claw Hammer
Description:
To complement that set of rarefied high steel nails.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Doman Iron Uchigatana
Description:
Don't try checking the blade to see if it's sharp. It's sharp.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Doman Steel Patas
Description:
A fine addition to any collection of eye-poking weaponry forged from Far Eastern materials.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Molybdenum Pliers
Description:
They're made of molydem...moldybe...a special kind of metal!

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Deepgold Anelace
Description:
An anelace forged from the deepest gold, purchased by those with the deepest pockets.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Deepgold Culinary Knife
Description:
Food tastes all the richer when prepared with this luxury utensil.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Bluespirit Gunblade
Description:
Placed in front of the window, the blade catches the morning sunlight just so.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Titanbronze Pickaxe
Description:
An epic tool destined for an attic stool.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Mythrite Sallet
Description:
Yes, I have the sallet. I'll be after the hauberk, next.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Mythrite Hauberk
Description:
Now I have the hauberk, I suppose I must have the matching sallet.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Mythrite Bladed Lantern Shield
Description:
A finely wrought shield for a less-civilized age.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Titanium Frypan
Description:
To be hung from a kitchen hook and admired as you pass through on your way to the Bismarck.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Titanium Vambraces
Description:
He was wearing them to prune the rose bushes. Unbelievable.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Adamantite Scutum
Description:
Such a coveted item will surely deflect the slings and arrows of your collection's critics...be they real or metaphorical.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied High Steel Thermal Alembic
Description:
Wait until your friends at the potion-making society see this shiny new toy. Envy guaranteed.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied High Steel Plate Belt
Description:
Beautiful when displayed alone, but be warnedthis is a gateway piece to collecting entire suits.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Doman Iron Greaves
Description:
I wasn't going to wear them <clunk> but the sound is so <clunk> satisfying!

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Doman Steel Tabard
Description:
An impressive piecethough some collectors are disappointed to discover the tabard itself isn't actually made of Doman steel.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Molybdenum Headgear
Description:
Never ask dedicated headgear enthusiasts how the thin strips of molybdenum protect the face...because they will tell you.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Deepgold Cuirass
Description:
This classic (and expensive) edition of the deepgold cuirass might grace a manor entry hall or private study. Battle-scarring optional.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Deepgold Wings
Description:
Such elegant design and divine workmanship could only be the work of the godsor one highly determined and talented artisan.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Bluespirit Gauntlets
Description:
Some armor aficionados claim that, with these splendid full-length gauntlets equipped, no other bodily protection is necessary.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Titanbronze Tower Shield
Description:
No, no, titanbronze. Far sturdier. A true masterpiece of a shield.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Mythrite Goggles
Description:
When one's eyesight is essential to one's livelihood, one cannot stint on the proper protections.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Mythrite Bangle
Description:
It may appear exactly the same as other mythrite bangles, but this one is special.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Mythrite Needle
Description:
A needle sufficiently fine to embroider the details of every leaf of vegetation on a goobbue's head.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Hardsilver Monocle
Description:
They said it provides an immediate +10 to sophistication! ...Nay, I've no idea what that means either.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Hardsilver Pole
Description:
All those moving parts help cycle the aether more efficiently. It's science! ...Magick science.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Aurum Regis Earrings
Description:
A serious collector of aurum regis wares would never use these tiny sword-shaped accessories to stage tiny mock duels.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Koppranickel Planisphere
Description:
Though its true majesty can only be appreciated when put in motion by an astrologian, this eccentric planisphere is nevertheless a fascinating talking point.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Koppranickel Necklace
Description:
When one has experience collecting pointy necklaces, one quickly learns not to nod too vigorously.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Durium Chaplets
Description:
The trick to displaying a stunning pair of chaplets is posing the fingers in a suitably mystical gesture. No, not that one.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Durium Rod
Description:
Ornate. Gothic. Black. Purple. Gold. For when you really need a rod that screams black mage.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Palladium Needle
Description:
Obsessed with tools made of materials that begin with the letter P? Look no further.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Stonegold Degen
Description:
The epitome of style and elegance, with a hilt long enough for a six-fingered man.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Stonegold Orrery
Description:
A limited edition stonegold orrery? I must have one! ...What does it do?

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Manasilver Ear Cuffs
Description:
How these ear cuffs improve craftsmanship is anyone's guess...but they sure are pretty.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Titanbronze Headgear
Description:
Another set of headgear that should provide minimal protection, but it is made of titanbronze, so...

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Archaeoskin Belt
Description:
Sturdy, fashionable, and it has a pouch to hold your stuff!

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Archaeoskin Cloche
Description:
While an archaeornis is not what most would consider a pretty creature, this hat made from its leather is a feather in anyone's cap.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Wyvernskin Mask
Description:
When you need to enhance your mystical talents whilst scaring the neighborhood children, this terrifyingly practical mask has you covered.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Dhalmelskin Coat
Description:
Crafted from real dhalmel leather, this coat is prized for its pre-weathered appearance.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Dragonskin Ring
Description:
Nothing quite compares to the feeling of wearing a ring which necessitated the slaying of an entire dragon.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Serpentskin Hat
Description:
Crafted in the classic style, this shiny specimen of haberdashery will be the talk of the local coven.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Gaganaskin Shoes
Description:
Considering the cost of acquiring such footwear, few collectors would dare to walk a malm in these shoes.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Gyuki Leather Jacket
Description:
Many gyuki died to bring you this jacket. Actually, it was probably just onethose things are huge.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Tigerskin Tricorne
Description:
I'm sure many rare and expensive materials went into the making of this hat, but now that I have it, I'm not so sure I'll wear it...

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Marid Leather Corset
Description:
Ironic that an item so sleek and shapely is crafted from a beast so large and ponderous.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Gazelleskin Armguards
Description:
Yes, these will pair beautifully with my twinsilk robe and turban!

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Smilodonskin Trousers
Description:
Tigerskin is nice, but have you ever draped your loins in smilodon?

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Gliderskin Thighboots
Description:
They'll glide right on, but you'll need to peel them off.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Atrociraptorskin Cap
Description:
When foraging in the wild, it helps to have the crafted remains of a vicious predator sat on your head as a constant reminder to maintain vigilance.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Zonureskin Fingerless Gloves
Description:
They say steel blades can break on the hide of a venerable zonure. But if you plan on blocking swords with your hands, just be careful of your fingertips.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Rainbow Bolero
Description:
Despite the straps and flaps and electrum adornments, this bolero affords the wearer a surprising amount of mobility.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Rainbow Ribbon
Description:
If you were expecting a riot of color to wrap around your neck, you will be sorely disappointed.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Holy Rainbow Hat
Description:
For when you need to gather in the afternoon, and compliment m'lady at dusk.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Ramie Turban
Description:
I find the little tassel jangling at the side of my head actually improves my concentration. I can't explain it...

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Hallowed Ramie Doublet
Description:
Not to be confused with the unhallowed ramie doublet. This is the one with the ruffles.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Chimerical Felt Cyclas
Description:
If you cannot find a stuffed chimera, an outfit made from its mane might be the next best thing.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Bloodhempen Skirt
Description:
These will be wonderful for traipsing about outdoors. ...Perhaps tomorrow!

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Ruby Cotton Gilet
Description:
Arterial spray is hardly noticeable on this gorgeous shade of red. Until it dries, of course.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Kudzu Hat
Description:
Just as the kudzu vine blocks the sun from the plants it envelops, so will this hat hide your face 'neath its brim. Probably for the best.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Serge Hose
Description:
Anyone who thinks these hose simple has no idea how steppe serge is made.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Twinsilk Apron
Description:
Made from twinsilk, which requires twinthread, which in turn is spun from twincoons. Feels wrong to own only one.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Brightlinen Himation
Description:
The basic himation is a rectangle of linen wrapped around the body, but no one said you couldn't accessorize.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Iridescent Top
Description:
A top which covers you from top to bottom. Belt dagger is purely ornamental.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Pixie Cotton Hood
Description:
A hood woven from pixie cotton. Not a cotton hood for pixies.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Ovim Wool Tunic
Description:
Is that a wand holder in the back? How convenient!

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Archaeoskin Grimoire
Description:
The more exotic the beast, the more likely someone has tanned its hide to make a spellbook. This one is archaeoskin, doubly bound.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Archaeoskin Codex
Description:
Some scholars will spare no expensenor fantastic beastto obtain protective covers for their tomes. 

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Dissolvent
Description:
When the rarest of artifacts must be cleansed of impurities, only the rarest of dissolvent will suffice.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Dhalmelskin Codex
Description:
Hopefully the rest of the dhalmel didn't go to waste.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Max-Potion
Description:
What theoretical maximum could a max-potion reach if a max-potion could theoretically be maximized?

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Book of Aurum Regis
Description:
There are noble metals, and then there's aurum regis. Some collectors need to be the king.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Koppranickel Index
Description:
I'd like to put it down before I eat, but I seem to have impaled a finger...

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Reisui
Description:
Try not to lose it amongst the regular bottles of reisuithat's an amateur's mistake.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Tigerskin Grimoire
Description:
Though crafted with materials of indisputable quality, many quietly consider the quill clasp on the back cover to be its greatest feature.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Growth Formula
Description:
When the pumpkin-growing crown is at stake, sometimes you need that little extra edge.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Gazelleskin Codex
Description:
An elegant and sturdy volume, with attachments to store both quill and ink. Practical!

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Alkahest
Description:
Dissolvent and reisui are all very well and good, but a true professional settles for nothing less than the highest quality alkahest.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Gliderskin Grimoire
Description:
Cracking open this tome is akin to swinging wide the gate to a lush garden of secrets.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Bluespirit Codex
Description:
I almost regret buying this one. It feels like all the other books are jealous.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Syrup
Description:
For when you absolutely, positively must not mess up that synthesis.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Dhalmel Gratin
Description:
Made with the choicest cuts and creamiest of sauces. Try not to burn your tongue.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Sohm Al Tart
Description:
This most mountainous of tarts will satisfy even the most famished of dragonslayers.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Sauteed Porcini
Description:
This fragrantly perfect dish would take pride of place next to the greatest trophies of war...if it weren't for that inconvenient rotting business.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Royal Eggs
Description:
You don't have to be royal to enjoy this delectable breakfast, but being friends with the royal culinarian might help.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Peperoncino
Description:
The extra spicy kick in these noodles will propel you through a difficult battle...or an afternoon with your future spouse's parents.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Marron Glace
Description:
You might think a chestnut soaked in any other honey would taste as sweet...but this is even sweeter.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Baklava
Description:
In the words of a famous djinn, How 'bout a little more Baklava?

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Shorlog
Description:
A tantalizing skewer of dzo meat fit for a khan.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Tempura Platter
Description:
It's the lightly fried batter which makes this platter better.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Persimmon Pudding
Description:
A single bite of this steamed dessert will reaffirm your belief in the divine.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Chirashi-zushi
Description:
Commonly eaten during celebrations, it is this dish which will be celebrated by salivating gourmands.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Grilled Rail
Description:
You wonder if some culinary critic awaits this succulent delight, table set and waiting by the nearest convenient aetheryte...

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Spaghetti al Nero
Description:
So tired of golden noodles, I want them to turn black.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Popotoes au Gratin
Description:
Popotoes? Mash 'em, boil 'em, stick them in a pot with a distinctive cream cheese sauce.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Espresso con Panna
Description:
Do not speak to me before I've had my espresso con panna.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Weathering Agent
Description: This corrosive concoction rusts and breaks down metal. Judicious application is key if it is to be used for aesthetic purposes.

Name: Seacloth
Description: So named for its origin among the isles of the southern seas, this fabric's unique loose weave has yet to be replicated elsewhere.

Name: Oddly Specific Cedar Lumber
Description: Must be cut within twenty paces of a lark's call, beneath a double rainbow.

Name: Oddly Specific Iron Nails
Description: Each and every nail must produce a sound akin to a Starlight Celebration chime when dropped from a height of precisely fourteen and a half ilms.

Name: Oddly Specific Mythril Rings
Description: The requirement that each ring be the same size does not seem to be especially odd or specific at first, but such opinions soon change upon realizing they must be crafted while blindfolded.

Name: Oddly Specific Silver Nugget
Description: Each specimen must have precisely the correct amount of nuggetiness.

Name: Oddly Specific Gaganaskin Strap
Description: The entire strap must be made from a single piece of skin, and being over a malm in length, is something of a tall order. Or long order, to be more precise.

Name: Oddly Specific Cloth
Description: Though the Skysteel Manufactory staff were oddly specific regarding the material itself, this odd level of specificity did not extend to its name, which is oddly unspecific.

Name: Oddly Specific Glue
Description: Most glues are designed to be used on certain types of material, whereas this sort is specifically meant to glue everything to everything else, including any container one may choose to place it in. This can make transporting it somewhat troublesome.

Name: Oddly Specific Oil
Description: While the instructions relating to the oil itself were not particularly specific, the bottle must be made from glass expertly crafted in the light of a full moon and blessed by forest spirits. Luckily, those conditions cannot be easily verified, and can therefore be ignored.

Name: Oddly Specific Cedar Plank
Description: One may be forgiven that an entire plank of anything is probably too much raw material for any sort of artisan's tool.

Name: Oddly Specific Iron Ingot
Description: The exact number of hammer blows used in its forging was specified by the Skysteel Manufactory's staff, but an extra tap here and there will likely go unnoticed.

Name: Oddly Specific Mythril Plate
Description: The instructions regarding the exact dimensions of each sheet were annoyingly specific, though one should be thankful that they did not request plates of mythril sheet, which are considerably more troublesome to craft.

Name: Oddly Specific Silver Ingot
Description: Considering that this ingot will inevitably be melted and hit repeatedly with hammers and so forth, the effort spent on making it look pretty seems rather pointless.

Name: Oddly Specific Gagana Leather
Description: The gagana itself must come from good stock, supposedly, though such wild creatures are not in the habit of keeping detailed records of their lineage.

Name: Oddly Specific Undyed Woolen Cloth
Description: Given the number of steps needed for the wool to reach this state, the possibility of a near-endless list of oddly specific instructions would be enough to deter all but the most stalwart of artisans. In the end, however, the Skysteel Manufactory staff asked only that it be free from any artificial colorings, which is presumably what the undyed part of its name implies.

Name: Oddly Specific Rubber
Description: The procurement of this rubbery specimen did not differ significantly from that of lesser varieties, though the manner in which it is handled before use tends to raise eyebrows. It must be thrown against a wall with an overarm motion, and then bounce exactly three and a half times before being caught in a bowl of hot porridge.

Name: Oddly Specific Paste
Description: Great pains must be taken while mixing to ensure the paste does not end up as a semi-liquid, or even worse, a liquid.

Name: Oddly Specific Cedar Log
Description: Must include the initials of star-crossed lovers carved into the bark. The Skysteel engineers will know if you have carved them yourself, especially if you use your own initials.

Name: Oddly Specific Coerthan Iron Ore
Description: As if specifying the location from which it is mined was not enough, the Skysteel engineers have also asked that you carry it about your person while walking an entire lap around Ishgard, so that it may soak up the local atmosphere.

Name: Oddly Specific Mythrite Sand
Description: Each pinch must contain mythrite and only mythrite, which in the grand scheme of things, seems perfectly reasonable.

Name: Oddly Specific Silver Ore
Description: The ore requested must be similar in appearance to gold, but with more of a light-grey tinge to it. Silver, in other words.

Name: Oddly Specific Gagana Skin
Description: Each gagana must be treated with the utmost care and allowed to live a life of uninterrupted bliss, right up until the moment they are brutally slaughtered.

Name: Oddly Specific Fleece
Description: The fleece must be soft enough that one can put their hand into the basket and not be able to feel a thingexcept for the inside of said basket.

Name: Oddly Specific Sap
Description: Before use, it should be shaken, stirred, shaken again, and then poured down a gagana's gullet and regurgitated, as tradition dictates.

Name: Oddly Specific Aloe
Description: Should only be harvested after being lightly dusted by the scales of an endangered species of moth, which also has its own set of oddly specific requirements.

Name: Oddly Specific Dark Chestnut Log
Description: Oddly enough, all of the specific requirements relate to the wood's aroma, which is strange considering it will most likely be covered in several layers of varnish, thereby obfuscating the original scent.

Name: Oddly Specific Leafborne Aethersand
Description: The original request was simply for green sand, which does not actually leave that many options.

Name: Oddly Specific Schorl
Description: Schorl is already in and of itself rather a specific thing to request, and it is somewhat surprising to find that it would play a significant part in improving an artisan's tool of the trade.

Name: Oddly Specific Landborne Aethersand
Description: While sand that is borne by the land is actually rather commonplace, the part about it being aetherially charged does make its procurement quite a challenge.

Name: Petal Shell
Description:
Sometimes mistaken for underwater flowers, though sadly, the aroma they produce is far less pleasant.

Can only be caught when equipped with a dragonsung fishing rod.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Oddly Specific Primordial Log
Description: The last remains of a great arboreal pillar, as old as time, that once towered over the earliest forms of life at the world's beginning. Smells a bit funny.

Name: Oddly Specific Primordial Resin
Description: The passing of time has rendered this once translucent jewel of the forest as opaque as obsidian. In fact, it may very well be an ordinary stone.

Name: Oddly Specific Primordial Ore
Description: Even among its rocky brethren, this specimen is especially ancient, having weathered the passing of ages, and is regarded as the grandfather of all stones. Well, not literally, that would be impossible for reasons far too complex to explain here. Or anywhere, for that matter.

Name: Oddly Specific Primordial Asphaltum
Description: The perfect substance for scalekin to dive into and enjoy a good frolic. Of course, it is all fun and games until someone gets dragged down and preserved for future generations to excavate.

Name: Allagan Hunter
Description:
Its aggressive temperament have ensured its place near the top of the food chain, although much of this aggression is directed at its own species. In a sense, the Allagan hunter is its own worst enemy.

Can only be caught when equipped with an augmented dragonsung fishing rod.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Workshop Materials
Description:
Even in their present state, this mishmash of materials exudes a decidedly workshop-like aroma, meaning it smells like puddles of grease and sweaty armpits.

Only for use in dwarf society quests.

Name: Workshop Supplies
Description:
Contains vital pieces of the puzzle that is Ronitt's workshop. Unfortunately, you are not privy to the details surrounding their assembly, though rather than being some closely guarded secret, it is largely due to the fact that Ronitt is hopeless when it comes to adequately explaining anything.

Only for use in dwarf society quests.

Name: Brewery Materials
Description:
These raw materials represent the first stage of a rather lengthy and complicated process by which the production of ale somehow expedites the completion of a series of war machines. Rather than stopping to consider the many, many flaws in this plan, you would be better off blindly obeying orders, or so your dwarven companions have conditioned you to believe.

Only for use in dwarf society quests.

Name: Brewery Supplies
Description:
A selection of parts and materials needed to build a brewery in the traditional Gogg style. That is to say, immediately adjacent to a place where heavy engineering takes place, thereby enabling the workers to drink themselves silly whenever it pleases them.

Only for use in dwarf society quests.

Name: Crystal Cannon Materials
Description:
As great oaks from little acorns grow, so too do crystal cannons from little sacks full of random junk grow. All it takes is a little bit of elbow grease.

Only for use in dwarf society quests.

Name: Crystal Cannon Supplies
Description:
The various components and concoctions contained within this crate will one day go on to form some of the most advanced weaponry in Norvrandt. No doubt the crate itself will look back on this time as one of the highlights of its career.

Only for use in dwarf society quests.

Name: Workshop Expansion Materials
Description:
One would be forgiven for thinking that the materials needed to expand the workshop would be exactly the same as those used to build it in the first place, but apparently not. Heavens forbid that Ronitt make anyone else's life easy.

Only for use in dwarf society quests.

Name: Workshop Expansion Supplies
Description:
While it seems that the production of the supplies within this crate could have been delegated to any one of the skilled engineers of Watts's Anvil, you alone have been chosen for this most prestigious of positions. Most prestigious among Ronitt's lackeys, that is.

Only for use in dwarf society quests.

Name: Automaton Worker Materials
Description:
If all goes according to plan, the contents of this sack may go on to join such illustrious company as the Megasonic Frogboy or the Fetchomatic Mechatoad, royalty among automata.

Only for use in dwarf society quests.

Name: Automaton Worker Supplies
Description:
Do automata dream of electric frogs? Those made from the contents of this crate certainly will not, as their every thought will be devoted only to the production of tank after tank, never to so much as rest, let alone dream.

Only for use in dwarf society quests.

Name: Armament Repair Kit Materials
Description:
Assorted materials necessary for putting together a specialized armament repair kit.

Only for use in dwarf society quests.

Name: Armament Repair Kit
Description:
This repair kit contains specialized items for the maintenance and mending of soldierly equipment.

Only for use in dwarf society quests.

Name: Grooming Kit Materials
Description:
Assorted materials necessary for preparing a grooming kit for dwarven beards.

Only for use in dwarf society quests.

Name: Grooming Kit
Description:
This grooming kit contains items essential to a dwarf's beardcare routine.

Only for use in dwarf society quests.

Name: Core Tank Component Materials
Description:
Assorted materials necessary for creating a vitally important tank component.

Only for use in dwarf society quests.

Name: Core Tank Component
Description:
This vitally important tank component is sure to impress even the most demanding dwarven engineer.

Only for use in dwarf society quests.

Name: Axle Component Materials
Description:
Assorted materials necessary for creating an axle component.

Only for use in dwarf society quests.

Name: Axle Component
Description:
A component that can make the axles of the bulkiest tank turn as quietly as a mouse.

Only for use in dwarf society quests.

Name: Blueprint Materials
Description:
Blueprints are generally simple to get started, but the dwarves of the Anvil demand materials of the highest quality.

Only for use in dwarf society quests.

Name: Blueprint Supplies
Description:
Blueprints are among the most prized possessions in the Anvil, and many dwarves will guard their own designs as jealously as they would a tankard of ale.

Only for use in dwarf society quests.

Name: Steel Plate Component Materials
Description:
Assorted materials necessary for creating a steel plate component.

Only for use in dwarf society quests.

Name: Steel Plate Component
Description:
The production of steel plates involves much more than an ingot and some fire, as can be plainly seen by the complexity of this component.

Only for use in dwarf society quests.

Name: Cask Component Materials
Description:
Assorted materials necessary for creating a cask component.

Only for use in dwarf society quests.

Name: Cask Component
Description:
Only the choicest of materials are used in these casks, for many dwarves would rather see their own blood spilt than a single drop of ale.

Only for use in dwarf society quests.

Name: Engine Component Materials
Description:
Assorted materials necessary for creating an engine component.

Only for use in dwarf society quests.

Name: Engine Component
Description:
The engine is the heart of a tank, and must be maintained with as much care as the heart of any living, breathing being.

Only for use in dwarf society quests.

Name: Filtration Materials
Description:
Filtration is a delicate science; one which often requires a long process of trial and error and, as a consequence, sacks and sacks of materials.

Only for use in dwarf society quests.

Name: Filtration Supplies
Description:
Science can only be perfected through a long series of experiments, which require a steady stream of supplies. Or in this case, a parcel of them.

Only for use in dwarf society quests.

Name: Cooling Device Component Materials
Description:
Assorted materials necessary for creating a cooling device component.

Only for use in dwarf society quests.

Name: Cooling Device Component
Description:
An overheated tank is no use to anyone.

Only for use in dwarf society quests.

Name: Tavern Supplies
Description:
Everything required to make a tavern worthy of the most discerning lush.

Only for use in dwarf society quests.

Name: Tavern Materials
Description:
Even dwarven taverns face plenty of competition, so every material used in its construction must be of the utmost quality.

Only for use in dwarf society quests.

Name: Heat-resistant Component Materials
Description:
Assorted materials necessary for creating a heat-resistant tank component.

Only for use in dwarf society quests.

Name: Heat-resistant Component
Description:
A tank component capable of withstanding high temperatures.

Only for use in dwarf society quests.

Name: Bespoke Barter Item Materials
Description:
Assorted materials necessary for creating a bespoke barter item pleasing to the Mord.

Only for use in dwarf society quests.

Name: Bespoke Barter Item
Description:
This creation is tailor-made to capture the heartand lower the pricesof a Mord merchant.

Only for use in dwarf society quests.

Name: Test-fire Target Dummy Materials
Description:
Assorted materials necessary for creating a test-fire target dummy.

Only for use in dwarf society quests.

Name: Test-fire Target Dummy
Description:
This target dummy is destined for destruction by tank cannon test-firing.

Only for use in dwarf society quests.

Name: Experimental Plating Component Materials
Description:
Assorted materials necessary for creating experimental armor plating components.

Only for use in dwarf society quests.

Name: Experimental Plating Component
Description:
An experimental component designed to strengthen a tank's armor plating.

Only for use in dwarf society quests.

Name: Unfailing Eye Opener Materials
Description:
Assorted materials necessary for creating the Unfailing Eye Opener.

Only for use in dwarf society quests.

Name: Unfailing Eye Opener
Description:
A special tool designed to jolt the recipient into wakefulness with a one hundred percent success rate.

Only for use in dwarf society quests.

Name: Eye-catching Custom Option Materials
Description:
Assorted materials necessary for creating an eye-catching custom option for a tank's exterior appearance.

Only for use in dwarf society quests.

Name: Eye-catching Custom Option
Description:
An attention-seeking custom option designed to distinguish a tank's exterior appearance.

Only for use in dwarf society quests.

Name: Automaton Repair Component Materials
Description:
Assorted materials necessary for creating an automaton repair component.

Only for use in dwarf society quests.

Name: Automaton Repair Component
Description:
A component needed for the repairs of a badly damaged automaton drudge.

Only for use in dwarf society quests.

Name: Low-profile Custom Option Materials
Description:
Assorted materials necessary for creating a low-profile custom option for a tank's exterior appearance.

Only for use in dwarf society quests.

Name: Low-profile Custom Option
Description:
A stealth-enhancing custom option designed to camouflage a tank's exterior appearance.

Only for use in dwarf society quests.

Name: Grade 3 Skybuilders' Plywood
Description: Some pieces of plywood have a thin veneer covering the surface to give the impression of being made from actual wood. This specimen, however, harbors no such pretensions and is every bit as cheap as it looks.

Name: Grade 3 Skybuilders' Alloy
Description: The favored alloy of the hoi polloi.

Name: Grade 3 Skybuilders' Steel Plate
Description: Despite the name, this is not a robust, metallic piece of tableware. The main reason it is unsuited to such a purpose is that there is nothing to stop peas from rolling off the edge.

Name: Grade 3 Skybuilders' Ingot
Description: Though ingots are fairly ubiquitous in most forms of metalworking, far less commonly seen is a variation known as an outgot, which is exactly the same but upside down.

Name: Grade 3 Skybuilders' Leather
Description: When choosing the name, the skybuilders were far more concerned with assigning a grade than specifying the animal from which the leather originally came. It does smell a bit like goat, if that is anything to go by.

Name: Grade 3 Skybuilders' Rope
Description: This is what string wants to be when it grows up.

Name: Grade 3 Skybuilders' Ink
Description:
If you took away my paper, I would write on my heart. If you took away my ink, I would write on the wind.
...It wouldn't be an ideal way to work.
Unknown author, dreamweaver, visionary, plus actor

Name: Grade 3 Skybuilders' Hemp Milk
Description: Being made from plant extracts, this refreshing beverage stretches the definition of what is normally considered to be milk. Then again, if seahorses and starfish are anything to go by, names can often be misleading.

Name: Grade 3 Skybuilders' Crate
Description: With all the crates scattered around the Firmament, the skybuilders have need of a means of storing them. It is for this exact purpose that this particular container was designed. Calls for it to be renamed the crate crate have been largely ignored.

Name: Grade 3 Skybuilders' Nails
Description: Even a simple table leg can be transformed into a deadly bludgeon by hammering a few of these nails into the end. Perfect for adventurers on a tight budget.

Name: Grade 3 Skybuilders' Rivets
Description: Some may argue that rivets are nothing more than nails without the pointy bit.

Name: Grade 3 Skybuilders' Rings
Description: These metal rings can apparently be joined and unjoined at will, though the only people capable of such a feat are sleight of hand artists. The skybuilders, however, are reluctant to employ such unscrupulous characters for fear of them fleecing the other workers, leaving these rings in a decidedly unjoined state.

Name: Grade 3 Skybuilders' Leather Straps
Description: When times are hard, many of the poor resort to eating leather to survive. Cutting said material into strips beforehand makes it somewhat easier to digest, or at the very least, easier to chew.

Name: Grade 3 Skybuilders' Cloth
Description: In most regions, people dress according to their personal preferences. In Ishgard, people dress according to their need to not freeze to death. Cloth such as this is as essential to survival as basic sustenance, if not more, as the cold will kill you faster than an empty stomach.

Name: Grade 3 Skybuilders' Plant Oil
Description: The people of Ishgard have endless uses for plant oil, though the local climate is less than ideal for the cultivation of said plants, or anything to cook using said oil, for that matter.

Name: Grade 3 Skybuilders' Sesame Cookie
Description: In order to be classed as grade 3, each cookie must contain a certain number of sesame seeds. Needless to say, counting them is one of the most tedious tasks undertaken by the skybuilders, though it works remarkably well as a cure for insomnia.

Name: Grade 3 Skybuilders' Grinding Wheel
Description: Primarily used for filing down the various materials used in goldsmithing, as well as providing an effectivethough not especially portablemeans of keeping fingernails short.

Name: Grade 3 Skybuilders' Pickaxe
Description: Useful not only for clearing rocks and debris, but also for dispatching any creatures that may emerge. In the case of Copperbell Mines, however, such creatures are often armed with pickaxes of their own.

Name: Grade 3 Skybuilders' Cookpot
Description: Can also be used as a makeshift bathtub by Lalafells, provided they refrain from sloshing water everywhere by making the pot sway back and forth.

Name: Grade 3 Skybuilders' Embroidery Frame
Description: Though there is little discernible difference between the grade 2 and grade 3 embroidery frames, the name alone strongly implies that this version is infinitely superior.

Name: Grade 3 Skybuilders' Leather Sack
Description: If one of the workers in the Firmament is given one of these sacks, it should be taken as meaning pack up your things and leave. Ishgard maintains the tradition of literally giving someone the sack when their employment has been terminated.

Name: Grade 3 Skybuilders' Broom
Description: Those who believe the tales of witches flying around on broomsticks have obviously never tried flying one for themselves. They take to the air about as well as a heavily armored Temple Knight takes to water, which is to say, not very.

Name: Grade 3 Skybuilders' Holy Water
Description: Believed to cure zombification. Grade 3 is claimed to grant a full recovery, whereas grade 2 only delays the onset of the symptoms, and grade 1 merely replaces the need to feast on the flesh of the living with a craving for copious amounts of bacon.

Name: Grade 3 Skybuilders' Tea
Description: A grade 3 cup is stirred using a figure of eight motion, rather than the traditional circular movement used for the grade 2 variety. Claims that this has any discernible effect on the flavor are largely regarded as nonsense, however.

Name: Grade 3 Skybuilders' Stepladder
Description: Perhaps when man and dragon have formed a stronger bond of trust, the skybuilders may take to the air on dragonback to perform all manner of tasks at higher altitudes. Until that day, mankind will just have to rely on good, old-fashioned stepladders.

Name: Grade 3 Skybuilders' Crosscut Saw
Description: Extremely effective at producing sawdust. Also cuts wood.

Name: Grade 3 Skybuilders' Mesail
Description: This would be perfect for protecting one's eyes from flying sparks while performing metalworkthe task it was primarily designed forwere it not for the large eyeholes.

Name: Grade 3 Skybuilders' Stone
Description: Despite its abundance in Coerthas, the skybuilders are quick to remind others that stone like this doesn't grow on trees. Factually accurate, yes. Logically sound, not so much.

Name: Grade 3 Skybuilders' Longboots
Description: In other parts of Hydaelyn, people would consider wearing two pairs of socks ample protection against the cold. In Coerthas, it is common to wear two pairs of boots, one over the other, as well as maybe a couple more pairs of socks for good measure.

Name: Grade 3 Skybuilders' Gloves
Description: For those wondering what the distinction between the grade 2 and grade 3 varieties might be, they need only smell the glove.

Name: Grade 3 Skybuilders' Soap
Description: When strategically placed on the floor, a wet bar of soap can be used to form a makeshift death trap for offing heiresses and the like.

Name: Grade 3 Skybuilders' All-purpose Infusion
Description: Whereas many concoctions are said to prevent various ailments, this one supposedly prevents all manner of accidents. In addition to drinking the recommended daily dose, one must avoid physical exertion, unnecessary excursions, and anything even remotely resembling danger to enjoy the effects of the infusion to their fullest.

Name: Grade 3 Skybuilders' Bed
Description:
Bed, bedder, bedst.
Never let it rest.
Till your bed is bedder, and your bedder bedst.

Name: Grade 3 Skybuilders' Oven
Description: Large enough to fit a whole witch inside.

Name: Grade 3 Skybuilders' Lamppost
Description: Keep this lamppost away from dogs, or alternatively, keep dogs away from this lamppost. Whichever is more feasible.

Name: Grade 3 Skybuilders' Brazier
Description: This traditional cooking apparatus offers Ishgardians the opportunity to enjoy two of their favorite pastimes: fried meat and not freezing to death.

Name: Grade 3 Skybuilders' Overalls
Description: Overall the best thing to wear over all of one's clothes.

Name: Grade 3 Skybuilders' Awning
Description: Protects one's eyes from the glaring sunlight, should any of it manage to find its way through the layers of dense cloud that hang almost perpetually over Ishgard.

Name: Grade 3 Skybuilders' Growth Formula
Description: The original creator claims it works on almost anything, within reason. Stone, for example, stubbornly refuses to grow no matter how much formula is applied.

Name: Grade 3 Skybuilders' Stew
Description: The grade 3 stew actually contains ingredients with names other than dunno or not sure, but it was definitely dead when I threw it in.

Name: Grade 3 Artisanal Skybuilders' Goldsmithing Bench
Description: Not only is the workbench rather lavishly made, it can also be used in the crafting of further lavishly made items.

Name: Grade 3 Artisanal Skybuilders' Smithing Bench
Description: Suited to almost any sort of smithing besides wordsmithing, for which a regular desk will suffice.

Name: Grade 3 Artisanal Skybuilders' Door
Description:
When one door closes, another one opens? Sounds like you'd have trouble keeping out the draught.
Unknown carpenter

Name: Grade 3 Artisanal Skybuilders' Chronometer
Description: Though the use of such timepieces is still fairly limited in Ishgard, this particular model includes a bell that be set to ring at a specified time, earning it the rather catchy appellation alarum chronometer.

Name: Grade 3 Artisanal Skybuilders' Leather Chair
Description: Luckily, only the upholstery is made from leather. If the inner frame were made from the same material, it would have a difficult time supporting the weight of anything heavier than a medium-sized cat.

Name: Grade 3 Artisanal Skybuilders' Apron
Description: Basically a large dishcloth with a few straps attached. However, it is these straps that earn the apron the right to be called artisanal, as they will not come undone no matter how hard they are tugged by needy children begging for cookies.

Name: Grade 3 Artisanal Skybuilders' Tiled Flooring
Description: The use of materials that are naturally cold to the touch in the chilly land of Coerthas may be considered a design flaw, but it is actually a designer floor.

Name: Grade 3 Artisanal Skybuilders' Luncheon
Description: Though an army may march on its stomach, the skybuilders choose a more effective means of forward locomotion: walking with their legs. It is for this reason they require sustenance, and this hearty meal provides exactly that, along with enough grease to kill a sasquatch.

Name: Approved Grade 3 Skybuilders' Switch
Description:
Makes a satisfying thwack sound when swung through the air. On the other hand, attempting to actually hit something will cause it to break immediately, so it is reserved only for scare tactics.

Used in level 20 crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 3 Skybuilders' Hemp
Description:
Compared to the grade 2 variety, this is the good shite.

Used in level 20 crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 3 Skybuilders' Ore
Description:
The first miner to discover this particular variety described it as extra-ore-dinary and was met with a chorus of groans from her peers.

Used in level 20 crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 3 Skybuilders' Bomb Ash
Description:
Some might argue that it would be easier to locate a living bomb and wait for it to explode than to scrabble about in the dirt and undergrowth looking for particles of ash from one that had exploded previously. The problem lies in finding volunteers who are not only foolhardy enough to attempt it, but hardy enough to survive.

Used in level 20 crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 3 Skybuilders' Ebony Log
Description:
Care must be taken when working with ebony wood, as its sawdust is both highly flammable and toxic. Strangely, the skybuilders failed to mention this...

Used in level 40 crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 3 Skybuilders' Sesame
Description:
Sesame is not only a useful plant, but the mere mention of its name is believed to open many doors in a very literal sense.

Used in level 40 crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 3 Skybuilders' Cotton Boll
Description:
Often misheard as cotton bowl, which has led to several nigh on useless pieces of fluffy tableware being submitted to the skybuilders.

Used in level 40 crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 3 Skybuilders' Titanium Ore
Description:
Unlike some other ores requested by the skybuilders, they actually deigned to give the name of the type of metal they would like in this case, rather than simply some ore.

Used in level 40 crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 3 Skybuilders' Rock Salt
Description:
This particular type of salt is for sprinkling on rocks to make them taste better, hence the name rock salt.

Used in level 40 crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 3 Skybuilders' Hardsilver Sand
Description:
Hardsilver's inherent hardness is somewhat difficult to gauge in granular form.

Used in level 40 crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 3 Skybuilders' Lauan Log
Description: The aesthetically pleasing bark of this particular tree allows it to be used in its natural state to give a rustic feel to a home's interior. On the other hand, rustic is often used to mean we can save time and effort by convincing gullible customers that having bits of rough-cut wood all over the place is somehow desirable.

Name: Approved Grade 3 Skybuilders' Mistletoe
Description: Used in a variety of medical treatments despite being highly toxic. Failure to adhere to the correct dosage may lead to symptoms far worse than the ailment it was meant to cure.

Name: Approved Grade 3 Skybuilders' Toad
Description: One of the skybuilders has been tasked with kissing every toad they receive on the off chance of it being a cursed prince. This, however, is suspected to be one of the many tasks designed to keep troublesome workers out of mischief, along with polishing the coal and washing the soap.

Name: Approved Grade 3 Skybuilders' Vine
Description: A naturally occurring substitute for rope, perfect for swinging through the trees while yodeling like a buffoon.

Name: Approved Grade 3 Skybuilders' Tea Leaves
Description: This variety is often used in tea leaf reading, and is said to result in a high rate of good fortunes, though most tasseomancers base their readings more on what they think the customer wants to hear than the patterns left in the cup.

Name: Approved Grade 3 Skybuilders' Diadem Iron Ore
Description: Though similar substances exist in other regions, the Diadem variety tends to be more highly coveted. This may simply be due to its scarcity rather than any intrinsic properties, as by and large, the more difficult something is to obtain, the more people want it.

Name: Approved Grade 3 Skybuilders' Alumen
Description: In recent years, there have been calls to abandon the use of pinches as a unit of measurement for powders. However, the fact that an amount equal to a single pinch is rarely enough to cause even the most sensitive of scales to budge leads to difficulties when deciding on a weight-based standard.

Name: Approved Grade 3 Skybuilders' Spring Water
Description: The name may indicate that there are very specific criteria to pass muster with the skybuilders, but the taste and smell are the same as almost any other type of water. That is to say: it tastes of nothing and smells of nothing.

Name: Approved Grade 3 Skybuilders' Diadem Iron Sand
Description: As is often the case with items found in the Diadem, this iron sand possesses unique properties. It is magnetically attracted not only to metallic objects, but a range of organic materials, such as skin and clothing, which means it is often gathered regardless of one's intentions.

Name: Approved Grade 3 Skybuilders' Siltstone
Description: This flaky, lightweight stone is a firm favorite with street performers who demonstrate their strength by smashing through rock with their bare hands.

Name: Approved Grade 3 Skybuilders' Cedar Log
Description:
Due to cedar being a natural repellent for mothswhich can be both extremely large and ferocious in some partsmany adventurers have taken to carrying it about their person. Hefting around an entire log might be going a touch overboard, however.

Used in level 80 crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 3 Skybuilders' Resin
Description:
He tried to take it from me, or at least, he looked like he wanted to. So I cut him. Can't blame a man for keeping his resin to himself, can you?
Excerpt from How to Win Friends and Execute People: Climbing the Ranks of the Temple Knights
by unknown author

Used in level 80 crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 3 Skybuilders' Wheat
Description:
May contain traces of chaff.

Used in level 80 crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 3 Skybuilders' Gossamer Cotton Boll
Description:
In this case, the word gossamer is applied in a literal sense, as each boll is covered in a fine layer of cobweb. This is kept intact until the cotton is spun into thread, which grants it extraordinary resilience to wear and tear.

Used in level 80 crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 3 Skybuilders' Adder
Description:
As one can imagine, there is a host of practical applications for a venomous snake in the Ishgardian reconstruction efforts. These include the production of snake wine, in which the scalekin is preserved in alcohol that gains a unique flavor and medicinal properties. In several cases, the snake has been known to spring to life after moons of being entirely submerged in the liquid.

Used in level 80 crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 3 Skybuilders' Aurum Regis Ore
Description:
Kingly is not an adjective that is often applied to metals of any sort, though in the case of aurum regis, it seems perfectly fitting, for some reason.

Used in level 80 crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 3 Skybuilders' Finest Rock Salt
Description:
Many people prefer to keep such chunks whole so that they may be used as salt rocks. These are placed in the center of the dining table so that anyone who feels their meal is lacking in saltiness can simply lick it and carry on with their meal.

Used in level 80 crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 3 Skybuilders' Truespring Water
Description:
Often confused with falsespring water, which is remarkably similar apart from the fact it smells like a wet dog.

Used in level 80 crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 3 Skybuilders' Fossil Dust
Description:
Despite the creature having been dead for millennia, fossilized, and then ground to dust, I was able to extrapolate its diet, breeding habits, and susceptibility to hiccups from the single, remaining fragment of vertebrae.
Excerpt from On the Trail of the Thunder Lizards

Used in level 80 crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 3 Skybuilders' Hard Mudstone
Description:
Mudstone may not be the most impressive of substances, but becoming a solid piece of rock after an extended period as a sticky semiliquid is something of an improvement.

Used in level 80 crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 3 Artisanal Skybuilders' Log
Description:
Grade 3 and artisanal it may be, yet the name of the tree from which it came is an enigma enveloped in a mystery. Before the skybuilders and their bizarre naming conventions, it was simply...log.

Used in expert crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 3 Artisanal Skybuilders' Amber
Description:
The grade is determined by the number of vilekin encased within each piece. Fewer is generally considered to be better, unless the buyer happens to be a naturalist, in which case, the opposite is true. They have been known to pay absurd amounts for the most heavily infested specimens.

Used in expert crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 3 Artisanal Skybuilders' Cotton Boll
Description:
These bolls contain roughly twice the amount of cotton as the regular sort, but due to the thickness of the plant's stems, take roughly twice as much effort to harvest.

Used in expert crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 3 Artisanal Skybuilders' Rice
Description:
Rice remains something of a novelty in Ishgard, though the skybuilders seem to be experts on the subject regardless. Apparently, they can tell the difference between the truly artisanal and the merely humdrum.

Used in expert crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 3 Artisanal Skybuilders' Vine
Description:
The artisanal vines that are chosen for the Firmament tend to stand out from the common-or-garden varieties. One could say they are vine for attention.

Used in expert crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 3 Artisanal Skybuilders' Cloudstone
Description:
One of the few stones light enough to float in water.

Used in expert crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 3 Artisanal Skybuilders' Basilisk Egg
Description:
Most recipients of such eggs would prefer them without a tiny, carnivorous scalekin inside.

Used in expert crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 3 Artisanal Skybuilders' Alumen
Description:
Though alumen is commonly used in the tanning of animal hide, the artisanal can supposedly be used to tan other materials, such as hair or soil. Such claims have yet to be verified, however.

Used in expert crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 3 Artisanal Skybuilders' Clay
Description:
Many apprentice potters have been known to misinterpret the meaning of throwing a pot, leading to hilarious capers, instant dismissal, or both.

Used in expert crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 3 Artisanal Skybuilders' Granite
Description:
Granite is said to be phaneritic, or in layman's terms, macroscopically crystalline.

Used in expert crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 3 Skybuilders' Umbral Galewood Sap
Description:
Practically pulsating with wind-aspected aether. Also has a distinct sweet taste, although one should take care when adding it to their beverages, unless the aim is to create a literal storm in a teacup.

Can only be gathered during an umbral tempest.

Used in expert crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 3 Skybuilders' Umbral Tortoise
Description:
In addition to its craggy hide and shell protecting it from the teeth and claws of predators, the earth-aspected aether with which it is infused causes it to taste like soil. Any creatures patient and strong enough to reach the tender meat inside are invariably left disappointed.

Can only be gathered during an umbral duststorm.

Used in expert crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 3 Skybuilders' Umbral Magma Shard
Description:
Though the name may seem at first to be an oxymoron, each fragment actually contains magma in liquid form beneath a thin crust. Anyone foolish enough to put one of these shards in their back pocket before sitting down will cause a hole to be burned not only in their breeches, but also the chair on which they sat.

Can only be gathered during an umbral flare.

Used in expert crafting recipes.

Name: Approved Grade 3 Skybuilders' Umbral Levinite
Description:
Some scholars maintain that levinite is the result of lightning taking solid form upon striking the earth. Most other scholars, however, maintain that this theory is bollocks.

Can only be gathered during umbral levin.

Used in expert crafting recipes.

Name: Grade 3 Skybuilders' Switch
Description:
Makes a satisfying thwack sound when swung through the air. On the other hand, attempting to actually hit something will cause it to break immediately, so it is reserved only for scare tactics.

Used in level 20 crafting recipes.

Name: Grade 3 Skybuilders' Hemp
Description:
Compared to the grade 2 variety, this is the good shite.

Used in level 20 crafting recipes.

Description:

Can only be gathered during umbral levin.

Used in expert crafting recipes.

Name: Slithersand
Description: Smooth granules of the mineral also known as green cinnabar, containing traces of quicksilver.

Name: Vermilion Paper Parasol
Description: Though one might assume that paper is less than ideal for protecting oneself from the rain, this parasol has been treated with waterproof oil. The makers cannot, however, be held responsible for any puddles stepped in. Use to acquire a vermilion paper parasol.

Name: Plum Paper Parasol
Description: Named for its color, not because the paper is made from the wood of a plum tree. Use to acquire a plum paper parasol.

Name: Gold Paper Parasol
Description: Unfortunately not covered in gold leaf, but fool's gold leaf, which is considerably cheaper on account of its rather silly name. Use to acquire a gold paper parasol.

Name: Calming Checkered Parasol
Description: Creates not only a small, portable circle of shade, but exudes a calming influence. Somehow. Use to acquire a calming checkered parasol.

Name: Cheerful Checkered Parasol
Description: There is something about a white background covered in many, many straight red lines that creates a cheerful atmosphere, though scholars have yet to determine exactly why. Use to acquire a cheerful checkered parasol.

Name: Classy Checkered Parasol
Description: Were one to describe this parasol's pattern as black-and-white check then perhaps it might conjure images of chessboards and the like. Even so, it could be argued that this design is far classier. Use to acquire a classy checkered parasol.

Name: Season Two Writ of Commendation
Description:
Documentation of noteworthy accomplishments on behalf of the Ishgardian Restoration.

Use to gain the Minor Miracle achievement for Season Two.

Name: Season Two Writ of Canonization
Description:
Documentation of noteworthy accomplishments on behalf of the Ishgardian Restoration.

Use to gain the Divine Ascension achievement for Season Two.

Name: Level 18 Weapon Coffer
Description:
A heavy chest containing a weapon of item level 18 through 21.

Weapon type determined by current job or class at time of opening. Cannot be opened in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.

Name: Level 21 Weapon Coffer
Description:
A heavy chest containing a weapon of item level 21 through 23.

Weapon type determined by current job or class at time of opening. Cannot be opened in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.

Name: Level 24 Weapon Coffer
Description:
A heavy chest containing a weapon of item level 24 through 26.

Weapon type determined by current job or class at time of opening. Cannot be opened in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.

Name: Level 28 Weapon Coffer
Description:
A heavy chest containing a weapon of item level 28 through 30.

Weapon type determined by current job or class at time of opening. Cannot be opened in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.

Name: Level 34 Weapon Coffer
Description:
A heavy chest containing a weapon of item level 34 or 35.

Weapon type determined by current job or class at time of opening. Cannot be opened in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.

Name: Level 36 Weapon Coffer
Description:
A heavy chest containing a weapon of item level 36 through 38.

Weapon type determined by current job or class at time of opening. Cannot be opened in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.

Name: Level 40 Weapon Coffer
Description:
A heavy chest containing a weapon of item level 40 through 42.

Weapon type determined by current job or class at time of opening. Cannot be opened in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.

Name: Level 45 Weapon Coffer
Description:
A heavy chest containing a weapon of item level 45 or 46.

Weapon type determined by current job or class at time of opening. Cannot be opened in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.

Name: Level 49 Weapon Coffer
Description:
A heavy chest containing an item level 49 weapon.

Weapon type determined by current job or class at time of opening. Cannot be opened in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Reproachful Rumination
Description: An illustrated manual of how to tactfully express one's doubt or disagreement when conversing in a formal setting. Use to learn the /consider emote.

Name: Irregular Tomestone of Esoterics
Description:
One of only a few in existence, this Allagan tomestone contains knowledge that is clearly uncommon for a reason.

Can be exchanged with itinerant moogles for certain items.

Name: Bozjan Coin
Description: A tarnished and dented coin minted in Bozja before it became subject to imperial rule.

Name: Bozjan Runner's Secrets (Head Gear)
Description: Clasps, protective material, and other accoutrements that can be applied to personal equipment for increased safety and mobility on the battlefield.

Name: Bozjan Runner's Secrets (Body Gear)
Description: Clasps, protective material, and other accoutrements that can be applied to personal equipment for increased safety and mobility on the battlefield.

Name: Bozjan Runner's Secrets (Foot Gear)

Name: Southern Front Lockbox
Description: A battered though still firmly sealed box discovered at the Bozjan southern front. Only a Gangos-trained locksmith might grant you access to the spoils within.

Name: Bozjan Earring
Description: Increases EXP earned by 10% when level 80 and below. Attributes and item level vary according to class/job and current level when equipped.

Name: Magitek Hyperconveyor Identification Key
Description: A thin, rectangular piece of what appears to be cermet. Placing it near your magitek hyperconveyor will magically bring the machine to life.

Name: Magicked Prism (Mandragora)
Description: This peculiar contraption creates illusions by weaving together myriad shades of light. Lovingly crafted by the children of Menphina's Arms.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - The Metaphysics of Merrymaking
Description: An illustrated manual including impenetrable text excerpts courtesy of Far Eastern scholar Seigetsu the Enlightened. Use to learn the /wasshoi emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Floral Rearrangement
Description: An illustrated manual of how to create a dazzling shower of petals to accompany your debut without conspicuously destroying whatever bouquets may be close at hand. Use to learn the /flowershower emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - The Flame Dance
Description: An illustrated manual of the various steps that comprise a traditional Lalafellin dance hailing from the sunny south sea isles. Use to learn the /flamedance emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Uncouth Congratulations
Description: An illustrated manual of congratulatory gestures best avoided in polite company. Use to learn the /highfive emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Pointed Misgivings
Description: An illustrated manual of how to make clear that you are keeping close watch over the whole of the banquet table, and will deliver swift retribution should anyone try to take more than the socially acceptable number of hors d'oeuvres. Use to learn the /guard emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Dark Entreaty
Description: An illustrated manual detailing how to visit an unholy fate upon your social rivals. Use to learn the /malevolence emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - The Bee's Knees
Description: An illustrated manual of the various steps that comprise the bee's knees, an unobtrusive-but-delightful dance that never gets old. Skimpy attire optional (and may be frowned upon at certain functions). Use to learn the /beesknees emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - The Lali Hop
Description: An illustrated manual of the various steps that comprise the lali hop, a dance thatlike most every dwarven customis tremendously rousing. Use to learn the /lalihop emote.

Name: Modern Aesthetics - Saintly Style
Description:
The realm's premier publication on beauty and fashion, this limited edition of Modern Aesthetics covers, in detail, shaping and feathering techniques for imitating the unique look of an Ishgardian saint of eld.

Use to unlock a new hairstyle at the aesthetician.
Unavailable to female Hrothgar.

Name: Modern Aesthetics - Wind Caller
Description:
The realm's premier publication on beauty and fashion, this limited edition of Modern Aesthetics covers, in detail, feathering and styling techniques to achieve the windswept look of a legendary Vartan warrior.

Use to unlock a new hairstyle at the aesthetician.
Unavailable to female Hrothgar.
