Name: Bozjan Silver Coin
Description: A faintly lustrous coin minted in Bozja before it became subject to imperial rule.

Name: Bozjan Gold Coin
Description: A highly burnished coin minted in Bozja before it became subject to imperial rule.

Name: Runner's Plating (Head Gear)
Description: Lightweight and remarkably durable alloy plate used in various pieces of personal equipment.

Name: Runner's Plating (Body Gear)
Description: Lightweight and remarkably durable alloy plate used in various pieces of personal equipment.

Name: Runner's Plating (Hand Gear)
Description: Lightweight and remarkably durable alloy plate used in various pieces of personal equipment.

Name: Runner's Plating (Leg Gear)
Description: Lightweight and remarkably durable alloy plate used in various pieces of personal equipment.

Name: Runner's Plating (Foot Gear)
Description: Lightweight and remarkably durable alloy plate used in various pieces of personal equipment.

Name: Orderly Runner's Secrets (Head Gear)
Description: Neatly arranged sheets of armor plating, bindings, and assorted doodahs that can be applied to personal equipment for increased protection and agility on the battlefield.

Name: Orderly Runner's Secrets (Body Gear)
Description: Neatly arranged sheets of armor plating, bindings, and assorted doodahs that can be applied to personal equipment for increased protection and agility on the battlefield.

Name: Orderly Runner's Secrets (Hand Gear)
Description: Neatly arranged sheets of armor plating, bindings, and assorted doodahs that can be applied to personal equipment for increased protection and agility on the battlefield.

Name: Orderly Runner's Secrets (Foot Gear)
Description: Neatly arranged sheets of armor plating, bindings, and assorted doodahs that can be applied to personal equipment for increased protection and agility on the battlefield.

Name: Field Notes on Lilja
Description:
Handwritten notes on the history and character of Garlond Ironworks' promising new recruit, Lilja Sjasaris.

Use to add to your field record.

Name: Field Notes on Bwagi
Description:
Handwritten notes on the history and character of Bwagi Ennze Panca, former sky pirate and member of the resistance group Lente's Tears.

Use to add to your field record.

Name: Field Notes on Mikoto
Description:
Handwritten notes on the history and character of the Archon Mikoto Jinba.

Use to add to your field record.

Name: Field Notes on Misija, Part II
Description:
Further handwritten notes on the history and character of the IVth's covert operative, Misija Votyasch.

Use to add to your field record.

Name: Field Notes on Gunnhildr, Part II
Description:
Further handwritten notes on the history and character of Gunnhildr, Queen of Bozja.

Use to add to your field record.

Name: Field Notes on the Trinity Seeker
Description:
Further handwritten notes on the history and character of those fated to become the trinity seeker.

Use to add to your field record.

Name: Field Notes on the Queen's Guard
Description:
Handwritten notes on the history and character of those fated to become members of the queen's guard.

Use to add to your field record.

Name: Field Notes on the Trinity Avowed
Description:
Further handwritten notes on the history and character of those fated to become the trinity avowed.

Use to add to your field record.

Name: Field Notes on Save the Queen
Description:
Handwritten notes on the history of the sacred blade, Save the Queen.

Use to add to your field record.

Name: Field Notes on Rostik
Description:
Handwritten notes on the history and character of the master of the gunblade, Rostik.

Use to add to your field record.

Name: Garlean Synthetic Fabric
Description: Material shorn from an imperial uniform proven to be exceedingly nonconductive to aether.

Name: Grilled Eel Set
Description:
An Eastern delicacy that fills stomachs as quickly as it empties coinpurses. Connoisseurs advise eating only the smallest amount at a time, so as to make it last as long as possible.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Direct Hit Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  VIT Bonus: +5% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Goobbue Lamp
Description: The elegance of the softly glowing fruit and beautiful verdant leaves is strangely juxtaposed by the gormless expression of the goobbue base.

Name: Dress Form
Description: Judging by its proportions, it appears to have been modeled after a Roegadyn woman, who have been rather in vogue as of late.

Name: Tankard
Description: Contains enough ale to drown at least a couple of sorrows.

Name: Emerald Weapon Bust
Description:
Includes six floating manipulators, all of which appear to be offering to take one's coat.

One per estate only.

Name: Stuffed Kupka Kupp
Description: So true to life it may very well be Kupka Kupp himself, albeit stuffed. You hope for his sake it is not.

Name: Unmelting Ice Partition
Description: One of the few furnishings that must rely on mystic energies simply to maintain structural integrity.

Name: Unmelting Ice Loft
Description: Though the ability to defy the laws of gravity and nature is certainly impressive, the best thing about this handy platform is that footprints can be made in the thin layer of snow on top. Go ahead, try it!

Name: Queen's Gunner Piece
Description: Can be strategically placed to deter burglars, providing that they are already inside the building at the time.

Name: Queen's Soldier Piece
Description: Though it appears to be some sort of mammet, it is entirely incapable of independent movement. Considering that it comes equipped with a potentially deadly blade, perhaps that is for the best.

Name: Shakshouka Pot
Description:
Of the many and varied ingredients that comprise this dish, it is the humble hen's egg that takes center stage.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Critical Hit Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  VIT Bonus: +5% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Stuffed Cait Sith
Description: Those expecting this stuffed creature to start shouting through a voice amplification device and riding a remarkably burly moogle may be disappointed.

Name: Antique Sink
Description: If by antique one means very old and likely to break at any moment, this sink has been accurately described.

Name: Spring Meadow Partition
Description: If one wishes to experience the joys of spring, this partition should be just the ticket. Alternatively, one could try stepping outside, assuming that it is currently the correct season.

Name: Ishgardian Stove
Description: Perhaps not quite as stable as one would like, considering that it is likely to contain burning coals and have a pot of boiling liquid balanced precariously on top.

Name: Extra-stuffed Carbuncle
Description: How much more stuffed could this be? The answer is none. None more stuffed.

Name: Carbuncle House Slippers
Description:
Don't get me wrong, I like Carbuncles. I just don't want them on my feet, that's all.
A bemused arcanist

Name: Iron Torch
Description: Give your home that authentic scary castle feel, but make sure the room is well ventilated to avoid smoke inhalation.

Name: Major-General Cushion
Description: It's a shark. With legs. And is also a cushion.

Name: Rose Trellis
Description: Keeps even the wildest of roses neatly organized.

Name: Dragon Icon
Description: One may struggle to fit a statue of a large golden dragon wrapped around an expensive-looking indigo orb into their existing dcor without spending large amounts of gil on suitably opulent furnishings to match.

Name: Royal Lion
Description: It may be best to consider this as half of a matching pair, as a single lion statue tends to look a bit lonely by itself.

Name: Swag Valance
Description:
This room has too much...wall. We should cover some of it in cloth.
Unknown furnishing connoisseur

Name: Rustic Chocobo Counter
Description: Bring the delights of a genuine chocobo stable to the inside of your home, complete with that unmistakable aroma.

Name: Wood Slat Partition
Description: Useful for when one wishes to block something from view while still being able to see it.

Name: Homemade Cookie Set
Description: This decorative ornament is ideal for giving guests the impression that one is an accomplished culinarian. Little will they know that the dough is in fact entirely inedible.

Name: Florist's Counter
Description: For some reason, the name flowermonger never quite caught on.

Name: Paissa Swing Chair
Description: For those who wish to be gently rocked by a hanging piece of furniture resembling the most terrifying creature in the known world.

Name: Showcase
Description: The lack of shelves makes this case ideally suited to displaying larger objects, unless one prefers to crouch while observing smaller ornaments.

Name: Shelving Showcase
Description: Ready to be filled with countless trophies, provided one is gifted enough to earn them in the first place.

Name: Elemental Wheel
Description: Depicts the intrinsic relationships between the six elements, which govern all life on this star, and probably a few other stars to boot.

Name: Toy Showcase
Description: It appears that stuffed animals have infested this showcase, which is normally reserved for more austere pieces of ornamentation.

Name: Apparel Showcase
Description: Some people like others to see their items of finery even when they are not being worn.

Name: Armament Showcase
Description: While such arms are largely displayed for heraldic purposes, they would still come in handy in a pinch.

Name: Art Showcase
Description: Provides fine pieces of art some degree of protection from the sticky hands of overly curious children.

Name: Baked Goods Showcase
Description: Though some people may be baffled by the idea of using pastries as ornaments, this display case is not for those people.

Name: The White Tiger
Description: Features the fearsome Byakko of Eastern legend. It seems he could leap from the canvas at any moment, and given his near-unlimited powers, he may do just that.

Name: Queen's Warrior Piece
Description: Guarding a queen is certainly not an easy job, but it does come with the unexpected perk of possibly being immortalized in the form of a household ornament.

Name: Queen's Knight Piece
Description: Though knights are known for standing their ground, their ability to remain steadfast is somewhat hindered by the three little wheels at the base, which all seem to want to roll off in a different direction.

Name: Season Seventeen Lone Wolf Trophy
Description: A trophy awarded to those who left their mark in Season Seventeen of the Feast.

Name: Toymaker's Show Window
Description: A perfect demonstration of one's toy-making abilities, or perhaps toy-buying abilities.

Name: Designer's Show Window
Description: Placing anything in a glass display case has the effect of making it appear expensive and luxurious, which many designers rely on to justify their ludicrously high prices.

Name: Smith's Show Window
Description: In case of emergency, smash glass and commence hacking and slashing.

Name: Artist's Show Window
Description: Though it is customary to charge for admission to art exhibitions, passersby can experience these works of fine art for free.

Name: Baker's Show Window
Description: When the sunlight hits the glass at the right angle, it has the effect of keeping the bread inside warm.

Name: Snow-dusted Tree
Description: Few realize the snow that rests on the boughs is in fact cake icing.

Name: Parkside Tree
Description: The parkside quality of this tree does depend rather heavily on its vicinity to a park.

Name: Brick Paving
Description: All these squares make a square.

Name: La Noscean Grape Pergola
Description: This wooden frame gives grape vines the means to climb to greater heights, in a quite literal sense.

Name: Fruitful Fountain
Description: Where most fountains would produce an upward-pointing spray of water, this one includes what experts call an arboreal protrusion.

Name: Herringbone Flooring
Description: Most herring would argue that their bones bear little resemblance to this flooring design.

Name: Skylight Chandelier
Description: This exquisite piece utilizes natural sunlight to provide illumination. How it continues to work at night, however, is a closely guarded secret.

Name: Varied Wood Interior Wall
Description: While the wooden pieces may appear to be randomly placed, there is method in the madness. Or possibly madness in the method.

Name: Small Florist's Walls
Description:
A set of four walls designed for those who wish to bedeck their home with an abundance of flowers. Allergy sufferers beware.

Can only be used with cottages on small plots of land.

Name: Medium Florist's Walls
Description:
A set of four walls designed for those who wish to bedeck their home with an abundance of flowersand be forever dusting the pollen from their deck chairs.

Can only be used with houses on medium plots of land.

Name: Large Florist's Walls
Description:
A set of four walls designed for those who wish to bedeck their home with an abundance of flowers. Note that certain flora are known to attract murderbees.

Can only be used with mansions on large plots of land.

Name: Edenmorn Leather Belt of Fending
Description: Before becoming obsolete due to advancements in tailoring, belts such as this were used for holding up trousers and the like.

Name: Edenmorn Leather Belt of Maiming
Description: Before becoming obsolete due to advancements in tailoring, belts such as this were used for holding up trousers and the like.

Name: Edenmorn Leather Belt of Striking
Description: Before becoming obsolete due to advancements in tailoring, belts such as this were used for holding up trousers and the like.

Name: Edenmorn Leather Belt of Aiming
Description: Before becoming obsolete due to advancements in tailoring, belts such as this were used for holding up trousers and the like.

Name: Edenmorn Leather Belt of Scouting
Description: Before becoming obsolete due to advancements in tailoring, belts such as this were used for holding up trousers and the like.

Name: Edenmorn Leather Belt of Healing
Description: Before becoming obsolete due to advancements in tailoring, belts such as this were used for holding up trousers and the like.

Name: Edenmorn Leather Belt of Casting

Carnation Seeds
Description:
Given the right conditions, these seeds will produce near endless amounts of beautiful carnations. Assuming that is, that the bag has been correctly labeled. If not, they may very well produce man-eating morbols...or worse.

For use in planters.

Name: Red Carnations
Description:
A bunch of red carnations, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Blue Carnations
Description:
A bunch of blue carnations, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Yellow Carnations
Description:
A bunch of yellow carnations, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Description:
A bunch of green carnations, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Name: Black Carnations
Description:
A bunch of black carnations, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Rainbow Carnations
Description:
A bunch of multicolored carnations, selectively fertilized to achieve a variety of vibrant colors.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Emerald Plating
Description: A hunk of verdant metal torn from the Emerald Weapon.

Name: Emerald Barding
Description: A suit of chocobo armor designed to resemble the Emerald Weapon.

Name: Queen's Guard Barding
Description: A suit of chocobo armor modeled after that worn by a legendary queen's personal guardwillingly and otherwise.

Name: Authentic Starlight Barding
Description: A suit of chocobo armor as worn by those legendary birds said to carry gifts from the stars. In fact, it was borrowed directly from one of the aforementioned legendary birds, making it as authentic as it can possibly be.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Concealing Meals
Description: An illustrated manual detailing how to best conceal Eastern foodstuffs about one's person in the likely event the hors d'oeuvres on offer are insufficient to sate one's hunger. Use to learn the /riceball emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Apples with Aplomb
Description: An illustrated manual of how to enjoy a delicious apple while projecting an air of unassailable dignity in spite of your squirrel-like gnawing. Use to learn the /eatapple emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Good Will Seeking
Description: An illustrated manual of how to bring oneself into the good graces of others. Use to learn the /wringhands emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Next, Godliness
Description: An illustrated manual detailing how to operate the quaint device known as a broom in event of dire circumstances involving the absence of one's servants. Use to learn the /broom emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Decadent Decoration
Description: An illustrated manual explaining the ideal method for painting over pesky or potentially haunted patterns in one's wallpaper. Use to learn the /paintblack, /paintred, /paintblue, and /paintyellow emotes.

Name: Forgotten Fragment of Contention
Description:
A single, unidentified memory of the lost.

Resistance rank required for appraisal: 15
Potential memories contained: Pure Essence of the Duelist, Lost Rend Armor

Name: Forgotten Fragment of Finesse
Description:
A single, unidentified memory of the lost.

Resistance rank required for appraisal: 15
Potential memories contained: Pure Essence of the Fiendhunter, Lost Dervish

Name: Forgotten Fragment of Fortitude
Description:
A single, unidentified memory of the lost.

Resistance rank required for appraisal: 15
Potential memories contained: Pure Essence of the Indomitable, Lost Aethershield

Name: Forgotten Fragment of Divinity
Description:
A single, unidentified memory of the lost.

Resistance rank required for appraisal: 15
Potential memories contained: Pure Essence of the Divine, Lost Seraph Strike

Name: Modern Aesthetics - Early to Rise
Description:
The realm's premier publication on beauty and fashion, this specific copy of Modern Aesthetics covers, in detail, techniques for weaving a simple-yet-elegant braid that can be employed by even those who are not yet fully awake.

Use to unlock a new hairstyle at the aesthetician.

Name: Modern Aesthetics - Sharlayan Studies
Description:
The realm's premier publication on beauty and fashion, this limited edition of Modern Aesthetics covers, in detail, techniques on transforming yourself into the prominentsome would say too prominentmember of the Scions of the Seventh Dawn, Alphinaud Leveilleur.

Use to unlock a new hairstyle at the aesthetician.
Unavailable to female Hrothgar.

Name: Snowman Bell
Description: For some reason, ringing this bell summons forth a behatted and begloved embodiment of festive cheer. With that in mind, it would be rather a shame not to ring it.

Name: Lunar Whale Identification Key
Description: A thin, rectangular piece of what appears to be cermet. Placing it near the Lunar Whale will grant you access to its voluminous belly, which is not nearly as awful as it may sound.

Name: Eden Crystal
Description: Raising this enigmatic gem aloft will summon forth a miniaturized version of the progenitor of all sin eaters, which may or may not be a good idea...

Name: Cerberus Horn
Description: This horn-carved instrument emits an ominous tone that calls forth a hellacious, three-headed beast.

Name: Big Shell Whistle
Description: This whistle emits a shrill tone that is said to summon a big shell, and presumably some sort of creature inside said shell.

Name: Arion Horn
Description: This undeniably divine horn emits a rumbling tone that calls a six-legged steed to your side. Any nearby farriers will be rubbing their hands with glee at the profits they stand to make.

Name: Emerald Gwiber Trumpet
Description: This horn-carved instrument emits an ethereal tone that beckons a gwiber clad in emerald scale from its refuge.

Name: Prototype Roader Identification Key
Description: A thin, rectangular piece of what appears to be cermet. Placing it near your prototype roader will bring it flailing and thrashing to life.

Name: Chocorpokkur Whistle
Description: This whistle emits a slightly saccharine tone that is said to summon a creature that defies description, other than the fact it is mostly comprised of chocolate.

Name: Gabriel Mark III Identification Key
Description: A thin, rectangular piece of what appears to be cermet. Placing it near your Gabriel Mark III will bring it to life.

Name: Much-coveted Mora
Description:
Few wavekin have ever been the object of so much anticipation, only to be followed by such crushing disappointment.

Use item to acquire the much-coveted Mora minion.

Name: Syldrion-class Insubmersible
Description:
Unlike the craft on which it is modeled, it will break immediately upon coming into contact with water.

Use item to acquire the Syldrion-class insubmersible minion.

Name: Wind-up Gaia
Description:
Those who think the hammer is just for show had best watch their toes.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Gaia minion.

Name: Wind-up Palom
Description:
Try not to break it.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Palom minion.

Name: Wind-up Porom
Description:
The rosy cheeks and pronounced eyelashes indicate that this is the female half of a matching pair.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Porom minion.

Name: Wind-up Edge
Description:
Based on one of the few people who had the chance to be a prince and a ninja, which seems like too much fun to squeeze into one lifetime.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Edge minion.

Name: Wind-up Rydia
Description:
Not to be confused with a sprig of broccoli.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Rydia minion.

Name: Wind-up Rosa
Description:
Based on the central corner of a one-sided love triangle, if such a thing is possible.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Rosa minion.

Name: Save the Princess
Description:
For every person who has ever dreamed of owning a wheeled, spindly legged, trumpet-blowing mammet, there is this wheeled, spindly legged, trumpet-blowing mammet.

Use item to acquire the Save the Princess minion.

Name: Drippy
Description:
With a will to wander the world, one wonders whether said world will welcome this well-meaning watery whelp.

Use item to acquire the Drippy minion.

Name: Trike
Description:
Very affectionate, but be prepared to make a quick sidestep if it comes running to greet you.

Use item to acquire the Trike minion.

Name: Golden Beaver
Description:
Remember: all that glitters is not gold. Sometimes, it is a beaver.

Use item to acquire the golden beaver minion.

Name: Magicked Prism (Bomb Head)
Description: This peculiar contraption creates illusions by weaving together myriad shades of light. Gives the impression that one's head is large, orange, and bulbous, which may be an improvement in some cases.

Name: Magicked Prism (Numeral 0)
Description: This peculiar contraption creates illusions by weaving together myriad shades of light. Causes a large O to appear in midair. Or is that an O?

Name: Magicked Prism (Numeral 1)
Description: This peculiar contraption creates illusions by weaving together myriad shades of light. Causes a large 1 to appear in midair.

Name: Magicked Prism (Numeral 2)
Description: This peculiar contraption creates illusions by weaving together myriad shades of light. Causes a large 2 to appear in midair.

Name: Magicked Prism (Numeral 3)
Description: This peculiar contraption creates illusions by weaving together myriad shades of light. Causes a large 3 to appear in midair.

Name: Magicked Prism (Numeral 4)
Description: This peculiar contraption creates illusions by weaving together myriad shades of light. Causes a large 4 to appear in midair.

Name: Magicked Prism (Numeral 5)
Description: This peculiar contraption creates illusions by weaving together myriad shades of light. Causes a large 5 to appear in midair.

Name: Mirage Gear Coffer (IL 400)
Description:
A banded chest containing a full set of mirage gear.

Required level: 70. IL: 400. Cannot be opened in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.

Name: Whalaqee Angel's Snack Totem
Description:
An intricately carved wooden totem imbued with the secrets of a potent healing technique.

Only for use by blue mages.

Name: Whalaqee Dragon Force Totem
Description:
An intricately carved wooden totem imbued with the secrets of a defensive technique.

Only for use by blue mages.

Name: Whalaqee Matra Magic Totem
Description:
An intricately carved wooden totem imbued with the secrets of a long-ranged offensive technique.

Only for use by blue mages.

Name: Heavensturn of the Tiger Ticket
Description: An ornamented piece of parchment recognizing services rendered to this year's bugyo.

Name: Painting of the New Nest
Description: A painting of the New Nest based off your own observations.

Name: Painting of Featherfall
Description: A painting of Featherfall based off your own observations.

Name: Painting of the Risensong Quarter
Description: A painting of the Risensong Quarter based off your own observations.

Name: Painting of the Firmament
Description: A painting of the Firmament based off your own observations.

Name: Grade 4 Skybuilders' Zagas Khaal
Description:
To Eorzeans, the name may seem rather exotic, but the fish itself is as plain as can be.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Grade 4 Skybuilders' Goldsmith Crab
Description:
Though it may be named for the deftness with which it uses its claws as tools to methodically dismantle its prey, perhaps butcher crab would be a more fitting appellation.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Grade 4 Skybuilders' Common Bitterling
Description:
Given the exacting standards of the skybuilders, the artisanal grade 4 variety of this species is anything but common.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Grade 4 Skybuilders' Skyloach
Description:
The ability to fly puts the skyloach rather higher in the hierarchy of wavekin than its water-bound brethren.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Grade 4 Skybuilders' Glacier Core
Description:
Despite being an entity of unknown origin and possessed of mysterious powers, it nevertheless has a habit of getting caught on fishers' hooks.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Grade 4 Skybuilders' Kissing Fish
Description:
Its kissing days are over.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Grade 4 Skybuilders' Cavalry Catfish
Description:
While this catfish mayaccording to the rumorsbe able to split a horse in two, perhaps the ability to cut through a fisher's line would have proved more useful.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Grade 4 Skybuilders' Manasail
Description:
Only when the manasail dips below its usual high altitude does it find itself within range of a fisher's line. This probably explains why they do not do it more often.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Grade 4 Skybuilders' Starflower
Description:
In the grand scheme of things, perhaps a flying mollusk is not so strange after all.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Grade 4 Skybuilders' Cyan Crab
Description:
It is common for creatures to be named for their color, but since blue crab was already taken, this species was granted somewhat more fanciful nomenclature.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Grade 4 Skybuilders' Fickle Krait
Description:
It seems the skybuilders seek this particular variety of snake for its deadly venom. Exactly why they require deadly venom is a question best left unanswered, but it is clandestine plots such as these that keep food tasters in work.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Grade 4 Skybuilders' Proto-hropken
Description:
These ferocious wavekin have a tendency to scare away more desirable fish. As such, the skybuilders seek to thin their numbers, preferably to zero.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Grade 4 Skybuilders' Ghost Faerie
Description:
While some wavekin are able to change their color to blend in with their surroundings, the ghost faerie takes this one step further by being almost entirely transparent. In a cruel twist of fate, this also makes it almost impossible for them to find a mate, which goes some way to explaining their scarcity.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Grade 4 Skybuilders' Ashfish
Description:
When it was first discovered, the ghostly coloration of this species led many to believe it was a waterborne ashkin. It was some time before anyone plucked up the courage to actually try eating one.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Grade 4 Skybuilders' Whitehorse
Description:
While it may not be a horse, it is white, so at least that part of its name is accurate.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Grade 4 Skybuilders' Ocean Cloud
Description:
Before it was first caught, fishers believed it to be a cloud drifting under the water's surface, despite the fact that would be next to impossible.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Grade 4 Skybuilders' Black Fanfish
Description:
This wavekin's dark coloration serves as camouflage in the ocean depths, but the effect is lost if it ventures into shallower waters. There is also the fact that its internal organs will rupture due to the changes in water pressure, as if any further discouragement were needed.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Grade 4 Skybuilders' Sunfish
Description:
The legends speak of the sunfish aiding those stranded at sea to shore by letting them ride on its back. The skybuilders have decided to return the favor by catching and eating it.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Grade 4 Artisanal Skybuilders' Sweatfish
Description:
Said to have been created from the beads of sweat that gathered on the Dawn Father and Dusk Mother's foreheads, the unfortunate name has made these delicious little fish rather difficult to sell.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Grade 4 Artisanal Skybuilders' Sculptor
Description:
The sculptor's sawlike rostrum is often placed next to the meat of the fish for identification purposes at market.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Grade 4 Artisanal Skybuilders' Little Thalaos
Description:
Though this wavekin is unaware that it was named after the beast of legend, it certainly seems to relish playing the part.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Grade 4 Artisanal Skybuilders' Lightning Chaser
Description:
Like its brethren the storm chaser, this fish uses gas expelled from its rectum as a crude means of propulsion. As its name would suggest, it spends much of its time chasing lightning bolts, though with little success due to the ludicrously slow pace at which it moves.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Grade 4 Artisanal Skybuilders' Marrella
Description:
The heavily armored protrusions that extend from what is presumably its head seem to be entirely at odds with the fact its innards are completely exposed. Some might consider this species to be an evolutionary dead end, yet it continues to survive to this day.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Grade 4 Artisanal Skybuilders' Crimson Namitaro
Description:
Experts believe its enormous dorsal fin is used to repel creatures that enter its territory. This is also the part that often gets caught on a fisher's hook, so perhaps it is more of a hindrance than a help.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Grade 4 Artisanal Skybuilders' Griffin
Description:
One would be forgiven for assuming the skybuilders were only joking when they requested a griffin be brought to them. Unfortunatelyand inexplicablythey were deadly serious.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Grade 4 Artisanal Skybuilders' Meganeura
Description:
Practically anything with mega in its name is bound to be big, and this overgrown dragonfly is no exception.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Approved Grade 4 Skybuilders' Zagas Khaal
Description:
To Eorzeans, the name may seem rather exotic, but the fish itself is as plain as can be.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Approved Grade 4 Skybuilders' Goldsmith Crab
Description:

Name: Approved Grade 4 Skybuilders' Black Fanfish
Description:
This wavekin's dark coloration serves as camouflage in the ocean depths, but the effect is lost if it ventures into shallower waters. There is also the fact that its internal organs will rupture due to the changes in water pressure, as if any further discouragement were needed.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Approved Grade 4 Skybuilders' Sunfish
Description:
The legends speak of the sunfish aiding those stranded at sea to shore by letting them ride on its back. The skybuilders have decided to return the favor by catching and eating it.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Approved Grade 4 Artisanal Skybuilders' Sweatfish
Description:
Said to have been created from the beads of sweat that gathered on the Dawn Father and Dusk Mother's foreheads, the unfortunate name has made these delicious little fish rather difficult to sell.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Approved Grade 4 Artisanal Skybuilders' Sculptor
Description:
The sculptor's sawlike rostrum is often placed next to the meat of the fish for identification purposes at market.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Approved Grade 4 Artisanal Skybuilders' Little Thalaos
Description:
Though this wavekin is unaware that it was named after the beast of legend, it certainly seems to relish playing the part.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Approved Grade 4 Artisanal Skybuilders' Lightning Chaser
Description:
Like its brethren the storm chaser, this fish uses gas expelled from its rectum as a crude means of propulsion. As its name would suggest, it spends much of its time chasing lightning bolts, though with little success due to the ludicrously slow pace at which it moves.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Approved Grade 4 Artisanal Skybuilders' Marrella
Description:
The heavily armored protrusions that extend from what is presumably its head seem to be entirely at odds with the fact its innards are completely exposed. Some might consider this species to be an evolutionary dead end, yet it continues to survive to this day.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Approved Grade 4 Artisanal Skybuilders' Crimson Namitaro
Description:
Experts believe its enormous dorsal fin is used to repel creatures that enter its territory. This is also the part that often gets caught on a fisher's hook, so perhaps it is more of a hindrance than a help.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Approved Grade 4 Artisanal Skybuilders' Griffin
Description:
One would be forgiven for assuming the skybuilders were only joking when they requested a griffin be brought to them. Unfortunatelyand inexplicablythey were deadly serious.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Approved Grade 4 Artisanal Skybuilders' Meganeura
Description:
Practically anything with mega in its name is bound to be big, and this overgrown dragonfly is no exception.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Silver Beech Lumber
Description: Processed silver beech lumber.

Name: Duraluminum Ingot
Description: An ingot of smelted duraluminum.

Name: Solstice Ingot
Description: A large block of solid crystal, ready to be chiseled into whatever form the craftsman desires.

Name: Saffron Cloth
Description: Finely woven cloth dyed a vibrant orange with gardenia fruit, rather than the expensive spice after which the color was named.

Name: Thylacoleo Leather
Description: A large piece of cured thylacoleo skin.

Name: Grade 4 Strength Alkahest
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this experimental alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to strength, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Grade 4 Dexterity Alkahest
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this experimental alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to dexterity, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Grade 4 Vitality Alkahest
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this experimental alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to vitality, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Grade 4 Intelligence Alkahest
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this experimental alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to intelligence, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Grade 4 Mind Alkahest
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this experimental alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to mind, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Horsetail
Description: A robust grass resembling a horse's tail, often used as an abrasive.

Name: Aluminum Ore
Description: A sizable piece of rock containing traces of the metal aluminum.

Name: Workbench Refining Sand
Description: This all-in-one abrasive, created for craftsmen of all disciplinesand even some with no discipline whatsoevercan be used to both sand metals and polish them to a lustrous sheen.

Name: Gardenia Fruit
Description: Originating in the Far East, the fruit may be dried and used to dye cloth.

Name: Thylacoleo Skin
Description: The hide of the thylacoleoa primitive beastkin predator.

Name: Spirit Extract
Description: The condensed aether of a once-living being. The essence of its essence, so to speak.

Name: Silver Beech Log
Description: A rough-cut log of silver beech timber.

Name: Dolomite
Description: A semi-translucent rock containing the rare mineral dolomite.

Name: Solstice Stone
Description: A mysterious crystal of purest white.

Name: Raindrop Cotton Boll
Description: The cotton produced by this particular species is said to be as delicate to the touch as a raindrop. Unfortunately, this makes it rather difficult to pick without crushing the boll.

Name: Wattle Petribark
Description: Though this bark has a number of uses, being in an apparently semi-fossilized state does make it somewhat troublesome to work with.

Name: Hard Water
Description: To the layman, hard water may sound like a convoluted way to say ice, but experts would disagree. In any case, it is at least soft enough to be poured into and out of a bottle.

Name: Loathsome Memory of the Dying
Description: The loathsome memory of a departed soul, forever trapped in crystal.

Name: Haunting Memory of the Dying
Description: The haunting memory of a departed soul, forever trapped in crystal.

Name: Vexatious Memory of the Dying
Description: The vexatious memory of a departed soul, forever trapped in crystal.

Name: Timeworn Artifact
Description: The delicate carving on this ancient artifact belies its pre-excavation position amidst so much midden.

Name: Aetherial Sealant
Description: A compound whose primary ingredient, aetherial siltstone, was said to have been used to fashion crystal foci in ancient Bozja.

Name: Authentic Starlight Celebration MMXVIII Advertisement
Description: A commissioned painting which depicts the Starlight Celebration choir and their delighted audience. It is so authentic that snow was used instead of white paint, although this soon melted, revealing the white canvas below.

Name: Authentic Starlight Roll Cake
Description:
Two cream-filled sponge cakes complete with strawberries on top. While it may not be the most obvious choice for a festive treat, the color scheme certainly conjures up images of the Starlight Celebration. The authenticity extends to the cream inside, which contains actual snow, although this does dilute the flavor somewhat.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Piety Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  VIT Bonus: +5% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Authentic Starlight Goobbue Wreath
Description: A stuffed goobbue sits within a festive wreath, its mouth agape, ready to devour your soul. It is so authentic that the makers claim it is made from genuine goobbue pieces, although it is probably best not to dwell on exactly what that entails.

Name: Authentic Heavensturn Bounty
Description: A traditional Heavensturn decoration meant to beckon fortune through its depiction of a traditional bumper crop of rice, traditionally infested by mice. In addition to the stuffed mouse included, it also attracts living mice, which some may find to be a nuisance, but it nevertheless adds to the overall authenticity of the piece.

Name: Authentic Chocolate Fountain
Description:
Complete with a range of fruit and other sweet treats. Just try not to get any chocolate on the upholstery. While the creators claim that the parts pertaining to the fountain itself are entirely authentic, they make no such claims regarding the chocolate, which raises concerns as to what it actually is.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Determination Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  VIT Bonus: +5% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Authentic Eastern Stage
Description: The festivities never need come to an end with this stage adorned with peach blossoms. While the exterior is considered to be entirely authentic, the same cannot be said for the interior, but as the saying goes, It's what's on the outside that counts.

Name: Authentic Little Ladies' Day Banner
Description: A princess needs no crown when this banner exists to always remind them how special they are. The feelings of undeniable specialness areaccording to the makers, at leastrather authentic.

Name: Authentic Stuffed Rabbit
Description: This rabbit looks as if he walked straight out of a storybook, and is prepared to keep on walking. (Please contact authorities immediately in the event that the toy actually demonstrates ambulatory capabilities.) Although the makers claim it to be extremely authentic, when it comes to stuffed animals, perhaps the less authentic, the better.

Name: Authentic Hatching-tide MMXVIII Advertisement
Description: A cheerful hand-painted notice proclaiming the eggcellence of Hatching-tide. The feelings of guilt one eggsperiences when making egg-based puns in the vicinity of this poster are eggstremely authentic.

Name: Rarefied Pyrite
Description:
Though widely disparaged as fool's gold, there are certain obsessive miners who would trade sacks of genuine precious metal for this glorious hunk of iron and sulphur.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Chalcocite
Description:
If you can't recognize the beauty inherent in its orthorhombic crystal system, then we can't be friends.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Limonite
Description:
Artistic collectors will swoon over the lustrous ochre pigment that can be produced from this seemingly unremarkable rock of iron ore.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Abalathian Spring Water
Description:
Vanu shamans collect spring water to make the paste they apply to their beaks before rituals. Some Vanu shamans are very, very particular about their spring water.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Aurum Regis Sand
Description:
When the aether of one's opus must flow unimpeded, one cannot skimp on the conductive component of one's ink.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Raw Triphane
Description:
The potential value of this uncut stone is obvious to the practiced eye. Especially if you love yellow.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Raw Star Spinel
Description:
Rubies are red. Sapphires are blue. Star spinels are more of a violet, though, and that's the hue glinting from within this promising stone.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Raw Kyanite
Description:
If I can cut this just so, it will provide the perfect accent for a rather rakish turban I've been weaving...

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Raw Azurite
Description:
Be sure to don your swimming trunks before losing yourself in the deep, deep blue of this entrancing raw gemstone.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Silvergrace Ore
Description:
It's beautiful! Stunning! Magnificent! Now find me three more.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Titancopper Ore
Description:
Never has titanium and copper existed in a more harmonious blend of minerals. It promises to make a wonderful teapot.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Raw Lazurite
Description:
One day, this unfinished gemstone of clearest blue could grace an elegant ring or an exquisite necklace or a face-smashing fist weapon. Possibilities!

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Raw Petalite
Description:
Not quite clear and not quite white, you're not quite sure why the jewel hiding in this rock is so valuable.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Sea Salt
Description:
Don't you dare throw that over your shoulder. Here, use the table salt.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Reef Rock
Description:
They say reef rock has been procured for restoration projects in a certain snowbound city. Perhaps this perfectly porous piece is destined for a structure of holey importance.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Raw Onyx
Description:
Even in its rough, natural form, the shimmering blackness of this jewel is almost dangerously captivating. So...pretty...

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Tungsten Ore
Description:
A truly precious find for one invested in the finest facets of tungsten-based fabrication.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Gyr Abanian Alumen
Description:
Well, tan my hide! You must have spent weeks in the mountains of Eastern Aldenard looking for this stuff. 

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Mythrite Sand
Description:
Unconfirmed rumors tell of an eccentric Lalafell with plans to use these glowing grains to build a private beach. She'll probably need a few more handfuls...

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Gyr Abanian Mineral Water
Description:
Should probably be saved for the concoction of valuable reisui, but it does make for a tasty cup of buckwheat tea.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Bluespirit Ore
Description:
If this mineral was any aether-richer, it would have to pay taxes.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Manasilver Sand
Description:
The customer requesting this liquid-like sand was oddly specific about the number of grains in the handful.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Dark Chestnut Sap
Description:
Rather than experiment with amusing applications for this superior sticky substance, it's perhaps best to relinquish it to a tree sap professional.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Dark Chestnut Log
Description:
Gazing upon this rough-cut log, you cannot help but wonder if its lustrous lumber is destined for a valiant knight's lance or a bilge-bottomed buccaneer's bar stool. Anyone's guess, really.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Dark Chestnut Branch
Description:
Aye, 'twould make a fine sentinel's longbow. But see, I have this prior commission to craft a fishing rod. N-No, that's not my penmanship!

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Dark Chestnut
Description:
A champion among chestnuts, predestined for the summit of a Sohm Al tart.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Dark Chestnut Resin
Description:
The viscous lifeblood you extracted from a vigorous yet defenseless chestnut tree. You monster.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Larch Log
Description:
You wonder if the fact that larch log is fun to say has anything to do with its inherent collectability.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Shiitake Mushroom
Description:
Only the finest fungi are foraged for fancy Far Eastern feast tables.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Larch Sap
Description:
Larch...sap. No, not nearly so fun to say as larch log but apparently just as collectable.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Pine Resin
Description:
Unsurprisingly, this exceptionally gooey mass is a prime ingredient in certain beetle-based adhesives.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Pine Log
Description:
Almost unnaturally straight and true, this log will hopefully be processed into lumber for a future masterpiece of carpentry...and not thrown into some chilly lordling's fireplace.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Pixie Apple
Description:
One bite of this almost unbearably sweet fruit will have you flitting about like a pollen-drunk pixie.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied White Oak Log
Description:
A difficult material to work with, any artisan would nevertheless be eager to craft an enduring handle or lasting piece of furniture from this marvelous hunk of hardwood.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Miracle Apple Log
Description:
The real miracle here is that any of these trees were left standing after a sudden and inexplicable surge in the demand for applewood staves.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Sandteak Log
Description:
After being carved and then covered with exquisitely woven wool, this attractive lump of timber could serve as the elegant display stand for some staggeringly expensiveand rarely wornneckwear.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Kelp
Description:
Yes, an oriental breakfast is generally a simple affair, but that doesn't mean one should settle for any old seaweed in the sea.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Amber Cloves
Description:
Once dried and enshrined in a sturdy jar, these flavorsome flower buds will take pride of place on a master chef's spice shelf.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Coral
Description:
This is it! The perfect piece of coral to complement my perfect coral butterfly. My aquarium is complete!

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Urunday Log
Description:
Compared to your average cut of timber, the quality of this log is the difference between urunight and urunday.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Rainbow Cotton Boll
Description:
Is it gold? Is it blue? Or mayhap green? Folk will spend all day arguing over the color of a dress made from these prismatic cotton fibers.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Bloodhemp
Description:
Either this is the bloodiest bloodhemp you've ever harvested, or some small vermin with terrible situational awareness came between the plant and your scythe.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Bright Flax
Description:
This incredibly hardy plant specimen is able to thrive under almost any conditions...except one populated by single-minded botanists.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Night Pepper
Description:
Guaranteed to make you sneeze. Just...aim it away from the cooking pot.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Calf Leather
Description: A large piece of cured calf hide.

Name: Pleasant Dot Parasol
Description: Should the weather prove so inclement, the skies so heavy with rain, that one is forced to rely upon a parasol, can it truly be called pleasant? (Yes. Just look at the name.) Use to acquire a pleasant dot parasol.

Name: Prim Dot Parasol
Description: Whether or not this parasol could be considered prim rather depends on the person holding it at the time. Use to acquire a prim dot parasol.

Name: Pastoral Dot Parasol
Description: It could be argued that any parasol could be made to appear pastoral if set against a suitably bucolic background. Use to acquire a pastoral dot parasol.

Name: Gold Parasaucer
Description: Nothing exudes an air of both wealth and whimsy as perfectly as a parasol decorated with stars and sabotenders, or so its creators convinced themselves when conjuring up this madcap design. Use to acquire a gold parasaucer.

Name: Angel Wings
Description: Perhaps a little too realistic. It would be wise to look out for a newly wingless angel seeking revenge. Use to acquire a pair of angel wings.

Name: Brand-new Alphinaud's Attire
Description: Cannot equip with arm, leg, or foot gear.

Description:
A banded chest containing a complete set of millfiend's costume attire.
