Name: Cashmere Attire Coffer
Description:
A banded chest containing a complete set of cashmere attire.

Required level: 1. IL: 1.

Name: Casual Attire Coffer
Description:
A banded chest containing a complete set of casual attire.

Required level: 1. IL: 1.

Name: Construct VI-S Core
Description: The golem summoned by this core is painted red so it goes faster. Painting the core itself red, however, does not appear to offer any discernible benefit.

Name: Humic Soil
Description: A carefully prepared blend of soil and decaying leaves.

Name: Pot Marjoram
Description: An aromatic herb used in various dishes and remedies.

Name: Water Mint
Description: A versatile herb that grows easily in moist soil.

Name: Wild Sage
Description: A fragrant herb popular with culinarians...and their customers.

Name: Countess Tea Leaves
Description: Once consumed exclusively by the upper classes but now available to the hoi polloi.

Name: Dacite
Description: A solid piece of cooled lava, its burning fury in a dormant state.

Name: Rhodolite
Description: A particularly radiant uncut gemstone.

Name: Obsolete Resplendent Carpenter's Component A
Description: The arboreal aroma is admired by accomplished artisans and aspiring aficionados alike. The techniques for creating resplendent tools with this material are sadly out of fashion, making it completely useless to any self-respecting artisan.

Name: Obsolete Resplendent Blacksmith's Component A
Description: A glowing golden globule. The techniques for creating resplendent tools with this material are sadly out of fashion, making it completely useless to any self-respecting artisan.

Name: Obsolete Resplendent Armorer's Component A
Description: Far simpler in design than its extravagant name would suggest. The techniques for creating resplendent tools with this material are sadly out of fashion, making it completely useless to any self-respecting artisan.

Name: Obsolete Resplendent Goldsmith's Component A
Description: Soapy bubbles in block form. The techniques for creating resplendent tools with this material are sadly out of fashion, making it completely useless to any self-respecting artisan.

Name: Obsolete Resplendent Leatherworker's Component A
Description: The skin of a blue animal. Maybe. The techniques for creating resplendent tools with this material are sadly out of fashion, making it completely useless to any self-respecting artisan.

Name: Obsolete Resplendent Weaver's Component A
Description: Only an engineer would refer to a length of thread as a component. The techniques for creating resplendent tools with this material are sadly out of fashion, making it completely useless to any self-respecting artisan.

Name: Obsolete Resplendent Alchemist's Component A
Description: Of all the liquids found in alchemy, this is one of the least suitably named. The techniques for creating resplendent tools with this material are sadly out of fashion, making it completely useless to any self-respecting artisan.

Name: Obsolete Resplendent Culinarian's Component A
Description: A curious little box that is tangentially related to the culinary arts, or so the Boutique of Splendors would have you believe. The techniques for creating resplendent tools with this material are sadly out of fashion, making it completely useless to any self-respecting artisan.

Name: Obsolete Resplendent Carpenter's Component B
Description: Like a flute but without the holes. The techniques for creating resplendent tools with this material are sadly out of fashion, making it completely useless to any self-respecting artisan.

Name: Obsolete Resplendent Blacksmith's Component B
Description: Can be used in place of legal tender, provided the phrase It's that or nothing! is uttered with enough conviction. The techniques for creating resplendent tools with this material are sadly out of fashion, making it completely useless to any self-respecting artisan.

Name: Obsolete Resplendent Armorer's Component B
Description: The term cock-a-hoop originates from a game in which competitors throw objects such as these over the neck of a male chicken. The techniques for creating resplendent tools with this material are sadly out of fashion, making it completely useless to any self-respecting artisan.

Name: Obsolete Resplendent Goldsmith's Component B
Description: Not only are such objects said to be found on the dark side of the moon, they are available in any color you like. The techniques for creating resplendent tools with this material are sadly out of fashion, making it completely useless to any self-respecting artisan.

Name: Obsolete Resplendent Leatherworker's Component B
Description: A not-so-neatly folded sheet of beast skin. The techniques for creating resplendent tools with this material are sadly out of fashion, making it completely useless to any self-respecting artisan.

Name: Obsolete Resplendent Weaver's Component B
Description: While not exactly as resplendent as the name would suggest, it is at least clean. The techniques for creating resplendent tools with this material are sadly out of fashion, making it completely useless to any self-respecting artisan.

Name: Obsolete Resplendent Alchemist's Component B
Description: One of the few substances in alchemy that is as light as it is heavy. The techniques for creating resplendent tools with this material are sadly out of fashion, making it completely useless to any self-respecting artisan.

Name: Obsolete Resplendent Culinarian's Component B
Description: This mustard is known as Eulmore's hottest yellow paste. The techniques for creating resplendent tools with this material are sadly out of fashion, making it completely useless to any self-respecting artisan.

Name: Obsolete Resplendent Carpenter's Component C
Description: A hardened lump of the crimson sap known as tree blood. The techniques for creating resplendent tools with this material are sadly out of fashion, making it completely useless to any self-respecting artisan.

Name: Obsolete Resplendent Blacksmith's Component C
Description: Just another cog in the machine. Or at least it will be once the rest of the machine has been built around it. The techniques for creating resplendent tools with this material are sadly out of fashion, making it completely useless to any self-respecting artisan.

Name: Obsolete Resplendent Armorer's Component C
Description: Most armorer's tools do not incorporate sheets of chainmail, but try telling the Boutique of Splendors that. The techniques for creating resplendent tools with this material are sadly out of fashion, making it completely useless to any self-respecting artisan.

Name: Obsolete Resplendent Goldsmith's Component C
Description: It is not yet known whether this resplendent orb will become the centerpiece in a fine item of jewelry or ground down into dust for a far less glamorous purpose. The techniques for creating resplendent tools with this material are sadly out of fashion, making it completely useless to any self-respecting artisan.

Name: Obsolete Resplendent Leatherworker's Component C
Description: While this incredibly long strap is an impressive example of leatherworking, calling it resplendent may be something of an exaggeration. The techniques for creating resplendent tools with this material are sadly out of fashion, making it completely useless to any self-respecting artisan.

Name: Obsolete Resplendent Weaver's Component C
Description: A bolt of cloth this luxurious surely warrants a better name. The techniques for creating resplendent tools with this material are sadly out of fashion, making it completely useless to any self-respecting artisan.

Name: Obsolete Resplendent Alchemist's Component C
Description: A handful of carbon rods. One for each finger, in fact. The techniques for creating resplendent tools with this material are sadly out of fashion, making it completely useless to any self-respecting artisan.

Name: Obsolete Resplendent Culinarian's Component C
Description: A small vial of unnamed gloopy stuff. The techniques for creating resplendent tools with this material are sadly out of fashion, making it completely useless to any self-respecting artisan.

Name: Resplendent Carpenter's Material A
Description: A sealed package containing carpenter's materials, most likely wood or something vaguely tree-related, at the very least.

Name: Resplendent Blacksmith's Material A
Description: A crate that makes a dull clanking sound when shaken.

Name: Resplendent Armorer's Material A
Description: This box of armorer's supplies is about as heavy as one might expect. The question is: which will give out first, the bottom of the crate or the carrier's back?

Name: Resplendent Goldsmith's Material A
Description: The clinking sound coming from within is suspiciously similar to that of broken glass. This does not bode well.

Name: Resplendent Leatherworker's Material A
Description: A bundle of leather wrapped in leather, bound with a leather strap.

Name: Resplendent Weaver's Material A
Description: Take care when delving into this sack as there are probably needles inside.

Name: Resplendent Alchemist's Material A
Description: The life of an alchemist tends to be something of a mixed bag, much like the manner in which their supplies are delivered.

Name: Resplendent Culinarian's Material A
Description: The strange way in which the package is twitching indicates the freshness of the ingredients inside, if one takes fresh to mean still alive.

Name: Resplendent Carpenter's Material B
Description: Though it is not entirely clear what is inside this potor indeed, what it is forthe members of the Boutique of Splendors trust your ability to work that out for yourself.

Name: Resplendent Blacksmith's Material B
Description: While blacksmiths tend to specialize in smashing hot bits of metal with a hammer, they are not averse to employing little pots of mysterious gunk from time to time.

Name: Resplendent Armorer's Material B
Description: Presumably the oily substance within is used to reduce scraping between the various pieces of metal, or perhaps for the armorer to smear onto their brow to stop sweat from running into their eyes.

Name: Resplendent Goldsmith's Material B
Description: While the final product may indeed turn out to be resplendent, this murky paste is anything but.

Name: Resplendent Leatherworker's Material B
Description: Quite where this unidentified substance fits into the leatherworker's grand schemes is anyone's guess.

Name: Resplendent Weaver's Material B
Description: According to the Boutique of Splendors, this oily substance can be applied to a weaver's needle to help it glide through the fabric with the greatest of ease. In fairness, the needle never had any trouble doing that in the first place, but perhaps it is best not to question the Boutique's methods.

Name: Resplendent Alchemist's Material B
Description: As with many materials used by alchemists, the recommended use for this substance is, Throw a good dollop into the mixture and see what happens.

Name: Resplendent Culinarian's Material B
Description: It is said of this viscous paste that a spoonful a day keeps the chirurgeon away, though that may be largely because of the smell.

Name: Resplendent Carpenter's Material C
Description: Said to contain kittens' tears.

Name: Resplendent Blacksmith's Material C
Description: Said to contain a child's laughter.

Name: Resplendent Armorer's Material C
Description: Said to contain the sound of one hand clapping.

Name: Resplendent Goldsmith's Material C
Description: Said to contain the breath of a thousand sighs.

Name: Resplendent Leatherworker's Material C
Description: Said to contain the Spirit of Starlight Past.

Name: Resplendent Weaver's Material C
Description: Said to contain wishes unfulfilled.

Name: Resplendent Alchemist's Material C
Description: Said to contain the sound of a heart breaking.

Name: Resplendent Culinarian's Material C
Description: Said to contain the scent of a summer meadow.

Name: Resplendent Carpenter's Final Material
Description: A resplendent golden pot filled with caustic grey slime.

Name: Resplendent Blacksmith's Final Material
Description: A resplendent golden pot filled with putrid ooze.

Name: Resplendent Armorer's Final Material
Description: A resplendent golden pot filled with halitosis in liquid form.

Name: Resplendent Goldsmith's Final Material
Description: A resplendent golden pot filled with murderous intent trapped in jelly.

Name: Resplendent Leatherworker's Final Material
Description: A resplendent golden pot filled with every nightmare you have ever had condensed into a soothing balm.

Name: Resplendent Weaver's Final Material
Description: A resplendent golden pot filled with lingering regret.

Name: Resplendent Alchemist's Final Material
Description: A resplendent golden pot filled with the echo of a bloodcurdling scream.

Name: Resplendent Culinarian's Final Material
Description: A resplendent golden pot filled with frozen fire.

Name: Landerwaffe Flute
Description: Appearing to operate by way of an elaborate mechanism, this mysterious flute emits a shrill sound that summons forth Landerwaffe, mechanical dragon of legend.

Name: Dravanian Scallop
Description:
Found in shallow water, this species of scallop is identifiable by its rugged, cream-colored shell.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Cloud Kelp
Description:
Found growing in the Sea of Clouds, this variety of kelp is known for its disinfecting properties.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Scarlet Frog
Description:
Native to Gyr Abania, this frog possesses a poison that induces mild paralysis in those predators that fail to heed its telltale hue.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: White Clam
Description:
Boasting a beautiful, pearlescent shell, this small Far Eastern clam is popularly used for decorative purposes.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Fragrant Sweetfish
Description:
Hailing from the Azim Steppe, this variety of sweetfish has taken to consuming water herbs that imbue its flesh with a tantalizing fragrance.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Patient Necessities
Description: From bars of soap to dining utensils, the patients of Ser Vaindreau's Grace have need of myriad items during their stay.

Name: Medical Supplies
Description: An infirmary without medical supplies is no infirmary at all.

Name: Rehabilitation Aids
Description: No few patients of Ser Vaindreau's Grace suffer from debilitating injuries, and rehabilitation aids are needed to help them recover and regain independence.

Name: High Tea Essentials
Description: Tea is good and high tea is better. With this assortment of items, the infirmary will be able to host an event the patients will remember.

Name: Art Supplies
Description: Painting is at once relaxing and rehabilitative, and these art supplies will do much good for the patients of Ser Vaindreau's Grace.

Name: Patient Necessity Materials
Description: Cleanliness being paramount, the infirmary can never have too many items such as soapnor the materials with which they are made.

Name: Medical Supply Materials
Description: Being a medical facility, Ser Vaindreau's Grace ever has need ofyou guessed itmedical supplies, and these materials are suitable for crafting them.

Name: Rehabilitation Aid Materials
Description: These strong and sturdy materials should make strong and sturdy rehabilitation aids for the patients of Ser Vaindreau's Grace.

Name: High Tea Ingredients
Description: No high tea is complete without scrumptious sweets, and the ingredients needed in their creation, such as syrups, never go astray.

Name: Art Supply Materials
Description: If art is like salve for the soul, then these materials are the ingredients for said salve.

Name: Patient Necessity Components
Description: An assortment of components suitable for crafting daily necessities for the use of the patients of Ser Vaindreau's Grace.

Name: Medical Supply Components
Description: An assortment of components suitable for crafting medical supplies for the treatment of the patients of Ser Vaindreau's Grace.

Name: Rehabilitation Aid Components
Description: An assortment of components suitable for crafting rehabilitation equipment for the use of the patients of Ser Vaindreau's Grace.

Name: High Tea Components
Description: An assortment of components suitable for crafting items required for hosting high tea at Ser Vaindreau's Grace.

Name: Art Supply Components
Description: An assortment of components suitable for crafting art supplies for the enjoyment of the patients of Ser Vaindreau's Grace.

Name: Listracanthus
Description:
Those fortunate enough to have seen this primitive species of shark patrolling the waters near the Isle of Ken are invariably puzzled by its flowing mane, which seems to serve no practical purpose whatsoever.

[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Aquamaton
Description:
Those hoping to catch their dinner in Seagazer Shoals are in for a shock if they reel in one of these strange, dwarven contraptions. Apparently, they fetch a high price at market, assuming one can find a buyer.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Cinder Surprise
Description:
These bizarre, steaming-hot creatures inhabit the River of Sand, and on rare occasions, find themselves on anglers' hooks. Said anglers are normally bemused by such an apparently inedible catch, but when desperately searching for sustenance in the arid desert, one takes what one can find.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Ealad Skaan
Description:
Very rarely caught in Longmirror Lake, the fisher is invariably struck by pangs of guilt at having sunk their hook into such a charming, delicate creature.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Greater Serpent of Ronka
Description:
Fishers who succeed in reeling this enigmatic beast in from the waters of Lake Tusi Mek'ta will almost certainly come to regret it. Whether that is due to its supposed likeness to a particular mythological, godlike creature, or simply because of its unnerving appearance depends entirely on the fisher.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Lancetfish
Description:
Those fishing the waters of the northwest Caliban Gorge are advised that, if they attempt to handle this bellicose wavekin, they should avoid the pointy bits. Many will attest, however, that as practically the entire fish fits that description, it is best to simply give it as wide a berth as possible.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 4 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Small Forge's Walls
Description:
A set of four walls designed for those who wish to transform their estate into a forge.

Can only be used with cottages on small plots of land.

Name: Medium Forge's Walls
Description:
A set of four walls designed for those who wish to transform their estate into a forge.

Can only be used with houses on medium plots of land.

Name: Large Forge's Walls
Description:
A set of four walls designed for those who wish to transform their estate into a forge.

Can only be used with mansions on large plots of land.

Name: Storm Blue Interior Wall
Description: A blue interior wall for those estate owners who wish to make a simple statement.

Name: Cream Yellow Carpet
Description: Durable-yet-fuzzy loop carpet in a cozy cream yellow.

Name: Cloud Acorn Chandelier
Description: Quaint does not begin to describe this chandelier made with cloud acorns still hanging on the branch.

Name: Cactuar Stool
Description: A stool designed in the likeness of a cactuar. Perfect for those guests whom you don't want getting too comfortable.

Name: Cactuar Round Table
Description: A round table designed in the likeness of a cactuar. Perfect for those guests whom you don't want getting too comfortable.

Name: Diamond Weapon Bust
Description:
Arguably more shoulders than bust, but undeniably menacing in either case.

One per estate only.

Name: Queen's Rest
Description: A monument fashioned in the likeness of the holy blade Save the Queen, as sealed in its binding stone.

Name: Hatching-tide Confections
Description:
A delightful set of bite-sized morsels of baked chocolate fashioned to resemble spriggans.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Determination Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  VIT Bonus: +5% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Grilled Corn
Description:
Sweet millioncorn on the cob, basted with authentic Hingan soy sauce and broiled over an open flame.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Critical Hit Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  VIT Bonus: +5% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Stuffed Peerifool
Description: This stuffed Peerifool is so true to life, you can almost smell the cloying stench.

Name: Eastern Indoor Pond
Description: Constructed in the Eastern fashion, this pond is hemmed in natural stone and comes with carp swimming gracefully.

Name: Grocery Counter Cart
Description: A mobile kitchen counter designed in the likeness of a wagon, laden with a selection of breads and fresh produce.

Name: Azim Steppe Phasmascape
Description: This advanced magitek contraption displays the wide, sweeping landscape of the Azim Steppe in vivid detail.

Name: Blue Moon Phasmascape
Description: This advanced magitek contraption displays a full moon hanging majestically in the night sky.

Name: Stuffed Android Units
Description: As they stood together as comrades, it is only fitting that 2B and 9S stand together as stuffed toys.

Name: Wooden Reel Table
Description: Formerly used to carry ropes and cables, this wooden reel has been repurposed as a table.

Name: Violin Showcase
Description: A wooden cabinet custom-made for displaying violins. Comes complete with instruments.

Name: Aetherolectric Guitar
Description: This instrument, quickly adopted by minstrels and now beloved across Hydaelyn, represents the best that musical magitek has to offer.

Name: Pub Signboard
Description: When it comes to indicating the presence of a pub, nary a word is needed.

Name: Windowed Partition
Description: Extending to the ceiling, this partition incorporates a wide rectangular window.

Name: Hingan Windowed Partition
Description: Extending to the ceiling, this partition incorporates a round Hingan-style window.

Name: Mushroom Lamp
Description: Grown from a ball of moss, this luminescent mushroom gives off a gentle light.

Name: Sealed Letter
Description: While the contents are a mystery, whoever reads this letter is certain to regret it for the rest of their days.

Name: Wooden Spiral Staircase
Description: Spiral staircases are ideal for situations where there is insufficient space for conventional stairs.

Name: Approved Ishgardian Lunch
Description:
Tasty and wholesome, this lunch set is said to be a favorite among skybuilders.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Control Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  VIT Bonus: +5% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Country Dining Set
Description: Enjoy the bucolic life with this wooden dining set for four, finished with a checkered tablecloth.

Name: Akadaemia Prospectuses
Description: This collection of brochures provides detailed information to prospective students of the Akadaemia Anyder.

Name: Icebox
Description: Rather than with magic or magitek, this wooden box keeps its contents chilled the old-fashioned waywith a large block of ice.

Name: Red Brick Counter
Description: For years, academics have sought to explain why such counters of brick and timber enhance the flavor of liquor. Thus far, they have little to show for their research except ferocious hangovers.

Name: Necrologos Transcription
Description: While appearing to be gibberish, the words written within this tome fiendishly incorporate a summoning spell. Readers are advised to exercise caution lest they inadvertently unleash an army of voidsent.

Name: Hand-poured Coffee
Description:
Aromatic coffee brewed by the time-honored pour-over method.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Perception Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  VIT Bonus: +5% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Back Bar
Description: A tall wooden shelf commonly used in taverns to store and display liquor.

Name: Pixie Apple Basket
Description:
A basket of pixie apples and a bottle of grape juice, perfect as a palate cleanser or simply a snack.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Piety Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  VIT Bonus: +5% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Philosopher's Stone Table
Description: A round table of polished stone with a tree growing at its center, all of which is said to be conducive to enlightened debate.

Name: Crystarium Wardrobe
Description: A simple-yet-elegant wardrobe designed in the Crystarium style, complete with an array of outfits.

Name: Low Bookshelf
Description: A low, wide bookshelf featuring both open and closed compartments.

Name: Qiqirn Shelf
Description: Designed in a Qiqirn motif, this wooden shelf is as charming as it is practical.

Name: Mogbureau
Description: A writing table with storage designed in a moogle motif. Do not attempt to remove the pom-pom.

Name: Bar Rack
Description: A wooden rack for holding a selection of drinks and glasses. Hanging the glasses upside down prevents dust from gathering inside while avoiding chips to the rims.

Name: Portrait of Gestahl
Description: A beautiful rendering of a sweet little dog who somehow exudes the air of a tyrannical emperor. But look at how adorable he is!

Name: Pepperoni Pizza Set
Description:
A freshly baked pizza delivered to your door in less than half a bell or your order is free!
Offer not valid for orders made during an Umbral Calamity.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Direct Hit Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  VIT Bonus: +5% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Archon Egg Pouch
Description: A compact, stylish pouch with a strap to be slung over the shoulder, designed with an egg motif perfect for the Hatching-tide season.

Name: Costa del Hielo
Description:
A delicious chilled dessert created by the confectioner Nekeke, this icy treat is both refreshing and easy on the waistline, as it largely consists of frozen water.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Skill Speed Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  VIT Bonus: +5% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Goobbue Wall Chronometer
Description: A wall chronometer designed in a goobbue motif, a dazed look upon the creature's face.

Name: Armor Hanger
Description: Originally designed for ceremonial purposes for those of the Elezen persuasion, the attachments on the side of the helm allow it to be worn without bending the ears out of shape.

Name: Mounted Dinosaur Skull
Description: In a case of the hunter becoming the hunted, the cranium of this ferocious predator is now doomed to spend eternity in ignominy mounted as a trophy on an adventurer's wall. Its headless body must be rolling in its grave.

Name: Plot of Hydrangeas
Description: Lush hydrangea bushes with flowers blooming in all their vibrant glory.

Name: Glade Gazebo
Description: A gazebo designed in the glade fashion.

Name: Garden Tool Shelf
Description: A wooden shelf used for storing gardening implements.

Name: Eastern Wisteria
Description: A tree native to the Far East that produces hanging clusters of light-purple flowers, pruned to fit in a garden.

Name: Moonfire Mask Stall
Description: A stall with an assortment of colorful masks on display, as seen during the Moonfire Faire festivities.

Name: Forging Bench
Description: An outdoor furnishing perfect for those who prefer to do their smithing out in the open. After all, attempting to do so in an enclosed space does come with the rather bothersome side effects brought on by smoke inhalation.

Name: Garden Anvil
Description: Best placed outdoors, as it tends to leave rather an undesirable impression on all but the most durable of floors.

Name: Materiel Table
Description: An outdoor furnishing including an assortment of arms and armor. Ideal for those situations where one finds oneself uttering, Choose your weapon, to an unruly houseguest.

Name: Fte Party Balloons
Description: Seen adorning the Firmament during the Skyrise Celebration, this colorful bunch of balloons is guaranteed to fill the air with festive cheer.

Name: Fte Skyrise Balloon
Description: Seen adorning the Firmament during the Skyrise Celebration, this oversized balloon set upon an elegant mount brings a touch of sophistication to any festive occasion.

Name: Authentic Sultana's Seven
Description: A faithful recreation of the stained glass artwork that adorned the main stage at Ul'dah's Rising festival. The historic moment when Nanamo Ul Namo and her seven most trusted followers confronted a baying crowd and restored peace to the city is captured in all its glory. Those present at the time of the event have described the determined expressions to be particularly authentic. For aesthetic reasons, however, the artist has wisely chosen not to include the angry mob.

Name: Authentic Water Bomb Stand
Description: Bring home this hallmark of the Moonfire Faire and pelt passersby with aquatic surprises from the comfort of your very own front garden! The exasperation experienced by your victims is especially authentic.

Name: Moth Orchid Seeds
Description:
Disagreement over whether these seeds thrive best in sunlight or lamplight has ended many a friendship between botanist and naturalist.

For use in planters.

Name: Red Moth Orchids
Description:
A bunch of red moth orchids, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Blue Moth Orchids
Description:
A bunch of blue moth orchids, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Yellow Moth Orchids
Description:
A bunch of yellow moth orchids, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Green Moth Orchids
Description:
A bunch of green moth orchids, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Orange Moth Orchids
Description:
A bunch of orange moth orchids, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Purple Moth Orchids
Description:
A bunch of purple moth orchids, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: White Moth Orchids
Description:
A bunch of white moth orchids, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Black Moth Orchids
Description:
A bunch of black moth orchids, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Rainbow Moth Orchids
Description:
A bunch of multicolored moth orchids, selectively fertilized to achieve a variety of vibrant colors.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Aster Trivi
Description:
A king among asteroidea, and lord of the waters of the Trivium.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Python Discus
Description:
A king among snakeskin discus, and lord of the waters of Sullen.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Steel Razor
Description:
A king among razorfish, and lord of the waters off the western Kholusian coast.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Shadeshifter
Description:
A king among shapeshifters, and lord of the waters of Seagazer Shoals.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Nabaath Saw
Description:
A king among desert saws, and lord of the sands of the Nabaath Severance.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Dammroen Herring
Description:
A queen among cherry herring, and the lady of the waters of the Spoiled One.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Celestial
Description:
A king among toadheads, and humbled lord of the waters of Father Collard's Failings.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Deephaunt
Description:
A king among darkdwellers, and lord of the waters of Woven Oath.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Golden Pipira
Description:
A queen among yellow pipira, and the lady of the waters of Mjrl's Tears.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Mora Tecta
Description:
A king among hoodwinkers, and lord of the waters of northwest Caliban Gorge.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Maru Crab
Description:
A king among yeti crabs, and lord of the waters of west Caliban Gap.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: G-Warrior MG
Description: A dynamic tabletop statue based on Garlond Ironworks' G-Warrior. The aethersaber emits sufficient light to be used as a bedside reading lamp, but be warned that touching it may result in severed appendages. The MG part of its name supposedly stands for Master Garlond, or something along those lines.

Name: Ostensibly Special Timeworn Map
Description:
This bottle is holding what appears to be an especially valuable leather map.

Use the action Decipher to extract the map and examine its contents.
Level 80 full party (eight players) recommended.
Guaranteed to summon a teleportation portal.

Name: Irregular Tomestone of Pageantry
Description:
One of only a few in existence, this Allagan tomestone contains knowledge of festivities for all manner of occasions, and even some created purely for sudden outbursts of inexplicable merriment.

Can be exchanged with itinerant moogles for certain items.

Name: Irregular Tomestone of Lore
Description:
One of only a few in existence, this Allagan tomestone contains knowledge of various events both probable and improbable, intertwining historical fact and flights of fancy to simultaneously amuse and confuse the reader.

Can be exchanged with itinerant moogles for certain items.

Name: Special Archon Egg
Description: An eggsquisite ornamental ovoid perfect for handing out during the Hatching-tide festivities.

Name: Chicken Suit
Description: Cannot equip with arm, leg, or foot gear.

Name: Bozjan Barding
Description: A suit of chocobo armor typical of those used by the Bozjan Resistance.

Name: Diamond Barding
Description: A suit of chocobo armor designed to resemble the Diamond Weapon.

Name: Antelope Doe Horn
Description: A small and slender horn that, when blown, will bring your antelope doe springing to your side.

Name: Antelope Stag Horn
Description: A large and elongated horn that, when blown, will bring your antelope stag springing to your side.

Name: Al-iklil Identification Key
Description: A thin, rectangular piece of what appears to be cermet. Placing it near your Al-iklil will magically bring the machine to life.

Name: Cruise Chaser Identification Key
Description: A thin, rectangular piece of what appears to be cermet. Placing it near your Cruise Chaser will magically bring the machine to life.

Name: Island Mandragora
Description: With just a single exposure to the sunlight outside of your bag, this island mandragora shall be primed to bear you forth like the most cacophonous of steeds.

Name: Island Onion Prince
Description: With just a single exposure to the sunlight outside of your bag, this island Onion Prince shall be primed to bear you forth like the most flavorful of steeds.

Name: Island Eggplant Knight
Description: With just a single exposure to the sunlight outside of your bag, this island Eggplant Knight shall be primed to bear you forth like the purplest of steeds.

Name: Island Garlic Jester
Description: With just a single exposure to the sunlight outside of your bag, this island Garlic Jester shall be primed to bear you forth like the most pungent of steeds.

Name: Island Tomato King
Description: With just a single exposure to the sunlight outside of your bag, this island Tomato King shall be primed to bear you forth like the juiciest of steeds.

Name: Island Mandragora Queen
Description: With just a single exposure to the sunlight outside of your bag, this island Mandragora Queen shall be primed to bear you forth like the noblest of steeds.

Name: Deinonychus Horn
Description: This horn of bone emits a primitive sound that summons forth your deinonychus to outwit your prey.

Name: Diamond Gwiber Trumpet
Description: This horn-carved instrument emits an ethereal tone that beckons a gwiber clad in diamantine scale from its refuge.

Name: Polar Bear Horn
Description: Though cold to the touch, this horn emits a heartwarming sound that summons your polar bear, all without needing to resort to using its favorite sweets.

Name: Gilded Mikoshi Flute
Description: The trill of this fin-carved flute will summon a squad of gilded Namazu to bear you upon a gilded mikoshiall of which is as gaudy as it sounds.

Name: Golden Ronkan Flute
Description: This whistle emits a sublime tone that summons forth the Resplendent Vessel of Ronka, pre-filled with divinity, majestic and blinding, for your worshipping convenience.

Name: Magicked Card
Description: Crafted by the realm's foremost goldsmith, this enchanted ridable Triple Triad card will take you wonder by wonder, over, sideways, and under.

Name: Gull
Description:
Has a keen eye for finding schools of fishand unguarded meals.

Use item to acquire the gull minion.

Name: Anteater
Description:
Definitely not a man-eater, otherwise that's what it would be called...right?

Use item to acquire the anteater minion.

Name: Dolphin Calf
Description:
Has more intelligence in a single winsome flipper than you do in your whole body.

Use item to acquire the dolphin calf minion.

Name: Magitek Predator F1
Description:
Comes complete with pilot and stands ready to wreak havoc among the enemy's ranks.

Use item to acquire the magitek predator F1 minion.

Name: Senorita Sabotender
Description:
Like a thousand adorable needles piercing your eyeballs.

Use item to acquire the Senorita Sabotender minion.

Name: Benben Stone
Description:
For when you need the top stone of a pyramid scampering around after you.

Use item to acquire the Benben stone minion.

Name: Wanderer's Campfire
Description:
Perfect for driving away the darkness and the chill and, most importantly, toasting marshmallows.

Use item to acquire the wanderer's campfire minion.

Name: Smaller Stubby
Description:
A little rusted but still fit for purpose...whatever that may be.

Use item to acquire the smaller stubby minion.

Name: Wind-up Lyna
Description:
Don't forget to salute, or you're liable to receive a dressing-down.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Lyna minion.

Name: Wind-up Runar
Description:
Because a single Runar pining for Master Matoya isn't enough.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Runar minion.

Name: Wind-up Gunnhildr
Description:
Protects her people as a queen, a god, and now a mammet.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Gunnhildr minion.

Name: 9S Automaton
Description:
For when you need the company of a compact version of an advanced combat android dressed in a distinctive subculture style.

Use item to acquire the 9S automaton minion.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Impromptu Performance
Description: An illustrated manual of how to perform an incredibly elaborate, albeit silent, routine to distract your fellow guestsfor good or ill. Use to learn the /pantomime emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Displaying Displeasure
Description: An illustrated manual of how to project an air of frustration so vivid as to make the emotion itself visible to the naked eye. Use to learn the /vexed emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Pizza & Prejudice
Description: An illustrated manual of how to stay true to your heart despite society's pretensions. Use to learn the /eatpizza emote.

Name: Modern Aesthetics - Both Ways
Description:
The realm's premier publication on beauty and fashion, this specific copy of Modern Aesthetics covers, in detail, a hair styling technique which marries a braid and a side ponytail in an exquisite union.

Use to unlock a new hairstyle at the aesthetician.

Name: Modern Aesthetics - Battle-ready Bobs
Description:
The realm's premier publication on beauty and fashion, this specific copy of Modern Aesthetics covers, in detail, techniques for shaping an uncannily perfect boblike that of your android acquaintance 2B.

Use to unlock a new hairstyle at the aesthetician.

Name: Modern Aesthetics - Scanning for Style
Description:
The realm's premier publication on beauty and fashion, this specific copy of Modern Aesthetics covers, in detail, techniques for attaining an uncannily effortless looklike that of your android acquaintance 9S.

Use to unlock a new hairstyle at the aesthetician.

Name: Magicked Prism (Namazu)
Description: This peculiar contraption creates illusions by weaving together myriad shades of light. Releases a floating Namazu head, complete with gormless expression.

Name: Nymeia Potpourri
Description: Made from the alchemically treated petals of Nymeia lilies, this fragrant bundle of potpourri brings a sense of tranquility to even the most troubled souls.

Name: Red Moon Parasol
Description: This elegant parasol features an image of a flaming moon, which seems strangely familiar... Use to acquire a red moon parasol.

Name: Fat Cat Parasol
Description: A charming parasol that's perfect for lounging about in the sun after filling your belly to bursting. Use to acquire a fat cat parasol.

Name: Great Paraserpent
Description: So lifelike that it appears about to let forth a mighty scree! at any moment. Use to acquire a great paraserpent.

Name: Faire Voucher
Description: Currency minted and distributed by the Adventurers' Guild for use during the Moonfire Faire.

Name: A Day in the Life: Battles for the Realm
Description: A hero's recollections of battles supposedly fought in the name of freedom. In actuality, said battles were largely motivated by a burning desire to obtain a slightly better weapon through a rather lengthy and complex sequence of transactions.

Name: A Day in the Life: Beyond the Rift
Description: A hero's recollections of foes felled in another plane of existence. The tales contained within are so fantastical that one would be forgiven for thinking they were merely figments of said hero's imagination. Or perhaps they were?

Name: Bleak Memory of the Dying
Description: The bleak memory of a departed soul, forever trapped in crystal.

Name: Lurid Memory of the Dying

Name: Raw Emotion
Description: Pure emotional energy, seemingly crystallized for the sole purpose of making it easier to carry. Even so, keeping too many of these about one's person will lead to excessive emotional baggage.

Name: Ancient Bone
Description: Discovered in the ocean depths, it bears the marks of having the flesh stripped from the bone by wavekin.

Name: Rusted Suit of Armor
Description: Found half-submerged in the sand of the seabed, one cannot but wonder what fate befell its previous owner.

Name: Damaged Icebox
Description: Salvaged from the ocean floor, the ice and foodstuffs once held inside are long since gone. It can be surmised that it was the property of a wealthy seafarer with a penchant for chilled refreshments.

Name: Bozjan Southern Front Riding Map
Description: A highly detailed map of the Bozjan southern front, including all the recent topographical information such as the position of craters left by explosions and so forth.

Name: Zadnor Riding Map
Description: A highly detailed map of Zadnor, which supposedly shows the correct positions of the many levitating rock formations, despite their tendency to float about a fair bit.

(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Use to instantly complete all main scenario quests up through Death Unto Dawn. Cannot be used outside large settlements. Can be used for any Disciple of War or Magic, excluding limited jobs. Automatic logout will commence upon usage.

Season Twenty Lone Wolf Trophy
Description: A trophy awarded to those who left their mark in Season Twenty of the Feast.

Name: Orchestrion Phonograph
Description:
A tabletop furnishing with a trumpetesque funnel designed to spread sweet melodies around a given space.

One orchestrion of any type per estate only.

Name: Shoe Rack
Description: A stack of shelves suited for storing shoes.

Name: Ivy Mural
Description: A plant-patterned wall adornment for those who wish to bring a taste of the outside in.

Name: Table Mat
Description: A place setting that protects pristine dining surfaces from the grimy undersides of your plates.

Name: Matching Cushions
Description: A pair of fluffy pillows that support not only your neck and shoulders, but each other as well.

Name: Marimba
Description: A mallet-sounded instrument with an intricate design so beautiful as to rival its woody timbre.

Name: Indoor Oriental Waterfall
Description: A fabulous water feature that will bless any space with a touch of Far Eastern flair.

Name: Round Wooden Loft
Description: A circular platform for all of your platforming needs.

Name: Heavenly Ornamental Array
Description: A string of celestial lights for those who wish to gaze upon the night sky without craning their necks upward.

Name: Woodland Chair
Description: A seat that was lost in the woods, never to be reunited with its original owner.

Name: Apothecary's Workbench
Description: A wooden workspace filled with enough tonics and tinctures to make one's fire burn and cauldron bubble.

Name: Candlelit Sundries
Description: This trio of potted plant, letter frame, and waxen candle makes for the most charming fire hazard you'll see today.

Name: Fat Cat Rug
Description: A carpet almost as cozy as the fluffy familiar that inspired it.

Name: Walnut Flower Vases
Description: A stable set of wooden stands, each adorned with a brightly colored blossom.

Name: Fluffy Pancakes
Description:
A two-tiered treat served with butter, powdered sugar, and a side of maple syrup.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Determination Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  VIT Bonus: +5% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Stuffed Bom Boko
Description: A plush toy modeled after a raccoon dog pup honing its transformative skills.

Name: Wooden Blinds
Description: A set of wooden slats designed to keep interiors dim and idle hands a-dusting.

Name: Dance Pole
Description: Even seasoned adventurers may find that sensually swiveling upon this pole proves a challenge to their balance and brawn alike.

Name: Antique Wall Shelf
Description: A wooden shelf with a somewhat artificial antique appearance. After all, who can afford the real thing?

Name: Wooden Bin
Description: A container assembled from materials not much greater in quality than the waste that fills it.

Name: Imitation Wooden Skylight
Description: A ceiling fixture for those who prefer their sunlight simulated.

Name: Square Niche Partition
Description: There are two types of people: those who use this divider as storage space for cubic containers, and those who spend their time pretending to be a haunted portrait.

Name: Pendant Wall Light
Description: A chain-strung lamp whose diminutive glow prioritizes fashion over function.

Name: Loft Bed
Description: A bed-over-desk set for authors whose solution to writer's block is sleeping on it.

Name: Restaurant Showcase
Description: A cabinet filled with eerily realistic recreations of various dishes.

Name: Ruby Sea Phasmascape
Description: This advanced magitek contraption displays a dazzling sunset over the water betwixt Othard and Hingashi.

Name: Aurora Phasmascape
Description: This advanced magitek contraption displays Coerthan snowfields beautifully illuminated by the northern lights.

Name: Il Mheg Garden Fountain
Description: A petit water feature inspired by the land of the pixies.

Name: Hanging Bench
Description: A seat strung from a sturdy branch and securely fastened so to assuage any safety concerns.

Name: Coldbare Tree
Description: A plant bereft of its foliage and thus ill-fit to fend off the elements.

Name: Poroggo Lawn Ornament
Description: An adorable little waterwheel adorned with an even cuter amphibian familiar.

Name: Miniature Antique Clock Tower
Description: An outdoor clock that will always tell you the timeso long as you keep it wound.

Name: Shirogane Pinwheel
Description: A tiny spinning toy that is quite popular among Hingan children.

Name: Gold Plating
Description: Plating required to repair Rurusha's mysterious relic.

Name: Gold Cog
Description: A cog required to repair Rurusha's mysterious relic.

Name: Gold Motor Component
Description: A component required to repair Rurusha's mysterious relic.

Name: Gold Mechanical Voice Box
Description: A component required to repair Rurusha's mysterious relic.

Name: Starlens Brace
Description: Required to support the starlens.

Name: Aetherial Lens
Description: Allows the starlens to capture aetherial flickers.

Name: Aetherial Amplifier
Description: Allows one to channel enough magic to operate the starlens.

Name: Aetherial Conductor
Description: Allows one to project the aether captured by the starlens onto water.

Name: Panaloaf Sweetener
Description: This sweet concoction is designed to bind together the disparate flavors of the foul-tasting panaloaf.

Name: Panaloaf Yeast
Description: This special yeast should greatly improve the powdery texture of panaloaf.

Name: Panaloaf Oil
Description: This fragrant oil will infuse freshly baked panaloaf with a delicious, savory aroma.

Name: Ascorbic Additive
Description: Extracted from coconut milk, this additive has been meticulously crafted to elevate the Mervynbread's ascorbic acid content to acceptable levels.

Name: Hannish Staple
Description: A must-have for anyone looking to recreate Hannish culture.

Name: Garlean Staple
Description: A must-have for anyone looking to recreate Garlean culture.

Name: Lunar Staple
Description: A must-have for anyone looking to recreate lunar culture.

Name: Elpis Staple
Description: A must-have for anyone looking to recreate the culture of Elpis.

Name: Giant Aetherlouse
Description:
A crustacean that is never far from an underwater aether current.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Garjana Wrasse
Description:
A tropical fish that emits low amounts of aether and travels as part of a school. 

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Garlean Clam
Description:
A clam commonly found in Garlemald.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Smaragdos
Description:
An ancient fish with a green body.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Description:

Can hold up to 200 furnishing items.
Small plot of land required.

Description:
A simple stable designed in the Coerthan highland style.

Cannot be retrieved once placed.
One per estate only.

Name: Master Carpenter IX
Description: This esoteric tomethe ninth in an equally esoteric seriescontains advanced woodworking recipes that can only be learned by esoterically skilled carpenters.

Name: Master Blacksmith IX
Description: This esoteric tomethe ninth in an equally esoteric seriescontains advanced smithing recipes that can only be learned by esoterically skilled blacksmiths.

Name: Master Armorer IX

Name: Master Alchemist IX

Name: Master Culinarian IX
Description: This esoteric tomethe ninth in an equally esoteric seriescontains advanced cooking recipes that can only be learned by esoterically skilled culinarians.

Name: Rarefied Horse Chestnut Kasa
Description:
Tired of carrying around an umbrella due to a chance of rain? Put this on your head instead and save yourself the trouble!

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Palm Bracelet
Description:
Each one of these accessories comes with a gemstone that is, as one might surmise, not made of palm.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Red Pine Spinning Wheel
Description:
If this wheel keeps on turning and the red pine smells like burning, you're probably spinning it too fast.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Ironwood Grinding Wheel
Description:
Not especially suitable when you have a bone to pick with someone, but the ideal implement when you have an axe to grind.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Integral Armillae
Description:
Little is known about the trees from which these integral accessories are made, but that air of mystery adds to the appeal.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied High Durium Pistol
Description:
This firearm eschews function for fashion, covering the cylinder with an ostentatious metal plate.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied High Durium Greatsword
Description:
Some blade wielders believe a weapon of this caliber would be more accurately dubbed an excellentsword, but it's a tad cumbersome as far as names go.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Bismuth Sledgehammer
Description:
This tool wants to be your sledgehammer; why don't you call its name?

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Manganese Cross-pein Hammer
Description:
Whoever decided cross would be a more easily understood substitute for perpendicular really hit the nail on the head.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Chondrite Culinary Knife
Description:
One could use this utensil outside of the kitchen, but conventional wisdom advises against bringing a culinary knife to a gunlance fight.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied High Durium Knuckles
Description:
Some say one punch from these is all it takes to fell any foe, but only when wielded by expert pugilists.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied High Durium Kite Shield
Description:
Great for defending the wielder against incoming enemy attacks; not quite as great for flying on a windy day.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Bismuth Fat Cat Frypan
Description:
Though this pan may be feline shaped, using it to fry a fat cat would be morally unacceptable.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Manganese Armor of the Behemoth King
Description:
Perfect for edgy adventurers who want to show off their hunting prowess without sacrificing their dark and brooding image.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Chondrite Sollerets
Description:
One can quite literally never go chond-wrong with a pair of these leg guards.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied High Durium Milpreves
Description:
A word of sage advice: never cross someone with an array of these in their possession.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Pewter Choker
Description:
Do not let the name intimidate you: this accessory actually sits quite comfortably around the wearer's neck.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Phrygian Earring
Description:
This syringe-shaped accessory is sure to inject one's ensemble with a touch of avant-garde style.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Manganese Horn of the Last Unicorn
Description:
Watch where you point this thing: you might poke an eye outor worse!

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Star Quartz Choker
Description:
Some say you can make a wish upon the gem embedded within this accessorywhich is technically truebut there is no guarantee it will be granted.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Gajaskin Shoes
Description:
These shoes made of gaja leather feature distinct flared collars that prioritize fashion over functionbut they sure look neat!

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Luncheon Toadskin Hose
Description:
Some dislike the bumpy texture of these stockings, but comfort is in the legs of the beholder...or however the saying goes.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Saigaskin Gloves
Description:
These hand coverings are made from the tanned hide of the snow-loving saiga. What they lack in coverage, they make up for in style.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Kumbhiraskin Shoes
Description:
A durable pair of white footwear. Though slightly hidden behind the laces, the bright-red tongue adds some visual contrast.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Ophiotauroskin Top
Description:
This vest features a fastener across the chest becauseas all style savants knowone can never have too many belts.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Darkhempen Hat
Description:
A charcoal black cap that offers excellent coverage for the top of one's head but little for anything below the brow. 

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Almasty Serge Gloves
Description:
These fluffy handwarmers ensure the wearer never gets frostbitten, but their black coloration means one must always be wary of potential staining.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Snow Linen Doublet
Description:
Though dubbed the doublet, this garment performs not only two functions, but several: it offers warmth, creates a striking silhouette, supports the wearer's hose, and so forth.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Scarlet Moko Wedge Cap
Description:
A neatly fitted hat with a crimson fabric lining that gives rise to the question, Why is the inside not the outside? and other such philosophical ruminations.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied AR-Caean Velvet Bottoms
Description:
Made from AR-Caean cotton, these trousers are softer to the touch than most, providing the wearer with extra lower-body comfort.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Gajaskin Codex
Description:
Collecting gaja tusks is generally frowned upon, but poaching gaja for their pelts is apparently fair game.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Luncheon Toadskin Grimoire
Description:
Contrary to what its name might suggest, this book is actually bound with leather made from a Sharlayan toad.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Moon Gel
Description:
This supremely sticky adhesive is said to be strong enough to withstand the pull of an interstellar vacuumwhich makes sense, given its place of origin.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Enchanted Manganese Ink
Description:
Infused with manganese ore, this reagent boasts impressive aetherial conductivity.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Draught
Description:
This delightful drink was distilled from the finest ingredients to help struggling craftsfolk get their creative juices flowing.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Archon Loaf
Description:
Diners can set their hearts at rest: no sages were harmed in the making of this bread.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied King Crab Cake
Description:
It is unclear which is kingthis cake or the crab from which it was madebut it tastes like royalty either way.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Happiness Juice
Description:
Although this drink's name suggests a joyful experience for all who imbibe it, the only folks who will find true happiness in this bottle are those who really like carrots.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Giant Haddock Dip
Description:
An ideal alternative for those particularly picky eaters who can't stand the sight of seafood but don't mind the taste.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Giant Popoto Pancakes
Description:
One stack of these delectable discs is sure to fill any adventurer's belly and satisfy their sweet tooth.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Horse Chestnut Weapon Coffer (IL 515)
Description:
A wooden chest containing a weapon, one whose size possibly exceeds the dimensions of its container.

Required level: 80. IL: 515. Weapon type determined by current job or class at time of opening. Cannot be opened in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.

Name: Horse Chestnut Ring Coffer (IL 515)

Required level: 80. IL: 515. Ring type determined by current job or class at time of opening. Cannot be opened in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.

Name: Pewter Weapon Coffer (IL 525)

Name: Triteleia Seeds
Description:
The triteleia is also known as the triplet lilyas the various parts of the flower come in threescare has been taken to ensure the number of seeds is divisible by three, so as not to ruin the pattern. After all, three is the mandatory number, as the saying probably goes.

For use in planters.

Name: Red Triteleia
Description:
A bunch of red triteleia, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Blue Triteleia
Description:
A bunch of blue triteleia, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Yellow Triteleia
Description:
A bunch of yellow triteleia, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Green Triteleia
Description:
A bunch of green triteleia, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Name: Orange Triteleia
Description:
A bunch of orange triteleia, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Name: Purple Triteleia
Description:
A bunch of purple triteleia, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Name: White Triteleia
Description:
A bunch of white triteleia, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Black Triteleia
Description:
A bunch of black triteleia, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Rainbow Triteleia
Description:
A bunch of multicolored triteleia, selectively fertilized to achieve a variety of vibrant colors.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Crystal of Eternal Darkness
Description: Brighten up your home with this charming tribute to the god of Darkness.

Name: Crystal of Divine Light
Description: Includes a unique serial number and certificate of authenticity supposedly signed by Hydaelyn Herself.

Name: Trophy of Eternal Darkness
Description:
An ideal conversation piece and focal point for clandestine rituals. Though it does not possess any arcane properties, it certainly looks the part.

One per estate only.

Name: Trophy of Divine Light
Description:
A somewhat abstract imagining of the god of Light. Perhaps it is best to give it a wide berth to avoid snagging one's clothingand eyeson the featherlike projections.

One per estate only.

Name: New World Burrito Lunch
Description:
One of many delicious dishes invented by inhabitants of the New World, this lunch stars a well-seasoned assortment of beans, vegetables, and meats wrapped in soft tortillas.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Piety Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  VIT Bonus: +5% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Hannish Silk Rack
Description: Even in their furled state, these silks bring a splash of color to any abode. Their weavers, however, would insist that they are rather more decorative when unfurled.

Name: Ancient Lamp
Description: An implausibly accurate recreation of the lamps used in the ancient world.

Name: Labyrinthos Warning Sign
Description: While there are many similarly designed placards, this particular example reads, Trespassers will be given a stern talking-to.

Name: Etheirys Globe
Description: Previous designs were much flatter.

Name: Nekropolis Table
Description: Anyone who doubts that furniture can be scary has obviously never seen this table.

Name: Pumpkin Flower Vase
Description: What does one call a gourd capable of supporting plant life? A gourden.

Name: Starlight Mobile
Description: This decoration remains in perpetual motion even when no wind is present, possibly as the result of some as-yet-undiscovered Ascian machination.

Name: Thavnairian Striking Dummy
Description:
A striking dummy designed in the Thavnairian fashion.

Up to three dummies may be placed in a single estate, regardless of type.

Name: Garlean Containers
Description: Give your home all the warmth and comfort of a Garlean military installation with this assortment of delightful metallic crates.

Name: Sharlayan Lamppost
Description: Hast thou ever licked a lamppost in winter?

Name: Thavnairian Dhow
Description: Nothing impresses the neighbors quite like a massive boat on one's lawn.

Name: Haunted Pumpkin Set
Description: Quite why ghosts would wish to haunt an assortment of prize gourds is anyone's guess. Perhaps they are the vengeful spirits of runners-up in a vegetable-growing contest?

Name: Garlean Concrete Inner Wall
Description: A cold, stark interior wall for those who fear their home is becoming a little too cozy.

Name: Varied Wood Flooring
Description: This style of flooring is also known as carpenters' leftovers.

Name: Leafy Ceiling Lamp
Description: Ceiling-mounted lighting designed to resemble a ceiling-mounted, glowing bush.

Name: Small Cafe Walls
Description:
A set of four walls designed for those who wish to transform their estate into a caf.

Can only be used with cottages on small plots of land.

Name: Medium Cafe Walls
Description:
A set of four walls designed for those who wish to transform their estate into a caf.

Can only be used with cottages on medium plots of land.

Name: Large Cafe Walls
Description:
A set of four walls designed for those who wish to transform their estate into a caf.

Can only be used with cottages on large plots of land.

Name: Astral Totem
Description: A small statue overflowing with astral energy. It is unclear exactly who crafted it.

Name: Umbral Totem
Description: A small statue overflowing with umbral energy. It is unclear exactly who crafted it.

Name: Unsung Helm of Asphodelos
Description:
A stunning but sadly unstoried helmet recovered from Pandmonium.

Two helms can be traded for special headgear.

Name: Unsung Armor of Asphodelos
Description:
Stunning but sadly unstoried armor recovered from Pandmonium.

Four suits can be traded for special body gear.

Name: Unsung Gauntlets of Asphodelos
Description:
Stunning but sadly unstoried gauntlets recovered from Pandmonium.

Two pairs can be traded for special arm gear.

Name: Unsung Chausses of Asphodelos
Description:
Stunning but sadly unstoried chausses recovered from Pandmonium.

Four pairs can be traded for special leg gear.

Name: Unsung Greaves of Asphodelos
Description:
Stunning but sadly unstoried greaves recovered from Pandmonium.

Two pairs can be traded for special foot gear.

Name: Unsung Ring of Asphodelos
Description:
A stunning but sadly unstoried ring recovered from Pandmonium.

One ring can be traded for a special accessory.

Name: Asphodelos Mythos I
Description:
A record of truths and somewhat exaggerated stories surrounding the creatures kept in Asphodelos.

Copies of the same Asphodelos Mythos volumes can be traded for special gear.

Name: Asphodelos Mythos II
Description:
A record of truths and somewhat exaggerated stories surrounding the creatures kept in Asphodelos.

Copies of the same Asphodelos Mythos volumes can be traded for special gear.

Name: Asphodelos Mythos III
Description:
A record of truths and somewhat exaggerated stories surrounding the creatures kept in Asphodelos.

Copies of the same Asphodelos Mythos volumes can be traded for special gear.

Name: Asphodelos Mythos IV
Description:
A record of truths and somewhat exaggerated stories surrounding the creatures kept in Asphodelos.

Copies of the same Asphodelos Mythos volumes can be traded for special gear.

Name: Unsung Blade of Asphodelos
Description: A stunning but sadly unstoried blade recovered from Pandmonium. Though such weapons were once considered highly valuable, demand has dried up and they are now essentially worthless.

Name: Radiant Roborant
Description: A translucent substance produced at the High Crucible of Al-Kimiya, used to enhance the properties of weapons borne by the Radiant Host. However, advances in crafting technology have rendered it obsolete.

Name: Radiant Twine
Description: A translucent thread produced at the High Crucible of Al-Kimiya, used to enhance the properties of the Radiant Host's vestments. However, advances in crafting technology have rendered it obsolete.

Name: Radiant Coating
Description: A translucent substance produced at the High Crucible of Al-Kimiya, used to enhance the properties of accessories worn by the Radiant Host. However, advances in crafting technology have rendered it obsolete.

Name: Discal Tomestone
Description: A surpassingly small means of storing knowledge, this style of tomestone never truly caught on amongst the Allagans due to the ease of accidentally dropping, pulverizing, or mistaking the discs for sweets. This particular variety is not as highly sought as it once was, and may no longer be exchanged for other wares.

Name: Pumpkin Cookie
Description: A devilish imp is thought to have made this slightly burnt biscuit shaped like a pumpkin head. One can only wonder what ingredients it contains.

Name: Bicolor Gemstone Voucher
Description:
Proof that you have delivered many a bicolor gemstone.

Copies of the same bicolor gemstone voucher can be traded with Edelina in Mor Dhona for special items.

Name: Irregular Tomestone of Scripture
Description:
One of only a few in existence, this Allagan tomestone contains knowledge of ancient scriptures.

Can be exchanged with itinerant moogles for certain items.

Name: Gold Core Material
Description: A piece of material required to craft a core to repair Rurusha's mysterious relic.

Name: Gold Core
Description: A gold core required to repair Rurusha's mysterious relic.

Name: Gold Connector Material
Description: A piece of material required to craft a connector to repair Rurusha's mysterious relic.

Name: Gold Connector
Description: A gold connector required to repair Rurusha's mysterious relic.

Name: Writing Utensil Materials
Description: Can be used to craft a stellar set of writing utensils.

Name: Writing Utensils
Description: A stellar set of writing utensils.

Name: Starlens Wand Material
Description: Can be used to craft a wand capable of channeling magic into the starlens.

Name: Starlens Wand
Description: A wand capable of channeling magic into the starlens.

Name: Golden Spice Ingredients
Description: This pouch contains the ingredients necessary to mix a batch of Master Dickon's golden spice.

Name: Golden Spice
Description: With this spice added into the mix, a standard curry dish is transformed into a flavorful culinary masterpiece.

Name: Fishcake Ingredient Supplies
Description: This set contains everything necessary to create a key fishcake ingredient.

Name: Sharlayan Fishcake Ingredient
Description: A key ingredient for making Sharlayan fishcakes.

Name: Hairpin Material
Description: Can be used to craft a beautiful hairpin in the right hands.

Name: Eternity Ring Material
Description: Can be used to craft a beautiful ring in the right hands.

Name: Alnairan Salmon
Description:
A migratory fish that is sometimes found wandering the coasts of Alnair.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Lunar Lamenter
Description:
An ancient creature that calls Mare Lamentorum home.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Labyrinthos Riding Map
Description: This highly detailed map of Labyrinthos, including everything from land elevation to the location of exposed rocks and roots, was originally drafted by researchers seeking to reduce delivery times of specimens.

Description: This highly detailed map of Thavnair, including everything from land elevation to the location of exposed rocks and roots, was originally drafted by chocobo couriers seeking to reduce delivery times.

Name: Garlemald Riding Map
Description: This highly detailed map of Garlemald, including everything from land elevation to the location of exposed rocks and roots, was originally drafted by imperial couriers seeking to reduce delivery times.

Name: Mare Lamentorum Riding Map
Description: This highly detailed map of Mare Lamentorum, including everything from land elevation to the location of large rocks and craters, was originally drafted by the Loporrits to allow for easier travel.

Name: Ultima Thule Riding Map
Description: This highly detailed map of Ultima Thule, including everything from land elevation to the location of exposed rocks and twisting spires, was originally drafted by peoples of a lost civilization.

Name: Elpis Riding Map
Description: This highly detailed map of Elpis, including everything from land elevation to the location of exposed rocks and roots, was originally drafted by couriers seeking to reduce delivery times.

Name: Wind-up Rudy
Description:
Eager to help, though perhaps not suited to guiding sleighs.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Rudy minion.

Description:
At once more powerful and adorable than a certain simian king.

Use item to acquire the squirrel emperor minion.

Description:
A little reindeer with a huge appetite.

Proof that you don't need to be big to think big.

Description:
Minimum proportions, maximum performance.

Use item to acquire the optimus Omicron minion.

Warning: cannot be used to teleport or upgrade weapons.

Name: Starbird
Description:
Gazing up at the stars in the heavens, it ever sings a song of hope.

Use item to acquire the starbird minion.

Description:
The very soul of grace and nobility, and can see souls to boot.

Use item to acquire the Nagxian cat minion.

Description:
Despite its diminutive size, its arms are no less weapons than those of the man himself.

Use item to acquire the brave new Urianger minion.

Description:
Last of his brood but certainly not least.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Vrtra minion.

Description:
Heavy. Assisted lift may be required.

If it were any crabbier, it would...probably still be a crab.

Use item to acquire the crabe de la crabe minion.

Description:
Use as a decoration at risk of suffering puncture woundslots of them.

Use item to acquire the Prince Lunatender minion.

The good kind that makes constructive, well-thought-out comments.

Use item to acquire the tiny troll minion.

Description:
Won't spit acid at you, so rest easy.

Use item to acquire the Caduceus minion.

Because no one should have to save the world on an empty stomach.

Use item to acquire the adventure basket minion.

Is it a bird? Is it a fish? No, it's a translation device!

Use item to acquire the Golden Dhyata minion.

Description:
Good at hiding, but clearly not good enough.

Use item to acquire the greener gleaner minion.

Name: Wind-up Grebuloff
Description:
Smells vaguely like a rocky shore.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Grebuloff minion.

Name: Nosferatu

Use item to acquire the nosferatu minion.

Come on, you know who this hero is.

Use item to acquire the wind-up herois minion.

Description:

Name: Lynx of Eternal Darkness Flute
Description: Emitting a shadowy and stoic tone, this flute summons a lynx of eternal darkness to your side.

Name: Lynx of Divine Light Flute
Description: Emitting a bright and hopeful tone, this flute summons a lynx of divine light to your side.

Name: Argos Horn
Description: Reaching across time and space, the sound of this horn brings Argos bounding to your side.

Name: Calydontis Horn
Description: When blown, this horn produces a feral sound that summons forth Calydontis, scourge of the forest.

Description: The shrill sound of this hand-carved whistle calls forth Victor, your champion show canis.

Name: Wivre Horn
Description: When blown, this horn produces a deep, booming sound that summons forth your mighty wivre.

Description: A thin, rectangular piece of what appears to be cermet. Placing it near your level checker will bring it blipping and blooping to life.

Name: Demi-Phoinix Horn
Description: This grim horn produces an unbridled sound that calls forth your Demi-Phoinix.

Description: When blown, this whistle emits a blank sound that brings Papa Paissa shuffling to your side.

Name: Porxie King Horn
Description: Wrought of clay, this horn emits a sound at once regal and soothing that calls the porxie king to your side.
