Name: Dark Hemp
Description: Native to the islands of the north seas, the fibrous stem of this plant can be used to weave cloth.

Name: Almasty Fur
Description: A softer fur you have never known.

Name: Snow Flax
Description: Sourced from the northern reaches of Ilsabard.

Name: Scarlet Moko Grass
Description: An ancient species of moko grass which can be used to weave cloth.

Name: AR-Caean Cotton Boll
Description: A rare variety of cotton which has been beloved as long as you can remember...which is not very long, given that your mind goes blank each time you attempt to recall its origins.

Name: Golden Cocoon
Description: These shining cocoons are woven only by Thavnairian silkworms.

Name: Dark Hempen Cloth
Description: A sturdy fabric woven from dark hemp.

Name: Almasty Serge
Description: Warm fabric woven with the fur of an almasty.

Name: Snow Linen
Description: A bolt of snow-white fabric.

Name: Scarlet Moko Cloth
Description: A fabric woven from scarlet moko grass.

Name: AR-Caean Velvet
Description: A rare fabric that delights mankind for unknown and possibly sinister reasons.

Name: Golden Silk
Description: A sleek and shining fabric woven from golden cocoons.

Name: Potent Spice
Description: Not for the weak of heart or palate, this powdered mixture of natural spices gives any dish a flavorsome kick.

Name: Stonehard Water
Description: Water so replete with minerals that drinking it unboiled is inadvisable, regardless of how appealing that may seem.

Name: Rime Dolomite
Description: This sample displays the particular dolomitization characteristic of the frozen wilds of Ilsabard.

Name: Double-edged Herb
Description: Incredibly potent, but also incredibly hard to find without getting lost in the woods and meeting an untimely end.

Name: Alchemical Charcoal
Description: A hot-burning fuel created by destructively distilling raw coal in the forges of the Great Work.

Name: Alchemical Abrasive
Description: This all-in-one abrasive, created by alchemists of the Great Work, can be used to both sand metals and polish them to a lustrous sheenand with only minor risk of fire.

Name: Thavnairian Horsetail
Description: A robust grass grown on Thavnair, often used as an abrasive.

Name: Thavnairian Thread
Description: Beautiful thread of the sort Ruveydah Fibers prides itself on.

Name: Amynodon Hide
Description: The hide of an ancient creature that is envisioned as an amalgam of those less-primitive creatures that most people fear being trampled by.

Name: Moonlight Aethersand
Description: The coarse-grained, elementally aspected remnants of aetherially reduced matter.

Name: Endstone Aethersand
Description: The coarse-grained, elementally aspected remnants of highly concentrated aetherially reduced mineral matter.

Name: Endwood Aethersand
Description: The coarse-grained, elementally aspected remnants of highly concentrated aetherially reduced mineral matter.

Name: Endtide Aethersand
Description: The coarse-grained, elementally aspected remnants of highly concentrated aetherially reduced mineral matter.

Description: Possesses a unique taste one might not normally associate with milk.

Name: Egg of Elpis
Description: Birthed by a bird of Elpis, the hope within this egg seems unwilling to come out...

Name: Mousse Flesh
Description: Apparently edible...?

Name: Lunatender Blossom
Description: A lovely flower found blooming on a lunatender's crown.

Name: Dynamite Ash
Description: All that remains after dynamite explodes.

Name: Petalouda Scales
Description: Scales from the wings of a petalouda.

Name: Berkanan Sap
Description: A highly sticky substance obtained from a berkanan.

Name: Dynamis Crystal
Description: A golden crystal rich in dynamis.

Name: Ambrosial Water
Description: Such fresh rainwater can only be collected on the highest of high isles in the sky.

Name: Amra
Description: The signature fruit of Thavnair, the amra is often spotted clutched in the tail of a vajralangula.

Name: Lunar Quartz
Description: A grey rock tinged with a ghostly green hue.

Name: Ghostly Umbral Rock
Description: A rock with an elemental aspect leaning unnaturally towards umbral.

Name: Ewer Clay
Description: Clay said to have been used to craft Thaliak's very own ewer.

Name: Palm Chippings
Description: Bark from a Thavnairian palm tree.

Name: Rarefied High Durium Ore
Description:
Donning equipment crafted from this elegant emerald alloy is sure to turn onlookers green with envy...right?

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Chloroschist
Description:
Some say peering into the murky depths of this stone will reveal secret truths of existencefor instance, that staring at a rock for extended periods causes significant ocular discomfort.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Raw Ametrine
Description:
This multicolored beauty was born from the fusion of amethyst and citrine.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Bismuth Ore
Description:
This mineral may look like a shiny rock, but when oxidized, it becomes a very shiny rock.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Sharlayan Rock Salt
Description:
Everyone talks so much about how salt tastes and not enough about how it looks.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Phrygian Gold Ore
Description:
Not everything that glitters is goldsometimes it is much more valuable.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Blue Zircon
Description:
The brilliance of this sample's blue hue remains nigh unparalleled in the natural worldparticularly now that it has been removed from it.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Eblan Alumen
Description:
No one would call this alumen rarefied were it overabundant in the frozen northcertainly not for marketing purposes. Perish the thought!

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Annite
Description:
Handling may cause this mineral to fracture or flake, so best not. What do you mean, too late?

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Pewter Ore
Description:
Pewter? I barely know her!

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Thavnairian Perilla Leaf
Description:
This herb's minty aroma is stronger than that of its perilla brethren, easily separating the Thavs from the Thav-nots.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Ironwood Log
Description:
More wood than iron...which is to say that it is not really iron at all.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Palm Log
Description:
The lack of rings makes this lumber impossible to dateor, as particularly aggravating naturalists might say, stuck in the frond zone.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Red Pine Log
Description:
While this wood is more red-adjacent than truly red, red-adjacent pine does not exactly roll off the tongue.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Coconut
Description:
Though this deceptive drupe does not taste like cocoa and it is not a true nut, culinarians tend to overlook these offenses in light of its deliciousness. It is on thin ice with the botanists, however.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Sykon
Description:
A succulent symbol of vitality, this fruit pairs nicely with some honey and stone cheese.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Dark Rye
Description:
This hearty grain is a culinarian's delightthough much more so after the tiresome grinding step is complete.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Elder Nutmeg
Description:
This sweet-scented spice is proven to help medicine go down. Consuming an entire spoonful, however, is not recommended.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Iceberg Lettuce
Description:
This crisp, refreshing vegetable is often thought to be lacking in flavor, but those who enjoy the flavor of water doubtless find it absolutely overpowering.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied AR-Caean Cotton Boll
Description:
These bolls are so irresistibly soft that some folks can't help but pluck them and pop them in their ears. Caution: under no circumstances should AR-Caean cotton be placed near the ears.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Resplendent Carpenter's Component A
Description: The arboreal aroma is admired by accomplished artisans and aspiring aficionados alike.

Name: Resplendent Blacksmith's Component A
Description: A glowing golden globule.

Name: Resplendent Armorer's Component A
Description: Far simpler in design than its extravagant name would suggest.

Name: Resplendent Goldsmith's Component A
Description: Soapy bubbles in block form.

Name: Resplendent Leatherworker's Component A
Description: The skin of a blue animal. Maybe.

Name: Resplendent Weaver's Component A
Description: Only an engineer would refer to a length of thread as a component.

Name: Resplendent Alchemist's Component A
Description: Of all the liquids found in alchemy, this is one of the least suitably named.

Name: Resplendent Culinarian's Component A
Description: A curious little box that is tangentially related to the culinary arts, or so the Boutique of Splendors would have you believe.

Name: Resplendent Carpenter's Component B
Description: Like a flute but without the holes.

Name: Resplendent Blacksmith's Component B
Description: Can be used in place of legal tender, provided the phrase It's that or nothing! is uttered with enough conviction.

Name: Resplendent Armorer's Component B
Description: The term cock-a-hoop originates from a game in which competitors throw objects such as these over the neck of a male chicken.

Name: Resplendent Goldsmith's Component B
Description: Not only are such objects said to be found on the dark side of the moon, they are available in any color you like.

Name: Resplendent Leatherworker's Component B
Description: A not-so-neatly folded sheet of beast skin.

Name: Resplendent Weaver's Component B
Description: While not exactly as resplendent as the name would suggest, it is at least clean.

Name: Resplendent Alchemist's Component B
Description: One of the few substances in alchemy that is as light as it is heavy.

Name: Resplendent Culinarian's Component B
Description: This mustard is known as Eulmore's hottest yellow paste.

Name: Resplendent Carpenter's Component C
Description: A hardened lump of the crimson sap known as tree blood.

Name: Resplendent Blacksmith's Component C
Description: Just another cog in the machine. Or at least it will be once the rest of the machine has been built around it.

Name: Resplendent Armorer's Component C
Description: Most armorer's tools do not incorporate sheets of chainmail, but try telling the Boutique of Splendors that.

Name: Resplendent Goldsmith's Component C
Description: It is not yet known whether this resplendent orb will become the centerpiece in a fine item of jewelry or ground down into dust for a far less glamorous purpose.

Name: Resplendent Leatherworker's Component C
Description: While this incredibly long strap is an impressive example of leatherworking, calling it resplendent may be something of an exaggeration.

Name: Resplendent Weaver's Component C
Description: A bolt of cloth this luxurious surely warrants a better name.

Name: Resplendent Alchemist's Component C
Description: A handful of carbon rods. One for each finger, in fact.

Name: Resplendent Culinarian's Component C
Description: A small vial of unnamed gloopy stuff.

Name: Omega-M Attire
Description: Cannot equip with arm, leg, or foot gear.

Name: Omega-F Attire
Description: Cannot equip with arm, leg, or foot gear.

Name: Fallen Angel Wings
Description: The perfect solution for anyone seeking a pair of edgier angel wings. Use to acquire a pair of fallen angel wings.

Name: Archangel Wings
Description: For those who go gaga for gold. Use to acquire a pair of archangel wings.

Name: Diabolos Wings
Description: Highly recommended for those who feel an affinity with voidsent. Use to acquire a pair of Diabolos wings.

Name: Pixie Wings
Description: Perfect for those who like to indulge their mischievous side. Use to acquire a pair of pixie wings.

Name: False Oval Spectacles
Description: Wish to look more intelligent with minimal effort? Then look no further than these superb specs. Though these were once considered a fashion accessory, trends are ever changing, and style enthusiasts now classify them as facewear. Use to unlock oval spectacles.

Name: Blackbosom Weapon Coffer
Description:
A banded chest containing six Blackbosom weapons.

Required level: 1. IL: 1.

Name: Onokoro Carp
Description:
This otherwise average wavekin would never be caught dead in less temperate climes.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Ruby-spotted Crab
Description:
Though this crab advertises its toxicity with its bright and spotted carapace, some people just never learn.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Marrow-eater
Description:
A bottom-feeder in the most literal sense, this fish can be found on the seafloor munching on all manner of carrion.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Cloudy Cat Shark
Description:
A variety of two-toned shark that should never be kept as a pet.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Red Gurnard
Description:
One always knows when this saltwater fish is coming thanks to its vivid blue-tinged fins.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Dream Pickle
Description:
Lucky are the Isari fishermen who can catch and sell this creature.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Ruby Haddock
Description:
One can find schools of these wavekin eking out an existence in the depths of the Ruby Sea.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Crown Fish
Description:
If one were judging by appearances alone, the marking around this fish's face would make it ruler of the seas. Alas, in the real world, the best it can hope for is to not be confused with the common clown fish.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Sword of Isari
Description:
This imposing ancient creature can be found around Isari.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Blue Shark
Description:
A shark with migratory habits that extend from the wide open ocean throughout the Ruby Sea.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Barb of Exile
Description:
A variety of seahorse living in the deepest part of the Ruby Sea.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Smooth Lumpfish
Description:
A white saltwater creature with a round body and a texture than can only be described as thoroughly unsettling.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Hells' Cap
Description:
This flat, disc-shaped fish can be found in the hottest parts of the Ruby Sea.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Keeled Fugu
Description:
Living within the abyssal zone, this fish is much smaller than it leads its predators to believe.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Eastern Seerfish
Description:
A wavekin found swimming the seas of the Far East.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: False Fusilier
Description:
This saltwater fish bears strong resemblance to both true fusiliers and squashed Far Eastern plums, but it is neither.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Skipping Stone
Description:
A diminutive wavekin living in the shallows northeast of Bekko.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Red-spotted Blenny
Description:
This white saltwater wavekin is flecked with spots, as if a painter flicked their brush at it.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Othardian Wrasse
Description:
A saltwater creature known for its beautiful coloration.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Grey Mullet
Description:
This sea-dwelling creature is not an uncommon a sight in the waters of the Far East.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Prayer Cushion
Description:
It is something of a marvel to watch these pale wavekin glide effortlessly through the sea.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Deepbody Boarfish
Description:
These saltwater wavekin are known far and wide for their unique shape and bright color.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Jointed Razorfish
Description:
This tiny creature, with its peculiar swimming habits, stands out more than it likely wishes to.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Pipefish
Description:
A long, red saltwater wavekin embellished with a white underbelly.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Righteye Flounder
Description:
A russet-colored kin of the flounder.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Mini Yasha
Description:
A saltwater wavekin with distinctive red and amber coloration.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 1 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Sawshark
Description:
With its saw-shaped snout, one would be hard-pressed to consider this shark inconspicuous.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Othardian Lumpsucker
Description:
A deep-sea wavekin with fins that will cling desperately to just about anything to avoid swimming.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Shogun's Kabuto
Description:
So curious is the shape of this creature's skull, one cannot help but want to wear it.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Bluefin Trevally
Description:
The sparkling blue of its fins sets this wavekin apart.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Kitefin Shark
Description:
A shark with shining, surreal eyes that stand out like gems against the dull background of its body.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 3 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Uzumaki
Description:
One would not be alone in saying this primordial beast haunts their dreams.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Natron Puffer
Description:
A wavekin which keeps to the deeper portions of Loch Seld.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Diamond Dagger
Description:
This wavekin enjoys higher levels of salinity than most.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Queenly Fan
Description:
Creatures which adorn themselves with glimmering gems of salt.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Pale Panther
Description:
A variety of eel with a monochrome pattern covering its body.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Saltsquid
Description:
A massive squid that calls Loch Seld home.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Platinum Hammerhead
Description:
The apex predator of the lochs, this shark can be found skimming the depths in search of prey.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Gold Salmon Roe
Description: Salmon eggs that glisten in the sunlight. Live bait for freshwater fishing.

Name: Leech
Description: Not as bloodthirsty as you might think. Live bait for freshwater fishing.

Name: Sky Spoon Lure
Description: A metal lure shaped like a spoon so it will oscillate when dragged through the water, attracting fish. Especially effective in lakes.

Name: Mayfly
Description: A short-lived thin insect. Live bait for freshwater fishing.

Name: Shrimp Ball
Description: A ball of shrimp and rye flour paste. Processed bait for saltwater fishing.

Name: Mackerel Strip
Description: A thin piece of mackerel flesh. Live(ish) bait for ocean fishing.

Name: Grey Worm
Description: An oddball worm with a taste for waters of an altogether stranger variety. Live bait for aetherfishing.

Name: Chimera Worm
Description: An altered moth larva. Live bait for aetherfishing.

Name: Panic Jig
Description: A lure with a shape so terrifying it sends anything that sees it into a state of abject panic. Especially effective for starfishing.

Name: Stardust
Description: The stuff dreams are made of. Bait for starfishing.

Name: Tome of Geological Folklore - Ilsabard and the Northern Empty
Description: Tales gathered from northern miners regarding the location of legendary ore veins and gem deposits.

Name: Tome of Geological Folklore - The Sea of Stars
Description: Tales gathered from miners regarding the location of legendary ore veins and gem deposits.

Name: Tome of Geological Folklore - The World Unsundered
Description: Tales gathered from miners regarding the location of legendary ore veins and gem deposits.

Name: Tome of Botanical Folklore - Ilsabard and the Northern Empty
Description: Tales gathered from northern botanists regarding the location of rare trees and herbs.

Name: Tome of Botanical Folklore - The Sea of Stars
Description: Tales gathered from botanists regarding the location of rare trees and herbs.

Name: Tome of Botanical Folklore - The World Unsundered
Description: Tales gathered from botanists regarding the location of rare trees and herbs.

Name: Tome of Ichthyological Folklore - Ilsabard and the Northern Empty
Description: Tales gathered from northern fishers regarding the location of legendary fish.

Name: Tome of Ichthyological Folklore - The Sea of Stars
Description: Tales gathered from fishers regarding the location of legendary fish.

Name: Tome of Ichthyological Folklore - The World Unsundered
Description: Tales gathered from fishers regarding the location of legendary fish.

Name: Regional Folklore Trader's Token C
Description: A certified note that can be exchanged for tomes of regional folklore.

Name: Timeworn Saigaskin Map
Description:
This bottle holds a timeworn map classified as risk-reward grade 13 among treasure hunters.

Use the action Decipher to extract the map and examine its contents.
Level 90 recommended.

Name: Timeworn Kumbhiraskin Map
Description:
This bottle holds a timeworn map classified as risk-reward grade 14 among treasure hunters.

Use the action Decipher to extract the map and examine its contents.
Level 90 full party (eight players) recommended.

Name: Paladin's Arms of the Round
Description:
A set of arms containing a Sword of the Round and a Shield of the Round.

Required level: 60. IL: 180. Cannot be opened in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.

Name: Heavens Weapon Coffer (IL 205)
Description:
A heavy chest containing a weapon of the Heavens.

Required level: 60. IL: 205. Weapon type determined by current job or class at time of opening. Cannot be opened in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.

Name: Divine Light Weapon Coffer (IL 580)
Description:
A heavy chest containing a weapon of divine Light.

Required level: 90. IL: 580. Weapon type determined by current job or class at time of opening. Cannot be opened in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.

Name: Modern Cosmetics - Clowning Around
Description:
The realm's premier publication on cosmeticsas well as dating advice and, for some reason, politicsthis copy of Modern Cosmetics covers, in detail, techniques for painting an appropriately spooky clown pattern on one's face.

Use to unlock new face paint at the aesthetician.

Name: Rarefied Integral Fishing Rod
Description:
Some advise against sparing the rod and spoiling the child, but what about spoiling the child with a fine rod like this one?

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Chondrite Lapidary Hammer
Description:
With one of these in hand, one can hammer in the morningor hammer in the eveningall over this realm.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Chondrite Alembic
Description:
Guaranteed to help one produce the most efficacious elixirs and the most potent potables.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Chondrite Needle
Description:
Often found in notable weaving establishments; less often found in haystacks.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Ophiotauroskin Halfgloves
Description:
Ideal for adventurers who have no need to cover their fingers or who don't have any fingers to cover in the first place.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied AR-Caean Velvet Work Cap
Description:
A simple cap that's soft to the touch and vaguely vocational in its design.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Ophiotauroskin Magitek Codex
Description:
Despite its leather binding, this tome is, in actual fact, a technological wonderproof that one should not judge a book by its cover.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Sykon Bavarois
Description:
This jiggly, figgy dessert must be jelly becausefamouslyjam doesn't shake.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Luxurious Paper
Description: Paper of such fine quality, it would be a shame to tarnish it with ink, no matter how skillful the penmanship.

Name: Cloth of Happiness
Description: Guaranteed to bring you eternal happiness if its name is anything to go by.

Name: Phonograph Plate
Description: A specially treated metal sheet used in the construction of phonographs. Even the slightest imperfection can lead to all sorts of ghastly noises being produced.

Name: Bird of Elpis Breast
Description: The most tender meat this bird has to offer.

Name: Valentione Mobile
Description: Dangling decorations crafted into various heart shapes, though none of them are anatomically accurate.

Name: Mechanical Lotus Ignition Key
Description: Clearing your mind of impure thoughts while inserting this key into your mechanical lotus will bring it sublimely to life.

Name: Chi Bolt
Description: A top-drawer bolt obtained from Chi.

Name: Daivadipa's Bead
Description: Brimming with Daivadipa's essence.

Name: Materiel Container 3.0
Description:
Awarded to those who have made an outstanding contribution to the realm.

Contains a random mount or minion introduced in A Realm Reborn or Heavensward.

Name: Materiel Container 4.0
Description:
Awarded to those who have made an outstanding contribution to the realm.

Contains a random mount or minion introduced in Stormblood.

Name: Royal Lunatender
Description:
All that glitters is not gold. It could also be a lunatender.

Use item to acquire the royal lunatender minion.

Name: Gaja Suit
Description: Cannot equip gear to hands, legs, and feet.

Name: Season Twenty Pack Wolf Voucher A
Description: Documentation of noteworthy accomplishments for Season Twenty of the Feast.

Name: Season Twenty Lone Wolf Voucher B
Description: Documentation of noteworthy accomplishments for Season Twenty of the Feast.

Name: Season Twenty Lone Wolf Voucher C
Description: Documentation of noteworthy accomplishments for Season Twenty of the Feast.

Name: Trophy Crystal
Description: Handsomealbeit impractically pointytokens issued by Eorzea's Grand Companies for use at the Wolves' Den.

Name: Irregular Tomestone of Verity
Description:
One of only a few in existence, this Allagan tomestone contains a truth so profound, it is said to inspire feelings of deep inadequacy in all those who attempt to comprehend it.

Can be exchanged with itinerant moogles for certain items.

Name: Inksquid
Description:
Found deep within salt lakes, this cephalopod earned its name by virtue of the copious amounts of ink it produces.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Seedtoad
Description:
Commonly found in dense forests, this rotund toad camouflages itself as a seed to avoid detection from predators.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Auroral Clam
Description:
Shimmering like an aurora, the unparalleled beauty of these clams have spawned no small few myths among divers in the Far East.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Holier-than Mogpom
Description:
Do not be disturbed by the name of this specimenit is merely a light-emitting formation of algae that shares a habitat with related species. Nothing more, surely.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Chalky Coral
Description:
It should come as no surprise that a coral of such remarkable writing capacity is often used for marking by merchants in the Near Eastthe region from which it hails. Indeed, such is its utility that it has come to be considered a tool of the trade.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Aetheroconductive Quill
Description: While undoubtedly an excellent writing implement, the aetheroconductive properties of this quill cause one slight brush from its plumage to jolt, rather than tickle.

Name: Aetheroconductive Focus
Description: One might saywith only the slightest hint of hyperbolethat wielding magicks without a focus is akin to cooking without fire. An aetheroconductive focus, then, should allow one to wield fine spells indeed.

Name: Luncheon Coffer
Description: A luncheon coffer affixed with a crystal to give it aetherically enhanced insulative properties. It can preserve the temperature of food placed within it for long periods of time.

Name: Aetheroconductive Mammet
Description: A mammet crafted with materials highly conductive to aether, making it an ideal training tool for fledgling wielders of magicks.

Name: School Supplies
Description: This thoughtful assortment contains myriad school essentials.

Name: Aetheroconductive Feather
Description: This aetheroconductive feather is destined to become the much-needed quill of a student lacking one.

Name: Aetheroconductive Focus Materials
Description: A sack of rare materials essential in the crafting of aetheroconductive foci.

Name: Luncheon Coffer Materials
Description: This may be the most extravagant set of materials you have ever seen used to craft what is essentially a box for one's lunch.

Name: Aetheroconductive Mammet Materials
Description: These aetheroconductive materials will make for highly responsive mammets, perfect for any aspiring mage's needs.

Name: School Supply Materials
Description: These materials can be used to craft school suppliesand hopefully a brighter future for the children in need of them.

Name: Aetheroconductive Quill Components
Description: An assortment of components suitable for crafting aetheroconductive quills for students enrolled in the academic homestead program.

Name: Aetheroconductive Focus Components
Description: An assortment of components suitable for crafting aetheroconductive foci for students enrolled in the academic homestead program.

Name: Luncheon Coffer Components
Description: An assortment of components suitable for crafting luncheon coffers for students enrolled in the academic homestead program.

Name: Aetheroconductive Mammet Components
Description: An assortment of components suitable for crafting aetheroconductive mammets for the use of students enrolled in the academic homestead program.

Name: School Supply Components
Description: An assortment of components suitable for crafting school supplies for children in need.

Name: Aetherolectric Guitarfish
Description:
A king among guitarfish, and lord of the waters of Scholar's Harbor.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Jumbo Snook
Description:
A king among fat snook, and lord of the waters of Unmoved Source Alpha.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Earful
Description:
A king among longear sunfish, and lord of the waters of Meghaduta.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Hippo Frog
Description:
A king among marid frogs, and lord of the Giantsgall Grounds.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Rimepike
Description:
A king among icepike, and lord of the waters of the Eblan Thaw.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Foun Ahlm
Description:
A king among foun myhks, and lord of apohelos 18-.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Forbiddingway
Description:
A king among terrifyingways, and lord of limne 18.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Thavnairian Calamari
Description:
A squid commonly featured in popular Thavnairian cuisine.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Crucible Rain
Description: A highly concentrated elixir blended by the elite alchemists of the High Crucible.

Name: Hannish Certificate of Grade 1 Import
Description: A note of promise granted for the delivery of classical equipment.

Name: Season One Final Conflict Chit
Description: Documentation of noteworthy accomplishments for Season One of Crystalline Conflict.

Name: Season One Endless Conflict Chit
Description: Documentation of noteworthy accomplishments for Season One of Crystalline Conflict.

Name: Season One Rising Conflict Chit
Description: Documentation of noteworthy accomplishments for Season One of Crystalline Conflict.

Name: Ultimatum Totem
Description: A small statue discovered at the end of all things. Given the circumstances, it is unclear exactly who crafted itand how they managed to do so while in the throes of existential despair.

Name: Dragonsong Totem
Description: A physical remembrance of war, loss, and longing.

Name: Fortune Egg
Description: A plain white Archon egg believed to bring its bearer good luck for as long as it remains uncracked.

Name: Modern Aesthetics - Liberating Locks
Description:
The realm's premier publication on beauty and fashion, this limited edition of Modern Aesthetics covers, in detail, unauthorized techniques for assuming the style of Ala Mhigo's fearless leader, Lyse Hext.

Use to unlock a new hairstyle at the aesthetician.
Fits:
Unavailable to female Hrothgar.

Name: Bluefeather Weapon Coffer (IL 595)
Description:
A physicallyand, somehow, psychologicallyburdensome chest containing a bluefeather weapon.

Required level: 90. IL: 595. Weapon type determined by current job or class at time of opening. Cannot be opened in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.

Name: Street Attire Coffer
Description:
A banded chest containing a complete set of street attire.

Required level: 1. IL: 1. Cannot be opened in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.

Name: Aglaia Coin
Description: An age-worn artifact recovered from Aglaia. Once considered to be of great religious significance, a sudden influx caused their value to plummet, rendering them almost worthless.

Name: Lyse's Leadership Attire
Description:
Fits: All 
Cannot equip with arm, leg, or foot gear.

Name: Bluefeather Barding
Description: A suit of chocobo armor designed to resemble a devastating blue bird.

Name: Wolf Barding
Description: A suit of chocobo armor designed to obfuscate your steed's unfortunate affliction during the full moon.

Name: Wind-up Arkasodara
Description:
Comes with modesty covered.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Arkasodara minion.

Name: Wind-up Kangaroo
Description:
Always has a spring in its step.

Use item to acquire the wind-up kangaroo minion.

Name: Protonaught
Description:
The amount it can lift would put a full-grown Roegadyn to shame.

Use item to acquire the protonaught minion.

Name: Teacup Kapikulu
Description:
Small but eager to work.

Use item to acquire the teacup Kapikulu minion.

Name: Chewy
Description:
Take care not to drown in its literal puppy dog eyes.

Use item to acquire the Chewy minion.

Name: Clockwork Novus D
Description:
Deftly driven by an unspecified (but doubtless incomparably brilliant) man.

Use item to acquire the clockwork Novus D minion.

Name: Hatching Bunny
Description:
If happiness had form, it would look like this.

Use item to acquire the hatching bunny minion.

Name: Wind-up Azeyma
Description:
For those who like it scorching hot.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Azeyma minion.

Name: Wind-up Ragnarok
Description:
Loporrit crew not included, delightful though that would be.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Ragnarok minion.

Name: Blue-footed Booby
Description:
A terror from beak to tailfeather.

Use item to acquire the blue-footed booby minion.

Name: Wind-up PuPu
Description:
Will bleed you dry of elixirs if you aren't careful.

Use item to acquire the wind-up PuPu minion.

Name: Clockwork Solus
Description:
No lands must remain beyond its grasp. Go forth. Conquer. Rule.

Use item to acquire the clockwork Solus minion.

Description: A highland wooden wall designed exclusively for use with cottages.

Name: Highland Classical Window
Description: A classical window in the highland style.

Name: Highland Lancet Window
Description: A lancet window in the highland style.

Name: Highland Oblong Window
Description: An oblong window in the highland style.

Name: Highland Wooden Door
Description: A wooden door in the highland style.

Name: Highland Ornate Door
Description: An ornate door in the highland style.

Name: Highland Classical Door
Description: A classical door in the highland style.

Name: Highland Interior Wall
Description: An interior wall designed to complement highland residences.

Name: Highland Flooring
Description: Floorboards designed to complement highland residences.

Name: Highland Pendant Lamp
Description: A pendant lamp designed to complement highland residences.

Name: Deluxe Highland Pendant Lamp
Description: A large pendant lamp designed to complement highland residences.

Name: Highland Chandelier
Description: A sumptuous chandelier designed to complement highland residences.

Name: Highland Composite Chimney
Description: A composite chimney designed to complement highland residences.

Name: Highland Rounded Chimney
Description: A rounded chimney designed to complement highland residences.

Name: Highland Stone Chimney
Description: A stone chimney designed to complement highland residences.

Name: Highland Wooden Awning
Description: A sturdy wooden awning designed to complement highland residences.

Name: Highland Stone Awning
Description: A sturdy stone awning designed to complement highland residences.

Name: Highland Composite Awning
Description: A sturdy composite awning designed to complement highland residences.

Name: Highland Placard
Description: A handsome placard designed to complement highland residences.

Name: Highland Hanging Placard
Description: A hanging placard designed to complement highland residences.

Name: Highland Banner
Description: A handsome banner designed to complement highland residences.

Name: Highland Stone Wall
Description: A stone wall designed to complement highland residences. Mix and match at your own peril.

Name: Highland Fence
Description: An arched stone fence designed to complement highland residences. Mix and match at your own peril.

Name: Highland Potting Fence
Description: A stone potting fence designed to complement highland residences. Mix and match at your own peril.

Name: Troll Horn
Description: When blown, this horn produces an untamed sound that calls your towering troll to your side.

Name: Fylgja Horn
Description: When blown, this lovingly wrought horn emits a lyrical sound that summons Fylgja to your side.

Name: Alkonost Whistle
Description: This whistle emits a shrill tone that summons your alkonost to your side.

Name: Hippo Cart Horn
Description: When blown, this horn produces a rumbling sound that calls a hippo to your side, cart and all.

Name: UFO Identification Key
Description: A thin, rectangular piece of some unknown material. Placing it near your UFO will magically bring the starship to life.

Name: Vinegaroon Horn
Description: Scaly to the touch, this horn of bone emits a primordial sound that summons your vinegaroon.

Name: Pod 602 Identification Key
Description: A thin, rectangular piece of some unknown material. Placing it near your pod 602 will magically bring the machine to life.

Name: Orthos Craklaw Horn
Description: When blown, this hardened horn emits a history-transcending sound that brings your Orthos craklaw scuttling to your side.

Name: Bluefeather Lynx Flute
Description: Emitting an uplifting tone evocative of light when it shines across a dark and starless sea, this flute summons a bluefeather lynx to your side.

Name: Megashiba Flute
Description: The shrill sound of this hand-carved whistle summons your massively adorable megashiba to your side.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Valentione's Dangers
Description: An illustrated manual detailing how to consume one's Valentione's chocolate without decorating oneself with unseemly evidence. Use to learn the /eatchocolate emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - An Egg a Day
Description: A needlessly detailed manual of how to consume an egg with dandy and panache. (Instructions on how to boil said egg are conspicuously absent.) Use to learn the /eategg emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Forearmed Is Well Armed
Description: An illustrated manual detailing the most stylishif debatably practicalway to ready one's trusty weapon. Use to learn the /draw emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Easily at Ease
Description: An illustrated manual detailing what to do once you have sated your barbaric inclinations and wish to return to civilized society. Use to learn the /sheathe emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Persuasive Perseverance
Description: An illustrated manual detailing how to show yourself undaunted by the tasks inevitably set to you by both stranger and acquaintance alike. Use to learn the /determined emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - The Tea
Description: An illustrated manual detailing how to serenely imbibe a steeped beverage, particularly with an all-knowing air. Use to learn the /tea emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Soliciting Applause
Description: An illustrated manual detailing how to best introduce persons of repute and particularly large desserts. Use to learn the /showright and /showleft emotes.

Name: Thavnairian Corn
Description: A selectively bred variant cultivated from the maize once brought to Thavnair from the New World. Valued for its nutritional value and alchemical uses alike.

Name: Raw Eblan Danburite
Description: An uncut, unpolished stone containing what appears to be Eblan danburite.

Name: Eblan Danburite
Description: A transparent jewel sourced from the Eblan Rime.

Name: Hannish Fiber
Description: An alchemically created bundle of fine, plant-based material.

Name: Calamari Ripieni
Description:
Fresh squid stuffed with a vibrant array of vegetables and cheese, then simmered to perfection in dry white wine.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Kalamarakia Tiganita
Description:
Thick slices of squid coated in spiced dark rye flour, then fried in perilla oil until crispy.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Immutable Solution
Description: Whatever else happens, you can always rely on this substancewhatever it isnot to change.

Name: Byregotia Seeds
Description:
They say it is by Byregot's very hand that these flowers are coaxed to blossom...but you should still water them nevertheless.

For use in planters.

Name: Red Byregotia
Description:
A bunch of red Byregotia, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Authentic White Tiger
Description: An authentic screen featuring the fearsome Byakko of Eastern legend. It seems he could leap from the canvas at any moment, and given his near-unlimited powers, he may do just that.

Name: Susano's Rapturous Paladin Arms
Description:
A set of arms containing Susano's rapturous longsword and Susano's rapturous shield.

Required level: 70. IL: 290.

Name: Gingerbread Cottage Walls
Description:
A set of four walls designed for those who wish to transform their estate into a delicious gingerbread cottage.

Can only be used with cottages on small plots of land.

Name: Gingerbread House Walls
Description:
A set of four walls designed for those who wish to transform their estate into a delicious gingerbread house.

Can only be used with houses on medium plots of land.

Name: Gingerbread Mansion Walls
Description:
A set of four walls designed for those who wish to transform their estate into a delicious gingerbread mansion.

Can only be used with mansions on large plots of land.

Name: Classic Dresser
Description: A lavish vanity that hearkens back to days long past.

Name: Log Rack
Description: A lovely rack to organize your logs.

Name: Indoor Marble Fountain
Description: A fountain carved from deep-sea marble and whimsically decorated with moogle statuettes.

Name: Ornamental Crystal Array
Description: A decorative wall ornament dripping with jewels.

Name: Log Pillar
Description: A decorative wooden pillar designed to resemble the tree it came from.

Name: Kweh-kweh Clock
Description: A charming chronometer designed to alert you of the time with a rousing Kweh-kweh! at convenient intervals. Recommended to those plagued by unwanted fits of napping.

Name: Small Blackboard
Description: Experience the joy of slapping two dusty erasers together again and again. And again.

Name: Eastern Canopy Bed
Description: Sleep in luxury under a canopy of softly blooming flowers from the Far East. Be advised that sleepers may or may not wake up subsumed in petals.

Name: Wondrous Parfait
Description:
A massive dessert layered with plenty of fresh fruit, whipped cream, and frozen confectionary. Strangely enough, it never seems to melt.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Spell Speed Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  VIT Bonus: +5% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Eulmoran Divan
Description: A cushioned settee expressly designed for contemplating one's more opulent sins.

Name: Sweetfish Skewers
Description:
Lightly salted and roasted to perfection, these sweetfish skewers make for a simple-yet-sublime snack.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Critical Hit Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  VIT Bonus: +5% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Ivy Curtain
Description: A natural veil of trailing greenery.

Name: Luminous Wooden Loft
Description: All the fun of a regular wooden loft, now with built-in light fixtures!

Name: Swinging-door Counter
Description: Be advised not to let the doors of this handsome counter hit you on the way out, as many a barkeep can attest that they pack a punch for both buttocks.

Name: Ironworks Tool Set
Description: A set of Garlond Ironworks' finest instruments.

Name: Trick Bookshelf Partition
Description: Pull the correct tome from the shelf to trigger the hidden door. Perfect for bibliophiles with a secret agenda.

Name: Simple Arched Window
Description: An arched window lovely in its simplicity.

Name: Factory Pillar
Description: A rusted metal pillar with an uncanny resemblance to those found in the Copied Factory.

Name: Curved Marble Partition
Description: A gently curved, cream-colored partition with a white marble baseboard.

Name: Iron Chair
Description: A refined chair wrought with diligence.

Name: Indoor Climbing Frame
Description: A curious, latticelike structure that inspires rampant frolicking and climbing upon contact. Approach with caution.

Name: Steel Locker
Description: A metal cupboard perfectly suited for stowing cleaning instruments, sundry items, and lithographs of your sweetheart.

Name: Alpine Cabinet
Description: A decorative cabinet designed in the alpine style.

Name: Alpine Wall Lantern
Description: A wall lantern crafted in the alpine style.

Name: Astrologicum Star Map
Description: An august chart rich with the secrets of the heavens. Good for study and impressing your guests.

Name: Imitation Highland Window
Description: Who needs a house in the freezing peaks when you can mount a frosty windowpane upon your wall instead?

Name: House Fortemps Fireplace
Description: A faithful replica of the fireplace found in Fortemps Manor.

Name: Alpine Doormat
Description: A welcome mat designed to complement alpine residences.

Name: Cathedral Lectern
Description: An uncanny recreation of the lectern used in Saint Reymanaud's Cathedral.

Name: Scholasticate Table
Description: A long desk much like those found at Saint Endalim's Scholasticate.

Name: Scholasticate Chair
Description: A wooden chair much like those found at Saint Endalim's Scholasticate.

Name: Scholasticate Bookshelf
Description: A laden bookshelf much like those found at Saint Endalim's Scholasticate.

Name: Bluefeather Astrolabos
Description:
A hauntingly beautiful model of the universe.

One per estate only.

Name: Royal Menagerie Phasmascape
Description: This advanced magitek contraption displays the splendor of Ala Mhigo's Royal Menagerie under a dying sun.

Name: Sea of Clouds Phasmascape
Description: This advanced magitek contraption displays the bevy of isles floating above Abalathia's Spine.

Name: Stuffed Sanduruva
Description: Said to bring prosperity to the one who displays it. Any rumors that great wealth is hidden within are certainly exaggerated.

Name: Stuffed Minduruva
Description: Said to bestow talent in the arts to the one who displays it. Any reports of it crafting shoes by night are likely exaggerated.

Name: Stuffed Cinduruva
Description: Said to bless the one who displays it with wisdom. Any reports of its eyes moving on their own accord are greatly exaggerated. Probably.

Name: Moogle Balloon
Description: That adorable moogle balloon from the Gold Saucer that you've always desirednow yours!

Name: Eggsemplary Basket
Description: An elegant and enticing example of exceptional egg-hunting.

Name: Hatching-tide Mobile
Description: The twirl and bob of this Hatching-tide mobile reminds you of all the hidden eggs you have yet to find...

Name: Emperor Portrait
Description: A commissioned portrait of the Garlean Empire's founding father, Solus zos Galvus, entitled Beyond the Horizon. Original artist unknown.

Name: Heavensturn Crane Banner
Description: A resplendent Heavensturn decoration bedecked with auspicious cranes.

Name: Azure Banner of Conflict
Description: A brilliant blue banner distributed at the Wolves' Den.

Name: Crimson Banner of Conflict
Description: A fierce red banner distributed at the Wolves' Den.

Name: Authentic Hatching-tide Confections
Description:
A delightful set of bite-sized morsels of baked chocolate fashioned to resemble spriggans. So delicious you're certain to sprigg for more!

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Determination Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  VIT Bonus: +5% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Authentic Archon Egg Pouch
Description: A compact, stylish pouch with a strap to be slung over the shoulder, designed with an egg motif perfect for the Hatching-tide season. Now shinier and eggier than ever!

Name: Authentic Costa del Hielo
Description:
A delicious chilled dessert created by the confectioner Nekeke, this icy treat is both refreshing and easy on the waistline, as it largely consists of frozen water. Guaranteed to be exactly as hydrating as it has always been.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Skill Speed Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  VIT Bonus: +5% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Authentic Grilled Corn
Description:
Sweet millioncorn on the cob, basted with authentic Hingan soy sauce and broiled over an open flame. So succulently delicious, you won't want to miss a kernel.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Critical Hit Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  VIT Bonus: +5% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Alpine Open-air Bath
Description: A luxurious, outdoor bath designed in the alpine fashion.

Name: Ivy-covered Bridge
Description: A stone bridge tastefully hemmed with tendrils of creeping ivy.

Name: Snowy Red Brick Bench
Description: Someone might have sat here, alone in the snow, thinking of warmer days since passed...

Name: Raised Wooden Deck
Description: An elevated platform designed for access by only those who dare to hop, skip, or jump.

Name: Garden Gate
Description: Curious what lies beyond the garden wall? The garden gate is here to help.

Name: Planter Set
Description: A vibrant arrangement of plant life bursting from a cluster of sturdy planters.

Name: Sweet Lawn Ornaments
Description: Giant, lifelike lawn ornaments that look tasty enough to lick. (Be advised that this item is for decorative purposes only and should not be licked or otherwise consumed under any circumstances.)

Name: Damaged Ishgardian Wall
Description: A damaged wall preserved for posterity during the Ishgardian Restoration.

Name: Ishgardian Lamppost
Description: A lamppost of steel such as one might see lining an Ishgardian street. Authentically frigid!

Name: Summer Bonfire
Description: A roaring bonfire perfect for activities such as celebrating the Moonfire Faire and establishing a solid alibi.

Name: Authentic Moonfire Mask Stall
Description: A stall with an assortment of colorful masks on display, as seen during the Moonfire Faire festivities. While a simple novelty item at first glance, each mask has, in truth, been expertly crafted by the hands of a master.

Name: Amaurotine Interior Wall
Description: An interior wall recreated from the memory of a city long since destroyed.

Name: Amaurotine Flooring
Description: Elegant stone flooring recreated from the memory of a city long since destroyed.

Name: Amaurotine Spire Chandelier
Description: A breathtaking light fixture resembling the once-proud spires of a city long since destroyed.
