Name: Authentic Egg Barding
Description: An egg-themed chocobo harness created in celebration of Hatching-tide. The authentic hat is rumored to have highly advanced egg-detection functionalities.

Name: Authentic Paramour Barding
Description: A gaudy suit of chocobo armor designed for use during Valentione's Day celebrations. While someincluding your steedmay question your fashion sense, the authenticity of your passion will be indisputable to all.

Name: White Lace Parasol
Description: A frill-rimmed umbrella perfect for any weather except rain. Use to unlock a white lace parasol.

Name: Blue Blossom Parasol
Description: A white umbrella printed with a charming pattern of blue flowers, moogles, chocobos, and more. Use to unlock a blue blossom parasol.

Name: False Shaded Spectacles
Description: These tinted lenses will place you at the forefront of trendinessso long as you avoid bumping into anything while wearing them. Though these were once considered a fashion accessory, trends are ever changing, and style enthusiasts now classify them as facewear. Use to unlock shaded spectacles.

Name: False Classic Spectacles
Description:
Wear these for a classic look of intelligence.*
* Glasses have no effect on actual intelligence. Generous bouts of silence may be advised. Though these were once considered a fashion accessory, trends are ever changing, and style enthusiasts now classify them as facewear. Use to unlock classic spectacles.

Name: Exciting Fiber
Description: Synthetic material invented and woven by the Loporrits. The texture is exhilaratingly different on either side.

Name: Deep-sea Marble
Description: Stone pulled from the bottom of the Sirensong Sea.

Name: Driftseeds
Description: A myriad assortment of seeds harvested from natural flotsam.

Name: Resplendent Feather
Description: This highly collectable feather appears to be larger and more beautiful than that of any documented fauna.

Name: Blue Feather
Description: A feather the color of a deep night sky yearning for dawn.

Name: Appointed Attire Coffer
Description:
A banded chest containing a complete set of appointed attire.

Required level: 1. IL: 1. Cannot be opened in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.

Name: Island Palm Leaf
Description: A fibrous frond from a palm tree native to the Cieldalaes.

Name: Island Apple
Description: A variety of apple selectively bred to not only survive, but flourish in the hot and humid climes of the southern isles.

Name: Island Branch
Description: An extra rest cycle is recommended for any mammets found using this small branch to charge down nearby windmills.

Name: Island Stone
Description: This stone has not gone unturned. Now for the rest...

Name: Island Clam
Description: A clam native to the Rhotano Sea, scooped from island sands despite its best efforts.

Name: Island Laver
Description: One can convert this seaweed into black salt by burning it to a crisp, providing additional salt variety when the entirety of the ocean simply will not suffice.

Name: Island Coral
Description: A fragment of coral native to the Rhotano Sea, commonly found along the coasts of isles in the Cieldalaes.

Name: Islewort
Description: This common grass found growing throughout the Cieldalaes can be used as an ingredient in delicious salads and markedly less delicious potions.

Name: Island Sand
Description: A sack of rough and coarse sand gathered from an isle in the Cieldalaes. Some say it has a mind of its own, with the charming proclivity to get anywhereand everywhereit possibly can.

Name: Island Log
Description: A freshly cut log of timber that mammets have helpfully identified as from a tree.

Name: Island Palm Log
Description: A fragrant, freshly cut log of timber from a palm tree native to the Cieldalaes.

Name: Island Vine
Description: Highly elastic vine harvested on an isle in the Cieldalaes.

Name: Island Sap
Description: A sweet, sticky substance harvested from trees in the Cieldalaes.

Name: Island Copper Ore
Description: A sizable chunk of metallic ore mined in the Cieldalaes.

Name: Island Limestone
Description: This sedimentary rock does not, in fact, taste of refreshing lime. Not that you would know.

Name: Island Rock Salt
Description: This red-hued salt is prized by islekeeps for its role in the creation of homemade frozen treats and myriad practical uses. By contrastand for reasons unknown to the localscertain Cieldalaes tourists insist upon licking it directly.

Name: Island Sugarcane
Description: The sturdy and stout stalk of this native flora is rich in sugar, making it far superior to other island plants. Especially that salad one.

Name: Island Cotton Boll
Description: The fluffy flower of a cotton plant, buffeted by Rhotano breezes no more.

Name: Island Hemp
Description: The stalk of this sun-kissed plant contains fibers used for weavingand only weaving, in case anyone asks.

Name: Island Clay
Description: Natural clay of the Cieldalaes variety, which is to say, excessively and perennially damp.

Name: Island Tinsand
Description: This sand sourced from Cieldalaes waters contains a high concentration of tiny grains of tin.

Name: Island Iron Ore
Description: A sizable chunk of iron-imbued ore mined in the Cieldalaes.

Name: Island Quartz
Description: What distinguishes this translucent mass of unpolished quartz from others is the novelty of its source in the Cieldalaes...so very little, all told.

Name: Island Leucogranite
Description: Attempting to say the name of this pale igneous rock three times in a row without severing one's tongue is a tried and true islekeep's pastime.

Name: Islefish
Description: Much like any wavekin, the islefish loves a nice body of water on a hot day, and also all other days.

Name: Island Squid
Description: A traveling culinarian once claimed that such squid offer a uniquely tropical flavor, but failed to mention how it was seasoned before her passing, thus accidentally spawning a culinary controversy that continues to this day. Let this be a warning.

Name: Island Jellyfish
Description: Innocuous though it may seem, this species of jellyfish makes a habit of swarming island coasts during the summer season, and has not proven particularly reticent to sting those who risk a dip in the water.

Name: Island Alyssum
Description: A rare species of alyssum found only in the Cieldalaes. Though it possesses a sweet honey fragrance, the flavor leaves much to be desired.

Name: Raw Island Garnet
Description: This dark red garnet is hard enough to sharpen a daggera strange priority to have, come to think of it, but here we are.

Name: Island Spruce Log
Description:
A freshly cut log of timber from a spruce native to the Cieldalaes.

...That wasn't so hard, now was it, mammets?

Name: Island Hammerhead
Description: The thalassocracy advises its islekeeps to seek shade and a tall glass of water immediately should they find themselves muttering, There must be a nailhead out there somewherea suspected early symptom of islestroke.

Name: Island Silver Ore
Description: A sizable chunk of shining ore mined in the Cieldalaes.

Name: Island Popoto Set
Description:
A bag chock-full of island popoto pieces that can be used to grow more popotoes, perpetuating an infinite popoto cycle that likely predates the advent of agriculture.

[Growth Period: Two days]

Name: Island Cabbage Seeds
Description:
A bag containing countless cabbage seeds, to be planted by those who enjoy their greens pale and tasting of flatulence.

[Growth Period: Two days]

Name: Isleberry Seeds
Description:
A bag plump with isleberry seeds. Plant them, grow them, weather an intense battle with the local birds, eat them.

[Growth Period: Two days]

Name: Island Pumpkin Seeds
Description:
One might say this is a bag full of pump's kin. Or one might not.

[Growth Period: Two days]

Name: Island Onion Set
Description:
A bag of onion cuttings. They can be planted as is, and will quickly mature into large onion bulbsunless the gardening mammets get hungry.

[Growth Period: Two days]

Name: Island Tomato Seeds
Description:
Though one may be unable to facilitate peace between those who call them toe-may-toes versus toe-mah-toes ere these seeds ripen, there is certainly time to cultivate a robust sunburn in solidarity.

[Growth Period: Two days]

Name: Island Wheat Seeds
Description:
You will get wheat.

[Growth Period: Two days]

Name: Island Corn Seeds
Description:
There was once a La Noscean farmer who insisted the growth of this crop was powered by puns. He has since been shipped off to a sanctuary, where he may do the world no more harm. 

[Growth Period: Two days]

Name: Island Parsnip Seeds
Description:
With a whole bag of these seeds, there is ample opportunity to cultivate the perfect parsnipand carve it into a horrific visage to ward off island spirits, should the mood strike.

[Growth Period: Two days]

Name: Island Radish Seeds
Description:
Rumor has it that these seeds grow into ravishingly redolent radishes. Rumor also has a startlingly suggestive way with words.

[Growth Period: Two days]

Name: Island Popoto
Description: A popoto a day keeps the Lalafells away...or was it the opposite?

Name: Island Cabbage
Description: Crisp and crunchy cabbage cultivated in the Cieldalaes.

Name: Isleberry
Description: A verifiably nonlethal berry found in the Cieldalaes.

Name: Island Pumpkin
Description: Son of a pump, perhaps.

Name: Island Onion
Description: Like its inland cousins, this round onion bulb does not take kindly to knives.

Name: Island Tomato
Description: A ripe tomato cultivated in the Cieldalaes. Goes well with onions, should one be willing to risk it.

Name: Island Wheat
Description: As predicted...wheat.

Name: Island Corn
Description: Always listening.

Name: Island Parsnip
Description: A perfect parsnip cultivated in an island paradise.

Name: Island Radish
Description: A robust radish ready to add a spicy kick to what will inevitably be dubbed island salad.

Name: Sanctuary Fleece
Description: A basket of wool sheared from a sheep that really, really needed the trim.

Name: Sanctuary Claw
Description: A stray claw shed by an animal in the sanctuary pasture.

Name: Sanctuary Fur
Description: Clumps of fur shed by an animal in the sanctuary pasture.

Name: Sanctuary Feather
Description: A white feather shed by a cloudkin in the sanctuary pasture.

Name: Sanctuary Egg
Description: An egg laid by an animal in the sanctuary pasture.

Name: Sanctuary Carapace
Description: A stray carapace shed by an animal in the sanctuary pasture.

Name: Sanctuary Fang
Description: A stray fang removed from an animal in the sanctuary pasture during routine dental care.

Name: Sanctuary Horn
Description: A stray horn shed by an animal in the sanctuary pasture.

Name: Sanctuary Milk
Description: This unlabeled liquid was freshly milked from a beast in the sanctuary pasture. Which one, who can recall?

Name: Island Sweetfeed
Description:
Scrumptious bite-sized fruit pieces prepared as feed for animals in the sanctuary pasture. Satisfactorily filling, a serving of this treat will brighten any hungry critter's mood.

[Improves mood up to: Content]

Name: Island Greenfeed
Description:
A healthy assortment of vegetables prepared as feed for animals in the sanctuary pasture. Pleasantly filling, a serving of this tasty fodder will have animals jumping for joy.

[Improves mood up to: Chipper]

Name: Premium Island Greenfeed
Description:
This assortment of vegetables is the veritable cream of the crop, prepared as feed for animals in the sanctuary pasture. Perfectly filling, a serving of this exquisite fodder will leave animals feeling jubilant and revitalized.

[Improves mood up to: Gleeful]

Name: Makeshift Net
Description:
A crude net made by attaching elastic vines to a branch of fleeting sturdiness. Breaks after a single use due to its frail construction.

[Can be used to catch small animals.]

Name: Makeshift Restraint
Description:
A rudimentary restraint made by attaching metallic weights to each end of a hempen rope. Breaks after a single use due to its frail construction.

[Can be used to catch average-sized animals.]

Name: Makeshift Soporific
Description:
A sleep-inducing pellet made by grinding an assortment of raw materials into a fine powder, before kneading them into a ball with bits of clay. A single pellet may only be used once.

[Can be used to catch large animals.]

Name: Isleworks Sauerkraut
Description:
This fermented cabbage dish has a distinctive sour flavor, and can be preserved for however long one is willing to tempt fate.

Category: Preserved Food
Required Time: 4 hours

Name: Isleworks Baked Pumpkin
Description:
Despite being a homemade recipe cobbled together with ingredients scrounged up in the Cieldalaes, this savory stone oven-baked pumpkin dish is a dainty delight.

Category: Foodstuffs
Required Time: 4 hours

Name: Isleworks Tunic
Description:
A simple hempen tunic woven in the sanctuary workshop.

Category: Attire/Textiles
Required Time: 6 hours

Name: Isleworks Culinary Knife
Description:
A knife made from a sanctuary claw. Can cut a mean vegetable, and nice ones too.

Category: Sundries/Creature Creations
Required Time: 4 hours

Name: Isleworks Brush
Description:
A basic brush assembled in the sanctuary workshop, fashioned from wood. 

Category: Sundries/Woodworks
Required Time: 4 hours

Name: Isleworks Boiled Egg
Description:
Boiled using fresh water from a sanctuary spring. Add a sprinkle of salt and a pinch of pepper for peak delectability.

Category: Foodstuffs/Creature Creations
Required Time: 4 hours

Name: Isleworks Hora
Description:
A pugilist's weapon made from a sanctuary carapace.

Category: Arms/Creature Creations
Required Time: 6 hours

Name: Isleworks Earrings
Description:
A pair of earrings fashioned from a sanctuary fang.

Category: Accessories/Creature Creations
Required Time: 4 hours

Name: Isleworks Butter
Description:
A slab of butter churned from sanctuary milk.

Category: Ingredients/Creature Creations
Required Time: 4 hours

Name: Isleworks Wooden Chair
Description:
A wooden chair assembled in the sanctuary workshop.

Category: Furnishings/Woodworks
Required Time: 6 hours

Name: Isleworks Potion
Description:
A simple restorative concoction made in the sanctuary workshop.

Category: Concoctions
Required Time: 4 hours

Name: Isleworks Necklace
Description:
A simple wooden necklace made in the sanctuary workshop.

Category: Accessories/Woodworks
Required Time: 4 hours

Name: Isleworks Grilled Clam
Description:
A fresh island clam grilled over an open flame until its shell has opened, then seasoned with a simple mixture of rock salt and butter.

Category: Foodstuffs/Marine Merchandise
Required Time: 4 hours

Name: Isleworks Coral Ring
Description:
A sanguine ring made of coral, constructed in the sanctuary workshop.

Category: Accessories/Marine Merchandise
Required Time: 6 hours

Name: Isleworks Barbut
Description:
A copper helm constructed in the sanctuary workshop.

Category: Attire/Metalworks
Required Time: 6 hours

Name: Isleworks Firesand
Description:
A highly flammable substance made in the sanctuary workshop.

Category: Concoctions/Unburied Treasures
Required Time: 4 hours

Name: Isleworks Macuahuitl
Description:
A blunt wooden weapon affixed with jagged obsidian shards. Occasionally used by practitioners of the sword.

Category: Arms/Woodworks
Required Time: 6 hours

Name: Isleworks Brick Counter
Description:
Built with bricks formed from dried island clay, this counter is of nearly professional construction. Nearly.

Category: Furnishings/Unburied Treasures
Required Time: 6 hours

Name: Bronze Sheep
Description:
A stupendous sheep statue sculpted from copper.

Category: Furnishings/Metalworks
Required Time: 8 hours

Name: Isleworks Growth Formula
Description:
A chemical solution capable of increasing the fertility of soil and promoting the growth of fauna.

Category: Concoctions
Required Time: 8 hours

Name: Isleworks Garnet Rapier
Description:
A rapier crafted with an accompanying garnet focus in the sanctuary workshop.

Category: Arms/Unburied Treasures
Required Time: 8 hours

Name: Isleworks Spruce Round Shield
Description:
A wooden shield made in the sanctuary workshop.

Category: Attire/Woodworks
Required Time: 8 hours

Name: Isleworks Shark Oil
Description:
According to an old wives' tale, the shock of losing its mother shortly after birth will induce a shark's offspring to follow her scent until its dying dayor until it finds the individual holding what remains of her.

Category: Sundries/Marine Merchandise
Required Time: 8 hours

Name: Isleworks Silver Ear Cuffs
Description:
A pair of ear cuffs forged from silver ore in the sanctuary workshop.

Category: Accessories/Metalworks
Required Time: 8 hours

Name: Isleworks Sweet Popoto
Description:
Delicious and easily prepared, this sweet variant of popotoes makes for the perfect snack.

Category: Confections
Required Time: 6 hours

Name: Isleworks Parsnip Salad
Description:
Thinly cut slices of fried island parsnips lend a refreshingly sweet flavor to this salad.

Category: Foodstuffs
Required Time: 4 hours

Name: Isleworks Caramels
Description:
This sublime treat is created from caramelized sugar mixed with fresh milk and butter. Best enjoyed with a cup of unsweetened tea.

Category: Confections
Required Time: 6 hours

Name: Isleworks Ribbon
Description:
A charming ribbon woven in the sanctuary workshop.

Category: Accessories/Textiles
Required Time: 6 hours

Name: Isleworks Rope
Description:
A reliable rope woven in the sanctuary workshop.

Category: Sundries/Textiles
Required Time: 4 hours

Name: Isleworks Cavalier's Hat
Description:
A refined hat for the refined personage, woven in the sanctuary workshop.

Category: Attire/Textiles
Required Time: 6 hours

Name: Isleworks Horn
Description:
A horn made fromwait for ita horn.

Category: Sundries/Creature Creations
Required Time: 6 hours

Name: Isleworks Salt Cod
Description:
This salted fish, though delicious, must be soaked in water for several hours before being cooked, lest one's taste buds be overwhelmed.

Category: Preserved Food/Marine Merchandise
Required Time: 6 hours

Name: Isleworks Squid Ink
Description:
A jar of freshly extracted ink often used as an ingredient in dishes, or, when squirted into a witless assailant's eyes, as a means of self-defense.

Category: Ingredients/Marine Merchandise
Required Time: 4 hours

Name: Isleworks Essential Draught
Description:
This unusual concoction of venom extracted from jellyfish and blended with palm leaves and seaweed makes for the perfect morning mixture, sure to put a pep in one's step. Mildly deadly if not taken in small doses.

Category: Concoctions/Marine Merchandise
Required Time: 6 hours

Name: Isleberry Jam
Description:
The best jam in the business. It's truly berry good.

Category: Ingredients
Required Time: 6 hours

Name: Isleworks Onion Soup
Description:
No tears were shed in the making of this soupa boon of mammet-based labor.

Category: Foodstuffs
Required Time: 6 hours

Name: Isleworks Tomato Relish
Description:
The perfect ingredient for those who relish tomatoes.

Category: Ingredients
Required Time: 4 hours

Name: Islefish Pie
Description:
This unusual recipe comprised of an islefish baked in wheat and topped with cane sugar has its fans. Surely.

Category: Confections/Marine Merchandise
Required Time: 6 hours

Name: Isleworks Corn Flakes
Description:
Though this dish of toasted corn flakes mixed with sanctuary milk is normally quite nutritious, it is decidedly less so when a rogue mammet sneakily adds several lumps of sugar to enhance its flavor.

Category: Preserved Food
Required Time: 4 hours

Name: Isleworks Pickled Radish
Description:
This ravishing radish-turned-pickle adds an additional layer of flavor to salads and sandwiches, and can also be enjoyed as a side dish.

Category: Preserved Food
Required Time: 8 hours

Name: Isleworks Iron Axe
Description:
A sturdy two-handed axe forged in the sanctuary workshop.

Category: Arms/Metalworks
Required Time: 8 hours

Name: Isleworks Quartz Ring
Description:
A ring forged from iron, affixed with a small chunk of quartz.

Category: Accessories/Unburied Treasures
Required Time: 8 hours

Name: Isleworks Porcelain Vase
Description:
An astoundingly ornateand unquestionably fragileporcelain vase that ought to make one pause and consider whether the mammets in one's employ are being paid enough for their services. And also when and why they learned to make porcelain vases.

Category: Sundries/Unburied Treasures
Required Time: 8 hours

Name: Isleworks Vegetable Juice
Description:
For those who love the taste of vegetables so much they would see them blended together to be enjoyed all at once. Alternatively, for those who hate vegetables so much they would see them blended until only their barest essence remains, to be imbibed solely for their nutrients.

Category: Concoctions
Required Time: 6 hours

Name: Isleworks Pumpkin Pudding
Description:
Liable to be confused with the flesh of a flan at first glance. Happily, the same cannot be said for the flavor.

Category: Confections
Required Time: 6 hours

Name: Isleworks Sheepfluff Rug
Description:
A rug of such pure fluffiness, even the wildest wolf would whimper in sheer disbelief at its softness.

Category: Furnishings/Creature Creations
Required Time: 6 hours

Name: Isleworks Garden Scythe
Description:
A simple-but-effective gardening tool fashioned in the sanctuary workshop.

Category: Sundries/Metalworks
Required Time: 6 hours

Name: Isleworks Bed
Description:
A surprisingly comfortable bed made in the sanctuary workshop.

Category: Furnishings/Textiles
Required Time: 8 hours

Name: Isleworks Scale Fingers
Description:
A pair of gauntlets crafted from a sanctuary carapace.

Category: Attire/Creature Creations
Required Time: 8 hours

Name: Isleworks Crook
Description:
A wooden, two-handed conjurer's arm crafted in the sanctuary workshop.

Category: Arms/Woodworks
Required Time: 8 hours

Name: Islekeep's Stone Hatchet
Description: Your very first tool on this uninhabited isle. With it in hand, you can gather additional types of materials from designated resources.

Name: Islekeep's Stone Hammer
Description: A roughly hewn mallet useful for hitting things and collecting additional materials from designated resources.

Name: Islekeep's Shovel
Description: A true adventurer shovels responsibly. Use this tool to collect additional materials from designated resources.

Name: Islekeep's Copper Scythe
Description: This curved blade is both pointy and dangerous, but will help you collect additional materials from designated resources so long as you mind your toes.

Name: Islekeep's Bronze Gig
Description: Skewer additional materials when gathering from designated resources and hone your stabbing skills with this spear.

Name: Islekeep's Bronze Beakaxe
Description: No birds were harmed in the making of this beakaxe. Use to collect additional materials from designated resources with a clear(ish) conscience.

Name: Mammet-sized Cropworker's Tools
Description: Gardening equipment specifically crafted for the tiny, industrious hands of mammets.

Name: Mammet-sized Pastureworker's Tools
Description: Creature caretaking tools specifically crafted for the tiny, industrious hands of mammets.

Name: Basic Mammet-sized Builder's Tools
Description: With these tools, any skilled mammet can enact noticeable change upon an island.

Name: Better Mammet-sized Builder's Tools
Description: With these tools, any hardworking mammet can enact noteworthy change upon an island.

Name: Best Mammet-sized Builder's Tools
Description: With these tools, any enthusiastic mammet can enact unbelievable change upon an island.

Name: Bestest Mammet-sized Builder's Tools
Description: With these tools, any mammet at all can become an enlightened genius of development, and pave the way to a paradise of vitality and affluence.

Name: Prime Crystalbloom
Description: This sap-coated plant has taken on a glossy, crystalline appearance, but it is yet in flux. Under the right conditions, it could become sublime.

Name: Sublime Crystalbloom
Description: This peerless crystalbloom has gone from prime to sublime through a process you don't understand and aren't going to worry about. What's important is that it promises an impressive yield from aetherial reduction.

Name: Verdurous Glioaether
Description: Rich green oil refined by aetherial reduction to a highly concentrated state.

Name: Prime Siderite
Description: A ferrous meteorite in apparent flux. Under the right conditions, it could become sublime.

Name: Sublime Siderite
Description: This lucky siderite specimen has gone from prime to sublime through a process you don't understand and aren't going to worry about. What's important is that it promises an impressive yield from aetherial reduction.

Name: Igneous Glioaether
Description: Vibrant red oil refined by aetherial reduction to a highly concentrated state.

Name: Mayashell
Description:
Native to the Font of Maya, this turtle has a tough-yet-beautiful shell.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Aqueous Glioaether
Description: Soothing blue oil refined by aetherial reduction to a highly concentrated state.

Name: Water Otter Fountain Lumber
Description: Basic material used in the construction of a water otter fountain.

Name: Water Otter Fountain Hardware
Description: Metal components used in the construction of a water otter fountain.

Name: Water Otter Fountain Resin
Description: A versatile compound necessary for the construction of a leak-free water otter fountain.

Name: Water Otter Fountain Permit
Description: Written permission for the construction of a sanctuary landmark. Use to unlock the water otter fountain.

Name: Master Carpenter X
Description: This esoteric tomethe tenth in an increasingly lengthy seriescontains advanced woodworking recipes that can only be learned by dedicated carpenters.

Name: Master Blacksmith X
Description: This esoteric tomethe tenth in an increasingly lengthy seriescontains advanced smithing recipes that can only be learned by dedicated blacksmiths.

Name: Master Armorer X
Description: This esoteric tomethe tenth in an increasingly lengthy seriescontains advanced armorcraft recipes that can only be learned by dedicated armorers.

Name: Master Goldsmith X
Description: This esoteric tomethe tenth in an increasingly lengthy seriescontains advanced goldsmithing recipes that can only be learned by dedicated goldsmiths.

Name: Master Leatherworker X
Description: This esoteric tomethe tenth in an increasingly lengthy seriescontains advanced leatherworking recipes that can only be learned by dedicated leatherworkers.

Name: Master Weaver X
Description: This esoteric tomethe tenth in an increasingly lengthy seriescontains advanced clothcraft recipes that can only be learned by dedicated weavers.

Name: Master Alchemist X
Description: This esoteric tomethe tenth in an increasingly lengthy seriescontains advanced alchemy recipes that can only be learned by dedicated alchemists.

Name: Master Culinarian X
Description: This esoteric tomethe tenth in an increasingly lengthy seriescontains advanced cooking recipes that can only be learned by dedicated culinarians.

Name: Rinascita Knuckles
Description: Weapon appearance may take precedence over the display of hand gear.

Name: Raw Rutilated Quartz
Description: An uncut, unpolished stone containing what appears to be rutilated quartz.

One of only a few in existence, this Allagan tomestone contains information regarding the nature of existence that most would be happier without.

Can be exchanged with itinerant moogles for certain items.

The flaky crust serves as a perfect complement to the thundermelon's sweet-yet-electrifying flesh.

(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m

Name: Windswept Archfiend Totem
Description: A tiny idol of Barbariccia carved by a lesser voidsentpresumably against its will.

Name: Unsung Helm of Abyssos
Description:
A stunning but sadly unstoried helmet recovered from Pandmonium.

Two helms can be traded for special headgear.

Name: Unsung Armor of Abyssos
Description:
Stunning but sadly unstoried armor recovered from Pandmonium.

Four suits can be traded for special body gear.

Name: Unsung Ring of Abyssos
Description:
A stunning but sadly unstoried ring recovered from Pandmonium.

One ring can be traded for a special accessory.

Name: Abyssos Mythos I
Description:
A record of truths and somewhat exaggerated stories surrounding the experiments secreted in Abyssos.

Copies of the same Abyssos Mythos volumes can be traded for special gear.

Description:

Name: Unsung Blade of Abyssos
Description: A stunning but sadly unstoried blade recovered from Pandmonium. Though such weapons were once considered highly valuable, demand has dried up and they are now essentially worthless.

Name: Moonshine Brine
Description: A luminous substance produced at the High Crucible of Al-Kimiya. One is probably better off not asking how the alchemical process of enhancing lunar envoy's weapons involves pickling. However, advances in crafting technology have rendered it obsolete.

Name: Moonshine Twine
Description:
A luminous thread produced at the High Crucible of
Al-Kimiya, used to enhance the properties of lunar envoy's vestments in a thoroughly normal fashion. However, advances in crafting technology have rendered it obsolete.

Name: Moonshine Shine
Description: A luminous substance produced at the High Crucible of Al-Kimiya, used to polish lunar envoy's accessories to transcendent perfection. Through copious trial and error, the chances of accoutrements enhanced in such a manner blinding those who look upon them has been reduced to nearly zero. However, advances in crafting technology have rendered it obsolete.

Name: Ultralight Tomestone
Description: A surpassingly small means of storing knowledge, this tomestone was clearly devised as a cost-saving measure, and accordingly lacks durability. This particular variety is not as highly sought as it once was, and may no longer be exchanged for other wares.

Name: Abyssos Weapon Coffer (IL 635)
Description:
A stygian chest containing an Abyssos weapon.

Required level: 90. IL: 635. Weapon type determined by current job or class at time of opening. Cannot be opened in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.

Description: This fist-sized hunk of meteorite contains rich deposits of exceedingly rare manderium ore. Provides a small quantity of mineral oil when subjected to a unique extraction and refinement process.

Name: Magicked Prism (Korpokkur Noggin)
Description: This peculiar contraption creates illusions by weaving together myriad shades of light. Releases a floating korpokkur, replete with realistic dampness.

Name: Windswept Barding
Description: A suit of chocobo armor designed to resemble Barbariccia, the archfiend of wind.

Name: Isle Pioneer's Barding
Description: A suit of practical chocobo armor custom-made for island pioneers.

Name: Modern Aesthetics - Tall Tails
Description:
The realm's premier publication on beauty and fashion, this specific copy of Modern Aesthetics covers, in detail, techniques on tying the perfect high ponytail.

Use to unlock a new hairstyle at the aesthetician.

Name: Modern Aesthetics - Practical Ponytails
Description:
The realm's premier publication on beauty and fashion, this specific copy of Modern Aesthetics covers, in detail, techniques for tying back even the most unruly manes with a minimum of effort.

Use to unlock a new hairstyle at the aesthetician.
Unavailable to female Hrothgar.

Name: Felicitous Fuzzball
Description:
Its presence is your present, and that's all the effort you're getting from this indolent island mammet.

Use item to acquire the felicitous fuzzball minion.

Name: Lumini
Description:
This floating ball of fleshy horror was modeled after an Ea who failed to regain full corporeality.

Use item to acquire the lumini minion.

Name: Clockwork Crimson Chaser
Description:
Painted a sleek shade of red, this miniature machina is a scale replica of the full-size model deployed in military training exercises.

Use item to acquire the clockwork crimson chaser minion.

Name: Clockwork Cerulean Chaser
Description:
Painted a stylish shade of blue, this miniature machina is a scale replica of the full-size model deployed in military training exercises.

Use item to acquire the clockwork cerulean chaser minion.

Name: Wind-up Scarmiglione
Description:
Is that hooded gaze regarding you with affection or insatiable hunger? Hard to tell.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Scarmiglione minion.

Name: Ryunosuke
Description:
Awww, he thinks he's dragons!

Use item to acquire the Ryunosuke minion.

Name: Pterosquirrel
Description:
Despite its chubby appearance, this bright-eyed companion can glide a surprising distance.

Use item to acquire the pterosquirrel minion.

Name: Sponge Silkie
Description:
This palm-sized cleaning familiar's only purpose is to scrub things until they shinetabletops, armor, ear canals, you name it.

Use item to acquire the sponge silkie minion.

Name: Sewer Skink
Description:
When it comes to keeping aqueducts free of creepy-crawlies, this lightning-tongued lizard is the hero of the day.

Use item to acquire the sewer skink minion.

Name: Wind-up Philos
Description:
By the by...you see it too, yes?

Use item to acquire the wind-up philos minion.

Name: Wind-up Erichthonios
Description:
He'll get them all out. He must.

Use item to acquire the Erichthonios minion.

Name: Garlond GL-II Ignition Key
Description: A thin key that ignites your Garlond GL-II's ceruleum engine, bringing the laid-back vehicle rumbling to life.

Name: Miw Miisv Horn
Description: When blown, this horn emits an ethereal sound that summons a Miw Miisv to envelop you in its otherworldly embrace.

Name: Wondrous Lanner Whistle
Description: This whistle emits a shrill tone that is said to summon a legendary falcon bred to serve the goddess among merchants, Rowena.

Name: Magicked Umbrella
Description: Enchanted to fly, this unassuming black umbrella will whisk you off your feet in the most delightful way.

Name: Magicked Parasol
Description: Enchanted to fly, this posh pink parasol will put the whole world at your feet.

Name: Starlight Steed Horn
Description: When blown, this gleaming horn produces a heartwarming sound that calls your Starlight steed to your side.

Name: Sil'dihn Throne
Description: Intricately adorned, this enchanted throne once seated the rulers of Sil'dih.

Name: Silkie Whistle
Description: An ornate whistle that, when blown, emits a squeaky-clean tone that summons the silkie to your side.

Name: Sunforged Crystal
Description: When invoked, this fiery crystal calls forth your blistering sunforged to your side.

Name: Lynx of Imperious Wind Flute
Description: Emitting a turbulent and oppressive tone, this flute summons a lynx of imperious wind to your side.

Name: Sil'dih Survey Framer's Kit
Description:
Tools for enhancing portraits and adventurer plates. Use to unlock embellishments fit for a scavenger of Sil'dihn secrets.
Includes Portrait Elements: Background, Frame, Accent
Includes Plate Elements: Pattern, Portrait Frame

Name: Omicron Framer's Kit
Description:
Tools for enhancing portraits and adventurer plates. Use to unlock embellishments fit for an allied unit.
Includes Portrait Elements: Background, Accent
Includes Plate Elements: Base Plate, Top Border, Bottom Border, Accent

Name: Sil'dihn Potsherd
Description: A relic from the aqueducts of fallen Sil'dih. Surely someone collects these...

Name: Sil'dihn Manuscript
Description: A miraculously undampened record concerning the Sil'dihn sultanate. Surely someone collects these...

Name: Island Prism
Description:
This unusual crystalline prism captures the likeness of a structure and projects it onto an edifice of comparable construction.

[For altering the appearance of structures and registering furniture glamours in your island sanctuary.]

Name: Sabotender Parasol
Description: Equipped with this accessory, none shall prevent you twirling to your heart's delightor else. Use to acquire a sabotender parasol.

Name: Bluepowder Pixie Wings
Description: Indulge your mischievous side once more, this time in a charming shade of aquamarine. Use to acquire a pair of bluepowder pixie wings.

Name: Deceiver's Diamonds
Description: Shines bright like diamonds in the skybut is actually old slag.

Name: Fieldcracker
Description: An otherworldly item of celebration that unleashes a blast of streamers, confetti, and freshly harvested produce.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Derisive Displays
Description: An illustrated manual of how to contemptuously bare your teeth like a verified stinker. Use to learn the /deride emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Ample Appreciation
Description: An illustrated manual of how to shownot tellthat the belle of the ball's newest fashion is quite ambitious, indeed. Use to learn the /wow emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Pumpkin Pleasures
Description: An illustrated manual of the steps required to sink your teeth into a delicious and crumbly autumnal biscuitas if you are not already aware. Use to learn the /cookie emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Taking Sides
Description: An illustrated manual of the steps required to cheer on your compatriots with wild abandon. Use to learn the /spirit emote.

Name: The Fae's Crown Paladin Arms
Description:

Required level: 80. IL: 430.

Description:

Name: Imitation Stained Crystal Roundel
Description: All the beauty of the original imitation stained crystal pane without the sharp edges.

Name: Hanging Planter Branch
Description: A set of hanging potted plants that come with their own handy branch.

Name: Simple Basket
Description: The sort of simple, square basket one might fill with simple, square things.

Name: Gaol Partition Door
Description: A partition with a built-in door. Allows you access to your self-made prison.

Name: Wall-climbing Ivy
Description: These obstinate vines will survive anywhere. Anywhere.

Name: Gaol Partition
Description: A wall of sturdy bars reaching from floor to ceiling. For that woke up on the wrong side of the law feeling.

Name: Hydaelyn, as We Know Her
Description: A map of Hydaelyn as drawn by a Baldesion cartographer. The unknown regions are obscured by billowing clouds.

Name: Wondrous Windoor
Description: You thought it was door, but it was actually window.

Name: Mummer's Shelf
Description: A shelving unit stocked with various tools and costume pieces one might use in a theatrical production.

Name: Cheese Fondue Set
Description:
A steaming pot complete with fondue forks and an assortment of foods to slather in delicious, dripping cheese.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Skill Speed Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  VIT Bonus: +5% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Enigma Partition
Description: A partition devised by the Illuminati, replete with whirlycogs.

Name: Wall-mounted Wings
Description: An ornamental pair of feathery wings to brighten up a plain wall.

Name: Dragonstar aux Marrons
Description:
An ode to the Dragonstar, in dessert form. Fittingly, perhaps, this edible delight is a reimagining of the Sohm Al tart.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Critical Hit Bonus: +4% (Max 10)

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Clavekeeper

This territorial species of moray patrols an area stretching from Seagazer Shoals to the coast of the Clave.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Spangled Pirarucu
Description:
Seemingly clad in a skin of metallic discs, this glimmering wavekin has been called the living treasure of Lake Tusi Mek'ta.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Splendorous Botanist's Component
Description: A rare material acquired by the Boutique of Splendors from one of Norvrandt's eclectic collectors. Required to enhance a base splendorous tool.

Name: Splendorous Miner's Component
Description: A rare material acquired by the Boutique of Splendors from one of Norvrandt's eclectic collectors. Required to enhance a base splendorous tool.

Description: A rare material acquired by the Boutique of Splendors from one of Norvrandt's eclectic collectors. Required to enhance a base splendorous tool.

Name: Splendorous Fishing Reel Component
Description: A rare material acquired by the Boutique of Splendors from one of Norvrandt's eclectic collectors. Required to enhance a base splendorous tool.

Name: Adaptive Botanist's Component
Description: A rare material acquired by the Boutique of Splendors from one of Norvrandt's eclectic collectors. Required to enhance an augmented splendorous tool.

Name: Adaptive Miner's Component
Description: A rare material acquired by the Boutique of Splendors from one of Norvrandt's eclectic collectors. Required to enhance an augmented splendorous tool.

Name: Adaptive Fishing Rod Component
Description: A rare material acquired by the Boutique of Splendors from one of Norvrandt's eclectic collectors. Required to enhance an augmented splendorous tool.

Name: Adaptive Fishing Reel Component
Description: A rare material acquired by the Boutique of Splendors from one of Norvrandt's eclectic collectors. Required to enhance an augmented splendorous tool.

Name: Select Bait Ball
Description: A specialized bait ball procured by the Boutique of Splendors. This unique paste has been designed to attract a highly specific type of catch.

Name: Splendorous Coffer
Description:
A tool chest containing a splendorous tool.

Required level: 90. IL: 570. Primary tool type determined by current class at time of opening. Cannot be opened in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.

Name: Ondo Kelp
Description:
This nutrient-rich seaweed is thought to have been introduced to the coast of Kholusia by the Ondo.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Ken Kiln
Description:
A species of large trout known for its ability to remain snug and warm at all times.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Purpure Cod
Description:
This delicious, fatty fish is particularly coveted by denizens of the ocean floor.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Glorianda's Tear
Description:
Named for the legendary Forebear of Pixies, this small shellfish is so beautiful it oft brings literal tears to the beholder's eyes.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Il Lydha
Description:
It is said that Bismarck himself dubbed this bivalve mollusk Flower of the Rainbow.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Sheep Equipment
Description: Perfect kit for happy sheep.

Name: Mountain Garb
Description: Fur-lined clothing guaranteed to keep its wearer toasty in even the harshest climes.

Name: Classic Voeburtite Cuisine
Description: A steaming pot of homemade cooking to fill the stomach and warm the cockles.

Name: Traditional Voeburtite Handicraft
Description: This expertly crafted statue reflects what the Voeburtite people truly valued: sheep.

Name: Lovely Box of Pretty Things
Description: This gift bursting with charming objects is said to be wildly popular amongst pixies. Funnily enough, the ones saying this are also pixies.

Name: Raw Sheep Fodder
Description: Delightful fodder for happy sheep.

Name: Combustible Fuel
Description: This bundle of flammable material is one spark away from a roaring firefor better or worse.

Name: Natural Ingredients
Description: The precise nature of these ingredients is unknown, but their addition to Voeburtite cuisine has undeniably delicious results.

Name: Crafters' Supplies
Description: Material ideal for the construction of Voeburtite handicrafts, including (but not limited to) sheep paraphernalia.

Name: Lovely Knickknacks
Description: An offering of whimsical miscellanea coveted by any pixie.

Name: Sheep Equipment Materials
Description: An assortment of supplies that, when properly assembled, create tools perfect for tending sheep.

Name: Mountain Garb Materials
Description: An assortment of supplies that, when properly assembled, create clothing ideal for weathering harsh climes.

Name: Classic Voeburtite Ingredients
Description: An assortment of raw ingredients that, when properly prepared, create a delicious meal in the Voeburtite tradition.

Name: Voeburtite Handicraft Materials
Description: An assortment of supplies that, when properly assembled, create a statue of deep cultural significance.

Name: Moderately Pretty Things
Description: With a little care and arrangement, these objects may well become a gift wildly popular amongst pixies.

Name: Catastrophizer
Description:
A king among ponderers, and lord of the waters of the reflecting pool.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 1 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Mossgill Salmon
Description:
A king among greengill salmon, and lord of the waters of the Mover Alpha.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Vidyutvat Wrasse
Description:
A king among garjana wrasse, and lord of the waters of the Great Runoff.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Browned Banana Eel
Description:
A king among banana eels, and lord of the waters of Pavana's Remorse.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Frozen Regotoise
Description:
A king among regotoises, and lord of the Frozen Fissure.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Cosmic Haze
Description:
A king among cosmic noises, and lord of apohelos 18-.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Antheian Dahlia
Description:
A king among antheia, and lord of the waters of Lethe.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Lakeskipper
Description:
This small freshwater fish is aptly named for its unique, prancing movement across the bottom of Bronze Lake.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Bronze Eel
Description:
Despite having achieved a perfect shade of bronze, this slender and snakelike fish understands better than anyone that there is always room for improvement.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Striped Peacock Bass
Description:
Whether the stripes are meant to be attributed to the peacock or bass is still largely up for debate amongst many ichthyologists. Regardless, this moderately sized and greenish fish is quite lovely.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Bronze Trout
Description:
This large freshwater fish has indeed come to resemble its eponymous lake after long years of inhabiting its waters.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Nosceasaur
Description:
This huge scalekin is believed to have inhabited the waters of La Noscea since time immemorial.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Musicking Station Component Materials
Description:
Raw materials that will soon become componentsnot materialsas per Managingway's extremely specific request (for components).

Only for use in Loporrit society quests.

Name: Musicking Station Component
Description:
This soon-to-be element of Dreamingway's dream stage has been carefully crafted to prevent injury to frolicking Loporrits.

Only for use in Loporrit society quests.

Name: Machining Supply Materials
Description:
Materials fit to create supplies fit for a befittingly named Inventingway.

Only for use in Loporrit society quests.

Name: Machining Supplies
Description:
These handcrafted itemsprovided in bulkwill hopefully result in the creation of inventive machines without any Loporrits being harmed in the process.

Only for use in Loporrit society quests.

Name: Restaurant-grade Supply Materials
Description:
Raw materials for certain supplies included in Dickon's list.

Only for use in Loporrit society quests.

Name: Restaurant-grade Supplies
Description:
Supplies indispensable to the sophisticated and sanitary serving of cuisine.

Only for use in Loporrit society quests.

Name: Painting Supply Materials
Description:
A convenient package of components necessary to create tools for enthusiastic amateur artists.

Only for use in Loporrit society quests.

Name: Painting Supplies
Description:
Judging by the requested volume, Loporrits really go through art supplies.

Only for use in Loporrit society quests.

Name: Radio Equipment Materials
Description:
Components apparently vital to the creation of inscrutable equipment. You don't knowyou just work here.

Only for use in Loporrit society quests.

Name: Radio Equipment
Description:
Delicate supplies for the broadcasting station, carefully packaged so as to sustain minimal damage from inevitable Loporrit excitement.

Only for use in Loporrit society quests.

Name: Audio Materials
Description:
An assortment of pieces compatible with Loporrit-made sound systems.

Only for use in Loporrit society quests.

Name: Audio Spare Parts
Description:
Useful parts for Loporrits who prefer surround sound.

Only for use in Loporrit society quests.

Name: Wind Instrument Component Materials
Description:
An assortment of materials necessary for creating a wind instrument component.

Only for use in Loporrit society quests.

Name: Wind Instrument Component
Description:
Why settle for humming when you could be piping!
Pipingway

Only for use in Loporrit society quests.

Name: Coin Manufacturing Component Materials
Description:
Materials for a component used in the manufacture of Loporrit carats, Coiningway's monetary invention.

Only for use in Loporrit society quests.

Name: Coin Manufacturing Component
Description:
This component will allow the Loporrits to manufacture more of their new currency, thereby paving the way to prosperityor rampant inflation.

Only for use in Loporrit society quests.

Name: Memorabilia Materials
Description:
An assortment of supplies useful for the production of self-gratifying paraphernalia.

Only for use in Loporrit society quests.

Name: Signed Memorabilia
Description:
A box of mementos personally crafted and signed by none other than Etheirys's Warrior of Light.

Only for use in Loporrit society quests.

Name: Lighting Materials
Description:
An assortment of supplies compatible with Loporrit-made lighting arrays.

Only for use in Loporrit society quests.

Name: Lighting Parts
Description:
Spare parts used for the upkeep of lights both dazzling and glaring.

Only for use in Loporrit society quests.

Name: Carrotlight Materials
Description:
An assortment of materials compatible with carrotlights.

Only for use in Loporrit society quests.

Name: Carrotlight Pieces
Description:
A set of pieces used for the assembly of delicious-looking luminescent carrotlights. Do not consume.

Only for use in Loporrit society quests.

Name: Cleaner Upgrade Component Materials
Description:
Materials for a component needed to upgrade the cleaner machina.

Only for use in Loporrit society quests.

Name: Cleaner Upgrade Component
Description:
Designed to enhance the effectiveness of the cleaner machina, this component will ensure that the Loporrits continue to have good, clean funthe kind they love best.

Only for use in Loporrit society quests.

Name: Audio Recording Component Materials
Description:
Materials for a component needed to grant a supporter machina audio recording capabilities.

Only for use in Loporrit society quests.

Name: Audio Recording Component
Description:
When installed, this component will grant a supporter machina audio recording capabilities, thus allowing the Loporrits to experience the weirdness of hearing their own voice.

Only for use in Loporrit society quests.

Name: Parasital Infection Protection Suit Component Materials
Description:
An assortment of materials to be used in the assembly of an airtight protective suit component.

Only for use in Loporrit society quests.

Name: Parasital Infection Protection Suit Component
Description:
Once implemented into the PIPS, this airtight component will serve to keep Loporrits safe from infectious sporesassuming any choose to wear the thing.

Only for use in Loporrit society quests.

Name: Occult Paraphernalia Materials
Description:
An assortment of strange and hazardous materials to be used in the construction of occult paraphernalia.

Only for use in Loporrit society quests.

Name: Occult Paraphernalia
Description:
What Thrillingway intends to do with this bizarre instrument is a question best left unanswered.

Only for use in Loporrit society quests.

Name: Cookbook Printing Paraphernalia Materials
Description:
An assortment of materials to be used in the grand pursuit of printing additional copies of Cookingway's highly sought-after cookbook.

Only for use in Loporrit society quests.

Name: Cookbook Printing Paraphernalia
Description:
At the rate his cookbooks are being printed, Cookingway's authorial exploits may soon eclipse his culinary achievements.

Only for use in Loporrit society quests.

Name: Carrot Chiller Component Materials
Description:
An assortment of materials compatible with the cooking station's carrot chiller.

Only for use in Loporrit society quests.

Name: Carrot Chiller Component
Description:
This component will serve to repair the cooking station's cherished carrot chilleruntil it inevitably breaks down again.

Only for use in Loporrit society quests.

Name: Loporrit's Gathering Tool Component Materials
Description:
An assortment of materials compatible with Loporrit-made gathering equipment.

Only for use in Loporrit society quests.

Name: Loporrit's Gathering Tool Component
Description:
A much-needed component for a Loporrit-sized tool capable of slicing and dicing even the sturdiest of fungi.

Only for use in Loporrit society quests.

Name: Kitchen Materials
Description:
A myriad array of kitchen supplies awaiting proper assembly.

Only for use in Loporrit society quests.

Name: Popular Kitchen Goods
Description:
Perfect kitchen items for the fuzzy, small-handed chef.

Only for use in Loporrit society quests.

Name: Potentially Body-enhancing Materials
Description:
Materials theoretically handy for creating items to tone, bulk, and provide satisfying gains to Loporrit bodies.

Only for use in Loporrit society quests.

Name: Exercise Equipment
Description:
Anything can be used to bolster fitness if you put your mind to it...right?

Only for use in Loporrit society quests.

Name: Artistic Materials
Description:
An assortment of materials to aid in the creation of paintthe brighter and sparklier, the better.

Only for use in Loporrit society quests.

Name: Paint-mixer's Toolbox
Description:
A crate of elements essential to the Loporrit who keeps the paint abundant, bright, and sparkly.

Only for use in Loporrit society quests.

Name: Sudsy Soap Supplies
Description:
An assortment of materials that will yield a highly effective, nontoxic cleaner.

Only for use in Loporrit society quests.

Name: Super Sudsy Soap Bars
Description:
Cleansing material guaranteed to magically dissolve any and all unwanted smudges. Gentle on fur and whiskers.

Only for use in Loporrit society quests.

Name: Fungi Fighter Materials
Description:
An assortment of pieces that may be assembled into a weapon debilitating to menacing mushrooms.

Only for use in Loporrit society quests.

Name: Fungi Fighter
Description:
Mushrooms will die.

Only for use in Loporrit society quests.

Name: Fashionable Materials
Description:
An assortment of supplies that hold great artistic promise for the fashion-forward Loporrit.

Only for use in Loporrit society quests.

Name: Fashionable Thingums
Description:
Objects meant to dazzle with individuality. Whether they are successful depends on the eye of the beholder.

Only for use in Loporrit society quests.

Name: Jhinga Biryani
Description:
A mouthwatering dish of bomba rice seasoned with hearty spices and baked with Thavnairian prawns.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Jhinga Curry
Description:
This variation of Thavnairian curry is a perfect marriage of regional prawns and traditional spices.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Zoisite
Description: An indigo jewel.

Name: Craftsman's Alkahest
Description: When applied to items such as crafting and gathering gear, this experimental alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to detrimental elements, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Mornveil Tree Bark
Description: The quality of this bark is undeniable and likely due to the hospitable surrounds of Labyrinthos.

Name: Raw Zoisite
Description: An uncut, unpolished stone containing what appears to be zoisite.

Name: Jhinga
Description:
The rusty red carapace of this Near Eastern prawn protects tender flesh that is a mainstay of popular Thavnairian cuisine.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Earthbreak Aethersand
Description: This coarse-grained, highly concentrated aetherially reduced mineral matter carries the distinctive scent of soil.

Name: Earthen Quartz
Description: A rock with an elemental aspect leaning heavily towards earth.

Name: Sophora Roots
Description: Tendrils of a perennial plant replete with earth aether.

Name: Verdigris Guppy
Description:
A fish prized not only for its green mottled beauty, but for the rarity of materials its body provides.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 1 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Complementary Chondrite
Description: This rare form of chondrite contains spherule groupings which greatly amplify aetherial conductivity when synthesized with manderiuman advanced process which demands a heightened state of battle-based enlightenment.

Name: Orthos Aetherpool Fragment
Description: A fragment of aetherpool gear found in Eureka Orthos.

Name: Orthos Tomestone
Description: Containing information on the Allagan Empire's most clandestine research, these tomestones were strictly prohibited from leaving the halls of Eureka Orthos.

Name: Orthos Aetherpool Grip
Description: A sturdy grip designed for Orthos aetherpool arms.

Name: Orthos Potion
Description:
Grants the effect of Rehabilitation (HP regeneration) to self.

Duration: 30s
Only available for use in Eureka Orthos.

Name: Bronze-tinged Sack
Description: This cumbersome bag containing a portion of Eureka Orthos's Accursed Hoard has been sealed with powerful magicks. Only an appraiser who has devoted their lives to studying Allagan relics might be able to undo such a seal.

Name: Silver-tinged Sack
Description: This cumbersome bag containing a portion of Eureka Orthos's Accursed Hoard has been sealed with powerful magicks. Only an appraiser who has devoted their lives to studying Allagan relics might be able to undo such a seal.

Name: Gold-tinged Sack
Description: This cumbersome bag containing a portion of Eureka Orthos's Accursed Hoard has been sealed with powerful magicks. Only an appraiser who has devoted their lives to studying Allagan relics might be able to undo such a seal.

Name: Special Midnight Archon Egg
Description: The dark enamel finish of this prophetic egg is singularly captivating to behold.

Name: Flamecloaked Archfiend Totem
Description: A small idol of Rubicante carved by a voidsent. The admiration with which it was created is palpable.

Name: Euphrosyne Coin
Description: An age-worn artifact recovered from Euphrosyne. Once considered to be of great religious significance, a sudden influx caused their value to plummet, rendering them almost worthless.

Name: Omega Totem
Description: This mechanical idol was created with technology beyond both the capabilities and understanding of mankind.

Name: Sukiya-zukuri Cottage Walls
Description:
A set of four walls designed for those who wish to transform their estate into a stylish Far Eastern residence with attached onsen.

Can only be used with cottages on small plots of land.

Name: Sukiya-zukuri House Walls
Description:
A set of four walls designed for those who wish to transform their estate into a stylish Far Eastern residence with attached onsen.

Can only be used with houses on medium plots of land.

Name: Sukiya-zukuri Mansion Walls
Description:
A set of four walls designed for those who wish to transform their estate into a stylish Far Eastern residence with attached onsen.

Can only be used with mansions on large plots of land.

Name: Hyper-Potion
Description: This highly concentrated concoction instantly restores a prodigious amount of HP.

Name: Augmented Rinascita Knuckles
Description: Weapon appearance may take precedence over the display of hand gear.

Name: Dharmic Rain
Description: A highly effective elixir presented as the pinnacle of alchemical achievement in Meghaduta.

Name: Hannish Certificate of Grade 2 Import
Description: A note of promise granted for the delivery of rinascita equipment.

Description: Amazing Manderville weapon.

Name: Ultimate Omega Knuckles
Description: Weapon appearance may take precedence over the display of hand gear.

Name: Island Resin
Description: It may be resinable to assume that handicrafts created with this natural polymer will resinate with the beholder.

Name: Island Coconut
Description: Lalafells must undergo special training to harvest this drupe, as it is larger, heavier, and altogether far more formidable than any other species of coconut.

Name: Island Beehive Chip
Description: A sweet fragment of an innocent bee's former abode. Well done, you monster.

Name: Island Wood Opal
Description: This opal was once a shard of petrified wood, proving that you can become anything you set your mind to so long as you have dedication and millions of years at your disposal.

Name: Multicolored Isleblooms
Description: Beautiful island flowers of various species native to the Cieldalaes.

Name: Island Paprika Seeds
Description:
Plant these seeds to grow bushels of healthy red peppers that may or may not taste like absolutely nothing once you grind them into dust.

[Growth Period: Two days]

Name: Island Leek Set
Description:
Bury your leeks. Never look back.

[Growth Period: Two days]

Name: Island Paprika
Description: A plump and healthy pepper, ready to be ruthlessly dried and ground into powder.

Name: Island Leek
Description: A vegetable once buried and abandoned. If only it had eyes with which to gaze woefully, tears would surely be leaking from them.

Name: Islekeep's Iron Hatchet
Description: An iron iteration of your very first island tool. Heavy in your hand, it promises to be useful in collecting additional materials from designated resources. I know, you whisper back.

Name: Prime Sphongos
Description: A spongy mushroom imbued with fascinating life energy. Under the right conditions, it could become sublime.

Name: Sublime Sphongos
Description: This magnificent sphongos has gone from prime to sublime through a process you don't understand and aren't going to worry about. What's important is that it promises an impressive yield from aetherial reduction.

Name: Pure Verdurous Glioaether
Description: Rich green oil refined by aetherial reduction to an extremely concentrated state.

Name: Prime Achondrite
Description: A meteorite primarily comprised of olivine and pyroxene. Under the right conditions, it could become sublime.

Name: Sublime Achondrite
Description: This superior chunk of achondrite has gone from prime to sublime through a process you don't understand and aren't going to worry about. What's important is that it promises an impressive yield from aetherial reduction.

Name: Pure Igneous Glioaether
Description: Vibrant red oil refined by aetherial reduction to an extremely concentrated state.

Name: Phyllinos
Description:
This ingenious creation traverses the fine line between plant and fish in a way that none have before nor ever will again.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Pure Aqueous Glioaether
Description: Soothing blue oil refined by aetherial reduction to an extremely concentrated state.

Name: Smaller Water Otter Fountain Lumber
Description: How much wood would an odder otter water if an odder otter watered some wood? Component crucial to the successful construction of the smaller water otter fountain.

Name: Smaller Water Otter Fountain Hardware
Description: Attempting to say odder otter metal several times aloud demonstrates some manner of mettle indeed. Components crucial to the successful construction of the smaller water otter fountain.

Name: Smaller Water Otter Fountain Resin
Description: Odder otters that stick together, stay together, and don't leak all over your garden. Components crucial to the successful construction of the smaller water otter fountain.

Name: Phoenix Riser Suit
Description: Cannot equip with arm, leg, or foot gear.

Name: Gaia's Attire
Description:
Fits: All 
Cannot equip with arm, leg, or foot gear.

Name: Isleworks Coral Sword
Description:
A timeless and highly pointy sword that has been faithfully recreated throughout the ages.

Category: Arms/Marine Merchandise
Required Time: 8 hours

Name: Isleworks Coconut Juice
Description:
A delicious beverage debatably improved by adding lime.

Category: Confections/Concoctions
Required Time: 4 hours

Name: Isleworks Honey
Description:
Thick and lickerous syrup obtained by shamelessly exploiting the hard work of bees.

Category: Confections/Ingredients
Required Time: 4 hours

Name: Isleworks Seashine Opal
Description:
A natural opal polished to a dazzling shine by tiny mammet hands.

Category: Unburied Treasures
Required Time: 8 hours

Name: Isleworks Dried Flowers
Description:
These island flowers are still beautiful, even in death.

Category: Sundries/Furnishings
Required Time: 6 hours

Name: Isleworks Powdered Paprika
Description:
Peppers ground to a fine, bright red powder. Can be sprinkled on food to impress fellow islekeeps with the appearance of sophistication.

Category: Ingredients/Concoctions
Required Time: 4 hours

Name: Isleworks Cawl Cennin
Description:
Thick soup developed from a base of leeks fried in butter.

Category: Concoctions/Creature Creations
Required Time: 6 hours

Name: Isleworks Isloaf
Description:
While technically bursting with essential nutrients, this bread is about as flavorful as damp parchment.

Category: Foodstuffs/Concoctions
Required Time: 4 hours

Name: Isleworks Popoto Salad
Description:
This delightful mash of popotoes and apples is rumored to have been seasoned with the tears of mammets unable to partake in its delicious glory.

Category: Foodstuffs
Required Time: 4 hours

Name: Isleworks Dressing
Description:
Not to be confused with a different sort of island dressing, this onion-based condiment is clearly the superior version as mammets were involved in its creation.

Category: Ingredients
Required Time: 4 hours

Name: False Monarchy Attire Coffer
Description:
A banded chest containing a full set of false monarchy attire.

Required level: 1. IL: 1. Cannot be opened in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.

Name: Irregular Tomestone of Mendacity
Description:
One of only a few in existence, this Allagan tomestone contains falsehoods so compelling, it can sway even the most discerning minds from the path of knowledge.

Can be exchanged with itinerant moogles for certain items.

Name: Paladin's Flamecloaked Arms (IL 625)
Description:
A set of arms containing a flamecloaked broadsword and flamecloaked scutum.

Required level: 90. IL: 625.

Name: Simple Low Table
Description: A quaint and practical addition to any room.

Name: Flower Boucage
Description: Beautiful addition to home dcor or archaic punishment for offending flora? Perhaps it is both.

Name: Faerie Door
Description: This sweet little door is believed to be used by the fae. Where it leads, none may ever know...

Name: Rattan Sofa
Description: A wicker couch painstakingly woven from climbing palm.

Name: Charcoal Iron
Description: This household instrument will smooth the wrinkles from your clothing, thereby smoothing the wrinkles from your forehead. Do not apply directly to the forehead.

Name: Grounded Cactuar
Description: A potted cactus lauded for its level head and firm grip on reality.

Name: Far Eastern Stained Crystal Roundel
Description: A beautiful, circular pane of stained crystal designed in the style of the Far East.

Name: Timeworn Thaumaturgic Array
Description: This intimidating set of instruments is mysteriously distilling sinister and arcane liquids all by itself. While this fact is unnerving to say the least, it may be best to let it brew...

Name: Darkest Hourglass
Description: An old chronometer that measures silence as much as time.

Name: Classical Water Jug
Description: A simple-yet-handsome pitcher with a timeless design.

Name: Allagan Terminal Alpha
Description: An N-shaped device created to access ancient Allagan systems. Though no longer functional, the light-up display is still hauntingly beautiful.

Name: Allagan Terminal Beta
Description: An L-shaped device created to access ancient Allagan systems. Though no longer functional, the light-up display is still hauntingly beautiful.

Name: Toy Cooking Set
Description: A whimsical set of chocobo-themed toys guaranteed to thrill any aspiring chef.

Name: Lalafell Lifter
Description: Tired of being forgotten in conversation and hitting the edge of the table with your nose? No longer with the Lalafell Lifter, the chair specifically designed to uplift even the smallest of heroes.

Name: Highland Partition
Description: This sturdy partition designed in the highland fashion is partially customizable.

Name: Highland Partition Door
Description: A partition with a built-in door designed to complement highland residences.

Name: Alpine Pillar
Description: A decorative pillar designed in the alpine fashion.

Name: Enigma Wall Chronometer
Description: A chronometer devised by the Illuminati, particularly abundant with whirlycogs.

Name: Rainbow Hopping Rug
Description: A multicolored mat perfect for vigorous and rhythmic bouncing.

Name: Loporrit Material Supplier Permit
Description:
This permit allows the hiring of Loporrit material suppliers on the estate.

Private chambers (apartments), cottages, houses, and mansions can host 4, 6, 8, and 10 vendors, respectively.

Name: Loporrit Junkmonger Permit
Description:
This permit allows the hiring of Loporrit junkmongers on the estate.

Private chambers (apartments), cottages, houses, and mansions can host 4, 6, 8, and 10 vendors, respectively.

Name: Loporrit Mender Permit
Description:
This permit allows the hiring of Loporrit menders on the estate.

Private chambers (apartments), cottages, houses, and mansions can host 4, 6, 8, and 10 vendors, respectively.

Name: Loporrit Servingway Permit
Description:
This permit allows the hiring of Loporrit manservants on the estate.

Private chambers (apartments), cottages, houses, and mansions can host 4, 6, 8, and 10 vendors, respectively.

Name: Hannish Pendant Wall Light
Description: A wall lantern crafted in the Hannish style.

Name: Hannish Screen
Description: A resplendent portable partition of Hannish design.

Name: Hannish Bed
Description: A roomy bed embellished with gold in the Hannish style.

Name: Hannish Chair
Description: A low-seated chair of Hannish design.

Name: Hannish Round Table
Description: An intricately patterned round table designed in the Hannish fashion.

Name: Hannish Table Lamp
Description: As much a decorative display of masterful Hannish metalwork as practical lantern.

Name: Hannish Bookshelf Partition
Description: A partition designed in the Hannish fashion, boasting a small library on one side.

Name: Hannish Rug
Description: A rectangular rug woven in the Hannish fashion.

Name: Waterfall Partition
Description:
A partition of softly falling water.

Up to twenty may be placed in a single estate.

Name: Infernal Archfiend Cloak
Description:
Smoldering with arcane power, this dark tapestry is perpetually warm to the touch.

One per estate only.

Name: Faerie Round Table
Description: The glass tabletop presents the illusion of solid water, but the claims that faeries assemble here for meetings has yet to be satisfyingly explained.

Name: Pudding Pudding
Description:
Delicious pudding in the shape of pudding. What's not to understand?

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Determination Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  VIT Bonus: +5% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Exciting Balloon
Description: The unblinking stare of this balloon is reminding you what a great time you're havingjust like in the Excitatron 6000.

Name: Simple Sink
Description: A small and practical washbasin.

Name: Crystal Tower Phasmascape
Description: This advanced magitek contraption displays the haunting majesty of the Crystal Tower at nighttime.

Name: Urth's Fount Phasmascape
Description: This advanced magitek contraption displays the electrifying stillness of Urth's Fount.

Name: Hatching-tide MMXXII Advertisement
Description: A hand-painted notice advertising the hippity-hoppity Hatching-tide festivities of a year gone by.

Name: Little Ladies' Day MMXXI Advertisement
Description: A hand-painted notice advertising a lovely Little Ladies' Day of a year gone by.

Name: Low Garden Hedge
Description: A stand of shrubbery cut to optimal height for confounding local Lalafells.

Name: Orthos Display Stand
Description:
An Allagan hologram which depicts a legendary weapon.

One per estate only.

Name: Smaller Water Otter Fountain
Description: A water otter fountain that is smaller and somehow odder than the water otter fountain found in island sanctuaries.

Name: Hannish Lamppost
Description: A lamppost of steel such as one might see lining a Hannish street.

Name: Simple Fountain
Description: A basic stone contraption from which water pours forth. May the sound of its splashing soothe unsettled souls.

Name: Jinrikisha
Description: A Far Eastern cab designed to be manpowered, not bird-poweredand definitely not Namazu-powered.

Name: Lemonade Stand
Description: When life gives you lemons, create a lemonade empire from but a humble stall like this one.

Name: Dorpokkur Kiln
Description: A charming woodstove topped with a decorative dorpokkur, incidentally colored a striking shade of burnt.

Name: Stone Garden Wall
Description: Someone painstakingly fitted these stones into a rustic wall for your garden. You didn't, but somebody did.

Name: Colorful Flower Patch
Description: A burst of blossoms that will bring a smile to any face.

Name: Hannish Interior Wall
Description: An interior wall designed to complement Hannish residences.

Name: Hannish Tile Flooring
Description: Dark, resplendent tiling detailed in gold.

Name: Hannish Ceiling Lamp
Description: A hanging light fixture of undeniably Hannish design.

Name: Stuffed Loporrit
Description: Alas, poor Stuffingway! I knew him...

Name: Authentic Valentione Mobile
Description: Though none of them are anatomically accurate, these dangling decorations crafted into various heart shapes are undeniably authentic.

Name: Authentic Eggsemplary Basket
Description: An elegant, enticing, and authentic example of exceptional egg-hunting.

Name: Authentic Hatching-tide Mobile
Description: The authentic twirl and bob of this Hatching-tide mobile reminds you of all the hidden eggs you have yet to find...

Description: Documentation of noteworthy accomplishments for Season Four of Crystalline Conflict.

Description: Documentation of noteworthy accomplishments for Season Four of Crystalline Conflict.

Name: Morning Glory Seeds
Description:
If given even a modicum of attention, these seeds will grow into delicate, twining flowers that greet each day in full blossomwhich is more than can be said of most people.

For use in planters.

Name: Red Morning Glories
Description:
A bunch of red morning glories, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Blue Morning Glories
Description:
A bunch of blue morning glories, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Yellow Morning Glories
Description:
A bunch of yellow morning glories, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Green Morning Glories
Description:
A bunch of green morning glories, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Orange Morning Glories
Description:
A bunch of orange morning glories, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Purple Morning Glories
Description:
A bunch of purple morning glories, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: White Morning Glories
Description:
A bunch of white morning glories, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.
