Name: Black Morning Glories
Description:
A bunch of black morning glories, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Rainbow Morning Glories
Description:
A bunch of multicolored morning glories, selectively fertilized to achieve a variety of vibrant colors.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Flamecloaked Barding
Description: A suit of chocobo armor designed to resemble Rubicante, the archfiend of fire.

Name: Allagan Barding
Description: A suit of chocobo armor that may or may not be an authentic and precious relic of an ancient civilization.

Name: Modern Aesthetics - Sharlayan Rebellion
Description:
The realm's premier publication on beauty and fashion, this limited edition of Modern Aesthetics covers, in detail, techniques on transforming your style into that of the prominentsome would say not prominent enoughmember of the Scions of the Seventh Dawn, Alisaie Leveilleur.
* Please note that, while bearing certain similarities, this edition is decidedly not a rerun of a previous edition. We thank you for your understanding.

Use to unlock a new hairstyle at the aesthetician.
Unavailable to female Hrothgar.

Name: Modern Aesthetics - A Close Shave
Description:
The realm's premier publication on beauty and fashion, this specific copy of Modern Aesthetics covers, in detail, techniques for cropping one's locks so as to improve aerodynamics in the face of impending danger, whilst still remaining at the height of trendiness.

Use to unlock a new hairstyle at the aesthetician.
Unavailable to female Hrothgar.

Name: Corgi
Description:
Fluffy, full of beans, and fit for a queen.

Use item to acquire the corgi minion.

Name: Sky Blue Back
Description:
Born in the Cieldalaes. It was born in the Cieldalaes. It was born in the Cieldalaes. Born in the Cieldalaes.

Use item to acquire the sky blue back minion.

Name: Suzusaurus
Description:
Might be able to tow a rowboat to safety if not a galleon.

Use item to acquire the suzusaurus minion.

Name: Mama Automaton
Description:
Mama knows best. Listen to Mama.

Use item to acquire the Mama automaton minion.

Name: Wind-up Cagnazzo
Description:
The puddles and ponds are his to command.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Cagnazzo minion.

Name: Findingway
Description:
Can find his own way without you, but chooses to tag along.

Use item to acquire the Findingway minion.

Name: Private Pachypodium
Description:
Its detonating days are thankfully over.

Use item to acquire the private pachypodium minion.

Name: Wind-up Halone
Description:
For those who like it icy cold.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Halone minion.

Name: Bantam Train
Description:
It choo-choo-chooses to haunt you.

Use item to acquire the bantam train minion.

Name: Wind-up Godbert
Description:
No less gentlemanly for its compact size, this mammet stands ever ready to do what only a Manderville can.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Godbert minion.

Name: Wind-up Aidoneus
Description:
If sighs could kill, you'd be dead a thousand times over.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Aidoneus minion.

Name: Moon-hopper Identification Key
Description: A thin, rectangular piece of some unknown material. Placing it near your moon-hopper will magically bring the machine to life.

Name: Aeturna Horn
Description: Wrought of bone, this horn emits a vigorous sound that summons the aeturna to your side.

Name: Ceruleum Balloons
Description: Filled with gasified ceruleum, this festive assortment of balloons will carry you sky-high in high spirits.

Name: Anden III Horn
Description: When blown, this sheep's horn emits a muted (and somewhat confused) sound that brings Anden III rustling to your side.

Name: Blackjack Identification Key
Description: A thin, rectangular piece of what appears to be cermet. Placing it near the Blackjack will magically bring the vessel to life.

Name: Phaethon Horn
Description: Hot to the touch, this horn emits a furious sound that summons forth Phaethon.

Name: Pinky Identification Key
Description: A thin, rectangular piece of what appears to be cermet. Placing it near your Pinky will magically bring the elephantine machine trumpeting to life.

Name: Lynx of Righteous Fire Flute
Description: Emitting an ardent and dignified tone, this flute summons a lynx of righteous fire to your side.

Name: Magitek Avenger G1 Identification Key
Description: A thin, rectangular piece of what appears to be cermet. Placing it near your magitek avenger G1 will magically bring the machine to life.

Name: Chrysomallos Horn
Description: When blown, this garish horn emits an ostentatious sound that summons forth Chrysomallos, the golden ram of legend.

Name: Island Alligator Horn
Description: Scaly to the touch, the sound of this horn brings your island alligator strutting to your side.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Illusions of Grandeur
Description: An illustrated manual of how to perform bewitching parlor tricks without expending a drop of aether. Use to learn the /magictrick emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Fan Fare
Description: An illustrated manual of the various steps and gestures that comprise the Little Ladies' Dance. Use to learn the /littleladiesdance emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Discreet Discussion
Description: An illustrated manual of the precise motions necessary for a surreptitious-yet-elegant conversation. Use to learn the /linkpearl emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Unnerving Undulations
Description: An illustrated manual of grotesque movements used by miscreants to terrorize and intimidate. Use to learn the /frighten emote.

Name: Magicked Prism (Faux Fox Face)
Description: This peculiar contraption creates illusions by weaving together myriad shades of light. The proud work of a particular auspice.

Name: Tropicracker
Description: An otherworldly item of celebration that unleashes a blast of streamers, confetti, and flowering island foliage.

Name: Felicitous Furball Umbrella
Description: Thankfully, this parasol is not nearly as indolent as its eponymous mammet, and will be sure to keep you dry during island squalls without a word of complaint. Use to acquire a felicitous furball umbrella.

Name: Raindrop Defense System
Description: This advanced piece of technology was painstakingly designed to protect its bearer from descending moistureno matter the cost. Use to acquire a raindrop defense system.

Paladin's Rubellux Arms
Description:
A set of arms containing a rubellux broadsword and rubellux scutum.

Required level: 80. IL: 430.

Name: Faded Copy of Forged in Crimson
Description: Timeworn pages of sheet music containing the full score for Forged in Crimson.

Name: Pearl of Flames
Description: The might of an archfiend is trapped within this precious jewel. If taken in hand, one can still feel the heat of eternal flames pulsing within...

Name: Flamecloaked Weapon Coffer (IL 625)
Description:
A slightly smoking chest containing a flamecloaked weapon.

Required level: 90. IL: 625. Weapon type determined by current job or class at time of opening. Cannot be opened in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.

Name: Timeworn Thaumaturgic Instruments
Description: These arcane tools were recovered from the ocean floor and quiver as though desiring to be reassembled.

Name: Enigmatic Gear
Description: At first glance a stray part from some ship, this gear seems equipped with complicated infrastructure.

Name: White Granite
Description: Strong, white stone pulled from the bottom of the ocean.

Name: Ominous Plating
Description: A somehow unnerving sheet of metal recovered from the ocean floor. If you press your ear flat against its surface, you can hear the screech of a train whistle in the distance.

Name: Hagnos Cloth
Description: Created in a stroke of pure brilliance, this soft, versatile fabric is incapable of being soiled in any way.

Name: Exciting Tonic
Description: An exciting pink liquid available in the Excitatron 6000. So exciting, in fact, that some collectors will even barter goods for just another bottle.

Name: Timeworn Ophiotauroskin Map
Description:
This bottle holds a timeworn map classified as risk-reward grade 15 among treasure hunters.

Use the action Decipher to extract the map and examine its contents.
Level 90 full party (eight players) recommended.

Name: Burning Horn
Description: A fragment of horn that is uncomfortably hot to the touch. Surely someone collects these...

Name: Potentially Special Timeworn Map
Description:
This bottle is holding what appears to be a singularly valuable leather map.

Use the action Decipher to extract the map and examine its contents.
Level 90 full party (eight players) recommended.
Guaranteed to summon a teleportation portal.

Description: Music roll for Somewhere in the World (Ambitions Writhe). Use to add to your orchestrion list.

Name: Gripgel
Description: A particularly strong adhesive created by the serendipitous combination of unknown substances.

Name: Hyposkhesphyra Weapon Coffer
Description:
A banded chest containing seven hyposkhesphyrai.

Required level: 1. IL: 1. Cannot be opened in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.

Name: Dark Cherry Log
Description: A rough-cut log of dark cherry timber.

Name: Softsilver Ore
Description: A decent-sized piece of rock containing a naturally occurring mix of silver and quicksilver.

Name: Raw Spodumene
Description: An uncut, unpolished stone containing what appears to be spodumene.

Name: Maghemite
Description: Originating in Thavnair, this iron oxide is often utilized as a pigment for its rusty red hue.

Name: Field Mustard
Description: The oil extracted from the seeds of this vivid yellow flower has various practical applications, not the least of which is as a reagent for curing skins and hides.

Name: Lovingbloom
Description: A prize flower grown in the nightmare fungal garden of Lovingway's Darlings.

Name: Liquid Glass
Description: This coating of remarkable clarity was produced by alchemical means, and is particularly suited to enhancing the durability of wooden surfaces.

Name: Thavnairian Flux
Description: Used to both soften and purify raw metals extracted from ore, this chemical agent is an invaluable addition to the metallurgical process. Hannish alchemists remain blissfully unaware of why its name gives potential buyers pause.

Name: Grinding Fluid
Description: In the hands of a goldsmith, this lubricant is more valuable than the gems it is used to polish. In the hands of anyone else, it is the source of oily residue.

Name: Hannish Cotton
Description: Woven with techniques perfected over generations on Thavnair, this cotton is durable, dyeable, andperhaps most importantlyaffordable.

Name: Deinosuchus Skin
Description: The skin of an enormous variety of crocodile that has remained unchanged since ancient times.

Name: Alche-mist
Description: Though to the layman's eye alche-mist appears to be little more than fancy purified water, the alchemically inclined folk of Thavnair insist that naught else will do.

Name: Dark Cherry Lumber
Description: Processed dark cherry lumber.

Name: Softsilver Ingot
Description: An ingot of smelted softsilver.

Name: Spodumene
Description: A light-pink jewel.

Name: Garnet Cotton
Description: A cloth woven with traditional techniques and dyed a deep red.

Name: Deinosuchus Leather
Description: A large piece of cured deinosuchus skin.

Name: Grade 8 Strength Alkahest
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this experimental alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to strength, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Grade 8 Dexterity Alkahest
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this experimental alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to dexterity, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Grade 8 Vitality Alkahest
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this experimental alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to vitality, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Grade 8 Intelligence Alkahest
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this experimental alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to intelligence, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Grade 8 Mind Alkahest
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this experimental alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to mind, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Grade 8 Tincture of Strength
Description:
This diluted brew temporarily increases strength for twice the duration of similar potions.

Duration: 30s

Name: Grade 8 Tincture of Dexterity
Description:
This diluted brew temporarily increases dexterity for twice the duration of similar potions.

Duration: 30s

Name: Grade 8 Tincture of Vitality
Description:
This diluted brew temporarily increases vitality for twice the duration of similar potions.

Duration: 30s

Name: Grade 8 Tincture of Intelligence
Description:
This diluted brew temporarily increases intelligence for twice the duration of similar potions.

Duration: 30s

Name: Grade 8 Tincture of Mind
Description:
This diluted brew temporarily increases mind for twice the duration of similar potions.

Duration: 30s

Name: Select Dark Chestnut Lumber
Description: A length of processed dark chestnut lumber, selected for its quality by a Boutique of Splendors procurer.

Name: Select Bismuth Ingot
Description: An ingot of bismuth, selected for its quality by a Boutique of Splendors procurer.

Name: Select Cobalt Plate
Description: A sheet of cobalt plate, selected for its quality by a Boutique of Splendors procurer.

Name: Select Bluespirit Tile
Description: A thin slab of bluespirit, selected for its quality by a Boutique of Splendors procurer.

Name: Select Green Glider Leather
Description: A sizable piece of cured green glider skin, selected for its quality by a Boutique of Splendors procurer.

Name: Select Waterproof Cloth
Description: A bolt of fabric that has been treated to repel water, selected for its quality by a Boutique of Splendors procurer.

Name: Select Rak'tika Seedling
Description: A seedling specimen native to the Rak'tika Greatwood, selected for its quality by a Boutique of Splendors procurer.

Name: Select Squid Ink
Description: A jar of rich and silky squid ink, selected for its quality by a Boutique of Splendors procurer.

Name: Connoisseur's Picture Frame
Description: A piece crafted to satisfy the discerning eye of an avid collector. Its fine detailing subtly directs the viewer's gaze toward the picture housed within.

Name: Connoisseur's Samurai Blade
Description: A piece crafted to satisfy the discerning eye of an avid collector. Its elegant blade forged of bismuth is a delight to any aficionado of swordsmithery.

Name: Connoisseur's Aquarium
Description: A piece crafted to satisfy the discerning eye of an avid collector, as well as the fish who would dwell within it.

Name: Connoisseur's Glaives
Description: A piece crafted to satisfy the discerning eye of an avid collector. With translucent blades forged of purest bluespirit, such a refined work of craftsmanship is more art than arm.

Name: Connoisseur's Varsity Shoes
Description: Footwear crafted to satisfy the discerning eye of an avid collector. Indeed, a single glance confirms both the luxuriousness of its materials and undeniable fashionability.

Name: Connoisseur's Linen Parasol
Description: A piece crafted to satisfy the discerning eye of an avid collectorand more crucially, shade them from the sun.

Name: Connoisseur's Topiary Moogle
Description: A piece crafted to satisfy the discerning eye of an avid collector. Its verdant raised pom and realistically rounded pate attest to its creator's skill in sculpting spheroids.

Name: Connoisseur's Squid Baguette
Description: A sandwich concocted to satisfy the discerning tongue of an avid gourmet. Having been slathered with squid ink, this baguette carries the pungent smell of the sea to one's nostrils with each bite. Yum.

Name: Connoisseur's Bookshelf
Description: A piece crafted to satisfy the discerning eye of an avid collector, whose library of rare works will find a fitting home on this handsome bookshelf.

Name: Connoisseur's Chandelier
Description: A piece crafted to satisfy the discerning eye of an avid collector. It is certain to become the highlight of any room.

Name: Connoisseur's Escutcheon
Description: A piece crafted to satisfy the discerning eye of an avid collector. With its distinctive coat of arms, this shield will undoubtedly become an heirloom treasured for generations.

Name: Connoisseur's Baghnakhs
Description: A piece crafted to satisfy the discerning eye of an avid collector. The reflective surfaces of its bluespirit claws shine when held under light.

Name: Connoisseur's Drinking Apkallu
Description: A piece crafted to satisfy the discerning eye of an avid collector. The apkallu's unquenchable thirst mirrors the insatiable desires of its destined owner.

Name: Connoisseur's Jacket
Description: An outerwear set tailored to satisfy the discerning eye of an avid collector, as well as the glazed eye of any fellow attendee at belabored ceremonies.

Name: Connoisseur's Planter Partition
Description: A piece crafted to satisfy the discerning eye of an avid collector. When gazing upon it, one can almost hear a faint la-hee in the distance.

Name: Connoisseur's Spaghetti al Nero
Description: A dish concocted to satisfy the discerning tongue of an avid gourmet. It shines with the luster of a resplendent black pearl, though is blessedly more chewable.

Name: Customized Carpenter's Component
Description: A rare material acquired by the Boutique of Splendors from one of Norvrandt's eclectic collectors. Required to enhance a crystalline tool.

Description: A rare material acquired by the Boutique of Splendors from one of Norvrandt's eclectic collectors. Required to enhance a crystalline tool.

Description: A rare material acquired by the Boutique of Splendors from one of Norvrandt's eclectic collectors. Required to enhance one of Chora-Zoi's crystalline tools.

Name: Connoisseur's Soiled Femur
Description: A material harvested with the discerning standards of an avid collector in mind, and well suited to aetherial reduction. Whether the layer of filth is truly required for it to maintain this property remains unclear, but why take the risk?

Name: Custom Ice Crystal
Description: A superior manifestation of aetheric ice energy obtained from Qeshi-Trao's hidden resources. Its unique makeup is ideal for enhancing a crystalline tool.

Name: Connoisseur's Miracle Apple
Description: A fruit harvested with the discerning standards of an avid collector in mind, and well suited to aetherial reduction (or consumption by hungry artisans).

Name: Custom Wind Crystal
Description: A superior manifestation of aetheric wind energy obtained from Qeshi-Trao's hidden resources. Its unique makeup is ideal for enhancing a crystalline tool.

Name: Gold Dustfish
Description:
Much as it may try to stay hidden beneath the billows of sand which cover the Nabaath Severance's depths, the golden sheen which radiates from this fish will not escape the gaze of a keen-eyed fisher.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Forgiven Melancholy
Description:
Found near the Isle of Ken, this death-white fish is a subject of curiosityand some suspicionamongst Kholusians.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Connoisseur's Aurum Regis Ore
Description: A mineral harvested with the discerning standards of an avid collector in mind, and royally suited to aetherial reduction.

Name: Brilliant Lightning Cluster
Description: A particularly brilliant manifestation of aetheric lightning energy. Due to its unique makeup, it can only be utilized by a master artisan.

Name: Connoisseur's Cloves
Description: A material harvested with the discerning standards of an avid collector in mind, and well suited to aetherial reduction. Also, pies.

Name: Brilliant Earth Cluster
Description: A particularly brilliant manifestation of aetheric earth energy. Due to its unique makeup, it can only be utilized by a master artisan.

Name: Oil Slick
Description:
Despite its less-than-appetizing name, this native of White Oil Falls is known for its delightfully sweet flavor, and is a treat for the eye besides.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Gonzalo's Grace
Description:
The legacy of Gonzalo the Honest, renowned for his wisdom and good humor, survives in this vibrant sea slug.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Customized Miner's Component
Description: A rare material acquired by the Boutique of Splendors from one of Norvrandt's eclectic collectors. Required to enhance a crystalline tool.

Name: Customized Botanist's Component
Description: A rare material acquired by the Boutique of Splendors from one of Norvrandt's eclectic collectors. Required to enhance a crystalline tool.

Name: Customized Fishing Rod Component
Description: A rare material acquired by the Boutique of Splendors from one of Norvrandt's eclectic collectors. Required to enhance a crystalline tool.

Name: Customized Fishing Reel Component
Description: A rare material acquired by the Boutique of Splendors from one of Norvrandt's eclectic collectors. Required to enhance a crystalline tool.

Name: Brilliant Miner's Component
Description: A rare material acquired by the Boutique of Splendors from one of Norvrandt's eclectic collectors. Required to enhance one of Chora-Zoi's crystalline tools.

Name: Brilliant Botanist's Component
Description: A rare material acquired by the Boutique of Splendors from one of Norvrandt's eclectic collectors. Required to enhance one of Chora-Zoi's crystalline tools.

Name: Brilliant Fishing Rod Component
Description: A rare material acquired by the Boutique of Splendors from one of Norvrandt's eclectic collectors. Required to enhance one of Chora-Zoi's crystalline tools.

Name: Brilliant Fishing Reel Component
Description: A rare material acquired by the Boutique of Splendors from one of Norvrandt's eclectic collectors. Required to enhance one of Chora-Zoi's crystalline tools.

Name: Dragonfruit
Description: This milky white fruit is shielded by scaly skin not entirely unlike that of dragonkind, though whether any member of the race approves of this comparison to vividly pink produce remains an open question.

Name: Dark Eggplant
Description: When asked to explain its flavor profile, a culinarian claimed that this subtropical eggplant is a little, hmm...richer? than the average wizard eggplant. This presumably means something to those versed in the inscrutable art of cuisine, who employ this nightshade in a wide variety of dishes.

Name: Pure Cumin
Description: This bright, earthy spice is prized for its versatility both culinary and otherwise, appearing in all manner of medicinal tinctures and beauty treatments.

Name: Caviar Sturgeon
Description: As its name implies, the eggs produced by this incredibly rare freshwater fish are considered something of a culinary miracle when salted and served as caviar.

Name: Broccoflower
Description: A unique vegetable boasting a fractal form that has baffled botanists for generations. Though tempting, it is best not to stare directly at its illusory buds.

Name: Honeyed Dragonfruit
Description:
A generous serving of dragonfruit slathered with a silky sweet layer of golden honey and a few sour drops of lemonette juice.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Dragonfruit Blend
Description:
Mashed dragonfruit is blended together with cloud banana and coconut milk to create this creamy, refreshing drink.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Baba Ghanoush
Description:
A traditional Thavnairian appetizer of finely chopped dark eggplant spiced with ground cumin and a tantalizing hint of garlic.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Baked Eggplant
Description:
Topped with sliced vegetables and a healthy coating of melted Garlean cheese, these rich eggplants have been roasted to tender perfection.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Spicy Stellar Soup
Description:
Simmered with diced alien onions and carrots of happiness aplenty, this stellar soup's flavor is quite literally out of this world.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Tandoori Raptor
Description:
A Near Eastern staple consisting of tender chunks of baked raptor meat marinated in mouthwatering spices and creamy yoghurt.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Caviar Sandwich
Description:
Its every bite extraordinary enough to render one speechless, this sandwich incorporates eggs from the caviar sturgeon and bird of Elpis both. Given the further inclusion of alligator pear slices, one cannot help but wonder at its inventor's obvious preference for ovoid foodstuffs.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Caviar Canapes
Description:
Perennial party favorites, these hors d'oeuvres feature delightfully bite-sized bread topped with cheese, vegetables, and salted caviar sturgeon eggs.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Marinated Broccoflower
Description:
A biting dish of broccoflower, paprika, and onion steeped in oil and dark vinegar.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Broccoflower Stew
Description:
Broccoflower slices boiled in a savory broth alongside tender poultry and root vegetables.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Onyx Knifefish
Description:
A king among darksteel knifefish, and lord of the waters of the Mover Beta.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Wakeful Warden
Description:
A king among wakeful watchers, and lord of the waters of the Wakeful Torana.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Basilosaurus Rex
Description:
A king among basilosaurs, and lord of the waters of the Perfumed Tides.

[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Eehs Fan
Description:
A king among eehs forhnesh, and lord of apohelos 18-.

[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Gilt Dermogenys
Description:
A king among dermogenys, and lord of the waters of the lower Hungering Gardens.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Rokkon Potsherd
Description: A relic of Mount Rokkon valuable enough to be sold to a collector, but not so valuable that Hancock might insist upon keeping it for his own.

Name: Rokkon Manuscript
Description: A thin tome recovered from Mount Rokkon. Though the Hingan script within is of an antiquated style that you could not hope to decipher, scholars would doubtless jump at the chance to acquire such a text.

Name: Island Coal
Description: What naughty island mammets can expect to receive come the Starlight Celebration.

Name: Island Shale
Description: A sedimentary rock believed to contain fossilized matter, the specific origin of which is unknown.

Name: Island Glimshroom
Description: A faintly glowing green fungus lit from within by moonlight.

Name: Island Marble
Description: This marble is, by all objective standards, very tropical.

Name: Island Mythril Ore
Description: The precious metal contained in this rock is unique to islands of the Cieldalaes.

Name: Island Effervescent Water
Description: Naturally sparkling water bottled at the source and particularly delicious in mammet-concocted cocktails.

Name: Island Spectrine
Description: Gaze into this pale silky stone to witness its natural patterns of unmarred beauty. Then grind it up and make it into commercially profitable stuff.

Name: Island Cave Shrimp
Description: A shrimp that happily made its home in the deepest, most solitary recesses of a deserted islanduntil you came along, that is.

Name: Island Runner Bean Seeds
Description:
A sack swollen with seeds that will grow into particularly athletic beans.

[Growth Period: Two days]

Name: Island Beet Seeds
Description:
A bag bursting with itty-bitty beet babies.

[Growth Period: Two days]

Name: Island Eggplant Seeds
Description:
Plant eggplant seeds, not eggs, for eggplants and thus avoid egg on your face or face-plants.

[Growth Period: Two days]

Name: Island Zucchini Seeds
Description:
These seeds will grow into zucchini whether you like it or not.

[Growth Period: Two days]

Name: Island Runner Beans
Description: These beans are a flight risk. You have been warned.

Name: Island Beet
Description: No other beet can beat these beets, unless these beets are brutally bruised.

Name: Island Eggplant
Description: Why not island aubergine? Why not, indeed.

Name: Island Zucchini
Description: Zucchini is as zucchini does. Which is to say, not much.

Name: Islekeep's Steel Hammer
Description: A strong and heavy mallet with formidable destructive power. It will no doubt collect you additional materials from designated resources, but rememberwith great hammers come great responsibility.

Name: Mammet-sized Spelunking Tools
Description: Excavation and exploratory tools crafted to fit tiny, desperate hands.

Name: Bestestest Mammet-sized Builder's Tools
Description: With these tools, any mammet may transcend their manufactured limits to become a metaphorical (and literal) machine of productivity.

Name: Prime Haritaki
Description: A lustrous leaf of the plant born from the popular Thavnairian nut. Under the right conditions, it could become sublime.

Name: Sublime Haritaki
Description: This spectacular sprig of haritaki has gone from prime to sublime through a process you don't understand and aren't going to worry about. What's important is that it promises an impressive yield from aetherial reduction.

Name: Concentrated Verdurous Glioaether
Description: Rich green oil refined by aetherial reduction to a state so concentrated that it cannot possibly get any greener...or can it?

Name: Prime Chloroschist
Description: A crystalline sample cultivated in the exacting environment of Labyrinthos. Under the right conditions, it could become sublime.

Name: Sublime Chloroschist
Description: This glorious chunk of chloroschist has gone from prime to sublime through a process you don't understand and aren't going to worry about. What's important is that it promises an impressive yield from aetherial reduction.

Name: Concentrated Igneous Glioaether
Description: Vibrant red oil refined by aetherial reduction to a state so concentrated that it cannot possibly get any redder...or can it?

Name: The Fury's Aegis
Description:
One must wonder whether this thick-shelled crustacean's name was approved by the Ishgardian Orthodox Church.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Concentrated Aqueous Glioaether
Description: Soothing blue oil refined by aetherial reduction to a state so concentrated that it cannot possibly get any bluer...or can it?

Name: Uncharted Course Lumber
Description: This unremarkable lumber is earmarked for the construction of an uncharted course.

Name: Uncharted Course Hardware
Description: Metal components required for the construction of a sturdy uncharted course.

Name: Uncharted Course Resin
Description: A versatile compound that the mammets insist is needed to seal your already-sunken ship against the elements.

Name: Uncharted Course Construction Permit
Description: Written permission for the construction of a sanctuary landmark. Use to unlock the uncharted course.

Name: Conceivably Special Timeworn Map
Description:
This bottle is holding what appears to be an unusually valuable leather map.

Use the action Decipher to extract the map and examine its contents.
Level 90 full party (eight players) recommended.
Guaranteed to summon a teleportation portal.

Name: Irregular Tomestone Of Tenfold Pageantry
Description:
One of only a few in existence, this Allagan tomestone contains knowledge of festivities for all manner of occasions, but especially those that endure year after year.

Can be exchanged with itinerant moogles for certain items.

Name: Majestic Manderville Sword
Description: Majestic Manderville weapon.

Name: Majestic Manderville Fists
Description:
Majestic Manderville weapon.
Weapon appearance may take precedence over the display of hand gear.

Name: Majestic Manderville Bardiche
Description: Majestic Manderville weapon.

Name: Majestic Manderville Spear
Description: Majestic Manderville weapon.

Description: Majestic Manderville weapon.

Description: Majestic Manderville weapon.

Name: Majestic Manderville Wings
Description: Majestic Manderville weapon.

Name: Majestic Manderville War Scythe
Description: Majestic Manderville weapon.

Name: Majestic Manderville Shield
Description: Majestic Manderville weapon.

Name: Dragon's Beard Fists
Description: Weapon appearance may take precedence over the display of hand gear.

Name: Augmented Dragon's Beard Fists
Description: Weapon appearance may take precedence over the display of hand gear.

Name: Voidcast Archfiend Totem
Description: A small idol of Golbez. Judging by the painstaking details carved into it, this statuette was likely fashioned by his most devout followers.

Name: Voidcast Weapon Coffer (IL 645)
Description:
A heavy chest containing a voidcast weapon.

Required level: 90. IL: 645. Weapon type determined by current job or class at time of opening. Cannot be opened in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.

Name: Unsung Helm of Anabaseios
Description:
A stunning but sadly unstoried helmet recovered from Pandmonium.

Two helms can be traded for special headgear.

Name: Unsung Armor of Anabaseios
Description:
Stunning but sadly unstoried armor recovered from Pandmonium.

Four suits can be traded for special body gear.

Name: Unsung Gauntlets of Anabaseios
Description:
Stunning but sadly unstoried gauntlets recovered from Pandmonium.

Two pairs can be traded for special arm gear.

Name: Unsung Chausses of Anabaseios
Description:
Stunning but sadly unstoried chausses recovered from Pandmonium.

Four pairs can be traded for special leg gear.

Name: Unsung Greaves of Anabaseios
Description:
Stunning but sadly unstoried greaves recovered from Pandmonium.

Two pairs can be traded for special foot gear.

Name: Unsung Ring of Anabaseios
Description:
A stunning but sadly unstoried ring recovered from Pandmonium.

One ring can be traded for a special accessory.

Name: Anabaseios Mythos I
Description:
A record of truths and somewhat exaggerated stories surrounding the unholy horrors of Anabaseios.

Copies of the same Anabaseios Mythos volumes can be traded for special gear.

Name: Anabaseios Mythos II
Description:
A record of truths and somewhat exaggerated stories surrounding the unholy horrors of Anabaseios.

Copies of the same Anabaseios Mythos volumes can be traded for special gear.

Name: Anabaseios Mythos III
Description:
A record of truths and somewhat exaggerated stories surrounding the unholy horrors of Anabaseios.

Copies of the same Anabaseios Mythos volumes can be traded for special gear.

Name: Anabaseios Mythos IV
Description:
A record of truths and somewhat exaggerated stories surrounding the unholy horrors of Anabaseios.

Copies of the same Anabaseios Mythos volumes can be traded for special gear or other mythos volumes.

Name: Ascension Weapon Coffer (IL 665)
Description:
An otherworldly chest containing an ascension weapon.

Required level: 90. IL: 665. Weapon type determined by current job or class at time of opening. Cannot be opened in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.

Description:
An otherworldly chest containing a piece of ascension attire.

Required level: 90. IL: 660. Head gear type determined by current job or class at time of opening. Cannot be opened in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.

Name: Unsung Blade of Anabaseios
Description: A stunning but sadly unstoried blade recovered from Pandmonium. Though such weapons were once considered highly valuable, demand has dried up and they are now essentially worthless.

Name: Divine Solvent
Description: A gleaming substance produced at the High Crucible of Al-Kimiya, used to enhance the properties of rare and unconventional weapons. However, advances in crafting technology have rendered it obsolete.

Name: Divine Twine
Description: A silvery, silklike thread produced at the High Crucible of Al-Kimiya, used to enhance the properties of credendum attire. However, advances in crafting technology have rendered it obsolete.

Name: Divine Shine
Description: A dazzling substance produced at the High Crucible of Al-Kimiya, used to enhance the properties of credendum accessories. Why it smells slightly of rotten fish and amra is a mystery better left unsolved. However, advances in crafting technology have rendered it obsolete.

Name: Hermetic Tomestone
Description: While it is a surpassingly small means of storing knowledge, the information deposited on this relic of Allagan society was compressed with heretofore unseen efficiency. Such a wealth of knowledge would not come without a sacrifice to portability, however, and this tomestone is unfathomably heavy as a result. This particular variety is not as highly sought as it once was, and may no longer be exchanged for other wares.

Name: Amplifying Achondrite
Description: This hunk of meteorite contains deposits of a rare form of pyroxene. When subjected to an advanced extraction process, the achondrite produces mineral oil which can be used to manipulate the pathways of aetherial conductivity.

Name: Paladin's Voidcast Arms (IL 645)
Description:
A set of arms containing a voidcast falchion and voidcast kite shield.

Required level: 90. IL: 645.

Name: Paladin's Ascension Arms (IL 665)
Description:
A set of arms containing a sword of ascension and kite shield of ascension.

Required level: 90. IL: 665.

Name: Phantasmal Attire Coffer (IL 530)
Description:
A banded chest containing a complete set of phantasmal attire.

Required level: 80. IL: 530. Cannot be opened in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Heroic Landing
Description: An illustrated manual of how to make a suitably grand entrance at any social function. Use to learn the /adventoflight emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Joyous Leaping
Description: An illustrated manual depicting the posing positions for socially acceptable expressions of airborne elation. Use to learn the various /jumpforjoy emotes.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Heartfelt Sincerity
Description: An illustrated manual of how to display one's heartfelt emotion in the most generic and inoffensive manner. Use to learn the /handtoheart emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Improper Praise (Cheer On: Bright)
Description: The fourth installment of what was to be a three-volume manual on how to express admiration in a manner unbefitting one of high birth. Use to learn the /cheeronbright emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Improper Praise (Cheer Wave: Violet)
Description: The fifth installment of what was to be a three-volume manual on how to express admiration in a manner unbefitting one of high birth. Use to learn the /cheerwaveviolet emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Improper Praise (Cheer Jump: Green)
Description: The sixth installment of what was to be a three-volume manual on how to express admiration in a manner unbefitting one of high birth. Use to learn the /cheerjumpgreen emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Wakeful Witchcraft
Description: An illustrated manual depicting the swish-and-flick motions required to conjure up and dispel innocent illusions with a magic wand. Use to learn the /allsaintscharm emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Scrupulous Citations
Description: An illustrated manual of how to effectively employ reference materials to support one's assertions in civilized debate. Use to learn the /reference emote.

Name: Rose-colored Spectacles
Description:
Wear these lenses to feel and exude optimism.*
* Optimism may or may not be warranted. Please act according to actual conditions. Though these were once considered a fashion accessory, trends are ever changing, and style enthusiasts now classify them as facewear. Use to unlock rose-colored spectacles.

Name: Tsukumogami Parasol
Description: Designed in the likeness of a Far Eastern umbrella spirit, this parasol is certain to attract quizzical eyes (and slobbery tongues). Use to unlock a tsukumogami parasol.

Name: Tactful Taskmaster Umbrella
Description: A handy accessory to have when you need a large visual reminder that there is work to be done and schedules to keep. Use to acquire a tactful taskmaster umbrella.

Name: Voidcast Barding
Description: A suit of chocobo armor designed to resemble Golbez.

Name: Felicitous Barding
Description: A suit of chocobo armor designed to resemble the felicitous furball.

Name: Puffin
Description:
Wants to work smarter, not harder.

Use item to acquire the puffin minion.

Name: Mossasaurus
Description:
It's adorable now, but wait till it grows up.

Use item to acquire the mossasaurus minion.

Name: Okuri Chochin
Description:
For those who like a little fright with their light.

Use item to acquire the okuri chochin minion.

Name: Posher Otter
Description:
Part futuristic, part antiquated, all class.

Use item to acquire the posher otter minion.

Name: Rubellite Weapon
Description:
Scaled down or no, it can scratch you up good.

Use item to acquire the Rubellite Weapon minion.

Name: Chimpanzee
Description:
This adorable critter will make you love every ape that you see, from chimpan-a to chimpan-z.

Use item to acquire the chimpanzee minion.

Name: Exciting Dynamite
Description:
For those who love the threat of death or serious injury to follow their every step.

Use item to acquire the exciting dynamite minion.

Name: Mikra Lyssa
Description:
Definitely meant to be a wolfthe ancients said so.

Use item to acquire the mikra Lyssa minion.

Name: Shiromaru
Description:
Because the only thing that's better than a dog is a ninja dog.

Use item to acquire the Shiromaru minion.

Name: Kuromaru
Description:
Because the only thing that's better than a dog is a ninja dog.

Use item to acquire the Kuromaru minion.

Name: Wind-up Athena
Description:
To follow you everywherethat is her wish.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Athena minion.

Name: Wind-up Barbariccia
Description:
Will blow you awayfiguratively speaking.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Barbariccia minion.

Name: Goggle-eyed Dogu
Description:
Guaranteed to win any staring contest.

Use item to acquire the goggle-eyed dogu minion.

Name: Island Buffalo Horn
Description: When blown, this horn emits a deep and languorous sound that summons your island buffalo.

Name: Traveling Supporter Identification Key
Description: A thin, rectangular piece of some unknown material. Placing it near your traveling supporter will magically bring the machine to life.

Name: Garlond GL-IS Ignition Key
Description: A thin key that ignites your Garlond GL-IS's ceruleum engine, bringing the sidecar-equipped vehicle rumbling to life.

Name: Megaloambystoma Horn
Description: Moist to the touch, this horn produces a carefree sound that brings your megaloambystoma floating to your side.

Name: Rising Phoenix Whistle
Description: Hot to the touch, this hand-carved whistle emits a lively shrill that summons your Rising Phoenix.

Name: Burabura Chochin Whistle
Description: A hand-carved whistle that, when played, emits an eerie tone that beckons your burabura chochin to your side.

Name: Shishioji Flute
Description: The spirited song of this flute is said to summon Shishioji, a princely fragment of Shishio, legendary auspice and king of the nue.

Name: Shadow Wolf Horn
Description: Steeped in shadow, this horn of bone emits a spine-chilling sound that brings your shadow wolf to your side.

Name: Magicked Children's Bed
Description: For as long as beds have existed, children have dreamed of having one that flies. Thanks to this winsome piece lovingly crafted for younglingsand the young at heartthat dream is now a reality.

Name: Lynx of Fallen Shadow Flute
Description: Emitting a grim and melancholic tone, this flute summons a lynx of fallen shadow to your side.

Name: Magicked Prism (Onibi)
Description: This peculiar contraption creates illusions by weaving together myriad shades of light. Casts an eerie aura around the user.

Name: Seacracker
Description: An otherworldly item of celebration that unleashes a blast of streamers, confetti, and assorted marine life.

Name: Magicked Prism (Loporrit Head)
Description: This peculiar contraption creates illusions by weaving together myriad shades of light. Envelops the user's head with the visage of an enormous-yet-endearing Loporrit.

Name: Augmented Hellhound Knuckles
Description: Weapon appearance may take precedence over the display of hand gear.

Name: Whalaqee Breath of Magic Totem
Description:
An intricately carved wooden totem imbued with the secrets of a technique causing lingering affliction.

Only for use by blue mages.

Name: Whalaqee Force Field Totem
Description:
An intricately carved wooden totem imbued with the secrets of a warding technique.

Only for use by blue mages.

Name: Commendation Crystal
Description: This special Trophy Crystal is proof of spectacular performance upon the crystal line.

Description:

Name: CCRC 2023 Champion Certification
Description:

Name: Pink Shrimp
Description:
The prettiest, pinkest shrimp you ever did see...unless you've laid eyes on its vivid pink cousin.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Sirensong Mussel
Description:
A razor-sharp mollusk found in the Sirensong Sea. Those averse to paper cuts are advised not to touch the edges of its shell without proper protection.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Arrowhead
Description:
In eras past, squid of this sort were used as lethal projectiles.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Deepshade Sardine
Description:
A dark-scaled fish that thought it could surreptitiously sneak through the shadows of a fishing boat and remain unnoticed. Alas, it thought wrong.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Sirensong Mullet
Description:
Business in the front. Sirensong in the back.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Selkie Puffer
Description:
Perhaps this puffer could equip a racket and fur armguards and depart on a grand adventure. Or perhaps it's just a fish.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Poet's Pipe
Description:
Warning: not an actual musical instrument. Do not attempt to blow on it.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Marine Matanga
Description:
Proof that anything looks friendlier when it has Matanga features, even sharks.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Spectral Coelacanth
Description:
This coelacanth took to the spectral currents out of dissatisfaction with the evolutionary hand it was dealtincluding, perhaps, its distinct lack of hands.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Dusk Shark
Description:
While known to scavenge the flesh of the drowned, this large grey shark will as surely feast upon the living.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Mermaid Scale
Description:
These rainbow-colored mollusks are believed to come from mermaids. Alas, not a one has ever been sighted, suggesting they have no desire to explore up where we walk, up where we run, up where we stay all day in the sun.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Broadhead
Description:
A squid whose head and mind are both as sharp as an arrow. It puts little thought into its diet, however, and will eat anything it can sink its barbed beak into.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Vivid Pink Shrimp
Description:
A shrimp known for its vibrant and resilient pink shell, as well as its long, sharp pincers.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Sunken Coelacanth
Description:
A long-lived fish that makes its home in the deepest recesses of the ocean.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Siren's Sigh
Description:
A variety of anglerfish thought to be breath spilled from a siren's lips.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Black-jawed Helicoprion
Description:
Though this ancient sea-dweller lacks a powerful bite, it makes up for it with the ability to bludgeon and grind its prey against rocks.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Impostopus
Description:
This doppelganger of the deep is able to mimic prey using its tentacles as it approaches. The psychological trauma of being attacked by oneselfor perhaps a loved one that relatives would jokingly call one's twinoften paralyzes the victim as the impostopus feeds.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Jade Mantis Shrimp
Description:
A beautiful jade-colored crustacean that is the envy of many a sea creature.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Nymeia's Wheel
Description:
An ancient wavekin allegedly born of divine erroror divine clumsiness, at the least.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Taniwha
Description:
Respected and feared by the peoples of the south sea isles, this ancient sea creature is the subject of myriad myths and legends.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 4 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Ruby Herring
Description:
Hingan merchants will offer fragrant samples of these toothsome fish when they do not care to haggle with their patrons, and thus its name has entered the local lexicon to refer to a misleading statement.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Whirlpool Turban
Description:
Legend has it that this spiral wavekin possesses dominion over water, whipping up violent whirlpools and lacerating fishing vessels to shreds...but it is, at least, a very charming little shell.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Leopard Prawn
Description:
The unpredictable patterns on this crustacean's carapace indicate its freshness and depth of flavor when cooked.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Spear Squid
Description:
In recent days, dried varieties of this squid have gained popularity as a convenient snack for traveling lancers.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Floating Lantern
Description:
An elegant jellyfish that emits a warm, gentle glow akin to its namesake.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Rubescent Tatsunoko
Description:
Despite being maybe, possibly, improbably the juvenile form of a Ruby Dragon, this wavekin prefers hiding amongst colonies of leopard prawns to confrontation, and is thus the envy of introverted naturalists across the realm.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Hatatate
Description:
With a dorsal fin that makes it look like a standard-bearer, this saltwater fish is ready to charge bravely into a pitched battle under the sea.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Silent Shark
Description:
A species of shark that is silent but deadlyin the literal sense, children. In the literal sense.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Spectral Wrasse
Description:
Though this wavekin may be small, it attempts to remedy such shortcomings by sporting splendidly spectral scales. In doing so, however, it has become more vulnerable to predators and skilled anglers.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 1 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Mizuhiki
Description:
A fish of good fortune, said to strongly resemble white and red cords commonly used to wrap gifts in Hingashi.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Snapping Koban
Description:
This wavekin's golden fins and mouth appear as coins floating in the ocean, giving the impression that sailors of the Kugane coast are quite cavalier with their finances.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Silkweft Prawn
Description:
Some have spent fortunes to have a single taste of this succulent shrimp.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Stingfin Trevally
Description:
If the poisonous sacs of this stingfin are carefully removed, the meat can make for a perfectly adequate meal.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Swordtip Squid
Description:
True to its name, the head of this squid is sharp enough to pierce straight through plate armor.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Mailfish
Description:
A school of these fish creates a striking sheet of silver, like an enormous suit of chainmail drifting through the ocean blue.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Idaten's Bolt
Description:
Said to be blessed by the gods with blinding speed, sometimes these fish tire of water and propel themselves into the sky on the back of a spectral current.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Maelstrom Turban
Description:
The presence of these shellfish in shallow waters is considered to be an ill omen, for they are believed to be the harbinger of storms, violent winds, and worse.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Shoshitsuki
Description:
The fleetness of these sharks is enough to tire even a god, but where divinity sees a menace, a fisher sees opportunity.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Spadefish
Description:
Which came first, the fish or the spade?

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Glass Dragon
Description:
Thought to be the counterpart of the Ruby Dragon, this legendary creature is far less fragile than its name implies.

[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Crimson Kelp
Description:
Found in every corner of the Ruby Sea, this kelp is known and loved for its culinary versatility.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Reef Squid
Description:
A cephalopod that lays its eggs on the Ruby Sea's rocky reefs.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Pinebark Flounder
Description:
If a pinebark flounder splashes in the Ruby Sea and no one is around to hear it, does it make a sound? Far Eastern philosophers have yet to determine a definitive answer.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Mantle Moray
Description:
A moray that resembles an ethereal raiment worn by the Ruby Princess...if ethereal raiments looked as though they were about to utter the punchline to a groan-worthy joke.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Shisui Goby
Description:
With its fondness for migratory journeys, this saltwater fish puts the go in goby.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Sanbaso
Description:
Said to be an omen of ample harvests, this wavekin is named for a traditional dance passed down in the Far East.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Barded Lobster
Description:
If one were to liken the spiny lobster to a valiant knight, then the barded lobsternearly twice the size of its counterpartwould serve as its seaworthy steed.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Violet Sentry
Description:
As dreadful as it is, people would be forgiven for mistakenly calling this seabeast the violent sentry.

[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Spectral Snake Eel
Description:
Now that its spectral nature has taken precedence, the question of whether this wavekin is a snake or an eel has become irrelevant.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Heavensent Shark
Description:
This shark is believed to be the reincarnation of a tiger descended from Heaven-on-High.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Fleeting Squid
Description:
When winter descends upon Kugane and its vibrant flora wilts, some look to the sea, where the skin of this cephalopod reminds them of warmer seasons.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Bowbarb Lobster
Description:
The long whiskers of this massive lobster curve like a bow, and some Kugane children cannot resist playing at imaginary war around the dinner table.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Pitch Pickle
Description:
Biting into the flesh of this wavekin will stain one's entire mouth black, which is useful if you have occasion to disguise yourself as ancient Far Eastern nobility.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Senbei Octopus
Description:
This wavekin resembles a popular Kugane treat outside of the water, causing sailors to look twice when rummaging through supplies for a late-night snack.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Tentacle Thresher
Description:
Displaying an almost exclusive predilection for preying on octopodes, this wavekin shows that even nature's deadliest predators can be picky eaters.

[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Bekko Rockhugger
Description:
The round body of this wavekin allows it to be carried swiftly through the ocean's currents, which might explain why it clings so desperately to the ocean's rocks.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Yellow Iris
Description:
Like its namesake flower, this fish has put many local ecosystems at risk.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Crimson Sentry
Description:
It takes little imagination to guess how this shark, one of two guardians keeping vigil over Shisui of the Violet Tides, got its name.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Flying Squid
Description:
What dried flying squid lacks in flavor, it makes up for in sheer quantity, and it is a staple in the diets of the Kugane commonfolk.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Hells' Claw
Description:
Protected by a thick layer of volcanic rock, this crustacean swims through the depths of the Ruby Sea to keep the flesh inside its shell from cooking.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Catching Carp
Description:
If only it knew where to find a pitching carp.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Garlean Bluegill
Description:
Though this invasive wavekin may appear harmless at first glance, the Yanxians will stop at nothing to hunt these tiny blue terrors down.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Yanxian Softshell
Description:
The world may be hard and cold, but this turtle's shell is soft...and questionably warm.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Princess Salmon
Description:
Not deigning to leave her domain, the princess salmon always remains in the waters of the One River.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Calligraph
Description:
When told the tale of this fish's creation, a Doman boy is said to have attempted to create more fish with inky scales. It did not end well for the carp in his father's prized pond.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Singular Shrimp
Description:
A small shrimp whose deep green hue is said to be a reflection of the One River. But more importantly, it's delicious.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Brocade Carp
Description:
Beautifully patterned and vibrantly hued, this freshwater fish has long been farmed in the One River for ornamental purposes.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Yanxian Sturgeon
Description:
A large freshwater fish whose eggs are considered so delicious, it gave rise to the saying hoes before roea reminder that work precedes pleasure.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Spectral Kotsu Zetsu
Description:
The bone-like tongues of these spectral wavekin are surprisingly sturdy despite their crystalline appearance, and are often used by highly skilled artisans to craft priceless accessories.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 3 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Fishy Shark
Description:
A large shark that, despite its size, prefers living among the reeds of the One River.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Gensui Shrimp
Description:
The green carapace of this shrimp is said to be the same emerald hue as the sweeping hills that make up the Gensui Chain.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Yato-no-kami
Description:
This wavekin makes an appearance in the folklore of Yanxia, where it is depicted as a demon who leaves the land fallow. Best eat it to prevent the tales coming true.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Heron's Eel
Description:
Although their early life is spent in Heron's Way, these eels eventually make their way to bigger ponds.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Crowshadow Mussel
Description:
A bivalve mollusk whose pitch-black shell hides a dazzling interior.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Yanxian Goby
Description:
Drawn down the One River from the Azim Steppe, these fish grow fat upon the smaller specimens inhabiting spectral currents.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Iridescent Trout
Description:
The scales of these fish are highly sought after by artisans in Kugane and beyond.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Un-Namazu
Description:
Believed to be a Namazu fallen from grace, this fish can not so much as affirm or deny the claim.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Gakugyo
Description:
Once the subject of a Far Eastern faerie tale, this wavekin may or may not seek revenge after being used by an adventurous rabbit.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Ginrin Goshiki
Description:
Valued for its vibrant scales, this variety of carp is occasionally mistaken for a gold ingot when viewed from above the water's surface.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Jewel of Plum Spring
Description:
Thought to be birthed from the gnarled trunk of an ancient plum tree, the blossoms atop this legendary turtle's shell neither wither nor fade with the passage of time.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Modern Aesthetics - Ambitious Ends
Description:
The realm's premier publication on beauty and fashion, this specific copy of Modern Aesthetics covers, in detail, styling techniques used to mixed success since the time of the ancients.

Use to unlock a new hairstyle at the aesthetician.
Unavailable to female Hrothgar.

Name: Watcher's Palace Interior Wall
Description: An interior wall crafted to mimic the design of the Watcher's Palace.

Name: Watcher's Palace Flooring
Description: A section of flooring crafted to mimic the design of the Watcher's Palace.

Name: Watcher's Palace Ceiling Lamp
Description: A chandelier crafted to resemble the lamps found in the Watcher's Palace.

Name: Botanist's Work Table
Description: A work station custom-made for the botanically inclined.

Name: Imitation Curtained Window
Description: A clever semblance of a window to the outside. One can almost hear the birds chirping.

Name: Assorted Cookies
Description:
A delectable assemblage of cookies catering to various tastes. Sure to satisfy any and every sweet tooth.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Spell Speed Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  VIT Bonus: +5% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Botanical Candle Display
Description: Similar to a normal candle display, but with considerably more dried flora.

Name: Cieldalaes Planter
Description: A tall pot featuring an even taller plant native to the Cieldalaes.

Name: Chair Hena
Description: An elegant piece of furniture named for the tragic civilization which produced its original design.

Name: Classic Table Lamp
Description: A simple shaded lamp.

Name: Imitation Moonlit Window
Description: The soft, lunar light of this deceptive window is best appreciated in near darkness.

Name: Metal Pipe Wall Shelf
Description: The exposed pipes and pressure gauges of this shelving system provide a distinct boiler room aesthetic.

Name: Steamed Shumai
Description:
Wrapped in a wafer-thin skin and steamed to perfection, these bite-sized dumplings are a Far Eastern favorite.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Determination Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  VIT Bonus: +5% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Fried Gyoza
Description:
While boiling is the norm in Yanxia, Kugane culinarians prefer to crisp these crescent-shaped dumplings in a pan before serving.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Critical Hit Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  VIT Bonus: +5% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Floating Kitchen Cabinet
Description: A wall-mounted kitchen cabinet. For those expecting a levitating cupboard, prepare to be disappointed.

Name: Azure Sky Phasmascape
Description: An imitation skylight with illusory properties. Gaze upwards to appreciate this portal to an inviting blue sky.

Name: Starry Sky Phasmascape
Description: An imitation skylight with illusory properties. Gaze upwards to appreciate this portal to a star-studded expanse.

Name: Freestanding Rattan Hammock
Description: Based on a southern seas furnishing, this freestanding hammock allows you to laze in the location of your choice.

Name: Classic Tableware
Description: A tableware set of simple, antique design.

Name: Classic Umbrella Stand
Description: An understated period piece that one might see in a grandsire's entryway.

Name: Rustic Log Table
Description: A plain table hewn from a single log.

Name: Rustic Log Bench
Description: A modest bench hewn from a single log.

Name: Scattered Tomes
Description: Create an impression of scholarly study with this artfully disordered pile of reference materials.

Name: Vintage Side Table
Description: A circular side table of unobtrusive design.

Name: Short Pillar Bookshelf
Description: A pillar to support your academic pursuits. Not so much your ceiling.

Name: Imitation Vault
Description: For those with more money than sense, yet less money than requires an actual vault.

Name: Ivy Pendant Wall Light
Description: A trio of lamps hanging from an ivy-covered, wall-mounted branch.

Name: Crystarium Pendant Wall Light
Description: A wall-mounted trio of hanging lamps crafted in the Crystarium style.

Name: Fishing Rod Rack
Description: A decorative display stand for the fishing gear enthusiast.

Name: Far Eastern Indoor Bamboo Fountain
Description: A masterfully crafted indoor fountain wrought from bamboo and stone.

Name: Cactuar Colony Planter
Description: A large pot containing an assortment of cacti fashioned to resemble a colony of cactuars. Their empty gaze is somehow unsettling.

Name: Verdant Pillar
Description: A pillar crafted to resemble a natural tree. Squirrels not included.

Name: Rattan Partition
Description: The division provided by this southern seas partition is more of a suggestion.

Name: Oyoroi Display
Description: A set of Far Eastern armor arranged to resemble a sternyet comfortably seatedwarrior.

Name: Far Eastern Brazier
Description: The dancing flames atop this Far Eastern-styled brazier warm the heart and soul.

Name: Imitation Closed Door
Description: The sign on this mock wooden door forbids entry. Please respect its authority.

Name: Wall-mounted Pot Rack
Description: A handy circular rack for hanging stovetop utensils.

Name: Serving Barrel
Description: A wooden barrel for storing your favorite alcoholic beverage. Complete with spigot for easy serving.

Name: Classic Secretaire
Description: An elegant desk perfect for penning what the less dignified might consider an excessive amount of missives.

Name: Raw Log Half Partition
Description: A rustic fence constructed of unrefined logs and branches.

Name: Forever at Your Side
Description: A commissioned portrait of a former imperial officer and his adopted children entitled Forever at Your Side.

Name: Blighted Earth Sword Stand
Description:
Cloaked in loam and enough ominous power to make the land tremble, this greatsword evokes memories of a fallen despot.

One per estate only.

Name: Drowned King Sculpture
Description:
This statue emanates the menace of a deadly undertow.

One per estate only.

Name: Eventide Sword Stand
Description:
It is uncertain what is on display here: the greatsword, or the shadowy energies which crackle and writhe along its length.

One per estate only.

Name: The Rising MMXXIII Advertisement
Description: A masterfully rendered oil depiction of a realm-wide celebration of hope and rebirth.

Name: Wall-mounted Vampire Bats
Description: Spookify a plain wall with this cloud of tiny bloodthirsty beasts.

Name: Springtide Fan Stand
Description: A verdantly decorated pair of folding fans displayed at Heavensturn to beckon winds of fair fortune in the seasons to come.

Name: Valentione's Heart Chair
Description: This charming wooden chair bears an adorable heart motif, making it clear not only by the comfort of its fluffy pink cushions but its very form factor that it is a product of love.

Name: Island Garden Fence
Description: A rudimentary wooden fence, designed to complement the simple lifestyle of the Cieldalaes.

Name: Island Parasol Table
Description: An understated outside table, designed to complement the simple lifestyle of the Cieldalaes.

Name: Island Wooden Chair
Description: A modest wooden chair, designed to complement the simple lifestyle of the Cieldalaes.

Name: Railway Sleepers
Description: A rustic ground covering made from repurposed railway sleepers.

Name: Garden Creek
Description: Complete with running water, this soothing stonebound creek is the perfect place to dip your toes on a hot summer's day.

Name: Mushroom Medley Lamp
Description: Illuminate your garden with this three-tiered collection of fungal furniture.

Name: Illuminated Topiary Chocobo
Description: Trimmed into the shape of a sitting chocobo, this shrubbery is liberally strung with glowing adornments in the style of the Starlight Celebration.

Name: Country Swing Seat
Description: Escape the midday sun beneath the roof of this charming wooden swing seat.

Name: Ornate Fountain
Description: Decorated with delicate designs and crystal panels, this water feature gushes elegance.

Name: Smashed Flower Pot
Description: Let the resilience of the flowers which persevere in the soil of this damaged pot serve as a reminder that hope springs eternal.

Name: Well Pump
Description: This working well pump provides a reliableand apparently endlesssource of clean water.

Name: Ivy-canopied Deck
Description: The ivy strung atop this wooden deck throws the seating area below into an idyllic dappled shade.

Name: Komainu Statue
Description: Ward off malevolent spirits with this dignified statue.

Name: Stone Toro Lantern
Description: A moss-covered stone lantern constructed in the Far Eastern style. Its base is attached to a thick stone slab for support.

Name: Planted Toro Lantern
Description: A moss-covered stone lantern constructed in the Far Eastern style and driven directly into the earth, the better to blend in with natural surrounds.

Name: Chrysanthemum Seeds
Description:
These seeds will grow into spectacular blooms, commonly held as the symbol for friendship, happiness, and well-being.

For use in planters.

Name: Red Chrysanthemums
Description:
A bunch of red chrysanthemums, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Blue Chrysanthemums
Description:
A bunch of blue chrysanthemums, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Yellow Chrysanthemums
Description:
A bunch of yellow chrysanthemums, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Green Chrysanthemums
Description:
A bunch of green chrysanthemums, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Name: Orange Chrysanthemums
Description:
A bunch of orange chrysanthemums, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Name: Purple Chrysanthemums
Description:
A bunch of purple chrysanthemums, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Name: White Chrysanthemums
Description:
A bunch of white chrysanthemums, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Name: Black Chrysanthemums
Description:
A bunch of black chrysanthemums, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Rainbow Chrysanthemum Bouquet
Description:
A bunch of multicolored chrysanthemums, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Weathered Fitting
Description: Despite weathering a stint on the ocean floor, this metal fitting should still serve as a suitable connecting piece for other building materials.

Name: Iroko Lumber
Description: A processed length of highly durable and water-resistant iroko lumber.

Name: Mossy Log
Description: This moss-covered log is clearly the deliberately cut remnant of a towering tree. Less clear is how it came to be lodged at the bottom of the sea.

Name: Damaged Side Table
Description: Seemingly a furnishing from some sunken galleon, this brine-soaked table might still serve its purpose with a little restorative woodworking.

Name: Malake Karpasos
Description: The method used to weave this luxuriously soft cotton fabric defies identification.

Description: Music roll for Another Moon. Use to add to your orchestrion list.

Description: Timeworn pages of sheet music containing the full score for Voidcast Savior.

Name: Isleworks Stove
Description:
An iron stove forged in the sanctuary workshop.

Category: Furnishings/Metalworks
Required Time: 6 hours

Name: Isleworks Lantern
Description:
Tragically, this lantern emits only a faint green light and is thus best used for decorative purposes, much to the disappointment of its mammet creators.

Category: Sundries
Required Time: 8 hours

Name: Isleworks Natron
Description:
A mixture commonly used for its effectiveness at removing even the most stubborn of oil stains.

Category: Sundries/Concoctions
Required Time: 4 hours

Name: Isleworks Bouillabaisse
Description:
A hearty soup consisting of various seafood procured in the Cieldalaes.

Category: Foodstuffs/Marine Merchandise
Required Time: 8 hours

Name: Isleworks Fossil Display
Description:
A mysterious fossil cleaned and then framed by the island mammets. 

Category: Creature Creations/Unburied Treasures
Required Time: 6 hours

Name: Isleworks Bathtub
Description:
A bathtub large enough to fit four mammets, maybe five. Possibly six at a pinch, and certainly no more than seven. Probably.

Category: Furnishings/Unburied Treasures
Required Time: 8 hours

Name: Isleworks Spectacles
Description:
A spectacular pair of spectacles. Exceedingly durable, being forged of mythril.

Category: Attire/Sundries
Required Time: 6 hours

Name: Isleworks Cooling Glass
Description:
When the weather is unbearably hot, do not be alarmed should you find the island mammets rubbing themselves against the surface of this glass for a moment's respite.

Category: Unburied Treasures
Required Time: 8 hours

Name: Isleworks Runner Bean Saute
Description:
Try to run away now.
Peeved island mammet.

Category: Foodstuffs
Required Time: 4 hours

Name: Isleworks Beet Soup
Description:
Beets boiled into a very, very purple soup.

Category: Foodstuffs
Required Time: 6 hours

Name: Isleworks Imam Bayildi
Description:
A dish said to be so delectable as to cause one to faint from sheer euphoria.

Category: Foodstuffs
Required Time: 6 hours

Name: Isleworks Pickled Zucchini
Description:
These sweet and sour pickles are best enjoyed on their own or in sandwiches.

Category: Preserved Food
Required Time: 8 hours

Name: Voidcast Pauldron
Description: A shoulder plate worn by a lordly voidsent. The stain of Darkness is sunk deep into its twisted whorls.

Name: Pearl of Fissures
Description: The might of an archfiend is trapped within this precious jewel. It carries a scent of soil not unlike that of a fresh-dug grave.

Name: Pearl of Tides
Description: The might of an archfiend is trapped within this precious jewel. Its glistening surface is ever slick with salt-tinged moisture.

Name: Pom from the Heavens Orchestrion Roll
Description: Music roll for Pom from the Heavens. Use to add to your orchestrion list.

Name: Shishu Reiseki
Description: A mystical stone quarried from the isle of Shishu.

Name: Seiryu Sculpture
Description: An imposing rendition of the serpentine auspice Seiryu. Place eastward for best results.

Name: Suzaku Sculpture
Description: An imposing rendition of the fiery auspice Suzaku. Place southward for best results.

Name: Authentic Copy of Newfound Adventure
Description: A masterfully rendered oil depiction of a hero embarking on a new chapter of thrilling adventure.

Name: Authentic Copy of Buried Memory
Description: A masterfully rendered oil depiction of an ancient dungeon and the wardens charged with keeping its occupants chained.

Name: Authentic Copy of Gods Revel, Lands Tremble
Description: A masterfully rendered oil depiction of two black-clad figures stood astride the boundary of two worlds.

Name: Authentic Copy of the Dark Throne
Description: A masterfully rendered oil depiction of an armored lord upon his shadowed throne. The mysterious orb and coiling dragon bespeak a mastery over dark powers.

Name: Loss, Fire, Faith Reproduction
Description: A large-scale reproduction of a piece entitled Loss, Fire, Faith.

Name: Authentic Summer Bonfire
Description: An authentic roaring bonfire perfect for activities such as celebrating the Moonfire Faire and establishing a solid alibi.

Name: Divine Rain
Description: The Hannish proffer this highly concentrated elixir to the divinity Gajasimha in hopes that they will in turn be showered by blessings.

Name: Hannish Certificate of Grade 3 Import
Description: A note of promise granted for the delivery of diadochos equipment.

Name: Mandervillous Falchion
Description: Mandervillous Manderville weapon.
