Name: Cosmic Crystallite
Description: This extremely rare form of crystal-based achondrite is infused with aether from its journey through the cosmos. Theoretically, its energies can be extracted in the form of a highly refined liquid essence.

Name: Voidvessel Totem
Description: A small idol of Zeromus. It is unclear exactly who crafted it.

Name: Voidvessel Weapon Coffer (IL 655)
Description:
A heavy chest containing a voidvessel weapon.

Required level: 90. IL: 655. Weapon type determined by current job or class at time of opening. Cannot be opened in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.

Name: Paladin's Voidvessel Arms (IL 655)
Description:
A set of arms containing a voidvessel bastard sword and voidvessel kite shield.

Required level: 90. IL: 655.

Name: Abyssal Diamond
Description: The might of a great and terrible voidsent is trapped within this precious jewel. A darkness beyond blackest pitch emanates from its core.

Name: Abyssal Barding
Description: A suit of chocobo armor designed to resemble Zeromus.

Name: Ossicula
Description:
A fish as nutritious as it is filled with bones, which sadly make the acquisition of said nutrients all the trickier.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Kitty Herring
Description:
Notably dined upon by the Empire's most pampered pusses.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Empyreal Spiral
Description:
Though equally beautiful intact, this conch shell becomes an in-demand pigment when ground to pieces, so pulverized it shall be.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Sarikuyruk
Description:
This species of yellowtail is particularly valued for its rich vitamin content.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Opal Tetra
Description:
Named for its scales' resemblance to the multicolored gemstone, this freshwater fish is enchanting to behold. Whether it is aware of its own beauty has yet to be determined.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Cushion Care Package
Description: A set of soft and profoundly healing pillows ideal for relieving back pain.

Name: Feline Recreational Device
Description: This apparatus has been guaranteed by science to entertain cats. Whether cats care to entertain the notion of said science, however, is another matter entirely.

Name: Mesmerizing Miniature
Description: A carefully handcrafted replication of a monstrous creature. The longer you stare at it, the longer it stares at you...

Name: Energizing Eye-lixir
Description: Apply directly to the eyeball for optimal exhaustion relief. If you experience side effects such as loss of vision, dizziness, nausea, or death, stop use immediately and seek the counsel of your nearest chirurgeon.

Name: Researcher's Relaxation Kit
Description: A delightful box brimming with relaxation implements of notable quality.

Name: Cushion Care Package Materials
Description: Simply by holding this miraculous substance in hand, you feel the lingering strain from collecting it fade from your fingers...

Name: Feline Fascinators
Description: But a whiff of this plain material is liable to show any kitty cat a glimpse of kitty heaven.

Name: Mesmerizing Miniature Materials
Description: Everything a monster-lover requires to replicate the horrors of their dreams. Or nightmares, as it were.

Name: Energizing Eye-lixir Materials
Description: Powder that promises to relieve eyestrain once properly prepared. Applying directly to the eyeball is likely to exacerbate ocular discomfort and is highly discouraged.

Name: Researcher's Relaxation Kit Materials
Description: Relaxation implements of notable quality, sans the delightful box.

Name: Cushion Care Package Components
Description: This mysteriously sourced gelatin is indeed quite soft to the touch, if fundamentally unnerving in nature...

Name: Feline Recreational Device Components
Description: All you require to create a scientifically certified device for entertaining any cat.

Name: Mesmerizing Miniature Components
Description: A bag of limbs, eyes, torsos, heads, tails, horns, and claws, mercifully bloodless and in the miniature.

Name: Energizing Eye-lixir Components
Description: Substances that should create eye drops with a high rate of alleviating ocular stress and a low rate of mortality upon contact.

Name: Researcher's Relaxation Kit Components
Description: Materials required to create relaxation implements of notable quality. Delightful box included.

Name: Aloalo Potsherd
Description: A relic of Aloalo Island surely possessed of immense cultural and anthropological worth.

Name: Aloalo Manuscript
Description: This esoteric tome discovered on Aloalo Island is a trove of historical knowledgeto those who can decipher it.

Name: Azeyma's Earrings
Description: Increases EXP earned by 30% when level 90 and below. Attributes and item level vary according to class/job and current level when equipped.

Name: Fern Interior Wall
Description: An interior wall delicately stenciled with a cascading leafy design.

Name: Greige Carpet
Description: For the ambivalent designer who cannot commit to grey or beige. Guaranteed unremarkable!

Name: Seabed Ceiling Lamp
Description: Simply install this light fixture to be immersed in the magic of the deep. Unsettling fish sold separately by popular request.

Name: Hanging Lure Display
Description: An aesthetic arrangement of angling accoutrements.

Name: Abyssal Wings Display
Description:
A sculpture incorporating several of Zeromus's key features, the power to destroy life as we know it thankfully not among them.

One per estate only.

Name: Crystarium Wall Canopy
Description: An elegant fixture reminiscent of Crystarium sensibilities.

Name: Nursery Canopy
Description: Lounge like a highborn tot with this elegant and cozy nursery canopy.

Name: Ronkan Fireplace
Description: A solid stone hearth rendered in the Ronkan architectural style.

Name: Tomestool
Description: Features a nook beneath the seat for all manner of tomes, dusty or otherwise.

Name: Magazine Display Rack
Description: An easily perusable collection of popular periodicals and other publications.

Name: Celestial Screen
Description: This rounded screen designed to resemble the heavens above is a must-have for astrologians, astrologists, astronomers, and whoever decides to prefix their vocation with astro next.

Name: Imitation Trapdoor
Description: All of the excitement of a true trapdoor, with none of the deadly pits below.

Name: Manderville's Adventurer Flakes
Description:
Manderville & Manderville's lovingly crafted Manderville's Adventurer Flakes (Manderville Mark Certified) supplement the diets of growing adventurers with the nutrients they need, while providing the convenience and non-perishability they crave. Now with flavor!

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Direct Hit Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  VIT Bonus: +5% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Cluster Lamp
Description: This artificial crystal formation produces a gentle glow certain to give heart to longtime adventurers.

Name: Lapis Manalis Banner
Description: A fraying banner emblazoned with the symbol of the reapers.

Name: Hyperboreia Bench
Description: This circular bench imitates a design seen in Ktisis Hyperboreia, complete with planted vegetation.

Name: Aitiascope Desk
Description: Simple, unadorned work desks such as this are used to make observations in the Aitiascope. Includes a monitor for keeping track of aetheric fluctuations.

Name: Aitiascope Lamp
Description: A softly glowing lamp of the kind used to provide illumination in the depths of the Aitiascope.

Name: Throne of the Foremost
Description: This artifact recovered from the Fell Court of Troia has the distinct air of a furnishing designed for only the greatest of individuals, but technically nothing can stop you from sitting on it.

Name: Wood Slice Loft
Description: This whimsical loft was hewn from a centuries-old tree.

Name: Faerie Pendant Wall Light
Description: No pixies were harmed in the making of these whimsical floral lights, and thus none will be lurking in wait to exact revenge during your next visit to Il Mheg. For this, anyway.

Name: Portaled Partition
Description: This partition features a quaint circular opening certain to invite the sort of guest who is keen on breakfast.

Name: Korpokkur Moss Ball
Description: So lifelike is this ornamental moss ball, it looks as though it could up and walk off at any moment, miniature tree and all.

Name: Sealing Wax & Letter Set
Description: When one pens a missive upon stationery of this caliber, coherency is optional.

Name: Bubbly Mogfloat
Description:
A tall glass of pom fizz topped with a heaping scoop of frosty ice cream.  

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Skill Speed Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  VIT Bonus: +5% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Royal Leather Sofa
Description: Lounge like royalty on this plush leather three-seater. Advisors and attendants not included.

Name: Wall Cabinet
Description: This towering feat of carpentry is replete with more tiny drawers than anyone could possibly need.

Name: Field of Hope Rug
Description: Walk free, and bear the light for others to follow.

Name: Sake Barrel
Description: This barrel of sake is wrapped in a mat of woven rice straw. A specialty product of Hingashi.

Name: Colossal Chronometer Window
Description: A looming reminder of the inexorable march of time.

Name: Hyper Hustle Trophy
Description: A trophy that represents the power of teamwork, friendly competition, shared cuisine, hope, dreams, purpose...and batteries.

Name: Authentic Copy of A Realm Awoken
Description: A masterfully rendered oil depiction of the Allagan atrocities sealed within the Crystal Tower.

Name: Authentic Copy of Through the Maelstrom
Description: A masterfully rendered oil depiction of the dauntless souls who laid low the Lord of the Whorl.

Name: Authentic Copy of Defenders of Eorzea
Description: A masterfully rendered oil depiction of those who would bring light to the sanctuary of the sylphs.

Name: Authentic Copy of Dreams of Ice
Description: A masterfully rendered oil depiction of a headstrong woman channeling the Lady of Frost.

Name: Authentic Copy of Before the Fall
Description: A masterfully rendered oil depiction of a familiar foe returned with a vengeance and a hero newly come to Ishgard.

Name: Authentic Copy of As Goes Light, So Goes Darkness
Description: A masterfully rendered oil depiction of a ghost ship and the adventurers who ventured into its depths.

Name: Authentic Copy of The Gears of Change
Description: A masterfully rendered oil depiction of the Word of the Mother, resting in Her embrace.

Name: Authentic Copy of Revenge of the Horde
Description: A masterfully rendered oil depiction of the Azure Dragoon as depicted in tales of the Dragonsong War.

Name: Authentic Copy of Soul Surrender
Description: A masterfully rendered oil depiction of five Warriors of Darkness fighting to save their realm.

Name: Authentic Copy of The Far Edge of Fate
Description: A masterfully rendered oil depiction of five Scions who defended the Twelveswood from the threat of war.

Name: Authentic Copy of Vows of Virtue, Deeds of Cruelty
Description: A masterfully rendered oil depiction of a self-styled android deep in the ruins of a forgotten factory.

Name: Authentic Copy of Echoes of a Fallen Star
Description: A masterfully rendered oil depiction of two warriors, an emissary, and a most convincing illusion.

Name: Authentic Copy of Reflections in Crystal
Description: A masterfully rendered oil depiction of the Crystal Exarch and a vessel of hope for mankind.

Name: Authentic Copy of Futures Rewritten
Description: A masterfully rendered oil depiction of two brave young women who together traversed myriad memories.

Name: Authentic Copy of Death Unto Dawn
Description: A masterfully rendered oil depiction of Eorzea's many great leaders, united to defend their homeland.

Name: Authentic Copy of Growing Light
Description: A masterfully rendered oil depiction of a figure blazing her path towards hope.

Name: The Builder
Description: A heavenly portrait of Byregot, god of architecture and industry.

Name: The Destroyer
Description: A heavenly portrait of Rhalgr, god of destruction.

Name: The Warden
Description: A heavenly portrait of Azeyma, keeper of the sun and goddess of inquiry.

Name: The Traders
Description: A heavenly portrait of Nald'thal, overseer of the underworld and god of commerce.

Name: The Matron
Description: A heavenly portrait of Nophica, tender of soils and harvests and goddess of abundance.

Name: The Keeper
Description: A heavenly portrait of Althyk, surveyor of change and space and god of time.

Name: Il Mheg Arbor
Description: The vibrant flowers of this elegant garden decoration put one in mind of the faeries' colorful homeland. Pixies thankfully not included.

Name: Mobile Garden Stairs
Description: The portability and convenience of this full flight of stairs ultimately render the age-old argument of ladder versus stepladder moot.

Name: Flower-wreathed Gazebo
Description: A charming and romantic pavilion for all those without allergies.

Name: Alzadaal's Garden Lamp
Description: An outdoor lighting fixture of the same ancient Hannish design encountered in the remnants above Alzadaal's Legacy.

Name: Elpis Garden Fountain
Description: A serene decoration fashioned after those thought to exist in ancient times.

Name: Wildflower Bed
Description:
A vibrant patch of various wild-growing flora.

Up to ten flower plots may be placed in a single garden, regardless of type.

Name: Bluecap Mushroom Lamp
Description: A quaint fungal lamp that emits a pale blue glow.

Name: Imitation Magitek Repair Station (Wall Unit)
Description:
Appearing as though it came straight from a Garlean castrum, one would be forgiven for attempting to maintain magitek armor with this repair station.
* Not an actual repair station; cannot be used in the maintenance of magitek armor.

Name: Labyrinthos Grape Lamppost
Description: Seeking to make grapes more transportable, a researcher at Meryall Agronomics is rumored to have produced a variety that grew in blocky clusters. Although complaints that they looked unappetizing led to a new strain with rounder edges, the original was regarded fondly by some, and so it was immortalized in the form of this lamppost.

Name: Hingan Rock Garden
Description: Designed to resemble a Far Eastern landscape, this carefully studied arrangement of sand, stone, and flora seems to invite quiet contemplation.

Name: Sharlayan Reflecting Pool
Description: A shallow decorative pool constructed in accordance with Sharlayan sensibilities.

Name: Authentic Caged Wisp
Description: This imprisoned orb of flickering blue flame is authentic by nature, and would therefore never lead anyone astray.

Name: Authentic Illuminated Tree
Description: A tree adorned with authentic decorative lights in honor of the Starlight Celebration. Popular with the neighborhood children (and the children at heart).

Name: Authentic Heavensturn Crane Banner
Description: An authentic and resplendent Heavensturn decoration bedecked with auspicious cranes.

Name: Authentic Valentione's Heart Desk
Description: A heart-shaped table crafted to commemorate the celebration of love that is Valentione's Day. Ideal for composing letters of authentic affection.

Name: Authentic Little Ladies' Day MMXXI Advertisement
Description: An authentic hand-painted notice advertising a lovely Little Ladies' Day of a year gone by.

Name: Authentic Hatching-tide MMXXII Advertisement
Description: An authentic hand-painted notice advertising the hippity-hoppity Hatching-tide festivities of a year gone by.

Name: Dedicated to Moonlight (Forge Ahead) Orchestrion Roll
Description: Music roll for Dedicated to Moonlight (Forge Ahead). Use to add to your orchestrion list.

Name: Lupin Seeds
Description:
Despite their wolfish namesake, the pointed flowering plants that bloom from these seeds are, in fact, a variety of legume.

For use in planters.

Name: Red Lupins
Description:
A bunch of red lupins, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Blue Lupins
Description:
A bunch of blue lupins, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Name: White Lupins
Description:
A bunch of white lupins, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Name: Black Lupins
Description:
A bunch of black lupins, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Rainbow Lupins
Description:
A bunch of multicolored lupins, selectively fertilized to achieve a variety of vibrant colors.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Select Bamboo Stick
Description: A cut and dried piece of thick bamboo, selected for its quality by a Boutique of Splendors procurer.

Name: Select Duraluminum Ingot
Description: An ingot of smelted duraluminum, selected for its quality by a Boutique of Splendors procurer.

Name: Select Brashgold Plate
Description: A sheet of highly durable brashgold plate, selected for its quality by a Boutique of Splendors procurer.

Name: Select Marble
Description: A chunk of marble with mesmerizing mottlings and streaks, selected for its quality by a Boutique of Splendors procurer.

Name: Select Chalicotherium Leather
Description: A large piece of cured chalicotherium skin, selected for its quality by a Boutique of Splendors procurer.

Name: Select Duskcourt Cloth
Description: Finely woven cloth with a distinctive duskbloom hue, selected for its quality by a Boutique of Splendors procurer.

Name: Select Cudweed
Description: An edible herb with myriad alchemical uses, selected for its quality by a Boutique of Splendors procurer.

Name: Select Blue Crab
Description: A crustacean with a vibrant blue shell, selected for its quality by a Boutique of Splendors procurer.

Name: Connoisseur's Bamboo Fence
Description: A piece crafted to satisfy the discerning eye of an avid collector. Though the Far Eastern regions of the First were lost to the Flood, this priceless hedge carries on its legacy.

Name: Connoisseur's Rousing Chronometer
Description: A piece crafted to satisfy the discerning eye of an avid collector. Even the heaviest of sleepers will wake up to this chronometer's clarion call.

Name: Connoisseur's Trumpet
Description: A piece crafted to satisfy the discerning eye of an avid collector. Its melodious timbre will soothe the souls of all who hear it...unless the souls in question are standing directly in front of it.

Name: Connoisseur's Washbasin
Description: A piece crafted to satisfy the discerning eye of an avid collector. This immaculately sculpted basin dispenses only the finest artisanal water, presumably for washing the finest artisanal faces.

Name: Connoisseur's Targe
Description: A piece crafted to satisfy the discerning eye of an avid collector. The patterns carved into it are so painstakingly detailed, it may be more suited to a gallery than a battlefield.

Name: Connoisseur's Petasos
Description: A piece crafted to satisfy the discerning eye of an avid collector. Stitched with care, this hat was made with mages in mind.

Name: Connoisseur's Lunar Curtain
Description: A reagent crafted to satisfy the discerning eye of an avid collector. Though this powder can supposedly resist formidable magicks and repel otherworldly flares, it can also be imbibed to reduce bouts of morning drowsiness.

Name: Connoisseur's Crab Cakes
Description: A meal concocted to satisfy the discerning tongue of an avid gourmet. Under the golden brown crust of this entre lies a savory-yet-fluffy crab filling that could win over the pickiest of eaters.

Name: Connoisseur's Shishi-odoshi
Description: A piece crafted to satisfy the discerning eye of an avid collector. Eulmoran elites would pay unthinkable sums of coin for this relic of lands long lost.

Name: Connoisseur's Retainer Bell
Description: A piece crafted to satisfy the discerning eye of an avid collector. Ringing the bell several times in a row may attract itinerant pixies.

Name: Connoisseur's Marching Horn
Description: A piece crafted to satisfy the discerning eye of an avid collector. The rich, baritone notes that echo from its bell must be heard to be believed.

Name: Connoisseur's Marble Fountain
Description: A piece crafted to satisfy the discerning eye of an avid collector. Why build a fountain from any old stone when it could be marble-ous instead?

Name: Connoisseur's Leather Jacket
Description: A piece crafted to satisfy the discerning eye of an avid collector. Despite its antique appearance, the leather is durable enough to withstand all manner of inclement weather.

Name: Connoisseur's Fat Cat Sofa
Description: A piece crafted to satisfy the discerning eye of an avid collector. Few can resist its charmingly cozy cushioning.

Name: Connoisseur's Tincture of Vitality
Description: A reagent crafted to satisfy the discerning eye of an avid collector. Drinking this concoction allegedly promotes growth. Allegedly.

Name: Connoisseur's Chili Crab
Description: A meal concocted to satisfy the discerning tongue of an avid gourmet. The tender crab flesh has been spiced to perfection, providing an intense heat while complementing the dish's milder flavors.

Name: Deadwood Shadow
Description:
Named for its resemblance to the sunken wood of the Greatwood's lakes, this carnivorous denizen of Mjrl's Tears inhabits the murky depths, where it awaits unwitting prey.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Ronkan Bullion
Description:
Due to its gilded scales and massive girth, this inhabitant of Mjrl's Tears is thought to be an ancient Ronkan treasure, transformed into a living creature.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Little Bounty
Description:
The Crystal Exarch once remarked that this wavekin of Saint Fathric's Temple resembled the seas of his faraway homeland, and thus the name stuck.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Saint Fathric's Face
Description:
This hulking creature's unnaturally sturdy head and stubborn nature won it the namesake of a famed Voeburtite saint.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Golding
Description:
Often likened to a pile of sunken gold coins, this wavekin has sentenced no few greedy souls to a watery demise in Mjrl's Tears.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Inspirational Fisher's Component
Description: A rare material acquired by the Boutique of Splendors from one of Norvrandt's eclectic collectors. Required to enhance a brilliant tool.

Name: Nightforged Fisher's Component
Description: A rare material acquired by the Boutique of Splendors from one of Norvrandt's eclectic collectors. Required to enhance a Vrandtic visionary's tool.

Name: Irregular Tomestone of Genesis I
Description:
One of only a few in existence, this Allagan tomestone contains moderately improbable theories of creation.

Can be exchanged with itinerant moogles for certain items.

Name: Irregular Tomestone of Genesis II
Description:
One of only a few in existence, this Allagan tomestone contains excessively improbable theories of creation.

Can be exchanged with itinerant moogles for certain items.

Description: An age-worn artifact recovered from Thaleia. Once considered to be of great religious significance, a sudden influx caused their value to plummet, rendering them almost worthless.

Name: Circuit Tilapia
Description:
A king among Labyrinthos tilapia, and lord of the waters of Deepmoat.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Durdina Fish
Description:
A king among Paksa fish, and lord of the waters of the Thavnairian coast.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Mayaman
Description:
A king among Thavnairian caimans, and lord of the waters of the Font of Maya.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Chlorophos Deathworm
Description:
A king among lunar deathworms, and lord of the Chlorophospond.

[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Starscale Ephemeris
Description:
A king among wandering starscales, and lord of the abode of the Ea.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: E.B.E.-852738
Description:
A king among E.B.E.s-9318, and lord of limne 3-.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Hyphalosaurus
Description:
A slippery reptile that can steer its way through Deepmoat's currents with a swish of its sizable tail.

[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Gharlichthys
Description:
This colossal inhabitant of the Perfumed Tides is thought to be one of the largest living fish on the star, growing nearly twenty fulms long. Those who miraculously haul one up from the depths should either be commended for their bravery or scolded for their folly.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 4 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Snowy Parexus
Description:
Armored with spiny growths and aetheric crystal camouflage, this unique wavekin of the Eblan Thaw was primed and ready for survival against its natural predators, save for the avid angler.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Furcacauda
Description:
Named for its forked tail, this elusive inhabitant of Lethe sports a remarkable bone structure rarely found among wavekin.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 1 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Lopoceras Elegans
Description:
Despite the sharp and dangerously pointed nature of its shell, this docile resident of the Chlorophospond is recognized as an honorary Loporrit.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Sidereal Whale
Description:
Legend has it that this ethereal whale of limne 3- was born from the yawning maw of a great dragon.

[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Prime Kukuru Beans
Description: This bean is born of a kukuru tree cultivated within Labyrinthos's precisely controlled climate. Under the right conditions, it could become sublime.

Name: Sublime Kukuru Beans
Description: This wondrous kukuru bean has gone from prime to sublime through a process you don't understand and aren't going to worry about. What's important is that it promises an impressive yield from aetherial reduction.

Name: Potent Verdurous Glioaether
Description: Rich green oil refined by aetherial reduction to an intensely concentrated state.

Name: Prime Fossilized Dragon's Scale
Description: This remnant of ancient draconic life was unearthed in Ultima Thule. Under the right conditions, it could become sublime.

Name: Sublime Fossilized Dragon's Scale
Description: This uncanny fossilized dragon's scale has gone from prime to sublime through a process you don't understand and aren't going to worry about. What's important is that it promises an impressive yield from aetherial reduction.

Name: Potent Igneous Glioaether
Description: Vibrant red oil refined by aetherial reduction to an intensely concentrated state.

Name: Stargilt Lobster
Description:
Uniquely well suited to survival in Ultima Thule. Uniquely poorly suited to survival on a star where most races enjoy the taste of lobster and laying claim to shiny objects.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Potent Aqueous Glioaether
Description: Soothing blue oil refined by aetherial reduction to an intensely concentrated state.

Name: Aetherial Arbor Lumber
Description: Fundamental material used in the construction of an aetherial arbor.

Name: Aetherial Arbor Hardware
Description: Metal components used in the construction of an aetherial arbor.

Name: Aetherial Arbor Resin
Description: A versatile compound used in the construction of an aetherial arbor.

Name: Aetherial Arbor Permit
Description: Written permission for the construction of a sanctuary landmark. Use to unlock the aetherial arbor.

Name: Goobbue Table Chronometer
Description: Is it a potted plant, timepiece, or adorable replication of a giant lumbering beast? The answer is yes.

Name: Cactuar Dining Table
Description: A communal surface ideal for breaking bread with your comrades and getting poked in the knee by spines.

Name: Minute Mindflayer Sprinkler
Description: Rest assured that this inanimate baby monster will spray you with water instead of the blood of its enemies.

Name: Senor Sabotender Chronometer
Description: The ruthless progression of time cannot be alteredbut its cruel effects on one's countenance can be mollified somewhat by the charms of Senor Sabotender.

Name: Imitation Magitek Repair Station (Floor Unit)
Description:
Appearing as though it came straight from a Garlean castrum, one would be forgiven for attempting to maintain magitek armor with this repair station.
* Not an actual repair station; cannot be used in the maintenance of magitek armor.

Name: Aloalo Pendant Wall Lamp
Description: The design of this wall-mounted light was inspired by similar relics discovered on Aloalo Island.

Name: Forgotten Figure
Description: A stunning replica of a statue once lost to the agesbut no longer.

Name: Aloalo Faerie Cushion
Description: A rude surprise awaits all those who dare plant their buttocks upon the image of Aloalo Island's most mischievous faerie.

Name: South Seas Coelacanth Display
Description: Proudly boast of this beautiful fish to your closest friends, or whomever else will forgive you for forcing them to admire a hanging fish.

Name: Sagely Sparrow Statue
Description: This replica of the avian figures enshrined on Aloalo Island is rather reminiscent of someone you know...

Name: Aloalo Island Palm
Description: This tree was imported from the balmy climes of Aloalo Island to brighten your abode with tropical whimsy. Pay no heed to the leaves it drops in homesickness.

Name: Aloalo Roselle Hedge
Description: Beautiful blooms of the south sea isles curated into a garden-friendly shrubbery.

Name: Blunderville Crown
Description:
Heavy is the heador the side tablethat wears the crown.

Up to twenty may be placed in a single estate.

Name: Blunderville Flag
Description: A colorful ornament that can add a hint of Blunderville charm to a room or residence.

Name: Blunderville Donut Bumper
Description: Any attempts to take a bite of this bumper may result in disaster. Or a very bad stomachache. Or both.

Name: Blunderville Padded Wall
Description: Perfect for those who often stub their toes on pointier partitions.

Name: Blunderville Rainbow
Description: Because every room could use a rainbow.

Name: Blunderville Hammer
Description: A pastel hammer modeled after those in Blunderville.

Name: Soul of the Pictomancer
Description: Upon the surface of this multi-aspected crystal are carved the myriad deeds of pictomancers from eras past.

Name: Soul of the Viper
Description: Upon the surface of this multi-aspected crystal are carved the myriad deeds of vipers from eras past.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - The Lop Hop
Description: An illustrated manual of the various steps that comprise the Lop Hop, the Loporrits' irrepressibly jolly dance. Use to learn the /lophop emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Greasy Delights
Description: An illustrated manual of the proper method for consuming a bucket of deep-fried chicken in polite company. Use to learn the /eatchicken emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Apocalyptic Charades
Description: An illustrated manual detailing the steps required to produce a convincing facsimile of Hydaelyn's world-ending strike. Use to learn the /sundering emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Defeatist Attitude
Description: An illustrated manual showing the exact angle at which to hang one's head to express a sentiment of utter defeat. Use to learn the /slump emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Projecting Affection
Description: An illustrated manual detailing how to secure the adoration of all who behold you. Use to learn the /loveheart emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Humble Triumph
Description: An illustrated manual detailing how to celebrate your victories without inciting the jealousy of rivals. Use to learn the /humbletriumph emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Embracing Blunders
Description: An illustrated manual detailing how to thoroughly bask in triumph and demand the praise of one's social rivals. Use to learn the /victoryreveal emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - The Eggcellent Host
Description: A detailed manual of how to graciously prepare breakfast for guests who overindulged in the wine. Use to learn the /fryegg emote.

Name: Modern Aesthetics - The Bold and the Braid
Description:
The realm's premier publication on beauty and fashion, this specific copy of Modern Aesthetics covers, in detail, techniques for braiding unruly locks into linewhile allowing others to flow free in defiance of expectation.

Use to unlock a new hairstyle at the aesthetician.
Unavailable to female Hrothgar.

Name: Statice's Wings
Description: For those who have indulged their mischievous side and now long for something stronger. Use to acquire a pair of Statice's wings.

Name: Giant Leaf Parasol
Description: This is a crafted imitation of plant life, not simply errant vegetation cleverly pruned for capitalistic purposes. Honest. Use to acquire a giant leaf parasol.

Name: Colorful Carrotsol
Description: Nine out of ten Loporrits agreethis parasol is without flaw. The tenth could not be reached for comment due to a carrot-induced stomachache. Use to acquire a colorful carrotsol.

Name: Knapsack
Description: Research has proven that wearing a knapsack or similar greatly reduces the likelihood of being pestered with questions about how you can carry so many items. Use to acquire a knapsack.

Name: Wayfarer's Barding
Description: A suit of bespoke chocobo armor lovingly handcrafted by Tataru Taru.

Name: Uolosapa
Description:
To fly after you and perch prettily on your head is its divine calling.

Use item to acquire the uolosapa minion.

Name: The Great White Tsuchinoko
Description:
Delightfully squidgy, and a veritable fountain of good fortune to boot.

Use item to acquire the Great White Tsuchinoko minion.

Name: Tourmaline Weapon
Description:
Stands ready to lend you a helping hand or six.

Use item to acquire the Tourmaline Weapon minion.

Name: Wind-up Oschon
Description:
Guaranteed not to wander off on you.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Oschon minion.

Name: Kydonia Strolls
Description:
For when you need a stony face to stare at you unflinchingly.

Use item to acquire the Kydonia Strolls minion.

Name: Vicarious Vacationer
Description:
A lean, mean, holidaying machine.

Use item to acquire the vicarious vacationer minion.

Name: Wind-up Golbez
Description:
Too small to conceive of and carry out a mass invasion of the Source...or is he?

Use item to acquire the wind-up Golbez minion.

Name: Torgal Pup
Description:
Go on, you know you want to pet the adorable fellow. What could possibly go wrong...?

Use item to acquire the Torgal pup minion.

Name: Pink Bean
Description:
Three, two, one...GO!

Use item to acquire the pink Bean minion.

Name: Pegwin
Description:
You chased after it; now it chases after you.

Use item to acquire the Pegwin minion.

Name: Hydaelyn Idol
Description:
When you ask your mother if you can have Hydaelyn, but she says you already have Hydaelyn at home.

Use item to acquire the Hydaelyn idol minion.

Name: Zodiark Idol
Description:
When you ask your mother if you can have Zodiark, but she says you already have Zodiark at home.

Use item to acquire the Zodiark idol minion.

Name: Wind-up Fourchenault
Description:
Don't even think about dragging it into conflict, or it shall give you a look of sternest disapproval.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Fourchenault minion.

Name: Wind-up Zidane
Description:
Despite appearances, he isn't one for monkeying around.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Zidane minion.

Name: Wind-up Garnet
Description:
She's not aloneshe's following you.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Garnet minion.

Name: Repulu
Description:
Comes complete with a fetching bow tie to prevent misplacement.

Use item to acquire the repulu minion.

Name: Torgal Whistle
Description: This horn-carved instrument emits a steadfast tone that calls the trusty Torgal to your side.

Name: Ark Identification Key
Description: A thin, rectangular piece of what appears to be cermet. Placing it near the Ark will magically bring the advanced transforming machine to life.

Name: Apocryphal Bahamut Horn
Description: When blown, this horn of bone emits an unbridled tone that calls your apocryphal Bahamut to your side.

Name: Crescent Moon
Description: With this dreamy magicked gondola, there is finally a moon that one can ask forand sit on.

Name: Rhiyes Identification Key
Description: A thin, rectangular piece of what appears to be cermet. Placing it near your Rhiyes will magically bring the machine to life.

Name: Oppressor Identification Key
Description: A thin, rectangular piece of what appears to be cermet. Placing it near the oppressor will magically bring the luxuriously appointed warmachina to life.

Name: Lynx of Abyssal Grief Flute
Description: Emitting a tone of irrepressible longing, this flute summons a lynx of abyssal grief to your side.

Name: Sabotender de la Luna Whistle
Description: When blown, this flute emits an adventurous sound that summons forth your sabotender de la luna.

Name: Spectral Statice Whistle
Description: This whistle emits a playful tone that brings spectral Statice fluttering to your side.

Name: Garlond GL-IIT Ignition Key
Description: A thin key that ignites your Garlond GL-IIT's ceruleum engine, bringing the tiller-equipped vehicle rumbling to life.

Name: Peatie Horn
Description: A curved horn that, when blown, emits a flowery tone that brings Peatie, the goobbue maiden, lumbering to your side.

Name: Quaqua Horn
Description: When blown, this horn produces a woody sound that summons forth your quaqua.

Name: Magicked Prism (Uolosapa)
Description: This peculiar contraption creates illusions by weaving together myriad shades of light. Casts a cloud of chittering island birds around the user.

Name: Islecracker
Description: An otherworldly item of celebration that unleashes a blast of streamers, confetti, and magicked projections of your island mammets.

Name: Magicked Prism (Doll Head)
Description: This peculiar contraption creates illusions by weaving together myriad shades of light. Envelops the user's head with the visage of an adorable, terrible doll.

Name: Fierce Tyrant's Attire Coffer
Description:
A banded chest containing a full set of fierce tyrant's attire.

Required level: 1. IL: 1. Cannot be opened in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.

Name: Metian Attire Coffer
Description:
A banded chest containing a complete set of Metian attire.

Required level: 1. IL: 1. Cannot be opened in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.

Name: Imp Suit
Description: Cannot equip with arm, leg, or foot gear.

Name: Paladin's Smaragdine Arms
Description:
A set of arms containing a smaragdine bastard sword and a smaragdine shield.

Required level: 80. IL: 430.

Name: Tonitrua ex Machina Orchestrion Roll
Description: Music roll for Tonitrua ex Machina. Use to add to your orchestrion list.

Name: Idylls of the Empire Orchestrion Roll
Description: Music roll for Idylls of the Empire. Use to add to your orchestrion list.

Name: Forevermore - The Grand Duchy of Rosaria Orchestrion Roll
Description: Music roll for Forevermore - The Grand Duchy of Rosaria. Use to add to your orchestrion list.

Name: Before the Storm - Caer Norvent Orchestrion Roll
Description: Music roll for Before the Storm - Caer Norvent. Use to add to your orchestrion list.

Name: Everybody Falls (Fall Guys Theme) Orchestrion Roll
Description: Music roll for Everybody Falls (Fall Guys Theme). Use to add to your orchestrion list.

Name: Island Durium Sand
Description: A jolly jade-colored sand found in the Cieldalaes.

Name: Island Yellow Copper Ore
Description: What if copper was yellow? Yellow copper, that's what.

Name: Island Gold Ore
Description: The Cieldalaes are rife with golden opportunities...and literal gold.

Name: Island Hawk's Eye Sand
Description: Some experts claim that the only way to obtain this sand is by alchemical processes. It is plain, then, that those experts have never been to the Cieldalaes.

Name: Island Crystal Formation
Description: This naturally occurring crystal from the Cieldalaes contains trace amounts of corrupted aether.

Name: Island Watermelon
Description: Can be sliced, diced, or crushed with one's limbs for sport.

Name: Island Sweet Popoto
Description: It is not known who first referred to this tuber as nature's candy, but whoever did was correct in doing so.

Name: Island Broccoli
Description: The littlest tree. Or the most tree-like vegetable.

Name: Island Buffalo Beans
Description: To bean, or not to bean... That is the question.

Name: Island Watermelon Seeds
Description:
These tiny seeds will grow into refreshing summer treats.

[Growth Period: Two days]

Name: Island Sweet Popoto Set
Description:
Ideal for pie. Just not yet.

[Growth Period: Two days]

Name: Island Broccoli Seeds
Description:
These seeds will grow to be beloved by clever younglings and despised by the unenlightened.

[Growth Period: Two days]

Name: Island Buffalo Bean Seeds
Description:
These beans grow buffalos. No really. They will.

[Growth Period: Two days]

Name: Flawless Net
Description:
An elite net that redefines the meaning of capture. Run...if you dare.

[Guaranteed to catch small animals.]

Name: Flawless Restraint
Description:
The creatures roaming your island have never known restraint until now.

[Guaranteed to catch average-sized animals.]

Name: Flawless Soporific
Description:
A pellet that will convince even the largest and most monstrous of creatures to close their eyes and accept their fate.

[Guaranteed to catch large animals.]

Name: Islekeep's Mythril Pickaxe
Description: This shiny pickaxe will realize your dreams, if your dreams are to gain new materials with shiny pickaxes.

Name: Islekeep's Chisel
Description: This shiny chisel will chip away at substances heretofore unchippable. Please do not use on mammets.

Name: Splendiferous Mammet-sized Spelunking Tools
Description: With these tools, mammets ascend.

Name: Island Peerifool Whistle
Description: This whistle emits a flighty tone that calls your island Peerifool to bear you forth like the most foolish of steeds.

Name: Island Adenium Whistle
Description: This whistle emits a florid tone that calls your island adenium to bear you forth like the floweriest of steeds.

Name: Alzadaal's Treasure Rug
Description: This beautiful replication of the cloth draped across the bounties of Alzadaal's Legacy will remind you of all the coin you yet stand to gain.

Name: Deep-sea Umbrite
Description: An uncommon variety of umbrite gathered from the darkest depths of the ocean.

Name: Athletikos Cloth
Description: Supple fabric with give enough to accommodate a wide range of vigorous movement.

Name: Faded Copy of FINAL FANTASY IV: The Final Battle (Endwalker)
Description: Timeworn pages of sheet music containing the full score for FINAL FANTASY IV: The Final Battle (Endwalker).

Name: FINAL FANTASY IV: The Final Battle (Endwalker) Orchestrion Roll
Description: Music roll for FINAL FANTASY IV: The Final Battle (Endwalker). Use to add to your orchestrion list.

Name: The Red Wings (Endwalker) Orchestrion Roll
Description: Music roll for The Red Wings (Endwalker). Use to add to your orchestrion list.

Name: Kingdom of Baron (Endwalker) Orchestrion Roll
Description: Music roll for Kingdom of Baron (Endwalker). Use to add to your orchestrion list.

Name: A Gentleman to Walk with Me Orchestrion Roll
Description: Music roll for A Gentleman to Walk with Me. Use to add to your orchestrion list.

Name: Fair Winds to Guide Orchestrion Roll
Description: Music roll for Fair Winds to Guide. Use to add to your orchestrion list.

Name: Course Uncharted Orchestrion Roll
Description: Music roll for Course Uncharted. Use to add to your orchestrion list.

Name: Myths of the Realm Orchestrion Roll
Description: Music roll for Myths of the Realm. Use to add to your orchestrion list.

Name: O Speaker, Slumber Orchestrion Roll
Description: Music roll for O Speaker, Slumber. Use to add to your orchestrion list.

Name: O Hunter, Rejoice Orchestrion Roll
Description: Music roll for O Hunter, Rejoice. Use to add to your orchestrion list.

Name: Pennons Aloft Orchestrion Roll
Description: Music roll for Pennons Aloft. Use to add to your orchestrion list.

Name: From Fear to Fortitude Orchestrion Roll
Description: Music roll for From Fear to Fortitude. Use to add to your orchestrion list.

Name: In the Balance (Amanda Achen Vocals) Orchestrion Roll
Description: Music roll for In the Balance (Amanda Achen Vocals). Use to add to your orchestrion list.

Name: Sanctuary Materiel Container
Description:
Awarded to islekeeps who have made an outstanding contribution to the island sanctuary initiative.

Contains a random assortment of items, including island sanctuary mounts and furnishings.

Name: Isleworks Fruit Punch
Description:
An assortment of fresh fruits blended together to delicious effect.

Category: Confections
Required Time: 4 hours

Name: Isleworks Sweet Popoto Pie
Description:
The sweet variant of popotoes made even sweeter and delectable as an oven-baked pie. 

Category: Confections/Foodstuffs
Required Time: 8 hours

Name: Isleworks Peperoncino
Description:
Sauteed island broccoli joins freshly prepared peperoncino to make for a delightfully savory dish.  

Category: Foodstuffs
Required Time: 6 hours

Name: Isleworks Buffalo Bean Salad
Description:
A salad not so much delicious as it is nutritious.

Category: Foodstuffs/Creature Creations
Required Time: 4 hours

Name: Island Durium Tathlums
Description:
A pair of durium tathlums forged in the sanctuary workshop.

Category: Arms/Metalworks
Required Time: 6 hours

Name: Isleworks Brass Serving Dish
Description:
A fancy dish for fancy people, fashioned in the sanctuary workshop.

Category: Sundries/Metalworks
Required Time: 4 hours

Name: Isleworks Gold Hairpin
Description:
A glamorous hairpin forged from gold ore in the sanctuary workshop.

Category: Accessories/Metalworks
Required Time: 8 hours

Name: Island Grinding Wheel
Description:
A grinding wheel manufactured in the sanctuary workshop.

Category: Sundries
Required Time: 6 hours

Name: Mammet of the Cycle Award
Description:
A dignified crystalline statue sculpted in honor of the hardest working mammet in a given cycle.

Category: Furnishings
Required Time: 8 hours

Name: Exquisite Dragon's Beard Fists
Description: Weapon appearance may take precedence over the display of hand gear.

Name: Elevated Ester
Description: An organic compound created by Studium scholars with the aim of further enhancing the abilities of previously augmented weaponry.

Name: The State of the Realm Orchestrion Roll
Description: Music roll for The State of the Realm. Use to add to your orchestrion list.

Name: Who I Really Am Orchestrion Roll
Description: Music roll for Who I Really Am. Use to add to your orchestrion list.

Name: Away (Refrain) Orchestrion Roll
Description: Music roll for Away (Refrain). Use to add to your orchestrion list.

Name: To Sail Forbidden Seas Orchestrion Roll
Description: Music roll for To Sail Forbidden Seas. Use to add to your orchestrion list.

Name: Find the Flame Orchestrion Roll
Description: Music roll for Find the Flame. Use to add to your orchestrion list.

Name: Land of Eikons Orchestrion Roll
Description: Music roll for Land of Eikons. Use to add to your orchestrion list.

Name: Standard Rationing Manual
Description:
Literature outlining basic cooking and rationing techniques.

Increases meal effect duration.
Duration Increase: +15m  Duration: 120m
Overwrites company actions with similar effects.

Name: Gold Saucer Aetheryte Ticket
Description: A voucher for instant teleportation to the Gold Saucer's entrance.

Name: Vegetal Voucher
Description:
A voucher ostensibly named for its verdant color.

Can be exchanged with the horrendous hoarder for an island adenium whistle.

Name: Tales of Adventure: Endwalker
Description:
A detailed record of one hero's journey to the far reaches of Eorzea and beyondso detailed, in fact, that all who read it come to swear they experienced the events firsthand.

Use to instantly complete all main scenario quests up through The Coming Dawn. Cannot be used outside large settlements. Automatic logout will commence upon usage.

Name: Tales of Adventure: One Paladin's Journey IV
Description:
A detailed record of one adventurer's continuing path to becoming a realm-renowned paladinso detailed, in fact, that all who read it come to swear they experienced the events firsthand.

Use to instantly level paladin to 90 and complete all job quests and tank role quests up through A Path Unveiled. Cannot be used outside large settlements. Automatic logout will commence upon usage.

Name: Tales of Adventure: One Retainer's Journey IV
Description:
A detailed record of one retainer's path to becoming a desperately sought-after servitorso detailed, in fact, that all who read it come to swear they experienced the events firsthand.

Hand over to instantly raise the level of a retainer up to a maximum of 90. (Retainer level cannot exceed current character level in the relevant class/job.)

Name: Irregular Tomestone of Goetia
Description:
One of only a few in existence, this Allagan tomestone contains a wealth of outrageous demonological theories that would shock and appall most contemporary experts.

Can be exchanged with itinerant moogles for certain items.

Name: Hrothgar Vest
Description: Fits: Hrothgar

Name: Hrothgar Vambraces
Description: Fits: Hrothgar

Name: Hrothgar Tights
Description: Fits: Hrothgar

Name: Hrothgar Caligae
Description: Fits: Hrothgar

Name: Yo-kai Watch Framer's Kit
Description:
Tools for enhancing a portrait. Use to unlock embellishments fit for a Yo-kai enthusiast.
Includes Portrait Elements: Background, Frame, Accent
Includes Plate Elements: Base Plate, Backing, Top Border, Plate Frame, Accent

Name: Sparkling Citrus Refreshment
Description:
Dehydrated adventurers, rejoicethis crisp, bubbly beverage boasts an invigorating citrus kick that will thoroughly quench one's thirst on the road. Guaranteed to make even the most arduous trials feel like a tropical vacation.

EXP Bonus: +4%  Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Mountain Zu Horn
Description: A curved horn that, when blown, emits a refreshing note that summons forth your mountain zu.

Name: Ttokrrone Scale
Description: A thick, hardy scale that once belonged to Ttokrrone, the serpentine tural vidraal.

Name: Mica Magicog
Description: A gear torn from the mechanical heart of Mica the Magical Mu.

Name: Twilight Gemstone
Description: A highly sought-after gem whose gentle gradation bears a striking resemblance to an early evening sky.

Name: High-density Fiberboard
Description: Countless wood fibers are bound together and highly compressed to create this manufactured board.

Name: Mount Token
Description: A pile of these certificates can be traded to certain splendors vendors for impressive tamed beasts.

Name: Country Cottage Wall
Description:
A set of four walls designed for those who wish to give their estate a quaint, rural look.

Can only be used with cottages on small plots of land.

Name: Country House Wall
Description:
A set of four walls designed for those who wish to give their estate a quaint, rural look.

Can only be used with houses on medium plots of land.

Name: Country Mansion Wall
Description:
A set of four walls designed for those who wish to give their estate a quaint, rural look.

Can only be used with mansions on large plots of land.

Name: Wine Coupe Tower
Description:
A decadent array of carefully stacked glasses, sure to impress guests at parties...as long as they don't come crashing down.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Critical Hit Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  VIT Bonus: +5% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Skyruin Trophy
Description:
This decorative winged object evokes Valigarmanda's elemental prowess and perilous wrath.

One per estate only.

Name: Resilient Sword Stand
Description:
Twin blades that tell a story of ambition, domination, and loss.

One per estate only.

Name: Kitchen Cabinet
Description: This wooden cabinet has a near-infinite capacity for storing utensils and knickknacks. Makes an excellent partition due to its imposing size and sturdy construction.

Name: Slovenly Chair
Description: Now cluttered with an ever-present collection of household odds and ends, this chair's transformation from seat to shelf was a gradual affair.

Name: Stuffed Axolotl Eft
Description: Although equally endearing, this stuffed ornament is considerably less slimy than its live counterpart.

Name: Stuffed Flag
Description: Modeled after a certain reindeer calf, this plush toy thankfully lacks the real Flag's prodigious appetite.

Name: Fluffy-wuffy Stuffed Drippy
Description: Crafted to resemble a splishy-wishy young nixie, and infused with levitation magicks, this whimsical plushie floats like a balloon.

Name: Stuffed Punutiy
Description: A cuddly punutiy lovingly rendered in fluffy fabric.

Name: Decorative Hingan Door
Description: A window crafted to resemble a Hingan-style sliding door.

Name: Sunset Phasmascape
Description: An imitation skylight with illusory properties. Gaze upwards to appreciate this portal to a striking crimson sky.

Name: Goblet Phasmascape
Description: This advanced magitek contraption displays a breathtaking view of the Goblet in all its splendor.

Name: Lavender Beds Phasmascape
Description: This advanced magitek contraption displays a picturesque cluster of hillside houses at the Lavender Beds.

Name: Mist Phasmascape
Description: This advanced magitek contraption displays the community of Mist and the stunning stretch of coastline it sits atop.

Name: Shirogane Phasmascape
Description: This advanced magitek contraption displays the vibrant rooves and tree-topped outcrops of Shirogane.

Name: Empyreum Phasmascape
Description: This advanced magitek contraption displays the ornate, pointed spires that punctuate the Empyreum skyline.

Name: Twintop Table
Description: A simple, functional table. The two-tiered design opens up a wealth of storage possibilities.

Name: Mug of Cocoa
Description:
A mug brimming with deliciously sweet, velvety hot cocoa.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Determination Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  VIT Bonus: +5% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Everkeep Striking Dummy
Description:
A striking dummy designed in the Everkeep fashion.

Up to three dummies may be placed in a single estate, regardless of type.

Name: Stargazing Deck
Description: Replete with seating, this elevated wooden platform affords an unparalleled view of the firmament. For the astrologer who prizes comfort as much as the pursuit of heavenly knowledge.

Name: Wooden Garden Gate
Description: A perfectly plain wooden gate that provides passage to your property.

Name: Ruinous Plume
Description: An arcanely complicated feather possessed of three conflicting elemental energies.

Name: Resilient Armor
Description: A piece of gear that became fused to the scales of Zoraal Ja, King of Resolve.

Description:
A banded chest containing a complete set of weathered snakebite attire.

A banded chest containing a complete set of weathered painter's attire.

Name: Skyruin Totem
Description: A small idol of Valigarmanda that emanates aether of varying elements.

Name: Resilient Totem
Description: A small idol of Zoraal Ja, forged primarily with electrope.

Name: Light-heavy Holohelm
Description:
When activated, this electrope-powered device from the Arcadion projects a holographic helmet.

Two helms can be traded for special headgear.

Name: Light-heavy Holoarmor
Description:
When activated, this electrope-powered device from the Arcadion projects a holographic suit of armor.

Four suits can be traded for special body gear.

Name: Light-heavy Hologauntlets
Description:
When activated, this electrope-powered device from the Arcadion projects a holographic pair of gauntlets.

Two pairs can be traded for special arm gear.

Name: Light-heavy Holochausses
Description:
When activated, this electrope-powered device from the Arcadion projects a holographic pair of chausses.

Four pairs can be traded for special leg gear.

Name: Light-heavy Hologreaves
Description:
When activated, this electrope-powered device from the Arcadion projects a holographic pair of greaves.

Two pairs can be traded for special foot gear.

Name: Light-heavy Holoearring
Description:
When activated, this electrope-powered device from the Arcadion projects a holographic earring.

One earring can be traded for a special accessory.

Name: Light-heavy Holoblade
Description: When activated, this electrope-powered device from the Arcadion projects a holographic blade.

Name: Universal Tomestone
Description: Researchers of a long-gone age supposedly constructed this peculiar variety of tomestone with a focus on versatility. When said versatility resulted in limited data storage and transfer capacity, however, they abandoned all hopeand these tomestones with it.

Name: AAC Illustrated: LHW Edition I
Description:
A publication covering the matches and fighters of the light-heavyweight tier.

Copies of the same AAC Illustrated edition can be traded for special gear.

Name: AAC Illustrated: LHW Edition II
Description:
A publication covering the matches and fighters of the light-heavyweight tier.

Copies of the same AAC Illustrated edition can be traded for special gear.

Name: AAC Illustrated: LHW Edition III
Description:
A publication covering the matches and fighters of the light-heavyweight tier.

Copies of the same AAC Illustrated edition can be traded for special gear.

Name: AAC Illustrated: LHW Edition IV
Description:
A publication covering the matches and fighters of the light-heavyweight tier.

Copies of the same AAC Illustrated edition can be traded for special gear.

Name: Surgelight Solvent
Description: A fulminous chemical mixture synthesized with advanced Everkeep technology. Applying it to Quetzalli weapons enables full optimization of the gear's offensive properties.

Name: Surgelight Twine
Description: A fulminous thread synthesized with advanced Everkeep technology. Applying it to Quetzalli vestments enables full optimization of the gear's defensive properties.

Name: Surgelight Glaze
Description: A fulminous coating agent synthesized with advanced Everkeep technology. Applying it to Quetzalli accessories enables full optimization of the gear's defensive properties.

Name: Timeworn Loboskin Map
Description:
This bottle holds a timeworn map classified as risk-reward grade 16 among treasure hunters.

Use the action Decipher to extract the map and examine its contents.
Level 100 recommended.

Name: Timeworn Br'aaxskin Map
Description:
This bottle holds a timeworn map classified as risk-reward grade 17 among treasure hunters.

Use the action Decipher to extract the map and examine its contents.
Level 100 full party (eight players) recommended.

Name: The Spinner
Description: A heavenly portrait of Nymeia, watcher of celestial bodies and goddess of fate.

Name: The Fury
Description: A heavenly portrait of Halone, mover of glaciers and goddess of war.

Name: The Lover
Description: A heavenly portrait of Menphina, keeper of the twin moons and the goddess of love.

Name: The Scholar
Description: A heavenly portrait of Thaliak, ruler of rivers and wisdom and god of knowledge.

Name: The Navigator
Description: A heavenly portrait of Llymlaen, watcher of the seas and goddess of navigation.

Name: The Wanderer
Description: A heavenly portrait of Oschon, ruler of the mountains and god of wanderers and vagrants.

Name: Company Seal Voucher
Description:
This voucher jointly issued by the Grand Companies of Eorzea is redeemable for 10,000 company seals.

Use to acquire the stated amount of company seals for the Grand Company you are enlisted in.

Name: Volcanic Heart Framer's Kit
Description:
Tools for enhancing a portrait. Use to unlock embellishments fit for a champion of the Volcanic Heart.
[Includes: Background/Frame/Accent]

Name: Clockwork Castletown Framer's Kit
Description:
Tools for enhancing a portrait. Use to unlock embellishments fit for a champion of the Clockwork Castletown.
[Includes: Background/Frame/Accent]

Name: Petit Punutiy
Description:
Leading scientists agree: gazing upon a punutiy daily enhances one's sense of well-being.

Use item to acquire the petit punutiy minion.

Name: Air-wheeler M9
Description:
Will whoosh, vroom, and zoom its way into your inner child's heart.

Use item to acquire the air-wheeler M9 minion.

Name: Alpaca Cria
Description:
Rest assured its spit isn't smelly. Yet.

Use item to acquire the alpaca cria minion.

Name: Honeysuckler
Description:
Doesn't have a taste for blood...yet.

Use item to acquire the honeysuckler minion.

Name: Not-so-bighorn
Description:
The bigger the horns, the brighter the future.

Use item to acquire the not-so-bighorn minion.

Name: Ilyikty'i
Description:
A little cub that has aspirations to be a great hunter.

Use item to acquire the Ilyikty'i minion.

Name: Quetzal
Description:
Do not be fooled by its winsome appearanceyou are in the presence of divinity.

Use item to acquire the quetzal minion.

Name: Squeak the Coyote
Description:
Quiet as a cloud and swift as a lightning bolt when on the prowl.

Use item to acquire the Squeak the Coyote minion.

Name: Rororrlo Teh
Description:
Caution: staring directly at its head may result in temporary blindness.

Use item to acquire the Rororrlo Teh minion.

Name: The Cornservant
Description:
Will never let you go hungry.

Use item to acquire the Cornservant minion.

Name: Tankardtender
Description:
Rather more manageable than a barrel.

Use item to acquire the tankardtender minion.

Name: Bluecoat Cat
Description:
Surprisingly sweet-tempered despite its regal bearing.

Use item to acquire the bluecoat cat minion.

Name: Speaking Stone
Description:
Don't even think about getting it started.

Use item to acquire the speaking stone minion.

Name: Wind-up Mamool Ja
Description:
Innocence never looked so adorable.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Mamool Ja minion.

Name: Mischief Maker
Description:
Should only make mischief and not do you one, if the name is to be believed...

Use item to acquire the mischief maker minion.

Name: Tin Sentry T1
Description:
It's your own fault if you get hit.

Use item to acquire the tin sentry T1 minion.

Name: Ambrose the Unfinished
Description:
Unfinished it may be, but it is certainly not unwilling.

Use item to acquire the Ambrose the Unfinished minion.

Name: Black Kitten
Description:
Can you hold your own against her feline ferocity!?

Use item to acquire the Black Kitten minion.

Name: Brushed-up Krile
Description:
She is not to be brushed off in the face of danger.

Use item to acquire the brushed-up Krile minion.

Name: Wind-up Zero
Description:
And thus she is returned.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Zero minion.

Name: Wind-up Erenville
Description:
Happy to follow rather than guide you for a change.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Erenville minion.

Name: Ty'aitya Whistle
Description: This whistle emits a sprightly tone that brings your ty'aitya gliding to your side.

Name: Air-wheeler A9 Identification Key
Description: A thin, rectangular piece of what appears to be electrope. Placing it near your air-wheeler A9 will magically bring the vehicle to life.

Name: Alpaca Whistle
Description: When blown, this whistle emits a snug and steady tone that calls your alpaca to your side.

Name: Wings of Ruin
Description: Manifest your wings of ruin and soar the skies with an aura of irrepressible might.

Name: Wings of Resolve
Description: Manifest your wings of resolve and soar the skies with an aura of undying pride.

Name: Outrunner Identification Key
Description: A thin, rectangular piece of what appears to be electrope. Placing it near your outrunner will magically bring the machine to life.

Name: Mehwapyarra Whistle
Description: When blown, this whistle emits a laid-back tone that calls your mehwapyarra to your side.

Name: Monowheel S1 Identification Key
Description: A thin, rectangular piece of what appears to be electrope. Placing it near your monowheel S1 will magically bring the vehicle to life.

Name: Rroneek Horn
Description: A curved horn that, when blown, emits a stout tone that summons forth your rroneek.

Name: Ullr Horn
Description: This heavy horn emits a dulcet tone that summons Ullr, the dragon with a love of song.

Name: Qeziigural Horn
Description: A curved horn that, when blown, emits an implacable sound that summons forth your qeziigural.

Name: Turali Barding
Description: A suit of chocobo armor designed for travel across a vast continent.

Name: Skyruin Barding
Description: Rest assured that equipping your chocobo with this suit of armor will not actually transform it into a vicious tural vidraal.

Name: Electrope Barding
Description: A suit of chocobo armor created by means of otherworldly technology.

Name: Wild Ride Barding
Description: A bright suit of chocobo armor for the adventurous and fashionable.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Easterly Winds
Description: An illustrated manual depicting the most efficient Far Eastern fanning methods to stave off sweltering summer heat. Use to obtain the /uchiwasshoi emote.

Name: Modern Aesthetics - It Takes Two
Description:
The realm's premier publication on beauty and fashion, this specific copy of Modern Aesthetics covers, in detail, techniques for shaping shorter locks into two feathery, distinct parts that softly frame one's visage.

Use to unlock a new hairstyle at the aesthetician.

Name: Urqopacha Riding Map
Description: This highly detailed map of Urqopacha, including everything from land elevation to the location of exposed rocks and roots, was originally drafted by Pelupelu merchants seeking to reduce delivery times.

Name: Kozama'uka Riding Map
Description: This highly detailed map of Kozama'uka, including everything from land elevation to the location of exposed rocks and roots, was originally drafted by Pelupelu merchants seeking to reduce delivery times.

Name: Yak T'el Riding Map
Description: This highly detailed map of Yak T'el, including everything from land elevation to the location of exposed rocks and roots, was originally drafted by the Yok Huy during their campaign of conquest.

Name: Shaaloani Riding Map
Description: This highly detailed map of Shaaloani, including everything from land elevation to the location of exposed rocks and roots, was originally drafted by the Yok Huy during their campaign of conquest.

Name: Heritage Found Riding Map
Description: This highly detailed map of Heritage Found, including everything from land elevation to the location of exposed rocks and roots, was originally drafted by local couriers seeking to reduce delivery times.

Name: Living Memory Riding Map
Description: This highly detailed map of Living Memory, including everything from land elevation to the location of exposed rocks and roots, was originally drafted by tour guides to prevent visitors from losing their way.

Name: Mosquito Fish
Description:
This inhabitant of Downripple was once utilized as a means of natural pest control.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Pel Frog
Description:
Prized by the Pelupelu, these tiny frogs are often seen traversing the shallow waters of Downripple.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Petticoat Tetra
Description:
Native to Downripple, this freshwater fish is readily identified by its black skirt-like fins. 

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 1 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Reasonscale Silverside
Description:
After being introduced to the Stardust Sea, this striking silver fish soon began to thrive.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 1 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Stardust Shrimp
Description:
This toothsome resident of the Stardust Sea often features in Tuliyollan cuisine.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Shallows Sot
Description:
This saltwater fish can be found lurking in the shallows beneath the For'ard Cabins, where it tries to avoid the attention of predators and inquisitive anglers besides.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 1 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Ghostfish
Description:
Calling the shallow waters of the For'ard Cabins home, this wavekin appears all but translucent.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Permit
Description:
This large saltwater fish roams the waters near the For'ard Cabins, where it enjoys a diet of crustaceans and smaller, slower sea creatures.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Floating Fife
Description:
Though its name may imply otherwise, attempting to play lovely little ditties with this wavekin is ill-advised.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Blue Purse
Description:
The dark body of this saltwater fish contrasts with the golden yellow margins of its fine scales.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Goldfin Cavalli
Description:
This domineering wavekin possesses powerful, gold-tinged fins.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Sea Alpaca
Description:
A peculiar wavekin that faintly resembles an alpaca. Thankfully, it does not share its landbound counterpart's penchant for spitting.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Marbled Hatchetfish
Description:
According to Yok Huy myth, this wavekin was once a mighty warrior's axe, transformed by its wielder's grief.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Starsnipper
Description:
Found among the rocky shallows of the Sunken Stars, this miniscule crustacean partially burrows into the gritty substrate to evade predators. 

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Urqotrout
Description:
The flesh of this trout species is naturally salty.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Yok Huy Stonecutter
Description:
This flatfish calls the still pool of the Sunken Stars its home.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Chirwagur Loach
Description:
An elongated wavekin capable of thriving in the briny waters of Chirwagur Lake.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Alright Alright Alright
Description:
Cautionary tales passed down among the Pelupelu suggest that upon learning of this creature's status as an apex predator, an itinerant Eorzean naturalist issued the confusing statement that it certainly has the milquetoast countenance of a champion, and began muttering a slew of potential appellations. Some of these sounded like dirklander or possibly burpswimmer, and so, in an attempt to save the poor fish's reputation abroad, the local Pelupelu kindly informed him of its indigenous name ere setting off in search of a stiff drink.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Zorlortor
Description:
An endearing amphibian with pale silver coloration.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Shooting Starscale
Description:
This moderately sized fish can be found plying the waters of Chirwagur Lake.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: First Feastfish
Description:
A vaguely egg-shaped freshwater fish found in the depths of Karvarhur the First.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 1 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Urqofrog
Description:
This bulbous amphibian inhabits the ample waters of Karvarhur the First.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Zeh Tortoh
Description:
Often likened to flower petals, these resplendent fish are sought after by aesthetically minded anglers.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Morsel Trout
Description:
This fair-sized freshwater fish is a popular source of sustenance in Urqopacha.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Deepwarden
Description:
An ancient wavekin that lurks in depths unfathomable.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Kozama'uka Skipper
Description:
A small freshwater fish distributed throughout the shallows of Kozama'uka.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Bopo'u Sleeper
Description:
This sizable wavekin is primarily found in the wetlands of Bopo'uihih.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Poison Dyefrog
Description:
A colorful frog endowed with deadly toxins.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Pleated Matamata
Description:
Replete with thorny protusions, the triangular heads of these turtles call to mind fallen leaves.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Uyuy Xage
Description:
As lethal as it is large, this monstrous scalekin calls the shallows of Bopo'uihih home.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Plattershell
Description:
Beneath this mottled crustacean's shell lies a hearty helping of delicious meat.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Candiru
Description:
The waters of Miyakabek'zu are rife with these fierce, carnivorous wavekin.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Trahira
Description:
A somewhat sizable fish that plies the muddy currents of Miyakabek'zu.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Driftwood Catfish
Description:
This species' resemblance to waterborne wooden debris gives it the edge when pursuing its prey.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Oho Hunu
Description:
This diminutive wavekin is known as one of the swiftest swimmers in Ihuykatumu.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 1 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Bronze Pleco
Description:
A rather timid freshwater fish that prefers to lurk among rocks and submerged timber.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Crenicichla
Description:
Found in the fast-flowing waters that cut through the Dewspun Bank, this wavekin is adorned with finely patterned scales.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Hunu Peacock Bass
Description:
This member of the peacock bass family is readily identified by its fiery lateral markings.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Pelubane
Description:
With its razor-sharp teeth and insatiable hunger, this vicious wavekin is as much a threat on land as it is at sea. 

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Giant Trahira
Description:
Native to the waters of Ihuykatumu, this predatory freshwater fish can grow to an impressive size.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Ku'uxage Bitterling
Description:
This variety of bitterling has a habit of leaping through the waterfalls of Ku'uxage.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 1 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Tonguesnatcher
Description:
An ancient crustacean equipped with impressively sharp pincers.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Corn Dace
Description:
A fair-sized freshwater fish said to resemble an ear of the finest Turali corn.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Ka Puyhu
Description:
A multitude of colors adorn the scales of this aesthetically pleasing wavekin.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Ligaka Guppy
Description:
Commonly found in Marsh Ligaka, this species of freshwater fish is known for its striking hue.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Dumplingfish
Description:
Easily identified by its outsized dorsal fin, this wavekin of Marsh Ligaka is a staple food among the Hanuhanu.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

Name: Banded Candiru
Description:
A deceptive wavekin that utilizes its striking scales to deter predators.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Oxydoras
Description:
If it looks like a bludgeon in the water, and floats like a bludgeon in the water...it may not be a bludgeon in the water. It might be this catfish instead.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 3 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Spotted Stingray
Description:
This ray of Marsh Ligaka is covered with a perplexing pattern, ideal for repelling potential predators.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Yellow Peacock Bass
Description:
The banded markings of this moderately large wavekin set it apart from other varieties of peacock bass.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 2 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Shovelnose Catfish
Description:
