Description: A durable tortilla press contrived for Aunt Tii's Tacos.

Name: Lightweight Lantern
Description: A durable-yet-light lantern designed with the diminutive Pelupelu in mind.

Name: Ceremonial Censer
Description: A censer designed for the ceremonial rites practiced within the palace.

Name: Handcrafted Cover Components
Description: A varied assortment of boards, covers, and cords necessary to bind a book of local folklore.

Name: Pelupelu Cover Components
Description: A collection of colorful components from Urqopacha, ideal for binding a book of Pelupelu tales.

Name: Moblin Cover Components
Description: A variety of Earthenshire-inspired components, tailor-made to bind a book of Moblin tales.

Name: Mamool Ja Cover Components
Description: Crafted with the azure forests of Yak T'el in mind, these components are fit for binding a book of Mamool Ja myths.

Name: Cherimoya Juice
Description: This blended beverage contains essential vitamins that moisturize Mamool Ja scales and relieve itching.

Name: Fermented Aloe Juice
Description: The pungent, oddly fruity smell is guaranteed to lure out Moblins from malms away.

Name: Ja Tiika Juice
Description: This bright green refreshment is the perfect pick-me-up for a Hanuhanu whose energy is flagging.

Name: Prickly Pear Juice
Description: As any Pelupelu will tell you, this curative tonic is made with tunas from Shaaloani... No, not those tunas!

Name: Shunye's Apothecary Staple
Description: A naturally sourced material that promotes a healthy body. Sold for a reasonable price at Shunye's Apothecary.

Name: Shunye's Apothecary Spiritual Supplement
Description: Guaranteed to lift the spirits and ward off malevolent humours, these are one of the most popular wares sold at Shunye's Apothecary.

Name: Household Cleansing Supplies
Description: A set of supplies commonly used by the Shetona to maintain their home's connection to nature even in the midst of bustling cities.

Name: Deep Earth Fragment
Description: The ancient mud and sand found in the Cexudross crater has solidified into stone-like fragments, which may contain traces of materials left behind in the meteorite impact.

Name: King Puffer
Description:
A satisfyingly spherical and perilously prickly fish native to the waters of Tuliyollal's harbor.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Yok Huy Pleco
Description:
This freshwater fish has scales as enduring as the Yok Huy's architectural legacy.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Qor Pirarucu
Description:
Three yalms of freshwater fish.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Raging Hanuhead
Description:
Between its bright coloring and twisted expression, this cloudfish resembles a sincerely ruffled Hanuhanu.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Fulcrum
Description: Though it will surely restore the scales' balance, there is more that hinges on the success of this replacement fulcrum...

Name: Solar Reflector
Description: A complex device capable of reflecting sunlight at such intensity as to produce a flame, specially designed for the Vows.

Name: Yok Huy Cover
Description: A durable book cover fashioned in Yok Huy stone.

Name: Tonawawtan Cover Components
Description: An assemblage of components and props reminiscent of Xak Tural.

Name: Kukuru Pulp Juice
Description: A sweet and tangy drink with a texture that is ever so faintly pulpy.

Name: Boonewa Soda
Description: Invented by a Mamool Ja juicecrafter, this bubbly brew is a traveler's treat.

Name: Precious Material
Description: Primarily used for decorative purposes, this precious material was found in Urqopacha. It can be purchased from Shunye's Apothecary at a competitive price.

Name: Azure Fragment
Description: Found at the bottom of Iq Rrax Tsoly, this tear-shaped fragment has a faint blue glow.

Name: Cenote Shark
Description:
This enormous creature commutes between cenote and ocean every day to support its loving family. Or, at least, it did.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Fulmisturgeon
Description:
When faced with shocking changes to its environment, this large freshwater fish became shocking itself.

Not included in the fish guide.

Name: Rarefied Raw Ihuykanite
Description:
You don't need to have a green thumb to get your hands on this valuable raw ihuykanite. You will likely need a pickaxe, however.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Artificial Volcanic Rock
Description:
This stone has been painstakingly sculpted to resemble an impressive find.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Raw Dark Amber
Description:
The gemstone of choice for dark goldsmiths.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Titanium Gold Ore
Description:
There's gold in these hills! Titanium gold, that is.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Magnesite Ore
Description:
In addition to its crafting purposes, this ore can be used to deter burglars, provided your aim is true.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Ra'Kaznar Ore
Description:
The perfect smithing material for someone with a penchant for black and purple color schemes.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Ash Soil
Description:
This faintly warm mixture of ash and soil was harvested from an active volcano by a true daredevil of a gatherer.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Kozama'uka Chamomile
Description:
You could keep it in reserve for the next time you require a gemdraught...or have yourself a cozy bedtime beverage. Decisions, decisions.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Wild Agave
Description:
If you think this agave is wild, just wait until you taste the mezcal distilled from it.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Mountain Flax
Description:
With this, perhaps you can craft yourself a nice pair of hiking boots to replace the ones you wore out climbing this mountain in the first place.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Sweet Kukuru Bean
Description:
A true chocolate connoisseur will accept no less than this, the sweetest of all kukuru beans, for their sinfully indulgent sachertortes.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Dark Mahogany Log
Description:
Bring me the darkest mahogany you have! Darker, I say! Darker!

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Acacia Log
Description:
Take this to a skilled carpenter to be processed, and by day's end, you could be the proud owner of a first-rate fork.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Windsbalm Bay Leaf
Description:
A tisane brewed from this exceptional bay leaf would afford a weaver enough energy to sew nearly three dozen muffed mets. Enjoy in moderation.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Electrocoal
Description: An ore containing trace amounts of electrope.

Name: Brightwind Ore
Description: Prolonged exposure to wind and sunlight has allowed this stone to absorb a great deal of aether.

Name: Goldbranch
Description: Though it appears withered at first glance, this glimmering branch is very much aliveor rather, it was, before being torn from its natural environment.

Name: Volcanic Grass
Description: Raised in nutrient-rich volcanic loam, this rare herbage is densely packed with aether.

Name: Fulcrum Components
Description: A set of components for crafting a fulcrum.

Name: Solar Reflector Components
Description: A set of assorted components which can be used to create the solar reflector you behold in your mind's eye.

Name: Yok Huy Supplies
Description: An organized selection of Urqopacha stones and other resources commonly used by the Yok Huy.

Name: Xak Tural Miscellany
Description: A batch of leaves, feathers, and other naturally occuring materials from Xak Tural, handpicked by Zemoweni.

Name: Yok Kukuru Pod
Description: A rather hefty pod harvested from a kukuru tree in Yok Tural. The value is in the beans, but the pulp has its own uses.

Name: Turali Spice Blend
Description: An expertly balanced mixture of medicinal herbs and flavorings local to the continent of Tural.

Name: Legacies Reproduction
Description: A large-scale reproduction of a piece entitled Legacies.

Name: Cracked Prismaticluster
Description:
An elongated crystalline manifestation of aetheric energy cracked in several places.

[Can be exchanged for select combat-based varieties of materia XI.]

Name: Cracked Prismaticrystal
Description:
An elongated crystalline manifestation of aetheric energy cracked in several places.

[Can be exchanged for select non-combat-based varieties of materia XI.]

Name: Cracked Novacluster
Description:
A stelliform crystalline manifestation of aetheric energy cracked in several places.

[Can be exchanged for select combat-based varieties of materia XII.]

Name: Cracked Novacrystal
Description:
A stelliform crystalline manifestation of aetheric energy cracked in several places.

[Can be exchanged for select non-combat-based varieties of materia XII.]

Name: Ornate Archeo Kingdom Cuirass of Fending
Ornate Archeo Kingdom Cuirass of Maiming
Ornate Archeo Kingdom Jacket of Striking
Ornate Archeo Kingdom Jacket of Aiming
Ornate Archeo Kingdom Jacket of Scouting
Ornate Archeo Kingdom Coat of Healing
Ornate Archeo Kingdom Coat of Casting

Tools for enhancing portraits and adventurer plates. Use to unlock embellishments fit for an allied heroa friend, a comrade, a hero.

Tools for enhancing portraits and adventurer plates. Use to unlock embellishments fit for an allied Little Solace supporter.

Includes Portrait Elements: Background, Accent

Tools for enhancing portraits and adventurer plates. Use to unlock embellishments fit for an allied shhhorewalker.

Name: Turali Bicolor Gemstone Voucher
Description:
Proof that you have delivered many a bicolor gemstone.

Copies of the same bicolor gemstone voucher can be traded with Edelina in Mor Dhona for special items.

Name: Garden Sunflower Seeds
Description:
The perfect seeds for novice gardeners. If at first you don't succeed, you can simply give up and eat the rest.

For use in planters.

Name: Red Sunflowers
Description:
A bunch of red sunflowers, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Blue Sunflowers
Description:
A bunch of blue sunflowers, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Yellow Sunflowers
Description:
A bunch of yellow sunflowers, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Green Sunflowers
Description:
A bunch of green sunflowers, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Orange Sunflowers
Description:
A bunch of orange sunflowers, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Purple Sunflowers
Description:
A bunch of purple sunflowers, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: White Sunflowers
Description:
A bunch of white sunflowers, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Black Sunflowers
Description:
A bunch of black sunflowers, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Rainbow Sunflowers
Description:
A bunch of multicolored sunflowers, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Cooking Mezcal
Description: Distilled from the fermented pulp of megamaguey pineapples.

Name: Ut'ohmu Chili Sauce
Description: A sweet and spicy condiment crafted from the paste of Ut'ohmu tomatoes.

Name: Royal Maple Syrup
Description: A viscous, sugary reduction of royal maple sap.

Name: Whipped Cream
Description: A fluffy and faintly sweet plant-based cream made with oilseed extract.

Name: Turali Corn Oil
Description: Extracted from the dried germ of Turali corn, this oil is perfect for frying.

Name: Mountain Salt
Description: Fine grains of divine blessing mined from the mountains of Urqopacha.

Name: Ut'ohmu Tomato
Description: Cultivated under the harsh sun of the Ut'ohmu Horizon, these ruby-red tomatoes are prized for their sweetness.

Name: Royal Maple Sap
Description: A clear, sticky substance extracted from royal maple trees.

Name: Shaaloani Oilseeds
Description: Indigenous to the wilds of Shaaloani, these robust seeds are developed over a period of months, then processed into oil for cooking.

Name: Turali Corn
Description: A superb species of grain native to the continent of Tural.

Name: Mountain Rock Salt
Description: Naturally occurring crystals of mineral-rich meltwater that flows down from the peaks of Urqopacha.

Name: Broccoli
Description: A cruciferous vegetable whose many florets form a distinct tree-like shape.

Name: Bell Pepper
Description: This faintly bitter Turali vegetable is also sometimes used in medicines and perfumes.

Name: Yyasulani Garlic
Description: What this Tural-grown garlic lacks in size, it makes up for with richness of aroma and nutrients.

Name: White Pepper
Description: An aromatic spice with a comparatively milder, sweeter heat.

Name: Mesquite Beans
Description: Prized for their adaptability, these beans can be planted even in the most arid of environs.

Name: Turali Pineapple
Description: This sweet and tangy Turali fruit is protected by a tough, spiky rind.

Name: Turali Aloe
Description: Distantly related to the strain that grows in Meracydia, this hardy succulent stores water in its leaves to survive in dry climates.

Name: Wild Ja Tiika Bananas
Description: These luminescent blue bananas are the direct predecessor of the selectively crossbred strain now grown in Golmajiik Grove. Under the peel, the fruit is mild in color and flavor both.

Name: Sweet Kukuru Bean
Description: An overpoweringly sweet variety of kukuru bean indigenous to Tural.

Name: Mountain Chromite Ore
Description: A decent-sized piece of rock containing the precious metal mountain chromite.

Name: Ruthenium Ore
Description: A decent-sized piece of rock containing the precious metal ruthenium.

Name: Cobalt Tungsten Ore
Description: A decent-sized piece of rock containing the precious metal cobalt tungsten.

Name: Titanium Gold Ore
Description: A decent-sized piece of rock containing the precious metal titanium gold.

Name: Ra'Kaznar Ore
Description: A decent-sized piece of rock containing a variety of darksteel known as Ra'Kaznar.

Name: Mountain Chromite Ingot
Description: An ingot of smelted mountain chromite.

Name: Ruthenium Ingot
Description: An ingot of smelted ruthenium.

Name: Cobalt Tungsten Ingot
Description: An ingot of smelted cobalt tungsten.

Name: Titanium Gold Nugget
Description: A small nugget of impure titanium gold.

Name: Ra'Kaznar Ingot
Description: An ingot of smelted Ra'Kaznar darksteel.

Name: Lar Ore
Description: A decent-sized piece of rock containing a naturally occurring alloy known as Lar.

Name: Raw Ihuykanite
Description: An uncut, unpolished stone containing what appears to be ihuykanite.

Name: Raw Pink Beryl
Description: An uncut, unpolished stone containing what appears to be pink beryl.

Name: White Gold Ore
Description: A decent-sized piece of rock containing the precious metal white gold.

Name: Raw Black Star
Description: An uncut, unpolished stone containing what appears to be black star.

Name: Magnesia Powder
Description: A fine-grain form of the mineral magnesia.

Name: Lar Ingot
Description: An ingot of naturally occurring Lar alloy.

Name: Ihuykanite
Description: A deep green jewel polished in the currents of Ihuykatumu.

Name: Pink Beryl
Description: A translucent pink jewel.

Name: White Gold Ingot
Description: An ingot of smelted white gold.

Name: Black Star
Description: A black jewel that shines with the radiance of the heavens.

Name: Magnesia Whetstone
Description: A whetstone carved from magnesia. Its endothermic properties make it ideal for sharpening metal.

Name: Ginseng Log
Description: A rough-cut log of ginseng timber.

Name: Ceiba Log
Description: A rough-cut log of ceiba timber.

Name: Dark Mahogany Log
Description: A rough-cut log of dark mahogany timber.

Name: Acacia Log
Description: A rough-cut log of acacia timber.

Name: Claro Walnut Log
Description: A rough-cut log of claro walnut timber.

Name: Ginseng Lumber
Description: Processed ginseng lumber.

Name: Ceiba Lumber
Description: Processed ceiba lumber.

Name: Dark Mahogany Lumber
Description: Processed dark mahogany lumber.

Name: Acacia Lumber
Description: Processed acacia lumber.

Name: Claro Walnut Lumber
Description: Processed claro walnut lumber.

Name: Snow Cotton
Description: The frosty flower of a cotton plant. Soft to the touch like a blanket of fresh snow upon the peaks of Urqopacha.

Name: Mountain Flax
Description: Sourced from the lofty mountains of Urqopacha.

Name: Sarcenet
Description: Compared to thread spun from ordinary cocoons, sarcenet is nearly invisible when held between the fingers.

Name: Rroneek Fleece
Description: Thick, heavy hair shorn from a rroneek.

Name: Levinsilk
Description: The dainty purple cocoon of a lightning-aspected silkworm.

Name: Snow Cotton Cloth
Description: Several yalms of snow cotton cloth wrapped around a short wooden distaff.

Name: Mountain Linen
Description: Several yalms of mountain linen wrapped around a short wooden distaff.

Name: Sarcenet Cloth
Description: Finely textured fabric painstakingly woven in the traditional Pelupelu style.

Name: Rroneek Serge
Description: Durable fabric woven from the hair of a rroneek.

Name: Thunderyards Silk
Description: This silk is spun from the crackling cocoons found in Yyasulani.

Name: Yak T'el Spring Water
Description: Clear water bottled at a secluded spring deep in the heart of Yak T'el. Has a distinct earthy aftertaste.

Name: Sungilt Aethersand
Description: The elementally aspected remnants of aetherially reduced matter. This coarse sand glitters most perceptibly in direct sunlight.

Name: Mythloam Aethersand
Description: The elementally aspected remnants of aetherially reduced mineral matter.

Name: Mythroot Aethersand
Description: The elementally aspected remnants of aetherially reduced floral matter.

Name: Mythbrine Aethersand
Description: The elementally aspected remnants of aetherially reduced sea life.

Name: Wind Parsley
Description: A medicinal herb with a crisp, fresh scent.

Name: Kozama'uka Chamomile
Description: A flowering herb found growing throughout Kozama'uka and other hot, humid environs.

Name: Windsbalm Bay Leaf
Description: An especially fragrant herb used in medicinal tinctures.

Name: Eucalyptus
Description: The tough, leathery leaves release a minty-smelling oil when crushed.

Name: Pearl Grass
Description: An aquatic plant with small, arched leaves. Though it has no culinary value, it is a desirable ingredient in many medicines.

Name: Grade 1 Gemsap of Strength
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this Turali gemsap will, similarly to Eorzean dissolvents, dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to strength, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Grade 1 Gemsap of Dexterity
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this Turali gemsap will, similarly to Eorzean dissolvents, dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to dexterity, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Grade 1 Gemsap of Vitality
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this Turali gemsap will, similarly to Eorzean dissolvents, dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to vitality, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Grade 1 Gemsap of Intelligence
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this Turali gemsap will, similarly to Eorzean dissolvents, dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to intelligence, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Grade 1 Gemsap of Mind
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this Turali gemsap will, similarly to Eorzean dissolvents, dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to mind, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Growth Formula Lambda
Description: This alchemically formulated potation accelerates the growth of foliage.

Name: Tungsten Ink
Description: Colorful ink fortified with cobalt tungsten sand to improve aetherial conductivity.

Name: Sanctified Water
Description: Water believed to be blessed by the will of the land. Used to exorcise evil spirits from worldly items.

Name: Acacia Bark
Description: This bark, when boiled down, produces large amounts of tannina substance used by leatherworkers to tan hides.

Name: Silver Lobo Hide
Description: The heavy hide of a silver lobo.

Name: Hammerhead Crocodile Skin
Description: The smooth hide of a hammerhead crocodile.

Name: Br'aax Hide
Description: The majestic hide of a br'aax.

Name: Gomphotherium Skin
Description: The thick hide of a gomphotherium.

Name: Gargantua Hide
Description: The fluffy hide of a gargantua.

Name: Silver Lobo Leather
Description: A large piece of cured silver lobo skin.

Name: Hammerhead Crocodile Leather
Description: A large piece of cured hammerhead crocodile skin.

Name: Br'aax Leather
Description: A large piece of cured br'aax skin.

Name: Gomphotherium Leather
Description: A large piece of cured gomphotherium skin.

Name: Gargantua Leather
Description: A large piece of cured gargantua skin.

Name: Alpaca Fillet
Description: A choice cut of alpaca meat commonly reserved for celebratory banquets.

Name: Swampmonk Thigh
Description: A moist, tender slice of meat taken from the leg of a swampmonk.

Name: Branchbearer Fruit
Description: Harvested from the body of a branchbearer. The green flesh is exceedingly sour.

Name: Nopalitender Tuna
Description: Harvested from the body of a nopalitender. Its flesh is watery, yet sweet.

Name: Megamaguey Pineapple
Description: Harvested from the body of a megamaguey. Like agave, it can be used to produce mezcal with a rich and full-bodied flavor.

Name: Poison Frog Secretions
Description: The viscous secretions of a poison frog.

Name: Lesser Apollyon Shell
Description: The chitinous exoskeleton of a lesser apollyon.

Name: Ty'aitya Wingblade
Description: The sharp keratin barb of a ty'aitya.

Name: Tumbleclaw Weeds
Description: Dried plant matter typically wrapped around the body of a tumbleclaw. May sometimes be seen rolling along in the breeze, divested of its owner.

Name: Alexandrian Axe Beak Wing
Description: The large, leathery wing of an Alexandrian axe beak.

Name: Boiled Alpaca Steak
Description:
Premium alpaca meat stewed to perfection in a tangy mezcal and lemon sauce.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Mezcal-marinated Swampmonk
Description:
Tender swampmonk thigh soaked overnight in mezcal, then grilled over an open flame.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Acqua Pazza
Description:
Fresh fish and mollusks sauted in frantoio oil, then simmered in a mezcal and tomato broth. Originally invented by fisherfolk who would come home from the markets and make soup using whatever remained of their haul.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Salmon Jerky
Description:
Filleted salmon submerged in brine, marinated in smoky mezcal, then dried for several hours until chewy.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Nasi Goreng
Description:
Cold leftover rice stir-fried with shrimp and spices until steaming hot, then garnished with an egg on top.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Shrimp Cocktail
Description:
Deveined shrimp poached in court bouillon broth and served with cocktail sauce for dipping. The tartness of the lemon helps to balance the spice.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Omelette Rice
Description:
A buttery, runny omelette laid neatly over a bed of pan-fried rice flavored with sweet tomato sauce.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Royal Toast
Description:
Thick sliced bread soaked in a batter of whisked egg and milk, pan-fried until fluffy, and served with a generous drizzle of royal maple syrup.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Banana Ponzecake
Description:
An otherwise ordinary ponzecake, infused with ripe bananas and aloe for a soft, moist textureand a heavenly aroma while baking.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Maple Teriyaki
Description:
Juicy white meat, sliced into strips and stir-fried in a sweet maple glaze.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Sweetmuffin
Description:
Kukuru bean powder has been mixed into the batter for even more sugary sweetness.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Creamy Hot Chocolate
Description:
Brewed with cocoa powder created from sweet kukuru beans, this warm winter beverage is made all the sweeter with a dollop of whipped cream on top.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Creamy Alpaca Pasta
Description:
The rustic handmade noodles are boiled until tender, then tossed in a pan with grilled alpaca fillet and broccoli florets in a cream sauce.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Gateau au Chocolat
Description:
This decadently moist cake is made with downright sinful amounts of kukuru bean powder.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Tender Shortcake
Description:
Layered with whipped cream and sliced nopalitender tunas, this light and fruity dessert is the perfect summertime treat.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Broccoli and Spinach Saute
Description:
A medley of healthy vegetables, stir-fried in corn oil until soft. May be served on its own or atop a bowl of rice.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Rroneek Steak
Description:
A large slab of lightly marinated rroneek chuck, pan-seared to perfection.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Roast Rroneek
Description:
Thin slices of rroneek chuck, seasoned and slow-roasted for hours until tender.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Spaghetti al Olio e Peperoncino
Description:
This classic pasta dish uses two types of oil to bring out the spice of the dragon peppers.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Grilled Urqotrout
Description:
A freshly caught urqotrout sprinkled with salt and roasted on a stick over a fire.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Driftwood Catfish Pie
Description:
A hearty seafood pie filled with juicy catfish meat and baked until golden brown.

Name: Rarefied Ginseng Earrings
Description:
Essential to complete your collection of unwearable wooden jewelry.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Ceiba Spear
Description:
The detailed etchings in the blade make this polearm ideal for displaying on walls, tables, or perhaps leaning upright in the corner of the lavatory to confuse your guests.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Dark Mahogany Necklace
Description:
Dark mahoganyfor when regular mahogany just isn't foreboding enough.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Acacia Rod

The glowing gem can also double as a lantern for your bedchambers, in case you happen to be deathly afraid of black mages hiding in your closet.

For collectable submissions only.

Description:
Here's a riddle: what is black when you get it, red while you use it, and white when you discard it? Hopefully not this grinding wheel.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Claro Walnut Fishing Rod
Description:
If you've ever wished your fishing rod could be mistaken for a crooked firearm, this might just be your lucky day.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Mountain Chromite Fists
Description:
Wearing these, you will surely feel as though you could punch a mountain. Note that punching a mountain is not recommended.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Ruthenium War Axe
Description:
Fit for only the most ruthless of warriors. Or miners, if you pretend it's a pickaxe.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Cobalt Tungsten Scimitars
Description:
Unlike other tungsten scimitars, these are ferromagnetic, which may prove disastrous should your opponent's weapon be made of manganese.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Titanium Gold Mortar
Description:
This mortar is made of titanium gold...which is assumed to be far better than regular gold.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Ra'Kaznar War Scythe
Description:
The automated saw chain makes this scythe an excellent choice for cutting down trees, branches, and other dastardly foes.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Ra'Kaznar Round Knife
Description:
Perfect for bored leatherworkers who would enjoy the added thrill of accidentally stabbing themselves with the little metal feather on the pommel.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Mountain Chromite Alembic
Description:
I'm not here to hikeI'm here to do science!

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Ruthenium Sabatons
Description:
Guaranteed to win you a saba-ton of envious looks from everyone in your vicinity.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Cobalt Tungsten Chocobo Frypan
Description:
You mean to tell me a chocobo fried this pan?

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Titanium Gold Thorned Corselet
Description:
As if this corselet wasn't already daunting enough, you will have to ask a friend to lace up the strings in the back for you.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Ra'Kaznar Greaves
Description:
A valuable rarefied addition to any greave enthusiast's collection...assuming there is such thing as greave enthusiasts.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Ra'Kaznar Ring
Description:
You hung it on a tree branch!? Well, now I'll never find it!

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Lar Longbow
Description:
When the House of Splendors conducted a survey among archers to gauge their clientele's ideal features on a longbow, an overwhelming majority answered with little feather tassels.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Ihuykanite Circlet
Description:
Remember to coordinate your other accessories when you wear this to formal functions. Gold and silver simply do not mix.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Cobalt Tungsten Tuck
Description:
Outside of combat, the serrated edge is perfect for slicing through particularly stale bread.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied White Gold Choker
Description:
Are you quite sure this is genuine white gold? Because to me it looks more...red and glowy.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Ra'Kaznar Orrery
Description:
Ask your local astrologian whether buying this orrery is in the cards for you.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Black Star Earrings
Description:
For those optimistic collectors who wish to be starry-eyed and starry-eared.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Loboskin Fingerless Gloves
Description:
Many silver lobos perished so that you might feel the breeze against your fingers.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Crocodileskin Leggings
Description:
As I have always said, the ideal footwear has no fewer than five belts on each shoe.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Br'aaxskin Armlets
Description:
For reasons unknown, avid collectors insist upon the inclusion of matching rings for these armlets.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Gomphotherium Brais
Description:
Do take care not to sit too close to your friends while wearing these. The little spikes are very sharp.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Gargantuaskin Trousers
Description:
The glossy fabric is surprisingly water-resistant, for those who tend to spill beverages directly onto their lap.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Gargantuaskin Hat
Description:
A single gargantua hide could theoretically produce a dozen of these hats, assuming the beast doesn't make you into a hat first.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Snow Cotton Beret
Description:
Should the fetching feather accents fall off, you need only ask the nearest Hanuhanu for a suitable replacement.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Mountain Linen Top
Description:
In order to try it on, you'll have to figure out which of its many belts are functional and which are purely decorative.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Sarcenet Kecks
Description:
The elastic waistband offers great succor to those attending fancy dinner parties with six or more courses.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Rroneek Serge Hat
Description:
Tragically, this hat is nowhere near as adorable as the rroneek whose hide was used to make it.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Thunderyards Silk Gloves
Description:
Do note that these are not one size fits all, or else you may soon end up with rarefied fingerless gloves.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Thunderyards Silk Culottes
Description:
Gives new meaning to the phrase fancy pants.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Loboskin Grimoire
Description:
The feather doubles as a bookmark in case you need to take a mid-summon bathroom break.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Gemsap of Dexterity
Description:
Once you've tried this superior gemsap, you'll wonder how you ever aimed a gun without it.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Br'aaxskin Codex
Description:
You'll feel like a wild br'aax in the jungle, wielding this codex in the comfort of your luxury estate.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Cunning Craftsman's Tisane
Description:
Perfect for the night before a major social function when you've just realized you forgot to craft your costume.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Gemdraught of Vitality
Description:
One sip and you'll feel as though every ilm of your body has been made steel, impervious to the feeble blows of mortal mennot altogether different from a night at the pub.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Claro Walnut Flat Brush
Description:
This one isn't for paintingit's for holding and thinking about painting.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Boiled Alpaca Steak
Description:
Tastes so good, you'll feel lightheaded...or perhaps that's just the rarefied air of Urqopacha. Hard to say.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Banana Ponzecake
Description:
Only the finest Ja Tiika bananas were allowed to overripen in order to make this exquisite dessert.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Turali Pineapple Ponzecake
Description:
Normally this ponzecake is reserved for large festivals, but when has that ever stopped anyone? Every day is a celebration where cake is involved.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Salmon Jerky
Description:
After you've had a taste of this jerky, you may find yourself strangely compelled to swim upstream in search of more.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Stuffed Peppers
Description:
These roasted bell peppers have been stuffed to bursting with deliciousnessa feeling you will surely relate to when you eat them.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Tacos de Carne Asada
Description:
These toothsome tacos are sure to steal the hearts of even the most stalwart Studium scholars.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied White Gold Ore
Description:
For those who seek to smelt only the whitest and goldest of white gold.

For collectable submissions only.

Name: Rarefied Acacia Bark
Description:
Used in the tanning of the finest quality hide for a leather so durable, the poor gargantua may one day forgive you for slaying it.

For collectable submissions only.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Nano Lord
Description:
The land probably won't tremble before his might.

Use item to acquire the Nano Lord minion.

Name: Uma-no-unicolt
Description:
Wishes to embark on a journey with one who is pure of heart.

Use item to acquire the uma-no-unicolt minion.

Name: Adamant Weapon
Description:
A diamond by any other name would shine as brightat least when scale is accounted for.

Use item to acquire the Adamant Weapon minion.

Name: Toco Toquito
Description:
A tropical bird that is all beak and has a squawk to match.

Use item to acquire the toco toquito minion.

Name: Shshuye
Description:
One day it may become a dread tural vidraal, but it is not this day.

Use item to acquire the shshuye minion.

Name: Spinettesaurus
Description:
Small though it may be, never let it be said that it has no spine.

Use item to acquire the spinettesaurus minion.

Name: Wind-up Pelupelu
Description:
The perfect souvenir, if it does say so itself.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Pelupelu minion.

Name: Tin Soldier S3
Description:
The toy with a body of tin and a heart of gold.

Use item to acquire the tin soldier S3 minion.

Name: The Deathservant
Description:
Literally has a taste for life.

Use item to acquire the Deathservant minion.

Name: Wisp of Darkness
Description:
What it cannot smother, it nibbles. What it cannot nibble, it tickles.

Use item to acquire the wisp of Darkness minion.

Name: Wind-up Themis
Description:
A minion as loyal as your star is brighta minion not bound by the confines of this world, or any other.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Themis minion.

Name: The Lawnblazer
Description:
Railroad not required.

Use item to acquire the Lawnblazer minion.

Name: Eternal Barding
Description: A suit of chocobo armor designed to resemble Queen Eternal.

Name: Starlight Stalls Barding
Description: A suit of chocobo armor designed and crafted by the Saint of Nymeia himself in order to help spread warmth and cheer at the Starlight Stalls.

Name: Punutiy Horn
Description: This horn of bone produces a languid sound that calls your trusty punutiy to your side.

Name: Hovering Hot Pot Whistle
Description: When blown, this whistle emits a divine tone that summons your hovering hot pot.

Name: Wings of Eternity
Description: Manifest your wings of eternity and soar the skies with an aura of unwavering determination.

Name: Dais of Darkness
Description: Take to the skies on this piece of the battlefield created by the Cloud of Darkness, safe in the knowledge that it will not suddenly phase from existence.

Name: Shroud of Darkness
Description: Envelop yourself in this sliver of the Cloud of Darkness's raiment, and know the feeling of being the dread voidsent queen. All-consuming powers of Darkness not included.

Name: Barreltender Whistle
Description: This whistle emits a lusty tone that calls your barreltender flexing to your side.

Name: Eggeater Horn
Description: A horn that, when blown, brings the eggeater scrambling to your side.

Name: Vacuum Suit Identification Key
Description: A thin, rectangular piece of some unknown material. Placing it near your vacuum suit will magically bring the machine to life.

Name: Modern Aesthetics - Doing the Wave
Description:
The realm's premier publication on beauty and fashion, this specific copy of Modern Aesthetics covers, in detail, techniques for achieving an effortlessly textured bob suitable for all occasions.

Use to unlock a new hairstyle at the aesthetician.

Name: Modern Aesthetics - A Half Times Two
Description:
The realm's premier publication on beauty and fashion, this specific copy of Modern Aesthetics covers, in detail, techniques for taming tresses into two perfectly plaited halfbraids, replete with ribbons and all.

Use to unlock a new hairstyle at the aesthetician.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Awaiting Orders
Description: An illustrated manual detailing the optimal stance in which to await further instruction. Use to learn the /attend emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Personal Perfection
Description: An illustrated manual detailing how to preserve an aesthetic image of your person. Use to learn the /visage emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Fancy Beverages
Description: An illustrated manual of the rhythmic motions required to produce any number of sophisticated beverages. Use to learn the /shakedrink emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Flowerbed Maintenance
Description: An illustrated manual of how to bring back neglected flowers from the brink of dry demise. Use to learn the /water emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Bubbly Diversions
Description: An illustrated manual of how to embrace your inner child and brew up an iridescent barrage of whimsy. Use to learn the /blowbubbles emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Floral Presentations
Description: An illustrated manual detailing the correct etiquette for a floral display of affection. Use to learn the /bouquet emote.

Name: Everkeep Certificate of Grade 1 Import
Description: A note of promise granted for the delivery of archeo kingdom equipment.

Name: Cattleya Seeds
Description:
With sufficient care, these seeds will grow into resplendent, and surprisingly resilient, orchid plants.

For use in planters.

Name: Red Cattleyas
Description:
A bunch of red cattleyas, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Blue Cattleyas
Description:
A bunch of blue cattleyas, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Bouquets can be placed within select vases for display in estates.

Name: Purple Cattleyas

Name: Rainbow Cattleyas
Description:
A bunch of multicolored cattleyas, selectively fertilized to achieve their vibrant color.

Name: Ceviche
Description:
Succulent chunks of cloudfish in a zesty salt and lemon marinade. Beloved by residents of Tuliyollal.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Cloudsail Meuniere
Description:
A delicate cut of cloudsail dusted with flour and sauted in butter until golden brown.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Optical Fibergrass
Description: The fibrous tendrils that form this peculiar grass have exceptional light-transmitting properties.

Name: Alexandrian Ore
Description: A decent-sized piece of rock containing metal composites unique to Alexandria.

Name: Optical Nanofiber
Description: A bundle of light-transmitting fibers hewn together into a length of curious cord.

Name: Alexandrian Plate
Description: A remarkably durable metal sheet that glows with a twilight luster.

Name: Condensed Solution
Description: A highly condensed and potent alchemical solution. Highly effective, but at what exactly remains to be seen.

Name: Eternal Queensguard
Description: A remnant of one of the units deployed in battle by Queen Eternal.

Name: Locomotive Lubricant
Description: A single thick coat of this oil will greatly reduce friction between the many moving parts of a train.

Name: Carriage Furnishing Supplies
Description: Packed with cushions, lighting fixtures, and other materials intended to enhance the train riding experience.

Name: Mapmaking Pigment
Description: Once properly processed, this colorant is applied to a map to add depth and detail.

Name: Industrial Sanitizing Fluid
Description: The chemicals contained herein are used to create a powerful cleaning agent popular among locomotive engineers.

Name: Trackbed Repair Materials
Description: An assortment of stone yet to be crushed into railroad ballast.

Name: Rail Grindstone
Description: When used to polish the rails and castings, the subsequent reduction in friction offers a much quieter train ride.

Name: Plush Carriage Seating
Description: These luxurious cushioned seats offer superior comfort for train rides of any duration.

Name: Map Printing Essentials
Description: Includes everything required to print painstakingly detailed maps, without which Tuliyollan citizens would surely struggle to navigate Vanguard.

Name: Engineer's Supply Kit
Description: These toolboxes hold a full set of supplies favored by the engineers of Xak Tural Railing.

Name: Railroad Repair Kit
Description: Packed neatly with spikes, ties, and other sturdy components used to lay rail.

Name: Rail Grindstone Components
Description: This heavy sack holds everything needed to assemble a grindstone that will polish your rails to silent perfection.

Name: Carriage Seat Components
Description: Contains just enough fabric and cushioning to build a single row of comfortable, durable train seats. Instructions not included.

Name: Map Printing Components
Description: An assortment of raw materials needed to create paper and ink for use in printing.

Name: Engineer's Supply Kit Components
Description: Used in the construction of various implements a locomotive engineer may need on the job.

Name: Railroad Repair Kit Components
Description: Once the included steel has been used to construct spikes and joints, the wooden box may be repurposed into ties for maximum efficiency.

Name: Modern Aesthetics - Head Hound
Description:
The realm's premier publication on beauty and fashion, this specific copy of Modern Aesthetics covers, in detail, techniques for coaxing one's locks into a rambunctious side braid and ponytail combination.

Use to unlock a new hairstyle at the aesthetician.

Name: Modern Aesthetics - Scion Special Issue IV
Description:
The realm's premier publication on beauty and fashion, this limited edition of Modern Aesthetics covers, in detail, techniques for emulating the style of G'raha Tiadefinitively the dreamiest Scion of the Seventh Dawn, despite what previous editions may purport.

Use to unlock a new hairstyle at the aesthetician.

Name: Modern Aesthetics - Voidswept Strands
Description:
The realm's premier publication on beauty and fashion, this specific copy of Modern Aesthetics covers, in detail, techniques for achieving a perfectly unbalanced asymmetric bob.

Use to unlock a new hairstyle at the aesthetician.

Name: Clouddark Demimateria I
Description: A crystallized mass of residual spiritbond energies transferred to an article of weaponry or armor by the Cloud of Darkness during its creation.

Name: Clouddark Demimateria II
Description: A crystallized mass of residual spiritbond energies transferred to an article of weaponry or armor by the Cloud of Darkness during its creation.

Name: Pure White Interior Wall
Description: An interior wall of plain, pristine white for maximum versatility.

Name: Light Wood Flooring
Description: Flooring made from rustic planks in an unpretentious pale shade.

Name: Flat Ceiling Lamp
Description: This unobtrusive lighting fixture is ideal for those who would rather not draw attention to the ceiling.

Name: Wood-fired Range
Description: This multi-purpose brick oven doubles as a charming fireplace.

Name: Holodisplay
Description: Activate (and deactivate) projections of important-looking graphs with the press of a button. The future is now.

Name: Storybook Bench
Description: Beloved by the orphans of Menphina's Arms, this bench is perfect for reading stories aloud to friends.

Name: Sweet Dreamer's Stall
Description: Packed chock-full of sweets and treats, this stall is guaranteed to delight children and inner children alike.

Name: Frilly Curtains
Description: The lace hem of the top treatment adds a delicate touch to these cutesy curtains.

Name: Botanist's Wall Frames
Description: A collection of wall hangings that celebrate flora and fauna. A painting of one's choosing may be placed in the center frame.

Name: Botanical Loft
Description: Lush green ivy dangles through the slats of this wood lattice fixture.

Name: Patchwork Sofa
Description: Stitched together using a hodgepodge of leather scraps, this sofa has a uniquely colorful charm.

Name: Gleaner's Knapsack
Description: Used to carry both supplies and commissions, the knapsack is arguably the most vital item among a gleaner's possessions.

Name: Popoto Chips
Description:
Thin slices of popoto, fried to a golden crisp and lightly salted to create the perfect snack.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Spell Speed Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  VIT Bonus: +5% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Investigation Map
Description: Clues and clippings linked together with thread in the fashion of a master sleuth. It probably doesn't mean anything.

Name: Apothecary Mortar
Description: Includes a selection of wild herbs commonly ground into medicine.

Name: Grassy Rug
Description: Brings new meaning to the phrase home turf.

Name: Royal Bed
Description: Rumor has it a royal family in the world of Vana'diel sleeps on resplendent beds such as these.

Name: Eternal Cenotaph
Description:
This monument stands as a solemn reminder of a queen who placed her beloved people above all else.

One per estate only.

Name: Skydeep Lamp
Description: Recovered from the Skydeep Cenote's innermost chamber, this lamp gives any room an ethereal purple tinge.

Name: Origenics Monitor Desk
Description: A spacious work desk taken from a storage room in the soul processing division. Additional monitors not included.

Name: Origenics Chair
Description: This office chair was designed to facilitate hours of soul-sucking work.

Name: Strayborough Wall Lamp
Description: The eerie glow of this three-light fixture brings to mind a haunted mansion.

Name: Traumerei Floor Stencil
Description: This whimsical floor stencil depicts a decidedly cuter interpretation of the Lord of Nightmares.

Name: Climbing Wall Partition
Description: Colorful footholds have been added to this partition to create an indoor climbing fixture.

Name: Billiard Table
Description: Upon this finely crafted table, a pole is used to strike a ball at other balls to knock them into the side pockets. Except that one.

Name: Imitation Closet
Description: For those who only want the appearance of storage space.

Name: Fighting Ring
Description: A scaled-down version of the type commonly used in martial arts competitions, this arena still gives you plenty of room to maneuver.

Name: Dartboard Cabinet
Description: Unlike archery or javelin throwing, this game may safely be played indoors.

Name: Laboratory Counter
Description: The inclusion of a sink makes this table well suited to experiments that involve dangerous chemicals.

Name: Kugane-yaki
Description:
The official name of this Far Eastern snack is hotly contested, with some insisting upon blade buns as a nod to the fan-like pattern traditionally stamped on top with a branding iron. Have care when ordering them at a restaurant, lest you inadvertently start an argument.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Determination Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  VIT Bonus: +5% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Classroom Desk
Description: This compact desk was built to accommodate young students throughout their educational journey.

Name: Classroom Chair
Description: This sturdy chair was built to accommodate young students throughout their educational journey.

Name: Classroom Blackboard
Description: Large enough to fit a single day's lesson in any one subject. Chalk and duster included.

Name: Contemporary Iron Shelf
Description: The metal framework will support even the heaviest of potted plants.

Name: Starlight Celebration MMXXIII Advertisement
Description: A festive hand-painted notice advertising the Starlight Celebration of a year gone by.

Name: Valentione's Day MMXXIV Advertisement
Description: A heartwarming and hand-painted notice advertising the Valentione's Day of a year gone by.

Name: Authentic Copy of Crossroads
Description: A masterfully rendered oil depiction of a two-headed champion, an otherworldly visitor, and three agents of darkness, each with their own aims and agendas.

Name: Starlight Kinderpunsch
Description:
A steaming-hot spiced beverage served in a decorative mug. The perfect pick-me-up for the cold and weary.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Piety Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  VIT Bonus: +5% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Starlight Mug Tower
Description: The best part of drinking kinderpunsch is that after you've had a few, you can stack the mugs to form this festive Starlight decoration.

Name: Weathered Porthole
Description: Relax below deck and enjoy smooth sailing, all from the comfort of your estate.

Name: Rail-and-stile Partition
Description: With no panes of glass, what's to stop you from climbing straight through?

Name: Tea Caddy Cabinet
Description: A professional tea drinker must always keep their estate well stocked.

Name: Indoor Awning
Description: The perfect accompaniment to reading nooks, storefront counters, and more.

Name: Dragoon Display Crystal
Description: Designed for those who take great pride in their work, this purely decorative crystal bespeaks enthusiastic commitment to the path of the dragoon.

Name: Paladin Display Crystal
Description: Designed for those who take great pride in their work, this purely decorative crystal bespeaks enthusiastic commitment to the path of the paladin.

Name: Warrior Display Crystal
Description: Designed for those who take great pride in their work, this purely decorative crystal bespeaks enthusiastic commitment to the path of the warrior.

Name: Monk Display Crystal
Description: Designed for those who take great pride in their work, this purely decorative crystal bespeaks enthusiastic commitment to the path of the monk.

Name: Ninja Display Crystal
Description: Designed for those who take great pride in their work, this purely decorative crystal bespeaks enthusiastic commitment to the path of the ninja.

Name: Bard Display Crystal
Description: Designed for those who take great pride in their work, this purely decorative crystal bespeaks enthusiastic commitment to the path of the bard.

Name: Black Mage Display Crystal
Description: Designed for those who take great pride in their work, this purely decorative crystal bespeaks enthusiastic commitment to the path of the black mage.

Name: Summoner Display Crystal
Description: Designed for those who take great pride in their work, this purely decorative crystal bespeaks enthusiastic commitment to the path of the summoner.

Name: White Mage Display Crystal
Description: Designed for those who take great pride in their work, this purely decorative crystal bespeaks enthusiastic commitment to the path of the white mage.

Name: Scholar Display Crystal
Description: Designed for those who take great pride in their work, this purely decorative crystal bespeaks enthusiastic commitment to the path of the scholar.

Name: Authentic Valentione's Heart Chair
Description: This charming wooden chair bears an adorable heart motif, making it clear not only by the comfort of its fluffy pink cushions but its very form factor that it is a product of love. And the passage of time has not made that love any less authentic.

Name: Cactus Patch
Description: Rest assured, these spiky succulents will stay right where you plant them. Don't worry about how many needles they have.

Name: Garden Palm Tree
Description: Add a tropical touch to your backyard with these leafy fronds.

Name: Far Eastern Gazebo
Description: A gazebo designed in the Far Eastern fashion.

Name: Square Stepping Stones
Description: Square stones of varying sizes, carefully placed so as to avoid crushing the flowers.

Name: Electrope Turret
Description: As formidable as it looks, it's merely a lawn decorationbut your neighbors don't need to know that.

Name: Lesser Pillar of Tural
Description: Recovered from Xak Turali ruins, this statue depicts an urn containing a serpentine entity of diminutive size.

Name: Ihuykatumu Flower Plot
Description:
You don't know the name of these grotto flowers, but looking at them makes you feel a bit drowsie.

Up to ten flower plots may be placed in a single garden, regardless of type.

Name: Zormor Stone Lantern
Description: Since olden times, this lantern has illuminated the rocky mountain path at the Summit of Zorbut no more.

Name: Ja Ja Gural Tree
Description: Originating in the depths of Cenote Ja Ja Gural, this luminescent tree lights up your lawn quite vividly.

Name: Authentic Illuminated Topiary Chocobo
Description: Trimmed into the shape of a sitting chocobo, this shrubbery is liberally strung with glowing adornments in the style of the Starlight Celebration. This holiday season, give the gift of authenticity.

Name: Maxims of Mahjong - Alphinaud
Description: A record of aphorisms shared while witness to triumphant victories and crushing defeats at the game table. Use to unlock voiced lines from Alphinaud during Doman mahjong.

Name: Venturous Kamuy Flute
Description: The audacious song of this stout flute is said to summon a kamuy favored by the merchant Rowena.

Name: Magicked Prism (Barreltender)
Description: This peculiar contraption creates illusions by weaving together myriad shades of light. Envelops the user's head with the visage of an exceptionally brawny sabotender.

Name: Cushioned Bench
Description: A wooden bench fitted with a sumptuously soft seat.

Name: Tropical Canopy Bed
Description: To rest upon this bed is to be whisked away to warmer climes and memories of past vacations.

Name: Wachumeqimeqi Balloon
Description: Add intrigue to your abode with a little piece of the Wachumeqimeqi Appreciation Sale.

Name: Paladin's Adamant Arms
Description:
A set of arms containing an adamant bastard sword and adamant scutum.

Required level: 80. IL: 430.

Name: Mandragora Parasol
Description: Whether you want to blend in amongst potentially sentient seedkin, or simply keep your head dry, this parasol quite literally has you covered. Use to unlock a mandragora parasol.

Name: Archon Egg Parasol
Description: Finished in a striking yellow and golden trim, this accessory provides eggceptional protection against all but the worst of downpours. Use to unlock an Archon egg parasol.

Name: Pelupack
Description: A rustic receptacle for all your Pelupossessions. Use to unlock a Pelupack.

Name: The Faces We Wear - Pince-nez
Description: An illustrated periodical on fashionable facial accessories, this particular issue contains a cover story on sophisticated round glasses of varying colors. Use to unlock the pince-nez facewear.

Name: The Faces We Wear - Magnifiers
Description: An illustrated periodical on fashionable facial accessories, this particular issue contains a cover story on practical magnifying glasses of varying colors. Use to unlock the magnifiers facewear.

Name: The Faces We Wear - Brass Goggles
Description: An illustrated periodical on fashionable facial accessories, this particular issue contains a cover story on metallic goggles of varying colors. Use to unlock the brass goggles facewear.

Name: The Faces We Wear - Under-rim Glasses
Description: An illustrated periodical on fashionable facial accessories, this particular issue contains a cover story on dainty oval glasses of varying colors. Use to unlock the under-rim glasses facewear.

Name: The Faces We Wear - Oval Reading Glasses
Description: An illustrated periodical on fashionable facial accessories, this particular issue contains a cover story on elegant oval glasses of varying colors. Use to unlock the oval reading glasses facewear.

Name: The Faces We Wear - Elegant Rimless Glasses
Description: An illustrated periodical on fashionable facial accessories, this particular issue contains a cover story on refined lightweight glasses of varying colors. Use to unlock the elegant rimless glasses facewear.

Name: The Faces We Wear - Cat Eye Glasses
Description: An illustrated periodical on fashionable facial accessories, this particular issue contains a cover story on effortlessly glamorous glasses of varying colors. Use to unlock the cat eye glasses facewear.

Name: The Faces We Wear - Slim Frame Glasses
Description: An illustrated periodical on fashionable facial accessories, this particular issue contains a cover story on delicate round glasses of varying colors. Use to unlock the slim frame glasses facewear.

Description: Timeworn pages of sheet music containing the full score for Paved in Solitude.

Name: Tattered First Movement Score
Description:
Faded sheet music inscribed in an unfamiliar format.

Can be exchanged for certain orchestrion rolls.

Name: Figmental Weapon Coffer
Description:
A fanciful chest containing a figmental weapon.

Required level: 1. IL: 1. Weapon type determined by current job or class at time of opening. Cannot be opened in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.

Name: Brachiosaur Horn
Description: When blown, this timeworn horn produces a thunderous rumble that calls forth your brachiosaur.

Name: Corduroy Felt
Description: The fine wales of this fabric lend it its characteristic sheen.

Name: Aromatic Wood Strips
Description: These slender wooden fragments fill the air with a sumptuous fragrance.

Name: Clouddark Head Gear Coffer (IL 730)
Description:
A tenebrous chest containing a piece of clouddark attire.

Required level: 100. IL: 730. Head gear type determined by current job or class at time of opening. Cannot be opened in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.

Name: Cordia Log
Description: A rough-cut log of cordia timber.

Name: Octahedrite
Description: A chunk of mineral not dissimilar to the meteorites that litter the forest floor in Yak T'el.

Name: Raw Rhodochrosite
Description: An uncut, unpolished stone containing what appears to be rhodochrosite.

Name: Shaaloani Coffee
Description: These rich, dark roasted coffee beans are often used as a tanning agent.

Name: Cochineal Pigment
Description: A vivid red pigment is derived from the tiny insects that cluster upon nopales to feed.

Name: Fulgurite
Description: A chunk of vitrified minerals formed by a lightning strike.

Name: Cordia Lumber
Description: Processed cordia lumber.

Name: Octahedrite Nugget
Description: A small nugget of impure octahedrite.

Name: Rhodochrosite
Description: A translucent red jewel.

Name: Cronopio Leather
Description: A large piece of cured cronopio skin.

Name: Diatryma Felt
Description: A ream of felt pressed from the soft fur-like down of a diatryma.

Name: Grade 3 Gemsap of Strength
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this Turali gemsap will, similarly to Eorzean dissolvents, dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to strength, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Grade 3 Gemsap of Dexterity
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this Turali gemsap will, similarly to Eorzean dissolvents, dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to dexterity, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Grade 3 Gemsap of Vitality
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this Turali gemsap will, similarly to Eorzean dissolvents, dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to vitality, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Grade 3 Gemsap of Intelligence
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this Turali gemsap will, similarly to Eorzean dissolvents, dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to intelligence, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Grade 3 Gemsap of Mind
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this Turali gemsap will, similarly to Eorzean dissolvents, dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to mind, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Hydrophobic Preservative
Description: When applied, this treatment permeates deep into the grain of timber, providing a water-repellant seal.

Name: Shaaloani Coke
Description: A hot-burning fuel made by firing minerals gathered in the plains of Shaaloani.

Name: Neo Abrasive
Description: An abrasive used by Everkeep artisans to buff their wares to a resplendent sheen.

Name: Cronopio Skin
Description: The hide of the mammalian cronopio, a small creature that has inhabited Tural since ancient times.

Name: Diatryma Pelt
Description: The downy pelt of a diatryma, an ancient species of flightless bird native to Tural.

Name: Dichromatic Compound
Description: A two-tone alchemical compound rich in polarizing aetherial energies.

Name: Cassava
Description: A root vegetable cultivated across Tural and staple of myriad different local cuisines.

Name: Splendid Mate Leaves
Description: Grown only in a few select regions, these premium leaves are brewed into an invigorating beverage which many believe has innate magical properties.

Name: Aji Amarillo
Description: A vibrant and versatile orange pepper. Equally delicious eaten raw, ground into a paste, or pickled with salt.

Name: Queso Fresco
Description: This fresh cheese is beloved by countless Turali for its mild, creamy flavor.

Name: Woolback Loin
Description: A prime cut of meat sourced from a woolback native to Yyasulani.

Name: Grade 3 Gemdraught of Strength
Description:
This diluted brew temporarily increases strength for twice the duration of similar potions.

Duration: 30s

Name: Grade 3 Gemdraught of Dexterity
Description:
This diluted brew temporarily increases dexterity for twice the duration of similar potions.

Duration: 30s

Name: Grade 3 Gemdraught of Vitality
Description:
This diluted brew temporarily increases vitality for twice the duration of similar potions.

Duration: 30s

Name: Grade 3 Gemdraught of Intelligence
Description:
This diluted brew temporarily increases intelligence for twice the duration of similar potions.

Duration: 30s

Name: Grade 3 Gemdraught of Mind
Description:
This diluted brew temporarily increases mind for twice the duration of similar potions.

Duration: 30s

Name: Paes de Queijo
Description:
A handful of sumptuously soft cheese-filled bread rolls.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Bubble Tea
Description:
An intensely sweet beverage brimming with chewy tapioca. This drink enjoyed a brief but meteoric rise in popularity among the youths of Everkeep.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:

  Gear Durability Bonus: +3

Name: Minimalist Glade Partition Door

Name: Minimalist Oasis Partition Door

One per estate only.

Name: Cosmic Circumferbench
Description: A marvel of space-saving public infrastructure, this lamppost incorporates 360-degree seating area.

One of only a few in existence, this Allagan tomestone contains apologues so absurd they can scarcely be understood by the modern mind.

Can be exchanged with itinerant moogles for certain items.

This bottle holds a timeworn map classified as risk-reward grade 18 among treasure hunters.

Use the action Decipher to extract the map and examine its contents.
Level 100 full party (eight players) recommended.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Two helms can be traded for special headgear.

Name: DAM
Description: This rainbow energy beverage will allegedly bestow the drinker with metaphorical fangs to gnaw through any challenge and do their DAM-dest. Excessive consumption is ill-advised.

Name: Raven-red Gobtank
Description:
Faster than the blue one.

Use item to acquire the raven-red gobtank minion.

Name: Falcon-blue Gobtank
Description:
Stronger than the red one.

Use item to acquire the falcon-blue gobtank minion.

Name: Wind-up Eald'narche
Description:
After ten long millennia, the dreams of the Zilart will become reality!

Use item to acquire the wind-up Eald'narche minion.

Name: Rroneek Calf
Description:
Has tusks and horns and isn't afraid to use them.

Use item to acquire the rroneek calf minion.

Name: Micro Crow
Description:
Clever and loyalwhat more could one ask for?

Use item to acquire the micro crow minion.

Name: Sunray Ray
Description:
Its eyes are up here.

Use item to acquire the sunray ray minion.

Name: Seikret Fledgling
Description:
Dreams of the day it attains rugged good looks and colorful feathers.

Use item to acquire the Seikret fledgling minion.

Name: Vigorwasp
Description:
Rest assured it won't dump its sac of nectar on you.

Use item to acquire the Vigorwasp minion.

Name: Model Suit
Description:
Comes complete with pocket-sized pilot.

Use item to acquire the model suit minion.

Name: Wind-up Yok Huy
Description:
Gazes out into eternity with eyes unblinking.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Yok Huy minion.

Name: Wind-up Feo Ul
Description:
As your lovely branch, it will lend you its strength!

Use item to acquire the wind-up Feo Ul minion.

Name: Pixie Parasol
Description: Protects the bearer from rain and sun, but not from pixie mischief. Use to acquire a pixie parasol.

Name: Mizutsune Parasol
Description: An extravagant parasol fashioned after a creature of another world. Use to acquire a Mizutsune parasol.

Name: Barding of the Dead
Description: A suit of chocobo armor designed to resemble Necron.

Name: Pilgrim's Barding
Description: A suit of chocobo armor inspired by designs from the Church of the First Light.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Local Libations
Description: An illustrated manual of how to take the perfect sip of piping hot punch. Use to learn the /gridaniansip, /uldahnsip, /lominsansip, /gridaniangulp, /uldahngulp, and /lominsangulp emotes.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - The Ceremony of Tea
Description: An illustrated manual with detailed instructions for enjoying a cup of warm green tea. Use to learn the /drinkgreentea and /savortea emotes.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Penning for Posterity
Description: An illustrated manual detailing the precise wrist motions required to take notes in style. Use to learn the /pen emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Anticipating Exertion
Description: An illustrated manual detailing a swift warm-up motion suitable for the moments immediately before a duel or particularly vigorous dance. Use to learn the /limber up emote.

Name: Modern Aesthetics - Hairscape M
Description:
The realm's premier publication on beauty and fashion, this otherworldly edition of Modern Aesthetics covers, in detail, techniques for molding one's coiffure into gravity-defying locks reminiscent of Omega-M. May you greet the world in style.

Use to unlock a new hairstyle at the aesthetician.

Name: Modern Aesthetics - Hairscape F
Description:
The realm's premier publication on beauty and fashion, this otherworldly edition of Modern Aesthetics covers, in detail, techniques for styling a gravity-defying ponytail reminiscent of Omega-F. May you greet the world in style.

Use to unlock a new hairstyle at the aesthetician.

Name: Modern Aesthetics - Simple and Clean
Description:
The realm's premier publication on beauty and fashion, this specific copy of Modern Aesthetics covers, in detail, techniques for achieving an eminently unfussy face-framing coiffure.

Use to unlock a new hairstyle at the aesthetician.

Name: Interstellar Dhalmel Whistle
Description: Augmented with advanced technology, this whistle produces an encoded sound that summons your interstellar dhalmel.

Name: Wings of Death
Description: Manifest your wings of death and soar the skies with an aura of impending doom.

Name: Ambulario
Description: This automaton designed in the likeness of the Impresario stands ready to bear you forth in the delightfully fiendish spirit of All Saints' Wake.

Name: Shagcoat Cat Whistle
Description: When blown, this whistle emits a warm and fuzzy tone that calls your shagcoat cat to your side.

Name: Yan Horn
Description: Summon forth your yan, a sheep spirit whose disarmingly adorable appearance belies its tremendous might.

Name: Vurgar the Loyal Horn
Description: A curved horn that, when blown, emits a stony note that summons forth Vurgar the Loyal.

Name: Forgiven Mimicry Resonator
Description: A metal tuning fork that, when struck, emits a tone both derivative and flattering that calls forth your forgiven mimicry.

Name: Chandelier of First Light
Description: This chandelier once graced the ceiling at the Church of the First Light as a furnishing. Now it can grace your feet as your ride.

Name: Seikret Horn
Description: This horn of bone produces a dauntless sound that calls your dependable Seikret to your side.

Name: Felyne Support Team Cart Horn
Description: This horn of bone produces a frantic tone that brings a Felyne support team cart careening to your rescue.

Name: The Faces We Wear - Bold-rimmed Glasses

Name: The Faces We Wear - Mythril-edged Eyepatch (Left)
Description: An illustrated periodical on fashionable facial accessories, this particular issue contains a cover story on decoratively adorned eyepatches of varying colors. Use to unlock the mythril-edged eyepatch (left) facewear.

Name: The Faces We Wear - Mythril-edged Eyepatch (Right)

Name: The Faces We Wear - Ornamented Leather Eyepatch (Left)

Name: The Faces We Wear - Tactical Goggles

Name: The Faces We Wear - Shaded Visor

Name: Blue Pixie Parasol
Description: Protects the bearer from rain and sun, but not from pixie mischief. Use to acquire a blue pixie parasol.

Name: Torch
Description: Ideal for adventurers who like their light sources accompanied by the scent of burning pine sap. Use to acquire a torch.

Name: Waxing Arcanite
Description: An even stranger ore warped by the abundant aether permeating the Occult Crescent.

Name: Ut'ohmu Siderite
Description: A fragment of rare meteorite found in the lush forests of Yak T'el.

Name: Rroneek Glue
Description: Derived from rroneek hide, this thick glue is prepared using time-honored Hhetsarro techniques.

Name: Synthetic Dark Matter Alpha
Description: This artificial psychosensitive compound is both highly pure and highly unstable, rendering it useless for all but a handful of applications.

Description: This artificial psychosensitive compound is both highly pure and highly unstable, rendering it useless for all but a handful of applications.

Description: This artificial psychosensitive compound is both highly pure and highly unstable, rendering it useless for all but a handful of applications.

Phials can be traded for special items.

Name: Magicked Prism (Moai Head)
Description: This peculiar contraption creates illusions by weaving together myriad shades of light. Bestows the user with a solemn stony visage.

Name: Valentione Round Table
Description: A round, cloth-draped table much like those used in the ptisserie.

Name: Rolanberry Valentione Cake
Description:
A towering spectacle of Valentione confectionery garnished with rolanberries aplenty.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Determination Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  VIT Bonus: +5% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Weeping Cherry Tree

Name: Hunter's Camp Chair
Description:
A foldable seat employed by many a hunter in the field, and only in the field.

Outdoor use only.

Name: Indoor Hunter's Grill
Description:
A simple grill used by particularly ravenous hunters who crave BBQ more than they fear suffocation by meat smoke in ill-ventilated lodges.

Up to twenty may be placed in a single estate.

Name: Hunter's Lodge Chair
Description: A foldable seat employed by many a hunter at home, where its camp-specific cousin simply will not do.

Name: Phaenna Exploration Token
Description: A slip awarded in exchange for successful completion of high-difficulty missions on Phaenna, and exchangeable for rare incentive items prepared by the Cosmic Exploration Initiative. Fortunately not made of glass.

May sound like a generous creature, but don't expect any favors.

Use item to acquire the boon baboon minion.

Description:
Painted a rugged shade of green, this miniature machina is a scale replica of the full-size model deployed in military training exercises.

Use item to acquire the clockwork oppressor minion.

Name: Ja Tiika Leafkin
Description:
What lies beneath its glowing blue leaves is best left a mystery.

Use item to acquire the Ja Tiika leafkin minion.

Name: Wind-up Gulool Ja Ja
Description:
It watches your progress with great interest.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Gulool Ja Ja minion.

Name: Mini Yan
Description:
A sheep spirit whose child-pleasing form and diminutive size belie its might.

Use item to acquire the mini yan minion.

Name: Gimme Kitten
Description:
An ill-mannered winged feline fiend that wants everything.

Use item to acquire the gimme kitten minion.

Name: Micro Rover
Description:
Won't be moving mountains, but can handle pebbles with aplomb.

Use item to acquire the micro rover minion.
