Description:
An entity born of the fire-wielding familiar Triton. That's the red one.

Use item to acquire the Psamathe minion.

Name: Naiad
Description:
An entity born of the ice-wielding familiar Nereid. That's the purple one.

Use item to acquire the Naiad minion.

Name: Deimos
Description:
An entity born of the poison-wielding familiar Phobos. That's the green one.

Use item to acquire the Deimos minion.

Name: Tipping Tortoise
Description:
Would be a generous tipper if its coins were real.

Use item to acquire the tipping tortoise minion.

Name: Royal Hound
Description:
As loyal as it is royal.

Use item to acquire the royal hound minion.

Name: Skallic Uolosapa
Description:
A winsome bird with pure white feathers and a pink beak.

Use item to acquire the Skallic uolosapa minion.

Name: Warp Loader Identification Key
Description: A thin, rectangular piece of some unknown material. Placing it near your warp loader will magically bring the machine to life.

Name: Air-wheeler C9 Identification Key
Description: A thin, rectangular piece of what appears to be electrope. Placing it near your air-wheeler C9 will magically bring the vehicle to life.

Name: Ancient Airship Identification Key
Description: A thin, rectangular piece of what appears to be cermet. Placing it near your ancient airship will magically bring the vessel to life.

Name: Wings of the Knighthood
Description: Manifest your wings of the knighthood and soar the skies with an aura of chivalrous passion.

Name: Branchbearer Horn
Description: A curved horn that, when blown, emits a verdant tone that brings a branchbearer gliding to your side.

Name: Demon Haul Horn
Description: When blown, this horn of bone emits a ghastly sound that manifests your demon haul.

Name: Petalodus Whistle
Description: This tiny flute emits a friendly tone that calls your petalodus stampeding to your side.

Name: His Royal Headness on Parade Whistle
Description: When blown, this whistle emits a heady tone that brings His Royal Headness on Parade shuffling to your side.

Name: Queen's Knight Barding
Description: A suit of chocobo armor designed in the image of a dedicated servant to her sovereign.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Fashion Forward
Description: An illustrated manual detailing proper methods of flaunting one's favorite fashions at every angle with a delightful pirouette. Use to learn the /twirl emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Feigning Fainting
Description: An illustrated manual of a weakened stance meant to incite pity, or potentially triumph, in the beholder. Use to learn the /dazed emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Bearing Insult
Description: An illustrated manual of how to effectively demonstrate disapproval of offensive comments without resorting to unbridled violencewhich any lady knows is always the second resort, never the first. Use to learn the /rage emote.

Name: Modern Aesthetics - The Warden
Description:
The realm's premier publication on beauty and fashion, this legendary edition of Modern Aesthetics covers, in detail, the cascading coiffure required to emulate the goddess Azeyma Herself.

Use to unlock a new hairstyle at the aesthetician.

Name: Modern Aesthetics - Fulsome Forelocks
Description:
The realm's premier publication on beauty and fashion, this specific copy of Modern Aesthetics covers, in detail, techniques for concealing one's visage with a luscious curtain of locks that fall past the eyes.

Use to unlock a new hairstyle at the aesthetician.

Name: Cabinkeep Permit
Description:
A king among permits, and lord of the shallows beneath the For'ard Cabins.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 3 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Muttering Matamata
Description:
A king among pleated matamata, and lord of the wetlands of Bopo'uihih.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Riverlong Candiru
Description:
A king among candirus, and lord of the currents of Miyakabek'zu.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Description:
A king among sailfins, and lord of the waters of the Iq Br'aax reservoir.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Awaksbane Apoda
Description:
A king among apoda, and lord of the depths of Yak Awak Tsoly.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Ttokatoa
Description:
A king among Turali paddlefish, and lord of the expanse of Lake Toari.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 4 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Thunderous Flounder
Description:
A king among crackling flounder, and lord of the depths of the crackling canyons.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Harlequin Queen
Description:
A queen among harlequin lancers, and ruler of the waters of the Knowable.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Big Bang Ticket (Sinus Ardorum)
Description: The sight of it alone enough to make a Loporrit hop with excitement, this ticket can be traded with Orbitingway for the chance to win valuable prizes.

Name: Big Bang Ticket (Phaenna)
Description: The sight of it alone enough to make a Loporrit hop with excitement, this ticket can be traded with Orbitingway for the chance to win valuable prizes.

Name: Fortune Carrot
Description:
There are bunnies in your future...

Only available for use on the Occult Crescent.

Name: Herringbone Interior Wall
Description: An interior wall perfect for those who can't decide which diagonal they prefer.

Name: Teal Carpet
Description: Durable-yet-fuzzy loop carpet in a rich blue-green.

Name: Fluorescent Tube Chandelier
Description: Elegant meets mundane in this tasteful ceiling decoration that emits wholly practical light.

Name: East End Tree
Description: This specimen transplanted from a disputed forest lends a touch of ennui to any lawn.

Name: Gardener's Gate
Description: Four out of five gardeners agree that this gate is, in design and practicality, perfect for any garden. (The fifth gardener was gardening during the vote.)

Name: Hewn Stone Circle
Description: Rocks carefully placed for purposes of aesthetics, social gatherings, or potentially arcane rituals.

Name: Hedge-trimmed Flower Bed
Description: A circular hedge tenderly blossoming and primly kept.

Name: Chocobo Chick Fountain
Description: Darling yellow birds float whimsically in this tiered fountain, providing decoration for the garden and succor for the soul.

Name: Occult Epitaph
Description: A replica of a sizable stone engraved with esoteric carvings found on the Occult Crescent.

Name: No-entry Door Partition
Description: If there was any doubt as to whether or not you can enter this false entryway, the answer is no.

Name: Hingan Dresser
Description: A wooden dresser designed in the Far Eastern style.

Name: Hingan Event Partition
Description: A partition of Far Eastern design traditionally used for festivities.

Name: Decorative Hingan Window
Description: A window fit for alcoves typically seen in traditional Far Eastern homes.

Name: Simple Hingan Pillar
Description: A decorative pillar fit for alcoves typically seen in traditional Far Eastern homes.

Name: Hingan Wall Shelf
Description: Simple planks fit for alcoves typically seen in traditional Far Eastern homes.

Name: Hingan Wall Cabinet

Name: Hingan Floor Cabinet
Description: Floor storage fit for alcoves typically seen in traditional Far Eastern homes.

Name: Wooden Frame Partition

Name: Vault Rib
Description: A sloping arch towards the ceiling guaranteed to impress the architecturally inclined.

Name: Lattice-windowed Cabinet
Description: For when you desire an obstructed view of the contents of your cupboard.

Name: Dark Knight Display Crystal

Name: Leg of Prosciutto
Description:
Salted pork that has been cured and aged to perfection. Guaranteed to impress!

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Critical Hit Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  VIT Bonus: +5% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Round Stepping Star
Description: For those who require adequate ankle lighting, look no further than this circular floor fixture.

Name: Recollection Sword Stand
Description:
The greatsword of a mighty knight who gave all in fealty to her queen.

One per estate only.

Name: Authentic Copy of Seekers of Eternity
Description: A masterfully rendered oil depiction of the disparate stances of allies and enemies alike, swirling together in multitudinous color.

Name: Blank Minimalist Partition
Description: A simple partition that may yet be freed from its simplicity by adornments.

Name: Minimalist Partition Door
Description: A simple partition affixed with a single door. Just one.

Name: Drafting Table
Description: A slanted desk suited for drawing up engineering designs.

Name: Tiika Selvaas
Description:
A Turali sandwich of lightly roasted meat and vegetables topped with savory olives.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Direct Hit Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  VIT Bonus: +5% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Up to twenty may be placed in a single estate.

Name: Crescent Trophy

Name: Occult Table

Name: Occult Chair

Name: Occult Tablets

Name: Knowledge Crystal Replica

Name: Occult Crescent Map
Description: This map is believed to have been inked by a navigator whose vessel made landfall on the isle in years past.

Name: Knight Core
Description: The glowing power source of Zelenia, loyal knight reimagined into formidable foe.

Description: Crafted with the finest lace gil can buy, this ornate parasol was designed for those fashionable frill-seekers who wish to accessorize in more subdued shades. Use to acquire a black embroidered parasol.

Name: The Faces We Wear - Metallic Eyepatch (Right)
Description: An illustrated periodical on fashionable facial accessories, this particular issue contains a cover story on metallic eyepatches of varying colors. Use to unlock the metallic eyepatch (right) facewear.

Name: Outsized Crystal Glass
Description: A stunningly clear and enormous cut of glass.

Name: Cosmochair
Description: An interstellar travel-ready seat with a futuristicyet still appropriately leporinedesign.

Name: Cosmotable
Description: This furnishing is designed to minimize the possibility of spills in low-gravity environments. Unfortunately, technology capable of compensating entirely for Loporrit error remains far in the future.

Name: Cosmolamp
Description: An energy-efficient lighting appliance with a design reminiscent of a solar system.

Name: Stellar Lamppost
Description: Though this piece of illuminating infrastructure has been specially designed to function in the icy vacuum of space, it is still not rated for licking.

Name: Esoteric Gold Piece
Description: This coin dating back to the Fifth Astral Era appears to have been miscast, for the design stamped upon its face is far from standard. Its uncanny tendency to enrapture those who gaze upon it should make it easy enough to sell at any price.

Name: Chemist's Soul Shard
Description:
Crystallized knowledge of a phantom job. Use to unlock Chemist.

Can only be used on the Occult Crescent.

Name: Thief's Soul Shard
Description:
Crystallized knowledge of a phantom job. Use to unlock Thief.

Can only be used on the Occult Crescent.

Name: Cosmic Prototype Coffer
Description:
A tool chest containing a cosmic prototype.

Required level: 10. IL: 10. Primary tool type determined by current class at time of opening. Cannot be opened in instanced areas such as dungeons, PvP areas, or raids.

Name: Irregular Tomestone of Aphorism
Description:
One of only a few in existence, this Allagan tomestone contains sentiments so concisely expressed they are scarcely expressed at all.

Can be exchanged with itinerant moogles for certain items.

Name: Fulgurpine Log
Description: A rough-cut log of fulgurpine timber. Caution is advised when handling due to the potent lightning energy suffusing its fibers.

Name: Dense Aluminum Ore
Description: A decent-sized piece of rock containing traces of highly dense aluminum.

Name: Rose Garnet Ore
Description: An uncut, unpolished stone containing what appears to be rose garnet.

Name: Carnauba Leaf
Description: A palm frond containing a naturally occurring wax used by all manner of artisans.

Name: Urqopacha Flax
Description: Highly sought fibers sourced from a mere handful of locations in Urqopacha.

Name: Windspath Water
Description: Filled to the brim with pleasantly smooth, almost entirely mineral-free water.

Name: Fulgurpine Lumber
Description: Processed fulgurpine lumber, treated with a special coating to seal in the excess lightning energy.

Name: Double Duraluminum Ingot
Description: An ingot of smeltedand doubly durableduraluminum.

Name: Rose Garnet
Description: A light-purple jewel.

Name: Mastodon Leather
Description: A large piece of cured mastodon skin.

Name: Urqopacha Linen
Description: Several yalms of quality Urqopacha linen dyed a delicate pink.

Name: Grade 4 Gemsap of Strength
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this Turali gemsap will, similarly to Eorzean dissolvents, dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to strength, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Grade 4 Gemsap of Dexterity
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this Turali gemsap will, similarly to Eorzean dissolvents, dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to dexterity, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Grade 4 Gemsap of Vitality
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this Turali gemsap will, similarly to Eorzean dissolvents, dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to vitality, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Grade 4 Gemsap of Intelligence
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this Turali gemsap will, similarly to Eorzean dissolvents, dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to intelligence, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Grade 4 Gemsap of Mind
Description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this Turali gemsap will, similarly to Eorzean dissolvents, dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to mind, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

Name: Insulating Varnish
Description: This specialized sealant is applied to various materials to contain excess lightning energy.

Name: Double Duracoat
Description: When applied to metals, this concoction forms a layer onto which dyes readily adhere.

Name: Everkeep Resin
Description: An artificial resin manufactured in Everkeep.

Name: Mastodon Pelt
Description: The rough pelt of a mastodon, a species that has endured unchanged since the days of yore.

Name: Turali Pigment
Description: This vibrant red powder is used to dye a range of traditional Turali textiles.

Name: Yollal Extract
Description: A concentrated liquid sourced from hardy Turali plants.

Name: Flint Corn
Description: The flint-like kernels of this rare purple corn burst open when heated.

Name: Turali Plum
Description: A somewhat bitter fruit native to the shores of Tural.

Name: Rroneek Milk
Description: As rroneek only produce small quantities of milk, this creamy, nourishing liquid is highly prized.

Name: Rock-fist Popoto
Description: A popoto variety that makes up for its lack of moisture with a glutinous abundance of starch.

Name: Quahog
Description: A large bivalve mollusk with a strong, sturdy shell.

Name: Grade 4 Gemdraught of Strength
Description:
This diluted brew temporarily increases strength for twice the duration of similar potions.

Duration: 30s

Name: Grade 4 Gemdraught of Dexterity
Description:
This diluted brew temporarily increases dexterity for twice the duration of similar potions.

Duration: 30s

Name: Grade 4 Gemdraught of Vitality
Description:
This diluted brew temporarily increases vitality for twice the duration of similar potions.

Duration: 30s

Name: Grade 4 Gemdraught of Intelligence
Description:
This diluted brew temporarily increases intelligence for twice the duration of similar potions.

Duration: 30s

Name: Grade 4 Gemdraught of Mind
Description:
This diluted brew temporarily increases mind for twice the duration of similar potions.

Duration: 30s

Name: Nachos
Description:
A small mountain of thin corn tortillas fried to perfection and topped with a tangy tomato sauce. 

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Caramel Popcorn
Description:
A moreish corn treat slathered in rich caramel sauce. Made by heating corn kernels until they expand, young and old delight in the pop and crackle made by the blooming kernels.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Prune Ponzecake
Description:
A fragrant ponzecake studded with silky soft prunes.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Prune-packed Fruitcake
Description:
Dried plums steeped in liquor are stirred into the batter to create this wonderfully rich, fruit-laden cake.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Rroneek au Gratin
Description:
Garlic and onion gently simmered in rroneek milk elevate this humble popoto dish to newly flavorful heights.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Popoto Potage
Description:
A thick, creamy soup made with fresh rroneek milk and plenty of popotoes.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Rock-fisted Popoto Stew
Description:
Based on a traditional Alexandrian recipe that does not call for the addition of any oglops, despite what some may have pondered.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Rock-fisted Popoto Salad
Description:
A creamy salad packed with mashed rock-fist popotoes and crunchy diced carrots.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Clam Cake
Description:
Tender strips of quahog baked into a delicate savory cake.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Quahog Chowder
Description:
An indulgently creamy soup brimming with succulent clams.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Runaway Totem
Description: A small idol of the Doomtrain. It was likely crafted to commemorate the locomotive's inaugural journey.

Name: Heavy Holohelm
Description:
When activated, this electrope-powered device from the Arcadion projects a holographic helmet.

Two helms can be traded for special headgear.

Name: Heavy Holoarmor
Description:
When activated, this electrope-powered device from the Arcadion projects a holographic suit of armor.

Four suits can be traded for special body gear.

Name: Heavy Hologauntlets
Description:
When activated, this electrope-powered device from the Arcadion projects a holographic pair of gauntlets.

Two pairs can be traded for special arm gear.

Name: Heavy Holotrousers
Description:
When activated, this electrope-powered device from the Arcadion projects a holographic pair of trousers.

Four pairs can be traded for special leg gear.

Name: Heavy Hologreaves
Description:
When activated, this electrope-powered device from the Arcadion projects a holographic pair of greaves.

Two pairs can be traded for special foot gear.

Name: Heavy Holoring
Description:
When activated, this electrope-powered device from the Arcadion projects a holographic ring.

One ring can be traded for a special accessory.

Name: Heavy Holoblade
Description: When activated, this electrope-powered device from the Arcadion projects a holographic blade.

Name: Universal Tomestone 3.0
Description: Having created a successful second iteration of the universal tomestone, researchers of yore continued to tweak and tinker, ultimately producing a data storage medium of such needless complexity that even they were left baffled by its functionality.

Name: Thundersteeped Solvent
Description: A highly charged chemical mixture synthesized with advanced Everkeep technology. Applying it to bygone brass weapons enables full optimization of the gear's offensive properties.

Name: Thundersteeped Twine
Description: A highly charged thread synthesized with advanced Everkeep technology. Applying it to bygone brass vestments enables full optimization of the gear's defensive properties.

Name: Thundersteeping Glaze
Description: A highly charged coating synthesized with advanced Everkeep technology. Applying it to bygone brass accessories enables full optimization of the gear's defensive properties.

Name: AAC Illustrated: HW Edition I
Description:
A publication covering the matches and fighters of the heavyweight tier.

Copies of the same AAC Illustrated edition can be traded for special gear.

Description:
Should you require more motivation in your horticultural endeavors, simply picture all the delightfully fragrant mugs of tea you will be enjoying once these seeds have bloomed. 

For use in planters.

Description: A hunk of burnished metal torn from the Doomtrain.

Description:
A rare () card used in the game Triple Triad.
Card No. 439

Name: Doomtrain Card
Description:
An epic () card used in the game Triple Triad.
Card No. 440

Description:
A legendary () card used in the game Triple Triad.
Card No. 441

Name: Purse of Riches
Description:
A king among blue purses, and lord of the waters of High Tide Harbor.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Punutiy Pain
Description:
A king among Pelubanes, and lord of the waters of Peaks Poga.

[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Shuckfin Dace
Description:
A king among corn dace, and lord of the currents of Ku'uxage.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Shin Snuffler
Description:
A king among Ankledeep catfish, and lord of the shallows of Ankledeep.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

Name: Moxutural Greatgar
Description:
A king among Moxutural gars, and lord of the depths of Cenote Moxutural.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Heirloom Goldgrouper
Description:
A king among goldgroupers, and lord of the waters of the Alexandrian ruins.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Datnioides Aeroplanos
Description:
A king among datnioides, and lord of the waters of leynode aero.

[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

Name: Esperance Carp
Description:
A king among ultimoat carp, and lord of the waters of Proto Alexandria.

[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

Name: Maxims of Mahjong - Erenville
Description: A record of aphorisms shared while witness to triumphant victories and crushing defeats at the game table. Use to unlock voiced lines from Erenville during Doman mahjong.

Name: Maxims of Mahjong - Metem
Description: A record of aphorisms shared while witness to triumphant victories and crushing defeats at the game table. Use to unlock voiced lines from Metem during Doman mahjong.

Name: Gallant Shepherd
Description:
Courageous and loyal, it does credit to caninekind.

Use item to acquire the gallant shepherd minion.

Name: La Noscean Shorthair
Description:
Will hunt rodents for board and lodging.

Use item to acquire the La Noscean shorthair minion.

Name: Mystic Knight's Soul Shard
Description:
Crystallized knowledge of a phantom job. Use to unlock Mystic Knight.

Can only be used on the Occult Crescent.

Name: Gladiator's Soul Shard
Description:
Crystallized knowledge of a phantom job. Use to unlock Gladiator.

Can only be used on the Occult Crescent.

Name: Dancer's Soul Shard
Description:
Crystallized knowledge of a phantom job. Use to unlock Dancer.

Can only be used on the Occult Crescent.

Name: Valentione Chair
Description: An elegant chair matching the design of those used in the ptisserie.

Name: Valentione Rug
Description: A plush pink rug similar to those found in the ptisserie.

Name: Scattered Archon Eggs
Description: A colorful smattering of prophetic eggs strewn about in a haphazard fashion.

Name: Filled Archon Egg Basket
Description: A decorative Hatching-tide basket replete with a clutch of vibrant eggs.

Name: Archon Egg Basket
Description: A decorative Hatching-tide basket bereft of its eggy cargo.

Name: Doom-engine Levinbox
Description:
Modeled after the motive apparatus of a monstrous locomotive.

One per estate only.

Name: Housing Design Award MMXXV Plaque
Description: Awarded in recognition of outstanding contributions to the Furnishing Design Contest 2025.

Name: Everkeep Mixing Booth
Description: A futuristic array of audio equipment bristling with buttons and dials that simply demand to be fiddled with.

Name: Unfriendly Yan Neon Wall Light
Description: A vivid wall light designed in the likeness of an otherworldlyand if its stern countenance is any indication, highly belligerentsheep spirit.

Name: Steaming Stew Bowl
Description:
Piping hot stew served in a rustic wooden bowl.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Tenacity Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  VIT Bonus: +5% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Sampler Board
Description:
A tasteful arrangement of appetizers, perfect for a sophisticated soire or humble family gathering.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Spell Speed Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  VIT Bonus: +5% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Peeling Wallpaper Sticker
Description: Give your abode an air of studied neglect, without investing the time required for such cosmetic damage to occur naturally.

Name: Fortune-teller's Table
Description: A modest round table laden with all the fortune-telling accoutrements one could need.

Name: Adventurer's Effects
Description: Ideal for storing oddments accumulated over the course of countless adventures.

Name: Lakeland Planter
Description: An ornate wooden barrel sporting a lilac-leaved tree reminiscent of Lakeland foliage.

Name: Eulmore Planter
Description: This gilded potted plant embodies Eulmore's unseemly decadence.

Name: Il Mheg Planter
Description: Features a slender tree snaking its way out of a miniature Lyhe Ghiah.

Name: Minishroom Lamp
Description: This organic light source features a cluster of faintly glowing mushrooms sprouting from a mossy globe.

Name: Authentic Copy of Into the Mist
Description: A masterfully rendered oil depiction of assembled Arcadion fighters, their stern gazes exuding unwavering determination.

Name: Valentione's Day MMXXV Advertisement
Description: A hand-painted and slightly fragrant notice advertising the Valentione's Day of a year gone by.

Name: Little Ladies' Day MMXXV Advertisement
Description: A hand-painted notice advertising a Little Ladies' Day gone by, which has been known to bring on bouts of swooning. Viewer discretion is advised.

Name: Tabletop Little Ladies' Day MMXXV Advertisement
Description: A conveniently sized notice, ideal for lending a festive air to household surfaces. Advertising a Little Ladies' Day gone by, it has been known to bring on bouts of swooning. Viewer discretion is advised.

Name: Little Ladies' Day MMXVIII Advertisement
Description: A hand-painted notice advertising a Little Ladies' Day gone by, which has been known to turn bystanders into passionate fans of the Songbirds. Viewer discretion is advised.

Name: Hatching-tide MMXXV Advertisement
Description: A hand-painted notice advertising the eggsquisite craftsmanship of a Hatching-tide past.

Name: Tabletop Hatching-tide MMXXV Advertisement
Description: A conveniently sized notice, ideal for lending a festive air to household surfaces. Advertising a Hatching-tide gone by, the eggsquisite craftsmanship of the occasion is on full display.

Name: Hatching-tide MMXVI Advertisement
Description: A hand-painted notice advertising the festivities of a Hatching-tide past, featuring the event organizers and an adorable interloper.

Name: Authentic Starlight Celebration MMXXIII Advertisement
Description: An authentic reprint of a festive hand-painted notice advertising the Starlight Celebration of a year gone by.

Name: Lauded Framer's Kit
Description:
Tools for enhancing a portrait. Use to unlock embellishments fit for the recipient of a special reward.
[Includes: Background/Frame/Accent]

Name: Certificate of Collaboration
Description: A small, square slip of parchment stamped with the Ul'dahn royal seneschal's seal proving your aid in the promotion of the Songbirds.

Name: Humble Overalls
Description: Cannot equip gear to legs.

Name: G-Warrior MGSD
Description:
The MGSD part of its name supposedly stands for Master Garlond Superior Design, or something along those lines.

Use item to acquire the G-Warrior MGSD minion.

Name: Grooving Green
Description:
Can you keep up with the rhythm?

Use item to acquire the Grooving Green minion.

Name: Mistic Condor
Description:
Feed it only perfectly cooked flesh, lest you incur its displeasure.

Use item to acquire the Mistic condor minion.

Name: Modern Aesthetics - Realms-ruffled
Description:
The realm's premier publication on beauty and fashion, this specific copy of Modern Aesthetics covers, in detail, techniques for an artfully accessorized style that appears tousled by otherworldly winds.

Use to unlock a new hairstyle at the aesthetician.

Name: Modern Aesthetics - Tail of the Teller
Description:
The realm's premier publication on beauty and fashion, this specific copy of Modern Aesthetics covers, in detail, techniques for a ponytail that suggests a great destiny awaits the wearer, in spite of its simplicity.

Use to unlock a new hairstyle at the aesthetician.

Name: Modern Aesthetics - Fit for a Princess
Description:
The realm's premier publication on beauty and fashion, this specific copy of Modern Aesthetics covers, in detail, techniques for pinning your hair in a princess-perfect style. 

Use to unlock a new hairstyle at the aesthetician.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Erudite Idleness
Description: An illustrated manual on how to appear scholarlyrather than simply shywhen struggling to socialize at soires. Use to learn the /carrybook emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Sophisticated Saunter
Description: An illustrated manual on how to draw the room's attention to one's perfectly tailored ensemble. Use to learn the /runwaywalk emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Improper Praise (Cheer Rhythm: Red)
Description: An installment in a long-running series of manuals on how to express admiration in a manner unbefitting one of high birth. Perhaps prudently, later editions do not specify the total number of volumes in the series. Use to learn the /cheerrhythmred emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Improper Praise (Cheer Light: Yellow)
Description: An installment in a long-running series of manuals on how to express admiration in a manner unbefitting one of high birth. Perhaps prudently, later editions do not specify the total number of volumes in the series. Use to learn the /cheerlightyellow emote.

Name: Authentic Oriental New Year's Meal
Description:
A colorful assortment of auspiciousand undeniably authenticappetizers, traditionally eaten in the Far East during the Heavensturn holiday.

Cannot be retrieved once used.
Can be used up to 10 times.

Meal benefits when used:
  Spell Speed Bonus: +4% (Max 10)
  VIT Bonus: +5% (Max 12)
  Gear Durability Bonus: +3
  EXP Bonus: +3%
  Duration: 30m
  (Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

Name: Authentic Springtide Fan Stand
Description: A verdantly decorated pair of authentic folding fans displayed at Heavensturn to beckon winds of fair fortune in the seasons to come.

Name: Occult Compass
Description: A curious compass perhaps once used by an isle-bound recluse, perhaps not.

Name: Occult Pyramicula
Description: A perplexing pyramidal ornament of the like appreciated by mysterious recluses residing on distant isles.

Name: Mhachi Lamppost
Description: This ornate, somewhat somber lamppost appears to be of ancient Mhachi design.

Name: Wanyudo Horn
Description: When blown, this horn of bone produces an eerie sound that calls forth your nightmarish wanyudo.

Name: Dynamite Whistle
Description: This whistle emits an explosive tone that calls your dynamite to your side.

Name: Lowrider T1RANT Identification Key
Description: A thin, rectangular piece of what appears to be electrope. Placing it near your Lowrider T1RANT will magically bring the vehicle to life.

Name: Uolon Horn
Description: When blown, this mossy horn emits a lush note that brings your uolon lumbering to your side.

Name: Wings of Mist
Description: Manifest your wings of mist and soar the skies with an aura of unstoppable resolve.

Name: Turali Snowman Bell
Description: When rung, this mysterious bell produces a playful sound that summons your Turali snowman.

Name: Runaway Barding
Description: A suit of chocobo armor designed to resemble the Doomtrain.

Name: The Faces We Wear - Blindfold Eyepatch (Left)
Description: An illustrated periodical on fashionable facial accessories, this particular issue contains a cover story on partially vision-obscuring eyepatches of varying colors. Use to unlock the blindfold eyepatch (left) facewear.

Name: The Faces We Wear - Blindfold Eyepatch (Right)
Description: An illustrated periodical on fashionable facial accessories, this particular issue contains a cover story on partially vision-obscuring eyepatches of varying colors. Use to unlock the blindfold eyepatch (right) facewear.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Concentrated Emotions
Description: An illustrated manual detailing how to channel one's emotions into a display of radiant strength. Use to learn the /divinearm emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Joy beyond Joy
Description: An illustrated manual detailing how to channel one's emotions into a display of radiant strength. Use to learn the /divinedisk emote.

Name: Ballroom Etiquette - Light beyond Light
Description: An illustrated manual detailing how to channel one's emotions into a display of radiant strength. Use to learn the /divinetiara emote.
